INSERT INTO `announcements_announcement` VALUES (1641,'The Great Debaters','the-great-debaters','<p>This is a debate style event that serves to foster open lines of communication while challenging students to focus on issues of concern. Two teams, composed of four individuals each, will either defend or argue on and assigned position. Winners will be selected by faculty and staff judges.\nRoom: 221 Garden Key\nStudent Union (STUN), 6:00 pm,\nThursday, February 7th</p>','2013-02-04','2013-03-03',' ','Kenny Parker','786-413-6621','mscasd@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1642,'Def Poetry Jam','def-poetry-jam','<p>A culmination of spoken word, song, art, etc. that displays the the history of African people through these different mediums. The entire production is a journey through time connecting themnes of the past to issues in the present and solutions for the future.\nRoom: 316 Cape Florida Ballroom\nStudent Union (STUN),8:00 pm\nWednesday, February 27th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Danielle Matthew','954-479-9784','csaucfpresident@gmail.com','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1643,'An Evening With Judy Smith','an-evening-with-judy-smith','<p>Keynote Speaker: Crisis Management &amp; Inspiration of the ABC hit TV show Scandal\nRoom: Pegasus Ballroom\nStudent Union (SU) Pegasus Ballroom, 6:00 pm\nWednesday, February 27th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Melissa Westbrook',' ','mwestbrook5757@knights.ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1644,'Uniting As One','uniting-as-one','<p>Step show and celebration of greek life\nRoom: Leisure Pool Green\nRecreation &amp; Wellness Center (RWC), 12:00 pm\nWednesday, February 27th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Andrea Snead','407-82-2408','Andrea.Snead@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1645,'How To Become An Entrepreneur Series','how-to-become-an-entrepreneur-series','<p>Innovative? Creative? Looking to be an entrepreneur? Join us in our 4 part Entrepreneurship Series as we discuss and highlight the various aspects of being a successful and effective entrepreneur\nLibra Community Center, 5:30 pm\nTuesday, February 26th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Wayne Jackson','407-823-2716','Wayne.Jackson@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1646,'Shop Talk Series\"The Barber Shop\" And The Beauty Shop\"','shop-talk-seriesthe-barber-shop-and-the-beauty-shop','<p>Brother to Brother seminar where men discuss images of African American men in the media and how it impacts their overall health and self-esteem.</p>\n<p>Black Women and their Bodies-Imagery or Fantasy also exploring stereotypes and fighting the negative focus on black women in America.\nRoom: 223\nStudent Union (STUN),1:00 pm\nTuesday, February 26th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Lorri M. Key','407-823-2811','lorri.key@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1647,'Nappy Roots','nappy-roots','<p>This is an interactive forum discussing and promoting the historical importance of African and African American hair.\nRoom: Auditorium\nHarris Corp. Engineering Center (HEC),6:30 pm\nSaturday, February 16th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Olutosin Teniola','954-980-2733','tosint@knights.ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1648,'Movie Screening: The Peculiar Kind','movie-screening-the-peculiar-kind','<p>The Peculiar Kind is a documentary about the lives of queer women of color.\nRoom: Graduate Student Center\nFerrell Commons (FC), 6:00 pm\nMonday, February 18th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Nick Simons','813-777-1453','lgbtq@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1649,'Becoming Competitive For Graduate School','becoming-competitive-for-graduate-school','<p>The goal of this program is to provide students with information on some the services, resources and strategies that will make students more competitive for graduate school\nRoom: 121\nCareer Services Experiential Learning CSEL)\nBuilding 140 on Memory Mall\n32816-0165\n11:00 am\nTuesday, February 19th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Evelyn Lora-Santos','407-823-1725','evelyn.lora-santos@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1650,'John T. Washington Awards Luncheon And Black History Month Celebration','john-t-washington-awards-luncheon-and-black-history-month-celebration','<p>The annual John T. Washington luncheon honors his legacy by celebrating the involvement of citizens who participate in community and civic programs in the greater central Florida area. The award recognizes people who exemplify the same humanitarian and scholarly characteristics that were so vividly demonstrated by Washington.</p>\n<p>The program requests the honor of your presence at this year\'s luncheon. The luncheon will be held on Monday, February 25, 2013 in the UCF Student Union Cape Florida Ballroom (Room 316). We also invite you to support this worthy cause by purchasing a Sponsorship Package or Program Advertisement, or by making a donation. For more information or learn more about these opportunities please see <a href=\"http://aas.cah.ucf.edu/luncheon.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://aas.cah.ucf.edu/luncheon.php</a>\nKindly RSVP by Friday, February 15, 2013.\nTicket required\nRoom: 316 Cape Florida Ballroom\nStudent Union (STUN),12:00 pm\nMonday, February 25th</p>','2013-02-11','2013-03-10',' ','Anjella Warnshius','407-823-0026','aas@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1651,'Performance Appraisals (Per067)','performance-appraisals-per067','<p>Performance Appraisals 101(PER 067) is being held on Wednesday, March 06, 2013 from 9:00 a.m. - 11:30 a.m. in the OD&amp;T training room 3280 Progress Drive Orlando FL 32826. Prepare now for the annual performance appraisals due to Human Resources. As a supervisor your role is to coach, motivate and empower others to use their skills, expertise and ideas to produce results. To provide this direction, you will learn:\n1) Benefits &amp; multiple uses of appraisals\n2) UCF procedures for USPS and A&amp;P.\n3) How to make the process faster/easier.\n4) What and how to document.\n5) How to set SMART goals with your staff.\nThis workshop is limited to current supervisors of USPS and A&amp;P eligible staff. Register now for PER067 at myUCF\n<a href=\"https://my.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CLICK HERE to Register NOW!.</a></p>','2013-02-19','2013-03-04','http://events.ucf.edu/?calendar_id=72&upcoming=upcoming','OD &amp; Training Staff','407.823.0440','od&training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1652,'Barnga (Game Of Five Cards) Registration Div077','barnga-game-of-five-cards-registration-div077','<p>Tuesday, March 5th 2:30-4:30 PM in HR room 105 Barnga is a simulation activity that allows participants to explore and experience the challenges and communication barriers of life in a cross-cultural setting.</p>\n<p>Participants will:\n<em>Recognize the subtlety of cultural differences\n</em>Understand how cultural differences can create communication barriers\n*Discover and discuss ways to overcome communication barriers</p>\n<p>Alignment with Workplace Goals: \n<em>Communication breaks down when two parties bring different assumptions to their interaction\n</em>Awareness of the pitfalls of cross-cultural relationships prepares employees to recognize potential problems and communicate clearly with coworkers, suppliers, and clients of a different culture.</p>\n<p>A minimum of 15 participants is required to effectively run this training event. </p>\n<p>Date:  Wednesday, October 17, 2012, at 2:30 p.m. - 4:30 p.m.</p>\n<p>Facilitated by: Patty Farris, OD&amp; Training\nHuman Resources</p>','2013-02-19','2013-03-04','http://events.ucf.edu/?y=2013&amp;m=03&amp;d=05&amp;eventdatetime_id=11110','OD &amp; Training','407-823-0440','od&amp;training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1653,'First Aid (Lif014) Registration','first-aid-lif014-registration','<p>Date and Time: Monday March 14, 2013 from 1:00 pm - 4:00 pm Learn how to determine the signs, symptoms, and treatment of everything from sprains and fractures to bleeding, poisonings, and burns. Please dress comfortably to participate in practice exercises on the floor. Workshop requires a minimum of 6 participants and maximum of 20 participants. Facilitated by: Jose Vazquez Environmental Health and Safety Register Now for LIF014 myUCF </p>','2013-02-19','2013-03-04','http://events.ucf.edu/?y=2013&amp;m=03&amp;d=04&amp;eventdatetime_id=11950','OD &amp; Training','407-823-0440','od&amp;training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1654,'Ucf Center For Success Of Women Faculty Spring Book Club','ucf-center-for-success-of-women-faculty-spring-book-club','<p>The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks by Rebecca Skloot, ISBN: 978-1-4000-5218-9 Her name was Henrietta Lacks, but scientists know her as HeLa. She was a poor black tobacco farmer whose cells--taken without her knowledge in 1951--became one of the most important tools in medicine, vital for developing the polio vaccine, cloning, gene mapping, in vitro fertilization, and more. Henrietta\'s cells have been bought and sold by the billions, yet she remains virtually unknown, and her family can\'t afford health insurance. Soon to be made into an HBO movie by Oprah Winfrey and Alan Ball, this New York Times bestseller takes readers on an extraordinary journey, from the \"colored\" ward of Johns Hopkins Hospital in the 1950s to stark white laboratories with freezers filled with HeLa cells, from Henrietta\'s small, dying hometown of Clover, Virginia, to East Baltimore today, where her children and grandchildren live and struggle with the legacy of her cells. The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks tells a riveting story of the collision between ethics, race, and medicine; of scientific discovery and faith healing; and of a daughter consumed with questions about the mother she never knew. It\'s a story inextricably connected to the dark history of experimentation on African Americans, the birth of bioethics, and the legal battles over whether we control the stuff we\'re made of. All dates are Wednesdays January 23, 2013 - Chapter (Part One) Life 1-11 February 20, 2013 - Chapters (Part Two) Death 12-22 March 27, 2013 - Chapters (Part Three) Immortality 23-38</p>','2013-02-22','2013-04-21','http://womenfaculty.afia.ucf.edu/','Fran Ragsdale','407-823-4240','fran.ragsdale@ucf.edu','Center for Success of Women Faculty','Publish',1),(1655,'Ucf Celebrates Women\'s History Month','ucf-celebrates-womens-history-month','<p>UCF Celebrates Women\'s History Month!  For each day of March, the UCF Center for Success of Women Faculty will highlight one wonderful UCF woman who has helped shape our University\'s first 50 years.  Our awardees include staff, faculty and administrators.  Please check our website daily during March <a href=\"http://womenfaculty.afia.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://womenfaculty.afia.ucf.edu/</a>\nand please thank all these wonderful women when you see them around campus! </p>','2013-02-22','2013-04-21','http://womenfaculty.afia.ucf.edu/','Fran Ragsdale','407-823-4240','fran.ragsdale@ucf.edu','Center for Success of Women Faculty','Publish',1),(1656,'P M P Exam Preparation Courses This Spring','p-m-p-exam-preparation-courses-this-spring','<p>UCF Continuing Education, in partnership with Seminole State College, is launching two 10 week Project Management courses this spring. Seats are still available for the intensive 10- week Project Management Exam Preparation Certificate Program in both East Orlando on Tuesday evenings and in Cocoa on Thursday evenings starting the week of March 11. Tuition is $3,990 ($1,995 per course) which includes instruction, textbooks and all study materials. All programs are held weeknights from 5:30-9:30pm and exceed the PMP education requirement of 35 hours of PM education and passing rates for first time takers is over 90%. Payment plans are available and tuition reimbursement is accepted. Please visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/PM</a> for full course outlines and registration.</p>','2013-02-25','2013-03-03','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/pm','Sarah Faehnle','407-882-0237','Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1657,'Accepting Nominations For Usps Employee Of The Month! Deadline March 15th','accepting-nominations-for-usps-employee-of-the-month-deadline-march-15th','<p>Know someone who is an outstanding employee?\nWant to help them win $2,500?\nHave they been a UCF USPS employee for at least 2 years?\nIf yes, they may qualify! \nCLICK  to submit an electric nomination\nCLICK to fill out a hard copy nomination form\nFor more information, CLICK to visit our website\nDeadlines for the year are as follows:\nFor April: March 15th \nFor May: April 19th\nFor June: May 17th\nFor July: June 17th\nFor August: July 19th\nFor September: August 16th\nFor October: September 13th\nFor November: October 18th\nFor December: November 15th</p>','2013-02-26','2013-03-11','http://www.hr.ucf.edu/web/employeerecognition/EOM.shtml','OD&amp;Training Human Resources','(407) 823-0440','od&amp;training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1658,'Leadership Week Key Note Speaker-Joshua Fredenburg','leadership-week-key-note-speaker-joshua-fredenburg','<p>Joshua Fredenburg is a National Speaker, Author, Leadership/Relationship Expert, and Generation Y Television Commentator that speaks on current issues and is on a mission as a National Speaker to empower at least 1 BILLION LEADERS WORLDWIDE with effective leadership strategies that will enable them to make a positive impact in their community, nation, and world! For the past seven years, not only has Joshua appeared as a television guest on the Daily Buzz Morning Show, BET, the Wayne Brady Show, the KTLA Morning Show in Los Angeles, and many other familiar radio and television programs throughout the country, but he has also served as a dynamic Keynote Speaker in 40 different states for lectures, leadership conferences, retreats and trainings at high schools, colleges, and corporate events.</p>','2013-02-26','2013-03-04','http://www.ucfsld.com/LeadershipWeek/?id=keynote','Germayne Graham',' ','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Student Leadership Development','Publish',1),(1659,'Gre Review Course','gre-review-course','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the GRE with our GRE Review course. Our GRE review course is 24 hours in length, and will help prepare you for the Verbal and Mathematics sections of the GRE exam. The GRE review course will review strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review of the arithmetic, geometry, and algebra formulas and rules that are needed to answer the mathematics questions on the GRE. You will also apply and practice the material that you learn during in class exercises and practice problems.</p>','2013-02-28','2013-03-13','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1660,'Marketing, Branding & Ucf (Lif113) Registration','marketing-branding-ucf-lif113-registration','<p>Sponsored by University Marketing, we\'ll discuss UCF\'s \"brand,\" and give a primer in marketing and branding basics that will allow you to apply these concepts to your own department/program. This informational workshop is free to all employees of the University, and offers valuable information to help ensure that the image of your department matches the image of the University.\nFacilitated by Michelle Fuentes, University Marketing, this class will be held Thursday, March 14, 2:00pm-4:00pm in the OD &amp; Training Room. For more information, please review the website below.</p>','2013-02-28','2013-03-13','http://events.ucf.edu/?y=2013&amp;m=03&amp;d=11&amp;eventdatetime_id=3215','OD &amp; Training Team','407.823.0440','od&amp;training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1661,'Gmat Review Course','gmat-review-course','<p>UCF Test Prep has been providing GMAT review courses since 1998. With more than 13 years of experience,\nOur courses are designed to help you prepare for the three main parts on the GMAT: the Analytical Writing Assessment, the Quantitative section, and the Verbal section. Several sample tests are given in class to give students the opportunity to use newly learned strategies and to understand how to best budget their time. This class will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2013-03-02','2013-03-15','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1662,'Enhance Your H R Knowledge With The Essentials Of Human Resources Management','enhance-your-h-r-knowledge-with-the-essentials-of-human-resources-management','<p>Learning the basics of the HR field is now being offered in a convenient, self-paced, online format. Perfect for professionals and students alike, the Essentials of HR Management, offers a comprehensive overview of the human resources function. This open entry program allows participants to begin and end at any time. Participants will receive the official SHRM Essentials of HR Management books, online tools and will gain access to recorded online lectures. Designed to challenge attendees and provide the skills needed to confidently face today\'s complex HR situations and compliance issues within any organization, the program is ideal for those new to the field, managers interested in learning more efficient employee management skills, and business managers seeking to learn HR best practices.</p>','2013-03-04','2013-03-10','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/779/Shrm---Professional-Human-Resource-Essentials-Program/ ','Sarah Faehnle','407-882-0237','Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1663,'Become Licensed In Healthcare Risk Management','become-licensed-in-healthcare-risk-management','<p>Continuing Education offers an entirely ONLINE Health Care Risk Management Licensure Program.  This course is now offered with an open entry, online format, so participants can start at any time and complete the program at their own pace. \nThe 120 hour contact program is approved by the Agency for Health Care Administration and includes 60 hours of online self-paced lectures and 60 hours of homework, projects, and additional work as assigned.  Additional networking is also built in so that you can talk with other participants and ask questions of instructors.<br>\nFor more information on the eligibility requirements for the program, please contact the Agency for Health Care Administration (AHCA) at 850.487.2717.  For complete program outlines, registration and more, visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement</a>  </p>','2013-03-04','2013-03-10','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement','Erika Nagy','407-882-0241','Erika.Nagy@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1664,'Fiber Optics Certification Courses! Begin In April 2013','fiber-optics-certification-courses-begin-in-april-2013','<p>Become Fiber Optics Certified!  As the demand for Fiber Optics increases, so will the demand of qualified and trained professionals who are able to install, troubleshoot and maintain these state-of-the-art networks and technologies.  Register today to ensure your spot in this expanding market.  Certified Fiber Optics Technician Course CFOT is April 8-10, 2013, and registration is $700. Advanced Certified Fiber Optics Specialist in Testing and Maintenance Course CFOS/T is April 11-12, 2013, and registration is $675. Certified Fiber Optics Specialist in Outside Plant Cabling Course CFOS/O is April 15-16, 2013 and registration is $775. For more information call 407-882-0241 or email Erika.Nagy@ucf.edu  Visit us on the web at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics</a></p>','2013-03-04','2013-03-10','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics','Erika Nagy','407-882-0241','Erika.Nagy@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1665,'Performance Appraisals 101 (Per 067)','performance-appraisals-101-per-067','<p>Performance Appraisals 101(PER 067) is being held on Wednesday, April 03, 2013 from 9:00 a.m. - 11:30 a.m. in the OD&amp;T training room 3280 Progress Drive Orlando FL 32826. Prepare now for the annual performance appraisals due to Human Resources. As a supervisor your role is to coach, motivate and empower others to use their skills, expertise and ideas to produce results. To provide this direction, you will learn:\n1) Benefits &amp; multiple uses of appraisals\n2) UCF procedures for USPS and A&amp;P.\n3) How to make the process faster/easier.\n4) What and how to document.\n5) How to set SMART goals with your staff.\nThis workshop is limited to current supervisors of USPS and A&amp;P eligible staff. Register now for PER067 at myUCF\n<a href=\"https://my.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CLICK HERE to Register NOW!.</a></p>','2013-03-04','2013-04-03','http://events.ucf.edu/?calendar_id=72&upcoming=upcoming','OD&amp;Training Staff','407-823-0440','od&training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1666,'Access, Excel, Word, Powerpoint 2010 Courses','access-excel-word-powerpoint-2010-courses','<p>Continuing Education offers many of the latest desktop application courses to help you learn Microsoft Office 2010. You can learn the New Features of Office 2010, Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint and many more. Regular Prices for UCF Students, Staff and Alumni: Microsoft 2010 Access, PowerPoint, Excel, Word, Office 2010 New Features and HTML Courses: $149.00 each. To register with these discounted UCF prices or to inquire about additional IT Courses, please visit us online at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu</a> or contact sfaehnle@ucf.edu or 407-882-0237. </p>','2013-03-04','2013-03-10','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Programs/30/Computer-Training/  ','Sarah Faehnle','407-882-0237','Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1667,'Communication, Teambuilding, And The Myers-Briggs (Per061 Registration)','communication-teambuilding-and-the-myers-briggs-per061-registration','<p>This session will be held on Tuesday, March 19, 2013 from 1PM-5PM in HR room 105.  Are you irritated by a teammate who doesn\'t focus on the details but prefers to talk about the big picture? How about the workmate who plays it by ear instead of planning out each detail? You will take an online Myers-Briggs Type Indicator assessment, an indispensable tool for understanding your own strengths, preferred communication style, decision making preferences, and helping your work team function better. It will help you: <em>Better understand yourself, and appreciate your teammates who differ from you. </em>Develop ideas for using \"Type\" preferences to make your work life easier and more fun. Register for this effective and fun workshop (or better yet, bring your whole team). Facilitated by: Beth Scheitzach, OD &amp; Training Manager, Human Resources </p>','2013-03-05','2013-03-18','http://events.ucf.edu/?y=2013&amp;m=03&amp;d=19&amp;eventdatetime_id=11108','OD&amp;Training','407-823-0558','od&amp;training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1668,'Collective Bargaining Notice','collective-bargaining-notice','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the United Faculty of Florida will take place on Thursday, March 14, 2013, from 1:00 to 3:30 p.m. in CDL 161B.</p>','2013-03-07','2013-03-13','http://www.collectivebargaining.ucf.edu','Sherry Andrews','407-823-1550','sandrews@ucf.edu','Faculty Relations','Publish',1),(1669,'Ftce Gk Review Course','ftce-gk-review-course','<p>The FTCE General Knowledge Review program is designed to familiarize professionals with the various areas covered on the General Knowledge Certification Exam.  As a strategic step in becoming state certified in the field, this program is consistent with accomplishing this goal. Beyond providing test-taking strategies, several sample tests are timed during class sessions to give individuals the opportunity to use their strategies and to manage their time for successful completion of the upcoming assessment. </p>','2013-03-09','2013-04-08','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1670,'Sat Review Course','sat-review-course','<p>Our 20-hour SAT review course is designed to do more than just review question types and cover material that will be on the test. Students will also dissect questions to gain a perspective from the test-taker\'s point of view.  By doing so, they will learn the common pitfalls and traps to avoid.  Students will also take two simulated tests to ensure the practice of their techniques and to prepare the students for what they can expect on test day.  The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2013-03-10','2013-03-23','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1671,'Interviewer Certification (Per 006 Registration)','interviewer-certification-per-006-registration','<p>This workshop is being held on March 28, 2013 from 1PM-5PM in HR room 105.  It introduces the concept of behavioral interviewing, a highly effective technique for identifying the best candidates for every level of position in the University. The course also examines areas of possible discrimination concerns and provides a review of the USPS hiring process. Upon completion of the program, participants earn the designation of \"certified interviewers,\" a requirement for those signing employment paperwork. To register for this class, go to the Training Section of the HR Website and click on the Training Calendar or call the HR Training Section at 407-823-0440. </p>','2013-03-14','2013-03-27','http://events.ucf.edu/?y=2013&amp;m=03&amp;d=28&amp;eventdatetime_id=10990','OD&amp;Training','407-823-0440','od&amp;training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1672,'Collective Bargaining Notice','collective-bargaining-notice-1','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the United Faculty of Florida will take place on Thursday, March 28, 2013, from 1:00 to 3:30 p.m. in MH 395. </p>','2013-03-21','2013-03-27','http://www.collectivebargaining.ucf.edu','Sherry Andrews','407-823-1550','sandrews@ucf.edu','Faculty Relations','Publish',1),(1673,'Gmat Review Course','gmat-review-course-1','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the GMAT with our GMAT Review course. Our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length, and is designed to help you prepare for the three main parts on the GMAT: the Analytical Writing Assessment, the Quantitative section, and the Verbal section. There is also time allocated during the class to practice and review what you have learned with practice problems and questions. There are also several sample tests are timed in class to give students the opportunity to use their strategies and to learn to budget their time. This class will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT. </p>','2013-03-24','2013-04-06','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1674,'Interviewer Certification (Registration)','interviewer-certification-registration','<p>This workshop introduces the concept of behavioral interviewing, a highly effective technique for identifying the best candidates for every level of position in the University. The course also examines areas of possible discrimination concerns and provides a review of the USPS hiring process. Upon completion of the program, participants earn the designation of \"certified interviewers,\" a requirement for those signing employment paperwork. To register for this class, go to the Training Section of the HR Website and click on the Training Calendar or call the HR Training Section at 407-823-0440.</p>','2013-03-28','2013-04-10','http://events.ucf.edu/?y=2013&amp;m=03&amp;d=28&amp;eventdatetime_id=10990','HR Training Section','407-823-0440','od&amp;training@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(1675,'Mcat Review Course','mcat-review-course','<p>Dr. Putzers Review &amp; UCF partner to bring you the MCAT Prep Program. The PCAT Prep Program is a comprehensive course that prepares you for the PCAT.  All instructors are highly trained professionals, and possess either an M.D. or Ph.D.  The course emphasizes critical and analytical reasoning which are the primary skills tested by the exam.  96 hours of expert PCAT teaching, including detailed strategies for analyzing PCAT passages, problem-solving skills, and thorough exposure to the scientific content of the test.</p>','2013-04-04','2013-05-03','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1676,'Sat Review Course','sat-review-course-1','<p>UCF Test Preps SAT review course is designed to do more than just review and cover material that will be on the test. Students will learn valuable testing strategies, understand the structure of the SAT, and gain perspective from the test-makers point of view. In addition to reviewing for the test itself, these strategies will help students lean to how avoid common traps and pitfall. The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2013-04-06','2013-04-19','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1677,'Couples Cafe: 5 Love Language','couples-cafe-5-love-language','<p>Discover ways to enhance your relationship and intimacy. Learn your love language, and explore how to keep the butterflies alive in your relationship.</p>\n<p>Combine your love language with practical ways to express your love!</p>\n<p>This workshop will focus on assisting couples to understand each others unique needs and speak each others love language using the Five Love Languages* model which include: Words of Affirmation, Quality time, Gifts, Act of Services, and Physical Touch.</p>\n<p>MUST be at least 18 years old to participate. Space is limited, call 407.823.1748 to reserve yours.</p>\n<p>Follow us on Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF</a></p>\n<p>*The Five Love Languages by Gary D. Chapman is property of Northfield Publishing.</p>','2013-02-05','2013-03-04','http://events.ucf.edu/?search=search&amp;q=couples','Tegan Graser','407.823.1748',' ','Marriage &amp; Family Research Institute','Publish',1),(1678,'Do You Know Your Roots? \"Genealogy Workshop\"','do-you-know-your-roots-genealogy-workshop','<p>Do You Know Your Roots? is a genealogical workshop with Carol Mundy to help participants prepare their own family tree. The event is free but preregistration is required. Community members are welcome to attend. The event will be on campus on Feb. 14 from 9-11am. Carol Mundy has requested that everyone fill out the multiple copies of the attached form with as much information as possible (1 for their parents, 1 for maternal grandparents, and 1 for paternal grandparents). Completed forms and contact information (name, email address, &amp; phone numbers) will be accepted until 5pm 1/25/13 or until all slots are filled. It is okay if the forms are incomplete. She will use them to pre-research for participants, start their family tree, and ensure that access can be obtained as needed for those of us whose backgrounds are outside of the USA. Forms can be emailed to aas@ucf.edu or dropped off at Colbourn Hall rm 112.</p>\n<p>We have 2 3month passes for <a href=\"http://Ancestry.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ancestry.com</a> that will be given away at the workshop\nRoom: 101, 9:00 am-11:00 am\nThursday, February 14th</p>','2013-02-08','2013-03-07',' ','Anjella Warnshuis','407-823-0026','Anjella.Warnshuis@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1679,'Black History Month Keynote Speaker-Michael Eric Dyson','black-history-month-keynote-speaker-michael-eric-dyson','<p>Our featured speaker of the month Dr.Michael Eric Dyson will speak about the relevance of understanding black history. Also featured during the evening will be Back in the Day jazz band,Dr. Vibert White and Mr.Kenny Parker.\nFerrell Commons - Live Oak (FC-7AB),6:00 pm\nWednesday, February 13th</p>','2013-02-08','2013-03-07',' ','Sederia Washington','407-823-1125','msc_sd@ucf.edu','Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services','Publish',1),(1680,'The Black Faculty And Staff Association (Bfsa) 2nd Annual Research Symposium','the-black-faculty-and-staff-association-bfsa-2nd-annual-research-symposium','<p>This event is postponed until Fall 2013.</p>','2013-02-08','2013-03-07',' ','Matha Lue Stewart',' ','martha.stewart@ucf.edu ','Student Leadership Development','Publish',1),(1681,'Gre Review Course','gre-review-course-1','<p>UCF Test Prep has been providing GRE review courses since 1998. With more than 13 years of experience, our courses will help prepare you for both the Verbal and Mathematical sections of the GRE Exam. Our review course will explore strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review of the arithmetic, geometry, and algebra formulas and rules that are needed to answer the mathematics questions on the GRE. These strategies, along with the practice materials, will help to ensure you of no surprises come test day.</p>','2013-04-06','2013-04-12','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1682,'Collective Bargaining Notice','collective-bargaining-notice-1-2','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the United Faculty of Florida will take place on Friday, April 19, 2013, from 2:00 to 4:30 p.m. in MH 395. </p>','2013-04-12','2013-04-18','http://www.collectivebargaining.ucf.edu','Sherry Andrews','407-823-1550','sandrews@ucf.edu','Faculty Relations','Publish',1),(1683,'Ftce Professional Review Course','ftce-professional-review-course','<p>The FTCE Professional Comprehensive Series is designed to familiarize professionals with the various areas that will be covered on the FTCE Professional Examination. As a strategic step in becoming state certified; the course is consistent with assisting teachers to accomplish this goal. Beyond providing test-taking strategies, several sample tests are timed during class sessions to give individuals the opportunity to use their strategies and to manage their time for successful completion of the upcoming assessment. It is the combination of: learning time management skills, confidence-building exercises and concept development that make this course an asset to all learners who desire to successfully take this examination.</p>','2013-04-13','2013-05-12','www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','407-882-TEST','testprep@ucf.edu','Continuing Education, Division Of','Publish',1),(1684,'Act Review Course','act-review-course','<p>Our 20-hour ACT review course is designed to do more than just review question types and cover material that will be on the test. Students will also dissect questions to gain a perspective from the test-taker\'s point of v