 the SAT, and gain perspective from the test-maker’s point of view. In addition to reviewing for the test itself, these strategies will help students lean to how avoid common traps and pitfall. The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-01-12','2014-01-26','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1873,'SAT Review Course','sat-review-course-1-2-3-4','<p>Our 20-hour SAT review course is designed to do more than just review question types and cover material that will be on the test. Students will also dissect questions to gain a perspective from the test-taker\'s point of view.  By doing so, they will learn the common pitfalls and traps to avoid.  Students will also take two simulated tests to ensure the practice of their techniques and to prepare the students for what they can expect on test day.  The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-03-08','2014-03-22','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1874,'SAT Review Course','sat-review-course-1-2-3-4-5','<p>UCF Test Prep’s SAT review course is designed to do more than just review and cover material that will be on the test. Students will learn valuable testing strategies, understand the structure of the SAT, and gain perspective from the test-maker’s point of view. In addition to reviewing for the test itself, these strategies will help students lean to how avoid common traps and pitfall. The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-04-13','2014-04-27','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1875,'ACT Review Course','act-review-course-1','<p>UCF Test Prep’s ACT Review Class is designed to familiarize students with the 5 topics covered on the test. Students will learn valuable testing strategies, understand the structure of the ACT, and gain perspective from the test-maker’s point of view. In addition to reviewing for the test itself, these strategies will help students lean to how avoid common traps and pitfall. The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2013-12-22','2014-01-05','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1876,'ACT Review Course','act-review-course-1-2','<p>Our 20-hour ACT review course is designed to do more than just review question types and cover material that will be on the test. Students will also dissect questions to gain a perspective from the test-taker\'s point of view.  By doing so, they will learn the common pitfalls and traps to avoid.  Students will also take two simulated tests to ensure the practice of their techniques and to prepare the students for what they can expect on test day.  The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-04-20','2014-05-04','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1877,'LSAT Review Course','lsat-review-course','<p>UCF Test Prep’s LSAT review course is designed to fully prepare you for all aspects of the LSAT Exam. This course includes over 1,000 pages of study materials along with practice exams to help you understand the exam. The instructors are subject–matter experts in their field and are completely qualified, dedicated and willing to offer extra help before and after every class.</p>','2013-12-20','2014-01-03','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1878,'MCAT Review Course','mcat-review-course-1','<p>Dr. Putzer’s Review &amp; UCF partner to bring you the MCAT Prep Program. The PCAT Prep Program is a comprehensive course that prepares you for the PCAT.  All instructors are highly trained professionals, and possess either an M.D. or Ph.D.  The course emphasizes critical and analytical reasoning which are the primary skills tested by the exam.  96 hours of expert PCAT teaching, including detailed strategies for analyzing PCAT passages, problem-solving skills, and thorough exposure to the scientific content of the test.</p>','2014-04-19','2014-05-03','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1879,'PCAT Review Course','pcat-review-course','<p>This is a comprehensive course that prepares you for the PCAT. The PCAT prep course includes detailed, expert PCAT teaching covering all the new changes including pertinent biology, microbiology, physiology, general and organic chemistry, reading comprehension, verbal and writing essay skills; analytical science problem passage solving and comprehension; honing scientific expertise through critical &amp; analytical thinking techniques and applications; mock practice exams.</p>','2014-04-02','2014-04-16','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1880,'December 2013 Employee of the Month','december-2013-employee-of-the-month','<p>Please join us in congratulating our newest USPS Employee of the Month for December, Cathy Hill.</p>\n<p>Cathy is an Accountant within Resource Management/ Facilities &amp; Safety Business Office. She has been described by her nominators as “one of those unsung heroes who behind the scenes, “makes ‘it’ happen” and that “Cathy initiates and promotes positive change among her peers and staff. She has been very successful in motivating all new staff members in her unit by maintaining a professional relationship with her staff and peers.”</p>\n<p>We\'d like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. We\'d also like to recognize their nominators who took the time to recognize outstanding efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>In addition to a one-time $200 cash award, a UCF Business Services (on campus vendor) $25 gift certificate, introduction to UCF\'s Board of Trustees, marquee announcement, goody bag, certificate and surprise presentation, Cathy is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year award, which is announced annually at the Employee Awards Program. One of the 12 USPS Employees of Month will be named Employee of the Year and will receive a $2,500 check. If you would like to nominate a USPS employee, the EOM nomination packet is available in hard copy format <a>Here</a>\nor via electronic submission visit <a>Here</a> . On this same webpage, you will also find a complete list of prizes the USPS Employee of the Month receives. The USPS Employee of the Month is selected by a committee comprised of Staff, Administrative &amp; Professional and Faculty employees. If you have questions about the USPS Employee of the Month process, please call 407-823-0440.  Congratulations again to Cathy Hill!</p>','2013-12-11','2013-12-31','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-month/','OD & Training ','(407)823-0440','od&training@ucf.edu','Patty Farris','Publish',1),(1881,'HAPPY (Having Active Participation Prepares You) Hour Student Showcase','happy-having-active-participation-prepares-you-hour-student-showcase','<p>The College of Education and Human Performance cordially invites you to join us at our annual HAPPY (Having Active Participation Prepares You) Hour Student Showcase.  Beat the rush and qualify for door prizes by registering online NOW for this terrific professional development opportunity! </p>\n<p>HAPPY Hour at the Movies featuring the inspirational teacher movie Freedom Writers from 4:30-7:00 p.m. in the Morgridge International Reading Center on Friday, January 24, 2014 will kick off this educational and fun-filled conference! </p>\n<p>The excitement continues on Saturday, January 25, 2014 from 8:30 a.m.-4:00 p.m. on the main campus of UCF where our teacher candidates - who will be the presenters - are the STARS!!  Learn strategies, activities, and information that can be applied to a myriad of careers.  The Showcase boasts keynote speaker, 2013 Florida Teacher of the Year Alexandre Lopes, who teaches children 3-5 years old in an inclusive setting at Carol City Elementary School in the Miami-Dade Public Schools.  Always seeking to make learning fun, he regularly uses singing and dancing to reach all of his students. Also enjoy the Panel of our Rising Stars (education alumni who are now beginning teachers), mock interviews with real-live administrators, numerous vendors, professional organizations, the Prize Patrol, pizza from Giovanni\'s, and the Yum Yum cupcake food truck!</p>\n<p>Get all of this for only $10 by registering online at <a href=\"http://education.ucf.edu/happyhour\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://education.ucf.edu/happyhour</a>  by Monday, January 13, 2014.  On-line registration will qualify you for a door prize.  On-site registration (the day of the Showcase) will cost $20.  </p>','2013-12-11','2014-01-26',NULL,'Karen Verkler',NULL,'Karen.Verkler@ucf.edu','D\'Ann Rawlinson','Publish',1),(1882,'The 6th Annual UCF Counseling Conference','the-6th-annual-ucf-counseling-conference','<p>The University of Central Florida Counselor Education Program is pleased to announce the dates for the <a href=\"http://events.ucf.edu/?y=2014&amp;m=02&amp;d=07&amp;eventdatetime_id=15338\" rel=\"nofollow\">2014 UCF Counseling Conference</a>. This year’s conference will be held on February 7-8, 2014 at the UCF Teaching Academy and Morgridge International Reading Center.</p>\n<p>The UCF Counseling Conference aims to support all counselors in the community of central Florida through relevant and innovative professional development sessions with the goal of inspiring and empowering their work with clients and students. Presentations are delivered by a diverse set of practitioners, graduate students, and university faculty, which enables a range of topics and issues that address the current needs of counseling practitioners. </p>\n<p>This year’s Heintzelman Lecturer is Dr. Mick Cooper from the School of Psychological Sciences and Health, University of Strathclyde, Glascow, Scotland.  His lecture is titled, Counseling and Psychotherapy Research Findings: What We Know and Where We’re Going.</p>\n<p>The UCF Counseling Conference in supported through the works of the Toni Jennings Exceptional Education Institute, the Heintzelman Altruism Endowment, and the UCF Counselor Education program.</p>','2013-12-13','2014-02-08','http://www.education.ucf.edu/counselored/conference.cfm','Ashley Windt ',NULL,'ashleyjwindt@knights.ucf.edu','D\'Ann Rawlinson','Publish',1),(1883,'Employee Tuition Waiver Program and Taxation','employee-tuition-waiver-program-and-taxation-1','<p>In preparation for the spring 2014 semester, please be reminded that UCF employees can claim up to $5,250 in tax-free educational benefits for graduate level and higher coursework (section 127, Internal Revenue Code).  Please be  advised that the value of the benefit in excess of $5,250 will be taxed at the supplemental tax rate (25%) for federal withholding, plus the appropriate Social Security and Medicare tax rates. Those taxes will be deducted from your paycheck(s) and be included on your Form W-2.</p>\n<p>The university does not provide tax advice. If you have questions about this information, please contact a tax professional.</p>\n<p>Non-tax related questions regarding the educational benefits addressed above may be directed to Payroll Services by emailing payroll@ucf.edu or calling (407) 823-2771.</p>','2014-01-02','2014-01-04',NULL,'Payroll Services','(407)823-2771','payroll@ucf.edu','Isha Guerrero-Londeree','Publish',1),(1884,'Who Do You Think That You Are Genealogy Workshop','who-do-you-think-that-you-are-genealogy-workshop','<p>Do you love to watch Who Do You Think You Are? Have you every wanted to trace your own family tree and didn’t know how? Would you like to have some help from a genealogy expert?</p>\n<p>Join us for the UCF edition of Who Do You Think You Are? on February 18th from 8:30-10:30 am. </p>\n<p>Carol Mundy with the African American Legacy and Yvette Birdsong with Afro-American Historical and Genealogical Society Central Florida will help participants trace their family  trees. </p>\n<p>Records from 1940 to the present aren’t yet available for searching so you need to know relatives born prior to 1940 in order to be able to find information.</p>\n<p>There will be giveaways courtesy of <a href=\"http://Ancestry.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ancestry.com</a></p>\n<p>Attendance is limited to 40 people. Please r.s.v.p. to bfsa@ucf.edu to receive the event location. </p>','2014-01-02','2014-02-14',NULL,'Anjella Warnshuis','(407)823-0026','bfsa@ucf.edu','Anjella Warnshuis','Publish',1),(1885,'New Year - New Computer Training courses','new-year-new-computer-training-courses','<p>Continuing Education offers many of the latest desktop application courses to help you learn to navigate the new Microsoft Office 2013 software. You can learn the New Features of Office 2013, Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint and many more. Courses will still be offered in Microsoft Office 2010. Regular Prices for UCF Students, Staff and Alumni: Microsoft Access, PowerPoint, Excel, Word, Office 2013 New Features Courses: $149.00 each. To register with these discounted UCF prices or to inquire about additional IT Courses, please visit us online at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu</a> or contact Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu or 407-882-0237. </p>','2014-01-01','2014-01-31','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Programs/30/Computer-Training/','Sarah Faehnle','(407)882-0237','sfaehnle@ucf.edu','Sarah Faehnle, UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(1886,'Money Matters Workshop 6:00-8:00 pm >At no cost to participants.','money-matters-workshop-600-800-pm-at-no-cost-to-participants','<p>The Money Matters workshop shows participants how to manage their money by preparing a personal spending plan and identifying ways to decrease spending and increase income. </p>\n<p>• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate. \n• At no cost to participants. \n• RSVP is required. Call the MFRI to reserve your space at 407.823.1748.</p>\n<p>Follow us on Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF</a></p>','2014-01-07','2014-01-30','http://www.mfri.ucf.edu/','Sandy Griffith ','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI: YC','Publish',1),(1887,'University Writing Center Offers Long-Term Help for Writers in Every Major','university-writing-center-offers-long-term-help-for-writers-in-every-major','<p>For help with writing in every discipline, the UWC now invites students, faculty, and staff to schedule recurring weekly consultations during Spring 2014. Weekly consultations help writers and tutors to focus not merely on fixing a single piece of writing, but on developing skills over the long term, for the next writing task, and the one after that.</p>\n<p>Trained peer tutors from a variety of majors assist writers at every stage of the writing process, from deciphering complex assignments, to drafting, to revising, to learning strategies for effective proofreading and editing.</p>\n<p>Faculty and staff may use the UWC\'s new Referral Form, available on the UWC website, to initiate ongoing help for students: <a href=\"http://uwc.ucf.edu/referstudents.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://uwc.ucf.edu/referstudents.php</a>.</p>\n<p>Students may use the same Referral Form to arrange a weekly appointment time for themselves.</p>','2014-01-13','2014-04-29','http://uwc.ucf.edu/','R. Mark Hall','(407)823-0504','rmarkhall@ucf.edu','R. Mark Hall, University Writing Center Director','Publish',1),(1888,'Accepting Submissions for the Graduate Research Forum','accepting-submissions-for-the-graduate-research-forum','<p>Beginning January 6, through February 10, 2014 at 5:00 p.m., all current graduate students are invited to submit their work for entry into the Graduate Research Forum.</p><p></p>\n<p>Submissions can include:</p><p></p>\n<p>Creative projects<br>\nA literature review<br>\nOriginal research</p><p></p>\n<p>The Eleventh Annual Graduate Research Forum is slated for Tuesday, April 1, 2014.</p><p></p>\n<p>Do not miss out on this fantastic opportunity to showcase your research or creative project and receive valuable feedback. Cash prizes are awarded to the best presentation in each discipline!</p><p></p>\n<p>Submissions must be the original work of the author(s). Previously presented or published papers are permitted. All presentations on the day of the event must be in poster format and adhered to a poster board, which will be provided.</p><p></p>\n<p>For more information, to submit and guidelines regarding the proposal submission, visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.graduate.ucf.edu/ResearchForum\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.graduate.ucf.edu/ResearchForum</a> or email researchweek@ucf.edu. </p>','2014-01-06','2014-02-10','http://www.graduate.ucf.edu/ResearchForum','Carreen Krapf','(407)823-2766','researchweek@ucf.edu','Carreen Krapf','Publish',1),(1889,'First COUPLES CAFÉ Workshop at the Daytona Beach Regional Campus! February 12 •  6:00-8:00pm','first-couples-cafe-workshop-at-the-daytona-beach-regional-campus-february-12-600-800pm','<p>This workshop will focus on assisting individuals and couples to understand other’s unique needs and “speak” the partner’s love language using the Five Love Languages* model which include: Words of Affirmation, Quality time, Gifts, Act of Services, and Physical Touch.</p>\n<p>Discover ways to enhance your relationship and intimacy. Learn your love language, and explore how to keep the butterflies alive in your relationship. Combine your love language with practical ways to express your love!</p>\n<p>• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• Space is limited, please RSVP by calling Yamille at 407.823.4507 or 407.823.1748, or by email Yamille.Feliciano-Aponte@ucf.edu.\n&gt;LOCATION: Daytona Beach Regional Campus, Building 150, Room 115</p>\n<p>*The Five Love Languages by @DrGaryChapman is property of Northfield Publishing.</p>','2014-01-07','2014-02-12','http://mfri.ucf.edu/','Yamille Feliciano','(407)823-4507','Yamille.Feliciano-Aponte@ucf.edu','MFRI: YC','Publish',1),(1890,'Stress and Relaxation in Relationships Workshop - January 27, 2014 - 6:00-8:00 pm','stress-and-relaxation-in-relationships-workshop-january-27-2014-600-800-pm','<p>Stress is a big part of today’s world and can impact our ability to function in our personal and professional lives. Come to this interactive workshop to learn about the ways in which stress affects us, how to manage stress in relationships, and, best of all, to learn effective tools and techniques to help you relax.</p>\n<p>• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• At no cost to participants. This workshop is open to the Central Florida Community.</p>\n<p>Space is limited, please RSVP by calling 407.823.1748.</p>','2014-01-07','2014-01-27','http://mfri.ucf.edu/','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI: YC','Publish',1),(1891,'Physical Therapy now available at the Health Center','physical-therapy-now-available-at-the-health-center','<p>UCF Health Services is proud to announce that Physical Therapy services are now available at the Health Center. The service is made possible by a partnership with Florida Hospital Sports Medicine and Rehabilitation and will compliment the care that patients receive from the center’s sports medicine doctors. As with all the services at the Health Center, it is open to students, faculty and staff. Most insurance plans are accepted and discounted self-pay rates are available. </p>\n<p>For appointments, call 407-303-6610. </p>\n<p>Learn more about the services available at the Health Center at <a href=\"http://www.hs.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.hs.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2014-01-09','2014-01-31','http://www.hs.ucf.edu','Megan Pabian',NULL,'megan.pabian@ucf.edu','Megan Pabian','Publish',1),(1892,'January 2014 USPS Employee of the Month','january-2014-usps-employee-of-the-month','<p>Please join us in congratulating our newest USPS Employee of the Month for January, Alan Holtz.</p>\n<p>Alan is a Program Assistant within the First Year Experience Department. He has been described by his nominators as “displaying integrity with unparalleled professionalism and selfless dedication.” Some may call him the “administrative go-to superstar,” while his student assistants describe him as a positive, caring, never give up kind of person. Alan is said to bring the core values he learned in the Navy to the work he does today by exuding Honor, Courage and Commitment. Lastly, Alan can be described as “one of the most dedicated, committed and dependable employees on the team.”</p>\n<p>We\'d like to thank this outstanding employee for his dedication and hard work. We\'d also like to recognize their nominators who took the time to recognize outstanding efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>In addition to a one-time $200 cash award, a UCF Business Services (on campus vendor) $25 gift certificate, introduction to UCF\'s Board of Trustees, marquee announcement, goody bag, certificate and surprise presentation, Alan is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year award, which is announced annually at the Employee Awards Program. One of the 12 USPS Employees of Month will be named Employee of the Year and will receive a $2,500 check. If you would like to nominate a USPS employee, the EOM nomination packet is available in hard copy format <a>Here</a>\nor via electronic submission visit <a>Here</a> . On this same webpage, you will also find a complete list of prizes the USPS Employee of the Month receives. The USPS Employee of the Month is selected by a committee comprised of Staff, Administrative &amp; Professional and Faculty employees. If you have questions about the USPS Employee of the Month process, please call 407-823-0440.  Congratulations again to Alan Hortz!</p>','2014-01-15','2014-01-21','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-month/','OD & Training ','(407)823-0440','od&training@ucf.edu','OD& Training','Publish',1),(1893,'VESPR Craft Coffee & Allures- FREE COFFEE For Graduate Students','vespr-craft-coffee-allures-free-coffee-for-graduate-students','<p>The VESPR Craft Coffee &amp; Allures (located in Waterford Lakes) is coming to the UCF Graduate Student Center (located in Colbourn Hall Suite 146) to give free coffee to graduate students. They will be here on Wednesday, January 29th from 3:00pm to 5:00pm to provide graduate students with the \"pick-me-up\" they need before embarking on an evening of classes and study time. So come on by and grab a free cup of \"Joe.\" </p>','2014-01-14','2014-01-29','http://www.graduate.ucf.edu/gradcenter','Graduate Student Center Assistants','(408)823-4689','gradcenter@ucf.edu','Chad Billington, Graduate Student Center','Publish',1),(1894,'Quit Smoking Now- Free patches!','quit-smoking-now-free-patches','<p>A you a smoker looking to quit? The UCF Health Center can help with FREE cessation support, including free nicotine-replacement therapy. Classes are scheduled per-request at your convenience. If you qualify for part of a research study, you can be reimbursed for your time. Email mary.schmidt-owens@ucf.edu to sign up or learn more!</p>','2014-01-17','2014-01-31',NULL,'Dr. Mary Schmidt-Owens','(407)823-1489','mary.schmidt-owens@ucf.edu','Megan Pabian','Publish',1),(1895,'2014 Believe Faculty & Staff Campaign','2014-believe-faculty-staff-campaign','<p>The 2014 Believe Faculty &amp; Staff Campaign kicks off January 27 and runs through the end of February. This annual employee-giving program supports a wide variety of needs, which include student scholarships, campus-wide programs, building enhancements and many more—it’s your choice! This campaign is your chance to help the UCF programs that mean the most to you. Again this year you have an opportunity to double the impact of your gift by helping fund scholarships for first generation students at UCF, as the state of Florida will match your gift dollar for dollar. </p>\n<p>Show your support at the open house kick-off event Jan. 27 from 2-3:30 p.m. at the Student Union Pegasus Ballroom and the mid-campaign social Feb. 18 from 2-3:30 p.m. at the Millican Statue in front of Millican Hall. Laptops and pledge cards will be on hand at the events, or you may submit your pledge card through your area volunteer or online at <a href=\"http://believe.ucffund.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">believe.ucffund.org</a>.</p>','2014-01-17','2014-02-18','http://believe.ucffund.org','Kara Steiner','(407)882-1254','kara.steiner@ucf.edu','The UCF Fund','Publish',1),(1896,'Eating Disorder Awareness Week','eating-disorder-awareness-week','<p>The objective of National Eating Disorders Awareness Week is to equip participants with the warning signs and treatment options for eating disorders as well as the language and behaviors that friends and family can adopt to create an effective support network.</p>','2014-02-23','2014-03-01',NULL,'Counseling and Psychological Services','(407)823-2811','councntr@ucf.edu','SDES','Publish',1),(1897,'FLORIDA SPACE INSTITUTE Seminar - Speaker Nicoleta Soroaica Hickman','florida-space-institute-seminar-speaker-nicoleta-soroaica-hickman','<p>FSI SEMINAR</p>\n<p>WEDNESDAY January 22, 2014\nSpeaker: Nicoleta Soroaica Hickman\nAffiliation: FSEC / UCF\nDay and Date: Wednesday, January 22, 2014\nTime: 11:00 - 12:00</p>\n<p>Location: Research Park\n12354 Research Parkway\nPartnership 1 Bldg. Suite 209\nOrlando, FL 32826</p>\n<p>Title: Fully-Functional Space And Terrestrial Photovoltaic/Electrodynamic Shield (PV/ES) Hybrid System For Dust Mitigation</p>\n<p>The dust deposit on sensitive and costly surfaces of investigative equipment is a serious concern for future lunar and Martian missions. Several methods have been surveyed to protect optical or photovoltaic surfaces from the dust deposition threat but limiting condition of lunar and Martian environment makes them either inefficient or infeasible. Since there is no drag force on particles, and the magnetic field is negligible, applying electrostatic field could be the best approach for dust control.</p>\n<p>The unique properties of ITO, Graphene and Carbon Nanotube (CNT) combined with recent scientific advancements that make these materials readily available allow development of smart surfaces on a small and large scale that will benefit the power generation devices. Our research groups from UCF and UF in collaboration with KSC have been working on high and low voltage technologies like Electrodynamic Dust Shield (EDS) and Electrostatic Lunar Dust Collector (ELDC) for future lunar and Mars Missions.</p>\n<p>The research team developed active and very efficient cleaning methods based on ITO, Graphene and CNT materials requiring minimal cost, weight, and power that repel and remove particulate buildup of surface contaminants, e.g., dust and dirt, from solar panels used for the space mission. The cleaning methods ensure that solar panels are operational for longer periods of time and with lower power loss due to dust obscuration.</p>\n<p>For further information please visit:\n<a href=\"http://fsi.ucf.edu/seminars/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://fsi.ucf.edu/seminars/</a></p>','2014-01-21','2014-01-22','http://fsi.ucf.edu/seminars/ ','Patricia Szczerba','(407)823-6351','patricia.szczerba@ucf.edu','patricia szczerba','Publish',1),(1898,'Research Computing Day to Showcase UCF\'s High Performance Systems','research-computing-day-to-showcase-ucfs-high-performance-systems','<p>Find out how high performance computers are increasingly needed for advanced research during a half-day series of presentations to be held at the STOKES Advanced Research Computing Center headquarters in the Central Florida Research Park next to campus.</p>\n<p>The event is set for Tuesday, Feb. 11, from 8 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. at the Partnership III Building, 3039 Technology Parkway. The event is open to faculty, students and the community at no charge, but an RSVP (thompson@ist.ucf.edu) is requested as space is limited.</p>\n<p>Members of the statewide research computing alliance and high-speed communication networks, and UCF faculty users of the STOKES high-performance cluster housed in the research park will show how high performance systems help meet advanced research challenges. A presentation by special guest Dr. Daniel A. Reed, Vice President for Research and Economic Development and University Chair in Computational Science and Bioinformatics, Professor of Computer Science, Electrical and Computer Engineering and Medicine at the University of Iowa, and an innovator in cloud computing, will highlight the event.</p>\n<p>UCF’s own Advanced Research Computing Center (the STOKES ARCC) has become a valuable resource for faculty. The STOKES ARCC is linked to other Florida universities—and nationwide institutions—via Florida Lambda Rail and Internet2.  Also, as a member of the Sunshine State Education &amp; Research Computing Alliance (SSERCA), UCF cooperates with other advanced computing centers in the state university system.</p>\n<p>More about this event, including additional information about speakers, is on the Institute for Simulation &amp; Training Website (<a href=\"http://www.ist.ucf.edu/researchcomputingday.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.ist.ucf.edu/researchcomputingday.html</a>).</p>','2014-01-24','2014-02-11','http://www.ist.ucf.edu/researchcomputingday.html','Brian Goldiez, Ph.D.','(407)882-1302','bgoldiez@ist.ucf.edu','Randall Williams','Publish',1),(1899,'Are you the parent of a young child who is 1.5- to 5-years of age?','are-you-the-parent-of-a-young-child-who-is-15-to-5-years-of-age','<p>Are you the parent of a young child who is 1.5- to 5-years of age? Researchers are asking parents to fill out surveys about parents’ temperament and emotion regulation, stress and coping, parenting behaviors, and children’s temperament for up to 1 hour via a packet by mail or online. If you are willing to help, please complete the online survey at <a href=\"http://edu.surveygizmo.com/s3/1367308/A-Closer-Look-at-the-Interactions-Among-Parent-and-Child-Temperament-Stress-and-Coping-Emotional-and-Behavioral-Regulation-and-Parenting-Behaviors\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://edu.surveygizmo.com/s3/1367308/A-Closer-Look-at-the-Interactions-Among-Parent-and-Child-Temperament-Stress-and-Coping-Emotional-and-Behavioral-Regulation-and-Parenting-Behaviors</a>. If you would like to receive a packet via postal mail, please contact Amanda Lowell at amanda.lowell.ucf@gmail.com, or Kimberly Renk, Ph.D. at Kimberly.Renk@ucf.edu or 407-823-2218. Thank you!</p>','2014-01-27','2014-05-30',NULL,'Kimberly Renk','(407)823-2218','Kimberly.Renk@ucf.edu','Kimberly Renk','Publish',1),(1900,'Free Tutoring for Writers in Every Major','free-tutoring-for-writers-in-every-major','<p>The University Writing Center (Colbourn 105) offers individual and small-group tutoring to students, faculty, and staff. We help, face-to-face and online, with any writing: Classwork, resumes, cover letters, personal statements, professional writing, and personal writing. You can visit the UWC at any stage of the writing process, from deciphering a complex assignment, to drafting, revising, and learning strategies to proofread and edit more effectively. Click on our website to schedule a consultation today. </p>\n<p>Here are some tips to help you make the most of your Writing Center experience: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Schedule an appointment well in advance of your due date.</li>\n<li>If you’re working on a collaborative project, bring all your group members.</li>\n<li>Return to the UWC frequently throughout your writing process.</li>\n<li>Bring your assignment, draft work, sources, course materials, and questions.</li>\n<li>Come to each consultation with a few specific learning goals.</li>\n<li>Begin by explaining your assignment requirements and instructor’s expectations.</li>\n<li>Focus on learning and practicing strategies you can apply to future writing tasks.</li>\n<li>Take notes during your consultation; your tutor will also email a summary to you.</li>\n<li>Plan what to do next as you revise—and what to work on in your next UWC visit.</li>\n<li>Practice what you learn in the UWC between consultations.</li>\n<li>Check out our writing resources on the web.</li>\n</ul>','2014-01-30','2014-05-03','http://uwc.ucf.edu/','R. Mark Hall, Director, University Writing Center','(407)823-0504','rmarkhall@ucf.edu','R. Mark Hall','Publish',1),(1901,'New Microsoft Office 2013 Training','new-microsoft-office-2013-training','<p>Continuing Education offers many of the latest desktop application courses to help you learn to navigate the new Microsoft Office 2013 software. You can learn the New Features of Office 2013, Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint and many more. Courses will still be offered in Microsoft Office 2010. Regular Prices for UCF Students, Staff and Alumni: Microsoft Access, PowerPoint, Excel, Word, Office 2013 New Features Courses: $149.00 each. To register with these discounted UCF prices or to inquire about additional IT Courses, please visit us online at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu</a> or contact Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu or 407-882-0237. </p>','2014-02-01','2014-02-28','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Programs/30/Computer-Training/','Sarah Faehnle','(407)882-0237','sfaehnle@ucf.edu','Sarah Faehnle, UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(1902,'Phi Alpha Delta Pre-Law Fraternity Weekly Meetings','phi-alpha-delta-pre-law-fraternity-weekly-meetings','<p>Meetings are held every Wednesday at 7:00pm in the Student Union (SU) Room 218C </p>\n<p>Phi Alpha Delta Pre-Law Fraternity, International is a professional pre-law fraternity advancing integrity, compassion and courage through service to the student, the school, the profession and the community.</p>\n<p>We are the preeminent law fraternity promoting the bonds of fraternalism and we are the leader in the development and advancement of professional ideals.</p>\n<p>The purpose of this Fraternity shall be to form a strong bond uniting students and teachers of the law with members of the Bench and Bar in a fraternal fellowship designed to advance the ideals of liberty and equal justice under law; to stimulate excellence in scholarship; to inspire the virtues of compassion and courage; to foster integrity and professional competence; to promote the welfare of its members; and to encourage their moral, intellectual, and cultural advancement; so that each member may enjoy a lifetime of honorable professional and public service.</p>','2014-02-04','2014-04-16','http://ucfpad.com','Janaye Garrett',NULL,'padmembership@gmail.com','UCF Phi Alpha Delta Pre-Law Fraternity, International','Publish',1),(1903,'Florida Wildlife Corridor Expedition','florida-wildlife-corridor-expedition','<pre><code> The Legacy Institute for Nature and Culture (LINC) and the University of Central Florida Arboretum invite you to an evening of discussion and education about the vision for the Florida Wildlife Corridor. With generous support from the Florida Humanities Council, the event will feature the award-winning documentary film Florida Wildlife Corridor Expedition: Everglades to Okefenokee.\n In 2012, four explorers hiked 1000 miles in 100 days from the Everglades in southern Florida to Okefenokee Swamp in southern Georgia. Their goal: to raise awareness of the potential to create a viable, continuous wildlife corridor across Florida. Bear biologist Joe Guthrie, conservationist Mallory Lykes Dimmitt, photojournalist Carlton Ward Jr., and award-winning cinematographer Elam Stoltzfus, traversed the wildlife habitats, watersheds and participating working farms and ranches, which comprise the Florida Wildlife Corridor opportunity area.\n The February 19th event at the UCF Fairwinds Alumni Center will be the eighth in a series of ten “Corridor Conservation” events supported by the Florida Humanities Council to publicize the film and facilitate public dialogue on the Florida Wildlife Corridor. Please join us at 5:30 pm for an opening reception, 6:30 pm film screening, and 7:30 pm panel discussion. The event is free and open to the public. Donations are welcome. Reception will begin at 5:30pm at the UCF Alumni Center. Seating is limited.\n</code></pre>','2014-02-19','2014-02-19','http://www.floridawildlifecorridor.org/','Tina Richards','(407)823-3583','Tina.Richards@ucf.edu','Arboretum','Publish',1),(1904,'Arboretum Volunteer Shifts','arboretum-volunteer-shifts','<p>The Arboretum offers a variety of volunteer opportunities. Volunteers can help in the community garden, assist with horticultural work in campus landscapes, or help in campus natural lands. Come out and get your feet wet, your hands dirty, and your knowledge expanded, as you learn more about gardening, landscaping, or natural lands management!</p>\n<p>Volunteer shifts for Spring 2014 are: Tuesday 8-10am, Thursday 8-10am, and Friday 10-12pm</p>\n<p>Volunteers can simply show up to our office punctually at the beginning of any of our volunteer shifts. Our website always has the most up-to-date volunteer schedule. Please bring a reusable water bottle, wear closed-toe shoes and a smile.</p>','2014-01-06','2014-04-22','http://arboretum.ucf.edu/get-involved/students/volunteers/','Tina Richards','(407)823-3583','Tina.Richards@ucf.edu','Arboretum','Publish',1),(1905,'Winter Park Garden Club Endowed Scholarship','winter-park-garden-club-endowed-scholarship','<p>The Winter Park Garden Club Endowed Scholarship is offered each fall and spring semester for qualified students majoring in Biology, Chemistry, Microbiology or Environmental Studies, who have an interest in botany, horticulture or environmental science. Scholarship information and application requirements are provided below.</p>\n<p>Scholarship Criteria:\n</p><ul>\n    <li>Amount of award: $1,000</li><p></p>\n<pre><code>&lt;li&gt;Two awards given, one during fall semester, one during spring semester&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Must hold a minimum 3.0 GPA&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Must be a resident of the State of Florida&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Must demonstrate financial need as determined by the FASFA&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Must be a full time student majoring in Biology, Chemistry, Microbiology or Environmental Studies (through Interdisciplinary Studies) with a demonstrated interest in botany, horticulture, or environmental studies&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Must be either a junior or senior undergraduate or graduate level student&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate involvement in campus leadership and/or community service related activities&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Must submit a one-page essay stating their specific goals related to education, career, and community service&lt;/li&gt;\n\n&lt;li&gt;Must submit three (3) letters of recommendation&lt;/li&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p></p></ul>\nTo apply for a scholarship you must log into <a href=\"http://my.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://my.ucf.edu</a>, go to the Student Self Service Portal, and click on Scholarship Application. A resume is required for all COS scholarship submissions. Please direct any questions about the application process to Susan Hill in the College of Sciences office Susan.Hill@ucf.edu. Please make sure your application packet is complete as incomplete applications will not be considered. Application deadline has been extended to March 1, 2014.<p></p>','2014-02-01','2014-03-01','http://www.cos.ucf.edu/scholarships/?p=47','Susan Hill','(407)823-1913','Susan.Hill@ucf.edu','Arboretum','Publish',1),(1906,'Internships in Washington, DC for Summer 2014 and beyond','internships-in-washington-dc-for-summer-2014-and-beyond','<p>Internships in Washington, DC for Summer 2014 and beyond:  Learn about these opportunities during Information Sessions given by Kourtnaye Lewis of The Washington Center on Wednesday, February 12 and Thursday, February 13, 2014 at 4:00 pm in the Office of Experiential Learning, CSEL, Suite 300.  She will also participate in the Co-Op &amp; Internship Fair on Thursday, February 13, 2014 at 10 am – 2 pm in the Student Union, Pegasus Ballroom. The internships are open to all degree seeking undergraduate and graduate students. UCF undergrads can qualify for a $7,500 Florida grant for 2014. Check The Washington Center website  <a href=\"http://www.TWC.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.TWC.edu</a>  for basic eligibility criteria. UCF contact: Ulla Isaac at the Office of Experiential Learning 407-823-2667.</p>','2014-02-06','2014-02-13','http://www.explearning.ucf.edu','Ulla Isaac','(407)823-2667','Ulla.Isaac@ucf.edu','Rick 3-1002','Publish',1),(1907,'Time Management Online WEB course:  OLX001  (UCF Faculty and Staff only)','time-management-online-web-course-olx001-ucf-faculty-and-staff-only','<p>Enroll now in Time Management Online WEB :  OLX001  (UCF Faculty and Staff only) -\nDo you need to leverage your productivity skills and don’t have time to come to a Time Management workshop?  Then sign up to attend our new online Time Management: Accomplishing More with Less course.\nBased on the best-selling FranklinCovey Time Management training, you will learn: \n•   5 steps for analyzing and mastering your use of time \n•   How to avoid / minimize office distractions\n•   How to plan and set SMART goals\n•   How to prioritize urgent versus important\nTo successfully complete the Time Management: Accomplishing More online course, you must complete one module which is delivered via Webcourses@UCF.   Scoring 100 percent on the assessment allows participants to receive course credit in People Soft.  It will take 24 hours to populate the course completion in People Soft. \nTo access the online course please follow the instructions provided below:\n1.  Sign on to the portal at <a href=\"https://my.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://my.ucf.edu</a>\n2.  Navigate to: Employee Self Service &gt; Learning &amp; Development &gt; Request Training Enrollment\n3.  Search by Course Name: Time Management Online WEB, then select Search\n4.  or Search by Course Number: OLX001, then select Search\n5.  Select View Available Sessions, then select the highlighted session # (choose the one with the timeliest date and it will be accessible immediately)<br>\n6.  Select continue to complete registration\n7.  Select submit\n8.  You can then access the course by logging into Webcourses@UCF via the <a href=\"http://my.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">my.ucf.edu</a> portal or <a href=\"http://webcourses.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://webcourses.ucf.edu</a>.\nPlease note that your PID and PID password are required to log into the myUCF portal.  If you have forgotten your PID Password or have never set your PID password, click on PID or NID Password Reset under myUCF Need Help section on the right of the web page and then click on Change PID Password.\nIf you have any questions, don’t hesitate to call us at (407) 823-0440 or send an email message to od&amp;training@ucf.edu. We will reply to your inquiry as soon as possible. \n*Note:  You may need to download the latest version of Flash Player, which is free (<a href=\"http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/</a>). \nPlease contact your IT support person if you need help with downloading the Flash Player.</p>','2014-02-07','2014-02-14','http://hr.ucf.edu/','OD & Training ','(407)823-0440','od&training@ucf.edu','Patty Farris','Publish',1),(1908,'New Microsoft Office 2013 Training','new-microsoft-office-2013-training-1','<p>Continuing Education offers many of the latest desktop application courses to help you learn to navigate the new Microsoft Office 2013 software. You can learn the New Features of Office 2013, Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint and many more. Courses will still be offered in Microsoft Office 2010. Regular Prices for UCF Students, Staff and Alumni: Microsoft Access, PowerPoint, Excel, Word, Office 2013 New Features Courses: $149.00 each. To register with these discounted UCF prices or to inquire about additional IT Courses, please visit us online at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu</a> or contact Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu or 407-882-0237.</p>','2014-02-07','2014-02-28','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Programs/30/Computer-Training/','Sarah Faehnle ','(407)882-0237','sfaehnle@ucf.edu','Erika Nagy, UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(1909,'UCF Alumni Association Scholarship Applications Now Available ','ucf-alumni-association-scholarship-applications-now-available','<p>Each year the UCF Alumni Association awards more than $40,000 in scholarships to UCF students demonstrating strong academic ability and significant extracurricular and community involvement. The UCF Alumni Association is pleased to again offer more than a dozen scholarship opportunities. UCF students are encouraged to apply for as many scholarships for which they are eligible. Applications are now available on <a href=\"http://my.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">myUCF</a>. Apply for scholarships based on eligibility<em> by following these simple steps: \n</em></p><ul><em>\n    <li>1. Read all scholarship criteria and complete ALL required supporting documents prior to submitting your application</li>\n    <li>2. Log into myUCF</li>\n    <li>3. Select “Student Self Service”</li>\n    <li>4. Click on “Scholarship Application” &gt; “Home Page” &gt; “Add New Scholarship” </li>\n    <li>5. Complete and submit application(s)</li>\n</em></ul><em>\n</em>Scholarships will appear in myUCF based on eligibility requirements specific to each scholarship. Criteria used to determine eligibility includes, but is not limited to: GPA, class standing and academic program. Be sure to visit <a href=\"http://www.ucfalumni.com/scholarships\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.ucfalumni.com/scholarships</a> for all criteria and application steps for each scholarship. The deadline to apply is midnight, Saturday, March 15, 2014. Late or incomplete applications will not be considered. Questions? Call 407.UCF.ALUM (823.2586) or e-mail scholarships@ucfalumni.com.<p></p>','2014-02-10','2014-03-15','http://ucfalumni.com/scholarships','Carla Cordoba','(407)823-3453','carla.cordoba@ucf.edu','Carla Cordoba','Publish',1),(1910,'John T. Washington Community Service Awards and Scholarship Luncheon ','john-t-washington-community-service-awards-and-scholarship-luncheon','<p>Each year, the Africana Studies Program hosts the John T. Washington Community Service Awards and Scholarship Luncheon in order to recognize adults and youths who have made outstanding contributions to our community.</p>\n<p>Besides being one of the first African Americans to hold a faculty position at the University of Central Florida, John T. Washington, Ph.D. was a humanitarian and leader who not only taught a life of service, but also lived it. His sincerity and altruism had a profound impact on those with whom he had contact.</p>\n<p>The annual John T. Washington luncheon honors his legacy by celebrating the involvement of citizens who participate in community and civic programs in the greater central Florida area. The award recognizes people who exemplify the same humanitarian and scholarly characteristics that were so vividly demonstrated by Washington.</p>\n<p>The program requests the honor of your presence at this year\'s luncheon. The luncheon will be held on Monday, February 24, 2014 in the UCF Student Union Pegasus Ballroom. We also invite you to support this worthy cause by purchasing a Sponsorship Package or Program Advertisement, or by making a donation. Please read the enclosed form to learn more about these opportunities. Kindly RSVP by Friday, February 14, 2014.</p>\n<p>You can also further support this program by distributing the application form to worthy candidates. Any individual who has served the African American community in Orange, Seminole, Osceola, or Brevard County is invited to submit the enclosed application. You may also nominate someone by completing the application on his or her behalf. We encourage you to duplicate this application as needed and distribute it to as many people as possible. Please be advised that applications must be received by Friday, January 24, 2014.</p>\n<p>Cost:  $32.50 individual seating or $300 corporate table (10 seats). Sponsorship packages are also available. For additional information about the Dr. John T. Washington awards program and luncheon, please feel free to contact the Africana Studies office at 407-823-0026 or africana@ucf.edu.</p>','2014-02-10','2014-02-14','http://africana.cah.ucf.edu/luncheon.php','Anjella Warnshuis','(407)823-0026','africana@ucf.edu','Anjella Warnshuis','Publish',1),(1911,'Celebrate Black History Month at the John T. Washington Center!','celebrate-black-history-month-at-the-john-t-washington-center','<p>Celebrate Black History Month by participating in the John T. Washington Center &amp; African American Studies Scavenger Hunt! </p>\n<p>Visit the SPOT for your free entry form. </p>\n<p>You could win $50 to the Barnes &amp; Noble bookstore, an iTunes gift card or a pair of suite tickets to see an upcoming Predators game.</p>','2014-02-10','2014-02-19',NULL,'Sue Gonzalez','(407)823-3539','sue.gonzalez@ucf.edu','Sue Gonzalez','Publish',1),(1912,'Thesis & Dissertation Coaching Workshop','thesis-dissertation-coaching-workshop','<p>This Coaching Workshop is designed for graduate students who would like support in the process of completing their Thesis or Dissertation. Coaching can help participants develop strategies for staying motivated, overcoming obstacles, managing time, and being productive. Participants will be encouraged to set weekly goals and report back each week.</p>\n<p>The workshop will be Thursdays, 3:00-4:30 and begin soon.  </p>\n<p>Graduate students must attend a brief pre-workshop meeting in order to participate.</p>\n<p>Call 407-823-2811 to register or for more information.</p>','2014-02-11','2014-02-25','http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/','Larry Marks, Ph.D.','(407)823-2811','Larry.Marks@ucf.edu','Larry Marks, Ph.D.','Publish',1),(1913,'USPS Staff Council Spring Scholarships for USPS members and their dependents currently taking classes','usps-staff-council-spring-scholarships-for-usps-members-and-their-dependents-currently-taking-classes','<p>The USPS Staff Council is offering Spring Scholarships for USPS members and their dependents currently taking classes.  There are many Scholarships available, and employees may apply for all or any of them they wish.  The application deadline is March 10, 2014.  </p>\n<p>If there are any questions please contact Jamie LaMoreaux at Jamie.LaMoreaux@ucf.edu or 2-0191.  </p>\n<p>The application is on the USPS Staff Council web site: <a href=\"http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html</a>.</p>','2014-02-14','2014-03-10',NULL,'Jamie LaMoreaux','(497)882-0191','Jamie.LaMoreaux@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',1),(1914,'UCF- CLASS (Center for Lunar Astroid Surface Science) ','ucf-class-center-for-lunar-astroid-surface-science','<p>Title: The impact hazard from small asteroids: Lessons from the Chelyabinsk airburst one year later\nAbstract:  A year ago a small asteroid exploded without warning with the force of 500,000 tons of TNT over Chelyabinsk, Russia. Dr. Peter Brown is one of the leading experts on this event and will speak on the explosion and the hazards to Earth poised by small asteroids. The impact hazard at the Earth due to small asteroids is uncertain. The root of this uncertainty is the poorly understood interaction of small asteroids in the atmosphere together with the associated impact effects at the ground together with the poorly constrained number of small objects impacting Earth. The Chelyabinsk airburst has provided detailed data on a well-observed damage-producing airburst for the first time. In this talk Dr. Brown will describe what we have learned about the Chelyabinsk airburst in the year since it occurred and what it may tell us more broadly about the effects we can expect from future impacts at the Earth.</p>\n<p>The Speaker:\nProfessor Peter Brown, Ph.D. is a Distinguished Research Professor in the Faculty of Science at the Department of Physics and Astronomy, Western University, London, Ontario, Canada. He is the Director of the Centre for Planetary Science and Exploration at Western University. Dr. Brown’s research on the interaction between meteoroids and the Earth’s atmosphere, the detection of meteor explosions, and the identification of the sources of meteors. Most recently he has lead an intensive study of the Chelyabinsk airburst.  </p>','2014-01-24','2014-01-28',NULL,'Patricia.szczerba','(321)543-9978','patricia.szczerba@ucf.edu','patricia szczerba','Publish',1),(1915,'Become Fiber Optics Certified. Courses Begin in April.','become-fiber-optics-certified-courses-begin-in-april','<p>UCF Continuing Education is proud to offer Fiber Optics certification courses approved and recognized nationwide and internationally by the Fiber Optics Association (FOA), BICSI, and the World-Wide Consortium on Network Cabling Standards. Register today to ensure your spot in this expanding market. Certified Fiber Optics Technician Course CFOT is April 7-9, 2014, and registration is $700. Advanced Certified Fiber Optics Specialist in Testing and Maintenance Course CFOS/T is April 10-11, 2014, and registration is $675. Certified Fiber Optics Specialist in Outside Plant Cabling CFOS/O is April 14-15, 2014, and registration is $775. For more information call 407-882-0241 or email Erika.Nagy@ucf.edu.</p>','2014-02-17','2014-03-14','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics','Erika Nagy','(407)882-0241','Erika.Nagy@ucf.edu','Erika Nagy','Publish',1),(1916,'Online Healthcare Risk Management Licensure Course','online-healthcare-risk-management-licensure-course-1','<p>Continuing Education offers an entirely Online Health Care Risk Management Licensure Program. The 120 hour contact program is approved by the Agency for Health Care Administration and includes 60 hours of online self-paced lectures and 60 hours of homework, projects, and additional work as assigned. Final exam for licensure is included in the program. For more information on the eligibility requirements for the program, please contact the Agency for Health Care Administration (AHCA) at 850.412.4364  For complete program outlines, registration and more, visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement</a></p>','2014-02-17','2014-03-14','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement','Erika Nagy','(407)882-0241','Erika.Nagy@ucf.edu','Erika Nagy','Publish',1),(1917,'Gabor A & P Excellence Award (Call for nominations)','gabor-a-p-excellence-award-call-for-nominations','<p>The Gabor Award, which is sponsored by The GABOR Agency, was established to recognize and reward the outstanding job performance of a selected Administrative &amp; Professional (A&amp;P) employee. The honoree, selected annually, will be announced during the Annual Employee Awards Program, and will receive a check for $2500. </p>\n<p>To be nominated to receive this award, the employees must meet the following criteria:\n1.  The nominee must be employed in an established non-unit A&amp;P position. \n2.  The nominee must have a minimum of one (1) year of continuous university service. \n3.  The nominee’s contributions should exceed those that are expected of the employee during the normal course of performing his/her duties. \n4.  The nominee should demonstrate the high standards and excellence expressed in the UCF Mission, Vision and Goals. We encourage all nominators to keep the Mission, Vision, and Goals in mind when identifying individuals to be considered for this award. \n5.  Nominees may receive this award a maximum of one (1) time every five (5) years.</p>\n<p>The selected Gabor Award winner will be announced at the Annual Employee Awards Program in August 2013 and will receive a check for $2,500. All nominations must be received in Human Resources by May 9, 2014.</p>\n<p>To nominate an employee, please complete and submit a Gabor A&amp;P Excellence Award Nomination \n<a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/files/GABOR-Nomination-and-Criteria-form.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/files/GABOR-Nomination-and-Criteria-form.pdf</a>\nFor more information see <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/gabor-ap-excellence-award\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/gabor-ap-excellence-award</a>  .</p>\n<p>For questions, please contact Patty Farris in OD &amp; Training-Human Resources at (407) 823-0440 or OD&amp;Training@ucf.edu. </p>\n<p>Thanks again for your active participation in recognizing UCF\'s greatest asset, YOU!  </p>','2014-02-14','2014-05-08','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/gabor-ap-excellence-award','OD & Training ','(407)823-0440','od&training@ucf.edu','Patty Farris','Publish',1),(1918,'Life Coaching for Students Workshop','life-coaching-for-students-workshop','<p>The purpose of this life coaching workshop is to enhance students’ well-being through pursuing personal and professional goals.  Participants will identify areas of their lives that they want to enhance such as personal wellness, academic and career success, or time management.  Participants will then establish specific goals in these areas, learn strategies for achieving their goals, and be encouraged to take action steps toward making their vision a reality.<br>\nOnly 2 spots remaining for the Spring 2014 workshop which will begin soon.\nThis is a 6 session workshop held on Tuesdays, 3:00-4:30.\nInterested students must attend a pre-workshop screening.  For more information or to register, please call CAPS at 407-823-2811.</p>','2014-02-18','2014-02-24','http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/','Larry Marks, Ph.D.','(407)823-2811','Larry.Marks@ucf.edu','Larry Marks','Publish',1),(1919,'Lambda Theta Alpha Latin Sorority, Inc. presents: \"The Purge\"','lambda-theta-alpha-latin-sorority-inc-presents-the-purge','<p>\"What would you do if you had two hours to ask and answer anything related to your organization, council, and greek community?\"\nHave you ever had that one question you wanted to ask another council?\nDo you wish to see all four councils on UCF\'s campus come together for one common purpose?\nDo you want to let the community know the truth behind the ridiculous stereotypes your organization type receives?</p>\n<p>Come join Lta BetaTheta Chapter in the College of Sciences building room 101 as we host an OPEN discussion, better known as THE PURGE, to better understand our differences and use our similarities to come together. There will be topics discussed ranging from our different recruitment styles, our purposes, stereotypes (both positive and negative), and more!</p>\n<p>There will be a panel with representation from the different councils here at The University of Central Florida. The event is an OPEN discussion, in which the audience will partake in giving their own responses as well as an opportunity for an open floor of questions. This is your chance to get any questions or explanations off of your chest in a friendly environment. It is also a chance to get a better understanding of one another, and unite for a common purpose to bring together the Greek CommUNITY!</p>\n<p>When this is over, we will be able to say \"Unity is at an all time high due to one night in February where all questions were answered\".</p>\n<p>So....ARE YOU READY FOR THE PURGE?</p>\n<p>College of Sciences Building\nRoom 101\nDoors will open at 6:30pm !!!!!!!</p>\n<p>Any inquiries should be directed to Danielle Wormley at events.ltabetatheta@gmail.com or (856)5779069.</p>\n<p>Let\'s PURGE!</p>','2014-02-20','2014-02-25','https://www.facebook.com/events/422618731203463/','Danielle Wormley','(856)577-9069','events.ltabetatheta@gmail.com','Lambda Theta Alpha Latin Sorority, Incorporated Beta Theta Chapter','Publish',1),(1920,'Cyber Security Conference @UCF','cyber-security-conference-ucf','<p>The inaugural Cyber Security Conference @UCF will be held on Saturday, March 15, 2014 from 8:00 AM - 12:30 PM. The event will be held in the UCF College of Business (BA1, Room 119).</p>\n<p>Speakers will include Dr. Sheau-Dong Lang, Associate Professor and UCF\'s Digital Forensics Program Coordinator, Professor and Dean-Emeritus Jon Mills, Fredric G. Levin College of Law at the University of Florida, Sandra Osborne Digital Forensics Unit Orange County Sheriff\'s Office, and UCF students Kristen Pratt, Nasa Quba and Kausar Khizra.</p>\n<p>Continental Breakfast will be provided. This event is free and open to the public.</p>','2014-03-07','2014-03-14','http://msdf.ucf.edu/cybersecurity/index.html','Dr. Lang','(407)823-2474','slang@ucf.edu','slang@ucf.edu','Publish',1),(1921,'Professional HR Management - Saturday course starting March 15 in Research Park','professional-hr-management-saturday-course-starting-march-15-in-research-park','<p>UCF Continuing Education offers human resources management training whether you are at the start of your HR career or a seasoned professional. </p>\n<p>-START: Build a foundation in human resources with our Essentials of Human Resources Management and HR Generalist Certificate programs. These entirely online courses are a convenient way to learn the fundamentals and achieve a certificate to attest to the knowledge acquired in the program. </p>\n<p>-CERTIFY: For professionals working in the field, let UCF guide you towards becoming PHR, SPHR or GPHR Certified. Instructor led courses are held in locations throughout Central Florida to accommodate busy schedules.  Courses use the SHRM Learning System for PHR/SPHR or GPHR Certification Preparation, offer structured learning with expert instructors, and provide an opportunity to network with peers for the best chance to pass the exam! \nCourses begin in Daytona on March 10th, Cocoa on March 11th and in Research Park on March 15th. </p>\n<p>-RENEW: Maintain your hard earned credential with recertification courses. UCF offers courses to help you earn recertification hours to keep your certification current. </p>\n<p>To start your career or certify the knowledge that you have in the field, visit us online at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm</a> or contact Sarah Faehnle at sfaehnle@ucf.edu. </p>','2014-03-01','2014-02-15','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm','Sarah Faehnle','(407)882-0237','sfaehnle@ucf.edu','Sarah Faehnle, UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(1922,'Certified Project Management (PMP) Training this Spring','certified-project-management-pmp-training-this-spring','<p>UCF Continuing Education offers two project management courses to bring you the programs right for your career and educational goals. Certified, industry expert facilitators bring real world experience to the classroom and utilize the latest curriculum with the 5th edition of the Project Management Body of Knowledge.  Participants have said that the \"training is incredibly helpful in understanding the key knowledge areas and processes required by PMI.” and the pass rate for first time takes is over 90%!</p>\n<p>Seats are still available in the 25 week Professional Certificate in Project Management that started on February 25th at UCF.  </p>\n<p>Two ten week intensive project management exam preparation courses will be offered in April.  The session in Research Park will begin on Thursday, April 3rd and the Cocoa session will begin on Wednesday, April 2nd.  </p>\n<p>For full schedule and more information, visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/pm\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/pm</a> or contact Sarah Faehnle at sfaehnle@ucf.edu.</p>','2014-03-01','2014-04-05','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/pm','Sarah Faehnle','(407)882-0237','sfaehnle@ucf.edu','Sarah Faehnle, UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(1923,'5th Annual UCF Book Festival','5th-annual-ucf-book-festival','<p>The 5th annual UCF Book Festival will be held at the CFE Arena on Saturday, April 5, 2014 from 9:00 a.m. – 3:30 p.m. The mission of the UCF Book Festival is to cultivate an interest and engagement in reading. Annually, the festival draws thousands of readers of all ages and features nationally recognized authors and illustrators, book signings and sales, vendors, book appraisals, and activities for all ages. This year’s festival features over 30 international, national, and local authors including Andre Dubus III, Mike Farrell, Capt. Luis Carlos Montalván, Chris Pavone, Avi, Nathan Holic, David James Poissant, Kristen Simmons, Hollis Wilder, and John Rivers. From popular children’s characters to author readings to book sales, join in a celebration of literacy!</p>\n<p>Free admission, free parking, and open to the public.</p>\n<p>The book festival is hosted by the UCF College of Education and Human Performance in association with the Morgridge International Reading Center. For more information on the festival and additional events connected to the UCF Book Festival, visit <a href=\"http://bookfestival.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bookfestival.ucf.edu</a></p>','2014-03-05','2014-04-05','http://bookfestival.ucf.edu','D\'Ann M. Rawlinson','(407)823-1642','D\'Ann.Rawlinson@ucf.edu','D\'Ann M. Rawlinson','Publish',1),(1924,'Save the Date: Florida Diversity and Leadership Conference April 3, 2014','save-the-date-florida-diversity-and-leadership-conference-april-3-2014','<p>Are you interested in diversity issues? Would you like to share your experiences and expertise with your peers statewide?\nIf so, then plan to attend the Florida Diversity and Leadership Conference on Thursday, April 3, 2014, at the Rosen Plaza — the theme, “Imagine Inclusion.” If you’d like to share your experiences, sign up to be a panelist. Currently, panelists are needed for all sessions, such as Multicultural Leadership Roundtable, Lean In and LGBTA Roundtable.\nThe one-day event will feature a keynote presentation by Tony Plana, actor and director, and multicultural leadership awards.\nRegistration is $249. Students receive a 50 percent discount. Group rate discounts are also available.\nFor more information, visit the National Diversity Council’s conference website at <a href=\"http://www.floridadiversityconference.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.floridadiversityconference.com</a>.\nIf you would like to be a panelist, contact Maria Cherjovsky, Assistant Director, Continuing Education, at mariac@ucf.edu or at extension 2-0247.</p>','2014-03-07','2014-04-02','http://www.floridadiversityconference.com/','Maria Cherjovsky','(407)882-0247','mariac@ucf.edu','Erika Nagy','Publish',1),(1925,'Life Coaching for Students Workshop','life-coaching-for-students-workshop-1','<p>The purpose of this life coaching workshop is to enhance students’ well-being through pursuing personal and professional goals.  Participants will identify areas of their lives that they want to enhance such as personal wellness, academic and career success, or time management.  Participants will then establish specific goals in these areas, learn strategies for achieving their goals, and be encouraged to take action steps toward making their vision a reality.<br>\nOnly 2 spots remaining for the Spring 2014 workshop which will begin soon!\nThis is a 6 session workshop held on Tuesdays, 3:00-4:30.\nInterested students must attend a pre-workshop screening.  For more information or to register, please call CAPS at 407-823-2811.</p>','2014-03-09','2014-03-15','http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/','Larry Marks, Ph.D.','(407)823-2811','Larry.Marks@ucf.edu','Larry Marks, Ph.D.','Publish',1),(1926,'Leadership Enhancement Program Applications - deadline 3/21/14','leadership-enhancement-program-applications-deadline-32114','<p>The Office of Diversity Initiatives is currently taking applications for the 2014-2015 Leadership Enhancement Program. Please download the application and instructions from the Web site <a href=\"http://www.diversity.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.diversity.ucf.edu</a>. Signed and dated applications should be sent to the Office of Diversity Initiatives, 12424 Research Parkway, Suite 169, by noon, Friday, March 21, 2013.   For more information, contact Carmen I. Afonso by phone 407-823-3643 or email her at carmen.afonso@ucf.edu.</p>','2014-03-13','2014-03-21','http://www.diversity.ucf.edu','Carmen I. Afonso','(407)823-3643','carmen.afonso@ucf.edu','Carmen I. Afonso','Publish',1),(1927,'Movie at MIRC - Free Private Screening of TEACH directed by Davis Guggenheim','movie-at-mirc-free-private-screening-of-teach-directed-by-davis-guggenheim','<p>Movie at MIRC - Free Private Screening and Panel Discussion Presented by the University of Central Florida\'s College of Education and Human Performance</p>\n<p>We all have had a teacher who\'s shaped us, inspired us, even scared us, and whom we can credit with having empowered us to become who we are today. In his third documentary to look at education in America, Davis Guggenheim brings us \"TEACH,\" which asks the question: what does it take to be a teacher? Offering a glimpse inside four public school classrooms, Guggenheim invites us to follow the struggles and triumphs of America\'s education system through the eyes, minds and hearts of its most essential resource: teachers.</p>\n<p>When: Wednesday, April 2, 2014\nShow Times: 11:00 AM - 1:30 PM and 2:30 PM - 5:00 PM\nWhere: UCF\'s Morgridge International Reading Center</p>\n<p>Join us for a free viewing of TEACH following by a panel discussion. Free popcorn and beverages will be served. RSVP to guarantee a seat:   <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_4INFzdAl74lmsTj\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_4INFzdAl74lmsTj</a></p>\n<p>Directed by Davis Guggenheim\nRunning Time: 85 minutes</p>\n<p>To view the trailer, visit: <a href=\"https://participant.wiredrive.com/present-project-detail/token/e3319444a58569184f51c4d8d9fa978a\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://participant.wiredrive.com/present-project-detail/token/e3319444a58569184f51c4d8d9fa978a</a></p>','2014-03-13','2014-04-01','http://ucf.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_4INFzdAl74lmsTj','Dr. Bryan Zugelder',NULL,'bryan.zugelder@ucf.edu','D\'Ann M. Rawlinson','Publish',1),(1928,'Harvard Professor Tom Conley to Speak at UCF on Wednesday','harvard-professor-tom-conley-to-speak-at-ucf-on-wednesday','<p>Tom Conley, who is the Lowell Professor in the Departments of Romance Languages and Visual and Environmental Studies at Harvard University, will present \"The Cartographic Imagination from the Early Modern to the Post-Modern,\" on Wednesday, March 19th, from 6:00-7:00 p.m., in the FCTL (Faculty Center for Teaching and Learning), Classroom Building 1, Room 205. Conley studies relations of space and writing in literature, cartography, and cinema and has won a Guggenheim\nFellowship for his work in topography and literature in Renaissance France. His work moves to and from early modern France and issues in theory and interpretation in visual media. This presentation is sponsored by the Texts &amp; Technology Ph.D. Program, the Department of English, and The UCF Center for Humanities &amp; DigitalResearch.</p>','2014-03-14','2014-03-19',NULL,'Barry Mauer','(407)683-4790','bmauer@ucf.edu','Barry Mauer','Publish',1),(1929,'DiversiTea: Civil Rights in Central Florida','diversitea-civil-rights-in-central-florida','<p>Join us in welcoming Sara Van Arsdel and Claudine Tomlinson-Burney from the Orange County Regional History Center as they share stories about the impact of the signing of the 1964 Civil Rights Act on the local Central Florida area.\nThursday, March 27, 2014\n12:00 Noon - 1:30 PM\nCareer Services Room 121\nRSVP to diverse@ucf.edu\nby Monday, March 24, 2014.</p>','2014-03-14','2014-03-27','http://www.diversity.ucf.edu/diversiTea.asp','Dayanara Hudson','(407)823-4112','Dayanara.Hudson@ucf.edu','Dayanara Hudson','Publish',1),(1930,'2014 Diversity Week Student Poster Contest','2014-diversity-week-student-poster-contest','<p>“Remember and Reflect – The Civil Rights Act of 1964”\nWe invite you to be part of the activities commemorating 50 years since the signing of the Civil Rights Act by designing a poster for Diversity Week 2014.\nFIRST PLACE PRIZE:\n$500\nMass reproduction and distribution of your creation in the UCF and Central Florida communities\nRecognition on the ODI website and in the Diversity Breakfast Program\nFor complete contest details and applicable contest rules please visit: <a href=\"http://www.diversity.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.diversity.ucf.edu</a>.\nDeadline: April 1, 2014</p>','2014-03-01','2014-04-01','http://www.diversity.ucf.edu','Dayanara Hudson','(407)823-4112','Dayanara.Hudson@ucf.edu','Dayanara Hudson','Publish',1),(1931,'16th Annual Literacy Symposium: Informational Text in the Age of New Educational Standards','16th-annual-literacy-symposium-informational-text-in-the-age-of-new-educational-standards','<p>Join us for a FREE day of professional development, fun, and learning that will focus on celebrating literacy and learning more about: Informational Text and Common Core State Standards and Instruction in K-12 Grades, quality literacy instruction, literacy in the disciplines, reading and writing, vocabulary and comprehension, coaching, literature, assessment, literacy leadership, and technology for students in grades K-12.</p>\n<p>Keynote Marc Aronson, Ph.D. from Rutgers University presents Why is Nonfiction Defined by What it Isn\'t? 10 Questions to Help You Rethink and Re-Imagine Informational Text.</p>\n<p>Date: Friday, April 11, 2014\nTime: 8:30 am - 3:30 pm\nLocation: UCF College of Education and Human Performance (Education Complex)\nTo register, please visit the <a href=\"http://education.ucf.edu/LitSymposium/index.cfm\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Literacy Symposium website</a>.</p>','2014-03-14','2014-04-11','http://www.education.ucf.edu/LitSymposium/index.cfm','Vicky Zygouris-Coe, Ph.D.',NULL,'vzygouri@ucf.edu','D\'Ann Rawlinson','Publish',1),(1932,'Recreation and Wellness Center Job Fair','recreation-and-wellness-center-job-fair','<p>March 19\n10:00am - 12:00pm</p>\n<p>March 20\n2:00pm - 4:00pm</p>\n<p>Joins us and come learn more about the positions at the RWC! These are informal, informational sessions but we highly encourage you to attend. Positions will be available for Summer and Fall. To apply, please submit your application, resume and cover letter. Job areas include:</p>\n<p>Marketing\nFitness\nSport Clubs\nAquatics\nMember Services\nIntramural Sports\nRWC Park\nOutdoor Adventure\nBuilding Manager</p>\n<p>The job fair begins in Room 206 at the RWC where you\'ll learn a little more about the RWC. After that drop of your cover letters, resumes and applications and meet our staff from all the program areas at the table set up in the main lobby. Opportunities for our International Students as well. See you there!</p>\n<p>For more information contact:\nScott Mauro\nRWC Marketing and Communications Manager\n407-823-2408\nscott.mauro@ucf.edu</p>','2014-03-19','2014-03-21','http://rec.ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','(407)823-2408','scott.mauro@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro, RWC Marketing and Communication Manager','Publish',1),(1933,'The Latest Issue of Pegasus Magazine: It\'s Everything you Love about UCF.','the-latest-issue-of-pegasus-magazine-its-everything-you-love-about-ucf','<p><a href=\"http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/\" rel=\"nofollow\">This issue is all about the gold standard</a>:</p>\n<p>To Coach George O’Leary, it’s recruiting the right student (<a href=\"http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/ucf-knights-2013-2014-football-season/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/ucf-knights-2013-2014-football-season/</a>). Good students listen, work hard, persevere and graduate. This year, the UCF football team has the highest graduation rate compared to other teams in The Associated Press’ Top 10.</p>\n<p>For Theatre UCF Chair Christopher Niess, opening night is the gold standard (<a href=\"http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/theatre-ucf-presents-nicholas-nickleby/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/theatre-ucf-presents-nicholas-nickleby/</a>). Theatre UCF and Orlando Shakespeare Theater worked for more than two years to premiere “The Life and Adventures of Nicholas Nickleby,” a 6-hour play.</p>\n<p>For freshman Ben Carpenter (<a href=\"http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/disabled-students-overcome-challenges-of-college/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/disabled-students-overcome-challenges-of-college/</a>), the gold standard requires gauging his on-campus activities so his battery-powered wheelchair will make it home to his dorm after classes.</p>\n<p>These stories, plus photos, alumni profiles and more at <a href=\"http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/</a></p>','2014-03-24','2014-03-31','http://www.ucf.edu/pegasus/','Pegasus Magazine',NULL,'pegasus@ucf.edu','UCF Marketing','Publish',1),(1934,'Life Coaching for Students','life-coaching-for-students-1','<p>The purpose of this 6 session life coaching workshop is to enhance students’ well-being through pursuing personal and professional goals. Participants will identify areas of their lives that they want to enhance such as personal wellness, academic and career success, or time management. Participants will then establish specific goals in these areas, learn strategies for achieving their goals, and be encouraged to take action steps toward making their vision a reality.\nThere are only 2 spots remaining for this workshop!\nThe workshop will be held on Tuesdays, 3:00-4:30 and begin soon.\nStudent must register in advance and attend a pre-workshop screening.</p>','2014-02-11','2014-04-21','http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu','Larry Marks','(407)823-2811','Larry.Marks@ucf.edu','Larry Marks','Publish',1),(1935,'2014 USPS Staff Assembly','2014-usps-staff-assembly','<p>Annual USPS Staff Assembly and Fundraiser\nThe Annual USPS Staff Assembly and Fundraiser will be held on Wednesday, April 16, from 9:30 to 11:30 a.m. in the Student Union Cape Florida Ballroom 316 A-D.\nIt is that time of year again to get UCF updates and address our administration with questions, concerns, or issues. The guest speaker is Mr. Todd Stansbury, Vice President and Director of Athletics. Other speakers at this year’s event will be Mr. William Merck, Vice President for Administration and Finance and Chief Financial Officer and our new Associate Vice President and Chief Human Resources Officer, Mr. Marvin Pyles. If you would like to submit questions in advance to any of our speakers, please submit them to joanne.mccully@ucf.edu by April 11.\nFor those staff members who are unable to attend the Staff Assembly, you may view a live internet broadcast at <a href=\"http://webcast.oir.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://webcast.oir.ucf.edu</a>.\nFUNDRAISING EVENT - Everyone is invited to participate!\nYou may view auction items and buy advance tickets for the auction starting Tuesday, April 8, from 8 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the front desk of the College of Sciences Room 201, their phone is 407-823-1997. Tickets will also be available for purchase on April 16, beginning at 8:45 a.m. in the Cape Florida Ballroom. For additional information go to our website at <a href=\"http://www.ucf.edu/uspsstaff\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ucf.edu/uspsstaff</a> and click on 2014 Staff Assembly Auction Items.\nPlease contact Joanne McCully for questions about the USPS Staff Assembly at joanne.mccully@ucf.edu.</p>','2014-04-04','2014-04-17','http://www.ucf.edu/uspsstaff','Marvin Pyles','(407)823-0425','Maryann.parker@ucf.edu','Mary Ann Parker','Publish',1),(1936,'2014-2015 Technology Fee Proposal Preparation Workshop ','2014-2015-technology-fee-proposal-preparation-workshop','<p>Information Technologies and Resources (IT&amp;R) will conduct a technology fee proposal preparation workshop on Thursday, April 17, 2014, at 1:00 p.m., in the Teaching Academy, room 130. Individuals considering submitting technology fee proposals for 2014-2015 are invited to attend. This session will address the process and review of the guidelines to assist submitters with writing a competitive proposal.</p>','2014-04-08','2014-04-17','http://itr.ucf.edu/TechFee/index.asp','Karen Cobbs','(407)823-0256','cobbs@ucf.edu','Karen Cobbs','Publish',1),(1937,'Service-Learning Student Showcase 2014','service-learning-student-showcase-2014','<p>Come and celebrate with us as students showcase 66 service-learning community-based projects. Pegasus Ballroom on Thursday, April 10 from 10:30 AM-3:30 PM.</p>','2014-04-10','2014-04-10',NULL,'Amy Zeh','(407)823-4395','Amy.Zeh@ucf.edu','Amy Zeh','Publish',1),(1938,'Leadercast UCF: Be A Leader Worth Following','leadercast-ucf-be-a-leader-worth-following','<p>Leadercast exists to positively change the way the world thinks about leadership. This year’s theme – Beyond You – challenges leaders to focus outward rather than inward. Leadercast UCF broadcasts LIVE the following speakers:</p>\n<p>•   Andy Stanley – Leadership Communicator and Best-Selling Author\n•   Malcolm Gladwell – Award-Winning Journalist and Best-Selling Author\n•   Archbishop Desmond Tutu – Nobel Laureate &amp; Human Rights Activist\n•   Randall Wallace – Screenwriter, Director, Producer and Songwriter\n•   Bill McDermott – CEO of SAP AG\n•   Laura Schroff – Former Advertising Sales Executive &amp; Best-Selling Author\n•   Dr. Henry Cloud – Clinical Psychologist and Leadership Consultant\n•   Simon Sinek – Leadership Expert and Best-Selling Author\n•   Laura Bush – First Lady of the United States (2001-2009)</p>\n<p>Date: Friday, May 9, 2014\nTime: 8:30 am – 4:30 pm\nLocation: UCF FAIRWINDS Alumni Center\nTo register, please visit the Leadercast UCF website.\nFacebook Page: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/leadercastucf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.facebook.com/leadercastucf</a> </p>','2014-04-10','2014-05-09','http://hr.ucf.edu/leadercast/','UCF HR OD&T','(407)823-0440','od&training@ucf.edu','UCF HR OD&T','Publish',1),(1939,'Spend 3 days at UCF and Become Fiber Optics Certified','spend-3-days-at-ucf-and-become-fiber-optics-certified','<p>UCF Continuing Education is proud to offer Fiber Optics certification courses approved and recognized nationwide and internationally by the Fiber Optics Association (FOA) and BICSI, the World-Wide Consortium on Network Cabling Standards. Register today to ensure your spot in this expanding market. Certified Fiber Optics Technician Course CFOT is July 14-16, 2014, and registration is $700. Advanced Certified Fiber Optics Specialist in Testing and Maintenance Course CFOS/T is July 17-18, 2014, and registration is $675. Advanced Certified Fiber Optics Splicing Specialist Course CFOS/S is July 21-22, 2014, and registration is $675. For more information call 407-882-0241 or email Erika.Nagy@ucf.edu Visit us on the web at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics</a></p>','2014-04-23','2014-05-07','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics','Erika Nagy','(407)882-0241','erika.nagy@ucf.edu','Erika Nagy','Publish',1),(1940,'Celebrate World Intellectual Property Day','celebrate-world-intellectual-property-day','<p>Visit the library and become better familiar with the differences between the different types of intellectual property - patents, trademarks and copyrighted items. Examples of each will be on display until May 5, on the second floor of the John C. Hitt Library, across from the Research and Information Services Desk in the Knowledge Commons.</p>','2014-04-24','2014-05-04',NULL,'Terri Gotschall','(407)765-6610','terri.gotschall@ucf.edu','Terri Gotschall','Publish',1),(1941,'MFRI 10 Year Celebration Event: MAY 17th, 6:30-10:30 pm','mfri-10-year-celebration-event-may-17th-630-1030-pm','<p>The UCF Marriage and Family Research Institute (MFRI) was created in 2003 with a mission to facilitate the development of research and clinical initiatives to better support couples, marriages, and families. The Institute conducts original research and promotes scholarly activity of faculty and graduate students interested in marriage, family, and child issues. Additionally, the Institute provides outcomes and process evaluation services for other research projects that are part of and independent of the Institute. </p>\n<p>This banquet event will celebrate and honor the excellence in achievement, spanning 10 years of past and present staff as well as partnerships supporting the Institute’s success. Join us for a night with two keynote speakers, Dr. Howard Markman and Dr. Ryan Carlson, and presentations highlighting our research.</p>\n<p>DATE: May 17th, 2014\nREGISTRATION: <a href=\"http://mfri.ucf.edu/email/celebration/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://mfri.ucf.edu/email/celebration/</a>\nTICKETS: $38 per person\nLOCATION: Radisson- UCF (<a href=\"http://www.radisson.com/orlando-hotel-fl-32826/florluni\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.radisson.com/orlando-hotel-fl-32826/florluni</a>)</p>','2014-05-17','2014-05-17','http://mfri.ucf.edu/email/celebration/','Naomi Wheeler','(407)823-1748','mfri@ucf.edu','MFRI: YC','Publish',1),(1942,'Online Healthcare Risk Management Licensure Course','online-healthcare-risk-management-licensure-course-1-2','<p>Continuing Education offers an entirely Online Health Care Risk Management Licensure Program. The 120 hour contact program is approved by the Agency for Health Care Administration and includes 60 hours of online self-paced lectures and 60 hours of homework, projects, and additional work as assigned. Final exam for licensure is included in the program. For more information on the eligibility requirements for the program, please contact the Agency for Health Care Administration (AHCA) at 850.412.4364. For complete program outlines, registration and more, visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement</a></p>','2014-04-28','2014-05-30','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/riskmanagement','Erika Nagy','(407)882-0241','erika.nagy@ucf.edu','Erika Nagy','Publish',1),(1943,'Photonics Certificate Program','photonics-certificate-program','<p>In partnership with the Society of Photo-Optical Instrumentation Engineers (SPIE), UCF Continuing Education offers the Photonics Certificate Program designed for anyone interested in gaining knowledge in the Photonics field and in earning a certificate. The Photonics Certificate Program consists of six online courses and one hands-on lab that prepares participants for the growing Photonics field. For complete program outlines, registration and more, visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Photonics\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Photonics</a></p>','2014-04-28','2014-05-30','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Photonics','Erika Nagy','(407)882-0241','erika.nagy@ucf.edu','Erika Nagy','Publish',1),(1944,'Brain, Sex, and Intimacy workshop: 6:00-8:00 pm','brain-sex-and-intimacy-workshop-600-800-pm','<p>Through recent advances in brain research, we are learning more specific information on our brain’s role in desire, intimacy, and sexuality.</p>\n<p>Participants in this interactive presentation will learn how to apply some of this new information and research to strengthen and deepen intimacy, increase desire within your relationship, enhance sexuality, prevent infidelity, and find or keep those butterflies alive in your relationship.</p>\n<p>FACILITATOR: Andrew P. Daire, Ph.D., LMHC; Professor &amp; Associate Dean for Research\nLOCATION: UCF Marriage &amp; Family Research Institute, building number 28 (Early Childhood), next to the Wellness Center and the tennis courts</p>\n<p>• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• This workshop is open to the Central Florida Community at no cost to participants.\nSpace is limited, please RSVP by calling 407.823.1748.</p>','2014-04-29','2014-05-20','https://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1945,'Money Matters (workshop): 10:00 am-12:00 pm','money-matters-workshop-1000-am-1200-pm','<p>The Money Matters module shows participants how to manage their money by preparing a personal spending plan and identifying ways to decrease spending and increase income.</p>\n<p>LOCATION: MFRI South, 7200 Lake Ellenor Drive, Orlando FL 32809 </p>\n<p>• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• This workshop is open to the Central Florida Community at no cost to participants.\n*Registration is required. Call 407.823.1748 to register.</p>','2014-03-05','2014-03-05','https://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1946,'Cuestiones de Dinero (taller): Mayo 31, de 10:00am a 12:00pm','cuestiones-de-dinero-taller-mayo-31-de-1000am-a-1200pm','<p>El taller Cuestiones de Dinero muestra a los participantes cómo administrar su dinero mediante la preparación de un plan de gastos personal y la identificación de maneras para reducir gastos y aumentar su ingreso.\nLOCATION: MFRI South, 7200 Lake Ellenor Drive, Orlando FL 32809</p>\n<p>• Eligibilidad: Tener 18 años de edad para participar.\n• Gratuíto para la comunidad de la Florida central.\n*El espacio es limitado, llame al 407.823.1748 para reservar.</p>','2014-04-30','2014-05-31','https://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1947,'May 2014 USPS Employee of the Month','may-2014-usps-employee-of-the-month','<p>Please join us in congratulating our newest USPS Employee of the Month for May, Jim Sullivan. </p>\n<p>Jim is a Maintenance Specialist at the Recreation &amp; Wellness Center. He has been described by his nominators as having “one of the most positive attitudes regarding his work duties combined with an extremely great work ethic that makes him a phenomenal employee. He has the responsibility for maintaining a 150,000 sq. foot indoor recreation facility along with an 8,800 square foot satellite facility.  Lastly, he is “an employee who is enthusiastic each day (and) boosts the morale of all the other team members.” </p>\n<p>We\'d like to thank this outstanding employee for his dedication and hard work. We\'d also like to recognize their nominators who took the time to recognize outstanding efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>In addition to a one-time $200 cash award, a UCF Business Services (on campus vendor) $25 gift certificate, introduction to UCF’s Board of Trustees, marquee announcement, goody bag, certificate and surprise presentation, Jim is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year award, which is announced annually at the Employee Awards Program. One of the 12 USPS Employees of Month will be named Employee of the Year and will receive a $2,500 check. If you would like to nominate a USPS employee, the EOM nomination packet is available in hard copy format (<a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOMNom.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOMNom.pdf</a> )or via electronic submission visit (<a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/3JDGMKY\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/3JDGMKY</a> ) . On this same webpage, you will also find a complete list of prizes the USPS Employee of the Month receives. The USPS Employee of the Month is selected by a committee comprised of Staff, Administrative &amp; Professional and Faculty employees. If you have questions about the USPS Employee of the Month process, please call 407-823-0440.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Jim Sullivan! </p>','2014-05-06','2014-05-31','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-month/','OD & Training ','(407)823-0440','od&training@ucf.edu','Patty Farris','Publish',1),(1948,'Own a Piece of UCF Football History! \"A Season to Remember\" Books on Sale Now!','own-a-piece-of-ucf-football-history-a-season-to-remember-books-on-sale-now','<p>A LIMITED supply of “A Season to Remember” 2013 UCF Football books are now on sale through May 30th or until sell-out (whichever comes first).  This is a 145+ page photo book of the 2013-2014 season from the first day of pre-season camp, kick-off luncheon, spirit splash, through each game, the Fiesta Bowl victory, and culminating with the celebration at Disney.  This is a terrific memento of an amazing season and one that every fan may cherish for years to come.  </p>\n<p>Price is $50 per book (this includes tax &amp; shipping) with proceeds going to the UCF Lettermen’s Club.  Books are expected to ship on approximately June 2, 2014.  </p>','2014-05-07','2014-05-30','http://www.ucfknights.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/043014aab.html','Kristy Belden','(407)823-3241','kbelden@athletics.ucf.edu','Kristy Belden, UCF Football','Publish',1),(1949,'Employee Tuition Waiver Program and Taxation','employee-tuition-waiver-program-and-taxation-1-2','<p>In preparation for the summer 2014 semester, please be reminded that UCF employees can claim up to $5,250 in tax-free educational benefits for graduate level and\nhigher coursework (section 127, Internal Revenue Code). Please be advised that the value of the benefit in excess of $5,250 will be taxed at the supplemental tax\nrate (25%) for federal withholding, plus the appropriate Social Security and Medicare tax rates. Those taxes will be deducted from your paycheck(s) and be\nincluded on your Form W-2.</p>\n<p>The university does not provide tax advice. If you have questions about this information, please contact a tax professional.</p>\n<p>Non-tax related questions regarding the educational benefits addressed above may be directed to Payroll Services by emailing payroll@ucf.edu or calling\n(407) 823-2771 .</p>','2014-08-05','2014-12-05',NULL,'Payroll Services','(407)823-2771','payroll@ucf.edu','Isha Guerrero-Londeree','Publish',1),(1950,'Graduate Student Center- Your Space On Campus','graduate-student-center-your-space-on-campus','<p>The Graduate Student Center, located in Colbourn Hall, Suite 146, is a friendly place on campus to study and do research. The Center provides space for graduate students to engage in: </p>\n<p>•   Professional development workshops \n•   Rehearsal of presentations \n•   Final defense of thesis or dissertation research \n•   Guest lectures and colloquia series \n•   Study and collaboration</p>\n<p>Additionally, the Center’s PC computers have Microsoft Office 2010, Origin 8.6, Adobe Master Collections CS 5.5, SPSS, Amos, LaTex, ArcGIS, Camtasia, Chem Bio Office, GAUSS, Interactive Data Language, Mat Lab, Nvio, SAS, STATA, UCINET, VLC Media Player, MAGic, JAWS, and Google SketchUp. </p>\n<p>Summer hours for the Graduate Student Center are as follows:</p>\n<p>Monday-Thursday: 1:00pm-6:00pm\nFriday: 1:00pm-4:00pm\nSaturday-Sunday: CLOSED</p>\n<p>When planning your visit to the Graduate Student Center don’t forget to bring paper to print and/or scan unlimitedly in the computer labs. Also, take a look at the events calendar for upcoming graduate events and workshops. Room reservations are available for your graduate student group meetings at <a href=\"http://www.students.graduate.ucf.edu/Events\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.students.graduate.ucf.edu/Events</a>.</p>\n<p>We look forward to seeing you here!</p>','2014-05-08','2014-08-15','http://www.graduate.ucf.edu/gradcenter','Graduate Student Center Assistants','(407)823-4689','gradcenter@ucf.edu','Graduate Student Center ','Publish',1),(1951,'Summer Institute @ UCF','summer-institute-ucf','<p>The University of Central Florida is dedicated to providing science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) related summer opportunities for area middle and high school students. The Summer Institute (SI) currently offers tracks in Computer Science and Physics. Each track offers a mix of activities designed to maximize learning through hands-on, individualized instruction with outstanding instructors. The Physics camp runs June 23-27, 2014 and the Computer Science (Cryptography) camp runs July 7-25, 2014. For complete information on these valuable summer camp opportunities, please contact UCF Continuing Education at 407-882-0264 or ce@ucf.edu.</p>','2014-05-12','2014-06-01','http://siucf.cs.ucf.edu/','Kourtney Dinkins','(407)882-0260','kourtney.dinkins@ucf.edu','Kourtney Dinkins','Publish',1),(1952,'Book Drive Extension','book-drive-extension','<p>Books in support of the United Way\'s summer literacy initiatives are needed by 4 p.m. on  June 4th.   Please bring in new and like new condition books, levels K-12, and turn in to Millican Hall suite 384.  </p>\n<p>The is the UCF United Way Campaign Team\'s 2nd annual book drive in support of the United Way\'s Day of Action literacy initiative. This effort is in response to research about summer reading loss and the impact of summer months on the educational progress of disadvantaged youth.  The Day of Action volunteer initiative and book distribution will take place on June 23 - visit <a href=\"http://hfuw.org/Day_of_Action.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hfuw.org/Day_of_Action.php</a> if you would like to volunteer.</p>','2014-05-29','2014-06-05','http://ucf.edu/liveunited/2014_BookDrive.pdf','Tee Rogers','(407)823-3094','tee.rogers@ucf.edu','UCF United Way Camapign','Publish',1),(1953,'HR Certification Announcement','hr-certification-announcement','<p>The Society for Human Resources Management (SHRM) recently announced a new competency based certification for HR professionals that will be offered starting in Spring 2015.   UCF Continuing Education will be launching preparatory courses for this new certification in Spring 2015 utilizing the updated, interactive online learning system platform from SHRM.</p>\n<p>In the meantime, we encourage those that are considering becoming PHR or SPHR Certified in 2014 to continue their path towards certification. UCF’s Fall 2014 courses will use the 2014 SHRM Learning System to prepare participants for the PHR and SPHR examinations. </p>\n<p>For more information on the PHR and SPHR preparatory courses for Fall, please visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1256/Shrm---Professional-Human-Resources-Exam-Preparation-Phrsphr/#phr\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1256/Shrm---Professional-Human-Resources-Exam-Preparation-Phrsphr/#phr</a> </p>\n<p>For those seeking an introduction to the field of HR, we offer a series of courses to help you gain an in-depth understanding of the field.  Visit  <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm</a> for more information.</p>','2014-06-04','2014-06-30','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm','Sarah Faehnle','(407)882-0237','Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu','Sarah Faehnle, UCF Continuing Education Coordinator','Publish',1),(1954,'Engineering and Quality Certification Preparation this June','engineering-and-quality-certification-preparation-this-june','<p>UCF Continuing Education is proud to now offer three of the American Society for Quality (ASQ) certification preparation courses including the Certified Reliability Engineer (CRE), Certified Quality Engineer (CQE), and the Certified Quality Improvement Associate (CQIA) in partnership with UCF’s College of Industrial Engineering and Management Systems.  </p>\n<p>ASQ is the leader in certification standards for the field of quality and reliability engineering.  Having an ASQ Certification “demonstrates that the certified individual has the knowledge to assure quality of products and services” and is an “investment in your career and in the future of your employer”1.  Not only does ASQ certification offer personal satisfaction, but it also provides for increased income and promotion possibilities and increases the odds of employment2.  Interested participants may visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/asq\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/asq</a> to learn more about the CRE, CQE and CQIA certification preparation programs or visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/News/172/New-Engineering-And-Quality-Certifications/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/News/172/New-Engineering-And-Quality-Certifications/</a> to continue reading about these new programs offered this June. </p>','2014-06-04','2014-06-30','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/asq','Sarah Faehnle','(407)882-0237','Sarah.Faehnle@ucf.edu','Sarah Faehnle, UCF Continuing Education Coordinator ','Publish',1),(1955,'22nd Annual UCF Diversity Week','22nd-annual-ucf-diversity-week','<p>Celebrating and Commemorating Remember and Reflect - The Civil Rights Act of 1964.\nFrom Monday, October 13 through Friday October 17, 2014, a series of events, presentations and programs will take place across the UCF campus. Each will highlight the diverse population that makes up our UCF Family.</p>','2014-09-05','2014-10-20','http://www.diversity.ucf.edu/diversity_week.asp','Katie Pomp','(407)823-6740','katie.pomp@ucf.edu','Dayanara Hudson','Publish',1),(1956,'Prom Night In Mississippi Film Presentation','prom-night-in-mississippi-film-presentation','<p>Join us on Monday, October 20, from 3-6PM in the Student Union\'s Cape Florida Room, for a presentation of the film that captured history in the making. Director/Producer Paul Saltzman takes viewers through conversations with senior students as they prepare to attend their first “mixed prom” in Tallahatchie County, Mississippi in 2008, after the screening, stay for a briefing of the film with Paul Saltzman.</p>','2014-09-09','2014-10-20','http://www.diversity.ucf.edu/index.asp','Katie Pomp','(407)823-6740','katie.pomp@ucf.edu','Dayanara Hudson','Publish',1),(1957,'Engineering Summer Camp at UCF ','engineering-summer-camp-at-ucf','<p>The College of Engineering and Computer Science Office of Diversity and Inclusion is gearing up to host its summer camp, Camp Connect I, during the week of July 14-18, 2014 at the University of Central Florida. </p>\n<p>Camp Connect I is a computer science/engineering-based camp designed to encourage problem solving, self-efficacy and collaboration in computer science and engineering through hands-on activities, team projects, lab tours, and meet and greet sessions with student, faculty and industry leaders.</p>\n<p>One of the goals of Camp Connect I is to create a diverse and inclusive pipeline for future Knights within the College of Engineering and Computer Science. Consequently, Camp Connect I targets rising 8th to 10th graders from underrepresented and underprivileged communities, but it is open to all.  </p>\n<p>If you are interested in being part of the program as a volunteer or know someone who might be interested in being a participant, please contact the Office of Diversity and Inclusion today!</p>','2014-07-14','2014-07-18','http://www.diversity.cecs.ucf.edu/campconnect/  ','LeeAnn Roberts or Perlee Davis','(407)823-3466','diversitycecs@ucf.edu','The College of Engineering and Computer Science Office of Diversity and Inclusion','Publish',1),(1958,'COUPLES CAFE -English: Saturday, June 21 from 2:00-4:00 pm','couples-cafe-english-saturday-june-21-from-200-400-pm','<p>Discover ways to enhance your relationship and intimacy. Learn your love language, and explore how to keep the butterflies alive in your relationship.</p>\n<p>This workshop will focus on assisting individuals and couples to understand other’s unique needs and “speak” the partner’s love language using the Five Love Languages* model which include: Words of Affirmation, Quality Time, Gifts, Act of Services, and Physical Touch.</p>\n<p>Combine your love language with practical ways to express your love!</p>\n<p>&gt; Registration is required. Call 407.823.1748 to register.\n• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• This workshop is open to the Central Florida Community at no cost to participants.\nLOCATION: MFRI South Office, 7200 Lake Ellenor Drive, Suite 205, Orlando, FL 32809</p>\n<p>*The Five Love Languages by @DrGaryChapman is property of Northfield Publishing.</p>','2014-06-16','2014-06-21','https://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1959,'Money Matters, Friday June 20 from 6:00-8:00 pm','money-matters-friday-june-20-from-600-800-pm','<p>The Money Matters module shows participants how to manage their money by preparing a personal spending plan and identifying ways to decrease spending and increase income.</p>\n<p>*MUST call to register 407.823.1748.\n• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• This workshop is open to the Central Florida Community at no cost to participants.\nLOCATION: MFRI South Office, 7200 Lake Ellenor Drive, Suite 205, Orlando, FL 32809</p>','2014-06-16','2014-06-20','https://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1960,'Money Matters, Saturday June 21 from 10:00 am - noon','money-matters-saturday-june-21-from-1000-am-noon','<p>The Money Matters module shows participants how to manage their money by preparing a personal spending plan and identifying ways to decrease spending and increase income.</p>\n<p>*MUST call to register 407.823.1748.\n• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• This workshop is open to the Central Florida Community at no cost to participants.\nLOCATION: MFRI Main Campus Office, University of Central Florida, 28 Gemini Blvd, Orlando, Florida 32826</p>','2014-06-16','2014-06-21','http://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1961,'Cuestiones de Dinero, Monday July 7 from 6:00-8:00 pm','cuestiones-de-dinero-monday-july-7-from-600-800-pm','<p>El taller Cuestiones de Dinero muestra a los participantes cómo administrar su dinero mediante la preparación de un plan de gastos personal y la identificación de maneras para reducir gastos y aumentar su ingreso.</p>\n<p>*El espacio es limitado, llame al 407.823.1748 para reservar.\n• Eligibilidad: Tener 18 años de edad para participar.\n• Gratuíto para la comunidad de la Florida central.</p>\n<p>LOCATION:   MFRI UCF Main Campus<em>, 28 Gemini Blvd., S.E., Building 28, Orlando FL 32826         </em>(Al lado del UCF Wellness Center)</p>','2014-06-17','2014-07-07','https://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1962,'Money Matters, Monday July 7 from 6:00-8:00 pm','money-matters-monday-july-7-from-600-800-pm','<p>The Money Matters module shows participants how to manage their money by preparing a personal spending plan and identifying ways to decrease spending and increase income.</p>\n<p>*MUST call to register 407.823.1748.\n• MUST be at least 18 years old to participate.\n• This workshop is open to the Central Florida Community at no cost to participants.</p>\n<p>LOCATION: MFRI South Office, 7200 Lake Ellenor Drive, Suite 205, Orlando, FL 32809</p>','2014-06-17','2014-07-07','http://www.facebook.com/MFRI.UCF/events','Sandy Griffith','(407)823-1748','Sandy-ann.griffith@ucf.edu','MFRI-YC','Publish',1),(1963,'STEM Summer Camps at UCF','stem-summer-camps-at-ucf','<p>The College of Engineering and Computer Science Office of Diversity and Inclusion is gearing up to host its summer camp, Camp Connect I, during the week of July 14-18, 2014 at the University of Central Florida. </p>\n<p>Camp Connect I is a computer science/engineering-based camp designed to encourage problem solving, self-efficacy and collaboration in computer science and engineering through hands-on activities, team projects, lab tours, and meet and greet sessions with student, faculty and industry leaders.</p>\n<p>One of the goals of Camp Connect I is to create a diverse and inclusive pipeline for future Knights within the College of Engineering and Computer Science. Consequently, Camp Connect I targets rising 8th to 10th graders from underrepresented and underprivileged communities, but it is open to all.  </p>\n<p>If you are interested in being part of the program as a volunteer or know someone who might be interested in being a participant, please contact the Office of Diversity and Inclusion via email at diversitycecs@ucf.edu.</p>','2014-07-14','2014-07-18','http://www.diversity.cecs.ucf.edu/campconnect/  ','LeeAnn Roberts','(407)823-6607','LeeAnn.Roberts@ucf.edu','College of Engineering and Computer Science Office of Diversity and Inclusion','Publish',1),(1964,'Mindful Eating Workshop on 7/2/14','mindful-eating-workshop-on-7214','<p>Learn how to slow down your eating, notice your hunger, and improve your relationship with food.</p>\n<p>This is a one time, 1 hour workshop presentation. All students are welcome.\nDate: Wednesday, 7/2/14\nLocation: Please come to Building #27 (<a href=\"http://map.ucf.edu/locations/27/counseling-center/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Counseling Center</a>)\nTime: 1pm-2pm</p>\n<p>For more information, please feel free to contact Megan Brault, MA or Candice Franco, Ph.D. at 407-823-2811.\nHope to see you there!</p>','2014-06-20','2014-07-03',NULL,'Megan Brault, MA','(407)823-2811','megan.brault@ucf.edu','Megan Brault, MA','Publish',1),(1965,'Pain and Stress Management Workshop on 7/9/14','pain-and-stress-management-workshop-on-7914','<p>Learn new skills to help cope with physical pain. \nFind balance and de-stress your busy lifestyle. </p>\n<p>This is a one time, 1 hour workshop presentation for students.\nNo sign-up necessary!</p>\n<p>Date: Wednesday, 7/9/14\nLocation: Building #27 (<a href=\"http://map.ucf.edu/locations/27/counseling-center/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Counseling Center</a>)\nTime:1pm-2pm</p>\n<p>Feel free to contact Candice Franco, PhD or Megan Brault, MA for more information.\nHope to see you there!</p>','2014-03-07','2014-10-07',NULL,'Megan Brault, MA','(407)823-2811','megan.brault@ucf.edu','Megan Brault, M.A.','Publish',1),(1966,'Being a Care-taker, and Caring for Yourself Workshop on 7/16/14','being-a-care-taker-and-caring-for-yourself-workshop-on-71614','<p>Learn ways to support yourself as you support others in your life. If you are living with your own health issues, learn to enhance your support systems.<br>\nThis is a one-time, 1 hour workshop presentation.\nNo sign-up necessary.</p>\n<p>Location: Building #27 (<a href=\"http://map.ucf.edu/locations/27/counseling-center/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Counseling Center</a>)\nDate: Wednesday, 7/16/14\nTime: 1pm-2pm</p>\n<p>All students welcome.\nPlease contact Candice Franco, PhD or Megan Brault, MA for more information</p>','2014-07-10','2014-07-17',NULL,'Megan Brault, MA','(407)823-2811','megan.brault@gmail.com','Megan Brault, MA','Publish',1),(1967,'HR Certification Courses this Fall','hr-certification-courses-this-fall','<p>UCF Continuing Education is pleased to provide human resources education to those new to HR or those preparing for HR Certifications.  </p>\n<p>The Society for Human Resources Management (SHRM) recently announced the new SHRM-CP and SHRM-SCP certifications for HR professionals that will begin in Spring 2015. UCF CE will be launching preparatory courses for this new certification in Spring 2015 utilizing the updated, interactive online learning system platform from SHRM.</p>\n<p>In the meantime, we encourage those that are considering becoming PHR or SPHR Certified in 2014 to continue their path towards certification. UCF’s Fall 2014 courses will use the 2014 SHRM Learning System to prepare participants for the PHR and SPHR examinations. </p>\n<p>For more information on the PHR and SPHR preparatory courses for Fall, please visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1256/Shrm—Professional-Human-Resources-Exam-Preparation-Phrsphr/#phr\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1256/Shrm—Professional-Human-Resources-Exam-Preparation-Phrsphr/#phr</a> </p>\n<p>For those seeking an introduction to the field of HR, we offer a series of courses to help you gain an in-depth understanding of the field. Visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm</a> for more information.</p>','2014-07-02','2014-07-31','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM','Sarah Faehnle, Coordinator of Continuing Education','(407)882-0237','sfaehnle@ucf.edu','Sarah Faehnle, Coordinator of Continuing Education','Publish',1),(1968,'Stress Management Workshop','stress-management-workshop','<p>Feeling Tired? Burned out? Experience aches and pains?\nCome learn great new strategies to manage stress in your every day life.\nLocated at the Counseling Center (Bldg #27) on 7/9/14 at 1pm-2pm.\nAll students welcome!</p>','2014-07-07','2014-07-09',NULL,'Megan Brault, MA','(407)823-2811','megan.brault@ucf.edu','Megan Brault','Publish',1),(1969,'EEC 6269 ONLINE  Play Development OPEN','eec-6269-online-play-development-open','<p>Fall 2014 enrollment for EEC 6269: Play Development is OPEN. This course explores play development in children from the ages of newborn through age 8 years.  It covers play theory, current research, and critical issues in play. Students pursuing the Play Therapy certificate as well as those studying Theater, Communication Disorders, and Psychology are encouraged to enroll. This is a graduate course and is done completely online, which means there are no meeting times/dates. For more information please contact Dr. Anne Culp at Anne.Culp@ucf.edu</p>','2014-07-14','2014-08-29',NULL,'Anne Culp',NULL,'Anne.Culp@ucf.edu','STLL Graduate Services','Publish',1),(1970,'UCF Test Prep GRE Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gre-review-course','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the GRE with our GRE Review course. Our GRE review course is 24 hours in length, and will help prepare you for the verbal and quantitative sections of the GRE. The GRE review course will review strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review emphasizing the rules and formulas needed to answer the qualitative questions on the GRE from the areas of arithmetic, geometry, data analysis and algebra. You will also apply and practice the material that you learn in class by doing exercises and practice problems.</p>','2014-07-27','2014-08-09','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1971,'UCF Test Prep Core Mathematical Concepts Review Course','ucf-test-prep-core-mathematical-concepts-review-course','<p>UCF test prep\'s Core Mathematical Concepts Review course is designed to familiarize you with the core math concepts that are tested in the GRE, GMAT, ACT, and SAT exams. You will also be reacquainted with concepts that you may not have seen for some time. It will allow you practice the different types of problems for each math concept, and the different ways each concept is used. This course will cover several different concepts, such as fractions, ratios and proportions, algebraic operations and solid geometry.</p>','2014-07-27','2014-08-09','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1972,'UCF Test Prep LSAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-lsat-review-course','<p>UCF Test Prep’s LSAT Review course is designed to fully prepare you for all aspects of the LSAT. This course includes an extensive materials package of 4 books covering all course materials, plus over 15 actual LSAT exams. The instructors are subject–matter experts in their field and willing to offer extra help before and after every class.</p>','2014-08-03','2014-08-16','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1973,'UCF Test Prep GMAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gmat-review-course','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the Graduate Management Admission Test with our GMAT Review course. Our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment.</p>\n<p>During the class there will be allotted time to practice and review what you have learned with practice problems and questions. Several sample tests are timed in class to give students the opportunity to use their strategies and to learn to budget their time. This course will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2014-08-06','2014-08-19','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1974,'UCF Test Prep MCAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-mcat-review-course','<p>Dr. Putzer’s Review and UCF Continuing Education partner to bring you the MCAT Prep Program. This is a comprehensive course that prepares you for all aspects of the current Medical College Admission Test. Dr. Putzer, the MCAT review instructor, is a highly trained professional who has been involved in premedical education for many years and possess both a MD and PhD.  The course emphasizes critical and analytical reasoning, which are the primary skills tested on the current exam. </p>\n<p>This course includes 96-hours of expert MCAT teaching, including detailed strategies for analyzing MCAT passages, problem-solving and thorough exposure to the scientific content of the test. Consider enrolling in our review course beginning Wednesday, August 20, 2014 if you intend on applying to medical school prior to the fall 2016 term.</p>','2014-08-06','2014-08-19','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1975,'UCF Test Prep GRE Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gre-review-course-1','<p>UCF TEST PREP has been providing GRE review courses since 1998. With more than 15 years of experience, our courses will help prepare you for both the verbal and quantitative sections of the GRE. Our GRE review course will review strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review emphasizing the rules and formulas needed to answer the qualitative questions on the GRE from the areas of arithmetic, geometry, data analysis and algebra. These strategies, along with the practice materials, will help to ensure you of no surprises come test day.</p>','2014-08-13','2014-08-26','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1976,'UCF Test Prep GMAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gmat-review-course-1','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the Graduate Management Admission Test with our GMAT Review course. Our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment.</p>\n<p>During the class there will be allotted time to practice and review what you have learned with practice problems and questions. Several sample tests are timed in class to give students the opportunity to use their strategies and to learn to budget their time. This course will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2014-08-20','2014-09-02','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1977,'UCF Test Prep GRE Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gre-review-course-1-2','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the GRE with our GRE Review course. Our GRE review course is 24 hours in length, and will help prepare you for the verbal and quantitative sections of the GRE. The GRE review course will review strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review emphasizing the rules and formulas needed to answer the qualitative questions on the GRE from the areas of arithmetic, geometry, data analysis and algebra. You will also apply and practice the material that you learn in class by doing exercises and practice problems.</p>','2014-08-28','2014-09-10','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1978,'UCF Test Prep SAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-sat-review-course','<p>Our 20-hour SAT review course is designed to do more than just review question types and cover material that will be on the test. Students will also dissect questions to gain a perspective from the test-taker\'s point of view.  By doing so, they will learn the common pitfalls and traps to avoid.  Students will also take two simulated tests to ensure the practice of their techniques and to prepare the students for what they can expect on test day.  The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-08-23','2014-09-05','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1979,'UCF Test Prep Core Mathematical Concepts Review Course','ucf-test-prep-core-mathematical-concepts-review-course-1','<p>UCF Test Prep’s Core Mathematical Concepts Review course is designed to familiarize you with the core math concepts that are tested in the GRE, GMAT, ACT, and SAT exams. You will also be reacquainted with concepts that you may not have seen for some time. It will allow you practice the different types of problems for each math concept, and the different ways each concept is used. This course will cover several different concepts, such as fractions, ratios and proportions, algebraic operations and solid geometry. </p>\n<p>Receive a discount when you combine the Core Mathematical Concepts Review with any live SAT or ACT course.</p>','2014-09-01','2014-09-14','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1980,'UCF Test Prep SAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-sat-review-course-1','<p>UCF Test Prep’s SAT review course is designed to do more than just review and cover material that will be on the test. Students will learn valuable testing strategies, understand the structure of the SAT, and gain perspective from the test-maker’s point of view in this 20-hour course. In addition to reviewing for the test itself, these strategies will help students lean to how avoid common traps and pitfall. The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-09-06','2014-09-19','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1981,'UCF Test Prep GMAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gmat-review-course-1-2','<p>UCF Test Prep has been providing GMAT review courses since 1998. With more than 15 years of experience, our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment. Several sample tests are given in class to give students the opportunity to use newly learned strategies and to learn to budget their time. This class will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2014-09-07','2014-09-20','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1982,'UCF Test Prep GRE Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gre-review-course-1-2-3','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the GRE with our GRE Review course. Our GRE review course is 24 hours in length, and will help prepare you for the verbal and quantitative sections of the GRE. The GRE review course will review strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review emphasizing the rules and formulas needed to answer the qualitative questions on the GRE from the areas of arithmetic, geometry, data analysis and algebra. You will also apply and practice the material that you learn in class by doing exercises and practice problems.</p>','2014-09-11','2014-09-23','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1983,'UCF Test Prep ACT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-act-review-course','<p>Our 20-hour ACT review course is designed to do more than just review question types and cover material that will be on the test. Students will also dissect questions to gain a perspective from the test-taker\'s point of view.  By doing so, they will learn the common pitfalls and traps to avoid.  Students will also take two simulated tests to ensure the practice of their techniques and to prepare the students for what they can expect on test day.  The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-09-07','2014-09-21','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1984,'UCF Test Prep SAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-sat-review-course-1-2','<p>UCF Test Prep’s SAT review course is designed to do more than just review and cover material that will be on the test. Students will learn valuable testing strategies, understand the structure of the SAT, and gain perspective from the test-maker’s point of view in this 20-hour course. In addition to reviewing for the test itself, these strategies will help students lean to how avoid common traps and pitfall. The classes are interactive and light and designed to make learning enjoyable.</p>','2014-09-20','2014-10-04','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1985,'UCF Test Prep GMAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gmat-review-course-1-2-3','<p>UCF Test Prep has been providing GMAT review courses since 1998. With more than 15 years of experience, our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment. Several sample tests are given in class to give students the opportunity to use newly learned strategies and to learn to budget their time. This class will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2014-09-23','2014-10-06','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1986,'UCF Test Prep GRE Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gre-review-course-1-2-3-4','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the GRE with our GRE Review course. Our GRE review course is 24 hours in length, and will help prepare you for the verbal and quantitative sections of the GRE. The GRE review course will review strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review emphasizing the rules and formulas needed to answer the qualitative questions on the GRE from the areas of arithmetic, geometry, data analysis and algebra. You will also apply and practice the material that you learn in class by doing exercises and practice problems.</p>','2014-09-27','2014-10-10','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1987,'UCF Test Prep GMAT Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gmat-review-course-1-2-3-4','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the Graduate Management Admission Test with our GMAT Review course. Our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment. During the class there will be allotted time to practice and review what you have learned with practice problems and questions. Several sample tests are timed in class to give students the opportunity to use their strategies and to learn to budget their time. This course will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2014-10-07','2014-10-15','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(1988,'UCF Test Prep GRE Review Course','ucf-test-prep-gre-review-course-1-2-3-4-5','<p>UCF TEST PREP has been providing GRE review courses since 1998. With more than 15 years of experience, our courses will help prepare you for both the verbal and quantitative sections of the GRE. Our GRE review course will review strategies for answering the four types of verbal questions--analogies, reading comprehension, antonyms, and sentence completion. You will also receive a thorough mathematics review emphasizing the rules and formulas needed to answer the qualitative questions on the GRE from the areas of arithmetic, geometry, data analysis and algebra. These strategies, along with the practice materials, will help to ensure you of no surprises come test day.</p>','2014-10-11','2014-10-21','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-0260','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF T