ta analysis and algebra. You will also apply and practice the material that you learn in class by doing exercises and practice problems.</p>','2015-05-18','2015-05-29','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-8378','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(2055,'2015 Executive and Professional Development Programs Announced','2015-executive-and-professional-development-programs-announced','<p>The UCF Executive Development Center located in Downtown Orlando has revealed its 2015 Open Enrollment Program calendar. The lineup of highly-applicable workshops suited for working professionals with varying responsibilities includes repeats of popular topics like Finance &amp; Accounting for Non-Financial Managers held on February 3 &amp; 4, 2015, The Path to Performance Excellence held on March 5, 2015, or Effective Negotiation held on April 28 &amp; 29, 2015, as well as brand new programs like Marketing in Action held on April 8, 2015. UCF faculty, staff and alumni receive discounts off all-inclusive registration fees. Please visit our website, <a href=\"http://edc.research.ucf.edu/open-enrollment-programs\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://edc.research.ucf.edu/open-enrollment-programs</a>, for details.</p>','2014-12-17','2015-01-14','http://edc.research.ucf.edu/open-enrollment-programs','Jana Breburdova','(407)235-3915','jbreburdova@bus.ucf.edu','Jana Breburdova','Publish',1),(2056,'UCF Apps: The software you need - anytime, anywhere, on any device!','ucf-apps-the-software-you-need-anytime-anywhere-on-any-device','<p>All UCF faculty and students now have access to many of the software applications required for coursework, at no additional out-of-pocket cost!\nStudents and faculty can use critical Windows applications such as SAS, SPSS, Microsoft Office, and ArcGIS anytime (24/7), anywhere (on or off campus), on just about any device they own!\nThe current application offerings are:\n</p><ul>\n    <li>AMOS</li>\n    <li>ArcGIS</li>\n    <li>JMP Pro</li>\n    <li>Microsoft Excel</li>\n    <li>Microsoft PowerPoint</li>\n    <li>Microsoft Publisher</li>\n    <li>Microsoft Word</li>\n    <li>Origin</li>\n    <li>SAS Base</li>\n    <li>SAS Enterprise Guide</li>\n    <li>SPSS</li>\n</ul>\nMore applications will be added as they become available.\nVisit <a href=\"http://apps.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://apps.ucf.edu</a> to watch an introductory video, get help and tutorials, submit feedback, and request applications.\nUCF Apps is a pilot project funded by the student technology fee and supported by contributions from UCF colleges and divisions.<p></p>','2015-01-05','2015-01-23','http://apps.ucf.edu','JP Peters',NULL,'jp@ucf.edu','JP Peters','Publish',1),(2057,'Diversity and Activity Grants','diversity-and-activity-grants','<p>The Office of Diversity and Inclusion has implemented a Diversity Activity Grants program to assist organizations and units in sponsoring diversity speakers, programs, and activities in support of the UCF goal to become more inclusive and diverse. A limited number of grants will be awarded. Grants will not exceed $250 and are limited to one per organization per academic year. The application is located at <a href=\"http://www.diversity.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.diversity.ucf.edu/</a> (click on the programs button).</p>','2014-12-18','2015-06-29','http://www.diversity.ucf.edu/','Carmen I Afonso','(407)823-3643','carmen.afonso@ucf.edu','Carmen I Afonso','Publish',1),(2058,'GMAT Review Course Starting January 8th','gmat-review-course-starting-january-8th','<p>Let UCF TEST PREP help prepare you for the Graduate Management Admission Test with our GMAT review course. Our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment. During the class there will be allotted time to practice and review what you have learned with practice problems and questions. Several sample tests are timed in class to give students the opportunity to use their strategies and to learn to budget their time. This course will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2014-12-22','2015-01-07','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-8378','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(2059,'GMAT Review Course Starting February 4th','gmat-review-course-starting-february-4th','<p>UCF Test Prep has been providing GMAT review courses since 1998. With more than 15 years of experience, our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment. Several sample tests are given in class to give students the opportunity to use newly learned strategies and to learn to budget their time. This class will help you prepare, study, and learn the material that will be tested on the GMAT.</p>','2015-01-21','2015-02-03','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)822-8378','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(2060,'Core Math Concepts Review Course Starting February 16','core-math-concepts-review-course-starting-february-16','<p>UCF Test Prep’s Core Mathematical Concepts Review course is designed to familiarize you with the core math concepts that are tested in the GRE, GMAT, ACT, and SAT exams. You will also be reacquainted with concepts that you may not have seen for some time. It will allow you practice the different types of problems for each math concept, and the different ways each concept is used. This course will cover several different concepts, such as fractions, ratios and proportions, algebraic operations and solid geometry. </p>\n<p>Receive a discount when you combine the Core Mathematical Concepts Review with any live SAT or ACT course.</p>','2015-02-02','2015-02-15','http://www.testprep.ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','(407)882-8378','testprep@ucf.edu','UCF Test Prep','Publish',1),(2061,'Poverty, Globalization, and Schooling Conference takes place February 26-28, 2015','poverty-globalization-and-schooling-conference-takes-place-february-26-28-2015','<p>The International Conference on Poverty, Globalization and Schooling will take place on the UCF campus February 26-28, 2015. This year’s conference focuses on the role of holistic teaching and learning in defining educational contexts, and in particular the influences or effects of poverty on the lives of research subjects and researchers themselves.</p>\n<p>Topics for this year’s conference will include teaching the concepts of poverty and social justice, developing students as concerned citizens in a global age, the impact(s) of teaching social justice issues, issues of social inequality, and in particular how international educators deal with notions of poverty and social justice within the context of their own discipline among many others.</p>\n<p>Proposals for papers are being accepted through January 16, and registration is open until January 30. For additional details about the conference, proposal submission instructions, and to register, visit the <a href=\"http://education.ucf.edu/form/PGS_reg.cfm\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">conference website</a>.</p>','2014-12-24','2015-02-28','http://education.ucf.edu/form/PGS_reg.cfm','Dr. Elsie Olan','(407)823-5179','Elsie.Olan@ucf.edu','Jason A. Brown','Publish',1),(2062,'GMAT Review Course Starting March 15th','gmat-review-course-starting-march-15th','<p>UCF Test Prep has been providing GMAT review courses since 1998. With more than 15 years of experience, our GMAT review course is 24 hours in length and is designed to familiarize students with the various parts of the GMAT:  the qualitative and verbal sections, the integrated reasoning section and the analytical writing assessment. Several sample tests are given in class to give stude