the USPS Employee of the year, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/</a> or email us at OD&amp;Training@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Arlene!</p>','2016-06-03','2016-06-07','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2287,'April 2016 USPS Employee of the Month - Jena Thomas','april-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-jena-thomas','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for April 2016 – Jena Thomas.</p>\n<p>Jena is a Program Assistant in SDES Health Services.  She is described by her nominators as:</p>\n<p>“having an extraordinary ability to successfully supervise and coordinate the processes and workflow of the Immunization Department.  Jena acted as a champion to implement an electronic process for immunizations proving more convenient and supporting campus and global efforts to decrease paper. </p>\n<p>Jena balances scholastics with her full-time and demanding position and continues to exude excellence and acts as a positive role model to her staff.</p>\n<p>Overall, Jena’s character and her support of University mission, vision and goals speak volumes to her unwavering exhibition of excellence and her undying need to help others.“</p>\n<p>We\'d also like to recognize her nominators, Donovan Williams and Kimberly Thrash, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.  </p>\n<p>For further information on the USPS Employee of the year, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/</a> or email us at OD&amp;Training@ucf.edu. </p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Jena!</p>','2016-06-14','2016-06-16','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2288,'The Centsible Knights Program  is Connecting with Students via Social Media','the-centsible-knights-program-is-connecting-with-students-via-social-media','<p>The Centsible Knights Financial Literacy program now has a presence on social media. This program provides students with information and resources that enhance financial knowledge and encourage sound financial decisions.</p>\n<p>A variety of social media platforms are being used to connect with students. Learn more about money management and being a Centsible Knight on the following social media sites:</p>\n<p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/CentsibleKnights\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.facebook.com/CentsibleKnights</a>\nTwitter: @centsibleknight\nInstagram: @centsibleknights</p>\n<p>Also, please visit the Centsible Knights website: <a href=\"http://www.finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy</a>.</p>','2016-06-16','2016-06-30','http://finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy/','Karemah Manselle','(407) 823-5393','karemah.manselle@ucf.edu','Karemah Manselle','Publish',1),(2289,'Fiscal year 2017 budget change - zero budget tolerance for projects','fiscal-year-2017-budget-change-zero-budget-tolerance-for-projects','<p>Effective July 5, 2016, the 5% project budget tolerance within UCF Financials will be reduced to 0% budget tolerance. The budget tolerance for departmental transactions will remain at 5%.</p>\n<p>On or after that date, if UCF Financials users should encounter a “Budget Exceeds Tolerance” budget error on a transaction (i.e. requisition, journal entry, etc.) against a project, they can add budget or change the funding source (chartfield information) before proceeding with the transaction.</p>\n<p>For questions, please contact the Financials Service Desk using the contact information below.</p>\n<p>Financials Support Services\nUCF Finance and Accounting\n12424 Research Pkwy, Suite 300\nOrlando, FL 32826</p>\n<p>Phone: (407) 823-5117 (Opt. 6)\nEmail: fntrain@ucf.edu</p>','2016-06-20','2016-06-24','http://www.fa.ucf.edu/News_and_Info/Fiscal_Year_2016/Fiscal_Year_End_2016.cfm','Financials Service Desk','(407) 823-5117','fntrain@ucf.edu','Mark Wray','Publish',1),(2290,'May 2016 USPS Employee of the Month - Lindell Jones','may-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-lindell-jones','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for May 2016 – Lindell Jones</p>\n<p>For almost 18 years, Lindell has been a Teacher’s Assistant at the Creative School for Children.  Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>“It is hard for new parents to entrust their child to someone else for 8-9 hours a day. It\'s placing trust in an individual and an institution to take care of the child as if the child were his/her own child.  Ms. Jones, is that person one can place all-encompassing trust in.  She treats our children as if they were her own!  Lindell knows every child by name, dedicated to teaching, a comforter, playmate, and a resource to parents.</p>\n<p>The goals of UCF are to become more inclusive and diverse and Ms. Jones’ room is a mini-United Nations representing 23 cultures. She displays her interests in learning about the different languages, different cultures which she incorporates in everyday learning.  Her goal and UCF’s, is to teach children to play together, work together, to share with each other, and to grow together.” </p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize her nominators, parent Kristine Shrauger and co-workers Amie Kusak and Amy Hesse who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>For further information on the USPS Employee of the year, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/</a> or email us at OD&amp;Training@ucf.edu. </p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Lindell!</p>','2016-06-22','2016-06-27','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2291,'Come Playtest Student Video Games at UCF On June 30','come-playtest-student-video-games-at-ucf-on-june-30','<p>A gung-ho police sketch artist and a war-weary girl are among the characters who will visit the University of Central Florida on June 30 as part of an on-campus video game playtest by UCF graduate students. Four student teams from UCF’s Florida Interactive Entertainment Academy (FIEA) will be seeking public input on their latest in-progress video games. </p>\n<p>The playtest will be held from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. on June 30, 2016 in Room 218 at UCF’s Student Union. UCF’s main campus is located at 4000 Central Florida Blvd, Orlando, FL 32816. The students will be on UCF’s concourse recruiting players the day of the playtest.</p>\n<p>These games serve as the students master’s thesis for the FIEA program, which was ranked the #1 graduate video game development program this year by the Princeton Review. The public will have a chance to play the games, meet the developers and shape the games with their feedback. The games will be finished on August 5, 2016.</p>\n<p>The games being tested are “The Channeler,” “Child No More,” “Ley Lines,” and “Sketch Artist.” “The Channeler” uses the Tobii EyeX eye tracker, which allows the player use their eyes as the game controller to solve crimes committed by spirits. “Child No More” is a story-driven adventure game about a girl fleeing war-torn Europe with her animal companions. In “Ley Lines” you solve puzzles in a ruined temple using powers like altering gravity, slowing time and shifting space. In “Sketch Artist” you play the role of a police sketch artist trying to create accurate drawings of outlandish suspects who are accused of often humorous crimes.   </p>\n<p>For more information, please contact fieaplaytesting12@gmail.com.</p>','2016-06-27','2016-06-30','http://fiea.ucf.edu/come-playtest-student-video-games-ucf-june-30/','Todd Deery','(407) 235-3580','fieaplaytesting12@gmail.com','Todd Deery','Publish',1),(2292,'2016 Annual Employee Awards Program','2016-annual-employee-awards-program','<p>Come join us for an afternoon of celebration as UCF Human Resources recognizes UCF\'s dedicated employees at our 44th Annual Employee Awards Program! Awardees include USPS and A&amp;P employees celebrating years of service and retirees. The Employee of the Year and the Gabor A&amp;P Excellence Award winners will also be announced at the event.</p>\n<p>Invitations will be sent to all awardees and nominees in July, however all employees are encouraged to attend. For more details, please visit the Human Resources Website at <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/annual-awards-program/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/annual-awards-program/</a>. </p>\n<p>For questions, please contact the Human Resources Benefits Section at Benefits@ucf.edu or (407) 823-2771.</p>','2016-06-27','2016-09-03','https://hr.ucf.edu/annual-awards-program/','Keven Ayala','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',1),(2293,'UCF CFP Information Session - July 21st','ucf-cfp-information-session-july-21st','<p>UCF Continuing Education invites you to attend our CFP information session on July 21st to learn more about our Certified Financial Planner Certification Education Program and network with financial planners from Charles Schwab and Raymond James and learn how the CFP credential helped in their careers. </p>\n<p>RSVP here <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3006/Certified-Financial-Planner-Certification-Education-Program-Open-House/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3006/Certified-Financial-Planner-Certification-Education-Program-Open-House/</a></p>','2016-07-21','2016-07-21','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3006/Certified-Financial-Planner-Certification-Education-Program-Open-House/','Kimberly Malac','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Kimberly Malac','Publish',1),(2294,'UCF Project Management Open House - July 20th','ucf-project-management-open-house-july-20th','<p>Join our open house session July 20th to learn more about the Applied Project Management Certificate Program</p>\n<p>•   Prepare for the Project Management Institute\'s PMP and CAPM Examinations\n•   Coursework relevant to the workplace\n•   12-week program includes active classroom discussion\n•   Complete learning system materials include 1,300 online sample exam questions\n•   Led by certified, industry experts\n•   Payment Plans available and Tuition Reimbursement may be accepted</p>\n<p>RSVP here <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/</a></p>','2016-07-20','2016-07-20','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/','Kimberly Malac','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Kimberly Malac','Publish',1),(2295,'UCF Financial and Retirement Strategy Series','ucf-financial-and-retirement-strategy-series','<p>UCF’s Financial and Retirement Strategy Series will provide you with the knowledge to build a secure financial foundation and create your own personalized financial plan to reach your financial goals.</p>\n<p>In this series all participants will have interaction with our Certified Financial Planners (CFP®), Certified Public Accountant (CPA) and Tax attorney.</p>\n<p>Our series focuses on the following key components:\n•   Cash Flow and Savings\n•   Insurance\n•   Liability Protection\n•   Retirement Accounts\n•   Investments\n•   Estate Planning\n•   Taxes\nFor more information about our Financial and Retirement Strategy Series program please visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/FRSS\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/FRSS</a>.</p>','2016-08-09','2016-08-09','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/FRSS','Kimberly Malac','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(2296,'Civics Teaching Certificate Offered by Lou Frey Institute','civics-teaching-certificate-offered-by-lou-frey-institute','<p>Undergraduate Certificate in Civics Teaching </p>\n<p>The Lou Frey Institute of Politics and Government is excited to offer a new civics teaching certificate! The Civics Teaching Certificate will provide pre-service teachers with complementary, civics teaching-focused coursework that will build on and enhance the Social Science Education B.S. curriculum. Individuals enrolled in the Civics Teaching certificate program will learn the substantive content, skills and pedagogical tools needed to deliver instruction explicitly linked to the 7th grade Civics End of Course Assessment (EOCA) in Florida. The Civics Teaching Certificate will also support and enhance high school U.S. government instruction. \nPre-service teachers enrolled in the Social Science Education B.S. major will complete four courses to develop expertise in civics content, pedagogy and\nassessment. The Civics Teaching Certificate will be completed as a three semester sequence. There will be two courses in the summer and one course in\nthe fall, followed by a final spring course. Summer coursework will include an internship in a local government office.\nFor more information, please visit the Lou Frey Institute website at: <a href=\"http://loufreyinstitute.org/civics-teaching-certificate\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://loufreyinstitute.org/civics-teaching-certificate</a> \nQuestions? \n Dr. Terri Susan Fine, Professor of Political Science\nand Civics Teaching Certificate coordinator at terri.fine@ucf.edu,\n407-823-2081 or 407-823-3636\n Dr. Stephen Masyada, Director of the Florida Joint Center for Citizenship, at Stephen.masyada@ucf.edu, 407-823-1146. </p>\n<p>Applications should be submitted to: civicsteaching@ucf.edu by August 1, 2016.</p>','2016-07-01','2016-08-01','http://loufreyinstitute.org/civics-teaching-certificate','Stephen S. Masyada','(407) 823-1146','stephen.masyada@ucf.edu','Steve Masyada','Publish',1),(2297,'Stand Out in Your HR Career!','stand-out-in-your-hr-career','<p>This is an exciting and pivotal time in the HR profession. HR teams are required to assume a greater leadership role, contributing to the strategic direction of their organization. Earn the SHRM certifications that will showcase your HR competencies and knowledge to lead your organization and the profession.</p>\n<p>Courses begin Fall 2016!</p>\n<p>UCF Wednesday courses begin September 7th; 6-9 pm\nLake Mary Thursday course begins September 8th; 6-9 pm\nLive-Online Tuesday course begins September 13th; 6-9 pm\nUCF Saturday course begins October 15th; 6-9 pm</p>\n<p>Benefits of UCF\'s SHRM Preparation Course: \n-Courses offered live-online and face-to-face\n-Evening and weekend schedules available - great for busy professionals and students \n-Learn with the official SHRM Learning System materials\n-Courses are facilitated by certified industry practitioners </p>\n<p>Reserve your seat now and secure our lowest course registration fee of $999.* Learn more about these sessions and additional HR trainings offered by UCF Division of Continuing Education by visiting <a href=\"http://ce.ucf.edu/PHRM\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ce.ucf.edu/PHRM</a>, or by contacting Nicole Baker Rosa at 407-882-0237 or Nicole.BakerRosa@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p>We also invite you to join our FREE virtual information session covering all of our HR programs!\n July 15th at 12 pm EST\nRegister at: <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Connect/?id=1188803&amp;folderId=1141109&amp;groupId=1182776\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Connect/?id=1188803&amp;folderId=1141109&amp;groupId=1182776</a></p>\n<p>If you\'re not ready to pursue certification at this time, explore our other online, open-entry HR offerings:\n-Essentials of  HR Management\n-HR Generalist Certificate </p>\n<p>*Early Bird Rate will be available one month prior to the start date of the course.</p>','2016-09-07','2016-12-06','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM','Nicole Baker Rosa','(407) 882-0237','Nicole.BakerRosa@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(2298,'“Move Beyond Civility: How to Facilitate Difficult Dialogues in the Classroom” Webinar on Sept. 27','move-beyond-civility-how-to-facilitate-difficult-dialogues-in-the-classroom-webinar-on-sept-27','<p>The UCF Office of Diversity and Inclusion invite students, faculty and staff to a webinar produced by PaperClip Communications*. The webinar topic will be introduced by Dr. Yovanna Pineda, UCF associate professor of history, and she will facilitate a discussion at the conclusion of the webinar.</p>\n<p>“Move Beyond Civility: How to Facilitate Difficult Dialogues in the Classroom”</p>\n<p>Tuesday, September 27, 2016\n2 to 3:30 p.m.\nTeaching Academy Room 117</p>\n<p>“This has been a particularly difficult year as students continue to challenge faculty and administrators to hear their concerns, engage in difficult conversation and make meaningful change on campus. In this webinar, participants will learn how to help faculty members better navigate difficult dialogues and conflict in the classroom. Many faculty members are experiencing a significant increase in both frequency and intensity of difficult dialogues in the classroom. The ability to engage students and facilitate meaningful dialogue in these moments not only further learning, but also impact student success. Mismanaged conversations often result in unresolved issues, misunderstanding and simmering conflict that undermine learning outcomes and campus-wide goals to create inclusive campus environments.”</p>\n<p>Participation Outcomes:</p>\n<p>Tools to create an inclusive classroom from the start and negotiate working agreements that set the stage for meaningful dialogue\nHow to recognize when a classroom discussion becomes “difficult” for students and/or themselves – get tools and approaches to de-escalate triggered reactions and promote engaged conversation\nCriteria to decide whether to engage in difficult conversations in the moment or table for a future setting\nTechniques to revisit classroom situations that did not further learning or group development to ensure everyone can learn how to do better the next time</p>\n<p>Facilitator:</p>\n<p>Dr. Yovanna Pineda’s research interests center on how global economic development impacts local communities and how these communities influence global institutions. Her current book project “Harvesting Innovation: Agricultural Science, Technology, and Memory” examines the social and cultural effects of technological innovation in farming communities of the fertile Pampas region of Argentina from 1860 to 1940. She teaches courses on Latin American history, the Atlantic World and the history of science.</p>\n<p>*PaperClip Communications specializes in serving the needs of educators around the world and offers higher education sessions on a broad range of topics, including student life and diversity issues.</p>','2016-07-06','2016-09-28','http://diversity.ucf.edu/events/','UCF Office of Diversity and Inclusion','(407) 823-6479','diverse@ucf.edu','UCF Office of Diversity and Inclusion','Publish',1),(2299,'June 2016 USPS Employee of the Month - Susan Terrill','june-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-susan-terrill','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for June 2016 – Susan Terrill</p>\n<p>For nine years, Susan has been an Office Assistant in the John C. Hitt Library. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>Sue is in many ways the face of Library Administration.  She is the first person visitors see and the voice callers hear.  She is total engaged in the care and maintenance of our 45 year old 220,000 square foot building hosting 1.3 million ‘house-guests’ per year.  In my opinion, she has the most difficult job in the building and she handles it with such skill and friendliness. </p>\n<p>Sue is dependable, hardworking, patient, attentive, detailed, creative, and the go-to person. Sue’s happy attitude, good judgment and follow through distinguish her work from the many.  She is one of our UCF employees who make the wheels of our university not only turn, but turn smoothly.”</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize her nominators, Raynette Kibbee and Frank Allen who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>For further information on the USPS Employee of the year, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/</a> or email us at OD&amp;Training@ucf.edu. \nCongratulations again to Susan!</p>','2016-07-13','2016-07-19','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2300,'Hidden Artists Exhibit at UCF John C. Hitt Library: August 1 - September 2','hidden-artists-exhibit-at-ucf-john-c-hitt-library-august-1-september-2','<p>Hidden Artists Exhibit at UCF John C. Hitt Library: August 1 - September 2, 2016 \nThe Tradition Continues</p>\n<p>University of Central Florida has many talented employees who use their creativity in their daily jobs. Some of these employees are “visual artists” who create artwork on their own time for themselves, their families and/or for the public. They are the “Hidden Artists.”</p>\n<p>The exhibit features the talents of: Gina Clifton, Pamela Williams Gruen, Dawn M. Herrod, Jacqui Johnson, Simona Loh, Meredith Malkin, Russ Muller, Fiona Murphy, Judy Bragg Pardo, Brian Pate, and M.C. Santana.</p>\n<p>Visit the Hidden Artists on Facebook at: <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/hiddenartists\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.facebook.com/hiddenartists</a> and click on “Like.” </p>\n<p>Hidden Artists membership is open to currently working UCF faculty or staff members who create artwork. For more information, email: judyart23@aol.com.</p>','2016-07-13','2016-09-01',NULL,'Judy Pardo',NULL,'judyart23@aol.com','Judy Pardo','Publish',1),(2301,'PBA Collective Bargaining Session','pba-collective-bargaining-session','<p>Collective bargaining session with the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) to be held at UCF Human Resources on Wednesday, August 10, 2016, from 9:30 to 11:30 a.m.</p>','2016-08-03','2016-08-10',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2302,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining','afscme-collective-bargaining','<p>Collective bargaining session with The American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) to be held on Tuesday, August 9, 2016, from 3:00-5:00 at UCF Human Resources.</p>','2016-08-03','2016-08-09',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-4025','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2303,'Alliance Mentoring Program/Lavender Council Applications Out','alliance-mentoring-programlavender-council-applications-out','<p>The Alliance Mentoring Program aims to match LGBTQ+ staff and faculty mentors with LGBTQ+ student mentees. Mentors will serve as a personal role model for the mentee(s) and will provide support and encouragement for mentees.</p>\n<p>The mentorship process will include goal-setting in areas such as personal, educational, academic and professional.</p>','2016-08-23','2016-09-02','http://www.ucfpride.org/mentoring.html','Justin Andrade','(407) 823-0401','justin.andrade@ucf.edu','Danielle Cottrill','Publish',1),(2304,'USPS Staff Council Scholarships now available!','usps-staff-council-scholarships-now-available','<p>The USPS Staff Council is accepting applications for their Fall 2016 Scholarships.  if you are a USPS member and will be taking classes, or have a dependent taking classes at UCF, you can apply for one of our 8 scholarships!  The deadline to apply is September 6th.</p>','2016-08-17','2016-09-06','http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/scholarships.html','Jamie LaMoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',1),(2305,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining Notice','afscme-collective-bargaining-notice','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will take place on Tuesday, August 23rd from 3:30pm-5:00pm in IC 105.</p>','2016-08-19','2016-08-23',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2306,'Benefit for American Heart/Stroke Association @ Buffalo Wild Wings','benefit-for-american-heartstroke-association-buffalo-wild-wings','<p>Immediately following the 2016 American Heart Association Walk, there will be a BIG celebration of life and 10% of proceeds will be donated from this event! Join us at Buffalo Wild Wings at 11400 University Blvd, immediately following the walk for food, fun and donate to a great cause!</p>\n<p>For questions, contact 832-326-7236! Thanks in advance for your support!</p>','2016-09-10','2016-09-10',NULL,'Brian - Manager Hosting Event','(407) 250-4880','dawn.schubert@gmail.com','Dawn Schubert','Publish',1),(2307,'Chick-Fil-A Spirit Night to Support American Heart Association','chick-fil-a-spirit-night-to-support-american-heart-association','<p>Come join us at the UCF Chick-Fil-A located at University and Rouse Rd. 11350 University Blvd. to support the Red Ribbon Gang for the 2016 American Heart and Stroke Association Walk! We will be there August 30, 2016  from 5-8:00 PM and please make sure to tell your cashier you are there to support the AHA!</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance for your support!</p>','2016-08-30','2016-08-30',NULL,'Dawn Schubert','(832) 326-7236','dawn.schubert@gmail.com','Dawn Schubert','Publish',1),(2308,'2016 American Heart and Stroke Walk','2016-american-heart-and-stroke-walk','<p>Join us to celebrate life and honor those who have passed due to cardiac or stroke issues! Honor your loved ones, friends and colleagues by walking on Saturday, September 10, 2016! </p>\n<p>Thank you in advance for your support! Hosted at the UCF Campus</p>','2016-09-10','2016-09-10','http://greaterorlandoheartwalk.kintera.org/faf/home/default.asp?ievent=1150110','Becky Kozak','(407) 481-6380','OrlandoHeartWalk@heart.org','Dawn Schubert','Publish',1),(2309,'July 2016 USPS Employee of the Month - Elvis Wanamaker','july-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-elvis-wanamaker','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month for July 2016 --</p>\n<p>Elvis Wanamaker is the Executive Administrative Assistant in SDES. He is described by his nominators as:</p>\n<p>“Elvis is a dedicated employee with 20 plus years of service to the university. He continues to reinvent himself and increase his work performance to meet the demands of a high-volume work environment. Elvis is known as a “superstar”, goes above and beyond in his job performance, and consistently volunteers to help others when needed. He embodies UCF’s mission, vision, values and goals by helping promote access, high-quality learning and enriched student development and leadership.”</p>\n<p>We\'d like to recognize his nominators, Sharon Ekern and Briant Coleman who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>For further information on the USPS Employee of Month, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu</a></p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Elvis!</p>','2016-08-27','2016-09-09','http://hr.ucf.edu/','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2310,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining Notice','afscme-collective-bargaining-notice-1','<p>Collective bargaining session with The American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) to be held on Wednesday, August 31, 2016, from 3:30-5:00 at UCF Human Resources.</p>','2016-08-26','2016-08-31',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2311,'Pegasus Palooza RWC Field Day','pegasus-palooza-rwc-field-day','<p>Come join us for the last Pegasus Palooza event of the fall kickoff for RWC Field Day. The Recreation and Wellness Center and UCF Sport Club Council will be on Memory Mall from 4pm-6pm to give students an opportunity to experience fun, field-day style games while learning about upcoming RWC programs. Take part in games such as bocce ball, corn hole, ladder ball, kanjam and more! Students will also have a chance to visit with over 40 of UCF\'s Sport Club teams.</p>','2016-08-29','2016-08-30','http://events.ucf.edu/event/238949/rwc-field-day/','Gary Cahen','(407) 823-2408','Gary.Cahen@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',1),(2312,'UCF Sport Clubs Showcase','ucf-sport-clubs-showcase','<p>One big event, countless opportunities for Knights! Whether you swim, throw, kick a ball or swing a club or bat now is your chance to get involved. Sport Clubs offers Knights a chance to compete, develop fundraising skills and make friendships that will last a lifetime. Come meet team members with more than 40 of UCF\'s Sport Clubs in our annual Showcase of club teams. Shake hands with members of our 2016 National Championship Wrestling and Kite boarding teams, enjoy some friendly, tailgate-style, competition and find out what opportunities await you on any of our teams. </p>\n<p>This event supports Pegasus Palooza and the RWC Field Day. Join us Tuesday, August 30 from 4pm-6pm on Memory Mall!</p>','2016-08-29','2016-08-30','http://events.ucf.edu/event/269472/sport-clubs-showcase/','Gary Cahen','(407) 823-2408','Gary.Cahen@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',1),(2313,'Flu Vaccinations available at the Health Center','flu-vaccinations-available-at-the-health-center','<p>Protect Yourself! Get a Flu shot!</p>\n<p>If you are in the habit of getting your flu shot every year, good for you! For those of you who don’t think you need a flu shot, consider the following: with more than 56,000 students on campus you WILL be exposed to the flu. If you catch the flu, you can expect to be out of school/work for up to 2 weeks recovering. Ask anyone who had the flu before, this is not something you can “tough out.” It will really wipe you out! Getting a flu shot is your best defense against catching the flu. </p>\n<p>The Health Center on campus offers flu shots to students for FREE with Student ID. Walk-in slots are available, or request it during your regularly scheduled visit within one of our pods. </p>\n<p>Check out website for walk-in flu shot clinics at <a href=\"http://www.StudentHealth.ucf.edu/flu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.StudentHealth.ucf.edu/flu</a></p>\n<p>The single best way to prevent the flu is to get a flu vaccine each season!</p>\n<p>Common Flu Myths Debunked\n•   The flu shot can NOT give you the flu. However, it is possible to catch the flu within 2 weeks of receiving your shot because your body has not built up the immunity yet. \n•   Trying to avoid people who have the flu will not protect you from catching it. Most healthy adults may be able to infect others beginning 1 day before symptoms develop and up to 5 to 7 days after becoming sick.</p>','2016-09-12','2016-12-19','https://shs.sdes.ucf.edu/flu','Crystal Colvenbach',NULL,'crystal.colvenbach@ucf.edu','Student Health Services','Publish',1),(2314,'Film Screening and Discussion. Memories of a Penitent Heart. A Film by Cecilia Aldarondo','film-screening-and-discussion-memories-of-a-penitent-heart-a-film-by-cecilia-aldarondo','<p>Free Film Screening of Memories of a Penitent Heart. A Film by Cecilia Aldarondo, followed by a conversation with the Filmmmaker. (2016 Tribeca Film Festival Selection, 2015 IFP\'s Independent Filmmaker Labs, 2015 Sundance Institute Edit &amp; Story Lab, 2015 Winner, Paley DocPitch). Cecilia Aldarondo is Assistant Professor of Film Studies at Skidmore College. She was the inaugural recipient of the 2015 Roberto Guerra Documentary Award and named by FILMMAKER Magazine as one of 2015’s “25 New Faces of Independent Film.”</p>\n<p>September 23rd, 3:30pm film screening. 5pm discussion.  in VAB 132.</p>\n<p>\"Twenty five years after Miguel died from AIDS, his niece, filmmaker Cecilia Aldarondo, embarks on an excavation into a quagmire of unresolved family drama. Like many gay men in the 1980s, Miguel moved from Puerto Rico to New York City; he found a career in theater and a rewarding relationship. Yet, on his deathbed he grappled to reconcile his homosexuality with his Catholic upbringing. Now, decades after his death, Cecilia locates Miguel’s lover Robert, who has been shunned and demonized by the family, in order to understand the whole story. Braiding recently discovered home movies, interviews, and contemporary vérité footage, Memories of a Penitent Heart dissects a family secret while exploring the AIDS crisis and the rarely heard story of Latino artists who died in the early days of the epidemic. This is a moving story about mistakes of the past and second chances that also questions how faith is used in times of crisis.\" —Dan Hunt</p>','2016-09-09','2016-09-23','http://events.ucf.edu/event/270257/film-screening-and-discussion-memories-of-a-penitent-heart-a-film-by-cecilia-aldarondo/','Dr. Claudia Schippert','(407) 823-4969','Claudia.Schippert@ucf.edu','Claudia.Schippert@ucf.edu','Publish',1),(2315,'I-Corps Life Sciences Cohort: Pizza Mixer and Information Session','i-corps-life-sciences-cohort-pizza-mixer-and-information-session','<p>UCF I-Corps is a 5-week program, funded by the National Science Foundation (NSF), that provides training on how to start a new business and identify customers for your ideas, and enables new ways to obtain funding from investors. We hope to provide this free training to interdisciplanary teams of researchers and students, and help  launch potential products into a multitude of markets and industries.</p>\n<p>In partnership with Florida Hospital, the upcoming I-Corps cohort will focus on Life Science innovations, though teams will be composed of members from a variety of disciplines.</p>\n<p>Want to learn more? Have an idea? Looking for a team to join? Attend our Pizza Mixer and Information session on September 6th, from 12 pm - 1 pm in HEC 101.</p>\n<p>Sign up here: <a href=\"http://icorps.cie.ucf.edu/life-sciences/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://icorps.cie.ucf.edu/life-sciences/</a></p>\n<p>To learn more about I-Corps visit: <a href=\"https://icorps.cie.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://icorps.cie.ucf.edu/</a></p>','2016-09-06','2016-09-06','http://icorps.cie.ucf.edu/life-sciences/','Nodari Gogoberidze','(407) 882-0345','nodari@ucf.edu','Nodari Gogoberidze','Publish',1),(2316,'Remember the 49 – Stories and Dialogue about the Pulse Tragedy','remember-the-49-stories-and-dialogue-about-the-pulse-tragedy','<p>Remember the 49 – Stories and Dialogue about the Pulse Tragedy</p>\n<p>Save the Date: Monday, September 12, 2016, at 1:45 p.m. in the Morgridge International Reading Center</p>\n<p>Students from the Latino, LGBTQ and Muslim communities will join UCF faculty and staff to share stories of healing and community. We are #OrlandoStrong! Be part of the renewal of our community’s spirit.</p>\n<p>We will observe 49 seconds of silence at 2 p.m. Join us wherever you are at that time.</p>\n<p>For more information, please contact Karen Morrison, <a href=\"mailto:Karen.Morrison@ucf.edu\">Karen.Morrison@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2016-09-12','2016-09-12',NULL,'Karen Morrison','(407) 823-6478','karen.morrison@ucf.edu','Briant Coleman','Publish',1),(2317,'Collective Bargaining Notice: PBA','collective-bargaining-notice-pba','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) will take place on Friday, September 9, 2016, from 9:30 to 11:30 a.m. at UCF Human Resources.</p>','2016-09-02','2016-09-09',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2318,'NEW! Nursing Adds Acute Care Certificate Track to Spring 2017 Admission Cycle','new-nursing-adds-acute-care-certificate-track-to-spring-2017-admission-cycle','<p>Due to demand, the College of Nursing has opened another Graduate Certificate track for Spring 2017. The priority application deadline is Sept. 15, however, the college will continue to review and consider qualified applications until the Spring 2017 cohort is full.</p>\n<p>Registered Nurses (RNs) with bachelor\'s and master\'s degrees in Nursing can submit their application and learn more about the popular Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner (AGACNP) Graduate Certificate program at <a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/acute-NP\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/acute-NP</a></p>\n<p>The AGACNP cares for adult/gerontology patients with medically-complex, stable and unstable acute, critical, and chronic illnesses across care settings ranging from hospitals to sub-acute, ambulatory care, clinic, and home care environments. The AGACNP provides a spectrum of care from disease prevention to acute and critical care management. The curriculum provides a strong scientific foundation for practicing in the current health care environment, teaches flexibility, and focuses on evidence-based practice and leadership.</p>\n<p>Upon graduation, students are qualified to sit for the required AGACNP board exam for national certification and state license to practice in the advanced practice role. Enrolling in the Doctor of Nursing Practice Post-Master’s program is an option after completing this program.</p>','2016-09-09','2016-09-30','http://www.nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/acute-NP','UCF College of Nursing, Graduate Student Services','(407) 823-2744','GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing, Office of Marketing &amp; Communications','Publish',1),(2319,'Rescheduled: PBA Bargaining Session','rescheduled-pba-bargaining-session','<p>The next collective bargaining session with the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) has been rescheduled for Thursday, September 14, 2016, 9:30-11:30 a.m., at UCF Human Resources.</p>','2016-09-08','2016-09-14',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2320,'Event/Exhibit proposals now being accepted for UCF Celebrates the Arts 2017','eventexhibit-proposals-now-being-accepted-for-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-2017','<p>The UCF Celebrates the Arts Steering Committee is seeking event and exhibit proposals for the 2017 festival at the Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts, April 7-14. As the festival enters its third year, we are looking to showcase the best in our students and faculty. The potential for a rich and exciting Celebration rests with ourselves and showcasing bold artistic works from within UCF.</p>\n<p>Proposals may be submitted by UCF faculty and staff, alumni, students, and community partners for collaborative works associated with UCF.</p>\n<p>The theme for UCF Celebrates the Arts 2017 is \"Journeys and Destinations.\" This theme may be interpreted in any way that you want, and all program items do not need to be centered around the theme. Additionally, the mission statement for UCF Celebrates the Arts is below and proposed events/exhibits will be considered for inclusion based on the mission’s guiding questions.</p>\n<p>Please send your proposals to UCFCTASteering@gmail.com. Proposals must include:\n1. Primary contact person(s)\n2. UCF and community entities involved\n3. Description of the event/exhibit, including any content that corresponds with the theme\n4. Community impact statement\n5. Space this event could best fit into (Lobby, DeVos, Pugh, Disney, lawn, other)\n6. Date and time constraints/requirements\n7. Number of performers\n8. Technical needs\n9. Budget, and where you propose those funds will come from\n10. Any additional information that would give the committee insight to your needs and that may help us make decisions to create the best possible experience for our faculty, students, and patrons.</p>\n<h2>All entities wishing to be included in UCF Celebrates the Arts MUST submit a proposal to UCFCTAsteering@gmail.com. Deadlines for submission will be Friday September 16, 2016 at 5 pm.</h2>\n<p>UCF Celebrates the Arts Mission Statement</p>\n<p>The UCF Celebrates the Arts event is an annual showcase featuring an interactive exhibition of student artworks in the areas of Visual and Performing Arts. In addition to the products and performances of the arts units, each year there are projects that demonstrate the arts vital role in innovation, communication and fostering creativity across all disciplines. The festival provides a platform to share with Orlando and the Central Florida region the collaboration that occurs among all the units at UCF and also with our community partners. UCF’s commitment to interdisciplinary activities and partnerships is well established and the festival celebrates these relationships as it demonstrates UCF’s strong positive impact in Central Florida and beyond.</p>\n<p>Proposals for inclusion on the Celebration Program will be considered utilizing the guiding questions:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Is it engaging content that includes the arts at UCF?</li>\n<li>How does it positively affect arts students at UCF?</li>\n<li>Does it involve a partnership with other UCF areas/schools/departments?</li>\n<li>How does it affect the community and our community partners?</li>\n<li>How is it funded, and how does it impact existing income?</li>\n<li>Is it logistically feasible?</li>\n</ol>','2016-09-09','2016-09-16','http://arts.cah.ucf.edu/','Heather Gibson','(407) 823-1732','heather.gibson@ucf.edu','Heather Gibson','Publish',1),(2321,'Homeless, Food-Insecure & Foster Youth Students: Decrease Barriers to Increase their Success, Retention & Graduation Webinar','homeless-food-insecure-foster-youth-students-decrease-barriers-to-increase-their-success-retention-graduation-webinar','<p>Multicultural Academic and Support Services in partnership with UCF Cares and the Florida Consortium will host Homeless, Food-Insecure &amp; Foster Youth Students: Decrease Barriers to Increase their Success, Retention &amp; Graduation webinar on Wednesday, September 14, 2016, 2 - 4 p.m., Classroom Building 1, room 205. </p>\n<p>In a recent study, of 4,000 students attending 10 different community colleges across the U.S., more than half of all community college students struggle with food insecurity. Plus, more than 32,000 young adults exit the foster care system as they age out to independence each year - and 70% of them plan to attend college, according to the Child Welfare Information Gateway. Despite an overall increase in college attendance, low-income youth and particularly those in the foster care system are less likely to attend college (Wolanin, 2005). Although youth in foster care report high educational aspirations, as little as 4% obtain a 4-year college degree (Nixon &amp; Jones, 2007).</p>\n<p>Please join us for a campus dialogue on collective impact approaches to engage, retain and graduate homeless, food-insecure and foster care students. The webinar will focus on ways to implement successful support strategies on our campus and target efforts that meet the unique needs of the students.</p>\n<p>Please RSVP to mass@ucf.edu.</p>','2016-09-14','2016-09-14',NULL,'Tammie Nadeau','(407) 823-1832','tammie.nadeau@ucf.edu','Tammie Nadeau','Publish',1),(2322,'The 44th Annual Awards Program Highlights','the-44th-annual-awards-program-highlights','<p>On behalf of the UCF Human Resources department, we extend a sincere thanks to everyone who joined us for the 44th Annual Awards Program on Friday, September 2. The event was a great success with over 500 attendees, and we would like to thank everyone who attended for helping to make this year’s event memorable.</p>\n<p>Please visit the 2016 Annual Awards Program website for awardee information as well as high resolution images of the event that are available for viewing and downloading.</p>\n<p>A few highlights of the Awards Program include:</p>\n<p>USPS Employee of the Year: Lindell Jones\nFor almost 18 years, Lindell has been a Teacher’s Assistant at the UCF Creative School for Children. Her nominators had this to say about her: \"It is hard for new parents to entrust their child to someone else for 8-9 hours a day. It involves placing trust in an institution and an individual at an institution to take care of the child as if the child were his or her own. Ms. Jones is a person that one can place all-encompassing trust in. She treats our children as if they were her own!” Congratulations, Lindell!</p>\n<p>A&amp;P Gabor Excellence Award: Rupert Neish\nRupert has served in the Department of Legal Studies since February 2013. Prior to that time, Mr. Neish worked as a Program Assistant for the UCF History department and as a Financial Aid Specialist for the UCF Office of Financial Aid. He is also the Treasurer-Elect for the Black Faculty and Staff Association at UCF. Since 2006, he has served in several capacities on the UCF Student Conduct Board. He has completed more than 60 hours of training and workshops on sexual misconduct, academic integrity, UCF\'s Golden Rule, drug and alcohol abuse awareness and prevention, and international student services. Congratulations, Rupert!</p>\n<p>Awards will be sent via intercampus mail within the upcoming weeks to awardees who did not attend the event.</p>','2016-09-14','2016-09-28','https://hr.ucf.edu/annual-awards-program-2016/','Keven Ayala','(407) 823-1937','keven.ayala@ucf.edu','HR Benefits','Publish',1),(2323,'NanoFlorida 2016 Science and Technology Conference','nanoflorida-2016-science-and-technology-conference','<p>NanoFlorida is an annual nanoscience technology symposium held at different Florida institutions of higher learning. Beginning in 2008 at the University of Central Florida, NanoFlorida 2016 is finally back for its “homecoming” at UCF. As a student-led conference NanoFlorida was designed to emphasize student leadership and development. Topics at NanoFlorida 2016 include frontiers of nanoscience and nanotechnology with a special emphasis on nanomedicine, environmental nanotechnology, and nanoagriculture. Nanoflorida 2016 will take place on the main campus of the University of Central Florida at the Student Union, known as the \"Heart of Campus.” (12715 Pegasus Dr.  Orlando, FL 32816)</p>','2016-09-25','2016-09-26','http://nanoscience.ucf.edu/nanoflorida/','Tyler Maxwell','(407) 882-1578','NanoFlorida@ucf.edu','Torus Washington','Publish',1),(2324,'Employee Tuition Waiver Program and Taxation','employee-tuition-waiver-program-and-taxation-1-2-3-4-5-6-7','<p>As a reminder for the fall 2016 semester, please remember that UCF employees can claim up to $5,250 in tax-free educational\nbenefits for graduate level and higher coursework (section 127, Internal Revenue Code). Please be advised that the value of the\nbenefit in excess of $5,250 will be taxed at the supplemental tax rate (25%) for federal withholding, plus the appropriate Social\nSecurity and Medicare tax rates. Those taxes will be deducted from your paycheck(s) and be included on your Form W-2.</p>\n<p>The university does not provide tax advice. If you have questions about this information, please contact a tax professional.</p>\n<p>Non-tax related questions regarding the educational benefits addressed above may be directed to Payroll Services by emailing\n<a href=\"mailto:payroll@ucf.edu\">payroll@ucf.edu</a> or calling (<a href=\"tel:4078232771\" rel=\"nofollow\">407) 823-2771</a>.</p>','2016-09-19','2016-09-23','http://hr.ucf.edu/files/tuitionwaiver.pdf','Payroll Services','(407) 823-2771','payroll@ucf.edu','Isha Guerrero-Londeree','Publish',1),(2325,'Exculsive Advance Screening of new film GOAT starring Nick Jonas and James Franco','exculsive-advance-screening-of-new-film-goat-starring-nick-jonas-and-james-franco','<p><a href=\"http://HazingPrevention.Org\" rel=\"nofollow\">HazingPrevention.Org</a>™ will host a series of college screenings of the new feature film GOAT as part of its efforts to empower people to prevent hazing. Starring Nick Jonas, Ben Schnetzer and James Franco, and based on the memoir by Brad Land, GOAT tells the story of two brothers who become embroiled in hazing at a college fraternity. What occurs in the name of ‘brotherhood’ tests both boys and their relationship in brutal ways. Directed by Andrew Neel, the film received wide acclaim at the Sundance Film Festival and will be released in select theaters nationwide, on demand and digital HD on September 23rd by Paramount Home Media Distribution.</p>','2016-09-19','2016-09-22','http://hazingprevention.org/feature-film-goat/','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','germayne graham','Publish',1),(2326,'New Director of Environmental Health and Safety','new-director-of-environmental-health-and-safety','<p>Please join me in welcoming Renee Michel as the new Director of Environmental Health and Safety (EHS) for UCF.   Renee comes to us from Florida Polytechnic University, the newest of the state’s universities, where she created and implemented the entire EHS program from the ground up.  She has developed numerous policies, procedures, and training programs to reduce and prevent safety hazards, dangers, and accidents in areas such as hazardous materials, occupational risk, and industrial hygiene.   Prior to working at Florida Polytechnic, Renee spent four years at UCF as the Regional Campus Health Science Manager for EHS.  She is the recipient of the 2016 Innovation Award of Commendation from the Campus Safety, Health and Environmental Management Association (CSHEMA) and received the City of Orlando Certificate of Achievement for the UCF Burnett School of Biomedical Sciences Industrial Waste Pretreatment Program in 2011.   Renee received her Bachelor of Science in Chemical Engineering and is pursuing her Master of Business Administration.  We are confident that her leadership will promote a culture of safety, health, and environmental protection in support of UCF’s mission of education, research, and public service.</p>\n<p>For further information, contact renee.michel@ucf.edu or visit <a href=\"http://www.ehs.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ehs.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2016-09-21','2016-10-21','http://www.ehs.ucf.edu','Renee Michel','(407) 823-6300','renee.michel@ucf.edu','Lee Kernek','Publish',1),(2327,'Solar Co-Op Informational Assembly','solar-co-op-informational-assembly','<p>Join UCF Sustainability Initiatives, FL SUN, and Orange County for the Solar Co-Op Informational Assembly to learn about solar installation savings and the opportunity to join the Co-Op for FREE!</p>\n<p>Who: UCF Faculty &amp; Staff (guests are welcome)\nWhen: September 27th, 2016 @ 11:30am\nWhere: UCF Student Union, 316A\nCost: Free</p>','2016-09-19','2016-09-27',NULL,'Yara Watson',NULL,'yarazeth.watsoncolon@ucf.edu','Sustainability Initiatives','Publish',1),(2328,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining Notice','afscme-collective-bargaining-notice-1-2','<p>A collective bargaining session with The American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will be held on Thursday, September 22, 2016, from 4:00-5:30 p.m.</p>','2016-09-19','2016-09-22',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2329,'Free Hands-Only CPR Classes Offered on World Heart Day','free-hands-only-cpr-classes-offered-on-world-heart-day','<p>Join UCF in celebrating World Heart Day by learning Hands-Only CPR in the Student Union, Pegasus Ballroom on September 29th. Free training sessions will start every few minutes from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. during this CPR marathon. Hands-Only CPR is CPR without mouth-to-mouth breaths. More than 1,000 members of the community are expected to learn this quick, basic emergency response.</p>\n<p>World Heart Day encourages people to reduce cardiovascular risk by making heart- healthy choices and knowing how to help others in cardiac distress.</p>\n<p>For further information, contact <a href=\"mailto:marcel.fernandez@ucf.edu\">marcel.fernandez@ucf.edu</a> or Environmental Health &amp; Safety at <a href=\"tel:4078236300\" rel=\"nofollow\">407-823-6300</a>.</p>','2016-09-23','2016-09-30',NULL,'Marcel Fernandez','(407) 823-6300','marcel.fernandez@ucf.edu','Montel Watson','Publish',1),(2330,'Campus Conversations: How to Have Difficult Discussions about Community Policing and Race','campus-conversations-how-to-have-difficult-discussions-about-community-policing-and-race','<p>The Division of Student Development and Enrollment Services, the Recreation and Wellness Center, The Multicultural Student Center and the UCF Police department is inviting the entire campus community to take part in a panel discussion and talk openly about racial tensions gripping our nation.</p>\n<p>Campus Conversations: How to Have Difficult Discussions about Community Policing and Race is a panel discussion which gives students, faculty, staff and others a chance to discuss ideas and share thoughts in an effort to bring the community together.</p>\n<p>The panel discussion will feature officers from the UCF Police Department, Edwanna Andrews the Director of UCF’s Social Justice and Advocacy department, Jim Wilkening the Executive Director of UCF’s Recreation and Wellness and 2 UCF Students. The event is open to the campus community and Knights from across campus are invited to attend. For more information on the panel discussion contact Andrea Snead at <a href=\"mailto:andrea.snead@ucf.edu\">andrea.snead@ucf.edu</a> or call <a href=\"tel:4078232408\" rel=\"nofollow\">407-823-2408</a>.</p>\n<p>Who: UCF Campus Community</p>\n<p>What: Campus Conversations: How to Have Difficult Discussions about Community Policing and Race</p>\n<p>Where: The UCF Recreation and Wellness Center, Multi-purpose Room (room #245) on the second floor near the lap pool patio</p>\n<p>Why: To bring the community together</p>\n<p>When: Monday, September 26, 2016 at 7pm</p>','2016-09-23','2016-09-27','http://events.ucf.edu/event/285600/campus-conversations-how-to-have-difficult-discussions-about-community-policing-and-race/','Andrea Snead','(407) 823-2408','andrea.snead@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',1),(2331,'Exclusive Advance Screening of new film GOAT staring Nick Jonas and James Franco','exclusive-advance-screening-of-new-film-goat-staring-nick-jonas-and-james-franco','<p><a href=\"http://HazingPrevention.Org\" rel=\"nofollow\">HazingPrevention.Org</a>™ will host a series of college screenings of the new feature film GOAT as part of its efforts to empower people to prevent hazing. Staring Nick Jonas, Ben Schnetzer and James Franco, and based on the memoir by Brad Land, GOAT tells the story of two brothers who become embroiled in hazing at a college fraternity. What occurs in the name of ‘brotherhood’ tests both boys and their relationship in brutal ways. Directed by Andrew Neel, the film received wide acclaim at the Sundance Film Festival and will be released in select theaters nationwide, on demand and digital HD on September 23rd by Paramount Home Media Distribution.</p>','2016-09-19','2016-09-23','http://hazingprevention.org/feature-film-goat/','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','germayne graham','Publish',1),(2332,'August 2016 USPS Employee of the Month - Denise Whiteside','august-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-denise-whiteside','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month for August 2016 --</p>\n<p>Denise Whiteside is a Senior Administrative Assistant in the College of Optics and Photonics (CREOL).  Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>“Denise is a vital part of the staff at CREOL.  She has attributes you want in an employee: dedicated, enthusiastic, punctual, confident, team player and smart.  </p>\n<p>Denise is always looking out for the best interest of CREOL/UCF.  No matter what she is involved with, she’s always trying to make sure the end result represents the College in the most favorable light. She takes ownership in her work and is proud to represent CREOL/UCF!”</p>\n<p>We\'d like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. Denise receives a one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, a marquee announcement, goody bag, certificate, and surprise presentation. Denise is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d also like to recognize her nominators, Bahaa Saleh and Mark Wagenhauser who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.  </p>\n<p>If you would like to nominate a USPS employee, the EOM nomination packet is available in hard copy nominator form at <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Nomination-Letter-Final.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Nomination-Letter-Final.pdf</a>   and supporter form <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Supportor-Letter-Form-Final.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Supportor-Letter-Form-Final.pdf</a>  or via electronic submission visit <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7PNhTbow5cKW0zH\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7PNhTbow5cKW0zH</a> .</p>\n<p>If you have questions, please contact Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu or 407-823-2777.</p>','2016-09-30','2016-10-07','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2333,'Health Professions Fall Career Seminar','health-professions-fall-career-seminar','<p>October 4, 4:30-5:50 HPA 112 Professionals from Pharmacy, Public Health, and Nutrition fields\nOctober 6, 4:30-5:50 HPA 119 Professionals from Medicine, Physician Assistant, and Dentistry fields\nOctober 11, 4:30-5:50 HPA 112 Professionals from Physical Therapy, Occupational Therapy, and Athletic Training fields\nOctober 13, 4:30-5:50 HPA 119 Professionals for careers that do not require graduate school completion</p>','2016-10-03','2016-10-13','https://www.facebook.com/UCF.HSPC/?fref=nf','Health Sciences Pre-Clinical','(407) 823-0946','pcinfo@ucf.edu','Kristal Johnson','Publish',1),(2334,'CANCELED: AFSCME Bargaining Session','canceled-afscme-bargaining-session','<p>The collective bargaining session scheduled for Wednesday, October 5, 2016, has been canceled and will be rescheduled.</p>','2016-10-05','2016-10-05',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2335,'RWC Job Fair','rwc-job-fair-1','<p>Come learn more about the positions at the UCF RWC! These are informal, informational sessions but are highly encouraged to attend. Information for international students is also available. Positions are available for the spring and summer. To apply, please bring a completed application, resume, and cover letter. Positions open to UCF students only.</p>\n<p>We\'ll have current staff here on 10/13 from 2pm-4pm in the lobby of our main building. We hope to see you here!</p>\n<p>Find more information on available positions and print an application from <a href=\"http://rec.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">rec.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2016-10-10','2016-10-14','https://www.facebook.com/events/564119477122973/','Scott Mauro','(407) 823-2408','scott.mauro@ucf.edu','Lauren Schoepfer','Publish',1),(2336,'Return on Investment (ROI) Training at UCF','return-on-investment-roi-training-at-ucf','<p>UCF Continuing Education, in partnership with the ROI Institute, are proud to bring you valuable Return on Investment (ROI) courses to help you and/or your organization measure return on investment for projects, programs, and initiatives.\nThe ROI MethodologyTM is a scalable and systematic approach to program evaluation. Using a process model, five-level framework, and operating standards to capture performance metrics from simple satisfaction scores to financial impact, the methodology enables you to collect appropriate data to report performance of a variety of initiatives and program types. The ROI MethodologyTM generates both qualitative and quantitative data and provides techniques to isolate the effects of the program from other influences - resulting in credible metrics and ROI reports accepted by financial executives and stakeholders.</p>\n<p>UCF Continuing Education in partnership with the ROI Institute offer:</p>\n<p>Measuring ROI 2-Day Workshop:\nNovember 3-4, 2016\n8 am - 5 pm\nThis two-day workshop focuses on the ROI MethodologyTM. Participants experience the application of the ROI Process model. This includes developing application and impact objectives, collecting various types of hard and soft data, isolating the effects of the program, converting data to monetary values, tabulating appropriate program costs, and calculating the return on investment.</p>\n<p>ROI 5-Day Certification:\nJanuary 23-27, 2017\n8:30 am - 5 pm (M-R), 8:30 am - Noon (F)\nThe five-day ROI Certification is an internationally-recognized process focused on measuring the true value of tough-to-measure initiatives using the ROI MethodologyTM. Participating in the ROI Certification is the most comprehensive way to gain the skills to evaluate your major programs and report the most credible results that drive organizational improvements.</p>\n<p>Learn more and register at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/ROI\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/ROI</a></p>','2016-11-03','2017-01-27','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/ROI','Nicole Baker Rosa','(407) 882-0237','ceprograms@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(2337,'Benefits Open Enrollment','benefits-open-enrollment-1','<p>The state\'s annual open enrollment period for eligible employees to change insurance benefits options begins on Monday, October 17th at 8 a.m. and ends Friday, November 4th at 6 p.m. EST.</p>\n<p>Please visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/open-enrollment\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/open-enrollment</a> for additional details and updates.</p>\n<p>Questions can be directed to <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\">benefits@ucf.edu</a> or <a href=\"tel:4078232771\" rel=\"nofollow\">407.823.2771</a>.</p>','2016-10-17','2016-11-04','https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/open-enrollment','UCF Human Resources Benefits Section','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',1),(2338,'2016 Benefits Fair','2016-benefits-fair','<p>The 2016 Benefits Fair will be held on Friday, October 28, from 9:00 a.m. - 2:00 p.m. in the Pegasus Ballroom at the Student Union. For additional information regarding the event visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/2016-Benefits-Fair-Sign.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/2016-Benefits-Fair-Sign.pdf</a>.</p>\n<p>The Benefits Fair is an opportunity to learn about benefit options and changes to help employees make the best choices during open enrollment, which begins on Monday, October 17 and ends on November 4 (6:00 p.m.). During open enrollment eligible employees can make changes to their insurance and other benefits for the upcoming plan year. Changes will be effective January 1, 2017, and must be made through <a href=\"https://peoplefirst.myflorida.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://peoplefirst.myflorida.com</a> or call toll-free, 866-663-4735.</p>\n<p>Employees who have not logged into People First within the past 90 days will need to update their password online.</p>\n<p>For questions regarding this information contact 407-823-2771 or <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\">benefits@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2016-10-28','2016-10-28','https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/open-enrollment/','UCF Human Resources Benefits Section','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',1),(2339,'B.L.A.C.K. Institute','black-institute','<p>The Building Leaders and Connecting Knights (B.L.A.C.K.) Institute is a culturally specific leadership development conference for the Black student population at UCF. Attendees of the B.L.A.C.K. Institute will engage in small group discussions, panel led dialogues and other experiential activities, as well as have opportunities to meet with UCF leadership, faculty, and staff that reflect their cultural identity. The goal of the B.L.A.C.K. Institute is to increase the retention of Black students at UCF through increasing their connection to the institution, the community and their roles as leaders within that community. The theme for this year’s Institute is “Uknighted We Stand.” The B.L.A.C.K. Institute will be held October 21 - 22, 2016.\nFor more information and to register, please visit: <a href=\"http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/blackinstitute\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/blackinstitute</a></p>','2016-10-16','2016-10-23','http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/blackinstitute','Keiron Timothy','(407) 823-2811','Keiron.Timothy@ucf.edu','Larry Marks','Publish',1),(2340,'UCF RWC Inclusive Rec Expo','ucf-rwc-inclusive-rec-expo','<p>Orlando, FL (October 17, 2016) – The University of Central Florida Recreation and Wellness Center continues its commitment to fulfilling one of UCF President John Hitt’s key goals of becoming a more inclusive and diverse university with its annual Inclusive Recreation Expo. Over the past five years, UCF Knights of all abilities have enjoyed the opportunity to learn more about the equipment, programs and services the RWC offers to students with disabilities on campus.</p>\n<p>Imagine scoring a basket from a wheelchair or scoring a goal blindfolded. Attendees will have an opportunity to try those activities and more throughout the day at the RWC’s main building Court 1 (Gemini Boulevard South across from Parking Garage B) Wednesday, October 19, 2016 from 3pm-8pm. The activities include:</p>\n<p>• 3:00pm-4:00pm Goalball\n• 4:15pm-5:15pm Unified Basketball\n• 5:30pm-6:30pm Sitting Volleyball\n• 6:45pm-7:45pm Wheelchair Basketball</p>\n<p>The RWC’s Adaptive and Inclusive Recreation Program is known nationally for its progressive programming which includes access to equipment and services for students with disabilities including but not limited to:</p>\n<p>• The Student Assisted Workout (S.A.W.) Program\n• Equipment such as: Krank Cycles, a Nu-Step Machine, an adaptive kayak and a Haul System used at the Climbing Tower\n• Intramural Sports Tournaments for wheelchair basketball and beep baseball\n• And for the first time ever, Intramural Sports leagues in Sitting Volleyball and Goalball. In the 2016 Rio Paralympic Games, the U.S. Women’s Sitting Volleyball team won a gold medal, Women’s Goalball won bronze, and Men’s Goalball won silver.</p>\n<p>Sport Clubs Coordinator, Andrea Snead, runs the Inclusive Recreation program at the RWC. She says this is the five-year anniversary of the Expo and the goal is to increase UCF’s inclusive profile, “Our goal this year is to increase awareness, of not just UCF\'s inclusive efforts but also of the extraordinary things that are going on in the world. This year in Rio, the Paralympics was an incredible event and I wanted to bring that excitement here by highlighting sports that we can program for our UCF students.”</p>\n<p>The UCF RWC is funded by the Student Government Association. Comprehensive and diverse programs like Adaptive and Inclusive Recreation are part of the RWC’s mission and goals to continually enrich campus life and advance UCF’s educational mission for all students. For more information and questions about the expo, please contact Andrea Snead at (407) 823-2408 or email her at andrea.snead@ucf.edu. You can also go to the RWC homepage: <a href=\"http://rec.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rec.ucf.edu/</a></p>\n<h3></h3>','2016-10-19','2016-10-19','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vzeh_RNV6M4&feature=youtu.be','Andrea Snead','(407) 823-2408','andrea.snead@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',1),(2341,'Health Professions Fall Career Seminar','health-professions-fall-career-seminar-1','<p>Meet current professionals and learn what it takes to enter the Medicine, Physician Assistant, and Dentistry fields.</p>','2016-10-25','2016-11-08','https://www.facebook.com/UCF.HSPC/events/','Health Sciences Pre-Clinical','(407) 823-0946','pcinfo@ucf.edu','Kristal Johnson','Publish',1),(2342,'September 2016 USPS Employee of the Month - Nicholas Schenk','september-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-nicholas-schenk','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month for September 2016 -- Nicholas Schenk. </p>\n<p>Nicholas Schenk is a Senior Admissions Specialist in the Political Science Department.  He is described by his nominators:</p>\n<p>“Nick is an excellent advisor to our undergraduate students. He provides outstanding service to them before some of them officially enroll to their graduation day.  He is detail oriented, understands complex issues related to advising across majors and minors.  He takes the time to listen to students’ needs and links them to other units on campus.</p>\n<p>Perhaps most noteworthy is not the fact that Nick performs a large number of diverse tasks and exceeds; but the fact he is self-directed and motivated and rarely needs supervision.  I cannot think of a better employee for the award.”</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize his nominators, Kerstin Hamann and Paul Vasquez, who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>If you would like to nominate a USPS employee, the EOM nomination packet is available in hard copy nominator form at <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Nomination-Letter-Final.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Nomination-Letter-Final.pdf</a> and supporter form <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Supportor-Letter-Form-Final.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Supportor-Letter-Form-Final.pdf</a> or via electronic submission visit <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7PNhTbow5cKW0zH\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7PNhTbow5cKW0zH</a>.  </p>\n<p>If you have questions, please contact Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu or 407-823-2777.</p>','2016-10-31','2016-11-04','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2343,'Bus To The Ballot','bus-to-the-ballot','<p>No matter who you support this election season, the most important part of the democratic process is to get out and VOTE!</p>\n<p>That’s why SGA will be providing shuttles to polling locations during the Early Voting period on November 2nd and 3rd from 10:00am - 7:00pm.</p>\n<p>Buses are located in front of the Communications Building by the bus loop.</p>','2016-11-02','2016-11-03',NULL,'Jeff Strange',NULL,'sgalegaffairs@ucf.edu','Hannah Hollinger','Publish',1),(2344,'Language Speed Dating','language-speed-dating','<p>Do you just love languages? Interested in getting to know new languages?</p>\n<p>Come to Language Speed Dating as part of International Education Week… Find your true language match!</p>\n<p>Learn basic phrases, try out different writing systems, and experience the pronunciation of Chinese, Arabic, Italian, German, Korean, Spanish, Japanese, French, Portuguese, and English. Rotations every 15 minutes.</p>\n<p>Mark your little black book. and join the multilingual excitement!</p>\n<p>Date: Wednesday, November 16, 2016; 2:30pm - 4:30pm\nLocation: Student Union, Cape Florida Ballroom (316C)\nCost: Free</p>\n<p>Offered by the Department of Modern Languages &amp; Literatures</p>','2016-11-09','2016-11-16','http://www.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=3719','Marcella A. Farina',NULL,'marcella.farina@ucf.edu','Marcella A. Farina','Publish',1),(2345,'October 2016 USPS Employee of the Month - Katie Connolly','october-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-katie-connolly','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month for October 2016 -- Katie Connolly.</p>\n<p>Katie is the Office Manager in the College of Health &amp; Public Affairs Legal Studies.  Her nominators had this to say about her: </p>\n<p>“I am happy to report that Ms. Connolly goes well beyond what is expected, volunteers for extra work, and gives maximum effort on demanding assignments. Katie – without a moment’s hesitation provides seamless, behind-the-scenes support!</p>\n<p>Katie has supported the mission, vision, values and goals of UCF by supporting our initiatives to transform our department, maintain our community partnerships, and develop experiential learning opportunities for students.  </p>\n<p>She manages the American Collegiate Moot Court Regional Tournament hosted at UCF.  UCF is known for running one of the best regionals in the country and we have been invited to host the national tournament in 2019.  Katie is the reason!”   </p>\n<p>We\'d like to recognize her nominators, Alisa Smith and James Beckman who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>If you would like to nominate a USPS employee, the EOM nomination packet is available in hard copy nominator form at <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Nomination-Letter-Final.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Nomination-Letter-Final.pdf</a> and supporter form <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Supportor-Letter-Form-Final.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EOM-Supportor-Letter-Form-Final.pdf</a> or for electronic submission visit <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com//SE/?SID=SV_7PNhTbow5cKW0zH\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com//SE/?SID=SV_7PNhTbow5cKW0zH</a></p>','2016-11-14','2016-11-18','http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2771','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2346,'Study-buddie (Find a buddie and study)','study-buddie-find-a-buddie-and-study','<p>Join the new social network designed to help students find a study partner or form study groups. The website is currently best for students in psychology courses, but with your help we can spread to even more classes. </p>\n<p>Just simply create an account and search for a study partner! </p>\n<p>Go Knights!!</p>','2016-11-11','2016-12-12','http://www.study-buddie.com/','Clifton Askew',NULL,'studybuddiemail@gmail.com','Clifton Askew','Publish',1),(2347,'LEAD Scholars Academy Undergraduate Research Program','lead-scholars-academy-undergraduate-research-program','<p>The LEAD Scholars Academy Undergraduate Research Program is designed to give current UCF students the opportunity to have a professional, hands-on, paid, career related experience with UCF faculty members. Accepted third and fourth year students will be funded up to 10 hours per week for 15 weeks during the spring semester. </p>\n<p>This program allows students in any field of study the opportunity to learn and develop research skills that can be applied to their future careers. This program differs from most undergraduate research programs at UCF, since it lasts for one semester, and is only available to UCF faculty members. Students will also participate in relevant leadership development workshops during the spring semester. </p>\n<p>A unique aspect of this program is the mentor relationship that is created. The faculty member will be expected to create and facilitate a mentor/mentee relationship with their matched student. Faculty and students will be matched based on the type of project available and the student\'s skills, abilities, and future career goals. </p>\n<p>If selected, there is a mandatory training session that students and faculty/staff must attend. Training times will be posted prior to the Fall deadline for applications to the program. Be sure to check <a href=\"http://lead.sdes.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://lead.sdes.ucf.edu/</a> for updates. </p>\n<p>Click here to apply: <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/research\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/research</a> </p>\n<p>Questions? Contact Mike McFadden at michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu.</p>','2016-11-14','2016-11-28','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/research','Mike McFadden','(407) 823-2223','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2348,'Light Up UCF Student Knights!','light-up-ucf-student-knights','<p>Come one, come all to this year\'s Light Up UCF student knights! Enjoy ice-skating, carnival rides, Insomnia Cookies, a photo booth, and performances by various UCF acapella groups. If you\'re lucky, you might catch Knightro skating on the ice! </p>\n<p>First SGA sponsored student knight: November 16th from 8 PM to 12 AM</p>\n<p>Second SGA sponsored student knight: November 22nd from 7 PM to 11 PM</p>\n<p>UCF students enjoy free admission to <em>one</em> of the two student knights if they bring a valid student ID to the event! There will no advanced ticket distribution this year. </p>\n<p>Every student who attends will be entered for a chance to win custom UCF scarves and \"Beat the Lines\" passes for early access to Universal Knights tickets.</p>','2016-11-16','2016-11-22','http://www.lightupucf.com/','Emily Dovydaitis','(407) 823-0320','sga_life@ucf.edu','Hannah Hollinger','Publish',1),(2349,'UCF Applied Project Management Certificate Program - Starts Feb 2017','ucf-applied-project-management-certificate-program-starts-feb-2017','<p>UCF Continuing Education is proud to bring you a valuable Applied Project Management Certificate Program that teaches practical principles and methods working in a project management capacity and prepares participants for the Certified Associate in Project Management (CAPM) and Project Management Professional (PMP) exams.</p>\n<p>Live course starting February 7, 2017 and June 6, 2017! <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/PM</a></p>\n<p>Why Choose our Program?\n• In person interactive 12 session program format to keep you on track\n• Includes textbooks, PowerPoint slide deck, online learning system and 1,300 online sample exam questions in registration fee\n• Learn and apply project management tools and techniques that are effective in initiating, planning, executing, monitoring, controlling and closing a project.\n• Learn test taking strategies to successfully pass the CAPM® or PMP® Exam\n• Meet PMI’s project management education requirement to become eligible to sit for the CAPM® or PMP® exam\n• Our program qualifies for most company tuition reimbursement and we offer payment plans</p>\n<p>Already a PMP® professional? We offer a variety of approved PMI professional development unit (PDU) courses to meet the need for project management credential holders to accumulate PDU hours necessary to maintain their designations. Learn more about our PDU courses here <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/4126/Project-Management---PDU-Courses/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/4126/Project-Management---PDU-Courses/</a></p>','2016-11-17','2017-01-27','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM','Kim Malac','(407) 882-0251','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Kim Malac','Publish',1),(2350,'Leadership Week 2017 Call for Proposals','leadership-week-2017-call-for-proposals','<p>The LEAD Scholars Academy invites individuals to share their leadership knowledge and experience with the UCF campus during Leadership Week 2017. The committee is looking for workshops or sessions that will challenge and inspire the campus community and showcase current leadership topics. Please complete the program proposal form at <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com//SE/?SID=SV_03exYw8YJ5ITAoZ\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com//SE/?SID=SV_03exYw8YJ5ITAoZ</a> . The deadline to submit a program proposal is Thursday, November 30, 2016. Program proposals will be evaluated and presenters will be notified by December 5, 2016</p>','2016-11-18','2016-12-01','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/callforprograms','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Germayne Graham','Publish',1),(2351,'UCF Priority 2017-2018 FAFSA Filing Date is December 1','ucf-priority-2017-2018-fafsa-filing-date-is-december-1','<p>The 2017-2018 Free Application for Federal Student Aid(FAFSA) became available on October 1. The 2017-2018 FAFSA uses tax information from 2015.</p>\n<p>UCF students are encouraged to file the FAFSA by UCF\'s priority filing date of December 1.</p>\n<p>The FAFSA can be completed online at <a href=\"http://www.fafsa.gov\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.fafsa.gov</a>.</p>','2016-11-21','2016-12-01','http://www.finaid.ucf.edu/FAFSA/','Karemah Manselle',NULL,'Karemah.manselle@ucf.edu','Karemah Manselle','Publish',1),(2352,'Study Union Fall 2016','study-union-fall-2016','<p>The UCF Study Union is right around the corner! Students, don\'t miss out on this great event. In preparation for final exams SARC will be hosting FREE review sessions, handing out snacks and prizes, and keeping you motivated to smash those finals! Study Union Sessions will be held in the UCF Student Union starting December 3rd-8th!</p>\n<p>For a complete schedule visit <a href=\"http://studentunion.ucf.edu/events/study-union\" rel=\"nofollow\">studentunion.ucf.edu/events/study-union</a>.</p>','2016-11-28','2016-12-09','http://studentunion.ucf.edu/events/study-union','Patricia Hartley',NULL,'Patricia.Hartley@ucf.edu','Danilsa Andujar','Publish',1),(2353,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining','afscme-collective-bargaining-1','<p>Collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida and The American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) to be held on Monday, December 5, 2016, from 3;00-5:00 p.m., at UCF Human Resources.</p>','2016-11-28','2016-12-05',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2354,'Omicron Delta Kappa national leadership honor society applications available!','omicron-delta-kappa-national-leadership-honor-society-applications-available','<p>Omicron Delta Kappa national leadership honor society applications available! Online application deadline is 2/1/17 at noon</p>\n<p>The Omicron Delta Kappa Society is the national leadership honor society for college students, faculty, staff, administrators, and alumni that recognizes and encourages superior scholarship, leadership, and exemplary character.</p>\n<p>The student and faculty members of Omicron Delta Kappa work closely together to foster leadership abilities within its members. The organization is also dedicated to a variety of projects that benefit the university and the surrounding community.</p>\n<p>Requirements for induction into the Central Florida Circle of ODK:</p>\n<p>Class standing: Junior (at least 60 credits), Senior, or Graduate Level\nMinimum GPA: 3.2 for undergraduates, 3.5 for graduate students\nInitiation fee of $95-includes lifetime membership and pin (graduation cords may be purchased for an additional $25) . If accepted your dues will be due by 2/10/17 at 12:00 PM.</p>\n<p>Demonstrated leadership in at least two of the five areas:\nScholarship\nAthletics\nCampus/Community Service, Social/Religious Activities, and Campus Government\nJournalism, Speech and the Mass Media\nCreative and Performing Arts</p>\n<p>How to Apply:</p>\n<p>Visit our website at <a href=\"https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form</a> to complete the online application\nQuestions may be directed to Dr. Stacey Malaret, Faculty Secretary for ODK, in the LEAD Scholars Academy Office, Ferrell Commons 165.</p>\n<p>Online application deadline is 2/1/17 at noon</p>','2016-12-02','2017-02-01','https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2355,'Canceled-USPS Employee walk','canceled-usps-employee-walk','<p>The Employee Walk sponsored by USPS Staff Council scheduled for this Saturday December 10th, 2016 has been cancelled.</p>','2016-12-08','2016-12-10','http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html','Deborah Pope','(407) 823-5284','Deborah.Pope@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',1),(2356,'USPS Staff Council Scholarship Application award live','usps-staff-council-scholarship-application-award-live','<p>The USPS Staff Council Spring Scholarship awards applications are now available and ready for you to apply.  The links to the applications are available on the website and the Councils Facebook page.  if you would like money to help you with classes and books, the Staff Council has an award for you or your dependent.  Apply today, the application is easy, online and can nab you some free money.  Apply before 11:59 p.m on January 15th.</p>','2016-12-08','2017-01-15','http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html','Jamie LaMoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',1),(2357,'Reflecting Pond Repairs','reflecting-pond-repairs','<p>The UCF Reflecting Pond will be drained from Monday, December 19th through January 13th in order to make repairs and improvements to the pond’s infrastructure. The dates are subject to change, based on weather conditions.</p>\n<p>For further information, contact <a href=\"mailto:Gary.Rudolph@ucf.edu\">Gary.Rudolph@ucf.edu</a> or <a href=\"tel:4078234984\" rel=\"nofollow\">407-823-4984</a>.</p>','2016-12-15','2017-01-13',NULL,'Gary Rudolph','(407) 823-4984','Gary.Rudolph@ucf.edu','Gary Rudolph','Publish',1),(2358,'Talk to Nursing Graduate Program Advisors Jan. 12 at Online Chat','talk-to-nursing-graduate-program-advisors-jan-12-at-online-chat','<p>Join the UCF College of Nursing graduate program advising team for an informative online chat session on Jan. 12 at 9 a.m. Learn the differences between our online and hybrid programs and get your most pressing questions answered about our nationally ranked graduate program.</p>\n<p>Online program options: Nursing Leadership and Management (MSN), Nursing and Healthcare Simulation (MSN, certificate), Nurse Educator (MSN, certificate), Advanced Practice Nurse (DNP), Nurse Executive (DNP), and Ph.D. in Nursing.</p>\n<p>Hybrid program options: Adult/Gero. Acute Care Nurse Practitoner (MSN, DNP, certificate), Adult/Gero. Primary Care Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate) and Family Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate).</p>\n<p>To log on to the chat, please visit the UCF Graduate Admissions website, click on the Student Tab and click on the “Chat With Us” link in the Resources section (left-hand side of page). If you have not done so already, you will need to complete the brief online registration form to create your login and password.</p>\n<p>For application deadlines and to learn more about the UCF College of Nursing, visit <a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.nursing.ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>For advising questions, email gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p>If you experience difficulty logging in, please contact Technical Support at support@chatuniversity.com or call 1.800.680.8911.</p>\n<p>We look forward to chatting with you!</p>','2017-01-12','2017-01-12','http://events.ucf.edu/event/114841/talk-to-graduate-nursing-advising-team-at-online-chat-msn-dnp-phd-certificates/','Ayanna Lopez or Ruth Visuete','(407) 823-2744','gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing, Office of Graduate Studies','Publish',1),(2359,'Spring Career Expo','spring-career-expo','<p>The Career Expo gives students and alumni the chance to meet with employers face-to-face to discuss career opportunities. This fair is perfect for those seeking full and part time professional positions, internships, volunteer positions and more! </p>\n<p>Bring lots of resumes for the chance to network and even interview onsite. Representatives from corporations of all industries and sizes participate. Last year the Expo drew close to 250 employers and over 1,600 students and alumni.</p>\n<p>View list of attending employers here: <a href=\"http://bit.do/SpringExpo17\" rel=\"nofollow\">bit.do/SpringExpo17</a></p>\n<p>PROFESSIONAL DRESS REQUIRED.</p>','2017-01-10','2017-01-31','http://events.ucf.edu/event/240933/spring-2017-career-expo/','Earnestine Jackson','(407) 823-4463','Earnestine.Jackson@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2360,'Career Readiness Week','career-readiness-week','<p>Ace your job search by perfecting your resume and practicing your interview skills with employers during Career Readiness Week. Network and prepare for the Career Expo all week long with helpful career prep workshops, Lunch and Learns, and professional head shot opportunities.</p>\n<p>September 23rd-27th, 2017 in the Career Services Building, all students and alumni welcome!</p>','2017-01-09','2017-01-27','https://directory.sdes.ucf.edu/file/588/news-attachment-career-readiness-week---january-23rd-27th-.pdf','Jessica Carter and Doris Alcivar','(407) 823-1366','Doris.Alcivar@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2361,'Spring Job Shadow Program','spring-job-shadow-program','<p>The Job Shadow Program pairs UCF students with employer/alumni partners to facilitate a one to five day job shadowing experience. Learn about a particular career or industry, gain workplace experience, and build your professional network.</p>\n<p>This program, held during academic breaks, will take place on May 8-12, 2017.</p>','2017-01-09','2017-01-29','http://career.ucf.edu/majors-and-careers#externship','Brooke Bivins','(407) 823-6689','externship@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2362,'Multicultural and First Generation Knights Networking Reception','multicultural-and-first-generation-knights-networking-reception','<p>This is an exclusive opportunity to connect multicultural &amp; first-generation students and alumni to premiere employers seeking to hire interns and full-time employees. Bring lots of resumes! Click the link to register.</p>\n<p>Monday, January 30th, 2017 from 5:30-7:30pm in the Cape FL Ballroom</p>','2017-01-09','2017-01-31','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ucfs-multicultural-first-generation-knights-networking-reception-tickets-29527666044','Tiana Tucker','(407) 823-2336','Tiana.Tucker@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2363,'Student Sustainability Coalition is here!','student-sustainability-coalition-is-here','<p>Sustainability Initiatives will begin hosting monthly Student Sustainability Coalition meetings. We recognize that many student organizations are likeminded in their goals at some capacity. For this reason, we can utilize this space to work together towards some great initiatives at UCF!</p>\n<p>This Thursday (1/12) at 4pm in the Student Union: Cedar Key, 223 is the first Student Sustainability Coalition meeting. These meetings will include:</p>\n<p>•             Sustainability leadership workshops </p>\n<p>•             RSO announcements </p>\n<p>•             Coordination/planning of the Green Jobs Fair</p>\n<p>•             Opportunities to gain insight into UCF sustainability operations</p>\n<p>All UCF students are welcome to attend! Each sustainability related RSO will be sending representation, so it’s also a great way to network and join other groups.</p>','2017-01-12','2017-01-12','http://sustainable.ucf.edu','Hannah Hollinger',NULL,'sustainable@ucf.edu','Hannah Hollinger','Publish',1),(2364,'Morgridge Student Success Foundation financial hardship awards','morgridge-student-success-foundation-financial-hardship-awards','<p>The Morgridge Family Foundation has generously given LEAD Scholars Academy a $4000 Student Support Foundation (SSF) grant to fund UCF students with financial hardship.</p>\n<p>Students who have a scholarly, community or personal financial need can apply for up to $200 in funding here: <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/ssf\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/ssf</a>. Only students with financial need are eligible to receive funding. UCF faculty and staff can also apply on behalf of a student.</p>\n<p>Examples of financial need may include funding needed for books, graduation materials, conference travel costs, food, rent, service learning background check fees, alternative break trip deposits, etc.</p>\n<p>Applications will be reviewed on a weekly basis by the UCF Student Support Foundation board (with all identifying information redacted) and these students will make decisions on grant applications based on the mission of the SSF and student need. The student board will have oversight from LEAD Scholars Academy staff. Student Financial Assistance will then disburse funds to approved student applicants directly from the SSF account.</p>\n<p>The SSF board exists to enrich the campus community through student-facilitated philanthropic support in order to promote the development and participation of UCF students in becoming global citizens and responsible leaders. SSF serves to also introduce student leaders to the goals of philanthropy work and working collectively to provide opportunities for the campus community at large.</p>','2017-01-26','2017-06-30','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/ssf','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2365,'Talk to Nursing Graduate Program Advisors Feb. 10 at Online Chat','talk-to-nursing-gradu