ogram Advisors March 14 at Online Chat','talk-to-nursing-graduate-program-advisors-march-14-at-online-chat','<p>Join the UCF College of Nursing graduate program advising team for an informative online chat session on Mar. 14 at 9 a.m. Learn the differences between our online and hybrid programs and get your most pressing questions answered about our nationally ranked graduate program.</p>\n<p>Online program options: Nursing Leadership and Management (MSN), Nursing and Healthcare Simulation (MSN, certificate), Nurse Educator (MSN, certificate), Advanced Practice Nurse (DNP), Nurse Executive (DNP), and Ph.D. in Nursing.</p>\n<p>Hybrid program options: Adult/Gero. Acute Care Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate), Adult/Gero. Primary Care Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate) and Family Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate).</p>\n<p>To log on to the chat, please visit the UCF Graduate Admissions website, click on the Student Tab and click on the “Chat With Us” link in the Resources section (left-hand side of the page). If you have not done so already, you will need to complete the brief online registration form to create your login and password.</p>\n<p>For application deadlines and to learn more about the UCF College of Nursing, visit <a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.nursing.ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>For advising questions, email <a href=\"mailto:gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu\">gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>If you experience difficulty logging in, please contact Technical Support at <a href=\"mailto:support@chatuniversity.com\">support@chatuniversity.com</a> or call 1.800.680.8911.</p>\n<p>We look forward to chatting with you!</p>','2017-03-06','2017-03-14','http://events.ucf.edu/event/114842/talk-to-graduate-nursing-advising-team-at-online-chat-msn-dnp-phd-certificates/','Ayanna Lopez or Ruth Visuete','(407) 823-2744','gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing, Office of Graduate Studies','Publish',1),(2367,'Talk to Nursing Graduate Program Advisors Apr. 10 at Online Chat','talk-to-nursing-graduate-program-advisors-apr-10-at-online-chat','<p>Join the UCF College of Nursing graduate program advising team for an informative online chat session on Apr. 10 at 3 p.m. Learn the differences between our online and hybrid programs and get your most pressing questions answered about our nationally ranked graduate program.</p>\n<p>Online program options: Nursing Leadership and Management (MSN), Nursing and Healthcare Simulation (MSN, certificate), Nurse Educator (MSN, certificate), Advanced Practice Nurse (DNP), Nurse Executive (DNP), and Ph.D. in Nursing.</p>\n<p>Hybrid program options: Adult/Gero. Acute Care Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate), Adult/Gero. Primary Care Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate) and Family Nurse Practitioner (MSN, DNP, certificate).</p>\n<p>To log on to the chat, please visit the UCF Graduate Admissions website, click on the Student Tab and click on the “Chat With Us” link in the Resources section (left-hand side of the page). If you have not done so already, you will need to complete the brief online registration form to create your login and password.</p>\n<p>For application deadlines and to learn more about the UCF College of Nursing, visit <a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.nursing.ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>For advising questions, email <a href=\"mailto:gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu\">gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>If you experience difficulty logging in, please contact Technical Support at <a href=\"mailto:support@chatuniversity.com\">support@chatuniversity.com</a> or call 1.800.680.8911.</p>\n<p>We look forward to chatting with you!</p>','2017-04-03','2017-04-10','http://events.ucf.edu/event/114842/talk-to-graduate-nursing-advising-team-at-online-chat-msn-dnp-phd-certificates/','Ayanna Lopez or Ruth Visuete','(407) 823-2744','gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing, Office of Graduate Studies','Publish',1),(2368,'2017 Leadership Week','2017-leadership-week','<p>Leadership Week is an initiative coordinated by the LEAD Scholars Academy with support from the Student Government Association, LEAD Students Association, The National Society of Leadership and Success, and numerous UCF offices and departments. Leadership Week was created to identify, recognize, and develop leadership among students, faculty, and staff.</p>\n<p>The theme this year is “Fantastic leaders and where to find them.” The events include workshops, guest speakers, and engaging activities. Students, faculty and staff are invited to attend all events.</p>','2017-02-20','2017-02-25','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/','Dr. Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2369,'UCF Hazing Prevention Workshops','ucf-hazing-prevention-workshops','<p>You are invited to attend spring semester workshops on hazing prevention. The topics that will be covered are: hazing behaviors, strategies of prevention, leadership development and group responsibility.</p>\n<p>LEAD Scholars Academy will offer several of these sessions during Leadership Week 2017: <a href=\"https://directory.sdes.ucf.edu/file/656/news-attachment-ucf-hazing-prevention-workshops.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://directory.sdes.ucf.edu/file/656/news-attachment-ucf-hazing-prevention-workshops.pdf</a>. See here for the full schedule of Leadership Week activities: <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/</a></p>\n<p>Participants will have the opportunity to gain leadership values and skills that will prevent hazing behavior at UCF. All workshops are open to students, faculty and staff.</p>','2017-01-31','2017-02-25','https://directory.sdes.ucf.edu/file/656/news-attachment-ucf-hazing-prevention-workshops.pdf','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2370,'Kill-A-Watt Competition Begins 02/01!','kill-a-watt-competition-begins-0201','<p>Want to win a scholarship for lowering your energy use? Participate in the Kill-A-Watt Energy Conservation Competition!</p>\n<p>In years past, this competition has resulted in an average savings of nearly $50,000 over the two-month period. We’ve saved the university a total of 2,216,485 kWh of energy, equivalent to $216,004. The energy saved could power 200 average homes in the United States for a full year!</p>\n<p>How To Win A Kill-A-Watt Scholarship</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Be an on-campus resident.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Participating communities: Apollo, Hercules, Nike, Lake Claire, Libra, Neptune, NorthView, Rosen, Towers, Greek Park</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Reduce your everyday energy usage.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Learn how at <a href=\"http://sustainable.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">sustainable.ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Work together with your hall/building to produce the largest energy savings within your community.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>On April 1st, find out if your building is a winner.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Residents of winning buildings can send in a video, digital art piece, or essay to enter. Submissions should demonstrate how you reduced your energy consumption. Email submissions to <a href=\"mailto:sustainable@ucf.edu\">sustainable@ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>Find out more on our website.</p>','2017-02-01','2017-03-31','http://sustainable.ucf.edu/kill-a-watt','Hannah Hollinger',NULL,'sustainable@ucf.edu','Hannah Hollinger','Publish',1),(2371,'2017 Heroes of the Dorm Competition','2017-heroes-of-the-dorm-competition','<p>Blizzard, Inc, has launched their 2017 Heroes of the Dorm competition. UCF needs two more highly motivated players to round out their team. This E-Sports tournament is for students only and we could win up to $500,000 in scholarship prizes.</p>','2017-02-02','2017-02-10','https://www.heroesofthedorm.com/','Patrick Williams','(813) 420-2400','prwilliams@knights.ucf.edu','Patrick Williams','Publish',1),(2372,'Clinton Global Initiative University (CGIU) applications now open!','clinton-global-initiative-university-cgiu-applications-now-open','<p>Do you know a student who has a great idea on how to create social change and wants to make the world a better place? If so, then please suggest that they apply for CGIU.</p>\n<p>Selected students will receive mentoring, partial funding for the conference trip to the annual CGIU meeting at Northeastern University in Boston, Massachusetts (October 13-15, 2017) AND seed money to help make their social change dream a reality! The meeting will bring together more than 1,000 innovative student leaders to make commitments to action that address some of the world’s most pressing challenges. Last year 17 UCF students were accepted. The early decision deadline is March 1, 2017 so students should apply soon! The final deadline is May 1, 2017 (May 2017 graduates are eligible to apply).</p>\n<p>The application may be found here: <a href=\"https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/meetings/cgi-university/apply/meeting-application</a></p>\n<p>CGIU Information session: Tuesday, February 21, 2017 from 3:30-5pm in LEAD Scholars Academy (Ferrell Commons 165)</p>\n<p>Please contact Mike McFadden at <a href=\"mailto:michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu\">michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu</a> or at 407-823-6957 with any questions!</p>','2017-02-02','2017-05-01','https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/meetings/cgi-university/apply/meeting-application','Mike McFadden','(407) 823-6957','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2373,'Scholarships A2O launched for 2017/2018 Scholarships','scholarships-a2o-launched-for-20172018-scholarships','<p>The General Scholarship Application for the 2017/2018 year is available for continuing and incoming admitted students to submit. Once you have submitted this application, throughout the year you will be matched with scholarship opportunities that you could be considered for and notified in the event that we need additional information for you to submit. For full scholarship consideration, please submit the general application by 3/3/2017.</p>\n<p>You will also have access to view a large scholarship listing for scholarship opportunities that are not determined through our system but may be determined through other areas on campus or outside of the university.</p>\n<p>Questions may be emailed to <a href=\"mailto:SFAScholarships@ucf.edu\">SFAScholarships@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2017-02-06','2017-03-03','http://finaid.ucf.edu/scholarships/index.html','Jamey Walker','(407) 823-2827','jamey.walker@ucf.edu','Jamey Walker','Publish',1),(2374,'Tutor Homeless Children','tutor-homeless-children','<p>You can sign-up to become a tutor for a homeless child living at an extended stay motel. This opportunity will not only create a tutor and student bond but help introduce a mentor figure in the child\'s life. ALL majors are welcomed and encouraged to come in order to provide a wide variety of different backgrounds. We hope you see this chance as a way to help empower children through education.</p>\n<p>This is a weekly commitment for one semester. Carpooling can be arranged from UCF and encouraged for all volunteers!</p>\n<p>You can get more information by contacting Yanelis at <a href=\"mailto:ucfchapter@chbob.org\">ucfchapter@chbob.org</a> or sign up at: <a href=\"http://www.chbob.org/volunteerUCF\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.chbob.org/volunteerUCF</a></p>','2017-02-03','2017-04-26','http://www.chbob.org/volunteerUCF','Yanelis Diaz',NULL,'ucfchapter@chbob.org','Children Beyond Our Borders UCF Chapter','Publish',1),(2375,'I-Corps Pizza Social & Informational Session','i-corps-pizza-social-informational-session','<p>We have all of the ingredients to help develop and build a business around your research ideas! Come network with us and learn more at this free social - open to students and faculty. Top it off with teams sharing their experience from the inaugural cohort. Don\'t miss your opportunity to do an optional 60-90 second quick pitch about your innovative idea.</p>\n<p>UCF I-Corps is a 5-week accelerated program to develop and build a business around your research. As a participant, you will be provided with $2,550 to advance and further develop your research and related market and business. By the end of the program, you will have developed a customer-validated business model, and discovered the market opportunity for your research innovation.</p>','2017-02-03','2017-02-13','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ucf-i-corps-information-and-pizza-social-february-13-tickets-17886334508','Nodar Gogoberidze',NULL,'nodari@ucf.edu','Cody Fishman','Publish',1),(2376,'December 2016 - USPS Employee of the Month - Lena Huntsman','december-2016-usps-employee-of-the-month-lena-huntsman','<p>Please join us in congratulating the USPS Employee of the Month for December 2016 - Lena Huntsman.</p>\n<p>Lena is the Program Assistant at Veterans Academic Resource Center.  She is described by her nominators as:</p>\n<p>“Lena works closely with our student veterans and dependents using VA Educational Benefits; resulting in millions of dollars being paid to our students. She has never failed to impress me with her patience, compassion, and care.  She works with student veterans who are at their breaking point and spends as much time as necessary to resolve the issue. While not a veteran herself, she often states the best part of her job is being able to give back to those who gave all for us.  She lives up to this on a daily basis.”</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize her nominators, Bethany Glassbrenner and Kelly D’Agostino who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2017-02-08','2017-02-10','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Debbie Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Debbie Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2377,'STEP club meeting','step-club-meeting','<p>Come on out to our STEP meeting on March 1st at 7pm in BA1 room 110! Come meet our dogs and find out who we are and what we do, we\'d love for you to join our team!</p>','2017-02-28','2017-03-02','https://www.facebook.com/stepucf/','Morgan Bell','(772) 418-5508','addyhudson@gmail.com','Addyson Hudson','Publish',1),(2378,'Women\'s History Month at UCF','womens-history-month-at-ucf','<p>March is Women’s History Month and several departments at UCF have compiled a full calendar of exciting, inspiring events. We hope to see you there!</p>\n<p>•   More than a Woman Opening Event: March 1 at 12pm in Student Union room 316A, hosted by Multicultural Student Center\n•   Women UKnighted Meet Your Mentor – Networking Event: March 1 at 6pm in FAIRWINDS Alumni Center, hosted by Career Services (must register in advance at link above!)\n•   ODI Series – Half the Sky: Turning Oppression into Opportunity for Women Worldwide (Part 1 – March 6 at 1:30pm; Part 2 – March 20 at 1:30pm)\n•   International Women’s Day Student Panel: March 6 at 12:30pm in Global UCF room 101ABC\n•   First annual WomanFest: 3/7 in UCF Library room 223 hosted by Women’s and Gender Studies Program and UCF Library; 10:30am-11:45pm AAUW Panel on leadership, 12:00-1:15pm Open Mic, 1:30-2:45pm Zine workshop\n•   Olympic Gold Medalist &amp; Survivor Kayla Harrison: March 21 at 3pm in Student Union room 316ABCD\n•   Actress &amp; UN Goodwill Ambassador Mira Sorvino – The Global Fight Against Human Trafficking on March 23 in Pegasus Ballroom at 3 pm hosted by Global Perspectives\n•   The Vagina Monologues hosted by Victim Services on March 25 at 7pm in Pegasus Ballroom\n•   Theatre UCF’s Hedda Gabler, 3/23-4/2, tickets available at <a href=\"http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=3443\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=3443</a> \n•   2nd Annual UCF Rosen College Women\'s Hospitality Leadership Forum, March 31\n•   Equal Pay Day, April 4: Student Union Atrium until 4pm, when we will have a group photo at the Reflecting Pond, WEAR RED &amp; bring your friends!\nDon’t miss the daily honoring of UCF faculty by the Center for the Success of Women Faculty and student leaders by the LEAD Scholars Academy.\nFor the full calendar of events and updates, be sure to check out <a href=\"http://diversity.ucf.edu/events/womens-history-month\" rel=\"nofollow\">diversity.ucf.edu/events/womens-history-month</a>.</p>','2017-02-28','2017-03-31','http://diversity.ucf.edu/events/womens-history-month/','Office of Diversity and Inclusion','(407) 823-6479','diverse@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',1),(2379,'Centsible Knights: #imsavingfor Social Media Photo Contest!','centsible-knights-imsavingfor-social-media-photo-contest','<p>Centsible Knights is hosting a photo contest on our Facebook and Instagram social media accounts! February 27 – March 4, 2017 is America Saves Week and in efforts to promote good savings behavior, we are having a photo contest to show off your savings goals! You can win one of two $50 Visa gift cards provided by FAIRWINDS Credit Union. To enter, like or follow Centsible Knights on Facebook or Instagram, post a picture of yourself that includes your savings goal, include the hashtag #imsavingfor and tag Centsible Knights in your post! The contest will start on March 1, 2017 and will end at 11:59pm EST on March 10, 2017. For more information about our photo contest and official rules, please visit <a href=\"http://finaid.ucf.edu/Financial-Literacy/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://finaid.ucf.edu/Financial-Literacy/</a></p>','2017-02-24','2017-03-10','http://finaid.ucf.edu/Financial-Literacy/','Yee Lui',NULL,'SFAFinLit@ucf.edu','Yee Lui','Publish',1),(2380,'January 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - Josefina Rosario','january-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-josefina-rosario','<p>Please join us in congratulating the USPS Employee of the Month for January 2017 -- Josefina Rosario.</p>\n<p>Josefina is the Senior Admissions Specialist in the Office of Undergraduate Admissions.  She is described by her nominators:</p>\n<p>“In Josefina’s role, she has a major role in setting the stage for a student’s first interaction with UCF. Both in her direct contact with students and through her leadership, setting an example and expectations, she is an integral part of starting the student’s journey in the UCF community.  Few people have a strong knack for processes AND exhibit the social skills necessary to be an effective communicator, empathetic listener, and an objective thinker.  She frequently goes above and beyond her own responsibilities, and never (ever!) shies away from taking on an additional favor or task.”</p>\n<p>We\'d also like to recognize her nominators, Debra Reynolds and Christopher Dahlstrand who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.  </p>\n<p>To nominate a USPS employee, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year/</a> or email us at Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu</p>\n<p>Josefina is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.\nCongratulations again to Josefina!</p>','2017-02-27','2017-03-06','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/employee-of-the-year','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2381,'Tickets for UCF Celebrates the Arts available starting March 1','tickets-for-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-available-starting-march-1','<p>Tickets for the third annual UCF Celebrates the Arts are available at <a href=\"http://www.arts.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.arts.ucf.edu</a> starting on March 1. A limited number of reserved seats may be purchased for $20 each from March 1-8 only. FREE, general admission seats will be available starting at noon on March 8. </p>\n<p>UCF Celebrates the Arts is a week-long festival at the Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts that celebrates UCF’s arts through exhibits, events, and performances. In its third year, the festival will include performances by Theatre UCF and UCF Music, gallery exhibits, films, and interactive displays by students in the School of Visual Art &amp; Design and Florida Interactive Entertainment Academy, a mini-festival themed around UCF’s Big Read, and events hosted by UCF’s partner organizations, the Orlando Repertory Theatre and Orlando Shakespeare Theater. </p>\n<p>The annual showcase is a unique event, bringing the skills, creativity, and dedication of the university’s artists to Orlando’s world-class performance venue.</p>\n<p>Some daily highlights include:\nFriday, April 7 and Saturday, April 8 – Rodgers &amp; Hammerstein’s OKLAHOMA!\nSaturday, April 8 – A mini-festival featuring The Grapes of Wrath, as part of the NEA sponsored Big Read\nSunday, April 9 – A concert by the UCF Choruses and alumni and faculty panels\nMonday, April 10 – UCF Bands concert and a cabaret by the Orlando Shakespeare Theater\nTuesday, April 11 – SVAD Digital Media Showcase – hands on playtesting of games developed by UCF students\nWednesday, April 12 – Percussion Festival and two film showcases \nThursday, April 13 – The REP presents Lois Lowry’s The Giver\nFriday, April 14 – The Flying Horse Big Band: The Bat Swings, premiering arrangements of the 1960s superhero movie and tv show</p>','2017-02-27','2017-04-06','https://arts.cah.ucf.edu/','Krissy Yagel','(407) 823-1500','boxoffice@ucf.edu','Heather Gibson','Publish',1),(2382,'HR Summit - May 11-12','hr-summit-may-11-12','<p><strong>UCF Continuing Education HR Summit</strong>\nMay 11-12 from 8 am - 5 pm</p>\n<p>2 day program, 14 speakers, professional development, networking, learn hot HR topics and earn recertification credits to remain certified</p>\n<p><strong>UCF Continuing Education</strong>\n3280 Progress Drive, Suite 700\nOrlando, FL 32826</p>\n<p>Continental Breakfast and Lunch provided</p>\n<p>Standard Price: $450\nUCF Alumni/Staff or UCF CE Alumni/Student Price: $405</p>\n<p>Register and view speakers/topics at <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM</a></p>','2017-05-11','2017-05-12','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM','Nicole Baker Rosa','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Nicole Baker Rosa','Publish',1),(2383,'2016-2017 Leadership Empowerment Program Institute','2016-2017-leadership-empowerment-program-institute','<p>The 2016-2017 Leadership Empowerment Program and the Office of Diversity and Inclusion invite you to attend our annual Leadership Institute, which will be held on March 24, 2017, from 8 AM to 12 PM at the FAIRWINDS Alumni Center. The Leadership Institute is a campus-wide professional development opportunity offered to the UCF faculty, staff, and students during the spring semester. The Leadership Institute is designed, organized, and sponsored by members of the current LEP class. Dr. Lisa Guion Jones Associate Provost for Strategy and Special Assistant to the President at the University of Central Florida will serve as our keynote speaker. In addition to our keynote speaker, we have seasoned leaders with a wide breadth of experience who will be serving as panelists. The theme of this year’s event is One Community, Collective Impact. The aim of the institute is to discuss how UCF’s strategic plan with its commitment to diversity and inclusion will impact the Central Florida community and beyond. Seating is limited for this event. Please register by March 17, 2017, at <a href=\"https://lep.online.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://lep.online.ucf.edu/</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Keynote Speaker</strong>\nDr. Lisa Guion Jones</p>\n<p>Associate Provost for Strategy and Special Assistant to the President\nProfessor of Higher Education at the University of Central Florida</p>\n<p><strong>Esteemed Panelists</strong></p>\n<p>Dr. Rosa Cintron (Dr. C.)</p>\n<p><strong>Associate Professor</strong></p>\n<p>UCF\nCollege of Education and Human Performance Alan Florez</p>\n<p><strong>CEO</strong></p>\n<p>Mitchell Noel Insurance and Director\nThe Weatherford Partners Brian Gray</p>\n<p><strong>Vice President</strong></p>\n<p>Organizational Capability &amp; HR Operations\nWyndham Vacation Ownership\nMichael Farmer</p>\n<p><strong>Director of Development</strong></p>\n<p>Equality Florida</p>\n<p>If you have any questions regarding this event, please contact Rhonda Hall via email at <a href=\"mailto:Rhonda.Hall@ucf.edu\">Rhonda.Hall@ucf.edu</a> or Arian L. Bryant at <a href=\"mailto:Arian.Bryant@ucf.edu\">Arian.Bryant@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2017-03-06','2017-03-17',NULL,'Rhonda C. Hall','(407) 823-5615','rhonda.hall@ucf.edu','Rhonda C. Hall','Publish',1),(2384,'You\'re invited to attend UCF\'s Coding Boot Camp Info Session March 22nd 2017','youre-invited-to-attend-ucfs-coding-boot-camp-info-session-march-22nd-2017','<p>If you are creative, driven, and intellectually curious, becoming a web developer could be a great career move-and the University of Central Florida’s Coding Boot Camp can be the perfect place to get started.</p>\n<p>Interested in learning more? Sign up to attend one of our FREE information sessions on March 22nd  2017 in the UCF Student Union and: </p>\n<p><em>Learn more about our upcoming NEW Summer Intensive, Full-time Program beginning May 2017! \n</em>Meet and greet some of our Coding Boot Camp Staff &amp; Instructors. \n<em>Hear testimonials from students who have successfully completed the program. \n</em>Participate in our \"Crushing Your Tech Interview\" workshop.</p>\n<p>Please RSVP by March 20th 2017 at <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/CBC\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.ce.ucf.edu/CBC</a>   </p>\n<p>Location:\nUCF STUDENT UNION- Key West Room 218 C&amp;D\n12715 Pegasus Dr. Orlando, FL 32816</p>\n<p>Session Times:\n11:00am-11:45am\n1:00pm-1:45pm</p>\n<p>SIGN UP TODAY! We are excited to meet you!</p>','2017-03-06','2017-03-22','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/CBC','Jyra Barnes',NULL,'Jyra.Barnes@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(2385,'Applications are Now Available to Join the Student Conduct Board!!','applications-are-now-available-to-join-the-student-conduct-board','<p>Are you interested in helping educate other students on their rights and responsibilities as University community members, facilitating an understanding of the balance between individual and community rights, and promoting a safe and inclusive atmosphere conducive to student success? Are you excited about encouraging students to embody the tenets of the UCF Creed: Integrity, Scholarship, Community, Creativity and Excellence?</p>\n<p>The Office of Student Conduct is looking for UCF faculty/staff and student community members who are dedicated to upholding the above-mentioned principles to volunteer to serve on the 2017 - 2018 Student Conduct Review Board. The application will be available on our website until April 1st.</p>\n<p>For additional information regarding the qualifications and training of Conduct Board Members, as well as a link to the application, please visit <a href=\"http://osc.sdes.ucf.edu/scb\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://osc.sdes.ucf.edu/scb</a>. If you need additional information, please feel free to contact Rosemarie Timothy at Rosemarie.Timothy@ucf.edu or st_condu@ucf.edu</p>','2017-03-08','2017-04-01','http://osc.sdes.ucf.edu/scb','Rosemarie Timothy','(407) 823-4638','Rosemarie.Timothy@ucf.edu','Rosemarie Timothy','Publish',1),(2386,'Closure Alert:  Main Floor, John C. Hitt Library','closure-alert-main-floor-john-c-hitt-library','<p>Beginning Friday, 3/10/17 at 5.00 p.m. until Monday, 3/20 at 7.30 a.m., the \"Student Union side\" of the 2nd (main) floor of the library building will be closed for work on the sprinkler system. Items from the Reference Collection will be retrieved by requests placed at the Circulation Desk. The \"Reflecting Pond\" side of the 2nd floor will remain open. Work is continuing on the 3rd-floor restrooms on the \"Student Union\" side, and continuing on the fifth-floor study area.</p>\n<p>More information on the 21st Century Library project is available at <a href=\"http://library.ucf.edu/21st/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://library.ucf.edu/21st/</a>\nLibrary hours during Spring Break can be checked at <a href=\"http://library.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://library.ucf.edu/</a></p>','2017-03-10','2017-03-20','http://library.ucf.edu/','Meg Scharf','(407) 823-6193','meg@ucf.edu','Meg Scharf','Publish',1),(2387,'Want Free Textbooks for the next Academic Year?','want-free-textbooks-for-the-next-academic-year','<p>If you can write an essay, you could be one of 19 UCF students to get free textbooks for the next academic year (2017-2018).</p>\n<p>Write a 250-word essay entitled, \"If I were a book, my title would be...\" and you could get FREE textbooks for the Fall 2017 and Spring 2018 semesters.</p>\n<p>Submit your application and essay here: <a href=\"https://businessservices.ucf.edu/bookstore-scholarship.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://businessservices.ucf.edu/bookstore-scholarship.html</a></p>','2017-03-10','2017-03-19','https://businessservices.ucf.edu/bookstore-scholarship.html','UCF Bookstore','(407) 823-2665','sm327@bncollege.com','Melissa Yopack','Publish',1),(2388,'UCF Project Management Information Session','ucf-project-management-information-session','<p>Join our information session March 21st at 5:30pm to learn more about the UCF Applied Project Management Certificate Program.</p>\n<p>Participants who attend our information session will learn about our program, gain a better understanding of the differences between the CAPM® and PMP® credentials, learn about the PMI eligibility requirements and network with other professionals.</p>\n<p>RSVP here <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/</a></p>','2017-03-21','2017-03-21','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/','Kim Malac','(407) 882-0251','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Kim Malac','Publish',1),(2389,'UCF Project Management Information Session','ucf-project-management-information-session-1','<p>Join our information session April 18th at 5:30pm to learn more about the UCF Applied Project Management Certificate Program.</p>\n<p>Participants who attend our information session will learn about our program, gain a better understanding of the differences between the CAPM® and PMP® credentials, learn about the PMI eligibility requirements and network with other professionals.</p>\n<p>RSVP here <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/</a></p>','2017-04-18','2017-04-18','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/','Kim Malac','(407) 882-0251','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Kim Malac','Publish',1),(2390,'LGBTQ Employer Panel','lgbtq-employer-panel','<p>Hear individual experiences about being out in the workplace and ask questions you may have about starting your career journey. </p>\n<p>Refreshments provided! </p>\n<p>No RSVP required.</p>','2017-03-17','2017-03-28','http://events.ucf.edu/event/355962/lgbtq-employer-panel-and-networking-mixer/','Laura Crouch','(407) 823-2361','Laura.Crouch@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2391,'Public Service Career Showcase','public-service-career-showcase','<p>Explore government, nonprofit and private sector careers, network with public service professionals and expand your internship for job search at the Public Service Career Showcase! This only happens once a year!</p>\n<p>Open to all UCF students &amp; alumni</p>\n<p>No need to RSVP.</p>','2017-03-17','2017-04-19','http://events.ucf.edu/event/397510/public-service-career-showcase/','Bradley Loomis','(407) 823-2361','career@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2392,'OMGraduation','omgraduation','<p>Are you a senior and still not sure how to write a resume? Do you think getting a root canal sounds more appealing than going to a job interview? Have you always meant to come into Career Services but never was able to fit the time into your busy schedule? If you find yourself stressed out about any of these questions and more, OMGraduation is for you! </p>\n<p>The days are broken into two sessions (both have the same content), so you can pick the session that works with your schedule!</p>\n<p>9:00-11pm- Resume, Job Searching, Networking, Interviewing and Social Media</p>\n<p>To RSVP: <a href=\"https://omgraduation2017morning.eventbrite.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://omgraduation2017morning.eventbrite.com</a></p>\n<p>1:30-4:00pm- Resume, Job Searching, Networking, Interviewing and Social Media</p>\n<p>To RSVP: <a href=\"https://omgraduation2017afternoon.eventbrite.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://omgraduation2017afternoon.eventbrite.com</a></p>\n<p>Get all the information you need to know before you graduate in one stop, during a time that is more convenient for your schedule. </p>\n<p>Space is very limited, so please RSVP today! Choose the session that works for you.  </p>\n<p>If you have any questions, contact Shauna Strickler at shauna.strickler@ucf.edu. OMGraduation is a free event hosted by Career Services.</p>','2017-03-17','2017-04-08','http://events.ucf.edu/event/397196/omgraduation/','Shauna Strickler','(407) 823-2361','career@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2393,'Statewide Job Fair','statewide-job-fair','<p>The Statewide Job Fair gives you the opportunity to network with over 150 employers, learn about full and part-time job opportunities, internships and more! Could you use a summer Internship? Graduating soon and need a job?</p>\n<p>Now is your chance, don’t miss out! Prepare, Practice &amp; Practice some more! Visit UCF Career Services to polish your resume &amp; cover letter and practice your elevator pitch!</p>\n<p>This fair is open to 9 other public universities in the state of FL. For more information and for a list of employers, visit:\n<a href=\"http://www.FloridaCareerCenters.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.FloridaCareerCenters.org</a></p>\n<p>IMPORTANT! \nDate: May 9, 2017\nTime: 10:00 AM to 3:00 PM\nLocation: CFE Arena</p>\n<p>Dress for Success! Professional Attire is required.</p>','2017-03-17','2017-05-09','http://events.ucf.edu/event/201106/statewide-job-fair/','Career Services','(407) 823-2361','career@ucf.edu','Melanie Brown','Publish',1),(2394,'Centsible Knights: #imsavingfor Social Media Photo Contest!','centsible-knights-imsavingfor-social-media-photo-contest-1','<p>Centsible Knights is hosting a photo contest on our Facebook and Instagram social media accounts! Centsible Knights is a financial literacy program available for UCF students. To promote good savings behavior, we are having a photo contest to show off your savings goals! You can win one of two $50 Visa gift cards provided by FAIRWINDS Credit Union. To enter, like or follow Centsible Knights on Facebook or Instagram, post a picture of yourself that includes your savings goal, include the hashtag #imsavingfor and tag Centsible Knights in your post! It\'s that easy! The contest will start on March 1, 2017 and will end at 11:59pm EST on March 22, 2017. For more information about our photo contest and official rules, please visit <a href=\"http://finaid.ucf.edu/Financial-Literacy/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://finaid.ucf.edu/Financial-Literacy/</a></p>','2017-03-17','2017-03-22','http://finaid.ucf.edu/Financial-Literacy/','Yee Lui',NULL,'ylui@ucf.edu','Yee Lui','Publish',1),(2395,'John C. Hitt Library Closures','john-c-hitt-library-closures','<p>Construction continues on the 21st Century Library project.  Current closures in the John C. Hitt Library include:\n<strong><em>4th floor stacks, call number areas N - QP981, the \"Student Union side\" of the 4th floor.  This area will be closed for the installation of sprinklers from Monday, 3/20 to Monday, 5/1.  Ask at the Circulation Desk for book retrieval from that area.\n</em></strong>5th floor study space is closed as the new quiet study zone space is created.\n***3rd floor restrooms on the \"Student Union side\" of the building are closed for renovation.\nAll of the inconvenience will result in great improvement, but we regret the disruption caused by the closure, noise, and dust.\nEarplugs are available at the Circulation Desk.\nInformation on the 21st Century Library project is available at <a href=\"http://library.ucf.edu/21st/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://library.ucf.edu/21st/</a></p>','2017-03-21','2017-05-01','http://library.ucf.edu/21st/','Meg Scharf','(407) 823-2564','libadmin@ucf.edu','Meg Scharf','Publish',1),(2396,'PTSD Awareness Seminar','ptsd-awareness-seminar','<p>UCF RESTORES and NAMI of Greater Orlando present PTSD Awareness Seminar on March 23, 2017 from 6-8pm.  This seminar will be held in Classroom Building II Room 206 on UCF\'s Main Campus.\nUCF RESTORES is a clinical research center dedicated to the study of all facets of anxiety, trauma and posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD) including etiology, psychopathology, treatment, resilience and prevention. A unique feature of UCF RESTORES is the development and use of established and emerging technologies to enhance prevention, intervention, treatment and resiliency efforts.\nThe National Alliance on Mental Illness (NAMI) is the nation’s largest grassroots mental health organization dedicated to improving the lives of persons living with serious mental illness and their families.\nBeginning at 6pm, attendees will have an opportunity to experience exposure therapy, used to treat PTSD by recreating the sights, sounds and smells of the traumatic event using virtual reality equipment.<br>\nAt 6:30pm, UCF RESTORES Director Dr. Deborah Beidel, Pegasus Professor of Psychology and Medical Education, will speak on the topic:  In the Aftermath of Trauma.\nAt 6:50pm, UCF RESTORES Co-Director Dr. Sandra Neer will speak on Trauma Management Therapy for PTSD, followed at 7:10pm by Dr. Robert Pollack, a Board Certified Psychiatrist, who will speak on Treatment of Depression in PTSD.\nA brief Question and Answer session from 7:30-7:50pm will conclude the seminar. Light refreshments will be provided.</p>','2017-03-20','2017-03-24','http://ucfrestores.com/','Jean Bagga','(407) 823-1269','jean.bagga@ucf.edu','JBagga.Department of Psychology','Publish',1),(2397,'Leadership Empowerment Program Institute','leadership-empowerment-program-institute','<p>The 2016-2017 Leadership Empowerment Program and the Office of Diversity and Inclusion invite you to attend our annual Leadership Institute, which will be held on March 24, 2017, from 8 AM to 12 PM at the FAIRWINDS Alumni Center. The Leadership Institute is a campus-wide professional development opportunity offered to the UCF faculty, staff, and students during the spring semester.  The Leadership Institute is designed, organized, and sponsored by members of the current LEP class. Dr. Lisa Guion Jones Associate Provost for Strategy and Special Assistant to the President at the University of Central Florida will serve as our keynote speaker. In addition to our keynote speaker, we have seasoned leaders with a wide breadth of experience who will be serving as panelists. The theme of this year’s event is One Community, Collective Impact. The aim of the institute is to discuss how UCF’s strategic plan with its commitment to diversity and inclusion will impact the Central Florida community and beyond. Seating is limited for this event.  Please register by March 23, 2017, at <a href=\"https://lep.online.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://lep.online.ucf.edu/</a>. </p>\n<p>If you have any questions regarding this event, please contact Rhonda Hall via email at Rhonda.Hall@ucf.edu or Arian L. Bryant at Arian.Bryant@ucf.edu.</p>','2017-03-20','2017-03-23',NULL,'Rhonda Hall','(407) 823-5615','rhonda.hall@ucf.edu','Rhonda Hall','Publish',1),(2398,'February 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - LaVera Henderson','february-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-lavera-henderson','<p>Please join us in congratulating the USPS Employee of the Month for February 2017 - LaVera Henderson.</p>\n<p>LaVera serves as the Administrative Assistant to the Director of the School of Public Administration in the College of Health and Public Affairs.   She is described by her nominators:</p>\n<p>“LaVera not only provides support to the Director but she is the sole administrative support for the 46 other school staff and more than 700 students.  This is done in ways many of us may not ever see.  LaVera consistently surpasses the expectations of her already daunting position description, and does so with a positive attitude that improves the experience of colleagues, students, faculty and the campus community at large. \nLaVera’s commitment to UCF is reflected in the manner she models the UCF values.  Her integrity is superior and has been displayed her entire life.”</p>\n<p>We\'d like to recognize her nominators, Nasrin Lakhani and Maria Augustin who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.  </p>\n<p>To nominate a USPS employee, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/#questions\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/#questions</a> or email us at Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu. </p>\n<p>LaVera is not eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to LaVera!</p>','2017-03-24','2017-03-31','http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/#questions','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2399,'Equal Pay Day events at UCF','equal-pay-day-events-at-ucf','<p>Join the Office of Diversity and Inclusion, the Department of Legal Studies, and NOW at UCF for a screening of the documentary \"Equal Means Equal\" on March 30th, 6-9pm in HPA1 room 112! <a href=\"http://equalmeansequal.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://equalmeansequal.com/</a></p>\n<p>EQUAL MEANS EQUAL offers an unflinching look at how women are treated in the United States today. Examining both real-life stories and precedent-setting legal cases, director Kamala Lopez uncovers how outdated and discriminatory attitudes inform and influence seemingly disparate issues, from workplace harassment to domestic violence, rape and sexual assault to the foster care system, and the healthcare conglomerate to the judicial system. Along the way, she reveals the inadequacy of present laws that claim to protect women, ultimately presenting a compelling and persuasive argument for the urgency of ratifying the Equal Rights Amendment.\nThere will be a moderated discussion after the screening.</p>\n<p>Equal Pay Day is April 4th – and we have so many ways for you to join in! Bring all your friends (men, women, everyone!) at 4pm for a group photo at the Reflecting Pond and WEAR RED! We want to get as many people as possible (in red!) in this photo! If you don’t wear red, stop by the Student Union first for a sticker and to tell us why you need equal pay! If you can’t make the photo but still want to participate, you can send a photo of your department or just yourself (wearing red!) to victoria.weston@ucf.edu to be included in a university-wide collage! Or, stop by our Equal Pay Day prequel event on March 29th on the Free Speech Lawn all day to get your picture taken and tell us why you need equal pay! Posters are encouraged for the photo – we’ll be making them all day March 29th if you want to take a minute to do so! #UCFEqualPayDay #EqualPayForEqualWork</p>','2017-03-27','2017-04-04','https://www.facebook.com/events/1882452685368398/','Victoria Weston','(407) 823-4112','victoria.weston@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',1),(2400,'Stressbusters Presentation by CAPS Peer Educators','stressbusters-presentation-by-caps-peer-educators','<p>Stressbusters Presentation serves to educate students on tips on how to maintain their mental fitness and reduces stress during Finals Week. The Presentation will be on Monday April 17th at 2pm in Student Union Cedar Key Room 223. There will be free promotional items for those that attend the presentation.</p>','2017-04-17','2017-04-17',NULL,'Alexi Minnick',NULL,'Alexandra.Minnick@ucf.edu','Alexi Minnick','Publish',1),(2401,'The Great Duck Derby - Volunteers Needed','the-great-duck-derby-volunteers-needed','<p>Gather up the kids and head on out to The Great Duck Derby for a day of family fun at Mead Botanical Garden in Winter Park, FL. The Duck Derby features a series of little rubber duck races in Alice\'s Pond and a host of great children\'s activities. Adopt a duck for just $5, all other activities are free. Activities including the duckoration station, bounce houses, Silly Song Sing-along with Mr. Harley, hayrides, nature hikes, and scavenger hunts, games and crafts, animal encounters and face paintings. Free tree giveaway. Explore the Winter Park Fire Department\'s big red engine. Bring a picnic or grab lunch at one of the onsite food trucks and treat stops. It\'s a great way to spend the day in the great outdoors! Also available: t-shirts, duck whistles, caps and visors. Enter drawing for a free week at the wildly popular Mead Garden Young Naturalist Summer Camp. All proceeds benefit youth programming at Meads Botanical Garden.\nThere are opportunities for volunteer hours and the help would be greatly appreciated. For volunteer information contact us at <a href=\"mailto:info@meadgarden.org\">info@meadgarden.org</a>.</p>','2017-04-06','2017-04-22','http://www.meadgarden.org','Beverly',NULL,'volunteer@meadgarden.org','Mead Botanical Garden','Publish',1),(2402,'Clinton Global Initiative University (CGIU) nominations!','clinton-global-initiative-university-cgiu-nominations','<p>CGI University is recruiting student leaders who are committed to addressing the world’s most pressing problems for its 2017 annual meeting. Accepted students will have the opportunity to meet with 1,000 fellow social innovators at an inspiring 3-day conference at Northeastern University and hear from high-caliber speakers and thought leaders, including President Bill Clinton and Chelsea Clinton. The deadline for students to apply is May 1, 2017.</p>\n<p>If you would like to nominate an undergraduate or a graduate student who would be an exceptional candidate for this opportunity, please take 2 minutes to fill out this nomination form at: <a href=\"https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/cgiu/form#Nominate-a-Student-to-Apply-for-CGI-U-2017\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/cgiu/form#Nominate-a-Student-to-Apply-for-CGI-U-2017</a>. To learn more about CGIU please see here: <a href=\"https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/meetings/cgi-university\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/meetings/cgi-university</a></p>\n<p>If you have any questions please contact Mike McFadden with the LEAD Scholars Academy at <a href=\"mailto:michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu\">michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2017-04-06','2017-05-01','https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/cgiu/form#Nominate-a-Student-to-Apply-for-CGI-U-2017','Michael McFadden','(407) 823-2223','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2403,'2017 UCF Financial Wellness Series','2017-ucf-financial-wellness-series','<p>The annual UCF Financial Wellness Series (previously the Retirement and Investment Series) will be held from April 3 through April 27, 2017.</p>\n<p>Schedules and descriptions of workshops and other series details: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series</a>.</p>\n<p>For questions please contact <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\">benefits@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2017-04-03','2017-04-27','https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series/','HR Benefits Section','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',1),(2404,'March 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month -- Kaitlyn Sweeney','march-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-kaitlyn-sweeney','<p>Please join us in congratulating the USPS Employee of the Month for March 2017 - Kaitlyn Sweeney.</p>\n<p>Kaitlyn Sweeney is the Office Assistant in Legal Studies at the College of Health and Public Affairs.  She is described by her nominators as:</p>\n<p>“Kaitlyn is a self-directed, motivated employee who interacts will with both students and faculty.  She is the face of the Legal Department with the students and promotes the department; serving not only as receptionist but liaison for the faculty in their interactions with students.</p>\n<p>Kaitlyn fully exhibits the values and creed of UCF through her activities in each of the areas of Integrity, Scholarship, Community, Creativity and Excellence.  She is the glue that binds our department together.” </p>\n<p>We\'d like to recognize her nominators, Dr. Abby Milon and David Slaughter, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.  </p>\n<p>To nominate a USPS employee, please visit the Human Resources website at <a href=\"http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/#questions\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/#questions</a> or email us at Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu </p>\n<p>Kaitlyn is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>','2017-04-13','2017-04-20','http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/#questions','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2405,'USPS staff general assembly','usps-staff-general-assembly','<p>The 2017 General staff assembly will be held Friday, April 14th at 9:15 in the Pegasus Ballroom. All USPS staff are invited to attend. the doors will open at 8:30, refreshments will be served. Please consider attending and learning something new!</p>','2017-04-14','2017-04-14',NULL,'Deborah Pope','(408) 823-3956','Deborah.Pope@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',1),(2406,'Megawatt Ventures Applications Open for UCF Students and Faculty','megawatt-ventures-applications-open-for-ucf-students-and-faculty','<p>MegaWatt Ventures is funded by the US Department of Energy in an effort to focus regional resources to empower the United States into a clean technology super-region. MegaWatt Ventures – a $50,000+ prize competition for student scientists, engineers, and entrepreneurs in clean tech, renewable energy, and energy efficiency – is accepting applications through April 21! This exciting accelerator-based competition provides top-notch mentoring and entrepreneurial training to enable teams to inevitably compete in a grand finale event with a $50,000 grand prize and a chance to move on to a national competition with an additional $50,000 prize available. This final forum pits highly competitive small businesses to pitch their technology and business model in front of a prestigious judges panel, comprised of renowned institutional investors as well as energy industry executives.</p>\n<p>10 teams will be selected to participate with the final competition occurring in June 2017. Eligible teams/companies must be comprised 50% or more of current university students (or students who enrolled in the 2016/2017 academic year) to apply. For more details on the competition and how to apply please visit <a href=\"http://www.megawattventures.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.megawattventures.com</a> or join us on Facebook and Twitter. Applications can be submitted at: <a href=\"https://www.f6s.com/megawattventures\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.f6s.com/megawattventures</a>.</p>\n<p>The MegaWatt Ventures team is available to provide assistance and guidance on your applications. Contact Jack Henkel at <a href=\"mailto:Jack@ucf.edu\">Jack@ucf.edu</a> or 407-882-0663 with any questions.</p>','2017-04-17','2017-04-21','http://www.megawattventures.com','Jack Henkel','(407) 882-0663','jack@ucf.edu','Jack Henkel','Publish',1),(2407,'Once in my LIFE: Embodied Journeys - an intergenerational performance','once-in-my-life-embodied-journeys-an-intergenerational-performance','<p>The public performance of a unique devised intergenerational play; featuring the words and stories of student participants from UCF and from the Learning Institute for Elders (LIFE) at UCF.    April 25, 7:00 pm  in VAB 132.  Free performance.</p>','2017-04-18','2017-04-25',NULL,'Claudia Schippert',NULL,'claudia.schippert@ucf.edu','Claudia Schippert','Publish',1),(2408,'Energy Whiz at the Florida Solar Energy Center, UCF Brevard Campus, Cocoa','energy-whiz-at-the-florida-solar-energy-center-ucf-brevard-campus-cocoa','<p>Energy Whiz is an annual event featuring student driven energy demonstrations, including model solar car races, energy efficient construction practices, electric powered go-carts, and solar cooking. Food trucks and the Solar Music DJ will be on hand. This family friendly event scheduled for Saturday, May 13, 2017 is in need of volunteers to serve as judges and support staff for the 1,000+ participants.</p>','2017-04-24','2017-05-13','http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/go/ewvolunteer','Susan or Penny','(321) 638-1017','susan@fsec.ucf.edu','Colleen Kettles','Publish',1),(2409,'Megawatt Ventures Applications Open for UCF Students and Faculty','megawatt-ventures-applications-open-for-ucf-students-and-faculty-1','<p>MegaWatt Ventures is funded by the US Department of Energy in an effort to focus regional resources to empower the United States into a clean technology super-region. MegaWatt Ventures – a $50,000+ prize competition for student scientists, engineers, and entrepreneurs in clean tech, renewable energy, and energy efficiency – is accepting applications through April 21! This exciting accelerator-based competition provides top-notch mentoring and entrepreneurial training to enable teams to inevitably compete in a grand finale event with a $50,000 grand prize and a chance to move on to a national competition with an additional $50,000 prize available. This final forum pits highly competitive small businesses to pitch their technology and business model in front of a prestigious judges panel, comprised of renowned institutional investors as well as energy industry executives.</p>\n<p>10 teams will be selected to participate with the final competition occurring in June 2017. Eligible teams/companies must be comprised 50% or more of current university students (or students who enrolled in the 2016/2017 academic year) to apply. For more details on the competition and how to apply please visit <a href=\"http://www.megawattventures.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.megawattventures.com</a> or join us on Facebook and Twitter. Applications can be submitted at: <a href=\"http://www.f6s.com/megawattventures\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.f6s.com/megawattventures</a>.</p>\n<p>The MegaWatt Ventures team is available to provide assistance and guidance on your applications. Contact Jack Henkel at Jack@ucf.edu or 407-882-0663 with any questions.</p>','2017-04-21','2017-04-28','http://www.megawattventures.com','Jack Henkel','(407) 882-0663','Jack@ucf.edu','Jack Henkel','Publish',1),(2410,'Congratulations to the 2017-2018 Class of the Leadership Empowerment Program!','congratulations-to-the-2017-2018-class-of-the-leadership-empowerment-program','<p>With a great deal of pride and enthusiasm, the UCF Office of Diversity and Inclusion announces the 2017-2018 Class of the Leadership Empowerment Program (LEP). \nLEP provides opportunities for selected faculty and staff to gain career-enhancing skills and experiences in today’s changing educational environment. The 2017-18 program will engage 19 scholars in an exploration of leadership principles and strategies, professional skills, and higher education issues through self-reflection, mentorship, engagement with dozens of guest speakers, and project development.\nThe UCF Office of Diversity and Inclusion congratulates these rising stars for their commitment to their careers. Their advancement benefits the entire UCF community.</p>\n<p>Dr. Anya Andrews, Director of Research and Associate Professor of Medicine, College of Medicine</p>\n<p>Justin Andrade, LGBTQ+ Services Coordinator, Social Justice &amp; Advocacy</p>\n<p>Dr. Po-Ju Chen, Associate Professor, Rosen College of Hospitality</p>\n<p>Kalpana Deva, Compliance Coordinator, Research &amp; Commercialization</p>\n<p>Veena Garib, Associate Director of Employer Relations, Career Services</p>\n<p>Renée Grigor, Talent Acquisition Manager, Human Resources</p>\n<p>Joffrey Heard, Legal Assistant, Student Legal Services</p>\n<p>Dr. Jennifer Kent-Walsh, Professor and Faculty Excellence Coordinator, College of Health and Public Affairs</p>\n<p>Margaret Mlachak, Program Manager of the Operations Unit, Office of the Provost</p>\n<p>Carrie Moran, User Engagement Librarian, John C. Hitt Library</p>\n<p>Lindsay Neuberger, Ph.D., Associate Professor, Nicholson School of Communication</p>\n<p>Jerron Parker, Assistant Director, Housing and Residence Life</p>\n<p>Raphel Robinson, Associate Director, Academic Support Services</p>\n<p>Josefina Rosario, Senior Admissions Specialist, Undergraduate Admissions</p>\n<p>Jennifer Sandoval, Associate Professor, Nicholson School of Communication</p>\n<p>Andrea Snead, Sport Clubs and Adaptive Recreation Coordinator, Recreation and Wellness Center</p>\n<p>Jessica Squires, Assistant Director, Global Perspectives</p>\n<p>Dr. Stephanie Vie, Department Chair, Department of Writing and Rhetoric</p>\n<p>Deborah Watkins, Admissions Specialist, Undergraduate Admissions</p>\n<p>Learn more about LEP on our website below.</p>','2017-04-24','2017-05-31','https://diversity.ucf.edu/faculty-staff/leadership-empowerment-program/','Karen Morrison','(407) 823-6479','diverse@ucf.edu','Office of Diversity and Inclusion','Publish',1),(2411,'April 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month -- Gary Burkhart','april-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-gary-burkhart','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for April 2017 – Gary Burkhart</p>\n<p>Gary is the Custodial worker in the Housing Department of Facility and Safety.  He is described by his nominators as:</p>\n<p>“Gary exemplifies the ideal University of Central Florida employee.  During his time with UCF, he has consistently gone above and beyond what is normally expected of a custodial worker.  Gary is the pillar of strength within the housekeeping department and plays a vital role in maintaining the cleanliness and safety of the university.  During a meeting with the building managers in Gary’s area, they had nothing but praises for his character, organization, and initiative.  </p>\n<p>UCF’s goal is to be the best, Gary understand this and works towards this goal every day.  He always looks for ways to improve himself and those around him.”</p>\n<p>We\'d also like to recognize her nominators, Alexander Fountain and Rachel Perry, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>To nominate a USPS employee, please visit   the Human Resources website at <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a> or email us at Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu </p>\n<p>Gary is not eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>','2017-05-05','2017-05-12','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2412,'United Way Book Drive','united-way-book-drive','<p>Each year the United Way Campaign Team at UCF hosts a book drive to support the Heart of Florida United Way summer literacy initiatives.  </p>\n<p>Books should be new condition, age-appropriate \"pleasure reading\" books.  The books will go home with youth; the more interesting the book, the more likely it will be opened and read.  We\'re hoping to focus on books for middle and high school level students.</p>\n<p>Please collect books in your departments and turn them in to Millican Hall 384 by close of business on May 31st. </p>\n<p>Summer reading loss is a serious problem contributing to a significant grade achievement gap.  A lack of available reading materials for at-risk youth is a major factor.  Summer literacy initiatives across the region are working to address this issue. We value the educational well-being of our community, and we can help by supporting the United Way\'s book drive!</p>','2017-05-10','2017-05-31','http://liveunited.ucf.edu/bookdrive/','Tee Rogers','(407) 823-3094','LiveUnited@ucf.edu','Tee Rogers','Publish',1),(2413,'Across the Board Website','across-the-board-website','<p>The university engages in business contracts and relationships that benefit the university community in many ways.  Employees have a responsibility to uphold the university\'s obligations and to act in the interest of our institution.</p>\n<p>\"Across the Board\" is a new website that provides employees information about exclusive and non-exclusive contracts.  The site provides additional resources and links to help employees learn information about our business services partners. The goal is to ensure that we all do our part to maintain these beneficial relationships.</p>','2017-05-16','2017-12-31','http://admfin.ucf.edu/across-the-board','Sue Gonzalez','(407) 823-3539','sue.gonzalez@ucf.edu','Sue Gonzalez','Publish',1),(2414,'FREE summer theatre for UCF employees','free-summer-theatre-for-ucf-employees','<p>This summer, UCF employees can use the code UCFstaff17 for two free tickets to The Lion in Winter and Seminar at Theatre UCF. To redeem, please visit <a href=\"http://www.theatre.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.theatre.ucf.edu</a> or call the UCF School of Performing Arts Box Office at 407-823-1500.</p>\n<p>2017-18 Season subscriptions available now! To find a package that works best for you, please visit <a href=\"http://www.theatre.ucf.edu/tickets.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.theatre.ucf.edu/tickets.php</a>.</p>\n<p>The Lion in Winter\nBy James Goldman\nJune 8-18 • Main Stage\nA modern day classic with sibling rivalry, adultery and dungeons...</p>\n<p>Seminar\nBy Theresa Rebeck\nJune 29-July 9 and August 24-27 • Main Stage\nInnocence collides with experience in this biting comedy...</p>\n<p>Iphigenia and Other Daughters\nAdapted by Ellen McLaughlin\nSeptember 14-24 • Black Box\nA modern retelling of the fall of the House of Atreus...</p>\n<p>Of Thee I Sing\nBook by George S. Kaufman and Morrie Ryskin, Music by George Gershwin, Lyrics by Ira Gershwin\nOctober 12-22 • Main Stage\nThe first musical to win the Pulitzer Prize...</p>\n<p>An Octoroon\nBy Branden Jacobs-Jenkins\nNovember 9-19 • Black Box\nWinner of the 2014 OBIE Award for Best New American Play...</p>\n<p>Pentecost\nBy David Edgar\nJanuary 25-February 4 • Main Stage\nThis powerful play by the Tony Award winning adapter of Nicholas Nickleby won the Evening Standard Award for Best Play of 1995...</p>\n<p>The Day Before Yesterday\nA New Play by Israel Horowitz\nFebruary 22-March 4 • Black Box\nBased around the terrorist attack on the Bataclan concert hall in Paris...</p>\n<p>Bernarda Alba\nLyrics and Music by Michael John LaChiusa, Based on the play The House of Bernarda Alba by Federico García Lorca\nMarch 22-31 • Main Stage\nPulsing castanets, trilling Spanish guitars...</p>\n<p>Fine print: Discount code cannot be combined with other offers. Discount code does not guarantee seating preference and is dependent on availability. It is highly recommended to reserve tickets in advance. Discount code may not be redeemed for cash. Discount excludes special events and benefits. No retroactive discounts. The UCF School of Performing Arts Box Office is open Monday-Friday, noon-5 p.m.</p>','2017-05-17','2017-07-09','http://www.theatre.ucf.edu/tickets.php','Krissy Yagel','(407) 823-1500','boxoffice@ucf.edu','Theatre UCF','Publish',1),(2415,'Call for Posters: Pulse Anniversary Blood Drive','call-for-posters-pulse-anniversary-blood-drive','<p>The 400 blood donors expected to participate in the June 8th blood drive will be waiting in the Atrium of Health Professions 1.  We\'re asking student organizations and departments to thank them for saving lives with us by creating a poster with a theme of gratitude for blood donors and/or support and remembrance of the Pulse tragedy.  Posters will be hung from the banisters in the Atrium on the day of the event.</p>\n<p>Posters should be no larger than 3 ft by 2 ft.  They may be poster paper or fabric (note we will need to put holes in the corners to hang them).</p>\n<p>Posters should clearly identify the organization or department and send a positive message of support and gratitude.</p>\n<p>Please turn in to Millican Hall 384 by 5 p.m. on June 5th.  If you want your art returned to you be sure there is contact information on the back of the poster.</p>\n<p>To donate blood with us or learn more about the Pulse Anniversary events, visit <a href=\"http://blooddrives-ucf.org/special-event\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://blooddrives-ucf.org/special-event</a>.</p>','2017-05-23','2017-06-05','http://blooddrives-ucf.org/special-event','Tee Rogers','(407) 823-3094','blooddrives@ucf.edu','Tee Rogers','Publish',1),(2416,'Collective Bargaining Notice - AFSCME','collective-bargaining-notice-afscme','<p>A collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will take place on Tuesday, May 30, from 11:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovation Center Suite 100.</p>','2017-05-24','2017-05-30',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2417,'Attend UCF Continuing Education’s complimentary Project Management information session on Thursday June 22nd at 5:30pm','attend-ucf-continuing-educations-complimentary-project-management-information-session-on-thursday-june-22nd-at-530pm','<p>Do you manage teams want to learn valuable skills about leading and directing projects? Then earning the Project Management Certification is the next career path for you! </p>\n<p>Attend UCF Continuing Education’s complimentary Project Management information session on Thursday June 22nd at 5:30pm to learn about our Applied Project Management Certificate Program. <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ce.ucf.edu/PM</a> </p>\n<p>Attendees will gain a better understanding about the differences between the CAPM® and PMP® credentials, learn about the PMI exam eligibility requirements and application process.  </p>\n<p>RSVP Here <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/</a></p>','2017-06-22','2017-06-22','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/3027/Project-Management-Open-House/','Kim Malac','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Kim Malac','Publish',1),(2418,'May 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - Elba Miscannon','may-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-elba-miscannon','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for May 2017 – Elba Miscannon.</p>\n<p>Ms. Elba Miscannon is the Executive Administrative Assistant in the Learning Support Services within Student Development and Enrollment Services.   </p>\n<p>She is described by her nominators as:\n“Creative, committed, diligent, inclusive and loyal are all qualities that Elba possess. She has a very strong sense of integrity and contributes to an inclusive community, which permeates to others in our unit.\nWhether it is tutoring a student, interpreting, helping students find jobs on campus, listening to students or helping someone, she is always willing to step up and step out to support her colleagues and UCF students.”</p>\n<p>We\'d like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. Elba receives a one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, an introduction at the UCF Board of Trustees, a marquee announcement, goody bag, certificate, and surprise presentation. Elba is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d also like to recognize her nominators, Alexander Fountain and Rachel Perry, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.  </p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit Employee of the Month form.</p>\n<p>Elba is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program. \nCongratulations again to Elba!!</p>','2017-05-30','2017-06-06','http://hr.ucf.edu/liaisons-and-managers/eom-nomination-form/','Debbie Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',1),(2419,'Office Plus/Staples Business Advantage Vendor Show','office-plusstaples-business-advantage-vendor-show','<p>You are cordially invited to the Office Plus/Staples Business Advantage Show. </p>\n<p>Come see all the new products and serviced offered by: \nStaples and their partnered vendors\nOffice Plus\nUCF Print Shop\nThe SPOT</p>\n<p>The show will be held at the Live Oak Event Center on Friday, June 2 from 11 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.\nLight refreshments and snacks will be served.</p>','2017-05-30','2017-06-02','https://stuff4u.wufoo.com/forms/m1bwumvk1gzm2p6/','Sue Gonzalez','(407) 823-3539','sue.gonzalez@ucf.edu','Sue Gonzalez','Publish',1),(2420,'Language Volunteers Needed','language-volunteers-needed','<p>WANTED:   SPEAKERS OF LANGUAGES/DIALECTS FROM THE FOLLOWING COUNTRIES/REGIONS:\n Sweden          Palestine             Azeri         Mozambique         Bosnia              Russia \nUkraine         Afghanistan        Sri Lanka              Bosnia(Roma)    Kurd                     </p>\n<p>The Department of Theatre is going to present a play – PENTECOST – next academic year.</p>\n<p>PENTECOST is a play of politics and ideas set within the context of a post-Communist Eastern Europe. It challenges our ideas of ethnicity, religion, nationalism and attitudes toward art, by asking the ‘big question’ - What if what we know as ‘the Renaissance’ took place 100 years earlier, and elsewhere?</p>\n<p>The play is set to run January 25 through February 4, 2018on Theatre UCF‘s Mainstage. The play involves not only an unusual amount of dialect work from the directors and cast, but also brief periods speaking in the language of their diverse cast of characters.</p>\n<p>TIME COMMITMENT: If you are fluent in any of the languages above, we will accommodate your availability as much as possible. Ideally, you will meet with our voice/speech coach and actors for an hour or two, you will read short sections of our script, and we will record your session.  Possible chance of a second session.  All of this we would like to take place during the months of August and September, into early October.</p>\n<p>Those assisting with this project will receive a complimentary ticket to the production.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in contributing to this multi-cultural production, please send via email to Pentecostsmteam@gmail.com :\nyour name,\nUCF department (major/affiliation),\nclass year or years with UCF,\nwhich region/language you are from/fluent or familiar with,\nand what schedule conflicts you may have.</p>\n<p>We will process the volunteers during the summer, and contact you early in the fall.\nThanks for your consideration, and we hope to be working with you soon.</p>','2017-05-31','2017-08-25','http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=3839','Justin Little',NULL,'Pentecostsmteam@gmail.com','Christopher Niess','Publish',1),(2421,'Community Outreach Opportunity: Summer Science Camp','community-outreach-opportunity-summer-science-camp','<p>Join us as we conduct experiments and workshops revolving science this summer! Children Within Our Borders is bringing science fun to underprivileged children in Orlando, Fl. Sessions will be held on Wednesdays from 1-3pm at Project Somos June 7th and 21st and July 5th and 19th. </p>\n<p>If you\'re interested in volunteering please let us know by signing up here: <a href=\"http://www.chbob.org/volunteerucf\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.chbob.org/volunteerucf</a> </p>\n<p>If you have any questions please contact outreachucf@chbob.org</p>\n<p>We\'re looking forward to working with the kids and stimulating their minds with science and we hope to see you there!</p>','2017-06-07','2017-07-19','http://www.chbob.org/volunteerucf','Bao Duong',NULL,'outreachucf@chbob.org','Yanelis Diaz','Publish',1),(2422,'Talk to Nursing Graduate Program Advisors June 15 at Information Session','talk-to-nursing-graduate-program-advisors-june-15-at-information-session','<p>Join the UCF College of Nursing graduate program advising team at a live information session. Attend the session on campus or dial in through a conference line. Learn the differences between our online and hybrid programs and get your most pressing questions answered about our nationally ranked graduate program.</p>\n<p>Date/Time: June 15 at 2 p.m.</p>\n<p>Location: UCF College of Nursing (University Tower in Central Florida Research Park), 12201 Research Parkway, Room 333</p>\n<p>Conference Line: Dial <a href=\"tel:8665644123\" rel=\"nofollow\">1-866-564-4123</a> / Enter Participant Code: 8663622#</p>\n<p>Online program options: Nursing Leadership and Management (MSN), Nursing and Healthcare Simulation (MSN, certificate), Nurse Educator (MSN, certificate), Advanced Practice Nurse (DNP), Nurse Executive (DNP), and PhD in Nursing.</p>\n<p>Hybrid program options: Adult/Gero Acute Care Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate), Adult/Gero Primary Care Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate) and Family Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate).</p>\n<p>For application deadlines and to learn more about the UCF College of Nursing, visit <a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.nursing.ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>For advising questions, email <a href=\"mailto:GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu\">GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>We look forward to chatting with you!</p>','2017-06-05','2017-06-15','https://events.ucf.edu/calendar/90/events-at-ucf-college-of-nursing/category/28/touropen-houseinformation-session/','Ayanna Lopez or Ruth Visuete','(407) 823-2647','GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing, Office of Graduate Studies','Publish',1),(2423,'Talk to Nursing Graduate Program Advisors July 19 at Information Session','talk-to-nursing-graduate-program-advisors-july-19-at-information-session','<p>Join the UCF College of Nursing graduate program advising team at a live information session. Attend the session on campus or dial in through a conference line. Learn the differences between our online and hybrid programs and get your most pressing questions answered about our nationally ranked graduate program.</p>\n<p>Date/Time: July 19 at 9 a.m.</p>\n<p>Location: UCF College of Nursing (University Tower in Central Florida Research Park), 12201 Research Parkway, Room 333</p>\n<p>Conference Line: Dial 1-866-564-4123 / Enter Participant Code: 8663622#</p>\n<p>Online program options: Nursing Leadership and Management (MSN), Nursing and Healthcare Simulation (MSN, certificate), Nurse Educator (MSN, certificate), Advanced Practice Nurse (DNP), Nurse Executive (DNP), and PhD in Nursing.</p>\n<p>Hybrid program options: Adult/Gero Acute Care Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate), Adult/Gero Primary Care Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate) and Family Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate).</p>\n<p>For application deadlines and to learn more about the UCF College of Nursing, visit <a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.nursing.ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>For advising questions, email <a href=\"mailto:GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu\">GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>We look forward to chatting with you!</p>','2017-07-10','2017-07-18','https://events.ucf.edu/calendar/90/events-at-ucf-college-of-nursing/category/28/touropen-houseinformation-session/','Ayanna Lopez or Ruth Visuete','(407) 823-2647','GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing, Office of Graduate Studies','Publish',1),(2424,'Do you want to dance???','do-you-want-to-dance','<p>The College of Education and Human Performance is happy to announce that Ballroom Dance and Salsa &amp; Latin Dance classes are BACK starting this Fall!!!!</p>\n<p>These courses are open to all students from any major!</p>\n<p>Search MyUCF for DAA 2300 0001 (Ballroom Dance) - 2 credit hours\nSearch MyUCF for DAA 2351 0001 (Salsa &amp; Latin Dance) - 2 credit hours</p>','2017-06-09','2017-06-19','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','L. Gidusko',NULL,'sesadvising@ucf.edu','Lana Gidusko','Publish',1),(2425,'Do you want to dance???','do-you-want-to-dance-1','<p>The College of Education and Human Performance is happy to announce that Ballroom Dance and Salsa &amp; Latin Dance classes are BACK starting this Fall!!!!</p>\n<p>These courses are open to all students from any major! \nSearch MyUCF for DAA 2300 0001 (Ballroom Dance) - 2 credit hours\nSearch MyUCF for DAA 2351 0001 (Salsa &amp; Latin Dance) - 2 credit hours</p>','2017-06-23','2017-06-30','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','L. Gidusko','(407) 823-0623','sesadvising@ucf.edu','Lana Gidusko','Publish',1),(2426,'Open Knight Climb','open-knight-climb-1','<p>These recreational events are free of charge and only available to first 120 currently enrolled UCF students to arrive at 7pm. They are planned to provide UCF students with the opportunity to enjoy and utilize the unique Odyssey III High Elements Course. No sign up or reservations are necessary; students must present a valid UCF ID.\nEvent duration varies but usually concludes around 11pm.\nNo open toed shoes or jewelry allowed; wear athletic attire and don\'t forget to bring your UCF ID.\nHope to see you there!</p>','2017-07-17','2017-07-27','http://rwc.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/outdoor-adventure/challenge-course','Scott Mauro','(407) 823-2408','Scott.Mauro@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',1),(2427,'Introducing your enhanced EAP benefit','introducing-your-enhanced-eap-benefit','<p>The University of Central Florida is pleased to announce that Health Advocate is the new Employee Assistance Program (EAP) provider effective July 1, 2017.</p>\n<p>The EAP is a university-funded benefit that offers the support and resources you need to address any personal challenges or concerns that may affect your personal well-being or work performance. It is confidential and free to all faculty and staff (excluding OPS employees) as well as their eligible family members, including spouses, dependent children, parents, and parents-in-law.</p>\n<p>Visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EAP-Announcement-Letter.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EAP-Announcement-Letter.pdf</a> for additional details including a benefit summary as well as Health Advocate contact information. </p>\n<p>Questions can be directed to benefits@ucf.edu or 407.823.2771.</p>','2017-06-28','2017-07-28','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/EAP-Announcement-Letter.pdf','UCF Human Resources Benefits Section','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',1),(2428,'June 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - Jerry Archambault','june-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-jerry-archambault','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for June 2017 - Jerry Archambault.</p>\n<p>Mr. Archambault is the Accountant in the Activity &amp; Service Fee Business Office of Student Development &amp; Enrollment Services. He is described by his nominators as:</p>\n<p>“An employee of UCF for more than 10 years, Jerry is committed to excellence and quality. He has created an excellent rapport with students, staff and members of the community. When problems emerge, he employs his creative abilities to resolve issues. He has the excellent skill of listening to students with issues and developing solutions to resolve any problems.</p>\n<p>Jerry\'s determination makes a difference by ensuring that numerous UCF students who receive allocations are able to attend and present at conferences. The students receive additional knowledge and experiences in their areas of interest, which results in the students being proficient in their field. He genuinely cares about the students and UCF!\"</p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for his dedication and hard work. Jerry receives a one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and gift certificates from UCF Theatre and Recreation and Wellness. Jerry will also receive a marquee announcement and an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees.</p>\n<p>We would like to recognize his nominators, Dr. Brenda Posey and Rabbi Lipskier, who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Jerry is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program on September 27, 2017, at 3:00 p.m.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Jerry.</p>','2017-07-07','2017-07-14','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2429,'Submit Diversity Breakfast Awards nominations ASAP!','submit-diversity-breakfast-awards-nominations-asap','<p>The University of Central Florida Office of Diversity and Inclusion presents an award to one student, faculty/staff and community member each year at the Diversity Breakfast. The deserving party may be nominated by a UCF community member and will be selected by a campus awards committee. Overall contributions to enhancing diversity and inclusion at UCF will be considered. This year\'s 25th Annual Diversity Breakfast will be October 16th, 2017. Nominations are open until August 19th, 2017. If you know of a deserving faculty or staff member, student, or community partner, submit a nomination today!</p>','2017-07-10','2017-08-19','https://diversity.ucf.edu/diversity-inclusion-impact-awards/','Victoria Weston','(407) 823-4112','victoria.weston@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',1),(2430,'Collective Bargaining - AFSCME','collective-bargaining-afscme','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida and the American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will take place on Tuesday, July 18, 2017, from 1:00 to 2:30 p.m. in UCF Human Resources - Innovation Center Suite 100.</p>','2017-07-11','2017-07-18',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2431,'Collective Bargaining - PBA','collective-bargaining-pba','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) will take place on Friday, July 21, 2017, from 11:00 a.m. to 1:00  p.m. in UCF Human Resources - Innovation Center Suite 100.</p>','2017-07-11','2017-07-21',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2432,'Application Deadline:  UCF Undergraduate Research Grant','application-deadline-ucf-undergraduate-research-grant','<p>The UCF Undergraduate Research Grant encourages undergraduate students from all disciplines to participate in independent research and creative projects in collaboration with UCF faculty. Individual students can apply for grants up to $500 and groups up to $1000 to support their research project. For information on eligibility, please review the application. Application deadline for fall funding is July 28, 2017.</p>\n<p>Questions? Contact the Office of Undergraduate Research at <a href=\"mailto:OUR@ucf.edu\">OUR@ucf.edu</a> or <a href=\"tel:4078233125\" rel=\"nofollow\">407-823-3125</a>.</p>','2017-07-13','2017-07-29',NULL,'Office of Undergraduate Research','(407) 823-3125','our@ucf.edu','Office of Undergraduate Research','Publish',1),(2433,'Do you want to dance???','do-you-want-to-dance-1-2','<p>The College of Education and Human Performance is happy to announce that Ballroom Dance and Salsa &amp; Latin Dance classes are BACK starting this Fall!!!!</p>\n<p>These courses are open to all students from any major!\nSearch MyUCF for DAA 2300 0001 (Ballroom Dance) - 2 credit hours\nSearch MyUCF for DAA 2351 0001 (Salsa &amp; Latin Dance) - 2 credit hours</p>','2017-07-17','2017-07-21','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','L. Gidusko','(407) 823-2595','sesadvising@ucf.edu','L. Gidusko','Publish',1),(2434,'Composite Fringe Benefit Rate Implementation - STAFF ONLY','composite-fringe-benefit-rate-implementation-staff-only','<p>The University of Central Florida is implementing a new cost allocation process for charging employee fringe benefit costs university-wide starting with fiscal year 2018. This cost allocation process, known as the composite fringe benefit rate (CFBR) or “pooled fringe rate” cost allocation method, will charge fringe benefits to departments and projects based on a set of fixed rates that will be applied to the gross salary expenses of defined employee groups. This charge will be posted in concurrence with each biweekly payroll journal. </p>\n<p>The use of a fringe benefits pool simplifies and improves the preparation and administration of budgets, including those associated with the grant proposal budget process. </p>\n<p>The composite fringe benefit charge will go into effect in early August, for the pay period ending July 27, 2017. The rates will be updated annually.</p>\n<p>This new process has accounting and budgeting implications for the university but does not impact employees benefit elections or costs. \nTo learn more, please visit <a href=\"https://fa.ucf.edu/cfbr/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://fa.ucf.edu/cfbr/</a>.</p>','2017-07-24','2017-07-26','https://fa.ucf.edu/cfbr/','Budget Planning and Administration Office',NULL,'budget@ucf.edu','Tera Alcala','Publish',1),(2435,'Meet the Greeks Pool Party','meet-the-greeks-pool-party','<p>\'Meet the Greeks Pool Party\' is a collaborative event put on by IFC, PAN, DGC, and NPHC that will be held July 30th from 1:00pm-5:00pm at the RWC Leisure Pool. This event is an opportunity for all students new to UCF to get introduced to the opportunities going Greek life at UCF has to offer. Come out and enjoy FREE food, music, and fun in the sun!</p>','2017-07-30','2017-07-30','https://twitter.com/NPHCUCF','Carl Hughes - NPHC President','(786) 663-5307','carlhughes@knights.ucf.edu','Carl Hughes','Publish',1),(2436,'Glow In The Dark ManHunt','glow-in-the-dark-manhunt','<p>Come join hundreds of other UCF students as we kick off the semester with GLOW IN THE DARK MANHUNT!\nGame starts at 8pm!</p>','2017-08-20','2017-08-20',NULL,'Jamie Spataro','(813) 624-3612','jamie15spataro@gmail.com','jamie spataro','Publish',1),(2437,'SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP Courses','shrm-cpshrm-scp-courses','<p>We partner with the Society for Human Resources Management to offer preparation using the SHRM Learning System materials for the SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP certification exams. The new SHRM certification recognizes that HR professionals are at the core of leading organizational success. It is built upon one singular body of knowledge designed to elevate the HR profession around the world. It ensures that the HR professional possesses the relevant HR knowledge required for today’s workplace, but it goes one step further. The SHRM certification tests the HR professional’s competencies – the ability to put knowledge to work through critical thinking and application.  </p>\n<p>This course is offered in both live-online and in-person formats. The Fall 2017 schedule is below:</p>\n<p>East Orlando/UCF Main Campus \nStart date: September 6\nWednesdays; 6:00-9:00pm </p>\n<p>Live-Online\nStart date: September 12\nTuesdays; 6:00-9:00pm</p>\n<p>Lake Mary\nStart date: September 14\nThursdays; 6:00-9:00pm </p>\n<p>East Orlando/ UCF Main Campus \nStart date: October 14\nSaturdays; 10:00am-5:00pm</p>\n<p>We have detailed information on this program and registration available on our web page at: <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm</a>.  The 2017 SHRM Learning System books and online access, along with additional online and printed materials, will be included within the cost of the course registration fee. We offer the early bird registration fee of $1179.00 until one month prior to the course start date. Additionally, UCF Continuing Education offers payment plans in which course fees can be paid in installments prior to the start of the course. You are able to also view these on our website, and we have options that allow participants to complete the payment in either two or three installments. If you miss the Early Bird rate deadline, we offer UCF Faculty, Staff and Alumni a discounted registration fee of $1229. </p>\n<p>If you would like to learn more about the SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP credentials, the eligibility, application or exam process, please visit <a href=\"http://certification.shrm.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://certification.shrm.org/</a> </p>\n<p>Although this course is preparatory for the SHRM-CP and SHRM-SCP Certification exams, not all participants intend to sit for SHRM’s exams after the course. We welcome HR practitioners into this course for the valuable knowledge and professional development and participants will also receive a certificate of completion at the end of the course. </p>\n<p>If you would like more information, please contact ceprograms@ucf.edu or 407-882-0260.</p>','2017-09-06','2017-12-12','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM','Nicole Baker Rosa','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','Nicole Baker Rosa','Publish',1),(2438,'Collective Bargaining Session - PBA','collective-bargaining-session-pba','<p>A collective bargaining session will be held between the University of Central Florida and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) on Friday, August 4, from 10:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center, Suite 100.</p>','2017-08-02','2017-08-04',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2439,'Do you want to dance???','do-you-want-to-dance-1-2-3','<p>The College of Education and Human Performance is happy to announce that Ballroom Dance and Salsa &amp; Latin Dance classes are BACK starting this Fall!!!!</p>\n<p>These courses are open to all students from any major! \nSearch MyUCF for DAA 2300 0001 (Ballroom Dance) - 2 credit hours\nSearch MyUCF for DAA 2351 0001 (Salsa &amp; Latin Dance) - 2 credit hours</p>','2017-08-04','2017-08-21','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','L. Gidusko','(407) 823-2000','sesadvising@ucf.edu','L. Gidusko','Publish',1),(2440,'Talk to Nursing Graduate Program Advisors Aug. 16 at 9 a.m. Online Chat Information Session','talk-to-nursing-graduate-program-advisors-aug-16-at-9-am-online-chat-information-session','<p>Join the UCF College of Nursing graduate program advising team at an online chat information session on Aug. 16 at 9 a.m. Learn the differences between our online and hybrid programs and get your most pressing questions answered about our nationally ranked graduate program.</p>\n<p>Online program options: Nursing Leadership and Management (MSN), Nursing and Healthcare Simulation (MSN, certificate), Nurse Educator (MSN, certificate), Advanced Practice Nurse (DNP), Nurse Executive (DNP), and PhD in Nursing.</p>\n<p>Hybrid program options: Adult/Gero Acute Care Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate), Adult/Gero Primary Care Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate) and Family Nurse Practitioner (DNP, certificate).</p>\n<p>For application deadlines and to learn more about the UCF College of Nursing, visit <a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.nursing.ucf.edu</a>. </p>\n<p>For advising questions, email gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p>We look forward to chatting with you!</p>','2017-08-07','2017-08-16','https://events.ucf.edu/calendar/90/events-at-ucf-college-of-nursing/category/28/touropen-houseinformation-session/','Ayanna Lopez or Ruth Visuete','(407) 823-2647','GradNurseAdvisor@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing, Office of Graduate Studies','Publish',1),(2441,'July 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - Julia Driskel','july-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-julia-driskel','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for July 2017 -- Julie Driskel.</p>\n<p>Julie Driskel is the Office Manager in the Office of Research and Commercialization. She is described by her nominators as:</p>\n<p>“Affectionately nicknamed the ORC “Mom-ager”, Julie Driskel truly loves her position in ORC and feeds off the responsibility of caring for the needs of over 250 staff members. Julie is a gifted, multi-tasking, problem-solving, organized, professional.</p>\n<p>Her work ethic and outstanding customer service are directly in line with ORC’s Vision Statement to foster a culture where employees thrive in pursuit of their personal and professional goals, leading to organizational success. Julie is proud to be a Knight.”</p>\n<p>We\'d like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. Julie receives a one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, an introduction at the UCF Board of Trustees, a marquee announcement, goody bag, certificate, and surprise presentation.</p>\n<p>We would like to recognize her nominators, Ami Zuclich and Lynn Aitken, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Julie is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program in 2018.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Julie.</p>','2017-08-11','2017-08-16','https://hr.ucf.edu/employee-month-new/','Debbie Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Debbie Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2442,'USPS Staff Council Scholarships are available for Fall!','usps-staff-council-scholarships-are-available-for-fall','<p>The USPS Staff Council scholarships for fall 2017 are now available for staff and their dependents. If you are full-time USPS staff and attending UCF, going at least part time you qualify for most of our scholarships. No application fee, no major hurdles to jump through, just fill out the online form and enter. The application is at the USPS Staff Council website as well as on our Facebook page. be sure to take a look and apply before the deadline of September 15th at 11:59 pm.</p>','2017-08-16','2017-09-15','http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html','Jamie LaMoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',1),(2443,'Amazon @ UCF now OPEN!','amazon-ucf-now-open','<p>Amazon@UCF offers a secure, convenient location for Amazon order pickup and free returns. No more packing and shipping college essentials. Order online and pickup when you arrive on campus. Visit <a href=\"https://amazon.com/ucf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">amazon.com/ucf</a> to get started.</p>','2017-08-16','2017-12-31','https://www.amazon.com/ucf','Sarah Kaczmarek',NULL,'kaczsara@amazon.com','Sue Gonzalez','Publish',1),(2444,'UCF Music Ensemble Auditions','ucf-music-ensemble-auditions','<p>The UCF Department of Music offers many ensemble experiences open to all students, regardless of major, some auditioned and some non-auditioned, including four concert bands, symphony orchestra, four choirs, jazz ensembles, opera, and more. Information on ensemble opportunities, audition schedules and requirements, as well as contact information for questions or additional information, is all available online via <a href=\"http://music.cah.ucf.edu/ensembleauditions.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://music.cah.ucf.edu/ensembleauditions.php</a></p>','2017-08-16','2017-08-19','http://music.cah.ucf.edu/ensembleauditions.php','Scott Lubaroff','(407) 823-0887','slubaroff@ucf.edu','Scott Lubaroff','Publish',1),(2445,'UCF Sports Medicine/ Football Volunteers','ucf-sports-medicine-football-volunteers','<p>Currently looking for students that are interested in a career in sports medicine or college football/athletics to volunteer with UCF football team. Join our UCF football and sports medicine developmental program and obtain the experience necessary to jump start your career to the next level.</p>','2017-08-21','2017-12-01','http://www.ucfknights.com/sports/2016/6/13/school-bio-ucf-sports-med-html.aspx','Ed Woodley','(407) 823-0585','ewoodley@athletics.ucf.edu','Allyson Grimshaw','Publish',1),(2446,'Hidden Artists Exhibit at UCF John C. Hitt Library: September 1-29','hidden-artists-exhibit-at-ucf-john-c-hitt-library-september-1-29','<p>University of Central Florida has many talented employees who use their creativity in their daily jobs. Some of these employees are “visual artists” who create artwork on their own time for themselves, their families and/or for the public. They are the “Hidden Artists.” </p>\n<p>The Hidden Artists will exhibit at the John C. Hitt Library from September 1-29, 2017 with an opening reception:</p>\n<p>Hidden Artists Art Reception\nThursday, Sept. 7 @ 4-6 p.m. \nUCF John C. Hitt Library, Room 223 \nRefreshments | Music by Aaron Lingelback, UCF alumnus\nEveryone is welcome to attend.</p>\n<p>Artwork will be exhibited in the library on the Art Wall and in the glass display cases with a variety of styles, subjects and mediums, including photography, mixed media, acrylic, graphic and jewelry. The exhibit features the talents of: Maribel Amaro-Garcia, Gina Clifton, Pamela Williams Gruen, Jacqui Johnson, Simona Loh, Russ Muller, Fiona Murphy, Judy Bragg Pardo, Brian Pate, Christopher Saclolo, M.C. Santana, and Paul Viau.</p>\n<p>Visit the Hidden Artists on Facebook at: <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/hiddenartists\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.facebook.com/hiddenartists</a> and click “Like.” to follow the group. Hidden Artists membership is open to currently working UCF faculty or staff members who create artwork. For more information, email Judy Bragg Pardo at: judyart23@aol.com.</p>','2017-09-01','2017-09-29','http://www.facebook.com/hiddenartists','Judy Pardo','(407) 435-1585','judyart23@aol.com','Judy Pardo, SDES','Publish',1),(2447,'Hidden Artists Art Reception at the UCF John C. Hitt Library: September 7','hidden-artists-art-reception-at-the-ucf-john-c-hitt-library-september-7','<p>Hidden Artists: The Tradition Continues</p>\n<p>“You might find us in front of the classroom or in the office down the hall and yet never suspect the secret we share. We are artists. Whether we have exhibited in galleries around the world or have never shown our work before, we are artists. We present to you our dreams, our hearts, our passion…We are the Hidden Artists.”</p>\n<p>University of Central Florida has many talented employees who use their creativity in their daily jobs. Some of these employees are “visual artists” who create artwork on their own time for themselves, their families and/or for the public. They are the “Hidden Artists.” </p>\n<p>The Hidden Artists will exhibit at the John C. Hitt Library from September 1-29, 2017 with an opening reception:</p>\n<p>Hidden Artists Art Reception\nThursday, Sept. 7 @ 4-6 p.m. \nUCF John C. Hitt Library, Room 223 \nRefreshments | Music by Aaron Lingelback, UCF alumnus\nEveryone is welcome to attend.</p>\n<p>Artwork will be exhibited in the library on the Art Wall and in the glass display cases with a variety of styles, subjects and mediums, including photography, mixed media, acrylic, graphic and jewelry. The exhibit features the talents of: Maribel Amaro-Garcia, Gina Clifton, Pamela Williams Gruen, Jacqui Johnson, Simona Loh, Russ Muller, Fiona Murphy, Judy Bragg Pardo, Brian Pate, Christopher Saclolo, M.C. Santana, and Paul Viau.</p>\n<p>\"In 2008, I got together a group of creative UCF faculty and staff members; and formed the Hidden Artists,” says Judy Bragg Pardo. “Since that time, I have coordinated nine exhibitions at the UCF John C. Hitt Library. Some members retired or left UCF and new members have joined. This year will be my last year exhibiting as I am retiring at the end of 2017. I wanted to say how proud I am of the dedicated Hidden Artists who have opened their hearts and souls to share their artworks with the UCF community. There were many artists who had never exhibited before and have gone on to enter juried exhibitions and display their art in galleries. Special thanks to Brian Pate who designed our beautiful postcards throughout the years and to those artists who have been with the group from the very beginning. With the collaborative effort of the group members, the Hidden Artists will keep its tradition of exhibiting at the library for years follow.”</p>\n<p>Visit the Hidden Artists on Facebook at: <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/hiddenartists\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.facebook.com/hiddenartists</a> and click “Like.” to follow the group. Hidden Artists membership is open to currently working UCF faculty or staff members who create artwork. For more information, email Judy Bragg Pardo at: judyart23@aol.com.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida John C. Hitt Library is located at 4000 Central Florida Blvd., Orlando, FL 32816. Call the library for hours of operation at 407.823.2580 or visit the website at <a href=\"http://library.ucf.edu\" rel=\"nofollow\">library.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2017-09-01','2017-09-07','http://www.facebook.com/hiddenartists','Judy Pardo','(407) 435-1585','judyart23@aol.com','Judy Pardo, SDES','Publish',1),(2448,'Now Accepting Proposals for UCF Celebrates the Arts 2018 and 2019','now-accepting-proposals-for-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-2018-and-2019','<p>As UCF Celebrates the Arts enters into its fourth year, we are looking to showcase the best in our students and faculty. The potential for a rich and exciting Celebration rests with ourselves and showcasing bold artistic works from within UCF.  </p>\n<p>The Steering Committee is looking for requests from the UCF community, for ideas of what could be included for both the 2018 and 2019 Celebrations. The ideas for these events can come out of your classes; outside projects by faculty, students, or alumni; or collaborative works associated with UCF. We want UCF Celebrates the Arts to be a showcase of the best and brightest UCF has to offer. While we will send out another call for proposals for 2019 during Spring semester, we encourage you to submit 2019 ideas now for consideration. </p>\n<p>Please note: In order to facilitate a much more thorough collaboration with other departments, being able to more closely marry academic classwork to the event, and overall better planning of the Celebration - we are accepting proposals for both 2018 and 2019.</p>\n<p>Central to our focus is:\n1.  Showcasing the work and talents of UCF students and faculty from the College of Arts and Humanities and University-wide \n2.  Presenting events that are interdisciplinary within or beyond the walls of the college\n3.  Presenting 1-3 key events that are large in scope that will attract regional, national, or international attention, and will be attract new audiences to our activities \n4.  Producing innovative events and happenings that can be out-of-the-box</p>\n<p>Proposals for inclusion on the Celebration Program will be considered utilizing the guiding questions:\n(See mission statement following submission request.)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Is it engaging content that includes the arts at UCF?</li>\n<li>How does it positively affect arts students at UCF?</li>\n<li>Does it involve a partnership with other UCF areas/schools/departments?</li>\n<li>How does it affect the community and our community partners?</li>\n<li>How is it funded, and how does it impact existing income?</li>\n<li>Is it logistically feasible?</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Send your proposals to UCFCTASteering@gmail.com. Proposals must include:\n1. Primary contact person(s)\n2. UCF and community entities involved\n3. Description of the event/exhibit, including any content that corresponds with the theme\n4. Community impact statement \n5. Space this event could best fit into (Lobby, DeVos, Pugh, Disney, lawn, downtown art gallery, other)\n6. Date and time constraints/requirements\n7. Number of performers\n8. Technical needs\n9. Budget, and where you propose those funds will come from\n10. Proposal Year: 2018, 2019, or both?\n11. Any additional information that would give the committee insight to your needs and that may help us make decisions to create the best possible experience for our faculty, students, and patrons.</p>\n<p>All entities wishing to be included in UCF Celebrates the Arts MUST submit a proposal to UCFCTAsteering@gmail.com. Deadlines for submission will be Friday September 15, 2017 at 5 pm.</p>\n<p>For questions, contact Michael.wainstein@ucf.edu (please do not submit proposals to this address.)</p>\n<hr>\n<p>UCF Celebrates the Arts Mission Statement</p>\n<p>The UCF Celebrates the Arts event is an annual showcase featuring an interactive exhibition of student artworks in the areas of Visual and Performing Arts.  In addition to the products and performances of the arts units, each year there are projects that demonstrate the arts vital role in innovation, communication and fostering creativity across all disciplines.  The festival provides a platform to share with Orlando and the Central Florida region the collaboration that occurs among all the units at UCF and also with our community partners.  UCF’s commitment to interdisciplinary activities and partnerships is well established and the festival celebrates these relationships as it demonstrates UCF’s strong positive impact in Central Florida and beyond.</p>','2017-08-23','2017-09-15','https://www.cah.ucf.edu/news/celebrates-proposals/','Michael Wainstein','(407) 823-2519','michael.wainstein@ucf.edu','Heather Gibson','Publish',1),(2449,'UCF Coding Boot Camp to Host Virtual Information Session, 20 Sep, 9PM','ucf-coding-boot-camp-to-host-virtual-information-session-20-sep-9pm','<p>Learn to Code at UCF Coding Boot Camp.  If you’re interested in an exciting career in web development—UCF Coding Boot Camp can help you get there.\nGet the inside scoop on this dynamic, full-stack web development program when you RSVP for the virtual info session September 20 at 9 p.m. ET—Powered by Trilogy Education Services.  RSVP at: <a href=\"https://codingbootcamp.ce.ucf.edu/webinar/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://codingbootcamp.ce.ucf.edu/webinar/</a></p>\n<p>Web development is a high-growth career track, with an estimated 27% growth rate through 2024 according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics. If you’re looking to switch career paths or learn new marketable skills, UCF Coding Boot Camp could be the opportunity you’ve been looking for.  Choosing the right boot camp is a BIG decision. That’s why we want to empower you with the knowledge you need. Here\'s what to expect at this live online event…</p>\n<p>Expert Insight\nYou\'ll get key insights from our boot camp evangelist who not only has years of experience in the field, but a passion for teaching and helping students succeed. Trust us—you won\'t want to miss it.</p>\n<p>Program Overview\nSee what makes us unique. We\'ll talk about our cutting-edge curriculum, our hands-on classroom environment, our student success team that will walk alongside you, and our career services team that will help prepare you for the job search.</p>\n<p>Q&amp;A Session\nHave specific questions? We\'ve got answers. Submit your questions with your RSVP and they may get answered LIVE during the Q&amp;A portion of the webinar.</p>\n<p>Join the fun. Reserve your spot for 9 p.m. ET on Wednesday, September 20.  RSVP at:  <a href=\"https://codingbootcamp.ce.ucf.edu/webinar/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://codingbootcamp.ce.ucf.edu/webinar/</a></p>','2017-08-29','2017-09-21','https://codingbootcamp.ce.ucf.edu/webinar/','Todd Freece','(407) 882-0236','todd.freece@ucf.edu','Todd Freece','Publish',1),(2450,'August 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - April Torre','august-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-april-torre','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month for August 2017 - - April Torre.</p>\n<p>April Torre is the Senior Grants Specialist in the Office of Research and Commercialization.  She is described by her nominators as:</p>\n<p>“April always demonstrates exemplary job performance and commitment to the ORC team.  I have always found her dependable, efficient, and consistently punctual.  She cultivates a culture of excellence in the workplace. Her overall positive working relationship with management and peers inspire us all. April is an example of the University’s goal to become more inclusive and diverse by her dedication to the ORC Diversity Program.”</p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work.  April receives a one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and gift certificates from UCF Theatre and Recreation and Wellness.  April will also receive a marquee announcement and an introduction at the UCF Board of Trustees. </p>\n<p>We would like to recognize her nominators, Marisol Ortega-Perez and Doshie Walker, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff.  We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a> </p>\n<p>April is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program. </p>\n<p>Congratulations again to April.</p>','2017-09-05','2017-09-12','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2451,'Leadership Week 2018 Call for Proposals','leadership-week-2018-call-for-proposals','<p>The LEAD Scholars Academy invites individuals to share their leadership knowledge and experience with the UCF campus during Leadership Week 2018. The committee is looking for workshops/sessions that will challenge and inspire the campus community and showcase current leadership topics.   Please complete the program proposal form at <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com//SE/?SID=SV_03exYw8YJ5ITAoZ\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com//SE/?SID=SV_03exYw8YJ5ITAoZ</a> .  The deadline to submit a program proposal is Wednesday, November 1, 2017. Program proposals will be evaluated and presenters will be notified by  November 8, 2017</p>','2017-09-01','2017-11-01','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Germayne Graham','Publish',1),(2452,'Tutor Homeless Students with Children Beyond Our Borders','tutor-homeless-students-with-children-beyond-our-borders','<p>Children Beyond Our Border\'s UCF Chapter is looking for volunteers that can tutor every Wednesday from 2-6pm for the entire semester. The students are considered homeless for they are living an a long-term stay motel. Volunteers will be assisting students with their homework as well as encouraging them throughout the year with their school work.</p>\n<p>Come out and join us as we make friendships with each other and motivate one another to succeed academically!</p>\n<p>If you\'re interested you can sign up at: <a href=\"http://www.chbob.org/volunteerucf\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.chbob.org/volunteerucf</a></p>\n<p>Note: Tutoring is for the children living at the Great Value Suites, address listed below, but takes place in the office next door.</p>','2017-09-06','2017-11-29','http://www.chbob.org/volunteerucf.html','Yanelis Diaz','(786) 202-1950','ucfchapter@chbob.org','Yanelis Diaz','Publish',1),(2453,'UCF Walking Club','ucf-walking-club','<p><span>The College of Education and Human Performance invites the community to join the UCF Walking Club every Tuesday at 5:30 p.m. at the Reflecting Pond on UCF’s main campus during the Fall and Spring semesters.</span></p>\n<p>The walking club is free and welcomes UCF faculty, staff, students, alumni, organizations, and the community to participate in this twice-a-week walk around the campus.</p>\n<p>The walk is about one mile and will start at 5:30 p.m. and end at the Reflecting Pond. Walks may increase in length to meet walkers’ expectations and will begin at the Reflecting Pond every week. Walkers may shorten the length of their walk to any distance during the fitness program.</p>','2017-09-13','2018-05-02','','Patty Lanier','(407) 823-6759','PattyLanier@ucf.edu','Sandra Carr','Publish',1),(2454,'Author’s Talk: \"Discovering the North-West Passage: The Journey from Research to Publication,\" by Glenn M. Stein, FRGS, FRCGS','authors-talk-discovering-the-north-west-passage-the-journey-from-research-to-publication-by-glenn-m-stein-frgs-frcgs','<p>Join author, historian, and political cartoonist Glenn M. Stein for a talk about researching, writing, and publishing his book, \"Discovering the North-West Passage: The Four-Year Arctic Odyssey of H.M.S Investigator and the McClure Expedition.\" A maritime and polar historian, Stein is a Fellow of the Royal Geographical Society, life member of the American Polar Society, and a member of the Orders of Medals Research Society. Stein’s work has been recognized by numerous national and international organizations and his writings are included in the collections of the Library of Congress and the University of Central Florida Libraries.</p>\n<p>Wednesday, September 13, 2017, 1:00 p.m., John C. Hitt Library, Room 223</p>\n<p>Sponsored by Special Collections &amp; University Archives, University of Central Florida Libraries</p>','2017-09-09','2017-09-13','http://library.ucf.edu/news/artist-talk-glenn-m-stein-9-13-2017/','David Benjamin','(407) 823-2788','david.benjamin@ucf.eud','David Benjamin','Publish',1),(2455,'USPS Staff Council scholarship application deadline extended!','usps-staff-council-scholarship-application-deadline-extended','<p>The USPS Staff Council scholarship application deadline has been extended through September 22nd at 11:59 pm.  If you haven\'t put in your application for yourself or your dependent because of the hurricane, please be sure to put one in now.</p>','2017-09-18','2017-09-22','http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/scholarships.html','Jamie Lamoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie Lamoreaux','Publish',1),(2456,'Clinton Global Initiative University (CGIU) Crowdrise Competition!','clinton-global-initiative-university-cgiu-crowdrise-competition','<p>Elena Pham is a UCF student representing the student organization Hearts for the Homeless (H4H) at the Clinton Global Initiative University (CGIU) annual conference in October. She was was chosen as one of 50 students to participate in the CGI U Commitments Challenge to raise funds to support their project. See here for a video about the group: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H_umUo68EMM\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H_umUo68EMM</a> </p>\n<p>Hearts for the Homeless contributes to the health and well-being of one of the most vulnerable populations in our nation with free blood pressure screenings, education, relief efforts, while simultaneously providing clinical outreach opportunities for students who wish to contribute to our mission.\nThrough partnering with local food shares and free healthcare clinics in the area, H4H hopes to help reduce the prevalence of hypertension and cardiac diseases in the homeless community. Hearts for the Homeless strives to increase their impact in the homeless community by spreading to different universities and partnering with more locations and clinics. Hearts for the Homeless is now operating in Orlando, Tallahassee, Miami, Gainesville, and at our newest chapter in Tampa.</p>\n<p>As of this morning, they’re in 6th place with $180 raised!  The organization will receive 100% of the funds raised, and the challenge will end October 12th. Please click here to help H4H with this competition!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.crowdrise.com/o/en/team/hearts-for-the-homeless\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.crowdrise.com/o/en/team/hearts-for-the-homeless</a></p>','2017-09-18','2017-10-12','https://www.crowdrise.com/o/en/team/hearts-for-the-homeless','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2457,'Morgridge Student Support Foundation financial hardship awards','morgridge-student-support-foundation-financial-hardship-awards','<p>Do you know a student in need? The Morgridge Student Support Foundation provides grants of up to $200 for students in financial hardship for scholarly, personal, or community expenses. Please apply here: <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/student-support-foundation/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/student-support-foundation/</a></p>','2017-09-22','2017-05-09','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/student-support-foundation/','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',1),(2458,'Collective Bargaining Session - AFSCME','collective-bargaining-session-afscme','<p>A collective bargaining session between the university and the American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will be held from 3:00 to 5:00 p.m. on Tuesday, September 26, 2017, at UCF Human Resources - Innovative Center -Suite 100.</p>','2017-09-25','2017-09-26',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2459,'16th Annual Central Florida Community Partners Nonprofit Management Conference','16th-annual-central-florida-community-partners-nonprofit-management-conference','<p>The 16th Annual Community Partners Nonprofit Conference will be held on Thursday, November 9, 2017 at the University of Central Florida Student Union. This year’s theme will focus on the concept of, “Advocacy in a Changing World.” Join us for the region’s largest gathering of nonprofit professionals and students for a day of enlightening and entertaining sessions from local and national advocacy leaders. This is a fantastic networking opportunity for emerging leaders and seasoned professionals alike.</p>','2017-10-02','2017-11-06','http://nonprofitnexus.ucf.edu/conferences/','Dorothy Loman','(407) 823-4737','dorothy.loman@ucf.edu','Dorothy Loman - UCF Continuing Education','Publish',1),(2460,'Collective Bargaining - AFSCME','collective-bargaining-afscme-1','<p>A collective bargaining session between the university and the American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will be held from 8:00 to 9:00 a.m. on Thursday, September 28, 2017, at UCF Human Resources, Innovation Center Suite 100.</p>','2017-09-27','2017-09-28',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Richner','Publish',1),(2461,'Prudential Productivity Awards -- Nominations Currently Being Accepted','prudential-productivity-awards-nominations-currently-being-accepted','<p>Each Fall, Florida TaxWatch opens up the nominations window for the Prudential Productivity Awards, and this year’s window opens September 4. This program has been recognizing and rewarding innovative, hardworking state employees for 29 years, providing cash and plaque awards to state workers in exciting ceremonies throughout the state. In 2017, UCF had three groups honored with plaque awards.</p>\n<p>Whether through an innovative new process that saves taxpayer money, or improving the quality and speed of our interactions with the public, or showing great initiative in tackling a problem to help our constituents, many individuals and teams at UCF have shown a commitment to excellence that would qualify for these great awards.</p>\n<p>Staff are strongly encouraged to submit nominations for this great program and show the taxpayers the quality of UCF\'s work this past year.</p>\n<p>For those of you who may not have submitted a nomination in the past, here are the basics:\n• You may nominate yourself, a colleague, a team of up to 8, or a whole department/agency for an award.\n• Winners are typically those nominations that show innovation, a clever approach to a problem, significant taxpayer savings, and/or dramatically improve service delivery.\n• Keep in mind, cost-saving estimations and FTE reductions will need to be verified by Florida TaxWatch staff, so please be sure that you have documentation where appropriate.\n• Nominators are allowed to upload supporting documents along with the nomination. This can be an official letter from [myself/your supervisor/department head, etc.] affirming the achievement or endorsing the nomination; or cost savings calculations; or even news clippings showing public recognition of the achievement. Anything that might show why your nomination deserves a top award.</p>\n<p>Please take a few minutes in the next couple of weeks and visit <a href=\"http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org</a> to download a document that will allow you to prepare your responses to the questions ahead of time.</p>\n<p>The nominations window this year is open September 4 — November 10.</p>\n<p>Human Resources Learning and Organizational Effectiveness staff are in direct contact with Florida TaxWatch and should be able to help you with any questions you may have. Please email <a href=\"mailto:HRLearning@ucf.edu\">HRLearning@ucf.edu</a> with any questions.</p>','2017-10-02','2017-11-10','http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org/Instructions.aspx','Rachelle Lehner/Lee Williams/Margie Chusmir','(407) 823-0440','HRLearning@ucf.edu','Rachelle Lehner','Publish',1),(2462,'September 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - Damien Chaffin','september-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-damien-chaffin','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for September 2017 – Damien Chaffin.\nDamien is the Administrative Assistant in the School of Teaching, Learning and Leadership in the College of Education and Human Performance. His nominators had this to say about him:</p>\n<p>“Mr. Chaffin’s superior ability centers on how he builds and manages personal relationships and strengthens partnerships. He is a bridge builder and equally important, he is not a bridge burner. He creates alliances and drives consensus. This combination of abilities and talents has enabled him to become a person that others look to for guidance when problems arise. He is consistent problem-solver and is known as the go-to person in the department.</p>\n<p>I cannot in the space allotted, describe all that Damien has done. He is a friendly person and a joy to be around. He is able to maintain a professional demeanor while making faculty, staff and students feel valued and appreciated.\"</p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for his dedication and hard work. Damien receives a certification, one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and this goody bag. Damien will also receive a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d like to recognize his nominators, Eric Brewington and Linda Alexander, who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Damien is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Damien.</p>','2017-10-02','2017-10-09','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Debbie Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',1),(2463,'Omicron Delta Kappa National Leadership Honor Society applications now available!','omicron-delta-kappa-national-leadership-honor-society-applications-now-available','<p>The Omicron Delta Kappa Society is the national leadership honor society for college students, faculty, staff, administrators, and alumni that recognizes and encourages superior scholarship, leadership, and exemplary character.</p>\n<p>The student and faculty members of Omicron Delta Kappa work closely together to foster leadership abilities within its members. The organization is also dedicated to a variety of projects that benefit the university and the surrounding community.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements for induction into the Central Florida Circle of ODK:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Class standing: Junior (at least 60 credits), Senior, or Graduate Level</li>\n<li>Minimum GPA: 3.2 for undergraduates, 3.5 for graduate students</li>\n<li>Initiation fee of $95-includes lifetime membership and pin (graduation cords may be purchased for an additional $25) . <strong>If accepted your dues will be due by 10/31/17 at 12:00 PM</strong>. <strong>Induction will be held on Tuesday, 11/14/17 at 4pm </strong>in Ferrell Commons 165-LEAD Scholars Academy</li>\n<li>Demonstrated leadership in at least two of the five areas:\n<ul>\n<li>Scholarship</li>\n<li>Athletics</li>\n<li>Campus/Community Service, Social/Religious Activities, and Campus Government</li>\n<li>Journalism, Speech and the Mass Media</li>\n<li>Creative and Performing Arts</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Visit our website at <u><a href=\"https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form</a> </u>to complete the online application</li>\n<li>Questions may be directed to Dr. Stacey Malaret, Faculty Secretary for ODK, in the LEAD Scholars Academy Office, Ferrell Commons 165 at <a href=\"mailto:Stacey.Malaret@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Malaret@ucf.edu</a></li>\n<li><strong>Online application deadline is 10/23/17</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>','2017-10-04','2017-10-23','https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',8),(2464,'The Importance of Voting & Voter Rights Within Civic Engagement','the-importance-of-voting-voter-rights-within-civic-engagement','<p></p>\n<p>The UCF Lou Frey Institute of Politics &amp; Government and UCF LEAD Scholars Academy are facilitating a civic engagement  conversation with special focus on voting and voter rights for ALL UCF Students and interested faculty and staff  on Friday, October 27, 2017 from 1:00p.m. - 2:00p.m. in the LEAD Scholars Office located in Ferrell Commons 168E (Gold Classroom). Dr. Terri Fine, UCF Professor and Associate Director of the Lou Frey Institute, will be presenting and holding a question and answer session. Join us!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>If you have any questions regarding the event please send your email to shena.parks@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p></p>','2017-10-05','2017-10-28','','Shena Parks','(407) 823-0644','shena.parks@ucf.edu','Shena Parks','Publish',9),(2465,'Celebrate 25 Years of UCF Diversity Week and join us at these great events!','celebrate-25-years-of-ucf-diversity-week-and-join-us-at-these-great-events','<p>UCF\'s 25th Diversity Week is October 16-20, 2017 with the theme of \"Transform and Inspire Inclusion.\"<br>All events are free and open to the public. Some highlights from the week include:</p>\n<p>Monday, October 16<br>Diversity Week Photo Mosaic | 9am-4pm @ Student Union Atrium<br>Be part of UCF history! Post photos on Instagram and Twitter with the hashtag #WeAreUCF to be featured in a giant photo mosaic! Anyone, anywhere can submit photos, so spread the word!<br>Two days to submit! 9am-4pm on Monday &amp;amp; 9am-6pm on Tuesday, October 17, both in Student Union Atrium</p>\n<p>Tuesday, October 17<br>Diversity Movie Viewings @ UCF Library 3rd floor media area<br>I Learn America, 9:30am-11am<br>Straightlaced: How Gender\'s Got Us Tied Up, 12pm-1:15pm<br>Hooligan Sparrow, 3pm-4:30pm<br>Humanism: The Experience of Living Without God | 1pm-2pm @ Student Union room 224<br>Courageous Conversation: Race and Social Justice | 2pm-4pm @ UCF Global room 101</p>\n<p>Wednesday, October 18<br>Diversity Week Blood Drive | 9am-7pm @ Memory Mall Flagpole<br>Black Card Revoked! | 12pm-1:30pm @ Student Union 316CD<br>Inclusive Recreation Expo @ RWC<br>Blindfolded Yoga: 9:30-10:30am @ RWC Multipurpose Rm; 12-1pm @ RWC at Knights Plaza<br>Wheelchair Tennis: 3:15-4pm @ RWC Court 1<br>Goalball &amp;amp; Sitting Volleyball: 4-5pm @ RWC Courts 1 &amp;amp; 2<br>Unified Basketball 5-6pm @ RWC Court 1<br>Wheelchair Basketball (Orlando Magic Wheels): 6-7pm @ RWC Court 1</p>\n<p>Thursday, October 19<br>\"True Tea\" with Kat Blaque | 1pm-3pm @ Student Union 316AB</p>\n<p>Friday, October 20<br>Israel Shabbat | 6pm-9pm @ Central Florida Hillel</p>\n<p>And many more! Check out the full calendar for all the details!</p>','2017-10-03','2017-10-21','https://diversity.ucf.edu/files/2017/10/2017-UCF-Diversity-Week-calendar.pdf','Office of Diversity and Inclusion','(407) 823-6479','diverse@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',10),(2468,'Be part of UCF history! #WeAreUCF','be-part-of-ucf-history-weareucf','<p>Be part of a huge photo mosaic coming to UCF!</p>\n<p>On October 16th &amp; 17th in the Student Union Atrium, join us by hashtagging photos of your favorite UCF memories with #WEAREUCF on Instagram and Twitter. Your submissions will help us create a UCF-themed mosaic in celebration of the 25th Diversity Week!</p>\n<p>We will be giving out printed photos and displaying the progression of the mosaic during the event in the SU Atrium on 10/16 and 10/17.</p>\n<p>You can post photos NOW! Any photos submitted will be included! But, you only get the print-out during the event hours on 10/16 and 10/17.</p>\n<p>Help spread the word! Anyone, anywhere can be part of the mosaic!</p>\n<p>Stay tuned for more hints and information coming your way as we countdown to the full image reveal!</p>','2017-10-05','2017-10-18','https://www.facebook.com/events/1967102756908881/','Office of Diversity and Inclusion','(407) 823-6479','victoria.weston@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',10),(2469,'Morgridge Student Support Foundation grants for students in financial need','morgridge-student-support-foundation-grants-for-students-in-financial-need','<p>SSF-UCF provides grants up to $200 for selected students through a generous grant provided by the Morgridge Family Foundation. All applicants will be reviewed by the SSF-UCF student board to determine eligibility. These funds can be used for scholarly, personal or community endeavors and will be disbursed through UCF Student Financial Assistance. This grant is intended for students in immediate financial need or crisis. Applications will be reviewed again at the beginning of the spring 2018 semester.</p>','2017-10-09','2018-04-17','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/student-support-foundation/','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',8),(2470,'UCF Debate Team Wins Big At Vanderbilt University','ucf-debate-team-wins-big-at-vanderbilt-university','<p>October 17, 2017</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>UCF Debate Team Wins Big At Vanderbilt University</p>\n<p>Last weekend was another strong showing for the UCF Debate Team.</p>\n<p>Vanderbilt University hosted their annual invitational debate tournament. Five teams of the UCF Debate Team competed at the invitational in both the novice and junior varsity divisions.  </p>\n<p>In the novice division, teams of Lauren Christie &amp; Anna Jurlina and Dveen Manoogian &amp; Brittany Bolger achieved top honors. Both teams finished their preliminary rounds undefeated with a record of 6-0. Manoogian &amp; Bolger squared off against a team from the University of Northern Iowa, winning on a 3-0 decision in semi-finals. The team of Christie &amp; Jurlina met Manoogian &amp; Bolger in the finals, and in a coach’s choice, were selected as the novice division champions.</p>\n<p>In addition to their strong performance, Manoogian, Bolger, Christie and Jurlina received 4 out of the top 5 speakers in the entire novice division. The debaters received 4th, 3rd, 2nd and 1st place, respectively. </p>\n<p>Three UCF teams competed in the junior varsity division. The teams of Ethan Uhlig &amp; his partner, Ariel Olson &amp; Ethan Smith and Joe Tracy &amp; Louis Dor finished their preliminary rounds with winning records 6-0, 5-1 and 4-2, respectively. The team of Tracey &amp; Dor finished their run at semi-finals in a coach’s choice with UCF’s Uhlig &amp; partner advancing. Tracy received an award as the 9th place speaker in the junior varsity division. Olson &amp; Smith also finished their elimination run in the semi-finals against Wayne State University in a 2-1 decision. Olsen received 8th place speaker.</p>\n<p>In the junior varsity final round, Uhlig &amp; partner debated Wayne State’s team of Logan Jancek and Shay Matmanivong. UCF’s top-seeded junior varsity team was one ballot shy of a final round win against Wayne State. Uhlig was the top speaker in the junior varsity with his partner earning 2nd place honors.</p>\n<p>The Vanderbilt tournament was the 3rd tournament in as many weeks for the UCF Debate Team.   The team earned honors in each of these three tournaments. </p>','2017-10-17','2017-10-24','http://facebook.com/ucfdebate','Nick J. Sciullo','(407) 823-5524','nick.sciullo@ucf.edu','Dr. Nick J. Sciullo','Publish',14),(2471,'Do you want to dance? Join us for Ballroom Dance and Salsa & Latin Dance classes','do-you-want-to-dance-1-2-3-4','<p><strong>The College of Education and Human Performance is once again offering Ballroom Dance and Salsa &amp; Latin Dance classes.  </strong></p>\n<p><span><strong>Just added to Spring 2018 -  Country Western Dance!</strong> </span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><span>These courses are open to all students from any major! </span></p>\n<p><span>Search MyUCF for DAA 2300 0001 (Ballroom Dance) - 2 credit hours</span></p>\n<p><span>Search MyUCF for DAA 2351 0001 (Salsa &amp; Latin Dance) - 2 credit hours</span></p>\n<p><span>Search MyUCF for PEM 2175 0001 (Country Western Dance) - 2 credit hours - NEW!!</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>','2017-10-19','2017-12-31','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','Lana G','(407) 823-0623','sesadvising@ucf.edu','Lana Gidusko','Publish',13),(2472,'Do you like sports and exercise? Register for Introduction to Sport and Exercise Science in Spring 2018','do-you-like-sports-and-exercise','<p><strong>The College of Education and Human Performance is offering Introduction to Sport and Exercise Science in the Spring 2018 semester!</strong></p>\n<p><span>This course is open to all students from any major! </span></p>\n<p><span>Search MyUCF for PET 3005 </span></p>','2017-10-19','2017-12-31','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','Lana G','(407) 823-0623','sesadvising@ucf.edu','Lana Gidusko','Publish',13),(2473,'Do you want to get fit? Register for Personal Fitness in Spring 2018','do-you-want-to-get-fit','<p><strong>The College of Education and Human Performance is offering Personal Fitness in the Spring 2018 semester!</strong></p>\n<p><span>This course is open to all students from any major! </span></p>\n<p><span>Search MyUCF for PEM 2104 </span></p>','2017-10-19','2017-12-31','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','Lana G','(407) 823-0623','sesadvising@ucf.edu','Lana Gidusko','Publish',13),(2475,'Do you want to learn self defense skills? Register for self defense courses in Spring 2018','do-you-want-to-learn-self-defense-skills','<p><strong>The College of Education and Human Performance is offering self defense courses in the Spring 2018 semester!</strong></p>\n<p><span>These courses are open to all students from any major! </span></p>\n<p><span>Search MyUCF for PEM 2405</span></p>','2017-10-19','2017-12-31','http://education.ucf.edu/sportexscience/','Lana G','(407) 823-0623','sesadvising@ucf.edu','Lana Gidusko','Publish',13),(2476,'Understanding Middle East Alliances in the Trump Era','understanding-middle-east-alliances-in-the-trump-era','<p>Please join the Prince Mohammad Bin Fahd Program for Strategic Research and Studies for a panel discussion featuring Dr. Gönül Tol and Dr. Paul Salem of the Middle East Institute, moderated PMBF Director David Dumke.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>October 26th, 2017, 12pm – 2pm, UCF Global Room 101</p>\n<p>Must RSVP</p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>','2017-10-20','2017-10-26','http://events.ucf.edu/event/573135/understanding-middle-east-alliances-in-the-trump-era/','Kinda Haddad','(407) 823-2510','kinda.haddad@ucf.edu','Kinda Haddad','Publish',15),(2477,'Mock Sexual Assault Trial','mock-sexual-assault-trial','<p>Victim Services is proud to announce our 4th Annual presentation of our Mock Sexual Assault Trial on Monday November 6, 2017 at 6pm in the Pegasus Ballroom. Join us as we explore the difference between consensual sex and rape. Hear testimony, cross examiniations, and be a member of the jury. This is an interactive, thought provoking and enlightening experience.</p>','2017-10-31','2017-11-07','','Christey Oberbeck','(407) 823-0698','christey.oberbeck@ucf.edu','Knight Advocates','Publish',19),(2478,'Prudential Productivity Award Nominations Deadline Extended - December 31','prudential-productivity-award-nominations-deadline-november-10','<p>Hurricane Irma and an early Legislative Session have created an unusual Fall for many of you, and we want to make sure that everyone has ample opportunity to get nominations in for next year’s awards. <strong>THE NEW DEADLINE IS DECEMBER 31, 2017.</strong> </p>\n<p>It is our hope that this extension will allow for an even greater number of nominations, and will result in the best year of awards yet! </p>\n<p>Information on the Prudential Productivity Award and the Nomination Process:</p>\n<p>Each Fall, Florida TaxWatch opens up the nominations window for the Prudential Productivity Awards, and this the deadline has been extended to December 31. This program has been recognizing and rewarding innovative, hardworking state employees for 29 years, providing cash and plaque awards to state workers in exciting ceremonies throughout the state. In 2017, UCF had three groups honored with plaque awards.</p>\n<p>Whether through an innovative new process that saves taxpayer money, or improving the quality and speed of our interactions with the public, or showing great initiative in tackling a problem to help our constituents, UCF teams has shown a commitment to excellence that would qualify for these great awards.</p>\n<p>Show the taxpayers the quality of our work this past year!</p>\n<p> Here are the basics:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You may nominate yourself, a colleague, a team of up to 8, or a whole department/agency for an award.</li>\n<li>Winners are typically those nominations that show innovation, a clever approach to a problem, significant taxpayer savings, and/or dramatically improve service delivery.</li>\n<li>Keep in mind, cost saving estimations and FTE reductions will need to be verified by Florida TaxWatch staff, so please be sure that you have documentation where appropriate.</li>\n<li>Nominators are allowed to upload supporting documents along with the nomination. This can be an official letter from [myself/your supervisor/department head, etc.] affirming the achievement or endorsing the nomination; or cost savings calculations; or even news clippings showing public recognition of the achievement. Anything that might show why your nomination deserves a top award.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please take a few minutes in the next couple of weeks and visit <a href=\"http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org</a> to download a document that will allow you to prepare your responses to the questions ahead of time.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>The nominations window now closes December 31.</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Human Resources Learning and Organizational Effectiveness staff are in direct contact with Florida TaxWatch, and should be able to help you with any questions you may have. Please email HRLearning@ucf.edu  with any questions. </p>','2017-10-24','2017-11-10','http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org','HR Learning and ORganizational Effectiveness','(407) 823-0440','hrlearning@ucf.edu','Rachelle Lehner, HR Learning and Organizational Effectiveness','Publish',20),(2479,'Benefits Open Enrollment Extended Through Friday, Nov 10','benefits-open-enrollment-extended-through-friday-nov-10','<p>Due to a People First system outage, the state\'s annual open enrollment period for eligible employees to change insurance benefit options has been extended through Friday, November 10, 2017 at 6 p.m. ET.</p>\n<p>Please visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment</a> for additional details and updates on when the People First system is operational and available for access by employees to make benefit elections.</p>\n<p>Questions can be directed to <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">benefits@ucf.edu</a> or 407.823.2771.</p>','2017-10-16','2017-11-10','https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment','Human Resources Benefits Section','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',21),(2481,'October 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - James McCully','october-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-james-mccully','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for October 2017 – James McCully.</p>\n<p>James is the Senior Broadcast Technologist in the Nicholson School of Communication in the College of Sciences. His nominators had this to say about him:</p>\n<p><em>                “There are many, many reasons to nominate Jim, but chief among them is his willingness to do whatever is asked of him.  He is consistently willing to assume any task/function that needs to be completed.  Jim stands apart from others by his consistent demonstration of exemplary performance that is above and beyond the scope of assigned responsibilities.  He has led or played a part in securing over $1.6 million dollars to support the maintenance of top-level equipment and is always looking for ways to provide educational opportunities for students, faculty and staff.</em></p>\n<p><em>Jim understand that his role is purposed to support the school’s faculty and students and to ensure our students get the best education. He lives and breathes this every day and has done so for more than 25 years.“ </em></p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for his dedication and hard work. James receives a certification, one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and this goody bag. James will also receive a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize his nominators, Dr. Boyd Lindsley and Dr. Robert Littlefield who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>James is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to James.</p>','2017-11-09','2017-11-16','https://hr.ucf.edu/employee-month-new/','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach Human Resources Department','Publish',23),(2482,'UCF 2017 Annual Employee Awards Program Highlights','ucf-2017-annual-employee-awards-program-highlights','<p>On behalf of the UCF Human Resources department, we extend sincere appreciation to everyone who joined us for the 45th Annual Employee Awards Program on Wednesday, September 27th. The event was a great success with over 600 attendees, and we would like to thank everyone who attended for helping to make this year’s event memorable. </p>\n<p>Please visit the <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/annual-employee-awards-program-2017/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">2017 Annual Employee Awards Program website</a> for awardee information, and to view the event webcast and download photos.</p>\n<p>Highlights of the Awards Program include:</p>\n<p><strong>USPS Employee of the Year: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/Recognition-136.jpg\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Elba Miscannon</a></strong></p>\n<p>Since 2008, Elba has worked in Student Development and Enrollment Services, where she supports Assistant Vice President Mark Gumble and manages payroll and hiring for 30 full-time professional positions and more than 200 student employees. According to her nominators, creativity, commitment, diligence, dedication, inclusivity, and loyalty are all qualities that Elba possesses. Elba has demonstrated a strong commitment to UCF\'s goals of offering the best education in the state of Florida and becoming more inclusive and diverse. Additionally, Elba has shown a commitment to UCF\'s Collective Impact Strategic Plan by supporting the development of UCF Downtown, the Reimagining the First Year in College project, and strategic planning as these new initiatives unfold. Congratulations, Elba!</p>\n<p><strong>A&amp;P Gabor Excellence Award: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/Recognition-128.jpg\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Vanessa Blackmon</a></strong></p>\n<p>Vanessa is currently the Assistant Director for the Office of Student Services at the UCF Rosen College of Hospitality Management, and director of the Rosen College Peer Outreach Mentoring Program (POMP). Vanessa joined UCF in July 2011 in a coordinator role, and immediately went to work creating this program. Two weeks later, POMP was up and running, beginning with 11 students. The program has grown to almost 100 students. On average, 98% of POMP mentees are retained at the Rosen College during the terms they participate in the program, and 90% have increased their cumulative GPAs, largely due to Vanessa’s efforts and support. Her interactions with students have proven to be positive and uplifting. In fact, many students affectionately refer to her as “mom.” Congratulations, Vanessa!</p>\n<p>Additional honorees of note include <strong><a href=\"https://liveunited.ucf.edu/2017/10/04/ucf-united-way-advocates-honored-at-employee-award-program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Joe Raditch</a></strong>, <span>Coordinator of Information and Publication Services for Communications and Marketing, who was selected as the </span>United Way Advocate Leadership Award winner; and <strong><a href=\"https://ucfhr.smugmug.com/Annual-Awards/2017-Annual-Employee-Awards-Program/n-MT4H2W/i-gFFKbxC/A\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Sandra Cherepow</a></strong>, Senior Administrative Assistant to President Hitt, who celebrated her 45th anniversary in service to UCF. </p>\n<p>Please join us in congratulating ALL of this year\'s nominees and honorees. We look forward to seeing you at next year\'s event!</p>','2017-11-09','2017-12-31','https://hr.ucf.edu/annual-employee-awards-program-2017/','HR Learning','(407) 823-0440','HRLearning@ucf.edu','HR Learning & Organizational Effectiveness','Publish',24),(2483,'Application Open - Showcase of Undergraduate Research Excellence (SURE)','application-deadline-showcase-of-undergraduate-research-excellence-sure','<p>The Showcase of Undergraduate Research Excellence (SURE) is hosted by the Office of Undergraduate Research each spring.  SURE is a poster- or display-based forum for UCF undergraduates to present their research and creative projects to the broader university community. Undergraduates from all disciplines are encouraged to present current or recently completed academic projects, showcasing the diversity of topics, approaches, and interests at UCF.</p>\n<p>Applications for the Showcase are due February 9 at 1 p.m.</p>\n<p>Visit <a href=\"http://www.Showcase.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.Showcase.ucf.edu</a> for more details.</p>\n<p>Questions? Feel free to contact the Office of Undergraduate Research (OUR@ucf.edu)</p>','2017-12-01','2018-02-09','http://www.Showcase.ucf.edu','Office of Undergraduate Research','(407) 823-3125','our@ucf.edu','Office of Undergraduate Research','Publish',26),(2484,'Prudential Productivity Award Nominations - Deadline Extended December 31','prudential-productivity-award-nominations-deadline-extended-december-31','<p>Hurricane Irma and an early Legislative Session have created an unusual Fall for many of you, and we want to make sure that everyone has ample opportunity to get nominations in for next year’s awards. <strong>THE NEW DEADLINE IS DECEMBER 31, 2017.</strong> </p>\n<p>It is our hope that this extension will allow for an even greater number of nominations, and will result in the best year of awards yet! </p>\n<p><strong>Information on the Prudential Productivity Award and the Nomination Process:</strong></p>\n<p>Each Fall, Florida TaxWatch opens up the nominations window for the Prudential Productivity Awards, and this the deadline is December 31. This program has been recognizing and rewarding innovative, hardworking state employees for 29 years, providing cash and plaque awards to state workers in exciting ceremonies throughout the state. In 2017, UCF had three groups honored with plaque awards.</p>\n<p>Whether through an innovative new process that saves taxpayer money, or improving the quality and speed of our interactions with the public, or showing great initiative in tackling a problem to help our constituents, UCF teams has shown a commitment to excellence that would qualify for these great awards. <em>Additional category for this year:</em> Did you or a colleague go above and beyond to help through the storm and post-storm cleanup? This service to the community is recognized by Florida TaxWatch and is eligible for the Prudential Productivity Award. </p>\n<p>Show the taxpayers the quality of our work this past year!</p>\n<p> Here are the basics:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You may nominate yourself, a colleague, a team of up to 8, or a whole department/agency for an award.</li>\n<li>Winners are typically those nominations that show innovation, a clever approach to a problem, significant taxpayer savings, and/or dramatically improve service delivery.</li>\n<li>Keep in mind, cost saving estimations and FTE reductions will need to be verified by Florida TaxWatch staff, so please be sure that you have documentation where appropriate.</li>\n<li>Nominators are allowed to upload supporting documents along with the nomination. This can be an official letter from [your supervisor/department head, etc.] affirming the achievement or endorsing the nomination; or cost savings calculations; or even news clippings showing public recognition of the achievement. Anything that might show why your nomination deserves a top award.</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n<p>Please take a few minutes in the next couple of weeks and visit <a href=\"http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org</a> to download a document that will allow you to prepare your responses to the questions ahead of time.</p>\n<p> <em>*In-unit faculty and contract employees are not eligible.</em></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>The nominations window now closes December 31.</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Human Resources Learning and Organizational Effectiveness staff are in direct contact with Florida TaxWatch, and should be able to help you with any questions you may have. Please email HRLearning@ucf.edu  with any questions. </p>','2017-11-14','2018-01-01','http://ppa.floridataxwatch.org','HR Learning and ORganizational Effectiveness','(407) 823-0440','hrlearning@ucf.edu','Rachelle Lehner, HR Learning and Organizational Effectiveness','Publish',20),(2485,'John C. Hitt Library closure, 12/16/17 through 1/1/18','john-c-hitt-library-closure-121617-through-1118','<p><span>Due to a planned power outage during this time, the John C. Hitt Library will be closed from <strong>Saturday, 12/16/17 through Monday, 1/1/18</strong>. Library resources will be available at <a href=\"http://library.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">library.ucf.edu</span></a>.</span></p>\n<p><span>Please return <strong>books</strong> by <strong>Friday, December 15</strong>, and <strong>check out</strong> books you need by <strong>Friday, December 15</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span>Interlibrary Loan/Document Delivery book requests </span></strong><span>received after <strong>Wednesday, December 6</strong> will be sent forward in January 2018. <strong>Article requests</strong> will continue to be processed until <strong>Wednesday, December 13.</strong> <strong>Document Delivery requests</strong> will be processed until <strong>Thursday, December 14.</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong><span>LibTech</span></strong><span> will perform regularly scheduled maintenance on all items during Winter Break.<br> <strong>iPads</strong> will no longer be circulated after <strong>5:00pm on Thursday December 7th</strong>.<br> All other LibTech items (except items with 4 hour loan periods) will no longer be circulated after <strong>5:00pm on Saturday December 9th.</strong></span></p>\n<p><span>The John C. Hitt Library will <strong>open on Tuesday, January 2, 2018.</strong></span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>','2017-12-05','2018-01-02','https://library.ucf.edu/','Meg Scharf','(407) 491-2424','meg@ucf.edu','Meg Scharf','Publish',28),(2486,'The LEAD Scholars Academy is now accepting applications for Spring 2018 Leadership Programs for 3rd and 4th year students!','the-lead-scholars-academy-is-now-accepting-applications-for-spring-2018-leadership-programs-for-3rd-and-4th-year-students','<p>The LEAD Scholars Academy provides students with various opportunities to learn more about themselves, develop new leadership skills, and become student leaders through programs and events, including Campus-wide Leadership Workshops, Leadership Retreats, and Leadership Conferences.</p>\n<p>There are several 3rd and 4th year programs available for students to apply to for the Spring 2018 term:</p>\n<p><strong><em>Lead Out Loud</em></strong> is an experiential program that focuses on the leadership development of multicultural students at the University of Central Florida. This program promises to enhance leadership skills, strengthen life skills and encourage positional leadership in this population of students at UCF. </p>\n<p>The<strong><em> Inspire Women\'s Leadership Program</em></strong> aims to provide leadership enhancement and empowerment opportunities for UCF women students. Through networking, mentoring, personal development, and experiential training, UCF women students will be prepared to hold various leadership positions on campus and in the work arena.</p>\n<p>The<strong><em> Civic Engagement Scholars Program</em></strong> is for students looking to increase their community involvement. Students will connect with nonprofit agencies, explore post-collegiate civic opportunities, and pursue their passions through civic engagement.</p>\n<p>The<strong><em> Global Leadership Program</em></strong> is for students with a strong interest in international and global issues. Students will complete internationally-focused service opportunities. This track challenges students to become more globally-minded citizens and leaders.</p>\n<p> <strong><em> </em></strong>Program Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Enrollment in LDR 2262 or Directed Independent Research</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum of 15 Service Hours</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Program specific events</li>\n<li>Minimum 3.0 cumulative GPA</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Learn more about each of the programs here: <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs</a></p>\n<p><strong>Application Deadline: </strong><strong>December 15, 2017</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/apply\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/apply</a></p>','2017-12-11','2017-12-15','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs','Michael McFadden','(407) 823-2223','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',8),(2489,'Applied Project Management Certificate Program','applied-project-management-certificate-program','<p><strong>Position Yourself for a Big Career Move</strong><br><br>UCF Continuing Education brings you Project Management training that fits your career and education goals. Training includes courses for those new to project management, those with senior level experience, and PDU courses to help maintain PM credentials.</p>\n<p>Ranked as one of the top 50 best project management programs our Applied Project Management Certification Program teaches a practical approach on project management principles working in a project management capacity and prepares participants for the CAPM® and PMP® examinations administered through the Project Management Institute (PMI).</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Schedule</strong></span><br>Twelve weeks, instructor-led<br>Tuesday Evenings, 5:30pm – 9:30pm<br>Spring: 2/20/2018 – 5/8/2018<br>Summer: 5/22/2018 – 8/7/2018</p>\n<p>Tuition Includes instruction, textbooks, and additional supplemental study materials.<br>$2,495 Registration Fee<br><em>$2,395 UCF Alumni Registration Fee</em></p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Location</strong></span><br>UCF Continuing Education,<br>Innovative Center<br>3280 Progress Drive Suite 700<br>Orlando, FL 32826</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Benefits</strong></span><br>• 12 week program offered in an interactive instructor-led classroom format to keep you on track.<br>• Our program exceeds PMI’s education requirement of 23 hours of CAPM® and 35 hours of PMP® education to become eligible to sit for the CAPM® or PMP® exam.<br>• Learn and apply project management techniques that are effective in initiating, planning, executing, monitoring, controlling and closing a project.<br>• Learn test taking strategies to successfully pass the CAPM® or PMP® exam.<br>• Qualifies for most tuition reimbursement and payment plans are available</p>\n<p>We have detailed information on this program and registration available on our web page at: <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/pm\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/pm</a></p>\n<p></p>','2017-12-18','2018-02-13','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/pm','Lisa Ruscigno','(212) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2490,'Spring 2018 SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP Courses','spring-2018-shrm-cpshrm-scp-courses','<p>We partner with the Society for Human Resources Management to offer preparation using the SHRM Learning System materials for the SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP certification exams. The new SHRM certification recognizes that HR professionals are at the core of leading organizational success. It is built upon one singular body of knowledge designed to elevate the HR profession around the world. It ensures that the HR professional possesses the relevant HR knowledge required for today’s workplace, but it goes one step further. The SHRM certification tests the HR professional’s competencies – the ability to put knowledge to work through critical thinking and application.</p>\n<p>This course is offered in both live-online and in-person formats. The <strong>SPRING 2018</strong> schedule is below:</p>\n<p><strong>East Orlando/UCF Main Campus Start date: February 21 Wednesdays; 6:00-9:00pm</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Live-Online Start date: February 27 Tuesdays; 6:00-9:00pm</strong></p>\n<p><strong>UCF Sanford/Lake Mary Start date: March 10 Saturdays; 10:00am-5:00pm</strong></p>\n<p>We have detailed information on this program and registration available on our web page at: <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm</a>. The 2018 SHRM Learning System books and online access, along with additional online and printed materials, will be included within the cost of the course registration fee. We offer the early bird registration fee of $1179.00 until one month prior to the course start date. Additionally, UCF Continuing Education offers payment plans in which course fees can be paid in installments prior to the start of the course. You are able to also view these on our website, and we have options that allow participants to complete the payment in either two or three installments. If you miss the Early Bird rate deadline, we offer UCF Faculty, Staff and Alumni a discounted registration fee of $1229.</p>\n<p>If you would like to learn more about the SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP credentials, the eligibility, application or exam process, please visit <a href=\"http://certification.shrm.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://certification.shrm.org/</a></p>\n<p>Although this course is preparatory for the SHRM-CP and SHRM-SCP Certification exams, not all participants intend to sit for SHRM’s exams after the course. We welcome HR practitioners into this course for the valuable knowledge and professional development and participants will also receive a certificate of completion at the end of the course.</p>\n<p>If you would like more information, please contact ceprograms@ucf.edu or 407-882-0260.</p>','2017-12-18','2018-02-13','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2491,'UCF Coding Boot Camp Information Session','ucf-coding-boot-camp-information-session','<p>Learn to Code at UCF Coding Boot Camp. If you’re interested in an exciting career in web development—UCF Coding Boot Camp can help you get there.<br>Get the inside scoop on this dynamic, full-stack web development program when you RSVP for the virtual info session December 19 at 9 p.m. ET—Powered by Trilogy Education Services. RSVP for the event <a href=\"https://zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_q8B0Y1JiQ2anpPstljjbVQ\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a> and use the code UCF17 when registering.   </p>\n<p>Web development is a high-growth career track, with an estimated 27% growth rate through 2024 according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics. If you’re looking to switch career paths or learn new marketable skills, UCF Coding Boot Camp could be the opportunity you’ve been looking for. Choosing the right boot camp is a BIG decision. </p>\n<p>Expert Insight<br>You\'ll get key insights from our boot camp evangelist who not only has years of experience in the field, but a passion for teaching and helping students succeed.<br><br>Program Overview<br>See what makes us unique. We\'ll talk about our cutting-edge curriculum, our hands-on classroom environment, our student success team that will walk alongside you, and our career services team that will help prepare you for the job search.<br><br>Q&amp;A Session<br>Have specific questions? We\'ve got answers. Submit your questions with your RSVP and they may get answered LIVE during the Q&amp;A portion of the webinar.<br><br>Join the fun. Reserve your spot for 9 p.m. ET on Tuesday, December 19. RSVP for the event<span> <a href=\"https://zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_q8B0Y1JiQ2anpPstljjbVQ\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a></span><span> </span>and use the code UCF17 when registering.  </p>','2017-12-15','2017-12-19','https://zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_q8B0Y1JiQ2anpPstljjbVQ','Todd Freece','(407) 882-0260','todd.freece@ucf.edu','Todd Freece','Pending',32),(2492,'November 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - Debra Urban','november-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-debra-urban','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for November 2017 – Debra Urban</p>\n<p>Debra is the Senior Administrative Assistant in the College of Nursing. She has worked for UCF since 2002. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>                “Debra is resourceful, creative, and a solution –oriented person who frequently develops new and efficient business processes. Her pro-active approach to the role prevents chaos and crisis at the last minute. She does all this, with a smile and positive attitude.</em></p>\n<p><em>Key words from UCF’s “Our Impact” statement personify what Debra does for the College of Nursing on a daily basis. She provides an example of excellence amidst the ‘scale’ of the CON. With thousands of nursing students and almost as many community partners, Debra has created an environment of excellence that allows lives and livelihoods to be transformed.” </em></p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. Debra receives a certification, one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag. She will also receive a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize his nominators, Dr. Mary Lou Sole and Norma Conner who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Debra is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Debra.</p>','2018-01-02','2018-01-09','http://hr.ucf.edu/','Deborah Frankenbach','','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Publish',23),(2493,'USTA Tennis Day','usta-tennis-day','<p>USTA Tennis Day is an opportunity to learn about tennis by experiencing different methods of playing. RWC intramural sports and fitness will have three activities: Cardio Tennis, Short Court Tennis and Wheelchair Tennis.</p>\n<p>Registration Link:<span> </span><a href=\"http://www.imleagues.com/spa/sport/057170ccd624458c943ad1d2db383aa8/home\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">IMLeagues.com/ucf</a></p>\n<p>Play Dates: Wednesday, January 10th at 4pm</p>','2018-01-10','2018-01-10','http://www.imleagues.com/spa/sport/057170ccd624458c943ad1d2db383aa8/home','Scott Mauro','(407) 823-2408','scott.mauro@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(2494,'Join the Knights Tonight for a Block Party','join-the-knights-tonight-for-a-block-party','<p><span>The UCF Football team will commemorate their undefeated season tonight at 6 p.m. with a free block party downtown on Church Street. For more information, visit <a href=\"http://today.ucf.edu/knights-celebrate-season-parades-walt-disney-world-downtown-orlando/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">today.ucf.edu/knights-celebrate-season-parades-walt-disney-world-downtown-orlando</a>.</span></p>','2018-01-08','2018-01-08','http://today.ucf.edu/knights-celebrate-season-parades-walt-disney-world-downtown-orlando/','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-3213','mtaylor@athletics.ucf.edu','Laura Cole','Publish',35),(2495,'MLK Day of Service','mlk-day-of-service','<p> Come join Volunteer UCF as we participate in the <strong>City of Orlando Mayor\'s MLK Day of Service</strong>! This event is a great way to become civically involved within your community and to honor the efforts of<strong> Martin Luther King Jr.,</strong> and others involved in the <strong>Civil Rights Movement</strong>. Lets make our day off from school, a day of service and impact. We will be volunteering at Catalina Elementary School and Memorial Middle School. Volunteers will be helping with landscaping, painting interior walls of the schools , and stocking the food pantry. Due to lack of available resources, the scope of the volunteer work really aides in the production of the two schools. </p>\n<p>If interested, volunteers must RSVP through the Volunteer UCF Knight Connect Page and follow the directions listed in the description section. We will be meeting in front of CFE Arena at <strong>7:30am</strong> for check in, next to Knights Plaza. For any questions, please contact Jayda Potts at vucfcivic@ucf.edu.<strong> </strong></p>\n<p><strong></strong></p>','2018-01-15','2018-01-15','https://ucf.campuslabs.com/engage/event/1677256','Jayda Potts','(228) 365-1144','vucfcivic@ucf.edu','Volunteer UCF','Publish',36),(2496,'Memorial Service for Professor Simon Fraser Barton','memorial-service-for-professor-simon-fraser-barton','<p>A memorial service for history Professor Simon Fraser Barton, who died Dec. 15, will be held 4 p.m. Feb. 1 in UCF’s <a href=\"http://map.ucf.edu/locations/7ab/live-oak-ballroomgarden-room-fc-a/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Live Oak Room</a>. He was 55. Barton, a historian of medieval Iberia, came to UCF in 2017 after nearly 24 years as a faculty member at the University of Exeter in England.</p>','2018-01-11','2018-02-01','','Heather Gibson','','heather.gibson@ucf.edu','Gene Kruckemyer','Publish',39),(2497,'Hazing 101','hazing-101','<p><span>Join us for a spring workshop on hazing behaviors and prevention strategies.  You will gain leadership values and skills to help prevent hazing at UCF.  You may register for the event  here:</span><a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2Fhazing101&amp;h=ATOavB9dExUZJv3nVHlMAx58XnxmFdjlO0dGymVmeFq76rCq26OXqNjniJsGsqd1xCZNKDLtJHe9Ogus4djmaL-rf3GEOR8_sZfG4qJZFVcY5dWopvWdm1LOX4koE86efNiabSuu6kiKHMB_II3t8ZqFPo1a68xKU4-JZuIh4jd_ehC-XReNYpye5JCYgcJO3iWF_jww8yjzJ94i_42CBK6fx9rOEqWJ7hLFDwNftsKIfeYcmjeknpAQKTm0QlFfmjUBO4s9Cdnd9x6g_q0t7ZxFRye_m8wMEV0oqm8\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/hazing101</a>.  The workshop will take place on Thursday, January 18, 2018 from 12:00pm- 1:00pm in the Student Union room 223.</p>','2018-01-12','2018-01-18','','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','germayne graham','Pending',41),(2498,'Tutor Homeless Students with Children Beyond Our Borders','tutor-homeless-students-with-children-beyond-our-borders-1','<p>Children Beyond Our Border\'s UCF Chapter is looking for volunteers that can tutor every Wednesday from 2-6pm for the duration of January 24 - April 18. The students are considered homeless for they are living in a long-term stay motel. Volunteers will be assisting students with their homework as well as encouraging them throughout the year with their school work.</p>\n<p>If you\'re interested you can apply at: <a href=\"http://www.chbob.org/volunteerucf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.chbob.org/volunteerucf</a>, applications are accepted on a rolling basis but we encourage you to sign-up as early as possible. </p>\n<p>Note:The tutoring session is from 2:30PM - 5:30PM however volunteer time (2-6PM) includes time spent driving, set-up, tutoring time and clean-up. <span>Tutoring is for the children living at the Great Value Suites, address listed below, but takes place in the office next door.</span></p>\n<p>*This tutoring program can be used as a Service Learning requirement for many classes.</p>\n<p>Come out and join us as we make friendships with each other and motivate one another to succeed academically!</p>','2018-01-17','2018-04-18','http://www.chbob.org/volunteerucf.html','Yanelis Diaz','(786) 202-1950','ucfchapter@chbob.org','Yanelis Diaz, Children Beyond Our Borders','Publish',43),(2502,'UCF RWC After Hours: The Greatest Knight on Earth! Signup Deadline.','ucf-rwc-after-hours-the-greatest-knight-on-earth-signup-deadline','<p>Step right right up and j<span>oin us Friday night, February 2nd at 10pm for After Hours: The Greatest Knight on Earth! 40 teams of four students will participate in carnival-themed games involving physical skill, intellectual challenges, and teamwork. A number of prizes will be awarded to the top teams as well as opportunities to win prizes during our social media contest The night of the event! All participants will enjoy free pizza from our sponsor Flipper Pizzeria and a t-shirt. </span></p>\n<p><span>The signup deadline is fast approaching on, Tuesday, January 23</span>rd<span>!</span></p>\n<p>This year\'s theme will be \"The Greatest Knight on Earth\" and all games are inspired by popular carnival attractions! Costumes are encouraged, but not mandatory. To sign your team up now go to this link in this posting. Can\'t wait to see you there. </p>','2018-01-16','2018-01-23','http://www.imleagues.com/spa/league/69dcbd373ab04c4a9a71c293a921e945/home','Heather Marshall','(407) 823-2408','Heather.Marshall@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Pending',34),(2503,'RWC After Hours: The Greatest Knight on Earth! Signup Deadline.','rwc-after-hours-the-greatest-knight-on-earth-signup-deadline','<p>Step right right up and j<span>oin us Friday night, February 2nd at 10pm for After Hours: The Greatest Knight on Earth! 40 teams of four students will participate in carnival-themed games involving physical skill, intellectual challenges, and teamwork. A number of prizes will be awarded to the top teams as well as opportunities to win pr