cial media contest The night of the event! All participants will enjoy free pizza from our sponsor Flipper Pizzeria and a t-shirt. </span></p>\n<p><span>The signup deadline is fast approaching on, Tuesday, January 23</span>rd<span>! </span>To sign your team up now go to <a href=\"http://www.imleagues.com/spa/league/69dcbd373ab04c4a9a71c293a921e945/home\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"RWC After Hours\">After Hours Registration</a>. Can\'t wait to see you there. </p>','2018-01-16','2018-01-23','http://www.imleagues.com/spa/league/69dcbd373ab04c4a9a71c293a921e945/home','Heather Marshall','(407) 823-2408','Heather.Marshall@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Pending',34),(2507,'Lake Apopka Birding Festival','lake-apopka-birding-festival','<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-5_content\">The Lake Apopka Birding Festival is a weekend event that is perfect for birders visiting Florida or locals wanting to learn more from well-known, knowledgeable birding guides. You can add to your life list while exploring a unique birding area. The Festival is only 35–45 minutes from Orlando attractions.</p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-6_content\"> </p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-16_content\">On Friday, January 19th, through Sunday, January 21st, participate in field trips on the 20,000-acre Lake Apopka North Shore property and other nearby sites, sponsored by<span> </span><span><a href=\"http://www.orangeaudubonfl.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Orange Audubon Society</a></span>.  Trips will search for as many as possible of the<span> </span><span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lakeapopkawildlifedrive/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">360+ species documented</a></span>, plus recently sighted rarities.</p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-17_content\"> </p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-19_content\">Timing in January is perfect to see a multitude of overwintering and resident species!</p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-26_content\">For photos of some of the fantastic birds  of the Lake Apopka North Shore,<span> </span><br>visit<span> </span><span><a href=\"http://facebook.com/lakeapopkawildlifedrive\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/lakeapopkawildlifedrive</a></span></p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-31_content\">or<span> </span><span><a href=\"http://facebook.com/groups/lakeapopkawd/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/groups/lakeapopkawd/</a></span></p>','2018-01-18','2018-01-21','http://orangeaudubonfl.org/birdapalooza/schedule.html','Deborah Green','(386) 690-4705','watermediaservices@icloud.com','Orange Audubon Society','Pending',33),(2508,'Lake Apopka Birding Festival','lake-apopka-birding-festival-1','<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-3_content\">The Lake Apopka Birding Festival is a weekend event that is perfect for birders visiting Florida or locals wanting to learn more from well-known, knowledgeable birding guides. You can add to your life list while exploring a unique birding area. The Festival is only 35–45 minutes from Orlando attractions.</p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-16_content\">On Friday, January 19th, through Sunday, January 21st, participate in field trips on the 20,000-acre Lake Apopka North Shore property and other nearby sites, sponsored by<span> </span><span><a href=\"http://www.orangeaudubonfl.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Orange Audubon Society</a></span>.  Trips will search for as many as possible of the<span> </span><span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lakeapopkawildlifedrive/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">360+ species documented</a></span>, plus recently sighted rarities.</p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-19_content\">Timing in January is perfect to see a multitude of overwintering and resident species!</p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-19_content\"><a href=\"http://orangeaudubonfl.org/birdapalooza/schedule.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-26_content\">For photos of some of the fantastic birds  of the Lake Apopka North Shore,<span> </span><br>visit<span> </span><span><a href=\"http://facebook.com/lakeapopkawildlifedrive\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/lakeapopkawildlifedrive</a></span></p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-31_content\">or<span> </span><span><a href=\"http://facebook.com/groups/lakeapopkawd/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/groups/lakeapopkawd/</a></span></p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-31_content\"><span>For more info check out our FB and website:</span></p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-31_content\"><span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lakeapopkabirdingfestival/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.facebook.com/lakeapopkabirdingfestival/</a></span></p>\n<p data-content-guid=\"u27972-31_content\"><span><a href=\"http://orangeaudubonfl.org/birdapalooza/schedule.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://orangeaudubonfl.org/birdapalooza/schedule.html</a></span></p>','2018-01-18','2018-01-21','http://orangeaudubonfl.org/birdapalooza/schedule.html','Deborah Green','(386) 690-4705','watermediaservices@icloud.com','Orange Audubon Society','Pending',33),(2512,'30 Under 30 Nominations','30-under-30-nominations','<p>The 30 Under 30 awards program recognizes outstanding young alumni who have found success in their professional and personal endeavors post-graduation. Universities within our CASE district and across the country have seen amazing results from creating these programs at their institutions. UCF Alumni is pleased to announce that nominations for the class of 2018 are open.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Eligibility and criteria:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must be a graduate of the University of Central Florida (undergraduate or graduate degree).</li>\n<li>Must be age 29 or under on May 19, 2018.</li>\n<li>Nominees for 30 Under 30 must demonstrate a commitment to maintaining a lifelong relationship with Knights and strive to uphold UCF Young Alumni values.</li>\n<li>UCF Young Alumni Values:</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\"Scholarship, Bold, Trailblazing, Generous, Resilient\"</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must be willing to submit a professional headshot that can be published by UCF Alumni and other UCF entities, as deemed appropriate.</li>\n<li>Self-nominations will not be accepted.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Timeline:</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Jan. 15, 2018: Nominations open</li>\n<li>Feb. 9, 2018 at 11:59 p.m. EST: Nominations close</li>\n<li>Mar. 30, 2018: Class of 2018 30 under 30 honorees notified</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>A committee comprised of volunteers from the Young Alumni Council will be tasked with the review and selection of our newest honorees. Nominations will be accepted through February 9, 2018. The nomination form can be found at: <a href=\"https://www.ucfalumni.com/30under30\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ucfalumni.com/30under30</a>. We are excited to continue this tradition of recognizing our best and brightest rising stars.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Please contact Yelitza Zamora via e-mail at Yelitza.Zamora@ucf.edu with questions.</p>\n<p> </p>','2018-01-19','2018-02-08','https://www.ucfalumni.com/30under30','Yelitza Zamora','(407) 882-0561','Yelitza.Zamora@ucf.edu','Elizabeth Irizarry on behalf of Michael Morsberger, Vice President for Advancement and CEO, UCF Foundation','Publish',44),(2514,'Omicron Delta Kappa National Leadership Honor Society applications now available!','omicron-delta-kappa-national-leadership-honor-society-applications-now-available-1','<p>The Omicron Delta Kappa Society is the national leadership honor society for college students, faculty, staff, administrators, and alumni that recognizes and encourages superior scholarship, leadership, and exemplary character.</p>\n<p>The student and faculty members of Omicron Delta Kappa work closely together to foster leadership abilities within its members. The organization is also dedicated to a variety of projects that benefit the university and the surrounding community.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements for induction into the </strong><strong>Central Florida Circle of ODK:</strong></p>\n<p>Class standing: Junior (at least 60 credits), Senior, or Graduate Level</p>\n<p>Minimum GPA: 3.2 for undergraduates, 3.5 for graduate students</p>\n<p>Initiation fee of $95-includes lifetime membership and pin (graduation cords may be purchased for an additional $25) . If accepted your dues will be due by 3/28/18 at 12:00 PM. Induction will be held on Tuesday, 4/12/18 at 4pm in Ferrell Commons 165-LEAD Scholars Academy</p>\n<p>Demonstrated leadership in at least two of the five areas:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Scholarship</li>\n<li>Athletics</li>\n<li>Campus/Community Service, Social/Religious Activities, and Campus Government</li>\n<li>Journalism, Speech and the Mass Media</li>\n<li>Creative and Performing Arts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply:</strong></p>\n<p>Visit our website at <u><a href=\"https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form</a></u> to complete the online application</p>\n<p>Questions may be directed to Dr. Stacey Malaret, Faculty Secretary for ODK, in the LEAD Scholars Academy Office, Ferrell Commons 165</p>\n<p><strong>Online application deadline is 3/8/18</strong></p>','2018-01-23','2018-03-08','https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',8),(2517,'Applications Open for the Leadership Empowerment Program!','applications-open-for-the-leadership-empowerment-program','<p><span>The Leadership Empowerment Program (LEP) provides opportunities for selected faculty and staff to gain career-enhancing skills and experiences in today’s changing educational environment. The  program engages scholars in an exploration of leadership principles and strategies, professional skills, and higher education issues through self-reflection, mentorship, engagement with dozens of guest speakers, and project development.</span></p>\n<p><span>Benefits include:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Monthly Seminars</strong><span> </span>– A core of seminars is designed around specific themes relevant to higher education administration in general and professional development. Combined with focused learning experiences, these seminars serve as the foundation upon which LEP scholars tailor the program to meet their individual needs and career goals.</li>\n<li><strong>Mentors</strong><span> </span>– Participants will be assigned a mentor to work with them to further develop their professional knowledge, skills and abilities during the program.</li>\n<li><strong>Leadership Institute</strong><span> </span>– The annual leadership institute, offered during the spring semester and managed by the LEP class, features a variety of leadership workshop sessions. It also allows members of the current class to present elements of their LEP project or career map.</li>\n<li><strong>Graduation Reception</strong><span> </span>– LEP graduates and their supporters will celebrate the successful completion of the program with a certificate and reflections on the year of growth.</li>\n<li><strong>Graduates of the program are eligible for a one-time waiver of search for a position at UCF.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><span></span><span>We are accepting applications for the 2018-2019 cohort until March 9, 2018. </span><span>For more information on LEP and the application process, please visit the website at <a href=\"https://diversity.ucf.edu/faculty-staff/leadership-empowerment-program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://diversity.ucf.edu/faculty-staff/leadership-empowerment-program/</a>.</span></p>','2018-01-25','2018-03-09','https://diversity.ucf.edu/faculty-staff/leadership-empowerment-program/','Dr. Cyndia Muñiz','(407) 823-6478','LEP@ucf.edu','Office of Diversity and Inclusion','Publish',45),(2521,'Volunteer to work on a student film!','volunteer-to-work-on-a-student-film','<p><span><strong>Production Meet &amp; Greet</strong></span></p>\n<p><span> </span><strong>ABOUT</strong><br><span></span></p>\n<p><span>At the start of the Fall and Spring semesters the Film Program at the UCF School of Visual Arts &amp; Design hosts a Production Meet &amp; Greet to help student filmmakers find crew members for their upcoming productions. It is like a job fair for UCF student film projects. This event also serves as a great opportunity for students to meet new friends and similarly minded individuals to collaborate with on future creative projects.</span></p>\n<p><span></span><span><strong>Students Who Want to Volunteer as Crew</strong></span></p>\n<p><span>Any and all students are eligible to volunteer as crew members. Come on down and see what the details are for each project and find a shoot that works for you. These projects will need all kinds of help, so don’t be afraid to try on different hats and take on new challenges. This is a great way to gain some experience!</span></p>\n<p><span><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Student Film Productions Looking to Recruit AND HOW TO RESERVE A SPOT</strong></span></p>\n<p><span>If you wish to participate and recruit crew members (hand out flyers about your film needs, have a sign-up sheet to collect info on interested students, display a poster, etc.) please email Lisa Peterson [<a href=\"mailto:Lisa.Peterson@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Lisa.Peterson@ucf.edu</a>] with the information requested in the <a href=\"http://lisacookfilm.files.wordpress.com/2010/06/f-2012-meet-and-greet-prod-info.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Meet &amp; Greet Project Information</a> form. There will be folding tables set up for you to use as a “booth.” </span><span>We are putting names on the tables this year, so you have to take the spot you have been randomly assigned. Due to popular demand, we have to place a many students as we can at each table.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>We have a great demand for table space this year, so to make sure you get your spot, you have to arrive at the stage no later than 4:00pm. After the event opens at 4p, we will be filling the empty spots with stand-by students. We can’t hold the spot for you, you or someone from your team has to be here by 4p to confirm a table spot.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>It is strongly recommended that you create a handout – you can use the Meet &amp; Greet Information form as an example if you want – so that each potential volunteer crew member has something to take away with all the important contact information and details about your project. You should also have a way to keep a record of the names and contact info of any students who want to work on your shoot. You can use the <a href=\"http://lisacookfilm.files.wordpress.com/2010/06/crew-contact-information1.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Crew Contact Information</a> form to do this or make your own.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>Any SVAD Film Program undergraduate and graduate student is welcomed to pitch their film project at the Production Meet &amp; Greet.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span><strong>The Spring Film Program Production Meet &amp; Greet will happen Friday, January 26, 2018 from 4:00pm to 6:00pm in the Film Sound Stage | NSC-181A.</strong></span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>','2018-01-25','2018-01-27','http://operationalportal.com/?page_id=4080','Lisa Peterson','(407) 823-5430','lisa.peterson@ucf.edu','Lisa Peterson, Associate Instructor, Film, School of Visual Arts & Design','Pending',48),(2522,'Harry Potter VFX Producer Joyce Cox to speak','harry-potter-vfx-producer-joyce-cox-to-speak','<p><span><strong>1/29/18 - NEXT Film Producers Guild Meeting</strong></span></p>\n<p><span>Hi everyone!</span></p>\n<p><span>Our next meeting will be held <strong>next Monday, January 29th from 6 PM to 7 PM in NSC 148.</strong>  Our guest speaker is going to be Joyce Cox, a VFX producer from LA. We will have her Skype in, </span><span>so make sure to prepare questions</span><span>!  You can check out her ImbD here: <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Ffacebook.us14.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D64496b7c4a06d730d4cbaf2b5%26id%3D55b2536ad3%26e%3D56c3087a40&amp;data=02%7C01%7Clisa.peterson%40ucf.edu%7C8b3e56a935e4497f052c08d5645fbb7c%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636525284695671435&amp;sdata=c5N%2F5PTci3H5ZToq%2B4%2Fqb%2BujGoUc3jnrc%2Fmg0z4dGaE%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1295476/?ref_=ttfc_fc_cr3</a> </span></p>\n<p><span>Joyce began her career producing live-action and post-production for commercial advertising. She moved into feature films in the mid 90’s as the visual effects industry began its rapid evolution into its present role as a creative and technical cornerstone for filmmaking. Initially, she produced visual effects within digital facilities working on TITANIC, HARRY POTTER AND THE SORCERER’S STONE, FANTASIA 2000 and HOW THE GRINCH STOLE CHRISTMAS. Facility producing gave Joyce the underlying knowledge she brought to the challenging role of production side Visual Effects Producer on X-MEN 2, SUPERMAN RETURNS, THE DARK KNIGHT, AVATAR, MEN IN BLACK III, THE GREAT GATSBY and most recently Jon Favreau’s THE JUNGLE BOOK.</span></p>','2018-01-26','2018-01-23','https://www.facebook.com/groups/1637132243230761/','Delana Wilkinson','(407) 823-5430','DelanaWilkinson@Knights.ucf.edu','Lisa Peterson Associate Instructor Film School of Visual Arts & Design','Pending',48),(2523,'The 8th Annual Knights Write Showcase','the-8th-annual-knights-write-showcase','<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/167679727183709/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>The 8th Annual Knights Write Showcase</strong></a></p>\n<p><strong>Wednesday, February 7, 2018 </strong>10 a.m. to 3 p.m. in the Student Union, Pegasus Ballroom</p>\n<p>The Knights Write Showcase provides a chance for students and faculty from across campus to get a glimpse of the exciting work currently going on in our First-Year Writing Program. Activities include student displays, three student panels, and an award ceremony. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Student Posters: 10:00 a.m.</p>\n<p>Awards Ceremony: 11:00 a.m.</p>\n<p>Student Panels: 11:45 a.m., 12:45 p.m., 1:45 p.m.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>For more information about the First-Year Writing Program or the Department of Writing and Rhetoric, visit <a href=\"http://writingandrhetoric.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://writingandrhetoric.cah.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2018-01-29','2018-01-08','https://www.facebook.com/events/167679727183709/','Department of Writing & Rhetoric','(407) 823-2295','writingandrhetoric@ucf.edu','College of Arts & Humanities','Pending',10),(2524,'The 8th Annual Knights Write Showcase','the-8th-annual-knights-write-showcase-1','<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/167679727183709/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>The 8th Annual Knights Write Showcase</strong></a></p>\n<p><strong>Wednesday, February 7, 2018 </strong>10 a.m. to 3 p.m. in the Student Union, Pegasus Ballroom</p>\n<p>The Knights Write Showcase provides a chance for students and faculty from across campus to get a glimpse of the exciting work currently going on in our First-Year Writing Program. Activities include student displays, three student panels, and an award ceremony. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Student Posters: 10:00 a.m.</p>\n<p>Awards Ceremony: 11:00 a.m.</p>\n<p>Student Panels: 11:45 a.m., 12:45 p.m., 1:45 p.m.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>For more information about the First-Year Writing Program or the Department of Writing and Rhetoric, visit <a href=\"http://writingandrhetoric.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://writingandrhetoric.cah.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2018-01-29','2018-01-08','https://www.facebook.com/events/167679727183709/','Department of Writing & Rhetoric','(407) 823-2295','writingandrhetoric@ucf.edu','College of Arts & Humanities','Pending',10),(2525,'The 8th Annual Knights Write Showcase','the-8th-annual-knights-write-showcase-1-2','<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/167679727183709/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>The 8th Annual Knights Write Showcase</strong></a></p>\n<p><strong>Wednesday, February 7, 2018 </strong>10 a.m. to 3 p.m. in the Student Union, Pegasus Ballroom</p>\n<p>The Knights Write Showcase provides a chance for students and faculty from across campus to get a glimpse of the exciting work currently going on in our First-Year Writing Program. Activities include student displays, three student panels, and an award ceremony. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Student Posters: 10:00 a.m.</p>\n<p>Awards Ceremony: 11:00 a.m.</p>\n<p>Student Panels: 11:45 a.m., 12:45 p.m., 1:45 p.m.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>For more information about the First-Year Writing Program or the Department of Writing and Rhetoric, visit <a href=\"http://writingandrhetoric.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://writingandrhetoric.cah.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2018-01-30','2018-02-08','https://www.facebook.com/events/167679727183709/','Department of Writing & Rhetoric','(407) 823-2295','writingandrhetoric@ucf.edu','College of Arts & Humanities','Publish',10),(2526,'UCF Doctor of Physical Therapy Activity Day','ucf-doctor-of-physical-therapy-activity-day','<p>The students from the Doctor of Physical Therapy program are hosting an annual event with the aim to promote a healthy lifestyle by creating a fun and memorable day for children with disabilities. <strong>Individuals aged 3 through 21 years</strong> and their families are invited to participate in this free event. </p>\n<p><strong>Date</strong>: March 24th, 2018</p>\n<p><strong>Time</strong>: two sessions = 10am to 11:30am or 11:30am to 1pm</p>\n<p><strong>Location</strong>: UCF IOA Plaza (behind Brighthouse stadium)</p>\n<p>The day is filled with fun games, sports, and activities that are adapted for children with various types of motor and/or cognitive impairments. There are several stations that kids can explore and they\'re all customized so children with disabilities are able to participate without feeling limited by their disabilities.</p>\n<p>There will be activities such as soccer, basketball, face painting, bubbles, and throwing, as well as great music and dancing! Each child will be partnered with a DPT student “buddy” for a 1.5-hour session. The physical therapy student will tailor activities to meet the child’s individual needs and ensure fun and safety!</p>\n<p>Family members, including siblings, and legal guardians are invited to participate in the activities or simply relax and watch. There will also be a low-stimulation station in case kids needs a break from all the excitement. </p>\n<p>The event will also feature a visit from Knightro and some UCF athletes. In addition, the Orlando chapter of Medals4Mettle will honor each participating child at the end of the event at a medals ceremony!</p>\n<p>Visit <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/UCFDPTactivityday/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/UCFDPTactivityday/</a></span> for pictures and to stay updated! </p>\n<p>To make a donation to help with equipment, snacks, and location cost, please visit <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"https://www.gofundme.com/ucf-activity-day\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.gofundme.com/ucf-activity-day</a></span></p>\n<p>This event is <strong>FREE</strong>, so why not come out, have some fun and make some new memories?! :) </p>\n<p>If you have any questions, comments, or concerns, please contact us on facebook or at <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">ucfdptactivityday@gmail.com</span></p>','2018-01-30','2018-03-24','http://ucfdptactivityday.wixsite.com/2018','Activity Day Committee','(407) 325-3559','ucfdptactivityday@gmail.com','Anh Truong (Activity Day committee chair)','Publish',50),(2527,'December 2017 - USPS Employee of the Month - Matthew Fazi','december-2017-usps-employee-of-the-month-matthew-fazi','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for December 2017 – Sgt. Matthew Fazi.</p>\n<p>Sergeant Fazi is the Law Enforcement Sergeant in the UCF Police Department. He has worked for UCF since May 2004.   His nominators had this to say about him:</p>\n<p><em>                “Sgt. Fazi always approaches his job as a Police Department Sergeant and shift supervisor over a group of officers with a focus on the protection of UCF students, employees, visitors and property being his priority. He consistently goes above and beyond to fulfill his duties to help people.   </em></p>\n<p><em>The UCF Police Department provides assistance and serves not only students, faculty and staff, but to visitors as well. In October 2017, Sgt. Fazi exceeded his duties to help out a homeless mother and daughter in need without hesitation. He did whatever it took to make sure they were safe and were provided with food and a safe place to stay. Sgt. Fazi is an outstanding role mode and UCF Employee.”</em></p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for his dedication and hard work. Sgt. Fazi receives a certificate, one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag. He will also receive a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize his nominators, Steven Keith and Christine Gigicos who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Sgt. Fazi is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Sgt. Fazi.</p>','2018-02-01','2018-02-09','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach Human Resources','Publish',23),(2528,'Discounted Universal Orlando Tickets Now Available to Faculty and Staff','discounted-universal-orlando-tickets-now-available-to-faculty-and-staff','<p>The Universal Orlando tickets sold in the SGA Ticket Center are now available to all University Faculty and Staff.  These tickets were previously only available to current UCF students.  You must present a valid UCF ID at the time of purchase.  Prices, ticket availability and purchase limits are detailed on the SGA Ticket Center website, <a href=\"https://ticketcenter.sdes.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ticketcenter.sdes.ucf.edu/</a>. </p>','2018-02-01','2018-02-22','http://ticketcenter.sdes.ucf.edu/','Richard Phillips','(407) 823-2304','richard.phillips@ucf.edu','SGA Ticket Center','Publish',47),(2529,'Janelle Picard to speak to Film Producers Guild at UCF!','janelle-picard-to-speak-to-film-producers-guild-at-ucf','<p><strong>Janelle Picard</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Creative Manager, Theme Park Development</strong></p>\n<p><strong>SeaWorld Parks &amp; Entertainment</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Janelle oversees and contributes to the design and development of major attractions from initial concept through completion, working with teams of architects, engineers, designers, artists, fabricators and more. Recently finished projects include the Dolphin Nursery at SeaWorld Orlando; InvadR™ at Busch Gardens Williamsburg; and Antarctica: Empire of the Penguin at SeaWorld Orlando. Current attractions in progress, scheduled to open in 2018, include Battle for Eire at Busch Gardens Williamsburg, a first-of-its-kind VR action ride, and Infinity Falls at SeaWorld Orlando, a river rapids attraction with surrounding experiences featuring gameplay with conservation and water replenishment messaging.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>A graduate of Bowling Green State University with a Bachelor of Science in Visual Communication Technology, her career path has developed a broad understanding of art and technology in printed and digital design, animation, and production, now supporting her work in the development of themed attractions and environments. She is a member of the Themed Entertainment Association and Harriet B\'s Daughters.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>DATE:  6p-7p   Monday February 5, 2018 in Nicholson 148. Open to all!</p>','2018-02-02','2018-02-06','https://www.facebook.com/groups/1637132243230761/','Delana Wilkinson','','DelanaWilkinson@Knights.ucf.edu','Lisa C. Peterson Associate Instructor School of Visual Arts & Design College of Arts and Humanities University of Central Florida  12400 Aquarius Agora Dr. Orlando, FL 32816   Office: 407.823.5430 Lisa.peterson@ucf.edu svad.cah.ucf.edu','Pending',48),(2530,'Student Call for Posters - Public Administration Research Conference','student-call-for-posters-public-administration-research-conference','<p>All UCF students are invited to submit their research poster proposals for the 12th annual Public Administration Research Conference, hosted by the Center for Public and Nonprofit Management. The conference will take place April 12-April 13 at the Live Oak Event Center. <span>Poster presentations may be research papers, professional projects, service learning projects, case studies or analytical papers. Current or past projects are eligible. Students who participate will receive free conference registration and reimbursement for poster printing costs. <br></span><br><span>Please submit your proposal (title, 250-word abstract, and contact information) to </span><a href=\"mailto:cpnm@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">cpnm@ucf.edu</a><span>. </span>The deadline for submission is March 2, 2018 with acceptance notification by March 9, 2018. <span></span></p>','2018-02-05','2018-03-02','https://ucfparc.wordpress.com/student-engagement/','Maria-Elena Augustin','','maria.augustin@ucf.edu','Center for Public and Nonprofit Management','Publish',51),(2531,'Leadership Week 2018','leadership-week-2018','<p><strong>LEADERSHIP WEEK 2018 </strong> is a week filled with exciting guest speakers, leadership workshops and educational activities designed to develop leadership and inspire social change on our campus and in the community. All sessions will be held February 19-23, 2018 in the University of Central Florida Student Union.  This event is  coordinated by the LEAD Scholars Academy within Student Development and Enrollment Services and supported by Student Government Association, LEAD Students Association and  various offices and departments throughout the University of Central Florida.</p>\n<p>This year we have four dynamic keynote speakers:</p>\n<p><strong>Jane Elliot</strong>- American former third-grade school teacher known for her “Blue eyes–Brown eyes” exercise.</p>\n<p><strong>Richard Lapchick</strong>- National expert on sport and social issues, human rights activist and pioneer for racial equality</p>\n<p><strong>Kaitlyn Chana</strong>- Founder of Reel Stories. Real People., Inc.</p>\n<p><strong>Julien Meyer</strong>- 3-time tech founder and career entrepreneur. </p>\n<p>Information about this year’s key note speakers can be found here <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/keynote\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/keynote</a></p>\n<p>There are 41 sessions and workshops on leadership and social change between the hours of 10:00am- 9:00pm daily.</p>\n<p>Additional information about  these educational sessions can be found on the Leadership Week website <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/</a> </p>','2018-02-06','2018-02-24','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Germayne Graham','Publish',41),(2532,'USPS Staff Council Scholarship applications live!','usps-staff-council-scholarship-applications-live','<p>The USPS Staff Council is now accepting applications for the Spring 2018 Scholarship awards.  Apply now at the Staff Council web site, (<a href=\"http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html</a>) or on the Staff Council Facebook page.  There are two awards available and there is an award dependents available as well.  Applications must be in by 11:59 p.m. February 20, 2018.  To apply you must be a member of the USPS for a minimum of one year, and if you have won an award you must wait one year before applying for that particular award again.  Apply now and avoid the rush!</p>','2018-02-09','2018-02-20','http://pegasus.cc.ucf.edu/~uspsstaf/index.html','Jamie','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie Lamoreaux','Publish',54),(2533,'Information Session - UCF Financials Chart of Accounts (CoA) Redesign','information-session-ucf-financials-chart-of-accounts-coa-redesign','<p>Finance and Accounting invites you to attend an information session on the proposed prototype of the new UCF Financials Chart of Accounts (CoA).</p>\n<p><strong>How does this affect me?</strong></p>\n<p>If your role at UCF involves working with the UCF Financials system, or if you have financial responsibilities for your area, the CoA redesign affects your job. The changes to UCF Financials are not slated to take effect until a later date, but they are very significant.</p>\n<p><strong>How will I benefit?</strong></p>\n<p>Attend the presentation to learn:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How the new chartfields will support the university’s continued growth and provide greater flexibility for financial management and reporting</li>\n<li>What the proposed new chartfields are called, and how they will be used</li>\n<li>The project timeline and when you’ll be able to get training and additional resources to support your area through the change</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>When and where will the information session take place?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>When – February 15, 2018 from 11:00 a.m. to noon</li>\n<li>Where – Teaching Academy, Room TA-117</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you have any questions, please contact the Financials Service Desk at <a href=\"mailto:fntrain@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">fntrain@ucf.edu</a> or (407) 823-5117, option 6.</p>','2018-02-09','2018-02-15','http://financials.ucf.edu/ucf-financials-chart-of-accounts-redesign-project/','Financials Service Desk','(407) 823-5117','fntrain@ucf.edu','Melinda Martin','Publish',55),(2538,'Rec & Wellness Job Fair','rec-wellness-job-fair-1-2-3-4','<p><span>Join us and come learn more about the positions at the Recreaiton and Wellness Center and Wellness and Health Promotion Services! Job fair on each day begins with a 20 minute information session in room 206 and then meet and greet with staff in the main lobby. These are highly encouraged so you can learn a little more about our mission. </span><br><br><span>Positions will be available for summer and fall 2018 in the following areas:</span><br><br><span>Marketing </span><br><span>Fitness</span><br><span>Sport Clubs</span><br><span>Aquatics </span><br><span>Member Services</span><br><span>Intramural Sports</span><br><span>RWC Park</span><br><span>Outdoor Adventure</span><br><span>Building Manager</span><br><span>Wellness and Health Promotion Services Peer Advocates</span><br><br><span>Materials to bring with you:</span><br><span>1) Application, cover letter and resume for each area above you plan to apply for.</span><br><span>2) Pen</span><br><span>3) Great attitude</span><br><br><span>Some of the areas do screen or interview students during the fair so we recommend you dress at least business casual. </span></p>','2018-02-19','2018-03-08','http://events.ucf.edu/event/713793/rwc-whps-job-fair/','Scott Mauro','(407) 823-2408','scott.mauro@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(2539,'January 2018 - USPS Employee of the Month - Iris Rios','january-2018-usps-employee-of-the-month-iris-rios','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for January 2018 – <strong>Iris Rios.</strong></p>\n<p>Ms. Rios is the Administrative Assistant in the College of Undergraduate Studies, Interdisciplinary Studies. Iris has been a UCF employee since 2008. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>”Ms. Rios exemplifies the best in professionalism, efficiency, and collegiality. She is thorough, knowledgeable, self-motivated, and reliable employee. She collaborates well with others, anticipates needs, and devises plans to coordinate complex tasks. </em></p>\n<p><em>Iris understands the growth potential in Interdisciplinary Studies and worked diligently to ensure the search for the permanent Director was successful. While serving current students in her daily responsibilities, Iris’ support throughout the search process displayed her dedication to the next generation of IDS majors and her commitment to our student’s success.” </em></p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. Ms. Rios receives a certificate, one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag. She will also receive a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize her nominators, Dr. Claudia Schippert and Dr. Keisha Hoerrner who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. </p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Ms. Rios is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Ms. Rios.</p>','2018-02-13','2018-02-20','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Debbie Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2540,'Health Care Simulation Program Information Session // Zoom Call','health-care-simulation-program-information-session-zoom-call','<p><span>Today health care professionals are increasingly using simulation and technology to advance the field and improve patient care – and the future applications are limitless. In fact, a recent national study published in the <em>Journal of Nursing Regulation</em> found that simulation can be substituted for clinical experience in up to half of all prelicensure core nursing courses, and other health care disciplines are rapidly adopting this practice as well. With this field rapidly evolving, there is <strong>growing demand for health care simulation experts</strong>.</span><br><br><span>Join us for a 30-minute Zoom Call to learn about <strong><a href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/Sim\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Health Care Simulation\">UCF\'s innovative online Health Care Simulation program</a></strong> where you can be trained on the skills needed to develop and lead health care simulation programs in academic and practice settings.</span><br><br><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Two Options</span>:</strong><br><span>- <a href=\"http://nursing.ucf.edu/Assets/files/Grad-Flyer_SimNurse.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Download flyer (pdf)\">MS in Nursing and Health Care Simulation (11 courses)</a></span><br><span>- <a href=\"http://nursing.ucf.edu/Assets/files/Grad-Flyer_SimNonNurse.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Download flyer (pdf)\">Graduate Certificate in Health Care Simulation* (3 courses)</a></span><br><br><em>* Open to non-nurses as well</em></p>\n<p><strong>Fall 2018 Admission Deadline is March 15 / No GRE requirement / Online program</strong></p>\n<p>____________<br><br>The Zoom Call is limited to 100 participants. Please register in advance: <a href=\"https://ucf-health-care-sim-zoom-call.eventbrite.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf-health-care-sim-zoom-call.eventbrite.com</a></p>','2018-02-14','2018-02-24','https://ucf-health-care-sim-zoom-call.eventbrite.com','Ayanna Lopez','(407) 823-2744','gradnurse@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing | nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/sim','Publish',57),(2541,'Scholarships A2O Has Scholarships Available For Students','scholarships-a2o-has-scholarships-available-for-students','<p><span>Don’t forget to complete the General Scholarship Application for this year to be considered for scholarships throughout the year at </span><span><a href=\"http://ucf.academicworks.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.academicworks.com/</a></span><span>. After you apply remember to go back to this page once or twice a week to look for potential scholarship matches that you may apply to.  Also, under the External Opportunities, there are many additional scholarship opportunities you may be interested in and can apply to!</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>','2018-02-15','2018-04-30','http://ucf.academicworks.com/','UCF Student Financial Assistance','(407) 823-2827','SFAScholarships@ucf.edu','Jamey Walker, UCF Student Financial Assistance','Publish',58),(2543,'Applications open for Clinton Global Initiative University 2018!','applications-open-for-clinton-global-initiative-university-2018-1','<p>Applications for the 11th annual Clinton Global Initiative University meeting are now open! <span>Hosted by President Clinton and Chelsea Clinton, the 11th annual CGI U meeting will take place October 19-21, 2018 at the University of Chicago in Chicago, Illinois. Through the CGI University Network and other opportunities, </span>over $750,000 in funding<span> will be available to select CGI U 2018 students to help them turn their ideas into action. </span></p>\n<p>To be considered for admission, all applicants are required to design a <a href=\"https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/meetings/cgi-university/commitments/about-cgiu-commitments\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Commitment to Action</a> in one of CGI U\'s five focus areas: Education, Environment and Climate Change, Peace and Human Rights, Poverty Alleviation, and Public Health.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Eligibility:</strong> <span>Applicants must be at least 18 years of age and currently enrolled in an institution of higher education at the time of application. (Ex: A student graduating in the Spring of 2018 would be eligible to apply.) Students who will be at least 18 years of age and enrolled in an institution of higher education by October 2018 are also eligible to apply. (Ex: A high school senior who turns 18 years of age in June 2018 and commences university studies by October 2018 or a university graduate enrolling in an advanced degree program by October 2018 would also be eligible to apply.)</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The Early Decision and Travel Assistance deadline is <strong>11:59 PM EST on March 16, 2018</strong>.</p>\n<p>The Regular Decision deadline is<span> </span><strong>11:59 PM EST on April 23, 2018</strong>.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>For more information, visit <a href=\"http://cgiu.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://cgiu.org/</a> or attend an information session by searching the tag \"CGI U\" on the <a href=\"http://events.ucf.edu/search/?q=cgi+u\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Events Calendar</a>.</p>','2018-02-19','2018-04-23','http://cgiu.org/apply','Mike McFadden','(407) 823-6957','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Mike McFadden','Publish',52),(2544,'UCF Celebrates the Arts 2018 - Tickets on sale March 1!','ucf-celebrates-the-arts-2018-tickets-on-sale-march-1','<p><span>UCF Celebrates the Arts is an annual eight day showcase of music, performances and interactive visual displays that runs April 6-14, 2018 at the Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts in downtown Orlando. </span><br><br><span>The festival will open with a tribute to American composer, conductor and educator Leonard Bernstein (Bernstein’s MASS: A Theatre Piece for Singers, Players and Dancers) and closes with a concert featuring major jazz artists, the UCF Orchestra and Flying Horse Big Band celebrating UCF President John C. Hitt’s contributi</span><span>on to UCF and Orlando (Imagine Something Wonderful: The Flying Horse Big Band meets the UCF Orchestra featuring special guests T-Bone, Veronica Swift, and The Jazz Professors).<br></span></p>\n<p><span>Tickets for UCF Celebrates the Arts will be available starting March 1. For a complete schedule, ticket reservations and other information, visit the festival’s website at <a data-lynx-mode=\"async\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.arts.ucf.edu%2F&amp;h=ATOHcEO-0PEX4hRq3oEkwQD9ztDnFzNO4bT5MnEdlimmgrl77jvz_9JIDbGsvHFiyrF24rKSD6hRXNKjBNk_RYi-lOuE_rKG_Ah9XeTaY7vUKyVLisrDwCPX1VebUAcILYxONB-ftHt6VWl0G5aA\" href=\"http://www.arts.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.arts.ucf.edu.</a></span></p>\n<p><span>Follow along for event updates, behind-the-scenes with students, livestreaming and more! - #artsatUCF <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ArtsAtUCF\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">@artsatUCF</a></span></p>','2018-02-19','2018-02-28','http://arts.ucf.edu/','UCF School of Performing Arts - Box Office','(407) 823-1500','boxoffice@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',10),(2545,'UCF Celebrates the Arts 2018 - Tickets on sale NOW!','ucf-celebrates-the-arts-2018-tickets-on-sale-now','<p><span>UCF Celebrates the Arts is an annual eight-day showcase of music, performances and interactive visual displays that runs April 6-14, 2018 at the Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts in downtown Orlando. </span><br><br><span>The festival will open with a tribute to American composer, conductor and educator Leonard Bernstein (Bernstein’s MASS: A Theatre Piece for Singers, Players and Dancers) and closes with a concert featuring major jazz artists, the UCF Orchestra and Flying Horse Big Band celebrating UCF President John C. Hitt’s contributi</span><span>on to UCF and Orlando (Imagine Something Wonderful: The Flying Horse Big Band meets the UCF Orchestra featuring special guests T-Bone, Veronica Swift, and The Jazz Professors).<br></span></p>\n<p><span>Tickets for UCF Celebrates the Arts will be available starting March 1. For a complete schedule, ticket reservations and other information, visit the festival’s website at <a data-lynx-mode=\"async\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.arts.ucf.edu%2F&amp;h=ATOHcEO-0PEX4hRq3oEkwQD9ztDnFzNO4bT5MnEdlimmgrl77jvz_9JIDbGsvHFiyrF24rKSD6hRXNKjBNk_RYi-lOuE_rKG_Ah9XeTaY7vUKyVLisrDwCPX1VebUAcILYxONB-ftHt6VWl0G5aA\" href=\"http://www.arts.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.arts.ucf.edu.</a></span></p>\n<p><span>Follow along for event updates, behind-the-scenes with students, live streaming and more! - #artsatUCF <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ArtsAtUCF\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">@artsatUCF</a></span></p>','2018-03-01','2018-03-09','http://arts.ucf.edu/','UCF School of Performing Arts - Box Office','(407) 823-1500','boxoffice@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',10),(2549,'ID&T Job Fair & Program Open House','idt-job-fair-program-open-house-1-2-3','<p><span>J</span><span>oin the Instructional Design &amp; Technology (ID&amp;T) faculty and representatives from business and industry, K12 and higher education to learn more about the field of Instructional Design and Technology and our various programs of study, potential internships,  and career opportunities on March 20, 2018 at the 2018 ID&amp;T Job Fair and Program Open House at UCF.</span><span></span></p>\n<p><span>Instructional Design and Technology considers the science and art of designing innovative, effective, and engaging training and educational programs in business and industry, K-12, and Higher Education. Major Corporations like JetBlue, Nemours, Hilton Grand Vacations, Disney University, Embry-Riddle, Carley Corp, UCF Center for Distance Learning, Florida Virtual School, 21st Century Learning Solutions, Volusia County Schools and many more will be present! </span><span></span></p>\n<p><span>ALL majors are welcome to attend! There will be food and refreshment for all.   <strong>GRADUATE APPLICATION fee WAIVERS will be awarded to the first 25 who apply for admission into the IDT program </strong>at the event.<strong> </strong>Drop by on March 20, 2018 between 5-8 pm at the Morgridge International Reading Center on campus to meet employers, internship coordinators, and program faculty!  A few minutes may change your life... </span></p>','2018-03-01','2018-03-20','','Dr. Laurie O. Campbell','(407) 823-3382','locampbell@ucf.edu','Dr. Laurie O. Campbell','Publish',59),(2550,'College of Education & Human Performance Graduate School Open House','college-of-education-human-performance-graduate-school-open-house','<p>Explore how our graduate programs will enable you to advance your career at our <strong>Graduate School Open House</strong>.  UCF\'s College of Education and Human Performance (CEDHP) offers a variety of <a href=\"https://edcollege.ucf.edu/academic-programs/graduate/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">graduate programs</a> that align with your professional interests and educational goals.  Join us to learn about your options and get an inside look into the graduate experience.</p>\n<p>The open house will include opportunities to speak with program representatives, learn about grants and scholarships, hear from faculty and current students, and receive advice and resources for your application.</p>\n<p>Please <a href=\"http://bit.ly/UCFopenhouse18\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP</a> for this event for a chance to have your graduate application fee waived.</p>\n<p>Drop by the Morgridge International Reading Center between 3:00 PM to 6:00 PM.</p>','2018-02-27','2018-03-08','http://events.ucf.edu/event/573310/graduate-school-open-house/','Jordan Grushka','(407) 823-2136','jordan.grushka@ucf.edu','Jordan Grushka','Publish',61),(2551,'USPS Employee of the Month February 2018 -- Aracelis Nieves','usps-employee-of-the-month-february-2018-aracelis-nieves','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for February 2018 – Aracelis Nieves.</p>\n<p>Aracelis is the Administrative Assistant in First Year Advising and Exploration (FYAE) in the Office of Student Development and Enrollment Services. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>                <em>“Aracelis strives for perfection and does not allow obstacles to stand in her way to make sure tasks are completed with the highest of standards. She is a reflection of her work, and always puts others before herself when undertaking and completing obligations for our office.  We could not ask for a more confident and professional individual.  </em></p>\n<p><em>                Beyond consistently exceling in the work that she does, Aracelis truly embodies the core values of a genuine individual.  She approaches everyday with the same positive attitude and desire to build successful relationships.  She is an employee who puts the mission of the university first, and does so with sincerity.” </em></p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. Ms. Nieves receives a certificate, one-time $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag. She will also receive a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize her nominators, Mr. Stephen O’Connell and Traci Milbuta who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Ms. Nieves is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program. </p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Aracelis.</p>','2018-03-01','2018-03-08','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2553,'4EVER KNIGHTS Ambassador Applications Due March 20, 2018','4ever-knights-ambassador-applications-due-march-20-2018-1','<p>4EVER KNIGHTS Ambassador applications are open! 4EVER KNIGHTS Ambassadors support the efforts of the UCF Advancement office and aid in the advancement of the institution through fostering relationships between students, alumni and donors. Ambassadors spearhead the coordination of events and initiatives including the Class Gift Campaign, Welcome Week Photo, Knights of Legend, Movie Knight Out and much more. All applications are accepted online. The deadline to apply is <strong>March 20, 2018</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><strong>Minimum Qualifications:</strong></strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Have a GPA of 3.00 or higher</li>\n<li>Have completed a minimum of 30 credit hours by the end of the Spring 2018 semester</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Desired Qualifications:\n<ul>\n<li>Be energetic, cordial, and an effective communicator</li>\n<li>Maintain professional office-appropriate etiquette at all times</li>\n<li>Demonstrate strong organizational skills and attention to detail</li>\n<li>Take initiative while highlighting problem solving and decision making skills</li>\n<li>Ability to make 4EVER KNIGHTS a top priority</li>\n<li>Passionate about UCF</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Ambassador Requirements:\n<ul>\n<li>Maintain a 3.00 GPA</li>\n<li>Participate in mandatory events and initiatives in the Fall &amp; Spring</li>\n<li>Adhere to the 4EK Ambassador hours requirement</li>\n<li>Attend bi-weekly meetings on Thursdays 5-6 p.m. at the UCF FAIRWINDS Alumni Center</li>\n<li>Attend Fall and Spring semester retreats</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Students can review qualifications and apply online at: <a href=\"https://ucfalumni.com/4ekambassadors\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucfalumni.com/4ekambassadors</a>. Questions? Email <a href=\"mailto:4EVERKNIGHTS@ucfalumni.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">4EVERKNIGHTS@ucfalumni.com</a>   </p>\n<p> </p>','2018-03-09','2018-03-19','https://ucfalumni.com/4ekambassadors','Latoya Jackson','(407) 882-0559','latoya.jackson@ucf.edu','Submitted By: Liz Irizarry on behalf of Michael Morsberger, Vice President Advancement and CEO, UCF Foundation, Inc.','Publish',44),(2554,'UCF Alumni Scholarships Now Available!','ucf-alumni-scholarships-now-available','<p>Alumni Engagement and Annual Giving Scholarship applications are now open.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>THE DEADLINE TO APPLY IS MIDNIGHT March 31, 2018!</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Each year UCF Alumni Engagement and Annual Giving awards more than $50,000 in scholarships to UCF students demonstrating strong academic ability and significant extracurricular and community involvement. UCF Alumni Engagement and Annual Giving are pleased to again offer more than a dozen scholarship opportunities for the 2018-2019 academic year.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Applications are now available on A2O: Access to Opportunities (<a href=\"https://ucf.academicworks.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.academicworks.com/</a>). You are encouraged to apply for as many scholarships for which you are eligible.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>How to apply through A2O: </strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Read all scholarship criteria online at <a href=\"http://ucfalumni.com/students/scholarships\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucfalumni.com/students/scholarships</a> and complete ALL required supporting documents.</li>\n<li>Log in to A2O: Access to Opportunities (<a href=\"https://ucf.academicworks.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.academicworks.com/</a>).</li>\n<li>Complete the general application if this is your first time logging in.</li>\n<li>Browse available scholarships &gt; click “Opportunities” and select “Ours” then search for the specific scholarship you are looking for.</li>\n<li>Complete and submit application(s).</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>*No paper applications will be accepted. Scholarship applications are only available online through the A2O portal. You will only see scholarships for which you meet the basic eligibility requirements. IMPORTANT! Please read each scholarship application carefully to make sure you meet ALL of the specific criteria required for each scholarship before applying. Criteria used to determine eligibility includes, but is not limited to: GPA, class standing, academic program and campus involvement. If you do not see a particular scholarship, you do not meet one or more of the basic eligibility requirements (refer to our FAQs at <a href=\"https://ucfalumni.com/students/scholarshipfaq\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucfalumni.com/students/scholarshipfaq</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Scholarships Available:</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>-<strong>Amy G. Buchman, \'95, Memorial Endowed Scholarship</strong> – any class standing, permanent resident of Pinellas/Hillsborough counties in Florida</p>\n<p>-<strong>Charles N. &amp; Frances Millican Scholarship</strong> – senior serving in a leadership role</p>\n<p>-<strong>College of Business Administration Alumni Chapter Scholarship</strong> – junior, senior or graduate student class standing enrolled in the College of Business Administration</p>\n<p> -<strong>Debbie K. Phillis Space Coast UCF Alumni Chapter Endowed Scholarship</strong> – any class standing, permanent resident of Brevard County in Florida</p>\n<p> -<strong>Dr. William K. Grasty Memorial Scholarship</strong> – undergrad, junior or senior in the Nicholson School of Communication</p>\n<p> -<strong>Jack &amp; Monica Thorsen Veteran Scholarship</strong> – any class standing, served in the U.S. Military</p>\n<p> -<strong>Lee A. Dumas Memorial Endowed Scholarship</strong> – any class standing, permanent resident of Volusia/Flagler counties in Florida</p>\n<p> -<strong>Phoenix Scholarship</strong> – non-traditional student, junior class standing</p>\n<p> -<strong>St. Onge Family Leadership Endowed Scholarship</strong> – undergrad, sophomore or junior class standing serving in a leadership role</p>\n<p> -<strong>UCF Alumni Fellows Leadership Scholarship</strong> – any class standing</p>\n<p> -<strong>UCF Alumni Legacy Scholarship</strong> – undergrad, any class standing, parent/grandparent are UCF graduates</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>-<strong>UCF Regional Alumni Chapter/Club Scholarships:</strong></p>\n<p>+ <u>Chicago UCF Alumni Chapter Scholarship</u> – any class standing, permanent resident of the state of Illinois</p>\n<p>+ <u>Jacksonville UCF Alumni Club Scholarship</u> – any class standing, permanent resident of Duval, Clay, St. Johns or Nassau counties in Florida</p>\n<p>+ <u>Ocala UCF Alumni Club Scholarship</u> – any class standing, permanent resident of Marion County in Florida</p>\n<p>+ <u>Tampa Bay Knights Legacy Scholarship</u> – any class standing from Tampa Bay Area, parent/grandparent are UCF graduates</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>The deadline to apply is midnight on Saturday, March 31, 2018. Late, incomplete or paper applications will not be considered.</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Questions? Call 407.UCF.ALUM (823.2586) or email <a href=\"mailto:scholarships@ucfalumni.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">scholarships@ucfalumni.com</a>.</p>','2018-03-09','2018-03-31','http://ucfalumni.com/students/scholarships','Carla Cordoba','(407) 823-2586','scholarships@ucfalumni.com','Submitted By: Liz Irizarry on behalf of Michael Morsberger, Vice President Advancement and CEO, UCF Foundation, Inc.','Publish',44),(2555,'Sick Leave Pool Open Enrollment','sick-leave-pool-open-enrollment','<p>The UCF Sick Leave Pool open enrollment is March 1 - March 30.  To be eligible for membership, applicants must be employed with UCF continuously for at least one year, and have accrued 64 hours of sick leave as of March 2018.  New members are required to donate 16 hours of their sick leave (part-time employees will donate an amount proportionate to their FTE).  Membership reply letters will be sent to new applicants by early April 2018.</p>\n<p>Please note that if you are already a current member of one of the Sick Leave Pools, you do not need to rejoin during Open Enrollment.  The link listed below includes details on how to verify your current membership status.</p>\n<p>Interested faculty and staff should send <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/SLPApplication.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"SLP application\">applications</a> to the Human Resources Leave Administration section at <a href=\"mailto:loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2018-03-12','2018-03-30','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/leave-and-general-attendance-information/sick-leave-pools','Todd Coon','(407) 823-2599','loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources-Leave Administration','Publish',62),(2556,'2018 UCF Financial Wellness Series','2018-ucf-financial-wellness-series','<p>The annual <strong>UCF Financial Wellness Series</strong> will be held from April 2 through April 30, 2018.</p>\n<p>Schedules and descriptions of workshops and other series details: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series</a><span>.</span></p>\n<p>For questions please contact <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">benefits@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2018-03-15','2018-04-30','https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/financial-wellness-series/','Keven Ayala','(407) 823-1937','keven@ucf.edu','UCF HR Benefits','Publish',65);
INSERT INTO `announcements_announcement` VALUES (2564,'Applied Project Management Certificate Program - Project Management Professional (PMP) - Class starts in May!','applied-project-management-certificate-program-project-management-professional-pmp-class-starts-in-may','<p>UCF Continuing Education\'s <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/954/Pmp-Project-Management-Professional---A-Premier-Classroom-Face-to-face-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Applied Project Management\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Applied Project Management Certificate Program</span></a> teaches practical approaches on project management principles and methods working in a project management capacity and prepares participants for the <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">PMP</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">®</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> exam</span>. Our program meets PMI\'s eligibility requirement of 35 contact hours of formal project management education in order to sit for the PMP® exam.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Program Benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>In-Person interactive 12 session program format to keep you on track </li>\n<li>Learn and enhance fundamental management principles, theories, and practices described in the most current version of the PMI\'s <span>PMBOK® Guide</span></li>\n<li>Learn and use project management tools and techniques that are effective in initiating, planning, executing, monitoring &amp; controlling, and closing a project.</li>\n<li>Skilled project managers are in high demand around the world. A globally recognized project management certification will show employers that you have the knowledge, experience, and education to be a valuable asset to their organization</li>\n<li>Assess your ability to successfully pass the PMP® or CAPM® Exam</li>\n<li>Meet PMI\'s project management education requirement to become eligible to sit for the PMP® or CAPM®</li>\n<li>A great start to a career track in Project Management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Summer 2018: </span><br>         Tuesday evenings <br>         5:30pm - 9:30pm <br>         <strong>May 22, 2018 - August 7, 2018</strong> <br> <br>         UCF East Orlando location: Innovative Center <br>         3280 Progress Drive, Suite 700<br>         Orlando, FL 32826</p>\n<p><strong>Fee:</strong><br>Course fee is <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">$2,495</span> which includes course instruction, textbooks, materials and Continuing Education Units (CEUs). Discounted registration fee available for UCF Alumni, Staff, Faculty and Students of <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">$2,395!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/954/Pmp-Project-Management-Professional---A-Premier-Classroom-Face-to-face-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Register Today\">Register Today!</a></span></p>','2018-03-20','2018-05-20','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/954/Pmp-Project-Management-Professional---A-Premier-Classroom-Face-to-face-Program/','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2565,'Relay for Life of UCF','relay-for-life-of-ucf-1','<p>Come out this weekend to help us raise money for the American Cancer Society. The event begins at 4 pm on Saturday, March 24 and ends at 6 am Sunday, March 25 and is hosted on Memory Mall. We will have games, music, live entertainment, food, and so much more! Help us celebrate life while fighting for a great cause! </p>','2018-03-19','2018-03-25','http://www.relayforlife.org/ucffl','HALEY HARDIN','(904) 891-7353','ucfrelaymarketing@gmail.com','HALEY HARDIN','Publish',67),(2569,'Funny Money: The Encore- A Night of Financial Comedy','funny-money-the-encore-a-night-of-financial-comedy-1-2-3','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Centsible Knights- You are invited to a night of comedy and pop culture. As a part of Financial Literacy Awareness Month, Colin Ryan, a nationally renowned financial comedian will provide students with a night of laughs and sound financial advice.  </p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">To RSVP please visit <a href=\"http://finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy/</a>. </p>','2018-03-19','2018-04-04','http://finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy/','Karemah Manselle','(407) 823-5393','karemah.manselle@ucf.edu','Karemah Manselle','Publish',68),(2571,'Just Be Day on Memory Mall','just-be-day-on-memory-mall','<p>Join us for<span> </span><strong>Just Be Day</strong> at Memory Mall and learn to be mindful with creative activities enhancing the present moment. Check in to receive a punch card to have signed at each activity to be entered for a giveaway! Activities include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mindful Cooking Demos</li>\n<li>Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS) Drumming Circle</li>\n<li>Mini Yoga Sessions</li>\n<li>Coloring Tent</li>\n<li>Sync your breathing lying under a parachute</li>\n<li>Practice mindful walking in a labyrinth meditation</li>\n<li>Start a conversation in the chat bubble ball pit</li>\n<li>Make your own scented lotion</li>\n<li>Write a letter for another Knight</li>\n<li>Enjoy a Relaxation Station Tent</li>\n<li>Relax with a cup of tea</li>\n</ul>','2018-03-21','2018-04-01','http://events.ucf.edu/event/730196/just-be-day/','Scott Mauro','(407) 826-2048','scott.mauro@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(2583,'4EVER KNIGHTS Ambassador Applications Deadline EXTENDED - Due March 31, 2018','4ever-knights-ambassador-applications-deadline-extended-due-march-31-2018','<p>4EVER KNIGHTS Ambassador applications are open! 4EVER KNIGHTS Ambassadors support the efforts of the UCF Advancement office and aid in the advancement of the institution through fostering relationships between students, alumni, and donors. Ambassadors spearhead the coordination of events and initiatives including the Class Gift Campaign, Welcome Week Photo, Knights of Legend, Movie Knight Out and much more. All applications are accepted online. The deadline to apply is <strong>March 31, 2018</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Minimum Qualifications:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Have a GPA of 3.00 or higher</li>\n<li>Have completed a minimum of 30 credit hours by the end of the Spring 2018 semester</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Desired Qualifications:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Be energetic, cordial, and an effective communicator</li>\n<li>Maintain professional office-appropriate etiquette at all times</li>\n<li>Demonstrate strong organizational skills and attention to detail</li>\n<li>Take initiative while highlighting problem-solving and decision-making skills</li>\n<li>Ability to make 4EVER KNIGHTS a top priority</li>\n<li>Passionate about UCF</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Ambassador Requirements:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Maintain a 3.00 GPA</li>\n<li>Participate in mandatory events and initiatives in the Fall &amp; Spring</li>\n<li>Adhere to the 4EK Ambassador hours requirement</li>\n<li>Attend bi-weekly meetings on Thursdays 5-6 p.m. at the UCF FAIRWINDS Alumni Center</li>\n<li>Attend Fall and Spring semester retreats</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Students can review qualifications and apply online at: <a href=\"https://ucfalumni.com/4ekambassadors\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucfalumni.com/4ekambassadors</a>. Questions? Email <a href=\"mailto:4EVERKNIGHTS@ucfalumni.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">4EVERKNIGHTS@ucfalumni.com</a>   </p>','2018-03-23','2018-03-31','http://ucfalumni.com/4ekambassadors','Latoya Jackson','(407) 882-0559','4EVERKNIGHTS@ucfalumni.com','Liz Irizarry on behalf of Michael Morsberger, Vice President for Advancement and CEO, UCF Foundation, Inc.','Publish',44),(2588,'UCF Cares Student Ambassador Recruitment','ucf-cares-student-ambassador-recruitment-1','<p>Are you looking for an opportunity to practice your leadership skills, give back to the UCF community, and continue your education?</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Student Care Services is offering a 1 credit Lead Scholars course (LDR 2262) for students interested in being a UCF Cares Ambassador. UCF Cares Ambassador’s educate students on issues of mental health, safety and wellbeing, respect, and diversity and inclusion through interactive campus programing and outreach. After participating in the course, students are fully trained to continue as a UCF Cares Ambassador for the duration of their academic career.</p>\n<p>Please click the link below to review the application requirements and expectations to become a UCF Cares Ambassador.</p>\n<p>The application process closes on March 30, 2018 at midnight. Students who apply and meet all requirements will be contacted by Student Care Services for group interviews. To learn more about UCF Cares visit <a href=\"http://ucfcares.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">ucfcares.ucf.edu</a>. </p>\n<p>Application: <a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6yrGGD1MqFAOjSR\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6yrGGD1MqFAOjSR</a></p>','2018-03-23','2018-03-30','http://ucfcares.ucf.edu','Ann Marie Palmer','(407) 823-5607','annmarie.palmer@ucf.edu','Ann Marie Palmer','Publish',73),(2589,'UCF Cares Student Ambassador Recruitment','ucf-cares-student-ambassador-recruitment-1-2','<p>Are you looking for an opportunity to practice your leadership skills, give back to the UCF community, and continue your education?</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Student Care Services is offering a 1 credit Lead Scholars course (LDR 2262) for students interested in being a UCF Cares Ambassador. UCF Cares Ambassadors educate students on issues of mental health, safety and well-being, respect, and diversity and inclusion through interactive campus programming and outreach. After participating in the course, students are fully trained to continue as a UCF Cares Ambassador for the duration of their academic career.</p>\n<p>Please click the link below to review the application requirements and expectations to become a UCF Cares Ambassador.</p>\n<p>The application process closes on March 30, 2018 at midnight. Students who apply and meet all requirements will be contacted by Student Care Services for group interviews. To learn more about UCF Cares visit <a href=\"http://ucfcares.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">ucfcares.ucf.edu</a>. </p>\n<p>Application:<span> </span><a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6yrGGD1MqFAOjSR\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6yrGGD1MqFAOjSR</a></p>','2018-03-24','2018-03-30','http://ucfcares.ucf.edu.','Ann Marie Palmer','(407) 823-5607','annmarie.palmer@ucf.edu','Ann Marie Palmer','Publish',73),(2590,'Navigating Through a Life of Poverty Event','navigating-through-a-life-of-poverty-event','<p>Please feel free to attend and share with students!</p>\n<p>Navigating Through a Life of Poverty: An Interactive Simulation April 5th, 2018 6:45pm-9:00pm Global UCF 101</p>\n<p>Can you endure a month living in poverty? Find out by joining us for our event Navigating Through a Life of Poverty: An Interactive Simulation presented by Student Care Services and Northland Church. The event features an hour-long interactive activity simulating a month living in poverty. Attendees will play the role of a low income family and throughout the course of the simulation will have to navigate the available community resources to attempt to provide for their basic needs. Following the activity we will reflect on our experience and share some UCF and community resources that can assist individuals in need.</p>\n<p>RSVP required!  <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">RSVPs will close on Sunday, March 30th, 2018 at 5:00pm. Event check-in will begin at 6:45pm and last until 7pm please arrive during that time frame.</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>This is a great way to provide students a different perspective. Link Loot, LEAD Impact Event, and DEU credit will be provided for those attending this event. Extra credit can also be signed off on at this event. Volunteer opportunities are available.</p>\n<p>This event is open to the public!</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>','2018-03-26','2018-04-02','https://www.facebook.com/events/2085865501697337/','Angela Newland','(407) 823-5607','angela.newland@ucf.edu','Angela Newland, LCSW, Student Care Services Care Manager + Lead Scholars Academy Adjunct Faculty','Publish',74),(2591,'UCF Marching Band Dance, Drumline, Colorguard and Majorette Auditions','ucf-marching-band-dance-drumline-colorguard-and-majorette-auditions','<p>The UCF Marching Knights are having auditions for those who have experience performing on a drumline, colorguard, dance, or with baton twirling. We seek highly motivated students who have a passion for school spirit and would love to join the other 330 musicians in the Marching Knights. Auditions are on <strong>Saturday, May 5, 2018 and Saturday, June 23, 2018</strong>. For more information and to register, visit <a href=\"https://ucfbands.com/marching-knights/join/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucfbands.com/marching-knights/join/</a>. You may also email Dr. Tremon Kizer, Director of Athletic Bands at tkizer@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p>Go Knights and Charge On!</p>','2018-03-29','2018-05-05','https://ucfbands.com/marching-knights/join/','Tremon Kizer','(407) 823-2212','tkizer@ucf.edu','UCF Marching Knights','Publish',75),(2592,'The 3rd Annual Central Florida Quality Conference','the-3rd-annual-central-florida-quality-conference','<p><span>The 3rd Annual Central Florida Quality Conference (CFQC) is the first known student-organized quality conference in the nation. In its third year, it is a unique opportunity tailored to provide extraordinary networking experience to quality professionals, students at University of Central Florida (UCF) and Central Florida as a whole. This conference is being held at UCF, a leading organization in promoting quality and innovation. It aims to equip next generation Quality leaders with substantial skills to lead and succeed. Current quality leaders from Walt Disney Parks and Resorts, NASA, Siemens, Park National Bank, UCF Industrial Engineering &amp; Management Systems department and other organizations are among the presenters, inspiring tomorrow\'s leaders with their vast experience in quality and leadership. </span></p>\n<p><span>As an addition to this conference, we will be hosting a Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification workshop.</span></p>\n<p>Please secure your seat as soon as possible as seating is limited.</p>\n<p>Ticket sales end April 12th or upon sale of last available ticket.</p>\n<p>Free parking at Garage F located north east of the arena.</p>\n<p><strong>Cost for Attending:</strong><br>Student: $10<br>Non-Student: $20<br>Breakfast, coffee breaks and<br>lunch Included</p>','2018-03-27','2018-04-12','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/3rd-central-florida-quality-conference-tickets-43862623287?aff=es2','ASQ@UCF','','asq.ucf@gmail.com','Mahjabeen Rahman','Publish',76),(2593,'The Improv Academy Show!','the-improv-academy-show','<p>Finals got you down? Then take a load off and come to The Improv Academy\'s final show of the semester! Watch the members of The Improv Academy show you what they\'ve learned this semester with some crazy performances, wacky characters, and off the wall comedy! And the best part? It\'s totally free!</p>\n<p>The Improv Academy is a Registered Student Organization at UCF that teaches students the fundamentals of improv comedy! Its members have been spending all semester learning how to spontaneously create characters and stories right before your eyes!</p>\n<p>The show takes place Thursday, April 19th at 7:30 PM in The College of Sciences Building (CSB) 101, on the UCF main campus! Come on out and share some laughs!</p>','2018-04-19','2018-04-19','https://www.facebook.com/events/1591559494296758/','The Improv Academy','(321) 271-9228','theimprovacademyucf@gmail.com','Jeffrey Narciso','Publish',77),(2594,'USPS Employee of the Month March 2018 -- Elizabeth Nemec','usps-employee-of-the-month-march-2018-elizabeth-nemec','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for March 2018 – Elizabeth Nemec.</p>\n<p>Elizabeth is the Office Manager in Student Accessibility Services in the Office of Student Development and Enrollment Services. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>           “Here are a few of the reasons I am nominating Elizabeth. She is the most dependable employee I have ever worked with; unbelievably organized; learns what she does not know; able to take on additional tasks; gets the work done and fantastic insight about our office operations and processes.               </em></p>\n<p><em>           She is dedicated beyond measure cares very deeply for a job well done and sets a great example for us all. She greets each day with a smile and never says no to any task or challenge, no matter how busy she truly is.  It is without hesitation that we recommend Elizabeth for this award and thank her for a job very well done.” </em></p>\n<p>We would like to thank this outstanding employee for her dedication and hard work. Ms. Nemec receives a certificate, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag.  Ms. Nemec will also receive a one-time $200 cash award, a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d like to recognize her nominators, Mr. Adam Meyer, Kim Foy and Missy Lesnewski who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Ms. Nemec is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>Congratulations again to Elizabeth.</p>','2018-04-01','2018-04-10','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2595,'Now Hiring - UNITE Ambassadors (Transfer Student Mentors)!','now-hiring-unite-ambassadors-transfer-student-mentors','<p>Transfer and Transition Services is currently seeking 2nd-semester transfer students to serve on the 18-19 UNITE Ambassadors team. UNITE ambassadors duties include: Transfer Orientations (morning show hosts, interactive lunch engagement), Facilitating goal-setting consultations, and participating in student leadership initiatives through TTS.</p>\n<p>Position Overview: <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=1Un_GrQv28oEj-dlvwGW1Kt87pgrkqiA5\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"UNITE\">UNITE Ambassador Job Description</a></p>\n<p><strong>Application Deadline: April 13th</strong></p>\n<p>Application Link: <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_dd3RHUvN9gNUHAN\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_dd3RHUvN9gNUHAN</a></p>\n<p>Anticipated Start Date: April 30th</p>\n<p><strong><em>*Applicants must identify at least one (1) UCF staff reference on their application in order to be considered.</em></strong></p>','2018-03-30','2018-04-14','http://transfer.sdes.ucf.edu/current','Bernard Huggins','(407) 823-3721','bernard.huggins@ucf.edu','Transfer and Transition Services','Publish',78),(2600,'Rally Social Enterprise Accelerator Summer Cohort Deadline is April 15','rally-social-enterprise-accelerator-summer-cohort-deadline-is-april-15','<p>The application deadline to apply for the <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fcflsea.com%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CLaura.Cole%40ucf.edu%7C1f3b7cdca61d4ac10fd908d59ae615df%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636585235371903002&amp;sdata=k1lYRqgZN3v9zP681JQjBjqi%2FUowDw9ZMdjnaPZ53Q4%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Rally Social Enterprise Accelerator</a> based here in Central Florida is April 15. The next cohort program which will launch May 1. </p>\n<p><span>Here\'s the link to apply: <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.f6s.com%2Frally-sea&amp;data=02%7C01%7CLaura.Cole%40ucf.edu%7C1f3b7cdca61d4ac10fd908d59ae615df%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636585235371903002&amp;sdata=TyA4TemE0jo4JXL10ETQOVhu%2BUvuZ7VKtMD1M%2BH3wF4%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.f6s.com/rally-sea</a>.</span></p>\n<p>Rally\'s mission is to create positive social change by propelling qualified social entrepreneurs to build their ideas into self-sustainable ventures within our community. They work with social entrepreneurs in the early stages of developing their product or business who are looking for help or guidance. The Rally program is made possible through a community partnership between Downtown CREDO, Entrepreneurs in Action, Central Florida Foundation, Rollins College and Clean the World.  </p>\n<p><br>Created by two UCF alumni, Omnimodal was a participant in the inaugural cohort that just concluded last month. The co-founders were awarded $25k in investment. The two cite working with their mentors as well as getting to know their peers in the cohort as an impactful experience.</p>\n<p>Below are some additional details on the program:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A 16-week immersive mentorship-based experience designed to help the most promising social enterprises and founders turn their vision into a sustainable venture</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A collaborative work environment located on the campus of Rollins College in Winter Park, Florida</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Access to Rollins College, nationally recognized for its focus on social entrepreneurship, faculty and student interns</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Access to a world-class network and team of mentors that are serial commercial and social entrepreneurs</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Access to legal, accounting and marketing service professionals</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Weekly peer gathers, expert panels and one-on-one mentoring sessions</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A guaranteed $25,000 minimum investment to the top venture in the cohort</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Additional funding opportunity from the Entrepreneurs in Action Social Enterprise Venture Fund or the Central Florida Foundation Social Enterprise Endowment Fund</li>\n</ul>','2018-04-05','2018-04-15','https://www.f6s.com/rally-sea','David Thomas Moran','','david@omnimodal.io','Laura Cole','Publish',35),(2601,'International Relations Forum - April 10th, 2018','international-relations-forum-april-10th-2018','<p>IRC’s International Relations Forum (IRForum) “Rogue States: Big Problems, Little Countries” will be hosted in our UCF Global Building (room 101) on April 10, 2018, starting at noon. “Rogue States”, as dubbed by Presidents George W Bush and Donald Trump, are lone anti-status quo nations with nuclear aspirations. Modern examples have included the governments of Iraq, Iran, Syria, Libya, Cuba, and North Korea. Our event seeks to educate students on these countries’ tools, effectiveness of American influence, and how to normalize these relations.<br>The IRForum will cover three panels: “Tools of Rogue States”, “Effectiveness of American Influence”, and “Transitioning from Rogue State”. It will feature nine guest speakers, including prominent academics and policy makers. </p>','2018-04-05','2018-04-10','https://www.facebook.com/events/128282844680594/?ti=icl','International Relations Club','(321) 890-3485','irclub.ucf@gmail.com','International Relations Club','Publish',81),(2603,'Student Loan Repayment Session','student-loan-repayment-session','<p><span>Student loan repayment is not one size fits all.  There is a variety of student loan repayment options available to borrowers. Come learn more about the options available to you. </span></p>\n<p><span>For more information and to RSVP, please visit:</span></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"http://finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy/financial-literacy-month/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy/financial-literacy-month/</a></span></p>','2018-04-13','2018-04-18','http://finaid.ucf.edu/financial-literacy/','Karemah Manselle','(407) 823-5393','karemah.manselle@ucf.edu','Centsible Knights','Publish',68),(2605,'State Conference of the ACE Women\'s Network of Florida','state-conference-of-the-ace-womens-network-of-florida','<p>Panels, tour and speakers, including keynote speakers Madlyn Hanes, vice president of Commonwealth Campuses and executive chancellor of Pennsylvania State University, and Dr. Deborah German, UCF vice president of medical affairs and dean of the College of Medicine. Conference will be 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. April 27 in the Cape Florida Ballroom of the UCF Student Union. Attendance is by invitation only, but seakers and panels will be live streamed 10 a.m. to 2:45 p.m. at <a href=\"http://oir.ucf.edu/webcast/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://oir.ucf.edu/webcast/.</a></p>\n<p>The schedule:</p>\n<p>Pre-conference networking <br>9:30 - 10 a.m.</p>\n<p><br>Opening Remarks<br>10 - 10:05 a.m.Dr. Lisa Jones<br>Associate Provost for Strategy and Special Assistant to the President<br>University of Central Florida<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Welcome<br>10:05 - 10:10 a.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. John C. Hitt<br>President<br>University of Central Florida<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Presentation to Dr. Hitt<br>10:10 - 10:15 a.m.Dr. Beth Barnes<br>Vice President Emerita<br>University of Central Florida<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Introduction of Opening Plenary Presenter<br>10:15 - 10:20 a.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. Genyne Boston<br>Associate Provost for Faculty Affairs and Faculty Development<br>Florida Agricultural and Mechanical University<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Advancing Women in Higher Education Leadership<br>10:20 - 11 a.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. Madlyn Hanes<br>Vice President for Commonwealth Campuses and Executive Chancellor<br>Pennsylvania State University<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Women in Leadership Panel<br>11 a.m. - 12 p.m.</p>\n<p>PANEL FACILITATOR:<br>Dr. Theresa Chisolm<br>Vice Provost for Strategic Planning, Performance &amp; Accountability<br>University of South Florida<br>PANELISTS:<br>Dr. Elizabeth Dooley<br>Interim Provost and Vice Provost for Teaching and Learning and Dean of the College of Undergraduate Studies<br>University of Central Florida<br>Dr. Maribeth Ehasz<br>Vice President of Student Development and Enrollment Services<br>University of Central Florida<br><br><br>Break and Transition to Lunch<br>12 - 12:10 p.m.</p>\n<p><br>Luncheon Remarks<br>12:10 - 12:20 p.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. Dale Whittaker<br>President-elect and Executive Vice President<br>University of Central Florida<br>Dr. Michael Preston<br>Executive Director<br>Florida Consortium of Metropolitan Research Universities<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Women in Leadership Panel cont.<br>11 a.m. - 12 p.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. Marie Gnage<br>Vice President for Institutional Effectiveness and Advancement<br>Florida State College at Jacksonville<br>Dr. Lua Hancock<br>Vice President for Campus Life and Student Success<br>Stetson University<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Building the Life You Want: Leadership Lessons from a Career in Academic Medicine<br>12:35 - 1 p.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. Deborah German<br>Vice President for Medical Affairs and Dean of the College of Medicine<br>University of Central Florida<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Introduction of Luncheon Keynote Speaker<br>12:30 - 12:35 p.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. Irma Becerra-Fernandez<br>Provost and Chief Academic Officer<br>St. Thomas University<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Transition to Campus Tour<br>1 - 1:10 p.m.</p>\n<p><br>Campus Tour<br>1:10 - 1:50 p.m.</p>\n<p>William Merck II<br>Vice President for Administration and Finance and Chief Financial Officer<br>University of Central Florida<br>Ms. Kaye-Alese Green<br>Project Manager for Administration and Finance<br>University of Central Florida<br><br><br>Concurrent Session:<br>2 - 2:45 p.m.</p>\n<p>Asset Mapping<br>(Cape Florida A/B)<br>In this interactive session, participants at all levels of career development will identify, map, and strategize to leverage assets for professional development ranging from their own internal characteristics and strengths to formal accomplishments, networks, and community resources.<br>Dr. Melody Bowdon<br>Associate Dean of the College<br>of Undergraduate Studies<br>and Executive Director of the Faculty Center for Teaching<br>and Learning<br>University of Central Florida<br>Dr. Amanda Wolcott<br>Instructional Specialist for the Faculty Center for Teaching<br>and Learning<br>University of Central Florida<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Break and Transition to Concurrent Sessions<br>1:50 - 2 p.m.</p>\n<p><br>Concurrent Session: Honing Your Negotiation Skills to Advance Your Career Goals<br>(Cape Florida D)<br>2 - 2:45 p.m.</p>\n<p>This interactive session will provide an introduction to value-creating negotiation skills. The session is designed to introduce negotiation strategies that can help effectively balance professional duties, protect time, secure needed resources, and advance career goals and plans.<br>Dr. Maureen L. Ambrose<br>Gordon J. Barnett Professor of Business Ethics<br>University of Central Florida<br><br></p>\n<p><br>IR Orientation and Strategic Visioning Session<br>2:50 - 3:50 p.m.</p>\n<p>Dr. Annie Becker<br>University Professor in Information Systems<br>Florida Institute of Technology<br>Dr. Anita Kaplan<br>Dean of Bachelor’s Degree Programs<br>Palm Beach State College<br>Dr. M.C. Santana<br>Associate Professor and Director of Women’s and Gender Studies<br>University of Central Florida<br><br></p>\n<p><br>Closing<br>Dr. Lisa Jones<br>3:50 - 4 p.m.</p>','2018-04-17','2018-04-27','http://www.acenet.edu/news-room/Pages/ACE-Womens-Network.aspx','Dr. Lisa Guion Jones','(407) 823-1466','Lisa.Jones@ucf.edu','Dr. Lisa Guion Jones','Publish',39),(2606,'Having difficulty passing the FTCE Professional Review Test? Review class starts May 24th!','having-difficulty-passing-the-ftce-professional-review-test-review-class-starts-may-24th','<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>FTCE Professional Review Program</strong></p>\n<p><em>Curriculum provided by Master Mind Educational Consulting<span> </span></em></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UCF Test Prep has developed a comprehensive<span> <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1099/Ftce---Professional-Review-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"FTCE Professional Review Program\">FTCE Professional Review Program</a></span><span> </span>to empower teaching professionals and prospective students with the knowledge to receive high scores on the FTCE Professional exam\'s sections.<span> </span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our FTCE Professional Review Program is taught by professional educators who are able to connect with the class to convey important test information and explain test-taking strategies that are easy to remember and apply.<span> </span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong></strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>FTCE PROFESSIONAL EXAM REVIEW<br></strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Offered as both an<span> </span>IN-PERSON<span> </span>and<span> </span>ONLINE<span> </span>option.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Those who choose to attend<span> </span><strong>IN-PERSON</strong><span> </span>will meet at our UCF Continuing Education building in Orlando, FL. </p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Those that choose to attend<span> </span></span>ONLINE<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span> </span>must login to view the live online sessions streamed during Eastern Standard Time. You will be able to hear the instructor lead the course discussions, view the course handouts, and engage in an online chat discussion with students and your instructor.</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>FTCE PROFESSIONAL REVIEW COURSE</strong><span> </span>- 12 hrs - 4 sessions<span> </span></li>\n<li>This course will focus on the 8 key domains for the FTCE Professional Exam. </li>\n<li>Registration Fee (In Person or Online):<span> </span><strong>$279</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong></strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Our review course will focus on understanding and mastering the 8 key domains for the FTCE Professional exam:<span> </span></strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Knowledge of instructional design and planning</li>\n<li>Knowledge of appropriate student-centered learning environments</li>\n<li>Knowledge of instructional delivery and facilitation through a comprehensive understanding of subject matter</li>\n<li>Knowledge of various types of assessment strategies for determining impact on student learning</li>\n<li>Knowledge of relevant continuous professional improvement </li>\n<li>Knowledge of the Code of Ethics and Principles of Professional Conduct of the Education Profession in Florida</li>\n<li>Knowledge of research-based practices appropriate for teaching English Language Learners (ELLs)</li>\n<li>Knowledge of effective literacy strategies that can be applied across the curriculum to impact student learning</li>\n</ol>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>REGISTER FOR THE FTCE EXAM<span> </span><br></strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UCF Test Prep only provides test preparation review courses and does not handle registration for the FTCE General Knowledge, FTCE Professional or FTCE Elementary Education exams. Please click the links below to get more information on how to register for the exam.<span> </span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://www.fl.nesinc.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.fl.nesinc.com</a></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The University Testing Center offers the FTCE exam onsite at UCF<span> </span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://www.utc.sdes.ucf.edu/tests\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.utc.sdes.ucf.edu/tests</a><span> </span></p>','2018-04-23','2018-05-24','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1099/Ftce---Professional-Review-Program/','Alexis Cason','(407) 882-0251','Alexis.Cason@ucf.edu','Alexis Cason','Publish',84),(2607,'Sign up for the United Way Campaign Team!','sign-up-for-the-united-way-campaign-team','<p>The 2018 UCF &amp; United Way Campaign is coming fast and we\'re looking for faculty and staff for the campaign team. The campaign is an annual pledge drive providing faculty and staff payroll deduction and other options for charitable giving. Opportunities for volunteers include joining marketing or event committees and serving as campaign ambassadors.</p>\n<p>Sign up to make a difference with us: <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_4ZsE9wFGfiOPjdH\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_4ZsE9wFGfiOPjdH</a></p>\n<p>For questions, contact liveunited@ucf.edu or 407-823-3094.</p>\n<p>Visit <a href=\"http://liveunited.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://liveunited.ucf.edu</a> for campaign information.</p>','2018-04-23','2018-05-11','http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_4ZsE9wFGfiOPjdH','Tee Rogers','(407) 823-3094','liveunited@ucf.edu','Tee Rogers','Publish',22),(2608,'The Florida Solar Energy Center presents EnergyWhiz','the-florida-solar-energy-center-presents-energywhiz','<p>What do a ping-pong ball, an umbrella and baby sea turtles have in common?  EnergyWhiz!</p>\n<p>This yearly event where young people from all over Florida participate in a variety of events and competitions will be held Saturday May 12, 2018 at the Florida Solar Energy Center (FSEC), 1679 Clearlake Road, Cocoa, FL 32922. The public is invited to attend the event starting at 9:15 am.</p>\n<p>FSEC, a research institute of UCF, created EnergyWhiz as a fun way for students to share what they have learned about renewable energy technologies. Events include a model solar car race and design competition called the Junior Solar Sprint; a solar cook-off, where young chefs use the solar ovens that they have designed and built to prepare an original dish;  and, Critter Comfort Cottage, where students design and build energy efficient habitats for their pet of choice. The Electrathon, an endurance race of electrified go-carts, will be running during the event. Solar energy systems and a variety of electric vehicles will be on display, and food trucks will be on-site with a variety of offerings.</p>\n<p>For more information, contact Susan Schleith, Energy Education Coordinator at <a href=\"mailto:susan@fsec.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">susan@fsec.ucf.edu</a></p>\n<p>Learn more about EnergyWhiz at <a href=\"http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/go/energywhiz\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.fsec.ucf.edu/go/energywhiz</a></p>','2018-04-27','2018-05-12','http://www.fsec.ucf.edu/go/energywhiz','Susan Schleith','(321) 638-1017','susan@fsec.ucf.edu','Colleen Kettles, Florida Solar Energy Center','Publish',86),(2609,'Destigmatizing Mental Illness','destigmatizing-mental-illness','<p>Hello UCF!</p>\n<p>I would like to announce that I have published a psychology-related blog<span> that discusses personal experiences and relevant research on mental disorders. I thought it would be a great way to share my stories as well as attempt to destigmatize mental illness while writing about something I love. I have resources on my blog for those struggling or simply wanting to learn more about psychology. I am also in need of some stories from students and the like, so if you\'d like to be featured (anonymously or not), I would love to have your <em>own</em> experiences on my blog (so it\'s not just about my perspective)! All you have to do is submit a request under my \"Contact Me\" content or email me, personally. Feel free to spread the word if you know anyone who would like to participate.</span></p>\n<p>Thank you,</p>\n<p><span>Laura Owen</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"mailto:owenl14@knights.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">owenl14@knights.ucf.edu</a></p>','2018-05-01','2018-06-30','https://www.theplatheffect.com','Laura Owen','(919) 698-8688','owenl14@knights.ucf.edu','Laura Owen','Publish',87),(2610,'SUS Florida Hazing Prevention Summit','sus-florida-hazing-prevention-summit','<p><strong>The Florida SUS Hazing Prevention Summit</strong> will be held at the University of Central Florida on May 18, 2018. We invite you to register to be a part of this important event. The target audience is staff, faculty, advisors, and graduate students. There will be a variety of sessions, case studies and discussions on hazing prevention strategies for clubs, organizations, fraternities, sororities, athletics, band, and ROTC.  You will also have the opportunity to learn from and network with representatives from other institutions in the state of Florida.</p>\n<p>Registration for the 2018 Hazing Prevention Summit: <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fau.edu%2Fstudent%2Fhazingpreventionsummit%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CGermayne.Graham%40ucf.edu%7Cef91f558e5f9405c658408d5a155a2c0%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636592312414313924&amp;sdata=%2Bf2Yf6BEu44H72hpcxInFoJ09whlsrssf5t2yLAwNyw%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.fau.edu/student/hazingpreventionsummit/</a></p>\n<p>For more information please contact Germayne Graham at  407-823-2223 or  <a href=\"mailto:germayne.graham@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">germayne.graham@ucf.edu</a></p>','2018-05-08','2018-05-17','http://www.fau.edu/student/hazingpreventionsummit/','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Germayne Graham','Publish',41),(2611,'DEADLINE EXTENDED! Call for 2017-2018 A&P Excellence Award Nominations','call-for-2017-2018-ap-excellence-award-nominations','<p>You are invited to submit nominations for UCF\'s annual Gabor Administrative and Professional (A&amp;P) Excellence Award. Sponsored by The Gabor Agency, the award was established to recognize, appreciate, and celebrate the outstanding job performance of a selected A&amp;P employee. The chosen candidate for the award will be announced at the Annual Employee Awards Program on October 19, 2018, and will receive a check for $2,500.</p>\n<p>All nominations must be received in Human Resources no later than <strong>5:00 p.m., August 3, 2018</strong>.</p>\n<p>Eligibility criteria and additional information about the award: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/gabor-ap-excellence-award/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/gabor-ap-excellence-award/</a></p>\n<p>Nomination form: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/2018-Gabor-Nomination-Form.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/2018-Gabor-Nomination-Form.pdf</a> (best viewed in Internet Explorer)</p>\n<p>If you have questions, or for more information, contact Learning &amp; Organizational Effectiveness at 407-823-0440 or <a href=\"mailto:HRLearning@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">HRLearning@ucf.edu</a>.</p>\n<p>Thank you for your active participation in recognizing UCF employees for their outstanding contributions!</p>','2018-05-09','2018-08-03','https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/employee-recognition/gabor-ap-excellence-award/','HR Learning & Organizational Effectiveness','(407) 823-0440','HRLearning@ucf.edu','Lee Williams','Publish',24),(2612,'USPS Employee of the Month for April 2018 - Dawn Tripp','usps-employee-of-the-month-for-april-2018-dawn-tripp','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for April 2018 – Dawn Tripp.</p>\n<p>Dawn has been the Senior Library Technical Assistant in the Research &amp; Information Services/Ask US at the John Hitt Library since July 2013. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>                <em>“<u>UCF Ask Us </u>is in partnership with <u>Florida Ask a Librarian </u>collaborative Chat. Dawn participates in collaborative chat by answering questions from students and faculty from over forty Florida colleges and universities. She has recently been selected to serve on a statewide steering committee to help determine the future direction of <u>Florida Ask a Librarian. </u></em></p>\n<p><em>                 Dawn provided over 1,000 hours of coverage for UCF Libraries’ <u>Ask a Librarian</u> virtual reference service by answering chat, telephone, and email inquiries. She models the exemplary customer service ethics every supervisor would envy. She is knowledgeable, professional, personable, kind, and patient with students and faculty.</em></p>\n<p><em>Each summer Dawn volunteers to assist with new student orientation sessions and welcomes new students at the Library Information Kiosk during the first week of fall classes. Dawn is truly an exemplary employee!” </em></p>\n<p>At this time, we would like to present Ms. Tripp with a certificate, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and this goody bag. Ms. Tripp will also receive a one-time $200 cash award, a marquee announcement, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>We\'d would like to recognize her nominators, Ms. Meredith Semones and Ms. Barbara Tierney who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and thank you for helping to identify and recognize exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p> Ms. Tripp is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p> Congratulations again to Dawn.</p>','2018-05-11','2018-05-18','https://hr.ucf.edu/employee-month-new/','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2613,'FREE summer theatre tickets for UCF faculty and staff!','free-summer-theatre-tickets-for-ucf-faculty-and-staff','<p>This summer UCF faculty and staff can use the code <strong><em>UCFstaff18 </em></strong>to reserve up to two complimentary tickets to one performance of Theatre UCF’s summer show dates of <strong><em>Human Error</em></strong>, running June 14-June 24 as part of Pegasus PlayLab. Tickets can be reserved online at <a href=\"https://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pr/988049/prm/UCFstaff18\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pr/988049/prm/UCFstaff18</a> or through the box office. Summer box office hours are Tuesday-Friday, 12pm-5pm, and we can be reached by phone at 407-823-1500.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>What is Pegasus PlayLab?</strong></p>\n<p>A new summer theatre festival dedicated to developing plays by emerging playwrights. Starting in 2018, Theatre UCF will offer three staged readings of new plays in the Black Box and one fully-mounted production on the Main Stage. The workshop process will span six weeks from mid-May through the end of June. This is your opportunity to be involved in a play development process with playwrights from across the country, and support emerging voices!<em> Subscriptions are available now—only $40!:</em> <a href=\"http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/tickets.php\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/tickets.php</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>About the New Plays</strong></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=4002\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Human Error</a></em> by Eric Pfeffinger, Directed by Be Boyd</p>\n<p>June 14-24; August 23-26; $20 standard tickets</p>\n<p>When a fertility clinic mistakenly implants Madelyn and Keenan’s embryo in someone else, an unlikely relationship is forged between couples with wildly different backgrounds.</p>\n<p><em><u>FREE tickets for UCF faculty and staff with code: <strong>UCFstaff18</strong></u></em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em><a href=\"http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=4004\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Intuitive Men</a> </em>by Sofya Levitsky-Weitz, Directed by Cynthia White</p>\n<p>June 2-3; $10 standard tickets</p>\n<p>Two men communicate through thoughts in an intuitive yoga class, questioning their shame, self-worth and pride.</p>\n<p><em>Meet the Playwright June 3!</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em><a href=\"http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=4005\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">He Did It</a></em> by Rachel Lynett, Directed by Michael Wainstein</p>\n<p>June 9-10; $10 standard tickets</p>\n<p>Ada and Lex know that Jefferson raped their friend, but they need him to advance their careers. Will they excuse a horrendous crime committed by an artistic genius?</p>\n<p><em>Meet the Playwright June 10!</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em><a href=\"http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/events.php?id=4006\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Bathsheba’s Psalms</a> </em>by April Ranger, Directed by Cynthia White</p>\n<p>June 16-17; $10 standard tickets</p>\n<p>A wild retelling of the biblical myth with Bathsheba’s voice front and center. Both hilarious and sensual, the play is an explosive journey through time immemorial, upending several genres and tropes on female beauty, power and desire.</p>\n<p><em>Meet the Playwright June 17!</em></p>','2018-05-18','2018-06-23','http://theatre.cah.ucf.edu/season.php','UCF School of Performing Arts Box Office','(407) 823-1500','boxoffice@ucf.edu','UCF School of Performing Arts','Publish',90),(2614,'Join the United Way Campaign Advocate Team','join-the-united-way-campaign-advocate-team','<p>Join the UCF &amp; United Way Advocates, a team dedicated to educating our Knight family about issues in our community while empowering them to make a difference. </p>\n<p>Register: <a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_4ZsE9wFGfiOPjdH\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_4ZsE9wFGfiOPjdH</a> </p>\n<p>Advocates serve as a point of contact in a department or college during the campaign in October and provide support &amp; information about the campaign.  There are also involvement and leadership opportunities such as campaign marketing and special events and eligibility for recognition and awards.</p>','2018-05-18','2018-06-08','http://LiveUnited.ucf.edu','Tee Rogers','(407) 823-3094','liveunited@ucf.edu','tee rogers, UCF & United Way Campaign','Publish',22),(2615,'Memorial Day','memorial-day','<p><span>UCF will be closed Monday, May 29, in observance of Memorial Day. </span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>','2018-05-23','2018-05-29','','Gene Kruckemyer','(407) 823-1637','gene.kruckemyer@ucf.edu','Gene Kruckemyer','Publish',39),(2618,'USPS Employee of the Month - May 2018: Sheryl Rowell','usps-employee-of-the-month-may-2018-sheryl-rowell','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for May 2018: Sheryl Rowell. Sheryl joined UCF in September 1991 and has been the Senior Training Specialist in SDES Health Center Operations since 2001. We would like to recognize her nominators, Ms. Joanne McCully and Dr. Tom Hall, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. They had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>            <em>“Sheryl has worked in UCF Health Services for 26 years and is a great example for our staff of young behavioral health professionals. Sheryl demonstrates loyalty to UCF and the department, professionalism, and a great attitude doing her job and being a team player.</em></p>\n<p><em>            Sheryl is responsible for helping students navigate AlcoholEdu, a required online alcohol prevention education to all first year and transfer students.  Her customer service exceeds our expectation as she responds to hundreds of calls and emails from students to be sure the program is completed by the deadline.  Her customer service with students is exceptional, and I am proud she is part of our team!”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Sheryl received a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2018-06-12','2018-06-19','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2619,'Applied Project Management Certificate Program - Project Management Professional (PMP) - Class starts in September!','applied-project-management-certificate-program-project-management-professional-pmp-class-starts-in-september','<p><strong>POSITION YOURSELF FOR A BIG CAREER MOVE</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"UCF Continuing Education\">UCF Continuing Education</a> brings you project management training that fits your career and education goals. Training includes courses for those new to project management, those with senior level experience, and PDU courses to help maintain PM credentials.</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong><br>• 12 week program offered in an interactive instructor-led classroom format to keep you on track.<br>• Our program exceeds PMI’s education requirement of 23 hours of CAPM® and 35 hours of PMP® education to become eligible to sit for the CAPM® or PMP® exam.<br>• Learn and apply project management techniques that are effective in initiating, planning, executing, monitoring, controlling and closing a project.<br>• Learn test taking strategies to successfully pass the CAPM® or PMP® exam.<br>• Qualifies for most tuition reimbursement and payment plans are available</p>\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong><br>Twelve weeks, instructor-led<br>Tuesday Evenings, 5:30pm – 9:30pm<br><em><strong>September 4 - November 20, 2018</strong></em><br><br>Tuition Includes instruction, textbooks, and additional supplemental study materials.<br>$2,495 Registration Fee<br>$2,395 UCF Alumni Registration Fee<br><br>East Orlando<br>Location<br>UCF Continuing Education<br>Innovative Center<br>3280 Progress Drive Suite 700<br>Orlando, FL 32826</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Applied Project Management Certificate Program\">Register today, classes fill up fast!</a></strong></p>','2018-06-12','2018-08-31','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/954/Pmp-Project-Management-Professional---A-Premier-Classroom-Face-to-face-Program/','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2620,'Human Resources: A Roadmap to Success in Your HR Career','human-resources-a-roadmap-to-success-in-your-hr-career','<p><strong>SHRM Essentials of HR Management</strong><br>Expose yourself to the HR field. The SHRM Essentials of Human Resource Management Certificate Program is an introductory course offering a comprehensive overview of the human resource function. The course covers today\'s most vital and timely topics, including employment law, selecting qualified employees, compensation, orientation and training, and the employee performance process. Move at your own pace in this online, three month course. <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/779/Hr-Shrm---Professional-Human-Resource-Essentials-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"HR Essentials\">Start at any time!</a></p>\n<p><strong>HR Generalist Certificate</strong><br>Succeed in an HR Generalist role. HR Generalists are responsible for a wide variety of HR functions in their roles. This online certificate program gives you the tools to enhance your knowledge and expand your understanding of the role\'s core competencies. Learn the SHRM HR Essentials curriculum and take three business electives in this online program. <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1868/Hr---Human-Resources-Generalist-Certificate/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"HR Generalist Certificate\">Start at any time!</a></p>\n<p><strong>SHRM-CP and SHRM-SCP Exam Certification Preparation</strong><br>Prepare for SHRM certification. Establish yourself as a globally-recognized human resource expert by earning the new standard in HR Certification: SHRM Certified Professional (SHRM-CP<span>®</span>) and SHRM Senior Certified Professional (SHRM-SCP<span>®</span>). Expand and test your knowledge and practical, real-life competencies in areas critical for HR career success. This program combines expert instruction with the SHRM Learning System® for SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP, so you will learn faster, retain more knowledge and stay on track for success on the exam. Join live-online or face-to-face courses for comprehensive and applicable exam review.<br><br><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>Fall SHRM Exam Course Schedule</em></span><br>September 5 - December 11     East Orlando     Wednesdays, 6-9pm<br>September 11 - December 11     Live Online     Tuesdays, 6-9pm<br><br>To register visit <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"PHRM\">www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM</a></p>','2018-06-12','2018-08-31','http://www.ucf.edu/PHRM','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2643,'Heart Notes - Wellness, Yoga & Music Concert','heart-notes-wellness-yoga-music-concert','<p>A unique enthralling Music concert by the<span> </span><strong>Grammy-nominated</strong>famous exponent of the Bamboo Flute, Shashank Subramanyam and<span> </span><strong>world-renowned</strong><span> </span>Indian classical Surbahar and Sitar player, Irshad Khan. Accompanied by multi-talented artist, singer, music producer &amp; composer Shankhachur Lahiri on Tabla. Vibrant and energetic Sriram Brahmanandam on Mridangam.</p>\n<p><strong>Leading-edge Health and Wellness</strong><span> </span>workshop + Yoga by Eminent Doctors and Yoga instructors. Learn practical techniques from renowned Heartfulness trainer Joshua Pollock, Co-author of the bestselling book \"The Heartfulness Way\"</p>\n<p><strong>A FESTIVAL OF INNER JOY</strong></p>\n<p><strong>JUNE 17th, 1-5 PM, PEGASUS BALLROOM, UCF, ORLANDO</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note: Admission is free for entire UCF community.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Register at: <a href=\"http://hfnorlando.eventbrite.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://hfnorlando.eventbrite.com</a></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/heartfulnessorl/videos/582481548790390/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Video Link</a></strong></p>\n<p></p>','2018-06-17','2018-06-17','http://hfnorlando.eventbrite.com','Tulsi Shukla','(443) 791-8952','tshukla1@knights.ucf.edu','A Heartfulness Meditation Experience - RSO','Publish',37),(2645,'UCF Coding Boot Camp Informational Webinar 20 Jun','ucf-coding-boot-camp-informational-webinar-20-jun','<p>UCF Coding Boot Camp: Program Overview Webinar on June 20th</p>\n<p>Join us for a <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2y6tKpe\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Coding Boot Camp Program Overview Webinar</a> on Wednesday, June 20 at 9 p.m. ET / 7 p.m. MT—Powered by Trilogy Education Services.<br><br>During this informative webinar, our Coding Boot Camp Director of Admissions will discuss our web development program and answer some frequently asked questions. The event will last approximately one hour.<br><br>Learn:<br>+ Why our student experience sets us apart<br>+ Our methodologies for teaching full-stack web development<br>+ How our career services team helps to prepare you for job hunt success<br><br>and MORE in this live program overview.<br><br>Through dynamic, in-person classes and a hands-on curriculum, we equip you with the fundamental skills for the booming field of technology. Built around the needs and schedules of busy students and full-time working professionals, we provide the flexibility you need to reprogram your career through convenient evening and weekend classes.<br><br>Over the course of 24 weeks, students are immersed into an intensive program that covers the most in-demand skills: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, jQuery, React.js, Node.js, MongoDB, MySQL, Git, and more.<br><br><a href=\"https://bit.ly/2y6tKpe\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP</a> now to save your spot!</p>','2018-06-15','2018-06-21','https://bit.ly/2y6tKpe','Todd Freece','(407) 882-0236','todd.freece@ucf.edu','Todd Freece','Publish',32),(2647,'USPS Employee of the Month Nominations','usps-employee-of-the-month-nominations','<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>All USPS Employee Of the Month recipients receive a $200 cash award, two $25 gift cards, and additional recognition.  The 12 USPS Employees Of the Month are also eligible for the prestigious USPS Employee of the Year award with an additional $2,500 award presented at the annual Employee Award\'s Program.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>If you have questions, please contact <a href=\"mailto:Deborah.Frankenbach@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Deborah.Frankenbach@ucf.edu</a> or 407-823-2777.</p>','2018-06-22','2018-06-30','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Debbie Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2648,'8 Month Dining Scholarship applications are now being accepted!','8-month-dining-scholarship-applications-are-now-being-accepted','<p>Business Services will award six (6) - All Access 7 Dining Membership scholarships for both the Fall 2018 and Spring 2019 semester, valued at $3,960 each.</p>\n<p>Due to the volume of applicants, only recipients will be notified if they are awarded the scholarship.</p>\n<p>Visit <a href=\"https://businessservices.ucf.edu/dining-scholarship/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://businessservices.ucf.edu/dining-scholarship/</a> to submit your application. Good luck!</p>','2018-06-20','2018-08-10','https://businessservices.ucf.edu/dining-scholarship/','Sue Gonzalez','(407) 823-3539','sue.gonzalez@ucf.edu','Sue Gonzalez','Publish',97),(2650,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining Session','afscme-collective-bargaining-session','<p><span>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the American Federation of State, County, and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will take place on Tuesday, July 3</span><span>, from 2:00 p.m. – 4:00 p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center, Suite 100.</span></p>','2018-07-03','2018-07-03','','Elizabeth Richner','(407) 823-2771','elizabeth.richner@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Publish',98),(2652,'Project Harmony- Workshops at NO COST!','project-harmony-workshops-at-no-cost-1','<p><span>Interested in learning how to </span><strong><em><span>communicate better</span></em></strong><span> </span><span>with your partner, friends, and family? Need to </span><strong><em><span>improve your job related skills</span></em></strong><span> </span><span>including your resume, interview techniques and personal brand? Want to <em>escape</em> the summer heat and enjoy </span><span>a <em>date night</em> with your partner or experience an <em>awesome night out</em> with friends? How about enjoy delicious, fresh, catered <em>meals at no cost </em>and<em> </em>earn up to <strong>$160 in <em>gift cards</em></strong> with a chance to <u>receive a one night hotel stay</u>? Parents, what about a <strong><em>FUN</em></strong> place for your child to engage in summer activities and crafts? </span></p>\n<p><span>If you answered <strong><u>YES</u></strong> to any of the questions above, please <u>call</u> us at <strong>407-823-1748</strong>, <u>e-mail</u> us at </span><a href=\"mailto:mfri@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span>mfri@ucf.edu</span></strong></a><strong><span> </span></strong><span>or complete a quick </span><a href=\"http://mfri.ucf.edu/contact-us/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span>online form</span></strong></a><strong><span> </span></strong><span>to learn about enrolling in Project Harmony! <u>ALL</u> workshops are at NO cost to you and new sessions start every month at UCF! <em>Evening and weekend</em> workshops are available with childcare for ages 0-12 years old at most events! </span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>Funding for this project was provided by the United States Department of Health and Human Services, Administration for Children and Families, Grant: # 90FM0078. These services are available to all eligible persons, regardless of race, gender, age, disability, or religion. </span><span>Project Harmony is classified as a research study at the University of Central Florida, UCF IRB SBE-15-11828. This study is under the direction of Dr. Sejal Barden, Principal Investigator and Dr. Dalena Dillman Taylor, Co-Principal Investigator.</span></p>','2018-06-27','2018-08-30','http://www.mfri.ucf.edu','Maria Riccardi','(407) 823-1748','mfri@ucf.edu','UCF Marriage and Family Research Institute- Project Harmony','Publish',100),(2653,'USPS Employee of the Month for June 2018: Christine Suleski','usps-employee-of-the-month-for-june-2018-christine-suleski','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for June 2018: Christine Suleski. Christine joined UCF in August 1992.   We would like to recognize her nominators, Ms. Nancy Brasel and Katherine Seeley, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. They had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>            <em>“Christine works diligently to provide a welcoming experience for students and faculty on the Cocoa campus. She is an integral part of the faculty and staff team and demonstrates the utmost professionalism in her work.  </em></p>\n<p><em>             Ms. Suleski’s mission and passion is to assist students to allow them the opportunity to grow, learn, succeed and be successful at UCF! She spends many months of the year working with faculty and the local school district to coordinate internship placements for our students.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Christine receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2018-06-29','2018-07-06','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2654,'PBA Collective Bargaining Session','pba-collective-bargaining-session-1','<p><span>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the Florida Police Benevolent Association will take place on Wednesday, July 11, from 1:30 p.m. – 3:30 p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center, Suite 100.</span></p>','2018-07-11','2018-07-11','','Elizabeth Richner','(407) 823-2771','elizabeth.richner@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Publish',98),(2655,'PBA Collective Bargaining Session','pba-collective-bargaining-session-1-2','<p><span>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida and the Police Benevolent Association will take place at 10:00 A.M. on Wednesday, July 25, 2018, in the Innovative Center (IC) room 105.</span></p>','2018-07-25','2018-07-25','','Elizabeth Richner','(407) 823-2771','elizabeth.richner@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Publish',98),(2656,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining Session','afscme-collective-bargaining-session-1','<p><span>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida and the </span><span>The American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees</span><span> will take place at 2:00 P.M. on Wednesday, July 18, 2018, in the Innovative Center (IC) room 105.</span></p>','2018-07-18','2018-07-18','','Elizabeth Richner','(407) 823-2771','elizabeth.richner@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Pending',98),(2657,'Having difficulty passing the FTCE exams?','having-difficulty-passing-the-ftce-exams','<p><strong><u>Having difficulty passing the FTCE exams?</u></strong><u><br> <br> </u></p>\n<p>Florida educators must be certified to teach in our public schools and in many of our private schools. UCF understands the significant role certification plays in pursuing your teaching career. Our IN-PERSON and ONLINE FTCE review programs provide Central Florida and other Florida regions with the opportunity and flexibility to enhance their skills and abilities to pass the FTCE General Knowledge, FTCE Professional Education, and the FTCE Elementary Education (K-6) exams.    </p>\n<p>FTCE General Knowledge English and Mathematics Review- September 6-28, 2018 – <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1098/Ftce---General-Knowledge-Review-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Enroll Now!</a></p>\n<p>FTCE General Knowledge English Review- September 6-27, 2018- <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1098/Ftce---General-Knowledge-Review-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Enroll Now!</a></p>\n<p>FTCE General Knowledge Math Review- September 7-28, 2018- <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1098/Ftce---General-Knowledge-Review-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Enroll Now!</a></p>\n<p>FTCE Elementary Education K-6 Review- October 12-November 16, 2018- <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1833/Ftce-Elementary-Education-K-6-Review-Course/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Enroll Now!</a></p>\n<p>FTCE Professional Review- October 26-November 16, 2018- <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1099/Ftce---Professional-Review-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Enroll Now!</a></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"http://www.testprep.ucf.edu/FTCE\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.testprep.ucf.edu/FTCE</a></span></p>\n<p> </p>','2018-07-18','2018-11-02','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1834/Ftce---Florida-Teacher-Certificate-Exam-Review-Courses/','Alexis Cason','(407) 882-0251','alexis.cason@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',84),(2658,'AFSCME Collective Bargaining Session','afscme-collective-bargaining-session-1-2','<p><span>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the American Federation of State, County, and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) will take place on Friday, July 20, from 2:30 p.m. – 4:30 p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center, Suite 100.</span></p>','2018-07-20','2018-07-20','','Elizabeth Richner','(407) 823-2771','elizabeth.richner@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Pending',98),(2659,'UCF Sports Medicine/football Developmental program now accepting new applicants for volunteers','ucf-sports-medicinefootball-developmental-program-now-accepting-new-applicants-for-volunteers','<p>We are currently looking for any current UCF students who are interested in a career in Sports Medicine or related field, and are interested in volunteering with UCF Sports Medicine working with the football team.</p>\n<p>Work would include helping set up sports medicine supplies, hydration of athletes at practices, minor first aid (if certified) and break down of supplies after practice. Additional opportunities will be available to observe Athletic Trainers, Doctors, Chiropractors, and massage therapists that work with UCF Sports medicine in the athletic training room on campus.</p>\n<p>This is a great opportunity for any student wanting to be involved in athletics and obtain valuable experience. Consideration will be given to students who have previous experience, currently in a related major or prepping for a master’s degree in athletic training.</p>\n<p>Please email Ed Woodley with a current resume and class schedule to ewoodley@athletics.ucf.edu if interested.</p>','2018-08-15','2018-12-10','http://ucfknights.com/sports/2016/6/13/school-bio-ucf-sports-med-html.aspx','Ed Woodley','(407) 823-0585','edwoodley@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Sports Medicine','Publish',102),(2660,'PBA Collective Bargaining Session','pba-collective-bargaining-session-1-2-3','<p>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) will take place on Friday, August 10, from 2:00 p.m. – 4:00 p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center, Suite 100.</p>','2018-08-01','2018-08-01','','Elizabeth Richner','(407) 823-2771','elizabeth.richner@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Pending',98),(2661,'2018 Annual Employee Awards Program','2018-annual-employee-awards-program','<p>Please join us on Friday, October 19th, for an afternoon of celebration as UCF Human Resources recognizes UCF\'s dedicated employees at our 46th Annual Employee Awards Program!</p>\n<p>Awardees include USPS and A&amp;P employees celebrating years of service anniversaries, as well as this year\'s retirees. Winners of the USPS Employee of the Year Award, the Gabor A&amp;P Excellence Award, and the United Way Advocate Leadership Award will also be announced.</p>\n<p>Invitations will be sent to awardees and nominees in late August; however, all employees are encouraged to attend.</p>\n<p>For more details, please visit the <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Annual Employee Awards Program webpage</a>.</p>\n<p>For questions, please contact the Human Resources Learning &amp; Organizational Effectiveness team at <a href=\"mailto:HRLearning@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">HRLearning@ucf.edu</a> or (407) 823-0440.</p>','2018-08-01','2018-10-19','https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/','HR Learning & Organizational Effectiveness','(407) 823-0440','HRLearning@ucf.edu','Lee Williams','Publish',24),(2662,'USPS Employee of the Month for July 2018: Ashli Vanhorn','usps-employee-of-the-month-for-july-2018-ashli-vanhorn','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for July 2018: Ashli Van Horn. Ashli was hired at UCF in March 2014 where she is the Facilities Scheduler in the College of Arts and Humanities. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>          <em>“Ashli is an integral part of the Academic support team for the College of Arts and Humanities, managing all aspects of the college schedule, including providing insight toward college initiatives with Global UCF, UCF Online and UCF Downtown. She has provided support for curriculum process, especially as we transition to a new tracking and management programs.</em></p>\n<p><em>          Ashli helped grow the student credit hour production 5.5% in the 2016-17 academic year.  This increase led the college to be in the top five performers at the university.  By ensuring we build a schedule that is student-focused, Ashli has helped the college stay on track to meet Challenge 2020 related goals to student success.” </em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Ashli received a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to the UCF Board of Trustees, and is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2018-08-09','2018-08-15','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2663,'Interested in becoming a Certified Fiber Optics Technician?','interested-in-becoming-a-certified-fiber-optics-technician','<p>This introductory in-person 3-day fiber optics course is designed for anyone interested in learning basic fiber optic networking and becoming a Certified Fiber Optic Technician. This program combines theory and 85% hands-on activities to prepare the student to take the <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">CFOT </span>(Certified Fiber Optics Technician) test that is sanctioned by the FOA (Fiber Optics Association) and given and graded the final class day. <br><br>This course also introduces the student to industry standards governing FTTD (Fiber To The Desk), FTTH (Fiber To The Home, LAN/WAN fiber networks, and further introduces the student to basic fusion and mechanical splicing. Students will learn how to identify fiber types, recognize various connectors used in fiber installation; and install, terminate, splice, and properly test installed fiber cable to existing standards. This program explores the history and future of fiber optics and fiber optics capabilities, and the cost of installation.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">To learn about all of our Fiber Optics courses, please visit </span><a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">www.ce.ucf.edu/fiberoptics</span></a></p>','2018-08-07','2018-11-26','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1278/Certified-Fiber-Optics-Technician-Cfot/','Alexis Cason','(407) 882-0251','alexis.cason@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',84),(2664,'New Member Meeting + Entrepreneurial Mindset Workshop','new-member-meeting-entrepreneurial-mindset-workshop','<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ceoknights/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">CEO Knights - Collegiate Entrepreneurs\' Organization at UCF</a><span> will be holding a new member meeting and workshop on Wednesday, August 29th at 6 pm in the Starterspace (BA1 135). The theme is Entrepreneurial Mindset!</span><br><br><span>Earn GEB points and meet up with fellow students who are interested in entrepreneurship! Your first meeting is free. This is a great opportunity to learn all about our club.</span><br><br><span>This event will be held in the Starterspace at 6 pm. All majors are welcome. You can earn GEB points at this event. </span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/212327642740740/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">*Please RSVP here*</a></strong></span></p>\n<p><span><br>Follow CEO Knights on Facebook: </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ceoknights/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/ceoknights/</a></p>\n<p><span>Join our member\'s group: </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/ceoknightsmembers/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/groups/ceoknightsmembers/</a><br><br><span>Follow us on Instagram: </span><a data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fceoknights&amp;h=AT1uLCl6mbqf3i0xXiiy5Ufk3Kp1IlByOizSHd5KLcKVixmh41W2xqGOhCjdXKvuBNfBJAXFa_ERmaNKAa1UpleyinOritCJBRieS8CMsGVy4F5WvP0_jebm4Mbm6m5bL4OW\" href=\"http://www.instagram.com/ceoknights\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.instagram.com/ceoknights</a><br><br><span>Sign up for our newsletter: </span><a data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Feepurl.com%2FD_Vyv&amp;h=AT1ErrF-LABWr41KcsfJBkErWMh-mv6_FYQsWBjsewKsqjZ1pj2hp6SOJLzBajknQPceo2Z4-5b82a30KBpZ2Dm5yOO44CYAKsEBEf0AvGMIeysXxDyRrAvxIvu1NVbrEHmD\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://eepurl.com/D_Vyv</a></p>','2018-08-15','2018-08-29','https://www.facebook.com/events/212327642740740/','Delaney Johnson','','ceoknights@gmail.com','CEO Knights','Publish',105),(2665,'Sick Leave Pool Open Enrollment','sick-leave-pool-open-enrollment-1','<p>The UCF Sick Leave Pool open enrollment is September 4 - September 28. To be eligible for membership, applicants must be employed with UCF continuously for at least one year, and have accrued 64 hours of sick leave as of September 2018.  New members are required to donate 16 hours of their sick leave (part-time employees will donate an amount proportionate to their FTE).  Membership reply letters will be sent to new applicants by early October 2018.</p>\n<p>Please note that if you are already a current member of the Sick Leave Pool, you do not need to rejoin during Open Enrollment. The URL listed below includes details on how to verify your current membership status and a link to the Open Enrollment Application.</p>\n<p>Interested faculty and staff should send applications to the Human Resources Leave Administration section at <a href=\"mailto:loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2018-09-04','2018-09-28','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/leave-and-general-attendance-information/sick-leave-pools','Todd Coon','(407) 823-2559','loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Publish',62),(2666,'Now accepting proposals: Pabst Steinmetz Foundation Arts & Wellness Innovation Awards','now-accepting-proposals-pabst-steinmetz-foundation-arts-wellness-innovation-awards','<p>Calling all UCF faculty and staff with interest areas in the field of Arts &amp; Wellness!</p>\n<p><strong>The Pabst Steinmetz Foundation Arts &amp; Wellness Innovation Awards are open for submission from Monday, August 20-Thursday, September 20, 2018. Two winners will be selected and receive $25,000 each.</strong></p>\n<p>The purpose of the<span> </span><a href=\"https://www.cah.ucf.edu/arts-wellness-innovation-awards/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Pabst Steinmetz Foundation Arts &amp; Wellness Innovation Awards</a><span> </span>is to build sustainable models for arts and wellness innovation both across the community and UCF campus. Interdisciplinary collaboration and evidence based community impact will be recognized as guides for building sustainability.</p>\n<p><strong>Award Criteria</strong></p>\n<p>All submissions must meet all of the following criteria:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Preference will be given to initiatives that are interdisciplinary, community-focused and sustainable.</strong></li>\n<li>Cross-disciplinary: Applicants must involve the UCF College of Arts and Humanities and at least one other college, unit or center at the University of Central Florida in each submission.</li>\n<li>All programs, initiatives or projects must contain an evaluation framework  (quantitative or qualitative.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Topic Examples</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Caregiving for loved ones with cognitive disorders</li>\n<li>Enforcing positivity with youth populations/mental health/bullying</li>\n<li>Daily wellness and self-care</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nomination Form and Selection Process</strong></p>\n<p>More information about the award, including the nomination form, is available at<span> </span><a href=\"https://www.cah.ucf.edu/arts-wellness-innovation-awards/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.cah.ucf.edu/arts-wellness-innovation-awards</a>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Nominations open August 20, 2018 and are due <strong>September 20, 2018</strong>.</li>\n<li>The selection committee comprises a representative from the UCF College of Arts and Humanities, the UCF College of Nursing, and the UCF College of Medicine, as well as up to three at-large members from the arts and wellness community.</li>\n<li>If a team is selected as the winner, the team leader will receive the award.</li>\n<li>Award presentations will be made in Spring 2019.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For questions, please contact Kara Robertson, Director for Advancement for UCF College of Arts and Humanities at<span> </span><a href=\"mailto:Kara.Robertson@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Kara.Robertson@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2018-08-20','2018-09-20','https://www.cah.ucf.edu/research/arts-wellness-innovation-awards/','Kara Robertson','(407) 823-3448','kara.robertson@ucf.edu','Heather Gibson','Publish',56),(2673,'USPS Staff Council Scholarships are now available!','usps-staff-council-scholarships-are-now-available-1-2-3-4-5-6','<p>The USPS Staff Council is now accepting applications for the Fall 2018 Scholarship awards.  Apply now at the Staff Council Facebook page, (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/UCFStaff/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/UCFStaff/</a>).  There are two awards up for grabs, the USPS Employee award and the Alumni award.  Applications must be in by 11:59 p.m. September 20th 2018.  You may apply for all the awards you qualify for.   The only restrictions are you must be a member of the USPS for a minimum of one year, and if you have won an award you must wait one year before applying for that particular award again.  Apply now and avoid the rush!</p>','2018-08-21','2018-09-20','https://www.facebook.com/UCFStaff/','Jamie LaMoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',54),(2674,'International Engineering Forum - The Impact of an International Education on your career success','international-engineering-forum-the-impact-of-an-international-education-on-your-career-success','<p><strong><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"></span></strong>Come to share an afternoon with our guest speakers who will be discussing how their companies value an international component to an engineering/CS/IT education.  A panel discussion to follow, Q&amp;A with speakers, UCF alumni and students returning from a study abroad experience.</p>\n<p><strong><span>Wednesday, September 5, 2018 </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span>2:00 to 5:00 PM </span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span>HEC 101</span></strong></p>','2018-08-24','2018-09-05','http://www.cecs.ucf.edu/international-engineering/','Maureen Waked','(407) 823-6037','mwaked@ucf.edu','Maureen Waked','Publish',109),(2677,'PBA Collective Bargaining Session','pba-collective-bargaining-session-1-2-3-4','<p><span>The next collective bargaining session between the University of Central Florida Board of Trustees and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) will take place on Wednesday, September 5, from 10:30 a.m. – 12:30 p.m. in UCF Police Department Room 316.</span></p>','2018-09-05','2018-09-05','','Elizabeth Richner','(407) 823-2771','elizabeth.richner@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Publish',98),(2678,'CEO Knights Networking Open House','ceo-knights-networking-open-house','<p>A new semester means new members to meet! Join us for this networking event to develop connections with new and returning members of CEO Knights. Who knows, you might meet your cofounder! </p>','2018-08-30','2018-09-06','https://www.facebook.com/events/996975133821085/','Nana Sackey','','ceoknights@gmail.com','CEO Knights','Publish',110),(2681,'Submit your UCF Celebrates the Arts event proposal','submit-your-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-event-proposal-1','<p><span>As <a href=\"http://arts.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Celebrates the Arts</a> embarks upon its fifth year, the festival Steering Committee is looking to showcase the best from UCF students and faculty and bring attention to our year-round activities on campus and in the community. The anticipated event dates are April 5-14, 2019.</span></p>\n<p><span>The committee is now seeking proposals for innovative and collaborative arts activities for inclusion in the 2019 festival. The ideas for these events can come out of classes; outside projects by faculty, students or alumni; or collaborative works associated with the university. <strong>Deadline for proposal submissions is Friday, September 21, 2018, at 5 p.m. Apply at <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_eDvXGdvF0MmnANv\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_eDvXGdvF0MmnANv</a></strong></span></p>\n<p><span>Some events are already on the schedule and may be used for inspiration. Proposals that tie into the scheduled events may be given additional consideration. 2019 events include:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span><em>Titanic</em>, a musical by Maury Yeston</span></li>\n<li><span>A concert by the Flying Horse Big Band and guests</span></li>\n<li><span>The NEA Big Read featuring \"Station Eleven\" by Emily St. John Mandel</span></li>\n<li><span>The National Young Composers Challenge and Emerging Composers Challenge</span></li>\n<li><span>A new musical that takes place in Puerto Rico during a hurricane</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span>Central to our focus is:</span><span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Showcasing the work and talents of students and faculty from UCF and the College of Arts &amp; Humanities </span></li>\n<li><span>Presenting events that are interdisciplinary within or beyond the walls of CAH</span><span></span></li>\n<li><span>Presenting 1-3 key events that are large in scope, that will attract attention nationally or regionally and will be major audience draws</span><span></span></li>\n<li><span>Presenting innovative, high-quality events and happenings that are unexpected, new, or out-of-the-box</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span><strong>Apply at <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_eDvXGdvF0MmnANv\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_eDvXGdvF0MmnANv</a>. </strong>Deadline for proposal submissions is Friday, September 21, 2018, at 5 p.m. </span></p>','2018-08-30','2018-09-21','http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_eDvXGdvF0MmnANv','Heather Gibson','(407) 823-5095','heather.gibson@ucf.edu','Heather Gibson','Publish',56),(2685,'In Financial Distress? Consider Student Support Foundation Grants','student-support-foundation-grants','<p>Are you in extreme financial distress? Then consider applying for a grant from the Student Support Foundation. </p>\n<p>All applications are reviewed anonymously and all information given will remain completely confidential. SSF applications are due each week on Monday at 8 a.m and applications are reviewed on a weekly basis. Please note that not all applicants will receive grant funding.</p>\n<p>SSF-UCF grants financial assistance up to $200 once a semester per student applicant. These funds can be used for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Academic Help – Books, school-related supplies, gowns/graduation materials, honor society dues</li>\n<li>Emergency Needs – Emergency travel, food, clothing</li>\n<li>Community – UCF Alternative Break trip deposits, leadership development event costs, student organization dues</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Need will be determined by Student Financial Assistance and all selected recipients will receive grant funding through Student Financial Assistance disbursements.  </p>','2019-03-18','2019-04-01','https://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/student-support-foundation/','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',8),(2686,'Jeanette Holder -- USPS Employee of the Month - August 2018','jeanette-holder-usps-employee-of-the-month-august-2018','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for August 2018: Jeanette Holder. Jeanette is the Senior Administrative Assistant at UCF Connect Headquarters Administration.  She has worked for UCF since May 1989. We would like to recognize her nominators, Dr. Kimberly Cole and Ms. Kimberly Hardy, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>          “Dedication, dependability and knowledge are only three of the attributes that come to mind when describing Ms. Holder.  Her dedication to UCF is illustrated by her commitment to the faculty, staff and students.  She embodies UCF’s mission, vision, values, and goals through her daily efforts of support for the administrative infrastructure of UCF Connect.</em></p>\n<p><em>          Jeanette is a professional who works in partnership with all areas and levels of the UCF Connect campuses.  She has proven to be a problem-solver when issues have arisen and offered to assist whenever appropriate.   Her extensive history at UCF provides her with a solid foundation and she is a valued and respected team member.” </em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Jeanette received a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to President Whittaker and members of the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2018-09-05','2018-09-13','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2687,'Applied Project Management Certificate Program - Project Management Professional (PMP) - Classes starts in April!','applied-project-management-certificate-program-project-management-professional-pmp-class-starts-in-january','<p><em><strong>UCF Continuing Education brings you project management training that fits your career and education goals.</strong></em> Training includes courses for those new to project management, those with senior level experience, and PDU courses to help maintain PM credentials.</p>\n<p>Ranked as one of the top 50 best project management programs our Applied Project Management Certification Program teaches a practical approach on project management principles working in a project management capacity and prepares participants for the CAPM® and PMP® examinations administered through the Project Management Institute (PMI).</p>\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong><br>Twelve weeks, instructor-led<br>Tuesday Evenings, 5:30pm – 9:30pm<br>April 2 - June 25</p>\n<p>Twelve weeks, live-online<br>Thursday Evenings, 5:30 - 9:30pm<br>April 4 - June 27<br><br><strong>Tuition</strong> Includes instruction, textbooks, and additional supplemental study materials.<br>$2,495 Registration Fee<br>$2,395 UCF Alumni Registration Fee</p>\n<p><strong>East Orlando Location</strong><br>UCF Continuing Education<br>Innovative Center<br>3280 Progress Drive Suite 700<br>Orlando, FL 32826</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong><br>• 12 week program offered in an interactive instructor-led classroom<br>format to keep you on track.<br>• Our program exceeds PMI’s education requirement of 23 hours of CAPM® and 35 hours of PMP® education to become eligible to sit for the CAPM® or PMP® exam.<br>• Learn and apply project management techniques that are effective in initiating, planning, executing, monitoring, controlling and closing a project.<br>• Learn test taking strategies to successfully pass the CAPM® or PMP® exam.<br>• Qualifies for most tuition reimbursement and payment plans are available</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Applied-Project-Management-Certificate-Project-Management-Professional-PMP\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Register Today!\">Classes fill up. Register Today! </a></p>','2018-10-01','2019-04-01','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2688,'Invest in Your HR Career','human-resources-a-roadmap-to-success-in-your-hr-career-1','<p><strong>As a top 10 SHRM Education Partner, UCF Continuing Education is proud to announce our Spring 2019 Professional Human Resources (SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP) Course dates to help you pass the exam!</strong></p>\n<p>Prepare for the SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP certification exam – the driving force behind effective business outcomes and talent management for all HR professionals.</p>\n<p><strong>UCF East Campus – </strong>February 20th (WEDNESDAYS) 6-9 PM</p>\n<p><strong>Live-Online </strong>– February 26th (TUESDAYS) 6-9 PM</p>\n<p><strong>Take advantage of the Early Bird rate of $1,199 until one month before the start of class!<br></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Why UCF?</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Live-online and face-to-face classes in multiple locations</li>\n<li>Evening and weekend schedules</li>\n<li>Study alongside peers from diverse backgrounds and discuss real-life examples</li>\n<li>Learn from the Official SHRM Learning System® and certified, seasoned instructors</li>\n<li>Thorough course introduction detailing the resources you will have access to beyond the SHRM books and learning system</li>\n<li>A bonus session to drive home the HR Competencies</li>\n<li>Access to the live-online recorded sessions</li>\n<li>Top quality program for a competitive price</li>\n<li>Early bird rates, discounts and payment plan options</li>\n<li>Global top 5 live-online &amp; top 10 face-to-face program</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Invest in Your HR Career. <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Professional-Human-Resources-Management-SHRM-CP-and-SHRM-SCP\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Register Now!\">Register Now!</a> </strong></p>\n<p> </p>','2018-10-01','2019-03-15','http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PHRM','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2689,'Volunteer with the UCF & United Way Campaign','volunteer-with-the-ucf-united-way-campaign','<p><em>Do you have a passion for making a difference? </em> Join the team of advocates who work throughout the month of October to support UCF\'s faculty &amp; staff United Way Campaign.  Visit <a href=\"http://liveunited.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">liveunited.ucf.edu</a> for more information or contact liveunited@ucf.edu or 407-823-3094.</p>','2018-09-17','2018-09-28','http://liveunited.ucf.edu','tee rogers','(407) 823-3094','liveunited@ucf.edu','tee','Publish',22),(2690,'National Hazing Prevention Week is Sept. 24-28, 2018.','national-hazing-prevention-week-is-sept-24-28-2018','<p>National Hazing Prevention Week takes place <strong>Sept. 24-28, 2018</strong>. UCF will take part in this nationwide effort to raise awareness about hazing through various activities events and programs.</p>\n<p>Hazing is defined as any activity expected of someone joining or participating in a group that humiliates, degrades, abuses or endangers them regardless of a person’s willingness to participate. <strong>More than half </strong>(51%) of college students involved in clubs, organizations and teams experience hazing on college campuses. </p>\n<p>Some of the programs during the week include Green Dot Bystander Intervention sessions, a Hazing 101 workshop, Anti-Hazing Pledge signing and an Open Mic-Knight.</p>\n<p>The key program of the week is the <strong>REP Your Colors: March Against Hazing</strong>.<strong> </strong>Students, faculty, staff and the campus community are invited to walk in a silent march against hazing on Wednesday, Sept 26 at noon from CFE Arena, down Memory Mall to the Reflection Pond. Participants are encouraged to represent organizations, teams or clubs by wearing logos, colors or letters.   </p>\n<p>“It is everyone’s responsibility to take a stand, challenge and fight against hazing on our campus. Together we can make a difference.”</p>\n<p>To learn more about UCF\'s Hazing Prevention Week and information about how to report hazing, visit <span><a href=\"http://antihazing.sdes.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">antihazing.sdes.ucf.edu</a></span>.</p>','2018-09-19','2018-09-28','https://antihazing.sdes.ucf.edu/','Paul Byron-Kelly','(407) 823-1072','Paul.Kelly@ucf.edu','Laura Cole','Publish',35),(2692,'Free Community Health Fair','free-community-health-fair','<p><span>The Digestive and Liver Center of Florida is hosting their Annual 2018 Free Community Health Fair on Saturday, November 3, 2018 from 10 AM to 2 PM at 100 N Dean Road Orlando, FL 32825.<br></span></p>\n<p><span>Free health screenings including Hepatitis A and B vaccines, Hepatitis C testing, veins screenings, liver fibroscans, hemoglobin checks, blood pressure checks, blood sugar checks, and more will be offered. </span></p>\n<p><span></span>As well as <span>flu shots (limited free vouchers for the uninsured), mammogram certificate raffles, and a </span><span>colonoscopy or endoscopy raffle.</span><br><br><span>Free food and local entertainment presentations. </span><br><br><span>Kids\' Zone will include jumpers and face painting for kids.</span><br><br><span>Free admission and free parking. </span><br><br><span>Call 407-384-7388 ext 706 or email info@dlcfl.com for more info!<br><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1906823856278277/?active_tab=about\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/events/1906823856278277/?active_tab=about</a><br></span></p>\n<p><span>Interested volunteers can sign up at <a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/A0VznSDgs9i1Xfo62\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://goo.gl/forms/A0VznSDgs9i1Xfo62</a></span></p>','2018-11-03','2018-11-03','https://www.facebook.com/events/1906823856278277/','Fatima Bawaney','(407) 384-7388','marketingdlcfl@gmail.com','Digestive and Liver Center of Florida','Publish',69),(2693,'Free Vitals Signs Hands-On Health Workshop','free-vitals-signs-hands-on-health-workshop','<p><span>Join MAPS in hosting Clinical Nurse Educator Susanna Bryan at the UCF Student Health Services for an exclusive health workshop. Learn more about vital signs and get some hands-on experience! Earn extra points for bringing a friend! Open to non-MAPS members as well.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>When: Friday, 19 October 2018 from 2:00pm-4:00pm</li>\n<li><span><em>Location: </em><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1060794567460661/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Student Health Services 2nd Floor Conference Room 206</a></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><span>RSVP: </span><a data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdaoWQhCEVywvDW39kERt4Mo2j7EdTjRe8kcOd5sVmif12ivg%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dsf_link&amp;h=AT3i6y5VfgP00o0ImIz6orJh5dSPVrcyzRLszP4F3j3TGqz8NuRU5za7Ydu8c7P5lx7iSOwQXYEWQbQnMTvRlEqjGmrkvChgLF4xb5y1yNi2kq-RX_1TI7g\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdaoWQhCEVywvDW39kERt4Mo2j7EdTjRe8kcOd5sVmif12ivg/viewform?usp=sf_link\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdaoWQhCEVywvDW39kERt4Mo2j7EdTjRe8kcOd5sVmif12ivg/viewform?usp=sf_link</a></p>','2018-10-19','2018-10-19','https://www.facebook.com/events/1060794567460661/','Fatima Bawaney','(321) 609-1202','maps.vpoperations@gmail.com','Multicultural Association of Pre-Health Students','Publish',69),(2694,'Free First Aid Hands-On Health Workshop','free-first-aid-hands-on-health-workshop','<p><span>Join MAPS in hosting Clinical Nurse Educator Susanna Bryan at the UCF Student Health Services for an exclusive health workshop. Lean more about first aid and get some hands-on experience! Earn extra points for bringing a friend! Open to non-MAPS members as well.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>When: Friday, 28 September 2018 from 2:30pm-4:30pm</li>\n<li><span><em>Location: </em><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/2209394399291706/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Student Health Services 2nd Floor Conference Room 206</a></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><span>RSVP: </span><a data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSfJWbw9LBiO3IacQCOYzCSgcQ_zeHn5vW3N8X_MKP1WQ38a2A%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dsf_link&amp;h=AT3qNDtswb0D3QlOlSpERj9Pvah2UnOllQo-YrFhV1sdVZY11rWMwsQhqmKNdqE9qQdgcsQJLK25hXCbXRdYYCAQBl4QePPKfe67e_ljKRibixs9koxeUqI\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfJWbw9LBiO3IacQCOYzCSgcQ_zeHn5vW3N8X_MKP1WQ38a2A/viewform?usp=sf_link\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfJWbw9LBiO3IacQCOYzCSgcQ_zeHn5vW3N8X_MKP1WQ38a2A/viewform?usp=sf_link</a><br><br><br><span>NOTE: Free flu shots will be provided by UCF Student Health Services. No appointment needed</span><br><br><span>Open to ALL</span></p>','2018-09-28','2018-09-28','https://www.facebook.com/events/2209394399291706/','Fatima Bawaney','(321) 609-1202','maps.vpoperations@gmail.com','Multicultural Association of Pre-Health Students','Publish',69),(2695,'Kappa Delta Pi International Society in Education Social/Partial Proceeds at Spoleto on 9/25 at 5:00 PM','kappa-delta-pi-international-society-in-education-socialpartial-proceeds-at-spoleto-on-925-at-500-pm','<p>Join us at Spoleto for a fun time and to help us raise funds for KDP between 5:00 p.m and 9:00 p.m. </p>\n<p>You may attend the event at any time during those hours. </p>\n<p>Please make sure to write \"KDP\" on your receipt and give it to the cashier to ensure that we get credit for it.</p>\n<p>This is a great opportunity for you to mingle with other KDP members and find out what KDP is all about!</p>\n<p>Applications will be available if you\'re interested in joining our organization. </p>\n<p>Let\'s get to know each other and have some fun!!!</p>\n<p>See you there!</p>\n<p>Jessica Thompson</p>\n<p>KDP President</p>','2018-09-25','2018-09-26','https://ucf.campuslabs.com/engage/event/2752786','Jessica Thompson','','kdp@ucf.edu','Kappa Delta Pi International Society in Education','Pending',113),(2696,'Kappa Delta Pi International Society in Education - KnightED Talk on 9/26 at 4:30 PM','kappa-delta-pi-international-society-in-education-knighted-talk-on-926-at-430-pm','<p>Join us for a workshop with KnightED Talks to find out more about our organization and network with current members. </p>\n<p>This is a great opportunity for education major/minor students to find out what KDP is all about! </p>\n<p>Applications will be available if you\'re interested in joining our organization</p>\n<p>Light refreshments will be provided!</p>','2018-09-25','2018-09-27','https://ucf.campuslabs.com/engage/event/2806006','Jessica Thompson','','kdp@ucf.edu','Kappa Delta Pi International Society in Education','Pending',113),(2697,'SCHOOL SUPPLY DRIVE!!!','school-supply-drive','<p>A school supply drive is an easy way to have a profound impact on students and their learning experience. Help us make a school a better place for both students and teachers by the simple act of providing school supplies. Students cannot be successful without the tools that they need.</p>\n<p><strong><u>Kappa Delta Pi, International Society in Education is holding a school supply drive until our next member meeting on October 9th in the Education Complex in Room 190. </u></strong></p>\n<p><strong><u>The supplies that we collect will be donated to one of the many schools that are in need of such important items.</u></strong></p>\n<p>Here is a list of suggested supplies. Feel free to donate items that are not on this list, this is just a suggested list.<strong> </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>lined paper, construction paper, spiral notebooks, composition books, index cards, sticky notes</li>\n<li>blue or black pens, #2 pencils, colored pencils, erasers, pencil sharpener, pencil case, colored markers, crayons, highlighters, dry-erase markers, sharpies</li>\n<li>paper towels, tissues, hand sanitizer, sanitizing wipes</li>\n<li>3-ring binders (2\" and 3\"), pocket folders, report covers, protector sheets</li>\n<li>stapler, staples, paper clips, binder clips, rulers, protractors, glue sticks, scissors, tape, calculator (4-function)</li>\n<li>thumb drives, earbuds</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>You may drop off any donations at the Education Complex in Suite 122 at the front desk. </strong></p>\n<p><strong></strong>Let us know if you have any questions or concerns. </p>\n<p>Jessica Thompson</p>\n<p>KDP President</p>\n<p>kdp@ucf.edu</p>','2018-09-25','2018-10-10','https://ucf.campuslabs.com/engage/event/2752790','Jessica Thompson','','kdp@ucf.edu','Kappa Delta Pi International Society in Education','Publish',113),(2698,'RWC and WHPS Fall Job Fair','rwc-and-whps-fall-job-fair','<p>Work at UCF\'s favorite place to play!</p>\n<p>Tuesday, October 9 <br>2:00pm - 4:00pm<br><br>Wednesday, October 10<br>5:00pm - 7:00pm<br><br>Join us and come to learn more about the positions at the RWC and WHPS! These are informal, informational sessions but we highly encourage you to attend. Positions will be available for Spring and Summer 2018. To apply, please submit your application, resume and cover letter. Job areas include:<br><br>Marketing<span> </span><br>Fitness<br>Sport Clubs<br>Aquatics<span> </span><br>Member Services<br>Intramural Sports<br>RWC Park<br>Outdoor Adventure<br>Building Manager<br>Wellness and Health Promotion Services Peer Advocates<br><br>The job fair begins in Room 206 at the RWC where you\'ll learn a little more about the RWC. After that drop of your cover letters, resumes and applications and meet our staff from all the program areas at the table set up in the main lobby. Opportunities for our International Students as well. See you there!<br><br>For more information contact:<br>Scott Mauro<br>RWC Marketing and Communications Manager<br>407-823-2408<br><a href=\"mailto:scott.mauro@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">scott.mauro@ucf.edu</a></p>','2018-10-01','2018-10-10','https://events.ucf.edu/event/400246/rwc-job-fair/','Scott Mauro','(407) 823-2408','scott.mauro@ucf.edu','Scott','Publish',34),(2699,'Employee Benefits Open Enrollment','employee-benefits-open-enrollment','<p>The state\'s annual open enrollment period for eligible employees to change insurance benefits options begins on Monday, October 15th at 8 a.m. and ends Friday, November 2nd at 6 p.m. EST.</p>\n<p>Please visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment</a> for additional details and updates.</p>\n<p>The annual Benefits Fair will be held on Wednesday, October 24th, from 9 a.m. - 2 p.m. in the Student Union Pegasus Ballroom.</p>\n<p>Questions can be directed to <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">benefits@ucf.edu</a> or 407.823.2771.</p>','2018-09-28','2018-11-02','https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment','Ashley Longoria','(407) 823-2771','ashley.longoria@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',21),(2705,'Leadership Week 2019 Call for Proposals','leadership-week-2019-call-for-proposals','<p>The LEAD Scholars Academy invites individuals to share their leadership knowledge and experience with the UCF campus during Leadership Week 2019. The committee is looking for workshops/sessions that will challenge and inspire the campus community and showcase current leadership topics.   Please complete the <strong>program proposal form at</strong> <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_3vXAbnfYYiwE5cV\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_3vXAbnfYYiwE5cV</a> .  The deadline to submit a program proposal is <strong>Friday, November 2, 2018</strong>. Program proposals will be evaluated and presenters will be notified by November 16, 2018.</p>\n<p><em>For more information please contact  Dr. Germayne Graham at <a href=\"mailto:Germayne.Graham@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Germayne.Graham@ucf.edu</a> or Zaria Woods at </em><em><a href=\"mailto:Zariawoods@Knights.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Zariawoods@Knights.ucf.edu</a></em><em>. </em></p>\n<p> </p>','2018-10-02','2018-11-02','https://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/callforprograms/','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Lead Scholars Academy','Publish',41),(2706,'UCF’s Certified Financial Planner™ Certification Education Program-Registration is NOW OPEN!','ucfs-certified-financial-plannertm-certification-education-program-registration-is-now-open','<p>UCF\'s <span>CFP</span><span>®</span> Certification Professional Education Program meets the educational needs of professionals who plan, assess, and evaluate a client\'s financial future through the development of a comprehensive financial plan. Our program\'s courses are taught by financial service professionals who provide current information in a variety of financial planning areas.</p>\n<p>UCF is partnering with Dalton Education to offer students a valuable, new way to complete their <span><em>CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ </em></span>education prior to passing the <span>CFP</span><span>®</span> exam. UCF\'s CFP model provides students with all-inclusive, CFP Board-registered and approved a program that will fulfill the coursework requirement and help participants prepare to be successful on the <span>CFP</span><span>®</span> exam.</p>\n<p>Individuals who successfully complete our program will fulfill the CFP Board contact hour minimum education requirement and become eligible to sit for the CFP® Certification Exam.</p>\n<p>Registration is now open for February 2019! <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1310/Ucfs-Cfp-Certification-Professional-Education-Program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for more information! </a></p>','2018-10-04','2019-02-09','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program-Search/1310/Ucfs-Cfp-Certification-Professional-Education-Program/','Alexis Cason','(407) 882-0251','alexis.cason@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',84),(2708,'Get a magical Halloween costume at Theatre UCF\'s Semi-Annual Costume Sale','get-a-magical-halloween-costume-at-theatre-ucfs-semi-annual-costume-sale','<p><span>Ever wanted to own something truly magical? Need a costume for Halloween? Theatre UCF\'s semi-annual sale is the perfect time to find the pieces you need to create a unique and inexpensive costume! All proceeds benefit future Theatre UCF productions. Thank you for your support!</span></p>\n<p>The sale is from 9 a.m.-5 p.m. in the <span>PAC-Theatre building Large Design Room, T244.</span></p>\n<p><br><span>*Cash preferred but checks are accepted. No credit cards. Most items are priced below $10!</span></p>\n<p><span>For more information, check our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/481389579028561/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook event</a>.</span></p>','2018-10-15','2018-10-19','https://www.facebook.com/events/481389579028561/','Steven Risko','(407) 823-3562','steven.risko@ucf.edu','School of Performing Arts','Publish',116),(2710,'Employee Benefits Open Enrollment','benefits-open-enrollment-1-2-3-4','<p>The state\'s annual open enrollment period for eligible employees to change insurance benefits options begins on Monday, October 15th at 8 a.m. and ends Friday, November 2nd at 6 p.m. EST.</p>\n<p>Please visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment</a> for additional details and updates.</p>\n<p>The annual Benefits Fair will be held on Wednesday, October 24th, from 9 a.m. - 2 p.m. in the Student Union Pegasus Ballroom.</p>\n<p>Questions can be directed to <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">benefits@ucf.edu</a> or <a href=\"tel:4078232771\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">407.823.2771</a>.</p>','2018-10-05','2018-11-02','https://hr.ucf.edu/open-enrollment','UCF HR Benefits Section','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Ashley Longoria','Publish',21),(2712,'UCF Cares Week of Action','ucf-cares-week-of-action','<p>This year’s Week of Action is inspired by the popular Netflix Series, <em>Stranger Things. </em>Demogorgon’s are known to cause distress and anytime during the semester you may feel like you’re stuck in the Upside Down. If you notice a student or yourself showing signs of “stranger things”, UCF Cares is here to help! Avoid entering the upside down- by doing your part to connect with programs and resources that can help! </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>UCF Cares Week of Action- Kick-Off Event</strong></p>\n<p>October 22nd from 11am-1pm</p>\n<p>Student Union Patio</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>L’Eggo my “Ego”: Get Trauma Informed</strong></p>\n<p>October 23rd from 2-3:30pm</p>\n<p>Trevor Colburn Hall 121</p>\n<p>Learn about the neurological responses that victims have to trauma. Through this workshop, participants learn how to identify these neurological responses to better aid the victims in getting the help and support they need.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Self-Defense Class</strong></p>\n<p>October 23rd from 2-4pm</p>\n<p>UCF Police Department</p>\n<p>Pre-Registration Required: <a href=\"https://police.ucf.edu/womens-self-defense\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://police.ucf.edu/womens-self-defense</a></p>\n<p>This course is designed to provide attendees with information, tactics and options which we believe may be useful for various types of crimes (no real-life demogorgons will be present during the demonstration).</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Fresh-U Cooking Demo and Stranger Things Trivia</strong></p>\n<p>October 24th at Noon</p>\n<p>Memory Mall</p>\n<p>Show off your Stranger Things knowledge with trivia while you watch the Wellness and Health Promotions team show off their culinary skills with an 80’s throwback meal. Watch the cooking process, taste the dish, and take home a recipe card so you can make it again.  </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Stranger Things Mini-Marathon and Games</strong></p>\n<p>October 24th from 5pm-10pm</p>\n<p>Neptune Multipurpose Room</p>\n<p>Join the UCF Cares Ambassadors for more themed activities and watch your favorite Stranger Things episodes! Get in the Halloween spirit with snacks, games, photo booth and more!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>UCF Cares Resource Fair</strong></p>\n<p>October 25th from 11am-1pm</p>\n<p>Student Union Patio</p>\n<p>Meet the UCF Cares Ambassadors and campus departments that help you avoid the Upside Down. Gather resources, talk with the experts, and win some prizes!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Green Dot Training</strong></p>\n<p>November 3rd from 10am-3pm</p>\n<p>Student Union, RSVP at <a href=\"mailto:greendot@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">greendot@ucf.edu</a> to receive complete details</p>\n<p>If you’ve completed the Week of Action, you’re a UCF Cares expert. Take your expertise to the next level with the complete Green Dot Training. Green Dot is a bystander intervention initiative that teaches people how to safely take action when they see personal violence. This training will teach attendees how to be a proactive bystander by utilizing three simple techniques: direct, distract, and delegate. Plus, you get a free swag bag and tee shirt for participating!</p>','2018-10-22','2018-10-26','https://cares.sdes.ucf.edu/','Ann Marie Palmer','(407) 823-5607','annmarie.palmer@ucf.edu','Ann Marie Palmer','Publish',73),(2713,'UCF Kids Trick or Treating Event','ucf-kids-trick-or-treating-event','<p>The National Residence Hall Honorary (NRHH) is our hosting our first ever Halloween event here at UCF. At this event, we hope to create a fun-filled night for the children of our faculty, staff, and students. We will be having a bounce house, games, food, raffles, a costume contest, and more! Our Halloween event will take place on <strong>Tuesday, October 30th from 5:00-7:30 PM in Academic Village<u>.</u></strong> The first 100 kids to arrive, will receive goodie bags! As we do strongly advocate for service to our community as well, we ask those in attendance bring at least one non-perishable item which we will donate back to the UCF community for our Knights Pantry, an on-campus food pantry catered to supporting our students. Any questions can be directed to <a href=\"mailto:NRHHUCF@gmail.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">NRHHUCF@gmail.com</a>. Thank you, hope to see you all there!</p>','2018-10-11','2018-10-30','','Jazmine Manriquez','(407) 882-5005','nrhhucf.bac@gmail.com','Department of Housing & Residence Life','Publish',119),(2714,'Pink Pong','pink-pong','<p>We would like to invite you to participate in our annual Pink Pong Tournament. One of our national philanthropies is Breast Cancer and this year we would like to raise money with a fun twist. This is a non-alcoholic beer pong tournament. We will be using pink lemonade in representation of breast cancer. This event will be held on October 17th, 2018 at 7pm. We are looking for teams of two to participate in this tournament with a $10 team registration fee. All proceeds will benefit the Susan G. Komen Race for a Cure Foundation.</p>\n<p>If you are interested in participating in our Pink Pong Tournament please contact Nicole Diaz by October 15th at 11:59pm to slg@ucf.edu or Tylisha Thompson at vp_iotabeta@yahoo.com. We will inform you of how to pay the registration fee of $10. Please feel free to contact us if you have any questions!</p>','2018-10-17','2018-10-17','http://www.twitter.com/iotabetagammas','Nicole Diaz','(321) 276-5818','SLG@UCF.EDU','Nicole Diaz','Pending',120),(2717,'Pink Pong Tournament','pink-pong-tournament','<p>Sigma Lambda Gamma National Sorority Incorporated is hosting our 7th annual “Pink Pong Tournament” on October 17th. All proceeds will be donated to the Susan G Komen Foundation to help fund breast cancer awareness and research. Team registration is 10$ right now for teams of 2 players and we would love to have you participate. If you have any further questions feel free to email us at SLG@UCF.EDU </p>\n<p>Thank you.</p>','2018-10-17','2018-10-17','http://twitter.com/iotabetagammas','Nicole Diaz','(321) 276-5818','SLG@ucf.edu','Nicole Diaz','Pending',120),(2718,'Pink Pong Tournament','pink-pong-tournament-1','<p>Sigma Lambda Gamma National Sorority Incorporated is hosting our 7th annual “Pink Pong Tournament” on October 17th. All proceeds will be donated to the Susan G Komen Foundation to help fund breast cancer awareness and research. Team registration is 10$ right now for teams of 2 players and we would love to have you participate. If you have any further questions feel free to email us at SLG@UCF.EDU </p>\n<p>Thank you.</p>','2018-10-17','2018-10-17','http://twitter.com/iotabetagammas','Nicole Diaz','(321) 276-5818','SLG@ucf.edu','Nicole Diaz','Pending',120),(2719,'Ping Pong Tournament','ping-pong-tournament','<p>Sigma Lambda Gamma National Sorority Incorporated is hosting the 7th annual “Pink Pong Tournament” on October 17th. All proceeds will be donated to the Susan G Komen Foundation to help fund breast cancer awareness and research. Team registration is 10$ right now for teams of 2 and we would love to have you participate. If you have any further questions feel free to email us at SLG@UCF.EDU <br>Thank you.</p>','2018-10-17','2018-10-17','','Nicole Diaz','(321) 276-5818','slg@ucf.edu','Nicole Diaz','Pending',120),(2720,'All are Welcome at UCF\'s 46th Annual Employee Awards Program','all-are-welcome-at-ucfs-46th-annual-employee-awards-program','<p>All employees are invited to attend the 2018 Annual Employee Awards Program on Friday, October 19, from 2:30 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. The event will take place in the Pegasus Ballroom at the Student Union and will be streamed live on UCF’s YouTube Channel. A reception will follow in the Key West Ballroom with an international-flavored menu. Only award recipients who received invitations need to RSVP.</p>\n<p>The Annual Employee Awards Program recognizes USPS and A&amp;P employees for longevity of service to UCF. Employees are recognized at five-year increments. Employees who are retiring from UCF and the Employees of the Month are also recognized. The USPS Employee of the Year and the A&amp;P Gabor Excellence Award winner will be announced; both will be presented with a $2,500 check. In addition, the United Way Advocate Leadership Award winner will be announced. </p>','2018-10-19','2018-10-19','https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/','Lee Williams','(407) 823-0858','lee.williams@ucf.edu','Lorie Matejowsky','Publish',122),(2725,'Archery Club Fundraiser with UNO\'s','archery-club-fundraiser-with-unos-1-2-3','<p>Join the UCF Archery Club Knight\'s Bow in raising funds by going to any of the Central Florida UNO\'s locations until the end of October. All you have to do is present the flyer that is on the facebook link when paying and 20% will be given to the club.</p>\n<p>Catering will also assist the club if you or any other organization contact Joyce Stackpole at <span data-ft=\'{\"tn\":\"K\"}\'>407-617-2827 and mention Knights Bow.</span></p>\n<p><span data-ft=\'{\"tn\":\"K\"}\'>Also, if anyone is interested in the club, don\'t hesitate to visit our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/KnightsBow/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Knight\'s Bow Facebook Page\">facebook page</a> and message us to get involved and to find more information about the event. </span></p>','2018-10-18','2018-10-31','https://www.facebook.com/KnightsBow/photos/a.1178886032178033/1919991408067488/?type=3&theater','Knight\'s Bow','','knightsbow@gmail.com','Knight\'s Bow at UCF','Publish',125),(2727,'Volunteer Opportunity: Halloween Spooktacular','volunteer-opportunity-halloween-spooktacular-1','<p><span>Come to join UCF CBOB for a spooky afternoon full of pumpkin carving, trick-or-treat bag making, spider making, ghost designing, face painting, and more! </span></p>\n<p><span>We will also have a trunk-or-treat taking place. This event will help give children that consider a motel their home a safe and fun way to have a \"trick or treat\" experience. Volunteers, please visit </span><a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fchbob.org%2Fvolunteerucf&amp;h=AT2N3yuqLeVS3C2fe3LFIZu2m0yQQk41TzLuQmpTlmDqMek02vey5oOOZRKybCd2AH_4bUuwLHDDL3YsBcMG9KkYy-PjPa5QUAGzYzGrhwtNT6Wt_I0y6B-VSl_mKwT11BKmSlg\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">chbob.org/volunteerucf</a><span> to sign up for this fun Halloween event! </span></p>\n<p><span>Winners of the trunk or treat competition will receive two tickets to Epcot. </span></p>','2018-10-17','2018-10-27','http://chbob.org/volunteerucf','Yanelis Diaz','(786) 202-1950','operationsdirector@chbob.org','Yanelis Diaz','Publish',43),(2732,'Last Week to Apply for the Cuba Study Abroad Program','journey-cuba-study-abroad-1-2-3-4','<p><em>JOURNEY CUBA STUDY ABROAD-SPRING BREAK 2019</em></p>\n<p><em>Program: Journey Cuba Havana, Trinidad, Cienfuegos March 9- March 17</em></p>\n<p><em>Program Description: Spend your spring break immersed in Cuban culture! In Spring 2019 the Department of Modern Languages &amp; Literatures will offer UCF students the opportunity to participate in this exciting program to Cuba. This program is open to UCF students across all disciplines and would appeal particularly to students in History, Political Science, Latin American Studies, Spanish, Literature, Education, Art, Engineering and Music. Through this program, students will gain awareness and appreciation of Cuban society, culture, and history through direct and unique experiences. Knowledge of Spanish is NOT a requirement for this program.</em></p>\n<p><em></em><em>Apply now at <a href=\"https://studyabroad.ucf.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&amp;id=10296\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://studyabroad.ucf.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&amp;id=10296</a></em></p>\n<p><em></em><em>Contact faculty directors for more information: Kacie Tartt <a href=\"mailto:Kacie.Tartt@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Kacie.Tartt@ucf.edu</a> and  Anne Prucha <a href=\"mailto:Kacie.Tartt@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Anne.Prucha@ucf.edu</a></em></p>','2018-10-18','2019-02-07','https://studyabroad.ucf.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=10296','Kacie Tartt','','kacie.tartt@ucf.edu','Kacie Tartt','Publish',126),(2736,'Study Abroad in Cuba This Summer','summer-cuba-study-abroad-1-2-3','<p>SUMMER CUBA STUDY ABROAD-SUMMER A 2019 Program: Journey Cuba Havana, Viñales May 26 - June 21</p>\n<p>Program Description: Spend your spring break immersed in Cuban culture! In Summer 2019 the Department of Modern Languages &amp; Literatures will offer UCF students the opportunity to participate in this exciting program to Cuba. This program is open to UCF students across all disciplines and would appeal particularly to students in History, Political Science, Latin American Studies, Spanish, Literature, Education, Art, Engineering and Music. Through this program, students will gain awareness and appreciation of Cuban society, culture, and history through direct and unique experiences. Knowledge of Spanish is NOT a requirement for this program.</p>\n<p>Apply now at <a href=\"https://studyabroad.ucf.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&amp;id=11458\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://studyabroad.ucf.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&amp;id=11458</a></p>\n<p>Contact faculty directors for more information: Kacie Tartt <a href=\"mailto:Kacie.Tartt@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Kacie.Tartt@ucf.edu</a> and Anne Prucha <a href=\"mailto:Anne.Prucha@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Anne.Prucha@ucf.edu</a></p>','2019-03-11','2019-04-26','https://studyabroad.ucf.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=11458','Kacie Tartt','(407) 738-5252','kacie.tartt@ucf.edu','Kacie Tartt','Publish',126),(2739,'Sexual Assault Mock Trial','sexual-assault-mock-trial','<p>Sexual Assault Mock Trial is an event by Victim Services and their partners, Knight Advocates, and LGBTQ+ Services. You will have the opportunity to hear testimony, cross-examinations, and be a member of the jury. Explore the difference between consensual sex and rape.</p>','2018-10-29','2018-11-06','','Christey Oberbeck','(407) 823-2425','knightadvocates@gmail.com','Knight Advocates','Publish',128),(2740,'Comparative Law Study Abroad in London!','comparative-law-study-abroad-in-london','<p>Study abroad in the UK this summer with the Department of Legal Studies!</p>\n<p>When: June 1-16, 2019 (16 days)</p>\n<p>Where: London and Oxford</p>\n<p>Learn about the comparative law while visiting historical courts and sites around London and Oxford. This opportunity is open to students of all majors but especially those with an interest in law or international justice such as Legal Studies, Political Science, and Criminal Justice majors. </p>\n<p>Apply <a href=\"https://studyabroad.ucf.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&amp;id=10077\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">now</a></p>\n<p>Contact Katie Connolly <a href=\"mailto:katiec@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Katiec@ucf.edu</a> for more information.</p>','2018-10-28','2019-02-01','https://ccie.ucf.edu/legalstudies/study-abroad/uk/','Katie Connolly','(407) 823-0205','Katiec@ucf.edu','Jordan Ackerman','Publish',129),(2741,'USPS Employee of the Month - September 2018 Hollesha Foster','usps-employee-of-the-month-september-2018-hollesha-foster','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for September 2018: Hollesha Foster. Hollesha is the Office Manager at the College of Science Dean’s Office. She has worked for UCF since October 2015. Jean Bagga and Donna Lucas who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts among their colleagues. Her nominators had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>          “What I have learned about Hollesha is she takes great pride in not just helping a single person or individual, but in helping all of us be successful at UCF RESTORES, College of Sciences and the University at large. She sets a great example for the University. She is open to new opportunities and doesn’t hesitate to reach out to help others. </em></p>\n<p><em>I think of Hollesha when I read UCF’s ‘The Power of Potential’ which states: ‘when more people unleash their full potential, anything is possible.’ I believe her attention to detail when training stems from her understanding of unleashing the potential in others. She demands excellence of herself and encourages others to be the best they can be.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Hollesha received a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to President Whittaker. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2018-10-31','2018-11-07','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2744,'Fall Festival presented by Knight-Thon','fall-festival-presented-by-knight-thon-1-2','<p>Fall Festival is a community event benefiting Orlando\'s local Children\'s Miracle Network (CMN) Hospital, Orlando Health Arnold Palmer Hospital for Children! Come out on November 3rd and enjoy fun, music, food, and fall festivities for all ages! All proceeds will benefit our local CMN Hospital. The event is free for UCF Students with a valid UCF ID! You won\'t want to miss this fun &amp; festive event!</p>\n<p>Activities &amp; Food Include:</p>\n<p>- Pumpkin Painting</p>\n<p>- Inflatables - Bounce house, Obstacle course, 3 in 1 Bungee run</p>\n<p>- Over 15 Carnival Games - including ring toss, fish bowl, balloon pop</p>\n<p>- Cotton candy</p>\n<p>- Popcorn</p>\n<p>- Snowcones</p>\n<p>- And more!</p>','2018-10-30','2018-11-03','https://www.facebook.com/events/482111798951935/','Knight-Thon','(407) 823-4496','knight-thon@ucf.edu','Knight-Thon at the University of Central Florida','Publish',131),(2745,'LAS 3930: Cuba a Collective Portrait','las-3930-cuba-a-collective-portrait','<p><span>n this course, UCF students will dive into today’s vibrant Cuban culture, examining it through exploration of visual arts, literature, music, history, and other themes. This course and affiliated short-term study abroad trip offer a rare opportunity and are<strong> open to UCF students across all disciplines</strong>. LAS 3930 would appeal particularly to students in history, political science, Latin American studies, Spanish, literature, education, art, engineering and music. Through this course, students will gain an awareness and appreciation of Cuban society, culture, and history through direct and unique experiences. Knowledge of Spanish is NOT a requirement.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>LAS 3930 features two distinct tracks: the first with a <strong>traditional study abroad</strong> experience, and the second with a <strong>virtual study abroad </strong>experience.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>As a traditional study abroad participant, you will go on the Spring Break trip to Cuba, where you will engage in a rigorous and active daily program including, but not limited to, visits to museums and cultural centers, art installations, medical clinics, schools, farms, sporting facilities, and sites claiming historic and cultural significance. You will be provided with a permission number to enroll in the course.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>For students who choose the virtual track, the study abroad experience will include collaborating with students who go on the trip on a variety of assignments shaped by the course goals and learning outcomes before, during, and after Spring Break. Students who wish to participate in this track may register for the course now! We have 20 spots available! Register today!</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>Feel free to share information regarding this course with anyone you think would be interested!</span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><strong><span>Please contact us if you are interested in this course, programs or have any additional questions:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span>Kacie Tartt (</span><a data-auth=\"NotApplicable\" href=\"mailto:Kacie.Tartt@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Kacie.Tartt@ucf.edu</span></a><span>) &amp; Anne Prucha (</span><a data-auth=\"NotApplicable\" href=\"mailto:Anne.Prucha@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Anne.Prucha@ucf.edu</span></a><span>)</span></p>','2018-11-08','2018-01-12','','Kacie Tartt','(407) 738-5252','kacie.tartt@ucf.edu','Kacie Tartt','Pending',126),(2746,'Are you missing 2-3 credit hours for the Spring 2019 Semester?','are-you-missing-2-3-credit-hours-for-the-spring-2019-semester','<p><strong>Are you missing 2-3 credit hours for the Spring 2019 Semester?</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Do you love working out?</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Do you like sports?</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Interested in learning about becoming fit/healthy?</strong></p>\n<p><strong>The following courses are perfect for you!</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Personal Fitness:</strong> Learn how to design your own workout program to reach your fitness goals! Class includes going to the gym and learning about different exercise techniques.</p>\n<p>- PEM 2104-0001 (11748) Tuesday 10:30am-1:20pm</p>\n<p>- PEM 2104-0002 (11649) Thursday 10:30am-1:20pm</p>\n<p>- PEM 2104-0003 (19764) Monday 6:00pm-8:50pm</p>\n<p><strong>Intro to Sport and Exercise Science:</strong> An introduction to the field where you will be exposed to different professions in the field including: physical therapy, athletic training, strength and conditioning coach and many more!</p>\n<p>- PET 3005-0003 (12118) Monday 6:00pm-8:50pm</p>\n<p>- PET 3005-0M01 (12099) Monday 1:30pm-4:20pm</p>\n<p>- PET 3005-0M02 (12117) Monday 10:30am-1:20pm</p>\n<p> <strong>Beginning Judo</strong>: Learn and practice how to throw people! Judo is great for learning self-defense and basic standing and ground techniques. Techniques include: falls, throws, choke holds and arm bar.</p>\n<p>- PEM 2431-0001 (12244) Tuesday 7:00pm-8:50pm</p>\n<p>- PEM 2431-0002 (12253) Wednesday 10:30am-12:20pm</p>\n<p>- PEM 2431-0003 (12254) Wednesday 1:30pm-3:20pm</p>\n<p> <strong>Strength &amp; Resistance Training:</strong> Learn how to make an effective strength training program for your strength and fitness goals! Class includes going to the gym and learning proper lifting techniques.</p>\n<p>- PEM 2131-0001 (21115) Wednesday 8:30am-10:20am</p>','2018-11-14','2019-01-10','https://healthprofessions.ucf.edu/kpt/kinesiology/','Sport and Exercise Science Advising','(407) 823-0623','SESadvising@ucf.edu','Division of Kinesiology','Publish',13),(2747,'Center for Distributed Learning, Cavanagh Win National Awards for Online Programs','center-for-distributed-learning-cavanagh-win-national-awards-for-online-programs','<p><span>Two new national UCF awards for distributed learning reflect the escalating prominence and reach of the university’s online programs.</span></p>\n<p><span>Read more at <a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/center-distributed-learning-cavanagh-win-national-awards-online-programs/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://today.ucf.edu/center-distributed-learning-cavanagh-win-national-awards-online-programs/</a></span></p>','2018-11-12','2018-11-16','https://today.ucf.edu/center-distributed-learning-cavanagh-win-national-awards-online-programs/','Center for Distributed Learning','(407) 823-4910','cdl@ucf.edu','CDL','Publish',35),(2748,'International Education Week Is Nov. 12-16','international-education-week-is-nov-12-16','<p><span>International students, faculty and staff are an integral part of who we are as Knights. To celebrate our cultural diversity, </span><a href=\"https://global.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Global</a><span> is hosting </span><a href=\"https://global.ucf.edu/resources/iew/#events\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">International Education Week</a><span>, a campuswide series of concerts, films, panel discussions, parties and other events showcasing traditions, viewpoints, arts, music and flavors from around the world.</span></p>\n<p><span>Learn more at <a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-global-international-education-week/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-global-international-education-week/</a></span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>','2018-11-12','2018-11-16','https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-global-international-education-week/','UCF Global','(407) 823-3227','ucfglobal@ucf.edu','UCF Global','Publish',35),(2749,'USPS Employee of the Month - October 2018','usps-employee-of-the-month-october-2018','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for October 2018: Miguel Guzman. Miguel is the Office Assistant at the Parking Services Operations. He has worked for UCF since April 2013. Andy Rampersand and Manuel Guerrero, who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues, had this to say about him:</p>\n<p><em>          </em><em>“To the UCF community, parking of one’s vehicle is often the first impression. With 18,000 parking spaces on our campus and 63,000+ students, Miguel is dedicated to excellence and promoting efficiency. He identifies gaps in the service experience and recommends to his supervisor solutions to enhance parking operations. His strategies help to amplify pedestrian safety, reduces personnel staffing, and manages pedestrians with a smile.</em></p>\n<p><em>On football game days, he’s always one step ahead of traffic flow by anticipating when to close a garage. As a field supervisor he always practices great customer service skills, never saying no and always finding a solution.   His character, experience, customer service, and dedication help our parking operations every day. He never sets out for praises, but honestly cares for the UCF community and strives for excellence each day.” </em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Miguel received a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, his name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to President Whittaker. He is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2018-11-15','2018-11-26','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2750,'Harvest Your Christmas Tree at UCF Arboretum on Dec. 2','harvest-your-christmas-tree-at-ucf-arboretum-on-dec-1','<p>Embark a new holiday tradition with your entire family! On December 2, anytime between 11 a.m. and 5 p.m., bring the family out to the UCF Arboretum and get into the holiday spirit with this one-of-a-kind experience that includes cutting down your very own Christmas tree, Florida style. </p>\n<p>During this experience, we will all load up in our van and drive out to the lot where you can search for your perfect tree. This is a very special type of Christmas tree, native to the Florida habitat, the Pinus Clausa, or the Florida Spruce Pine. While you are out choosing your tree, you will also learn about Florida’s ecosystems and help us manage them at UCF.</p>\n<p>If the tree you choose is small enough, you can cut it down with a hand saw we provide for you. Otherwise, the Arboretum staff will help cut the tree down with a chainsaw. We will then haul the tree back to the nature pavilion where you can enjoy complimentary cookies and hot chocolate before you load the tree on your car to take home.</p>\n<p>More details can be found at <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fevents.ucf.edu%2Fevent%2F1058158%2Fucf-arboretum-christmas-tree-harvest%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CLaura.Cole%40ucf.edu%7Cb3640e74a3d8476459a608d64e30a1c8%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636782368102682812&amp;sdata=NyG1XK13GeS2S%2BGGJAFXezYZi7Pq8K3fLXhqyaKCrv0%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://events.ucf.edu/event/1058158/ucf-arboretum-christmas-tree-harvest/</a> </p>','2018-11-19','2018-12-02','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1058158/ucf-arboretum-christmas-tree-harvest/','UCF Arboretum','(407) 823-3583','arboretum@ucf.edu','Judy Froehlich','Publish',35),(2751,'FIEA Startup Showcase','fiea-startup-showcase','<p><span>Student game-designers from the Florida Interactive Entertainment Academy, UCF’s graduate videogame development program, will get the “Shark Tank” experience when they present and pitch the latest games and apps to investors, faculty and staff. Their nine gaming projects include a multiplayer virtual escape room, virtual chemistry game and a number of entertaining mobile apps! The projects are part of FIEA’s Venture Class, which teaches the entrepreneurial side of games.</span></p>','2018-11-21','2018-12-12','https://fiea.ucf.edu/startupshowcase/','Todd Deery','(407) 235-3582','todd.deery@ucf.edu','Todd Deery','Publish',137),(2753,'Graduates - Be Sure to Pick Up Your Cap, Gown and Tickets','graduates-be-sure-to-pick-up-your-cap-gown-and-tickets-before-dec-7','<p><span>Candidates are required to wear official regalia available exclusively through the <a href=\"http://ucf.bncollege.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Bookstores</a> (407-882-0364) and online through <a href=\"http://colleges.herffjones.com/college/ucf/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Herff Jones</a>. Students can pick up their cap, gown and tickets during cap and gown distribution, which is held <strong>at the UCF Fairwinds Alumni Center</strong>. The event includes giveaways, free cap decorating and more.</span></p>\n<p><span>All rented items are due back by <strong>5 p.m. on Graduation Day</strong>.</span></p>','2018-11-29','2018-12-14','https://commencement.ucf.edu/','UCF Alumni','(407) 882-0364','knights@ucfalumni.com','UCF Today','Publish',35),(2754,'Vote for Becky Cramer for USRowing Fan\'s Choice Collegiate Coach of the Year','vote-for-becky-cramer-for-usrowing-fans-choice-collegiate-coach-of-the-year','<p>UCF Head Women’s Rowing Coach Becky Cramer is a finalist for USRowing Fan’s Choice Collegiate Coach of the Year. </p>\n<p>Becky has led the Knights to four-consecutive American Athletic Conference championships – just one of two women’s programs in our league to do so. Her Varsity Eight and Second Varsity Eight squads have won their conference events in each of the last four years and the Knights have posted Top 20 finishes at NCAAs for four years straight.</p>\n<p><strong>Voting is open until 11:59 p.m. on Nov. 27 and the winner will be announced on Nov. 28. </strong></p>\n<p>Help us push Becky to the top:<strong> <a href=\"usrowing.org/2018-fans-choice-collegiate-coach-of-the-yea\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">usrowing.org/2018-fans-choice-collegiate-coach-of-the-yea</a></strong>r.</p>','2018-11-26','2018-11-27','http://www.usrowing.org/2018-fans-choice-collegiate-coach-of-the-year','Amy Sterk','(407) 823-1954','ucfknights@ucf.edu','Amy Sterk','Publish',35),(2755,'UCF, Conservation Florida Join Forces to Protect Natural Lands','ucf-conservation-florida-join-forces-to-protect-natural-lands','<p>A new partnership between Conservation Florida and both UCF’s biology<span> </span>department and<span> UCF Coastal </span>increases the bench strength of statewide land protection work. The partnership aims to produce research, guidance, and a multidisciplinary voice to land and wildlife conservation to propel advancement in the greater Central Florida region.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-conversation-florida-join-forces-protect-natural-lands/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Read more...</a></p>','2018-12-06','2018-12-07','https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-conversation-florida-join-forces-protect-natural-lands/','Kyle Martin','(407) 823-0348','kyle.martin@ucf.edu','UCF Today','Publish',35),(2756,'WUCF, Producer Win Emmy for Mister Rogers Program','wucf-producer-win-emmy-for-mister-rogers-program','<p>TV producer Kyle Fuchs and WUCF won a regional Emmy on Saturday for the program<span> </span><em>Mister Rogers in Our Neighborhood</em>, a broadcast about Fred Rogers’ Winter Park roots and his legacy in Central Florida.</p>\n<p>The National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences presented the Suncoast Regional Emmy Award in the nostalgia program category during an Orlando banquet. The show was broadcast in February to commemorate the half-century anniversary of the beginning of the children’s show.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/wucf-producer-win-emmy-mister-rogers-program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Read more...</a></p>','2018-12-06','2018-12-07','https://today.ucf.edu/wucf-producer-win-emmy-mister-rogers-program/','Gene Kruckemyer','(407) 823-1637','gene.kruckemyer@ucf.edu','UCF Today','Publish',35),(2757,'UCF Writing Center Director Wins International Award','ucf-writing-center-director-wins-international-award','<p>Mark Hall, program director of the UCF Writing Center and professor of writing &amp; rhetoric, won the International Writing Center Association award for Outstanding Book/Major Work of 2018 for his book <em>Around the Texts of Writing Center Work</em>. The award is given to one book a biennium that makes a significant contribution to the scholarship of and research on writing centers. In his book, Hall illustrates how educating tutors enhances their professional development.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-writing-center-director-wins-international-award/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Read more...</a></p>','2018-12-06','2018-12-07','https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-writing-center-director-wins-international-award/','Mark Hall','(407) 823-0504','rmarkhall@ucf.edu','UCF Today','Publish',35),(2758,'Considering a career as a nurse practitioner? Attend a zoom call information session about UCF\'s BSN to DNP doctoral programs.','considering-a-career-as-a-nurse-practitioner-attend-a-zoom-call-information-session-about-ucfs-bsn-to-dnp-doctoral-programs','<p>Hop on a 30-minute zoom call with one of our graduate program advisors and learn about the BSN to DNP doctoral programs that prepare nurses for advanced practice:</p>\n<p>-<span> </span><a data-id=\"l-5728220312\" href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/graduate-programs/dnp/adult-gerontology-acute-care-nurse-practitioner-post-bsn/index\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">DNP: Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner</a><br>-<span> </span><a data-id=\"l-5254216347\" href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/graduate-programs/dnp/adult-gerontology-primary-care-nurse-practitioner-post-bsn/index\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">DNP: Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner</a><br>-<span> </span><a data-id=\"l-9944517371\" href=\"http://www.nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/graduate-programs/dnp/family-nurse-practitioner-post-bsn/index\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">DNP: Family Nurse Practitioner</a></p>\n<p>Zoom calls are scheduled on Dec. 19 at 3 p.m. and Dec. 20 at 10 a.m.</p>\n<p><strong>Register<span> </span><a href=\"https://www.smore.com/hkez-graduate-program-info-sessions\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Graduate Information Sessions\">HERE</a><span> </span>for call details. The Fall 2019 application deadline is Feb. 1.</strong></p>\n<p></p>','2018-12-12','2018-12-20','https://www.smore.com/hkez-graduate-program-info-sessions','College of Nursing, Office of Graduate Student Services','(407) 823-2744','gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','Tijuana Rollins, M.Ed., Academic Advising Coordinator, Graduate Studies, UCF College of Nursing','Publish',57),(2759,'Last Call: Registration ends Feb. 25 for Interprofessional Healthcare Simulation Conference on March 7-8.','ucf-is-co-hosting-a-healthcare-simulation-education-conference-on-march-7-8-at-the-college-of-nursing-registration-is-now-open','<p><strong>Interprofessional Healthcare Simulation Conference</strong><span> <br></span> <em><span>From Simulation to Innovation and Beyond </span></em> |  March 7-8, 2019<br><span> </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Pre-Conference Sessions are on the morning of March 7. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Conference Sessions are in the afternoon of March 7 and all-day on March 8.</span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><strong>Speakers</strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Keynote: Michelle L. Aebersold, PhD, RN, CHSE, FAAN, University of Michigan School of Nursing<br>Plenary: Nicole Blodgett, PhD, RN, <span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Purdue University Northwest College of Nursing</span><br>Endnote: KT Waxman, DNP, RN, CNL, CENP, CHSE, FSSH, FAAN, University of San Francisco</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">UCF College of Nursing healthcare simulation experts will lead a pre-conference workshop on <em>Simulation Development from A to Z</em>. Other speakers are experts from the National League for Nursing, <span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">UCF College of Medicine, AdventHealth, VHA SimLEARN, <span>Brandman University, Dartmouth Hitchcock Medical Center, Pacific Lutheran University, Pennsylvania College of Health Sciences, Thomas Jefferson University, </span></span>University of Maryland and University of Massachusetts-Lowell. <span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Tours of the</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> </span><a href=\"https://www.ist.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"UCF IST\">UCF Institute for Simulation and Training</a><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> will also be offered.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Who should attend</strong></p>\n<p>This is an interprofessional conference open to faculty, alumni, healthcare professionals, and current or prospective students of athletic training, audiology, healthcare systems administration, healthcare systems engineering, medicine, nursing, physical therapy, social work, speech-language pathology, and any other discipline where simulation can be used for educational purposes.</p>\n<p><strong>Theme</strong></p>\n<p>To promote excellence in simulation education and engage with a culture where innovation and transformation are embraced.</p>\n<p><span> </span><br><span> </span> <strong>Goals</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Explore innovative technologies for teaching and learning.</li>\n<li>Examine challenges in operationalizing simulation and other technologies.</li>\n<li>Discover ideas for future growth and sustainability of simulation programs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n<p>This conference is co-hosted by the National League for Nursing and the University of Central Florida College of Nursing, a division of UCF\'s Academic Health Sciences Center.</p>\n<p><strong>To learn more and to register, visit:</strong> <a href=\"https://members.nln.org/iMIS/Events/Event_Display.aspx?EventKey=20190307\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Learn more and register now!\">NLN-UCF Healthcare Simulation Conference website</a></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><strong>Sponsors</strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Platinum: Gaumard<br>Silver: CAE Healthcare, Medline, Project Concert<br>Bronze: B-Line Medical, ATI, Laerdal, <span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Shadow Health, EMS</span><br>Grant support: UCF Office of Research <br>Coffee and Cookies with Avkin</p>','2019-02-21','2019-02-26','https://members.nln.org/iMIS/Events/Event_Display.aspx?EventKey=20190307','College of Nursing','(407) 823-2744','laura.gonzalez@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing','Publish',57),(2760,'USPS Employee of the Month - November 2018','usps-employee-of-the-month-november-2018','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for November 2018: Aristotle Fidel Fernandez. Mr. Fernandez is the Senior Clerk at the Postal Services Operations in Facilities. He has worked for UCF since December 1995 – 23 years! Mike Jackson and Hector Cardona, who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues, had this to say about him:</p>\n<p><em>“Fidel comes to work with a positive attitude daily and is always helping others before himself. He gets multiple jobs done while exceeding expectations. He keys in hundreds of UCF departmental packages sorts thousands of letters and makes sure the mail is delivered to the correct department. He is a model of the type of employee we strive to have at UCF Postal Services.”   </em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Aristotle received a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, his name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to President Whittaker. He is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2018-12-14','2018-12-28','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2761,'UCF Omicron Delta Kappa Society','ucf-omicron-delta-kappa-society','<p>The Omicron Delta Kappa Society is the national leadership honor society for college students, faculty, staff, administrators, and alumni that recognizes and encourages superior scholarship, leadership, and exemplary character.</p>\n<p>The student and faculty members of Omicron Delta Kappa work closely together to foster leadership abilities within its members. The organization is also dedicated to a variety of projects that benefit the university and the surrounding community.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements for induction into the </strong><strong>Central Florida Circle of ODK:</strong></p>\n<p>Class standing: Junior (at least 60 credits), Senior, or Graduate Level</p>\n<p>Minimum GPA: 3.2 for undergraduates, 3.5 for graduate students</p>\n<p>The initiation fee of $95-includes lifetime membership and pin (graduation cords may be purchased for an additional $25). If accepted your dues will be due by 3/20/19 at 12:00 PM. The induction will be held on Thursday, 4/4/19 at 4 pm in Ferrell Commons 165-LEAD Scholars Academy</p>\n<p>Demonstrated leadership in at least two of the five areas:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Scholarship</li>\n<li>Athletics</li>\n<li>Campus/Community Service, Social/Religious Activities, and Campus Government</li>\n<li>Journalism, Speech and the Mass Media</li>\n<li>Creative and Performing Arts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply:</strong></p>\n<p>Visit our website at <u><a href=\"https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form</a></u> to complete the online application.</p>\n<p>Questions may be directed to <a href=\"mailto:stacey.malaret@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Stacey Malaret</a>, Faculty Secretary for ODK, in the LEAD Scholars Academy Office, Ferrell Commons 165.</p>\n<p><strong>Online application deadline is </strong><strong>3/6/19</strong></p>','2018-12-18','2019-03-06','https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-3942','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',8),(2762,'USPS Employee of the Month - November Aristotle Fidel Fernandez','usps-employee-of-the-month-november-aristotle-fidel-fernandez','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for November 2018: Aristotle Fidel Fernandez. Mr. Fernandez is the Senior Clerk at the Postal Services Operations in Facilities.  He has worked for UCF since December 1995 – 23 years! Mike Jackson and Hector Cardona, who took the time to acknowledge his excellent efforts among their colleagues, had this to say about him:</p>\n<p><em>“Fidel comes to work with a positive attitude daily and is always helping others before himself.  He gets multiple jobs done while exceeding expectations. He keys in hundreds of UCF departmental packages, sorts thousands of letters and makes sure the mail is delivered to the correct department.  He is a model of the type of employee we strive to have at UCF Postal Services.”   </em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Aristotle received a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, his name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to President Whittaker. He is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff.  We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2019-01-04','2019-01-11','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2766,'B.L.A.C.K. Institute (Building Leaders And Connecting Knights) Registration NOW OPEN, Register TODAY','black-institute-building-leaders-and-connecting-knights-registration-now-open-register-today-1-2-3','<p>Registration is NOW OPEN for the B.L.A.C.K. Institute (Building Leaders And Connecting Knights). REGISTER NOW at<span> </span><a href=\"http://bit.ly/BLACKInstitute\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/BLACKInstitute</a><span> </span>(case sensitive).</p>\n<p>The<span> </span><span>Building Leaders And Connecting Knights (B.L.A.C.K.) Institute</span><span> </span>is a culturally specific leadership development program for the Black student population at UCF. Attendees of the B.L.A.C.K. Institute will engage in small group discussions,<span> </span>panel<span> </span>led dialogues and other experiential activities; as well as have opportunities to meet with UCF leadership, faculty and staff that reflect their cultural identity.</p>\n<p>Participants of the B.L.A.C.K. Institute will complete the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Connect with the UCF Institution</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Connect with the UCF community and their cultural identity</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Gain an understanding of their purpose within the UCF community</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>**Check in<span> </span>begins at<span> </span>12:30pm.<span> </span>Program begins at 1pm and concludes at 5:00pm**</strong></p>','2019-01-07','2019-01-21','http://bit.ly/BLACKInstitute','Melissa Comeau','(407) 823-2811','melissa.comeau@ucf.edu','UCF CAPS','Publish',140),(2769,'USPS Staff Council scholarship available!','usps-staff-council-scholarship-available','<p>The USPS Staff Council is now accepting applications for the Spring 2019 Scholarship awards. Apply now at the Staff Council web site, (<a href=\"http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/</a>) or on the Council Facebook page. There are many awards up for grabs and there are some awards for dependents available as well.  Applications must be in by 11:59 p.m. January 15th, 2019. The only restriction is you must be a member of the USPS for a minimum of one year, and if you have won this award you must wait one year before applying for it again. Apply now and avoid the rush!</p>','2019-01-04','2019-01-15','http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/','Jamie Lamoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie LaMoreaux','Publish',54),(2770,'USPS Employee of the Month - December Susan Sumser','usps-employee-of-the-month-december-susan-sumser','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for December 2018: Susan Sumser. Susan is the Program Assistant in the Immunization Department of Health Services. Kimberly Thrash and Donovan Williams, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>“Since Sue took over the position in 2016, she has set the bar for program management. She successfully completed 56 orientations, ensuring the lowest number possible of incompletes, processing 14,856 incoming and transfer students. Her customer service is outstanding, she can be counted on to always follow through and find the answers to any questions. It is because of professionals like you, with that personal touch, that makes UCF such an amazing university.</em></p>\n<p><em>Sue wholeheartedly exudes the UCF core values of Integrity, Scholarship, Community, Creativity and Excellence.” </em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Susan receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to President Whittaker. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2019-01-09','2019-01-15','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2771,'Community Flood Risk Management Workshop','community-flood-risk-management-workshop','<p><span>This National Science Foundation (NSF)-sponsored workshop will bring researchers, practitioners, and students together to discuss the challenges associated with mitigating flood hazards, current developments in the field of community flood risk management, and ideas on how to improve communities’ resilience to future flood disasters. </span></p>\n<p><span>The workshop will take place on Thursday, February 28, 2019 from 9:00 am to 1:00 pm at the Live Oaks Center at UCF. Lunch will be provided for workshop attendees.  </span></p>\n<p><span>For more information and to reserve your seat, please visit: <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/community-flood-risk-management-workshop-tickets-53810806571\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/community-flood-risk-management-workshop-tickets-53810806571</a>. </span></p>','2019-01-10','2019-02-26','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/community-flood-risk-management-workshop-tickets-53810806571','Jenna Tyler','','jentyler@knights.ucf.edu','Jenna Tyler','Publish',145),(2772,'Considering a master\'s degree in nursing? Attend a zoom call to learn about our Leadership & Management MSN program.','considering-a-masters-degree-in-nursing-attend-a-zoom-call-to-learn-about-our-leadership-management-msn-program','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Hop on a 30-minute Zoom Call with one of our graduate program advisors and learn about the online Leadership &amp; Management MSN program that prepares nurses for leadership roles:</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">- <a href=\"http://nursing.ucf.edu/admissions/graduate-programs/msn/leadership-management/index\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\">Leadership &amp; Management MSN</a></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Register</span><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"> </span><a href=\"https://www.smore.com/hkez-graduate-program-info-sessions\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Graduate Information Sessions\">HERE</a><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"> </span><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">for call details. The Fall 2019 application deadline is April 1.</span></p>','2019-01-28','2019-01-28','https://www.smore.com/hkez-graduate-program-info-sessions','Tijuana Rollins, M.Ed.','(407) 823-2647','gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','Tijuana Rollins, M.Ed., Academic Advising Coordinator, Graduate Studies, UCF College of Nursing','Publish',57),(2776,'Legacy Pointe at UCF  - New Campaign!','legacy-pointe-at-ucf-new-campaign-1','<p>Everyone is invited to the exclusive viewing of the UCF Promise campaign of Legacy Pointe at UCF.   The presentation is in the Fairwinds Alumni Center on January 22nd from 4pm - 6pm.  Light hour devours will be served.  </p>\n<p>Come hear about the progress of the only university-based senior living community in Central Florida and see the new UCF Promise campaign that will be airing on TV and in newspapers locally.</p>\n<p>Dr. Abe Pizam of the Rosen College of Hospitality will be the master of ceremonies and will be sharing about the integration of the project with the UCF Colleges.</p>\n<p>Certain floor plans have sold out, so you won’t want to miss this opportunity to hear about Legacy Pointe;  for yourself, your parents, or your friends.</p>','2019-01-10','2019-01-23','http://www.legacypointeatucf.com','Zan Reynolds','(407) 739-6498','zreynolds@me.com','Zan Reynolds','Publish',147),(2778,'Hack@UCF - The Collegiate Cyber Defense Club @ UCF','hackucf-the-collegiate-cyber-defense-club-ucf','<p>If you\'re interested in cybersecurity, come and learn with us.  <span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">The Collegiate Cyber Defense Club @ UCF meets every </span><strong>Friday at 4:30 PM in BA 119</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> during the academic year.  </span>We offer workshops that teach various security topics from the ground up.  Our competitive teams, such as our three-time national champion CCDC Team, participate in many security competitions each year which often involve travel and prizes.  We look forward to seeing you!  Visit <a href=\"https://hackucf.org/blog\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hackucf.org</a> for more information on the club and sign up for the club mailing list.  </p>','2019-01-15','2019-04-19','https://hackucf.org','David Maria','','dmaria@hackucf.org','Thomas Nedorost','Publish',144),(2779,'UCF to Host Telescope Night for 1st Total Lunar Eclipse of 2019','ucf-to-host-telescope-night-for-1st-total-lunar-eclipse-of-2019','<p>Pack a blanket, bring some snacks and head to UCF’s Memory Mall on Sunday, Jan. 20, for a front-row seat of 2019’s first total lunar eclipse.</p>\n<p>The observatory, the library, and the student-run Astronomy Society are hosting the free public event on the main campus to give the community an opportunity to take it all in. Telescopes and volunteers will be ready to help the public find the best view of the moon and answer questions.</p>\n<p>To learn more, visit <a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-host-telescope-night-1st-total-lunar-eclipse-2019/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">today.ucf.edu/ucf-host-telescope-night-1st-total-lunar-eclipse-2019</a>.</p>','2019-01-16','2019-01-21','https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-host-telescope-night-1st-total-lunar-eclipse-2019/','UCF Planetary Sciences Group','(407) 823-2325','planets@planets.ucf.edu','UCF Observatory','Publish',35),(2780,'Attend This Week’s UCF Science Cafe on Ultrafast Photonics','attend-this-weeks-ucf-science-cafe-on-ultrafast-photonics','<p><span>Peter Delfyett, Ph.D.</span></p>\n<p><span>January 17, 2019<br></span>University Trustee Chair<br>Pegasus Professor of Optics &amp; Photonics, ECE, and Physics<br>Director of the Townes Laser Institute<br>College of Optics and Photonics<br>University of Central Florida</p>\n<p><strong>Time:</strong><span> </span>Networking, drinks and appetizers at 6:30 p.m. and talk begins at 7:00 p.m.</p>\n<p><strong>Location:</strong><span> </span><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Physical+Sciences+Building,+Orlando,+FL+32816/@28.5998675,-81.2001849,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x88e7685cdbf90435:0x4919b39016a397b!8m2!3d28.5998675!4d-81.1979962\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Physical Sciences Building 160/161</a></p>\n<p>The development of high speed communication, interconnects and signal processing are critical for an information based economy.  Lightwave technologies offer the promise of high bandwidth connectivity from component development that is manufacturable, cost effective, and electrically efficient.</p>\n<p>This presentation will highlight our research in the generation of stabilized frequency combs, and in developing approaches for filtering, modulating and detecting individual comb components.  We then show how these technologies can be applied in signal processing applications such as arbitrary waveform generation, arbitrary waveform measurement, laser radar and matched filtering for pattern recognition.</p>\n<p>To RSVP, visit <a href=\"https://sciences.ucf.edu/cafe/ultrafast-photonics/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">sciences.ucf.edu/cafe/ultrafast-photonics</a>.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>','2019-01-16','2019-01-18','https://sciences.ucf.edu/cafe/ultrafast-photonics/','Judy Froehlich','(407) 823-0446','judy.froehlich@ucf.edu','Judy Froehlich','Publish',35),(2781,'UCF Students Encouraged to Apply Now for Scholarships A2O','scholarships-a2o-has-scholarships-available-for-students-to-apply','<p>The Scholarships A2O system is available for students to complete the General Application and apply for scholarship opportunities. There will be some scholarships for the current 2018-19 year but a lot of these scholarships will be for the 2019-20 year which will be fall 2019, spring 2020 and summer 2020. </p>\n<p>We encourage all current and incoming UCF students to complete the General Application.  Then please check the system at least once a week to look for applying to scholarships that may be available to apply for and also to look at the External Scholarships which are outside opportunities that students may qualify to apply.  Once selections are made students will have the option to accept offered scholarships.</p>\n<p>Receipt of scholarship funding can reduce the need for loans and can assist with other educational expenses.  </p>\n<p>Thank you</p>','2019-01-21','2019-02-28','http://ucf.academicworks.com/','Jamey Walker','(407) 823-5030','jamey.walker@ucf.edu','Jamey Walker, UCF Student Financial Assistance','Publish',58),(2783,'Knights for Knights Ambassadors,, a Hazing Prevention and Education Program','knights-for-knights-ambassadors-a-hazing-prevention-and-education-program','<p>We are looking for students who are interested in learning more about hazing prevention and education. These students will also be working with various campus partners and organizations in order to raise awareness and educate our UCF community on hazing prevention. Students will gain valuable leadership and various skills through the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Peer to peer education</li>\n<li>Programming presentations &amp; events</li>\n<li>Marketing &amp; networking</li>\n<li>Helping to plan the annual SUS Hazing Summit... and more!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Those who are interested should <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fucf.us12.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D186300af03c6e5c8814d03b70%26id%3Da13d463b14%26e%3De0a7474caf&amp;data=02%7C01%7CStacey.Malaret%40ucf.edu%7C0e812b23621945ac271808d67d7592e3%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636834341335823709&amp;sdata=T0iJs0%2BeowZDVgodDXAuWlrnmXvXvtjXpRx4YlbRgUg%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">apply here</a>. Applications close on January 25th!</p>','2019-01-18','2019-01-25','https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7X2CAjYq2fBvVR3','Gabrielle Bell','(407) 823-2223','gabrielle.bell2@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret, LEAD Scholars Academy','Publish',8),(2784,'Heartfulness Meditation Workshop','heartfulness-meditation-workshop','<p>Looking for a way of self-improvement?</p>\n<p>How to simplify your thoughts, letting go of stress? How do one make wiser choice?</p>\n<p>How can one develop confidence and balance from within?</p>\n<p>Come join us for our first practical session of the semester to learn how Heartfulness Meditation can help achieve it. </p>','2019-01-18','2019-01-22','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1190144/heartfulness-meditation-start-your-year-off-right/','Nitesh Dhasmana','(321) 945-4322','heartfulness.ucf@gmail.com','A Heartfulness Meditation Experience','Pending',37),(2785,'Spring 2019 Scholarship Awards','spring-2019-scholarship-awards','<p>The USPS Staff Council is now accepting applications for the Spring 2019 Scholarship awards.  Apply now at the Staff Council web site, (<a href=\"http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/</a>) or on the Council Facebook page.  The application must be in by 11:59 p.m. January 31st 2019.  You must be a member of the USPS for a minimum of one year. </p>','2019-01-22','2019-01-31','','Jamie LaMoreaux','(407) 882-0191','Jamie.LaMoreaux@ucf.edu','Cissy Glowth - USPS Staff Council - President','Publish',107),(2786,'Up to Us: Exclusive Civic Leadership Opportunity','up-to-us-exclusive-civic-leadership-opportunity','<p>Since its inception in 2012, more than 1,000 emerging leaders have participated in the Up to Us Competition and have gone on to work at think tanks like the Bipartisan Policy Center, U.S. Department of Education, Goldman Sachs, and more. You have the opportunity to join the brightest changemakers across the nation in addressing the challenges facing our fiscal and economic future.<br><br>It\'s simple to participate. Form a team on campus, design events engaging your peers on the national debt and fiscal issues, and receive:<br>-Resume building leadership and campaign management training<br>-An all-expenses-paid trip to Northern California<br>-$1,000 in funding to turn your ideas into action<br>-A chance to win a $10,000 grand prize<br>-Exclusive paid internship opportunities<br><br>Apply at the link below or email Bailey Greene, <a href=\"mailto:bgreene@netimpact.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">bgreene@netimpact.org</a>, for more information. The program is from February 5 – April 12.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.itsuptous.org/get-involved/campus-competition/competition\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.itsuptous.org/get-involved/campus-competition/competition</a></p>','2019-01-23','2019-02-01','http://www.itsuptous.org/get-involved/campus-competition','Mike McFadden','(407) 823-6957','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Mike McFadden','Publish',52),(2787,'Research Administration Graduate Programs - Online Open House','research-administration-graduate-programs-online-open-house','<p>Join us for a 30-minute information session to learn about the <strong>completely online</strong> research administration graduate programs at UCF. In this session, we\'ll discuss the program options, application requirements, and how the Master of Research Administration or Research Administration Graduate Certificate can take your career to the next level. More information about our programs can be found at <a href=\"http://ucf.edu/online/degree/research-administration-m-r-a\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">ucf.edu/online/degree/research-administration-m-r-a</a>. </p>','2019-01-24','2019-01-30','https://applynow.graduate.ucf.edu/register/JanUCFMRA','Angela White-Jones','(407) 823-5786','angela.white-jones@ucf.edu','Yasmyn Chambers','Publish',155),(2788,'Public Administration Research Conference','public-administration-research-conference','<p><span>The 13th Annual UCF Public Administration Conference, </span><em>Evidence-Based Policymaking: Using Big Data to Evaluate Public Sector Innovation and Improve Organizational Performance,</em><span> will be held at the UCF </span><em>FAIRWINDS</em><span> Alumni Center on Friday, March 1, 2019. Academics, practitioners, and students are invited to participate in robust conversation. On February 28, please join us for pre-conference activities with our keynote speaker Dr. Gary R. VanLandingham, Professor and Reubin O’D. Askew Senior Practitioner in Residence, Florida State University.</span></p>','2019-01-24','2019-02-28','https://public-administration-research-conference-ucf.eventbrite.com/','Maria-Elena Augustin','(407) 823-3794','maria.augustin@ucf.edu','Yasmyn Chambers','Publish',155),(2789,'Inaugural College Night at UCF Men\'s Basketball Game','inaugural-college-night-at-ucf-mens-basketball-game','<p>UCF Men’s Basketball will hold its inaugural <a href=\"https://healthprofessions.ucf.edu/csd/wp-content/uploads/sites/23/2019/01/mbb_vs_houston_chps_updated.jpg\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">College Night</a> at its game on Thursday, Feb. 7, at 7 p.m. at the CFE Arena — and the <a href=\"healthprofessions.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">College of Health Professions and Sciences </a>will be the featured college.</p>\n<p>The team will play the University of Houston. </p>\n<p>\"CHPS Night\" will feature 1) an on-court recognition, 2) a video and facts on the scoreboard, 3) an information table with hosts, 4) groups seating for the college\'s faculty and staff, and 5) a suite for honored guests.</p>\n<p>Tickets are FREE for students. Sign up <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.UCFStudentTix.com&amp;data=02%7C01%7CKaren.Guin%40ucf.edu%7Cb2b566c8044b453f953108d68072ac9b%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636837627336120572&amp;sdata=XBRLJYfkeXLGhT05ayvKLxjB8US%2BJ9EM2zE53rLdBC8%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.UCFStudentsTix.com</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"Learn more\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a></p>','2019-02-06','2019-02-01','https://healthprofessions.ucf.edu/csd/wp-content/uploads/sites/23/2019/01/mbb_vs_houston_chps_updated.jpg','Karen Guin','(407) 823-1270','karen.guin@ucf.edu','Karen Guin','Publish',157),(2790,'Announcing the I Am UCF Scholarship Showcase winners','announcing-the-i-am-ucf-scholarship-showcase-winners','<p>On Thursday, January 24th, the I Am UCF project held its first Scholarship Showcase,<span> </span>with $2000 total in scholarships to students who had submitted personal digital stories to the I Am UCF project. Of the 50+ videos published on<span> </span><a href=\"https://iamucf.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://iamucf.cah.ucf.edu/</a>, 15 were selected for the competition. We are pleased to announce our winners! </p>\n<p>Alumni Category: Ximena Gonzalez (Theatre)<br>Peer Choice Award: Lucas Camusso (Film) <br>3rd Place: Tanesha Bridenback (Theatre) <br>2nd Place: Christina Chung (Psychology)<br>1st Place: Lucas Camusso</p>\n<p>A special thank you to UCF\'s Quality Enhancement Plan, whose generosity funded the 2018-2019 I Am UCF program and scholarship, and to the CAH Dean\'s Office for sponsoring the catering for the event. </p>','2019-01-28','2019-02-28','https://iamucf.cah.ucf.edu/','Elizabeth Horn','(770) 769-2442','elizabeth.horn@ucf.edu','I Am UCF','Publish',159),(2793,'Webinar: The Value of Colleges and Universities: How to Use ROI to Survive and Thrive in Turbulent Economic Times','webinar-the-value-of-colleges-and-universities-how-to-use-roi-to-survive-and-thrive-in-turbulent-economic-times','<p>Friday, Feb 1, 11:30AM EST</p>\n<p>In this free 30-minute webinar, Return on Investment (ROI) authority Dr. Jack Phillips will demonstrate how the ROI Methodology is being used to transform universities, empowering them to not only survive in difficult times but to thrive and succeed.  Presented in cooperation with UCF Continuing Education by the ROI Institute - the #1 source for measuring return on investment for projects, programs, and initiatives.</p>\n<p>Register now at: <a href=\"https://goo.gl/sJiWcW\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://goo.gl/sJiWcW</a></p>\n<p>To join the audio conference only, call 415-655-0002, access code: 666 035 153</p>','2019-01-29','2019-02-02','https://goo.gl/sJiWcW','UCF Continuing Education','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',32),(2801,'USPS Employee of the Month - January 2019 Liara Maharaj','usps-employee-of-the-month-january-2019-liara-maharaj','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for January 2019: Liara Maharaj. Liara is the Accountant in Business Services and splits her time between the Business Services Office and the CARD office on Campus. Liara has worked at UCF since 2008. Jenna Capps and Kevin Sowers, who took the time to acknowledge her excellent efforts, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>“Liara accepted a location change for her position with the assignment of taking on additional responsibilities. She now has more direct involvement with the campus community and meets the challenge every day. Everyone knows they can count on her to be accurate in her work, passionate about the students, vendors and employees she helps daily. While balancing her job duties, she earned her MBA at UCF. </em></p>\n<p><em>Liara displays a positive attitude and consistently works to further her department goals. She supports the university’s goals by staying active in financial management improvements and diversity initiatives.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Liara receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to President Whittaker. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <span><a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></span></p>','2019-01-30','2019-02-13','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources Department','Publish',23),(2802,'Opening Reception - Healing Art Exhibition','opening-reception-healing-art-exhibition','<p>Thriving: Ongoing Evolution and Growth</p>\n<p>Please join us for the fifth annual UCF Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS) collaboration with the School of Visual Arts and Design to create UCF Healing Art Exhibition that will showcase artworks by UCF students, faculty, staff and alumni. The UCF Healing Art Exhibition\'s mission is designed to create campus-wide awareness of the power between arts and healing, to increase inclusivity across campus, and to create an open exhibition space for creativity in a healing environment. We welcome you to honor our artists who have been transformed by the healing power of creativity to inspire others to do the same.</p>\n<p>The Exhibition will be held at CAPS (building 27) on 02/13/2019 from 5:30pm to 7 pm.</p>','2019-02-01','2019-02-13','http://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/art/','Kavita Sawh','(407) 823-2811','ksawh@ucf.edu','Kavita Sawh','Publish',161),(2803,'CAPS to Host Leadership Development Program Feb. 28','black-institute-1','<p>The<span> </span><span>Building Leaders And Connecting Knights (B.L.A.C.K.) Institute</span><span> </span>is a culturally specific leadership development program for the Black student population at UCF. Hosted by Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS). Attendees of the B.L.A.C.K. Institute will engage in small group discussions, panel led dialogues and other experiential activities; as well as have opportunities to meet with UCF leadership, faculty and staff that reflect their cultural identity.</p>\n<p>Participants of the B.L.A.C.K. Institute will complete the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Connect with the UCF Institution</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Connect with the UCF community and their cultural identity</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Gain an understanding of their purpose within the UCF community</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>**Check in begins at 12:30. Program begins at 1 and concludes at 5:00**</strong></p>\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Date And Time</strong></p>\n<p>Thu, February 28, 2019</p>\n<p>1:00 PM – 5:00 PM EST</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Location</strong></p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida</p>\n<p>12789 E Plaza Dr, Orlando, FL 32816</p>\n<p>Cypress Room</p>\n<p>Orlando, FL 32816</p>','2019-02-04','2019-02-28','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/black-institute-building-leaders-and-connecting-knights-registration-48251015085?ref=elink','Melissa Comeau','(407) 823-2811','melissa.comeau@ucf.edu','Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS)','Publish',162),(2808,'Drum Your Stress Away at CAPS','drum-your-stress-away-at-caps-1-2-3-4','<p>Experience the power of music to help you lower stress, increase relaxation skills, build intrapersonal support and discover your personal rhythm. In this workshop, you will use drums* to express yourself by engaging in an<span> </span>evidence-based program to increase overall wellness. Come to one, two, or all three workshops.</p>\n<p>Arrive up to 15 minutes prior to start time to sign up at the front desk.</p>\n<p>* No musical experience necessary. Drums will be provided.</p>\n<p>Tuesday, February 19, 12-1 PM</p>','2019-02-19','2019-02-19','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1171700/drum-your-stress-away/','Christine Dassow','(407) 823-2811','christine.dassow@ucf.edu','Christine Dassow','Publish',170),(2809,'How to Have Healthy Relationships: Serving Your Partner Without Codependency','how-to-have-healthy-relationships-serving-your-partner-without-codependency','<p><span><strong>Looking for something to do on Valentine\'s Day</strong> because<br>1. You\'re Single <br>2. You\'re broke (like us)<br>3. It\'s on a Thursday so who goes out anyways?</span></p>\n<p><span>Well, join H2O on Thursday, February 14th at 8pm for a night of <em>practical relationship discussion!</em></span></p>\n<p><span>Our Campus Director, Jim, will be talking about how to Love others WELL! How to be healthy in love and life for not only others but for yourself!! He\'s been <strong>married for 25 years</strong> and he and his wife have mentored countless men and women in this area!! Seriously... they are experts.</span></p>\n<p><span>We will have<strong> Panera pastries</strong> (gotta have the sweets on V-Day), warm hearts, and some practical, life-building discussion! Come celebrate Love with us!</span></p>\n<p><strong>Visit our <a href=\"http://www.h2ocollege.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">website</a> or follow us on Instagram!! @h2ocollege</strong></p>','2019-02-14','2019-02-14','http://www.h2ocollege.org','Savannah Zona','(561) 235-9586','savannahzona@knights.ucf.edu','Savannah Zona','Publish',103),(2810,'H2O Game Nights!','h2o-game-nights','<p><span>Every Friday Night (yes.. every Friday) at Ron and David\'s house its GAME NIGHT! It\'s an awesome time of Nerf gun fights, board games, role playing games, and overall FUN! Invite friends! There is food (like chili and rice perhaps... Ron loves to cook) and games and good times. Carpools are available. Message us for details on getting there!</span></p>','2019-02-07','2019-07-26','http://www.h2ocollege.org','Savannah Zona','(561) 235-9586','savannahzona@knights.ucf.edu','Savannah Zona','Publish',103),(2811,'CAPS and SVAD to host Healing Art Exhibition- Opening Reception','caps-and-svad-to-host-healing-art-exhibition-opening-reception','<p>Join UCF Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS) and the School of Visual Arts and Design (SVAD) for a collaborative annual healing art exhibition that celebrates the powerful connection between art and wellness. The exhibition will showcase artworks by UCF students, faculty, staff, and alumni. </p>\n<p>Opening Reception: Wednesday, February 13th 5:30-7 PM.<br>Location: Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS)<br><span>Refreshments, live music, awards, and artwork tour</span></p>\n<p>Let’s celebrate the healing power of art! All are welcome to attend.</p>\n<p></p>','2019-02-08','2019-02-14','https://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/art','Meredith Malkin','(407) 823-2811','Meredith.Malkin@ucf.edu','Meredith Malkin','Publish',163),(2812,'Happening Now: Leadership Week 2019','leadership-week-2019','<p><strong><span>The<a href=\"https://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/)\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></span></strong><a href=\"https://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/)\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><span>19th Annual Leadership Week</span></strong></a><strong><span> at UCF is approaching fast so mark your calendars for February 18-22! </span></strong><span>Leadership Week is an initiative coordinated by LEAD Scholars Academy and supported by the UCF Student Government Association and numerous offices and departments throughout the university. <br></span><span><br>Leadership Week was created to identify, recognize, and develop leadership throughout UCF. It is a week of lectures, programs, events, and workshops intended to educate the campus community. Students, faculty, and staff are invited to attend all events.<br></span><span><br>During Leadership Week there are many opportunities to learn and develop skills for leaders. In addition to the keynote speakers, there are workshops and educational meetings on a variety of topics related to leadership development and social change. This year, we have two </span><span>available </span><span>tracks; UCF Cares &amp; Hazing Prevention &amp; Education. <br></span><span><br>Please see our website (</span><a data-auth=\"NotApplicable\" href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Flsa.sdes.ucf.edu%2Fleadershipweek%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CStacey.Malaret%40ucf.edu%7C4460d52bd300427e83d508d68be5b657%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636850216065410059&amp;sdata=VDniFQCMRodI4dsw88cMVVGu1shaJILGqXiEylvKSJc%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><span>https://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/</span></a><span>) for more details, information on our keynote speakers, and our calendar. We hope to see you soon!<br></span><span><br><strong>Have any questions?</strong></span><strong><span> </span></strong><span>If you have any questions, please e-mail <a data-auth=\"NotApplicable\" href=\"mailto:taylor.zeigler@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">taylor.zeigler@ucf.edu</a> or <a data-auth=\"NotApplicable\" href=\"mailto:taylor.zeigler@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">zariawoods@knights.ucf.edu</a>.  </span></p>','2019-02-11','2019-02-23','https://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/leadershipweek/','Taylor Zeigler','(407) 823-2223','taylor.zeigler@ucf.edu','Taylor Zeigler','Publish',171),(2814,'Discounted tickets for UCF Celebrates the Arts available with UCF ID','join-us-for-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-at-dr-phillips-center-for-the-performing-arts','<p>Tickets for the 5th annual UCF Celebrates the Arts at Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts will be available starting at <strong>noon on February 21</strong>. The festival runs April 5-14, 2019 and showcases performers and artists from across the university.</p>\n<p>UCF students, faculty and staff can receive discounted or free tickets for many events (reservation deadline is April 5). Valid UCF ID is required. Ticket prices range from free to $50.</p>\n<p>Three ways to get your tickets:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Online at <a href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.arts.ucf.edu&amp;data=02%7C01%7CVictoria.Weston%40ucf.edu%7C35f2800d22c04c3e13a408d6976562be%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636862859032658936&amp;sdata=Si0D%2FdLbZmnUojc%2FiDsTG9kKM4HtFJ4Ie0Aelf5os%2Fw%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.arts.ucf.edu</a>.</li>\n<li>In person at the UCF School of Performing Arts Box Office.</li>\n<li>Via phone: 407-823-1500</li>\n</ol>\n<p><br> Events include performances of the musical <em>Titanic, </em>art installations, talks by novelist Emily St. John Mandel and architect Christian Hoenigschmid, a concert by the Flying Horse Big Band, opera, large and chamber ensemble concerts, films, and more. See the full schedule and reserve tickets at <a href=\"http://arts.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">arts.ucf.edu</a>.  </p>','2019-04-08','2019-04-14','https://arts.cah.ucf.edu/','UCF School of Performing Arts Box Office','(407) 823-1500','boxoffice@ucf.edu','Victoria Weston','Publish',10),(2815,'Open House for UCF Downtown to be Held Feb. 13','open-house-for-ucf-downtown-to-be-held-feb-13','<p><span>Any UCF student is welcome to attend an open house for UCF Downtown on Feb. 13 from 2-6 p.m. on the UCF main campus in the Student Union\'s Pegasus Ballroom. Learn more about the academic programs and services that will be offered at UCF Downtown, which is set to open in Fall 2019. You\'ll also have the chance to view pictures of the new campus and new downtown residence hall. Students will receive free giveaways, food, drinks and more.</span></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ucf-downtown-open-house-registration-53405870396\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register now</a> and enter to win prizes including a free annual UCF parking permit!</span></p>\n<p><span>Presented in partnership with the College of Community Innovation and Education and Nicholson School of Communication and Media.</span></p>','2019-02-11','2019-02-12','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1178015/ucf-downtown-open-house/','Jamie Giller','(407) 823-2474','ucfdowntown@ucf.edu','Jenna Lee','Publish',165),(2817,'Black History Month 2019 presents the Stage Reading of \"In The Midst of Metal Clouds\"','black-history-month-2019-presents-the-stage-reading-of-in-the-midst-of-metal-clouds-1','<p><em>In the Midst of Metal Clouds</em><span> </span>is the story of a survivor of police brutality, a police officer, and a prosecutor are forever changed during the trial of a century as they struggle to understand their shared destiny, trauma, healing and roles as Black people in America. The play addresses the realities, known and unknown, of being Black in America from a millennial perspective and was written and directed by UCF students and alumni. Following the theatrical protest there will be a talk-back about topics addressed during the reading. Come and be a part of our journey for Black History Month on Sunday, February 24 at 6:30 p.m. in the Pegasus Ballroom.  </p>\n<p><em>Register for the event here: <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/in-the-midst-of-metal-clouds-free-ticket-tickets-48131575839\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/in-the-midst-of-metal-clouds-free-ticket-tickets-48131575839</a></em></p>','2019-02-13','2019-02-24','','Kelsey Jay','','kelsey.j@knights.ucf.edu','Kelsey Jay','Publish',174),(2818,'RSVP for Chabad Jewish Student Group\'s Mega Shabbat','mega-shabbat','<p><span>Mega Shabbat</span><br><span>A Knight of Jewish Unity</span><br><span>Friday, February 22, 2019</span><br><br><span>5:30PM - Mix Mingle &amp; Appetizers</span><br><span>6:00PM - Shabbat Candle Lighting Ceremony</span><br><span>6:30PM - Shabbat Dinner </span><br><br><span>Pegasus Ballroom, UCF Student Union</span><br><br><span>Don\'t miss out. The people... the food... the vibes...</span><br><span>There is nothing more magical than a room with hundreds of JewCF Knights all celebrating Shabbat together. </span></p>\n<p><span>It\'s a once in a lifetime experience....and truly the Jewish event of the year.</span><br><br><span>You must RSVP here! Clicking going on FB is not enough!</span><br><a data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jewishucf.com%2Fshabbat%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR36e0jocBdmJiGZUppA3T015rUweadG5suzAuSaeXWi0ViX9IQLcT0Ie-o&amp;h=AT3VIo1wXMzQV9T_Q1-BYZ0ABGoI0F4ZWNuQAznJh8Lj4T_xoIvAHfmA5WE9IgmIbnz58QquxzZxSIqcHCVNtdUI33yPiqM4T7U7e58ScU2nT5k4LAWExWqqk0fNEfE6hUg_N7s\" href=\"http://www.jewishucf.com/shabbat?fbclid=IwAR36e0jocBdmJiGZUppA3T015rUweadG5suzAuSaeXWi0ViX9IQLcT0Ie-o\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.jewishucf.com/shabbat</a><br><br><span>This a project of</span><span> Chabad Jewish Student Group</span></p>','2019-02-12','2019-02-22','http://www.jewishucf.com/shabbat','Rivkie Lipskier','(407) 949-8732','rivkie@jewishucf.com','Chabad at UCF','Publish',175),(2820,'Clinton Global Initiative University Showcase','clinton-global-initiative-university-showcase','<p>Last year, UCF sent a total of 14 students to participate in <a href=\"http://cgiu.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">CGI U 2018</a>, representing 8 Commitments to Action. Join us on <strong>Thursday, February 28th from 12:00-1:00pm</strong> (SU 220 - Sand Key) to hear from some of last year\'s commitment makers about their experience and an update on their progress since the conference. There will also be two CGI U Info Sessions for students who are interested in attending CGI U 2019 (details TBA).</p>\n<p>Event schedule (subject to change):</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>11:30-12:00</strong><span> </span>- CGI U Info Session</li>\n<li><strong>12:00-1:00</strong><span> </span>- Commitment Presentations/Q&amp;A</li>\n<li><strong>1:00-1:30</strong><span> </span>- CGI U Info Session</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Building on the successful model of the<span> </span><a href=\"http://www.clintonglobalinitiative.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Clinton Global Initiative</a>, President Clinton launched the Clinton Global Initiative University (CGI U) in 2007 to engage the next generation of leaders on college campuses around the world. Each year, CGI U hosts a meeting where students, university representatives, topic experts, and celebrities come together to discuss and develop innovative solutions to pressing global challenges. Students create their own<span> </span><a href=\"https://www.clintonfoundation.org/clinton-global-initiative/meetings/cgi-university/commitments/about-cgiu-commitments\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Commitments to Action</a> that address issues on campus, in local communities, or around the world. Since 2008, students have made more than 6,250 commitments, and nearly $3 million in funding has been awarded to these commitment-makers through CGI U.</p>','2019-02-15','2019-02-28','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1203960/clinton-global-initiative-university-showcase/','Mike McFadden','(407) 823-2223','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Mike McFadden','Publish',52),(2822,'TADHack-mini Hackathon Orlando','tadhack-mini-hackathon-orlando','<p>We’re back in Orlando for TADHack-mini Orlando #3, the weekend before<span> </span><a href=\"https://www.enterpriseconnect.com/orlando?_mc=ECHACK19\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Enterprise Connect 2019!</a><span> </span>Here you can see what we got up to last year:<span> </span><a href=\"http://blog.tadhack.com/2018/03/12/tadhack-mini-orlando-2018-winners/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">TADHack-mini Orlando 2018</a>.</p>\n<p>Telecoms is now democratized so anyone can program with it. You can add programmable voice, calling, text messages (SMS and IM), audio and video messages, video calling, faxing (yep, fax still exists), secure communications and authentication, decentralized communications, mobile payments, and much much more through easy to use APIs/SDKs, and even easier to use GUIs. Programmable Telecoms is everything to do with communications between people and things that can be controlled by software (on your phone/laptop, in the cloud, or in your business).</p>\n<p>A TADHack is an event in which people (e.g. students, graphic designers, project managers, product managers, IT Managers, Enterprise Connect attendees, computer programmers, interested individuals, and subject-matter-experts) collaborate on a software project focused on programmable telecoms. You do not need to be a coder to take part.</p>\n<p>For Enterprise Connect attendees you get hands-on experience with Telecom APIs, UCaaS (Unified Communications as a Service), CCaaS (Contact Center as a Service), UC&amp;C (Unified Communications and Collaboration), and much more. For those not attending EC you get to build your portfolio of skills in programmable telecoms that will be in demand for the next decade.</p>\n<p>We encourage people who can not attend TADHack in person in Orlando to take part remotely.</p>\n<p>Winners and runners up from TADHack-mini Orlando can pitch at Enterprise Connect for even greater exposure!</p>\n<p>TADHack is all about learning, sharing, coding (you can even avoid this with some of the GUIs), creating, and most importantly having fun with a diverse group of people. And if that is not enough to entice you, we have lots of cash prizes, free entrance, and free food.</p>\n<p>Any questions just contact the organizer, Alan Quayle,<span> </span><a href=\"mailto:info@tadhack.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">info@tadhack.com</a></p>\n<p>Hope to see you there!</p>','2019-03-16','2019-03-17','https://tadhack.com/2019/mini-orlando','Alan Quayle','(908) 419-6960','info@tadhack,com','UCF Continuing Education','Publish',32),(2823,'Sigma: Theta Epsilon Chapter\'s 27th Annual Scholarship Day','sigma-theta-epsilon-chapters-27th-annual-scholarship-day','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Mark your calendars: the Theta Epsilon chapter of Sigma will be hosting its 27th Annual Nursing Scholarship Day on April 9th, 2019. </span><br><br>Their<span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> keynote speaker this year will be Nora Warshawsky, PhD, RN, NEA-BC, CNE, FAAN. Dr. Warshawsky will be presenting, “Why the nurse manager practice environment is important: Outcomes that matter!”</span><br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">The conference will be held at the DoubleTree on University Blvd near UCF.</span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><a href=\"https://bit.ly/2TXMDRA\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register Here</a></p>','2019-02-19','2019-04-09','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/sigma-theta-epsilon-chapters-27th-annual-scholarship-day-april-9-2019-tickets-54972686786?utm_source=eb_email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=new_event_email&utm_term=viewmy','Sigma: Theta Epsilon Chapter',NULL,'sttihonorsociety@ucf.edu','College of Nursing','Publish',146),(2824,'Urban and Regional Planning Distinguished Lecture Series: Does Address Determine Life Expectancy?','urban-and-regional-planning-distinguished-lecture-series-does-address-determine-life-expectancy','<p><span data-offset-key=\"7jka8-0-0\">Join the School of Public Administration for this spring\'s Urban and Regional Planning Distinguished Lecture Series, which discusses the role of community design in economic, environmental and public health. This lecture features a networking reception hosted by the Urban Knights student organization and an invigorating lecture from Mark Fenton, planning consultant and former host of the \"America’s Walking\" series on PBS.</span></p>\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"fsplm-0-0\"><br></span><span data-offset-key=\"cmmr2-0-0\"><strong>Does Address Determine Life Expectancy? The Role of Community Design in Economic, Environmental, and Public Health</strong></span></p>\n<p><span data-offset-key=\"64o0-0-0\">Professionals tell us it’s clear that Americans must be more physically active, but it’s also very clear that simply telling people to exercise is not working. Increasingly, planners, engineers, and public works departments are sought as allies in the effort to create “healthier” communities by design. In this thought-provoking and entertaining presentation, Mark Fenton will explore whether there’s any evidence that contemporary planning and design actually matters to community well-being, and the related impacts on the economic vibrancy and environmental sustainability. And he’ll share a handful of practical lessons from over two decades of simply trying to get people to walk and bicycle more.</span></p>','2019-02-20','2019-03-28','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Urban-and-Regional-Planning-Distinguished-Lecture-Series','Roberta Fennessy','(407) 823-1712','roberta.fennessy@ucf.edu','UCF School of Public Administration','Publish',155),(2827,'Eminent Scholars Lecture Series: Towards a Broader Theory of Performance Management','eminent-scholars-lecture-series-towards-a-broader-theory-of-performance-management-1-2','<p>Gary VanLandingham, Ph.D. is a distinguished professor and the Reuben Askew Senior Practitioner in Residence with the Askew School of Public Administration and Policy at Florida State University. In this talk, titled \"Towards a Broader Theory of Performance Management - Fits, Starts, and Paths Forward,\" he will discuss individual elements of the broader public management system and how better outcomes can be achieved through an integrated approach to performance management that holistically uses evidence throughout the program selection, implementation, and oversight processes.</p>','2019-02-20','2019-02-28','https://ucfparc.wordpress.com/pre-conference-activities/','Center for Public and Nonprofit Management','(407) 823-3794','cpnm@ucf.edu','Yasmyn Chambers','Publish',155),(2828,'Drum Your Stress Away at CAPS','drum-your-stress-away-at-caps','<p>Experience the power of music to help you lower stress, increase relaxation skills, build intrapersonal support and discover your personal rhythm. In this workshop, you will use drums* to express yourself by engaging in an<span> </span>evidence-based program to increase overall wellness. </p>\n<p>Arrive up to 15 minutes prior to start time to sign up at the front desk.</p>\n<p>* No musical experience necessary. Drums will be provided.</p>\n<p>Tuesday, April 16, 12 PM-1 PM</p>','2019-04-16','2019-04-16','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1171703/drum-your-stress-away/','Christine','(407) 823-2811','christine.dassow@ucf.edu','Christine Dassow','Publish',170),(2829,'Attention Seniors: Make an Impact by Helping Break UCF Record for Class Gift','attention-seniors-make-an-impact-by-helping-break-ucf-record-for-class-gift','<p><a href=\"https://ucfalumni.com/students/4ek\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">4EVER KNIGHTS</a> is hosting the 3rd annual UCF Class Gift Campaign. In two years, more than 2,200 students have made a donation to a scholarship fund, the food pantry, CAPS, research and more! We are calling on senior Knights to help break our record of 1,405 student donors and reach our goal of 1,750.</p>\n<p>All graduating Knights who <a href=\"https://www.givecampus.com/y0jtu6\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">make a Class Gift donation of $20.19</a> will receive a thank you cord to wear during their commencement ceremony. <span>Student donors will pick up their cord during cap and gown pick up week at the UCF <em>FAIRWINDS</em> Alumni Center at the end of April</span>.</p>\n<p>Any student that makes a gift of any amount or participates in a contest during the month can win the following prizes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Have Memory Mall, Reflecting Pond or Ferrell Commons named after you for a day</li>\n<li>Have the Reflecting Pond named after you for a day</li>\n<li>Be captain of the UCF squirrels for a day</li>\n<li>Be Knugget\'s *official* best friend for a day </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Questions? Email <a href=\"mailto:4EVERKNIGHTS@ucfalumni.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">4EVERKNIGHTS@ucfalumni.com</a>.</p>','2019-02-23','2019-03-01',NULL,'Latoya Jackson','(407) 882-0559','latoya.jackson@ucf.edu','4EVER KNIGHTS','Publish',165),(2830,'Free Student Bus for Wednesday\'s War On I-4','free-student-bus-for-wednesdays-war-on-i-4','<p><span>UCF Athletics will be providing a free student bus to Wednesday’s War On I-4 showdown between the Knights and the USF men’s basketball teams. The bus will depart UCF’s campus at 3:15 p.m. from the Student Union Loop.</span></p>\n<p><span>Students can pickup a voucher for the bus at the Spectrum Stadium Box Office with student ID. The transportation will be free for UCF students and includes one ticket for the 7 p.m. game at South Florida’s Yuengling Center.</span></p>\n<p><span>The bus will first stop at the first ChargeOn Tour event of 2019, which takes place from 5:30-6:30 p.m., before making its way to the game for a 7 p.m. tip. The bus will depart the arena approximately 20 minutes after the game ends in Tampa.</span></p>\n<p>The matchup between the Knights and the Bulls has major postseason implications down the final stretch of the 2018-19 season. UCF is 20-6 and 10-4 in American Athletic Conference action. With four crucial games remaining, UCF could secure its first at-large bid to the NCAA Tournament with success against USF, Houston, Cincinnati and Temple, as well as The American Championship in Memphis.</p>','2019-02-25','2019-02-27',NULL,'Alex Cesarano','(407) 823-0382','acesarano@athletics.ucf.edu','Jenna Lee','Publish',165),(2839,'Safe Knight Week Happening March 4-7','safe-knight-week-happening-march-4-7','<p>A series of interactive events starting March 4 will bring awareness to personal well-being and safety.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/safe-knight-week-starts-march-4/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Safe Knight Week</a>, which runs through March 7, is an opportunity to learn about self-care, personal safety and emergency preparedness. The goal for the week is to provide learning opportunities that will be useful to apply during UCF’s spring break (March 11-16) and in the future.</p>\n<p>A full listing of the week’s events can be accessed through the<span> </span><a href=\"https://events.ucf.edu/tag/1286708348/safe-knight-week-2019/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF events calendar</a>.</p>\n<p>Safe Knight Week 2019 is a collaboration among Wellness and Health Promotion Services; Recreation and Wellness Center; Green Dot; Student Care Services; Environmental Health and Safety; UCF Police Department; Security and Emergency Management; Student Government Association; Counseling and Psychological Services; and the Office of Institutional Equity.</p>','2019-03-03','2019-03-08','https://today.ucf.edu/safe-knight-week-starts-march-4/','Amanda Sellers','(407) 823-2833','Amanda.Sellers@ucf.edu','Jenna Lee','Publish',165),(2841,'Join the 2019 UCF & United Way Team','join-the-2019-ucf-united-way-team','<p><strong>Make a difference with us!</strong>  Each year we host a workplace giving campaign for university employees to make charitable donations through payroll deduction and other options. It is a great way for our Knight family to stand together and fight challenges facing our community.  Advocates serve in their departments and are invited to join university-level committees like special events teams, campaign marketing, and support for Boys &amp; Girls Club initiatives.</p>\n<p>You can contact us for more information at liveunited@ucf.edu or 407-823-3094.</p>\n<p>Ready to sign up as an Advocate?  <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_8ddjgqHDRFfHCRv\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register here: </a><a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_8ddjgqHDRFfHCRv\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_8ddjgqHDRFfHCRv</a> </p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>','2019-03-04','2019-04-30','http://liveunited.ucf.edu','Tee Rogers','(407) 823-3094','liveunited@ucf.edu','Tee Rogers','Publish',22),(2842,'Calling All UCF Fans to #SellOutCFE Tonight','calling-all-ucf-fans-to-selloutcfe','<p>The UCF men\'s basketball team <span>is coming off a huge win at No. 6/8 Houston that strengthened its resume for a bid to the NCAA Tournament. Now, we\'re calling on all Knights fans to help to #SellOutCFE for another big game against No. 22/23 Cincinnati on Thursday, March 7, at 7 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>Tickets for the last home game of the 2018-19 season can be purchased at <a href=\"https://www1.ticketmaster.com/ucf-knights-mens-basketball-vs-cincinnati-bearcats-mens-basketball/event/2200554AC061AAEF\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucfknights.co/selloutCFE19</a>. </span></p>\n<p><span>UCF students can claim their free tickets and purchase guest passes at <a data-expanded-url=\"http://www.ucfstudenttix.com\" href=\"https://t.co/nohRnKEJ0j\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://www.ucfstudenttix.com\">www.ucfstudenttix.com</a>. </span></p>\n<p><span>Charge On!</span></p>','2019-03-04','2019-03-07','https://ucfknights.co/selloutCFE19','Alex Cesarano','(407) 823-0382','acesarano@athletics.ucf.edu','Jenna Lee','Publish',165),(2843,'UCF to Test Emergency Communication Tools Wednesday','ucf-to-test-emergency-communication-tools-wednesday','<p>UCF’s preparations for potential emergency situations include regular tests of the communication tools that provide critical information to the UCF community.</p>\n<p>Several of those UCF Alert communication tools will be tested Wednesday, March 6.</p>\n<p>In preparation for Wednesday’s alert testing, students and faculty and staff members are encouraged to log in to<span> </span><a href=\"https://my.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">myUCF</a><span> </span>and review their UCF Alert settings to ensure that contact information (email, cell phone number, and mobile provider) is correct.</p>\n<p>A complete listing of the <span>emergency communication functions that will be tested can be found at <a href=\"https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-test-emergency-communication-tools-march/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">today.ucf.edu/ucf-test-emergency-communication-tools-march/</a>.</span></p>\n<p><span>For more information on the UCF Alert emergency communication system, visit </span><a href=\"http://www.emergency.ucf.edu/ucfalert.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.emergency.ucf.edu/ucfalert.html</a><span>.</span></p>','2019-03-04','2019-03-07','https://today.ucf.edu/ucf-test-emergency-communication-tools-march/','Amanda Sellers','(407) 823-5300','Amanda.Sellers@ucf.edu','Jenna Lee','Publish',165),(2844,'Lunch & Learn with Dr. Kim Anderson - School of Social Work, Elevate Month','lunch-learn-with-dr-kim-anderson-school-of-social-work-elevate-month','<p>Attend Dr. Kim Anderson\'s Lunch &amp; Learn on March 27 from 12:00 p.m. to 1:30 p.m. in HPA 1 - Room 304</p>\n<p>Dr. Anderson will be discussing Community-Based Participatory Research: An Example of a Collaborative Community-University Partnership for Social Change</p>\n<p>*Sanguiliano, J., *Santis, E., *Mack, R., *Sualp, K., Hissom, P., Welcome, S., &amp; Chaney, T. (*doc. students)</p>','2019-03-11','2019-03-11',NULL,'Mikita Nayee','(407) 823-3114','mikita.nayee@ucf.edu','School of Social Work','Pending',184),(2845,'Celebrate Elevate Social Work Month!','celebrate-elevate-social-work-month','<p><strong>March is Social Work Month! </strong></p>\n<p>The 2019 campaign elevates social work and highlights the impact that it has on marginalized individuals and groups. </p>\n<p>Every day this month, the School of Social Work will be posting updates on how our BSW and MSW students encapsulate the core values to empower, service, and honor disenfranchised people by providing them with the necessary resources and tools to succeed. </p>\n<p>Students &amp; Faculty can use the below hashtags to share how they are celebrating Social Work Month and may be featured in our end of the month video! </p>\n<p>#SWgetinvolved</p>\n<p>#SWmonthUCF</p>\n<p>#ElevateSWUCF</p>','2019-03-01','2019-03-31',NULL,'Mikita Nayee','(407) 823-3114','mikita.nayee@ucf.edu','School of Social Work','Publish',184),(2846,'UCF 3rd Annual Health Fair to be Held March 19','ucf-3rd-annual-health-fair','<p><strong>Tuesday, March 19, 2019 10 a.m. to 1:30 p.m.</strong></p>\n<p><span>This event aims to educate students on healthy living and healthcare practices and to raise awareness of the various health amenities available to students by UCF and within the Orlando community. This event offers the opportunity for the UCF student body to attain free health screenings (blood pressure checks, spinal alignment screenings, eye exam, etc) and information on the services provided through multiple organizations. This is a free event open to all students. The Health Fair will take place in the Key West Ballroom (on the 2nd floor) March 19 from 10am-1:30pm. Be sure to bring your friends!</span></p>\n<p><span>Check out our FB for more event information: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/UCF-Health-Fair-306961953478363/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/UCF-Health-Fair-306961953478363/</a></span></p>','2019-03-11','2019-03-19','https://www.facebook.com/UCF-Health-Fair-306961953478363/','Fatima Bawaney','(321) 609-1202','maps.vpoperations@gmail.com','Fatima Bawaney','Publish',69),(2847,'Webinar: UCF Coding Boot Camp Overview','webinar-ucf-coding-boot-camp-overview-20-mar-197pm-et','<p><span>Join us for a Coding Boot Camp Program Overview Webinar on Wednesday, March 20, at 7 p.m. ET — Powered by Trilogy Education Services.</span><br><br><span>During this informative webinar, our Admissions Team will discuss our web development program and answer some frequently asked questions. The event will last approximately one hour.</span><br><br><span>You\'ll Learn:</span><br><span>+ Why our student experience sets us apart</span><br><span>+ Our methodologies for teaching full-stack web development</span><br><span>+ How our career services team helps to prepare you for job hunt success</span><br><span>...plus much more in this live program overview.</span><br><br><span><a href=\"https://zoom.us/webinar/register/6615490391000/WN_JLQFYgv8SDml5KDXn2RKzA\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP Now to Save Your Spot</a> </span></p>','2019-03-12','2019-03-21','https://zoom.us/webinar/register/6615490391000/WN_JLQFYgv8SDml5KDXn2RKzA','UCF Continuing Education','(407) 882-0260','ceprograms@ucf.edu','UCF Division of Continuing Education','Publish',32),(2849,'Seminar - Anjali Gupta - Forensic Evidence Comparisons Using Multivariate and Spectroscopic Data','seminar-anjali-gupta-forensic-evidence-comparisons-using-multivariate-and-spectroscopic-data','<p></p>\n<p><strong>Tuesday March 12th, 2019 – 1.30 PM </strong></p>\n<p>College of Science Building, Room 221</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Forensic scientists use various instruments like LA-ICP-MS, LIBS, SEM-EDX, Raman spectroscopy to analyze forensic evidence (glass, tapes, inks). These instruments generate spectroscopic or multi-elemental data. Although modern instruments generate data that consists of details about the elements that constitute the samples, the number of observations are usually limited. Analyzing multi-dimensional data where the number of observations are less than the number of dimensions (n &lt; p) has been a problem of interest in statistics for many years now. Commonly used statistical methods fail to analyze spectral data due to its high-dimensionality and insufficient sample observations in forensic laboratories. It is challenging to estimate variance-covariance matrices reliably for high-dimensional data that are required for Hotelling\'s T2 test, as well as, likelihood ratio computations using the formulae given by Aitken and Lucy in 2004. We propose three methods, two of which are used for dimensionality reduction of multi-elemental data (principal component analysis and random projections). The method of random projections is gaining popularity in high dimensional machine learning problems before performing clustering. We use the transformed data to calculate likelihood ratios for glass comparisons. The third method focuses on using spectral data for inks comparisons with the help of functional data analysis and the Hotelling’s T2 test statistic derived by Pini et al. (2018). In this talk, I will discuss how the three approaches affect the evidence comparisons.</p>\n<p><strong>Biography</strong></p>\n<p>Anjali Gupta is a Forensic Statistician who is pursuing PhD at the University of Auckland (New Zealand). She worked using glass, tapes and inks evidence and used data generated using LIBS, LA-ICP-MS, SEM-EDX and Raman spectroscopy during her PhD. She used both, Bayesian and Frequentist analysis, to compare forensic evidence. In particular, she based her research on the concepts of dimensionality reduction and functional data analysis. She completed her MSc in Applied Statistics at University of Oxford (UK) in 2011 after which she worked as a Statistician and Analytics Consultant for a few years before she started her doctoral research.</p>','2019-03-11','2019-03-13',NULL,'Matthieu Baudelet','4078236910','baudelet@ucf.edu','Matthieu Baudelet','Pending',188),(2850,'2019 Financial Wellness Series','2019-financial-wellness-series','<p>The annual <strong>UCF Financial Wellness Series</strong> will be held from April 1 through April 30, 2019.</p>\n<p>Schedules and descriptions of workshops and other series details: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series</a><span>.</span></p>\n<p>For questions please contact <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">benefits@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2019-04-01','2019-04-30','https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/financial-wellness-series/','Venessa Williams','(407) 823-5187','Venessa.williams@ucf.edu','UCF HR Benefits','Publish',189),(2851,'Sick Leave Pool Open Enrollment','sick-leave-pool-open-enrollment-1-2','<p>The UCF Sick Leave Pool open enrollment is March 1 - March 29. To be eligible for membership, Faculty, A&amp;P, and USPS applicants must be employed with UCF continuously for at least one year and have accrued 64 hours of sick leave as of March 2019. New members are required to donate 16 hours of their sick leave (part time employees will donate an amount proportionate to their FTE). Membership reply letters will be sent to new applicants by early April 2019.</p>\n<p>Please note that if you are already a current member of the Sick Leave Pool, you do not need to rejoin during Open Enrollment. </p>\n<p>Interested faculty and staff should send applications to the Human Resources Leave Administration section at loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p>Application: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/SLPApplication.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/SLPApplication.pdf</a></p>','2019-03-18','2019-03-29','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/leave-and-general-attendance-information/sick-leave-pools','HR Leave Administration','(407) 823-0540','loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Publish',62),(2852,'Spring 2019 UCF Creed Art Contest','spring-2019-ucf-creed-art-contest','<p>The Spring 2019 Creed Art Contest is starting now. Express yourself with creating a work of art by using this year\'s theme: Celebrate the Creed! You could win an iPad as a first or second-place winner. Submissions are due at the Office of Student Rights and Responsibilities by 5 p.m on Friday, April 5. </p>\n<p>Contest rules have changed. See our website at<a data-ft=\'{\"tn\":\"-U\"}\' data-lynx-mode=\"async\" href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fosrr.sdes.ucf.edu%2Fcreedart%2Frules%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR06nLN_OmecgUiIq1s5OCpi0pcgVCznDauZwwKuoBLAhuVKn6MQJsbRgYQ&amp;h=AT2JhRpFDln2xRS1At3Yarumymai3PV6WX3Ga_FXu2jwT0-xSdNLgTjwA81qA_v-sDIUFViO3IiCG7NHhLS5OVAr9vbaNrxwUM-KvMXwjRqciZv4DykCg2IYJOOjr1tin4K0rpwXv6hnnodHV-KlwnCJYT8oJnwgMwL0Jz9u2V4Rb55Cme