gn Intern','ucf-united-way-campaign-intern','<p>The UCF &amp; United Way team is looking for a student interested in making a difference for our community as the United Way Campaign intern.  You will be supporting marketing, communications, data collection and analysis, campaign events, and more.  The campaign happens in October – but the team is working now to get things ready! <em>Come change the world with us!</em> </p>\n<p>If you’re up for this unique challenge, apply on UCF Handshake: <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fucf.joinhandshake.com%2Fjobs%2F2454314&amp;data=02%7C01%7Ctee.rogers%40ucf.edu%7C2a35cb8fad884d6d164708d6aba4dd05%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C636885121903303373&amp;sdata=tlaMzOTntJFWbJ6uCS9gRQuJVSs74QBvETjS%2FqJWGAk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.joinhandshake.com/jobs/2454314</a></p>','2019-03-18','2019-03-22','https://ucf.joinhandshake.com/jobs/2454314','Tee Rogers','(407) 823-3094','liveunited@ucf.edu','Tee Rogers','Pending',22),(2856,'UCF Cares Ambassador Information Sessions','ucf-cares-ambassador-information-sessions','<p>UCF Cares is recruiting Ambassadors for the 2019-2020 year! Come to one of our sessions to learn more about building a culture of care and what it\'s like to be an Ambassador!</p>\n<p>Our Sessions will be held in the Recreation and Wellness Center room 206:</p>\n<p>- Wednesday, March 27th from 4-5pm </p>\n<p>- Tuesday, April 2nd from 4-5pm</p>\n<p>For more information visit: <a href=\"https://cares.sdes.ucf.edu/involvement/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://cares.sdes.ucf.edu/involvement/</a> or apply: <a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6yrGGD1MqFAOjSR\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6yrGGD1MqFAOjSR</a></p>','2019-03-25','2019-04-05','https://cares.sdes.ucf.edu/involvement/','Morgan MacDougall','(407) 823-5607','morgan.macdougall@ucf.edu','Morgan MacDougall','Publish',183),(2861,'USPS Employee of the Month - February 2019 Jon Bowen','usps-employee-of-the-month-february-2019-jon-bowen','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month for February 2019: Jon Bowen. Jon is the Senior Broadcast Technologist in the Department of Film and Mass Media in the Nicholson School of Communication and Media. Jon has worked at UCF since 2011. His nominators Dr. Boyd Lindsley and Mr. Jason Burrell had this to say about him:</p>\n<p><em>          “Jon is a rare combination to find in a staff member; his professional experience in the field of film, his education and training, coupled with his technical skills make him a great asset for the school. Not only does he oversee the distribution of thousands and thousands of dollars in film equipment to student, he writes and wins Tech Fee Grants ($1.5 million over the past 10 years). </em></p>\n<p><em>         He is committed to excellence. Jon brings cutting edge technology to UCF and puts it in the hands of our faculty and students. He insists on the highest technical and professional standards our equipment and students can deliver. Because of his involvement in the film program’s new curriculum, the department and thousands of students will benefit from his efforts.” </em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Jon receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, his name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, an introduction to the Board of Trustees. He is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2019-03-25','2019-04-10','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2863,'Paws-a-tively Stress Free','paws-a-tively-stress-free-1','<p>Come by CAPS to play with <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Bodhi</strong> </span>and some of his fun, playful therapy dog friends to help you relieve some stress and get ready for Finals. Stop by on April 17 anytime between noon and 2 p.m. to play and hang with our great Therapy Dog teams.</p>','2019-03-22','2019-04-17',NULL,'Kavita Sawh','(407) 823-2811','ksawh@ucf.edu','Counseling and Psychological Services','Publish',161),(2864,'U-LEAD Programs Application Open','u-lead-programs-application-open','<p>The applications for the Summer and Fall 2019 U-LEAD Programs are now open! The U-LEAD Programs are single-semester programs designed for upperclassmen and transfer students with 60+ credits, a minimum 3.0 GPA, and an interest in service and leadership. For more information about each of the U-LEAD programs, please visit <a data-ft=\'{\"tn\":\"-U\"}\' data-lynx-mode=\"async\" href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Flsa.sdes.ucf.edu%2Fprograms%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR22P5NbIHkxJw5W8gom1mKX4Z5gJRGIXZaeCenTX9DFXF8_1GN261zsA8g&amp;h=AT1cjB789WaxxGClrvViuv1_CXDAxKJOnB7JRyR-7BDKLCaj7ttpgJZXGWZH0j2BH5tS2LNJlTzHRGnSK741iJgdI1YXTW1Xg6-JgMCJIhibVrq-1odSvfNMmaoKES5JHcEhZbxQlF2INPLRr2cXTQEJ5fZNDmk9CBy560Dpte6nnFCk2c3fvQ0IdA-CxX_RO7PgQYe4DR1FAghiyghUWqg0CS812ZHL8J5DDi0Dr18arYjNu3OadIX5em6kW1vFYRcAi7QFMkK8AP2SxzCA6CwzTZuDYgUK703Kt1LaQ3lJligdqZTmgd_WBK57R9t3RO351uUBQrfaOl_dI-mCeFYdA2-X0-rBrBz6-fRtfKQStsrRnO9nWPbuiVCwzf4T5N9FUUXrCgC32TuzOlsutQq8aeOPUWT4m6yyyHNoF8on-4k0hX6rlpoEHLoY1wW_BI5j8FAq9qq1W_9yPkfGgOkmEcMmgEvfibQhDI9iYIgfltYCLSSndm9fUaL1uDMseqIylvDBp4BxhYllUmlMArkbokFUuJOBjnGHTf0b5M9PF4rKBqGaU6-iivMQpvWvjLyIEHRkhkogrkWm9ACkcc6vPlvKrhbdGjha281oKmthcsemHgGTsqA\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/</a><span> </span>or contact us at leadscholarsacademy@ucf.edu.</p>\n<p>Applications are due by April 29th for Summer 2019 and by August 16th for Fall 2019. Click here to apply: <a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0TjNZJWOP0jE5iR\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0TjNZJWOP0jE5iR</a></p>\n<p> </p>','2019-04-01','2019-04-29','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/','Mike McFadden','(407) 823-2223','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Mike McFadden','Publish',52),(2868,'CPNM Research Seminar Series: From Science to Global Hazard: Addressing Space Weather and Other Technological Hazards','cpnm-research-seminar-series-from-science-to-global-hazard-addressing-space-weather-and-other-technological-hazards-1-2','<p><span>Please join us for a talk by UCF alumnus, Seth Jonas, presenting “From science to global hazard: addressing space weather and other technological hazards”. </span></p>\n<p>Dr. Seth Jonas is a researcher at the Institute for Defense Analysis, Science and Technology Policy Institute (STPI), a congressionally chartered and federally funded research and development center that supports the White House Office of Science and Technology Policy and other executive agencies. Areas of study include space weather, hazard preparedness, infrastructure security and resilience, national security, and emergency preparedness communications. He was a 2017 US-UK Fulbright Scholar serving as a visiting researcher at Rutherford Appleton Laboratory and the Acting Deputy Head of Resilience at the UK Government Office for Science.</p>\n<p>Dr. Jonas holds an MA and a Ph.D. in physics from Johns Hopkins University and two BS degrees from the University of Central Florida in physics and liberal science studies.</p>\n<p>This discussion will be held in HPA I, Room 304 on April 12 from 10:00 - 11:30 am. </p>','2019-03-26','2019-04-11',NULL,'Maria-Elena Augustin',NULL,'cpnm@ucf.edu','Center for Public and Nonprofit Management','Pending',155),(2873,'Shimmy Knights Presents: Shimmy Across the Seven Seas','shimmy-knights-presents-shimmy-across-the-seven-seas-1-2-3','<p><span>Splash into Shimmy Knights\' <strong>FREE</strong> annual belly dancing showcase!<br></span><br><span>Join us for a musical night of mystifying performances under the sea!</span><br><span>Grab your friends and swim with Shimmy Knights across the seven seas!</span><br><span></span></p>\n<p><span>See us perform on April 12th in the Harris Engineering Corporation Center building (HEC) at 8 pm!!</span></p>\n<p><span>Doors open 7:30 pm. See you there!<br><br></span></p>','2019-04-01','2019-04-13',NULL,'Netanya Andrews','(786) 728-0920','shimmyknightsatUCF@gmail.com','Netanya Andrews','Pending',194),(2874,'Joan Reynolds Named USPS Employee of the Month (March 2019)','usps-employee-of-the-month-march-2019-joan-reynolds','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for March 2019: Joan Reynolds. Joan is the Library Technical Assistant in the John C. Hitt Library. She has worked at the university since December 1986. Her nominators, Kristine Shrauger and Patricia Tiberii, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>      “Joan or ‘Joanie’ to almost everyone in the library and on campus, is an exemplary UCF employee. She has worked the past 30 years, to support the students, faculty and staff in their research needs, providing a strong customer service for all in their pursuit for gathering sources. Her resourcefulness and perseverance in fulfilling requests for obscure and difficult-to-find materials has a direct impact on student and faculty research exemplifies her outstanding work ethic. Joanie’s efforts have been acknowledged within the dedications of faculty-published works and dissertations.</em></p>\n<p><em>     In addition to her daily responsibilities, she regularly volunteers her time by serving on a variety of UCF committees, taking on extra duties within the library and participating in UCF-led outreach opportunities throughout the greater Orlando community. Joanie plays an integral part within the UCF community and the university is lucky to have someone like her improving the academic quality and experience of our students, faculty and staff.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Joan receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2019-04-03','2019-04-10','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2875,'UCF Football Spring Game Ticket Info','ucf-football-spring-game-ticket-info','<p>The 2019 UCF Spring Game presented by DEX Imaging is almost here. On April 13 at 2:30 p.m. Knight Nation can get a glimpse of the 2019 team inside Spectrum Stadium.</p>\n<p>General admission to the game is free. All 2019 season ticket holders can<span> </span>login<span> </span>to their<span> </span><a href=\"https://am.ticketmaster.com/ucf/tickets?DB_OEM_ID=34100\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Account Manager</a> to save their complimentary tickets to their mobile device.</p>\n<p> Fans who do not have 2019 season tickets must<span> </span><a href=\"https://oss.ticketmaster.com/aps/ucf/EN/buy/quickbuy/623?DB_OEM_ID=34100&amp;camefrom=EMCL_2784002_131313093\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a><span> </span>to register and receive free general admission tickets to the Spring Game.</p>\n<p> For 2019 premium season ticket holders in the Carl Black &amp; Gold Cabana, Stadium Club or Tower Club, there will be free access to their respective club area for the Spring Game. Please note, seats within those sections will be general admission and available on a<span> </span>first-come first-served<span> </span>basis. Tickets must be printed or saved to a mobile device prior to April 1, 2019.</p>\n<p>For those who do not already have premium season tickets, but would like to sit in one of the premium sections for the Spring Game, a limited amount of tickets are available. Spring Game prices for premium areas are as follows: Tower Club - $20, Stadium Club - $10, Carl Black &amp; Gold Cabana ($5).<span> </span><a href=\"https://oss.ticketmaster.com/aps/ucf/EN/buy/quickbuy/623?DB_OEM_ID=34100\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a><span> </span>to purchase premium seating.</p>\n<p>As always, admission for students at Spectrum Stadium is free with a valid UCF student identification card.</p>','2019-04-01','2019-04-13','http://ucfknights.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=34100&ATCLID=211795222','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-1000','bsmoley@athletics.ucf.edu','Jenna Marina Lee','Publish',165),(2876,'2019 Founders\' Day Awardees','2019-founders-day-awardees','<p><strong>The College Awards for Excellence in Undergraduate Teaching</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>College of Arts an