-of-nurses-with-ucfs-online-msn-or-graduate-certificate-programs','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">The online Nurse Educator program prepares nurses to teach in undergraduate nursing and health professions programs at colleges and universities, healthcare agencies, or in the community.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Graduates of this program are eligible to take the optional national exam to become a Certified Nurse Educator®.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Please join our information session to learn additional information about the program. Information on how to connect to the session is listed below: </span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Join Zoom Meeting</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><a href=\"https://zoom.us/j/839466358\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">https://zoom.us/j/839466358</a></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> One tap mobile</p>\n<ul>\n<li>+16465588656,,839466358# US (New York)</li>\n<li>+14086380968,,839466358# US (San Jose)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> Dial by your location</p>\n<ul>\n<li>        +1 646 558 8656 US (New York)</li>\n<li>        +1 408 638 0968 US (San Jose)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Meeting ID: 839 466 358</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Find your local number: <a href=\"https://zoom.us/u/ad6X09wYEE\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">https://zoom.us/u/ad6X09wYEE</a></p>','2019-06-18','2019-07-24','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1297573/information-session-msn-nurse-educator-and-nurse-educator-certificate/','Ayanna Lopez','(407) 823-2744','gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','College of Nursing','Publish',146),(2921,'APRNs can add an Additional Specialty to their Practice with UCF\'s Hybrid Certificate Programs','aprns-can-add-an-additional-specialty-to-their-practice-with-ucfs-hybrid-certificane-programs','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Our hybrid<span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> </span>post-master’s<span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> nurse practitioner certificate programs are open to nurses who have already earned an MSN degree and are a licensed APRN and are seeking to add a specialty to their current practice. We offer certificates in 3 specialty areas:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Family Nurse Practitioner</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Please join our information session to learn additional information about the programs listed above. Information on how to connect to the session is listed below:</span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Join Zoom Meeting</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><a href=\"https://zoom.us/j/123326014?status=success\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">https://zoom.us/j/123326014</a></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> One tap mobile</p>\n<ul>\n<li>+16465588656,,123326014# US (New York)</li>\n<li>+14086380968,,123326014# US (San Jose)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> Dial by your location</p>\n<ul>\n<li>        +1 646 558 8656 US (New York)</li>\n<li>        +1 408 638 0968 US (San Jose)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Meeting ID: 123 326 014</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Find your local number: <a href=\"https://zoom.us/zoomconference?u=gp4PEgsMAZH3rghj2VYLkGLtwGK1DzmLqph525UbY2Q\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://zoom.us/u/ad6X09wYEE</a></p>','2019-06-18','2019-07-24','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1297620/information-session-post-msn-nurse-practitioner-certificates/','Ayanna Lopez','(407) 823-2744','mailto:gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','College of Nursing','Publish',146),(2922,'Become a Clinical Practice Leader with UCF\'s Practice-Focused Online DNP for APRNS','become-a-clinical-practice-leader-with-ucfs-practice-focused-online-dnp-for-aprns','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">UCF’s online Advanced Practice Nurse Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP) is designed to enhance the development of master’s prepared Nurse Practitioners, Clinical Nurse Specialists, Registered Nurse Anesthetists, and Nurse Midwives into clinical practice leaders.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Clinical practice leaders participate at the highest level in their organizations and community, and are equipped to improve quality, outcomes and systems of healthcare.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Doctoral students in the Advanced Practice DNP track are encouraged to lead scholarly inquiry in their current practice environment. Integral components of the program will include translating current evidence into practice, and designing, implementing and evaluating new models of care.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Graduates are prepared to initiate and lead change in the clinical practice environment with emphasis on contributing to the body of evidence being considered in the reshaping of healthcare.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Students will take course work corresponding to the <a href=\"https://www.aacnnursing.org/DNP/DNP-Essentials\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">eight DNP essential competencies</a> delineated by the American Association of Colleges of Nursing (AACN).</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Please join our information session to learn additional information about the program. Information on how to connect to the session is listed below:</span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Join Zoom Meeting</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><a href=\"https://zoom.us/j/633618184?status=success\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">https://zoom.us/j/633618184</a></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> One tap mobile</p>\n<ul>\n<li>+16465588656,,633618184# US (New York)</li>\n<li>+14086380968,,633618184# US (San Jose)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"> Dial by your location</p>\n<ul>\n<li>   +1 646 558 8656 US (New York)</li>\n<li>   +1 408 638 0968 US (San Jose)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Meeting ID: 633 618 184</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Find your local number: <a href=\"https://zoom.us/zoomconference?u=gp4PEgsMAZH3rghj2VYLkGLtwGK1DzmLqph525UbY2Q\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://zoom.us/u/ad6X09wYEE</a></p>','2019-06-18','2019-07-24','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1297622/information-session-advanced-practice-dnp/','Ayanna Lopez','(407) 823-2744','gradnurseadvisor@ucf.edu','College of Nursing','Publish',146),(2924,'Fall 2019/Spring 2020 Dining Scholarship Applications Now Open','fall-2019spring-2020-dining-scholarship-applications-are-now-being-accepted','<p>UCF Business Services is now accepting dining scholarship applications for the upcoming academic school year.</p>\n<p>Six (6) dining scholarships will be awarded to students for use during the fall 2019 and spring 2020 semesters. The scholarships are valued at $4,180 each.</p>\n<p>Due to the volume of applicants, only recipients will be notified.</p>\n<p>Please visit <a href=\"https://businessservices.ucf.edu/dining-scholarship/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://businessservices.ucf.edu/dining-scholarship/</a> to apply. Thank you and good luck!</p>','2019-07-22','2019-08-08','https://businessservices.ucf.edu/dining-scholarship/','Sue Gonzalez','(407) 823-3539','sue.gonzalez@ucf.edu','Sue Gonzalez','Publish',97),(2925,'UCF Squad Care Movie Night','ucf-squad-care-movie-night','<p>Join the UCF Cares Ambassadors, Let\'s Be Clear, and the Student Health Services Sober Knights team, on July 8, 2019, to learn how to build your own #squad with giveaways, activities, and care related resources! We will be sending out a poll on Facebook for you to vote for your favorite Netflix original film that we will be streaming just for you! Grab your friends, roommates, and classmates and enjoy some popcorn and a movie! We will be doing some recess style activities beginning art 5pm outside of the Neptune Multipurpose room before the film screening for you to enjoy!</p>\n<p> </p>','2019-06-26','2019-07-09','https://www.facebook.com/UCFCares/','Morgan Quinn','(407) 823-5607','morgan.quinn@ucf.edu','Morgan Quinn','Publish',183),(2926,'USPS Employee of the Month May 2019 - Megan Haught','usps-employee-of-the-month-may-2019-megan-haught','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for May 2019: Megan Haught. Megan is the Administrative Assistant in the Research &amp; Information Services Department of the John Hitt Library. She has worked at the University since September 2012. Her nominators, Ms. Barbara Tierney and Ms. Barbar Thompson, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>          “Megan is dependable, hardworking, honest and always goes the extra mile for UCF Libraries and her department. She excels at ‘taking ownership’ of complex, multi-step projects. Megan created an outstanding award submission for UCF Libraries bid to win the prestigious Assoc. of College of Research Libraries (ACRL) 2019 Excellence in Academic Libraries Award to be announced in 2019. The ACRL Award instructs the applicant to demonstrate how the library works to support its institution’s mission and goals. </em></p>\n<p><em>          Over the years, and in whatever position she is employed, Megan is a true ‘champion’ of diversity and inclusion, supporting the work of UCF’s Office of Diversity and Inclusion with enthusiasm, creativity and energy. She has a deep understanding of what it means to be respectful and inclusive, and she models this perspective daily.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Megan receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <span><a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></span></p>','2019-06-25','2019-07-05','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(2927,'Student Veterans and Dependents Can Certify Fall 2019 Hours Beginning July 15','student-veterans-and-dependents-can-certify-fall-2019-hours-beginning-july-15','<p><span>Student Veterans and Dependents using G.I. Bill Benefits can stop by the Veterans Academic Resource Center (VARC) starting on Monday, July 15, 2019. For more information about certifying your Fall 2019 hours visit the VARC\'s </span><a href=\"https://varc.sdes.ucf.edu/news/summer-certifications-starts-monday-april-1st/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Fall 2019 Certification Page</a><span> or call 407-823-2707.</span></p>','2019-07-15','2019-07-31','https://varc.sdes.ucf.edu/news/summer-certifications-starts-monday-april-1st/','Veterans Academic Resource Center','(407) 823-2707','varc@ucf.edu','Veterans Academic Resource Center','Publish',165),(2928,'UCF Art Gallery Exhibition: Specters of Capital','ucf-art-gallery-exhibition-specters-of-capital','<p><em>Specters of Capital: An Exploration in Architecture and Identity </em>explores architectural structures as both repositories and as vehicles for memory and provide a framework through which culture and identity can be expressed. The work does not act merely as a method of documentation, but a sociopolitical/socioeconomic commentary on the effects of avarice, outsourcing, deregulation, neoliberalism, obsolescence, and international finance capital upon communities throughout the world. Within the realm of Jacques Derrida’s theory of Hauntology, the paintings speak of the slow disintegration of the future, and the abysmal fragmentation of the past.<span> </span><a href=\"https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/exhibition-specters-of-capital-an-exploration-in-architecture-and-identity-by-morgan-craig/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a></p>\n<p>Morgan Craig has exhibited both nationally and internationally, including OK Harris in New York City, SPACES in Cleveland, the Delaware Center for Contemporary Arts and the Australian National University. Craig has received numerous awards including, the Pollock Krasner Foundation Grant, the Elizabeth Greenshields Foundation Grant (2007, 2011), and the Pennsylvania Council on the Arts Individual Artist Fellowship for 2006 and 2008. He has also been invited to several residencies including, Cite Internationale des Arts in Paris, the Macdowell Colony, Bemis Center for the Contemporary Arts, Proekt Fabrika in Moscow, and Red Gate in Beijing.</p>\n<p><strong>Exhibition Dates: </strong><br>June 13 – July 11</p>\n<p><strong>UCF Art Gallery Summer Hours:</strong><br>Monday – Thursday<br>10 a.m. – 5 p.m.</p>\n<p><strong>Parking: </strong><span>Free parking is available in Garage F next to CFE Arena. $5 parking lot H-4 or Garage I requires purchasing a visitor permit from a kiosk. Please note that visitors should park in green student spaces ONLY, as the $5 daily permit does not cover red and blue spaces.</span></p>\n<p></p>','2019-06-26','2019-07-11','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/','UCF Art Gallery','(407) 823-2676','Shannon.Lindsey@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',165),(2931,'UCF Sports Medicine Looking for Student Volunteers for Football Season','ucf-sports-medicinefootball-developmental-program-now-accepting-new-applicants-for-volunteers-1','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span>The UCF Athletics Sports Medicine department is looking for volunteers for the upcoming football season. UCF students interested in pursuing a career in sports medicine can apply to gain valuable experience with an NCAA Division I football team. </span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span>Send your resume and fall class schedule to Associate Athletic Trainer Ed Woodley at ewoodley@athletics.ucf.edu. Students who have direct experience will be to be considered first. Resumes will be accepted throughout the summer. </span></p>','2019-07-22','2019-12-07','http://ucfknights.com/sports/2016/6/13/school-bio-ucf-sports-med-html.aspx','Ed Woodley','(407) 823-0585','ewoodley@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Sports Medicine','Publish',204),(2932,'UCF Sports Nutrition Program Seeking Student Volunteers','ucf-sports-nutrition-program-seeking-new-applications-for-volunteers','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span>The UCF Athletics Sports Nutrition department is looking for volunteers for the Fall 2019 semester. UCF students interested in pursuing a career in nutrition/dietetics within the sports industry can apply to gain valuable experience with an NCAA Division I athletics program. </span></p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><span>Send your resume and fall class schedule to the director of sports nutrition, Carly Fancher, at cfancher@athletics.ucf.edu. Students who have previous experience will be to be considered first. Resumes will be accepted throughout the summer. </span></p>','2019-07-08','2019-12-07',NULL,'Carly Fancher','(321) 445-0827','cfancher@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Sports Nutrition','Publish',204),(2933,'Collective Bargaining Session - PBA','collective-bargaining-session-pba-1','<p><span>A collective bargaining session is scheduled between the Board of Trustees and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) for July 12 at 10 a.m. in UCF Human Resources Innovative Center Room 105.</span></p>','2019-07-11','2019-07-12',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Brittny Bannister','Publish',205),(2934,'USPS Employee of the Month June 2019 - Christine Rivera','usps-employee-of-the-month-june-2019-christine-rivera','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for June 2019: Christine Rivera. Christine is the Administrative Assistant in Academic Services in the College of Undergraduate Studies. Her nominators, Ms. Juanita Sembrano and Dr. Keisha Hoerrner, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>“Christine’s performance is aligned with the University’s goal of offering our students unique experiences and the best undergraduate education available in Florida. She uses her exceptional people skills to provide confidentiality, support, knowledge and a positive experience to the students and their parents during difficult situations. </em></p>\n<p><em>          “Christine illustrates UCF’s commitment to innovation. She is a ‘yes, let’s figure out a better way’ individual, who is constantly striving for improvement. She works collaboratively with her peers, understand the centrality of partnership, and develops innovative solutions to better serve our students. She is a key asset to Academic Services.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Christine receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <span><a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></span></p>','2019-07-10','2019-07-17','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2935,'Tickets on Sale for Aug. 22 Kickoff Luncheon','tickets-on-sale-for-aug-22-kickoff-luncheon','<p>Tickets are now available for the 2019 UCF Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon, presented by KnightPass, which will be held Aug. 22 at Addition Financial Arena.<span> </span><br><br>The annual event will celebrate the Knights’ back-to-back American Athletic Conference football championships—with 2018 highlights from UCF’s record-breaking volleyball and soccer teams as well. Fans will hear from UCF head football coach Josh Heupel and have a chance to interact with UCF football student-athletes.<br><br>Single tickets ($120 each) and corporate tables (8 seats/$900) are available in limited quantities. Sponsorship opportunities for the Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon also are available. All proceeds from the Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon help provide scholarships and resources for UCF student-athletes.<br><br><strong>2019 Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon</strong><br>Addition Financial Arena<br>Thursday, Aug. 22<br>11 a.m. – Registration<br>11:30 a.m.-1:30 p.m. – Luncheon<br><br><strong>Ticket Information</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Single tickets are $120</li>\n<li>Corporate tables (8 seats) are $900</li>\n<li>Fans are encouraged to purchase their seats early as this event routinely sells out</li>\n<li>Contact the UCF Championship Resources office at (407) 823-2086 or<span> </span><a href=\"mailto:championshipresources@athletics.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">championshipresources@athletics.ucf.edu</a></li>\n</ul>','2019-07-15','2019-08-01','http://ucfknights.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=34100&ATCLID=211806914','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-2086','championshipresources@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Athletics','Publish',165),(2936,'Take the PMP Exam Before it Changes - Fall Class Available!','take-the-pmp-exam-before-it-changes-fall-class-available','<p><strong>UCF Continuing Education is pleased to offer our <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Applied-Project-Management-Certificate-Project-Management-Professional-PMP\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Applied Project Management Certificate Program</a> before the PMP exam changes.</strong></p>\n<p>Ensure you\'re prepared with UCF’s <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Applied-Project-Management-Certificate-Project-Management-Professional-PMP\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Applied Project Management Certificate Program</a>. This intensive program combines expert instruction with The CertWise® Learning System for PMP® Exam Preparation training materials and meets PMI’s <u>35</u> contact hour PMP Exam requirement. <em>Our course will help you learn faster, retain more knowledge and stay on track for success on the PMP exam.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Face-to-face and Live Online Instruction </strong></p>\n<p>Tuesday and Thursday evenings, September 5, 2019 - October 29, 2019<br>5:30 - 9:30 p.m.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Sessions 9/5, 9/10, 9/17, 9/24, 10/1, 10/8, 10/15, 10/22, 10/29 meet Face-to-Face in UCF Continuing Education Classroom </em></li>\n<li><em>Sessions 10/10, 10/17, 10/24 meet via Live Online</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>This course aligns with the <strong><em>PMBOK</em>®<em> Guide – </em>Sixth Edition</strong> and this session is designed to prepare CAPM/PMP students who seek to test prior to the <a href=\"https://www.pmi.org/certifications/types/project-management-pmp/exam-prep/changes\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">expiration</a> of the current version of the PMP/CAPM exam (December 15, 2019).</p>\n<p>Our 12 session program includes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Three textbooks organized into 14 chapters that follows the PMBOK® Guide – Sixth Edition.</li>\n<li>Participants will have access to an online repository of study resources including a pre-test to help identify topics you already know and areas that require more time and attention.</li>\n<li>A computer-based practice exam is included that mimics the certification exam in style, function, timing and weighted topics.</li>\n<li>Discussion and guidance from our PMP-certified and experienced instructors along with networking with other participants in various industries.</li>\n<li>Learn and apply project management tools and techniques that are applicable to initiating, planning, executing, monitoring, controlling and closing a project.</li>\n<li>Meet PMI’s PM education requirement to become eligible to sit for the CAPM® or PMP® exam.</li>\n<li>Our program qualifies for most company tuition reimbursements.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Class fills quickly, <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Applied-Project-Management-Certificate-Project-Management-Professional-PMP\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">REGISTER TODAY</a>!</strong></p>','2019-07-29','2019-09-02','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Applied-Project-Management-Certificate-Project-Management-Professional-PMP','LIsa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','Lisa.Ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(2937,'47th Annual Knight Star Awards - Celebrating Our Employees!','47th-annual-knight-star-awards-celebrating-our-employees','<p>Please join us for an afternoon of celebration as UCF Human Resources recognizes our dedicated employees at the 47th Annual Knight Star Awards (formerly Annual Employee Awards). The event will take place on Wednesday, September 25, 2019 at 2:30 p.m. in the Student Union Pegasus Ballroom, with a reception to follow in the Cape Florida Ballroom. Honorees include employees celebrating years of service anniversaries, and recipients of the United Way Advocate Leadership Award, USPS Employee of the Year, and Gabor A&amp;P Excellence Award.</p>\n<p>For more details, please visit the <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Knight Star Awards webpage</a>. We look forward to seeing you there!</p>','2019-08-12','2019-09-25','https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/','HR Learning & Organizational Effectiveness','(407) 823-0440','HRLearning@ucf.edu','Lee Williams','Publish',24),(2938,'USPS Employee of the Month July 2019 - Miriam Beckles','usps-employee-of-the-month-july-2019-miriam-beckles','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for July 2019: Miriam Beckles. Miriam was hired at UCF in July 2014. She is currently the Administrative Assistant in the College of Science, Chemistry Department. Her nominators, Kurt Lorenz and Cherie Yestrebsky, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>          “In a department that has 57,000 student credit hours per year, Miriam is an exemplary employee who regularly supports department growth and development. She is creative in developing new protocols to more efficiently save money while still helping our students progress toward their career goals. </em></p>\n<p><em>She gives freely of her time to help and advocate for students. She provides one-on-one support with class overrides, chemistry placement exam support, course/program advisement, and regular support helping students find research advisors. Miriam’s ability to guide student through our program; and to supportive and relevant research experience produces future professional success and fosters future partnerships.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Miriam receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <span><a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></span></p>','2019-07-26','2019-08-09','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Debbie Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(2941,'Collective Bargaining Session - PBA','collective-bargaining-session-pba-1-2-3-4','<p><span>A collective bargaining session is scheduled between the Board of Trustees and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) for August 5th at 2:00p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center Room 105.</span></p>','2019-08-02','2019-08-05',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Brittny Bannister','Pending',205),(2942,'Collective Bargaining Session - AFSCME','collective-bargaining-session-afscme-1','<p><span>A collective bargaining session is scheduled between the Board of Trustees and the American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) for August 8th at 2:00p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center Room 105.</span></p>','2019-08-07','2019-08-08',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Brittny Bannister','Pending',205),(2943,'UCF Football FanFest Set For Aug. 17','ucf-football-fanfest-set-for-aug-17','<p><span>Knights fans will have their annual opportunity to celebrate the start of the 2019 season with UCF FanFest, set for Aug. 17. The event will take place at Addition Financial Arena with doors opening to the arena lobby at 6 p.m. and autographs beginning at 6:30 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>Fans will have the opportunity to meet with and get autographs from UCF head football coach Josh Heupel, as well as members of the football team and other fall sports teams. </span></p>\n<p><strong><span>Note: Fans are allowed to bring one item to be autographed and football posters will be distributed throughout the event. In order to accommodate as many fans as possible, coaches and players can only sign one item per person and photo opportunities are limited.</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Fans should enter through the main Addition Financial Arena doors or through <a href=\"https://map.ucf.edu/locations/50c/the-venue/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">The Venue</a> entrance located on East Plaza Drive</span></li>\n<li><span>Admission is free.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span>Sponsors of the event include Addition Financial, AdventHealth, Buffalo Wild Wings, Blaze Pizza, Carl Black, Chick-fil-A, Duffys, Drive Shack, Dunkin and Paradise Grills.</span></p>','2019-08-12','2019-08-17','http://ucfknights.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=34100&ATCLID=211808863','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-3213','jskiles@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Athletics','Publish',165),(2945,'Collective Bargaining Session - PBA','collective-bargaining-session-pba-1-2','<p><span>A collective bargaining session is scheduled between the Board of Trustees and the Police Benevolent Association (PBA) for August 16th at 1:00p.m. in UCF Human Resources, Innovative Center Room 102.</span></p>','2019-08-15','2019-08-16',NULL,'Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Brittny Bannister','Pending',205),(2948,'Instructional Design Open House - Jobs and Internships','instructional-design-open-house-jobs-and-internships','<p>Instructional Design and Technology Open House</p>\n<p>Instructional Design is the science and art of designing innovative, effective, and engaging training and educational programs in business and industry, K-12, and Higher Education. Come to our Open House and learn about UCF\'s IDT programs and certificates. Visit with over 30 companies that hire Instructional Designers. Learn about a Career in IDT, Jobs, Internships, and Research opportunities. Drop-in at the UCF Morgridge International Reading Center on October 16th between 5pm and 8pm.</p>','2019-10-01','2019-10-17','https://ccie.ucf.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2017/11/IDT-OpenHouseFlyer.pdf','Dr. Laurie O. Campbell','(407) 882-6472','locampbell@ucf.edu','Instructional Design and Technology Program','Publish',210),(2949,'Sim Talk on Augmented Clinical Training','sim-talk-on-augmented-clinical-training','<p>Join the UCF College of Nursing for a <strong>SIM TALK</strong> featuring Fluvio Lobo, who will be discussing <strong>Augmented Clinical Training</strong> on Thursday, Sept. 19, from 4-5 p.m. </p>\n<p>Fluvio is PD3D’s Principal Research and Development Engineer at the Institute for Simulation and Training at the University of Central Florida. He is an expert in medical devices and systems capable of assessing user performance.</p>\n<p>This SIM TALK is talking place during national Healthcare Simulation Week (#HcSimWeek19). <span>Healthcare Simulation Week celebrates global professionals like you who use simulation to improve the safety, effectiveness, and efficiency of healthcare delivery. This week also raises awareness in communities nationwide about how healthcare simulation is leading us to safer, more knowledgeable patient care. </span></p>\n<p><span>Following the talk, join the <strong>SIMSATIONS 4 LIFE CLUB</strong> for networking and simsational food and beverage specials at Island Wing Co. from 5:30-6:30 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><span></span><em>This event is made possible with funds supporting the AdventHealth Endowed Chair in Healthcare Simulation.</em></p>','2019-08-26','2019-09-19','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/sim-talk-tickets-67087577751','Syretta Spears',NULL,'syretta.spears@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing','Publish',57),(2951,'UCF Business Incubator Startup Hosts Challenge for $10K Prize','ucf-business-incubator-startup-hosts-challenge-for-10k-prize','<p><span>AireHealth LLC is revolutionizing care management and drug delivery for respiratory illness via a connected-portable nebulizer. AireHealth sees the potential to positively impact 100 million people in the U.S. who live with respiratory illness,</span><span> including 29 million “wheezy” kids. </span><span>To do this, the UCF Business Incubation Program startup is calling all superheroes that use innovation challenge tools to submit their ideas and possibly watch them be implemented in a way that will change the lives of children. Together with Synapse Innovation, they are offering a prize of $10,000. </span></p>\n<p><span>Help AireHealth deliver an innovative solution that allows a child to receive their treatments more consistently, even while on the go in a silent, effective and not so scary way. Think big, think broad — everything from customization of device “skins” to fun mask redesigns to patient engagement tools for their mobile app. </span></p>\n<p>More information about the challenge can be found at <a href=\"https://app.synapsefl.com/challenge/connected-asthma-care-with-airehealth/28\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://app.synapsefl.com/challenge/connected-asthma-care-with-airehealth/28</a></p>','2019-08-19','2019-09-10','https://app.synapsefl.com/challenge/connected-asthma-care-with-airehealth/28','AireHealth',NULL,'Info@Aire.Health','UCF','Publish',165),(2952,'UCF Football Walk-On Tryouts','ucf-football-walk-on-tryouts','<p><span>The UCF football team will hold walk-on tryouts in advance of the 2019 season. Information on necessary requirements to tryout is below.<strong><br><br>Monday, August 26</strong> </span></p>\n<p><span>5:15 p.m.: Walk-on Information meeting – Team Meeting Room (Wayne Densch Sports Center, 4180 N. Orion Blvd., Orlando, FL 32816)</span><span> </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Participants must be current UCF students and bring a copy of their Fall 2019 class schedule </span><span> </span></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Participants must bring <u>physical examination</u> results and <u>sickle cell test</u> results from your doctor (must have been completed within the last 6 months)</span><span> </span></li>\n<li><span>Participants must be registered with the NCAA Eligibility Center (<u><a href=\"http://www.eligibilitycenter.org/?DB_OEM_ID=34100\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.eligibilitycenter.org</a></u>)</span><span> </span></li>\n<li><span>Participants must bring a copy of both sides of insurance card</span><span> </span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span><strong>Tuesday, August 27</strong> </span></p>\n<p><span>11 a.m.: Walk-on tryouts at UCF practice fields (Wayne Densch Sports Center, 4180 N. Orion Blvd., Orlando, FL 32816)<br><br>Participants can print out the forms linked below to fill out and turn in at the information meeting.<br></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://ucfknights.com//attachments1/files/34100/642693.pdf?DB_OEM_ID=34100\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Clearance Form</span><span> </span></a></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://ucfknights.com//attachments1/files/34100/642694.pdf?DB_OEM_ID=34100\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Tryout Waiver</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span> </span></p>','2019-08-19','2019-08-26','http://ucfknights.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=34100&ATCLID=211809435','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-3213','ucffootball@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Athletics','Publish',165),(2954,'Free Tailgate Concert: Smash Mouth','free-tailgate-concert-smash-mouth','<p><span>The UCF Tailgate Concert Series presented by Pacifico is back for 2019 with a big name for the nationally ranked football team\'s season opener on Thursday, Aug. 29. Smash Mouth — known for songs like All-Star, Can\'t Get Enough of You Baby, I\'m a Believer and Walkin\' on the Sun — will kick off the season with a free concert starting at 5:30 p.m. on IOA Plaza at Spectrum Stadium.</span></p>\n<p><span></span><span>The Knights will then take on Florida A&amp;M at 7:30 p.m. on CBS Sports Network. </span></p>\n<p><strong>UCF Tailgate Concert Series Lineup for 2019 Season<br></strong><span>Aug. 29 – Smash Mouth – 5:30 p.m.<br></span><span>Sept. 14  – Three Sheets to the Wind – 1:30 p.m.<br></span><span>Sept. 28 – Hardy – Time TBA<br></span><span>Oct. 19 – John Michael Montgomery – Time TBA <br></span><span>Nov. 2 – Dylan Scott – Time TBA<br></span><span>Nov. 29 – TBA – Time TBA </span></p>\n<p><span>Each UCF Tailgate Concert Series show begins approximately 2 hours prior to kickoff and is contingent on UCF football kickoff times. All activities at IOA Plaza begin four hours prior to kickoff.</span></p>\n<p></p>','2019-08-22','2019-08-29','http://ucfknights.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=34100&ATCLID=211809598','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-3213','knights@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Athletics','Publish',165),(2955,'USPS Staff Council Fall Scholarships Available','usps-staff-council-fall-scholarships-available','<p>The USPS Staff Council is now accepting applications for the Fall 2019 Scholarship awards.  Apply now at the Staff Council web site, (<a href=\"http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/</a>) or on the Council Facebook page.  There are two awards available.  Dependents of USPS Staff may apply for the Campus Bookstore Scholarship.  Applications must be submitted by 11:59 p.m. September 15, 2019.  You may apply for one or both of the awards if you wish.  The only restrictions are you must be a member of the USPS for a minimum of one year, and if you have won an award you must wait one year before applying for that particular award again.  Apply now and avoid the rush!</p>','2019-08-26','2019-09-15','http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/','Jamie Jo LaMoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie Jo LaMoreaux','Publish',54),(2958,'USPS Staff Council Fall Scholarships Available','usps-staff-council-fall-scholarships-available-1-2-3','<p>The USPS Staff Council is now accepting applications for the Fall 2019 Scholarship awards.  Apply now at the Staff Council web site, (<a href=\"http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/</a>) or on the Council Facebook page.  There are two awards available.  Dependents of USPS Staff may apply for the Campus Bookstore Scholarship.  Applications must be submitted by 11:59 p.m. September 15th 2019.  You may apply for one or both of the awards if you wish.   The only restrictions are you must be a member of the USPS for a minimum of one year, and if you have won an award you must wait one year before applying for that particular award again.  Apply now and avoid the rush!</p>','2019-08-21','2019-09-15','http://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/','Jamie Jo LaMoreaux','(407) 882-0191','lamoreaj@ucf.edu','Jamie Jo LaMoreaux','Publish',54),(2959,'Call for collaborators: UCF Celebrates the Arts 2020','seeking-collaborators-for-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-2020','<p>The sixth annual <a href=\"http://arts.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Celebrates the Arts</a> festival will be held April 6-19, 2020 at Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts. Building upon the festival\'s growing success, the festival steering committee has selected anchor events for the 2020 festival. These include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>In the Disney theater:\n<ul>\n<li>a concert by the Flying Horse Big Band with</li>\n<li>a concert by the UCF Symphony Orchestra featuring a multimedia composition about oceanic noise pollution by Stella Sung</li>\n<li>a dance concert from Theatre UCF</li>\n<li>the National Young Composers Challenge Composium</li>\n<li>a choral concert and invitational</li>\n<li>a band invitational and concert by the UCF Wind Ensemble and Symphonic Band</li>\n<li>a percussion invitational and concert by the UCF Percussion Ensemble</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>In the Pugh/DeVos:\n<ul>\n<li>a cabaret by Theatre UCF</li>\n<li>an opera from UCF Opera (piece TBA)</li>\n<li>a Shakespeare reading from Orlando Shakes</li>\n<li>a chamber music performance by UCF faculty</li>\n<li>events/exhibits related to the NEA Big Read selection <em>(The Things They Carried)</em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>In the lobby spaces:\n<ul>\n<li>a exhibit of art by Dorothy Gillespie from the UCF Gallery vault</li>\n<li>a digital media showcase</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Other events and exhibits are being planned, but have yet to be added to this list pending final details.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The committee is seeking additional events to fill several spots on the schedule, as well as visual art and interactive exhibits that will showcase the best from UCF students and faculty and bring attention to our year-round activities on campus. Of particular interest are events that relate to the existing programming.</p>\n<p>If you have an event or exhibition that you wish to include in UCF Celebrates the Arts, please contact <a href=\"mailto:michael.wainstein@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Wainstein</a> by September 13. The ideas for these events can come out of classes; outside projects by faculty, students or alumni; or collaborative works associated with the university. Please note that the person suggesting an event/exhibit will also be responsible for the coordination and may need to cover production expenses.</p>\n<p>---------</p>\n<p>Central to the event\'s mission is:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Showcasing the work and talents of students and faculty from UCF and the College of Arts &amp; Humanities</li>\n<li>Presenting events that are interdisciplinary within or beyond the walls of CAH</li>\n<li>Presenting 1-3 key events that are large in scope, that will attract attention nationally or regionally and will be major audience draws</li>\n<li>Presenting innovative, high-quality events and happenings that are unexpected, premieres or incapable of being produced elsewhere</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Deadline for event suggestions is Friday, September 13, 2019.</strong></p>','2019-08-26','2019-09-13','http://arts.ucf.edu','Michael Wainstein','(407) 823-0876','michael.wainstein@ucf.edu','UCF Celebrates the Arts Steering Committee','Publish',10),(2960,'Learn Hands-only CPR','learn-hands-only-cpr','<p>In anticipation of World Heart Day, UCF Heart Day will provide free hands-only CPR instruction to the UCF community on Monday, Sept. 9.</p>\n<p>Recurring 20-minute hands-only CPR sessions will be offered from 10 a.m. until 2 p.m. in the Pegasus Ballroom at the UCF Student Union. The event also will include instruction on the use of AEDs and information about heart health.</p>\n<p>Hands-only CPR is cardiopulmonary resuscitation without mouth-to-mouth. It is recommended for use by people who see a teen or adult suddenly collapse in an “out-of-hospital” setting, such as at home, work, or in a public place.</p>\n<p>UCF Heart Day is a collaboration among UCF Environmental Health and Safety, the Recreation and Wellness Center, the Department of Emergency Management, the Department of Security, the UCF Police Department, Orange County Fire Rescue, and CPR and AED Foundation, Inc.</p>\n<p>World Heart Day will be celebrated across the globe on Sunday, Sept. 29.</p>','2019-10-06','2019-09-10','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1358540/2019-ucf-heart-day-learn-hands-only-cpr/','Amanda Sellers','(407) 823-2833','amanda.sellers@ucf.edu','UCF Police','Pending',165),(2961,'Girija: A lifetime in music-Film Screening and Panel Discussion','girija-a-lifetime-in-music-film-screening-and-panel-discussion','<p><span data-offset-key=\"75plb-0-0\">The Interdisciplinary Studies Program (Diversity Studies) is pleased to be hosting the opening film of the 25th Annual South Asian Film Festival 2019 — <em>Girija: A Lifetime in Music</em> explores the life and unique contribution to classical Northern Indian music of the renowned vocalist Girija Devi. This film is the recipient of the National Film Award in 2017 awarded by the government of India. It won the Los Angeles Independent Film Festival award for Best Documentary Feature, and its filmmakers were declared as being among the best of international filmmakers by the Euro Film Awards. </span></p>\n<p><span>This event is being co-sponsored by the UCF India Center, The College of Undergraduate Studies, and the Asian Cultural Center of Central Florida.</span></p>\n<p><span>Please join us on Tuesday, October 8, 2019 in the Pegasus Ballroom in the Student Union here at UCF. </span></p>\n<p><span>6:00pm-Reception and live music by a former student of Girija</span></p>\n<p><span>7:00pm-Screening followed by a panel discussion with the filmmakers </span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>','2019-09-01','2019-10-08','https://www.facebook.com/events/541599919918345/','Sharon Woodill','(407) 823-3773','sharon.woodill@ucf.edu','Sharon Woodill, Interdisciplinary Studies','Publish',208),(2962,'Asian Pacific American Coalition Assembly: Unity in Motion','apac-assembly-unity-in-motion','<p>Hello! APAC\'s 14th annual assembly is right around the corner! This is the chance for everyone, but especially our new students, to come out and experience the Asian cultural RSOs we have here at UCF. There will be entertainment, wonderous performances and free food! Our theme this year is Unity in Motion and you will get the opportunity to see our talented RSOs recreate some of the most iconic pieces of Asian filmography! All are welcome to attend. Please come out and participate in one of the largest and most exciting events of the year! Assembly will take place in the Pegasus Ballroom, Sept. 7. Doors open at 5:30 p.m., and the show begins at 6 p.m.</p>','2019-08-29','2019-09-07','https://www.facebook.com/events/499924367475915/','Angela Yen','(813) 326-1794','apacucf.pr@gmail.com','Asian Pacific American Coalition','Publish',216),(2963,'UCF Sick Leave Pool Open Enrollment','ucf-sick-leave-pool-open-enrollment','<p>The UCF Sick Leave Pool open enrollment for Faculty, A&amp;P, and USPS employees is Sept 3 - Sept 30. To be eligible for membership, applicants must be employed with UCF continuously for at least one year and have accrued 64 hours of sick leave as of Sept 2019. New members are required to donate 16 hours of their sick leave (part time employees will donate an amount proportionate to their FTE). Membership reply letters will be sent to new applicants by early Oct 2019.</p>\n<p>Please note that if you are already a current member of the Sick Leave Pool, you do not need to rejoin during Open Enrollment. The url listed below includes details on how to verify your current membership status.</p>\n<p>Interested faculty and staff should send <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/SLPApplication.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">applications</a> to the Human Resources Leave Administration section at loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu.</p>','2019-09-03','2019-09-30','http://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/leave-and-general-attendance-information/sick-leave-pools','Ben Anderson','(407) 823-3730','loaandworkcomp@ucf.edu','UCF Human Resources','Publish',62),(2964,'RSVP for College of Nursing\'s Simulated Participant Workshop','simulated-participant-workshop','<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">The UCF College of Nursing is co-hosting this Simulated Participant Workshop with Avkin. During the workshop, UCF professors and healthcare simulation experts <span>Mindi Anderson, Desiree Díaz and Laura Gonzalez</span> are presenting on “Content Expert versus Expert Facilitators: Implications” and will provide a tour of the College of Nursing\'s STIM Center.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Attendees can earn 2 hours of CEU credits.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">The Oct. 9 workshop begins at 4 p.m. and ends at 7:30 p.m.</p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\"><a href=\"https://pages.avkin.com/avkin-workshop-univeresity_of_central_florida\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP with Avkin<span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">. </span></a></p>','2019-09-09','2019-10-09','https://pages.avkin.com/avkin-workshop-univeresity_of_central_florida','Laura Gonzalez',NULL,'Laura.Gonzalez@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing','Publish',218),(2973,'Research Administration Virtual Open House','research-administration-virtual-open-house','<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Interested in learning more about UCF\'s graduate programs in research administration? Join us for our next virtual open house, <span>September 12, at 1 p.m. </span>Discuss the program requirements, application process, and career opportunities in research administration with program director, Angela White-Jones, and online success coach, Renee Montgomery. </p>\n<p style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Register at <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fapplynow.graduate.ucf.edu%2Fregister%2FSepUCFMRA&amp;data=02%7C01%7CYasmyn.Chambers%40ucf.edu%7C2c3b9143467b42da219008d725943606%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637019190793864219&amp;sdata=uvH%2Fm5QKu4XtHbhR%2FDBCpWfH2KN8pld%2Bh7HVscbN2Pk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://applynow.graduate.ucf.edu/register/SepUCFMRA</a>. </p>','2019-09-10','2019-09-13','https://ccie.ucf.edu/public-administration/research-administration/master-research-administration/','Renee Montgomery','(407) 823-4561','renee.montgomery2@ucf.edu','UCF School of Public Administration','Publish',155),(2976,'Made in Space: A New Manufacturing Paradigm','made-in-space-a-new-manufacturing-paradigm','<p>Join the Department of Mechanical and Aerospace Engineering for a special presentation from Patrick Flowers of Made in Space, creators of 3D printers for space. The event will take place in HEC 117 at 11 a.m. on Sept. 13. </p>','2019-09-09','2019-09-14','http://mae.ucf.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/made-in-space-3.pdf','Seetha Raghavan','(407) 823-1737','seetha.raghavan@ucf.edu','Department of Mechanical and Aerospace Engineering','Publish',51),(2977,'Learn to Manage Your Grief at Journey to Hope','journey-to-hope','<p>An atmosphere of compassion and confidentiality allows young adults ages 19 to 25 to become empowered and equipped with tools that will help them journey through the grief process.</p>\n<p>This safe social setting is designed to place young adults in an environment where they will be supported by peers and given the opportunity to participate in conversations and activities to help them heal.</p>\n<p>Journey to Hope offers a place to take what you are feeling and learn to better manage it alongside young adults with similar experiences. <br> <br> Grieving is not easy, but together we can make it a little less difficult.</p>\n<p>Every other Wednesday<br>September 11 – November 20, 2019 <br>7:30 PM – 9:00 PM</p>\n<p>New Hope for Kids<br> 544 Mayo Avenue, Maitland, FL 32751<br> Refreshments provided.</p>\n<p><br>Registration is required to attend - Please Contact: <br><a href=\"https://newhopeforkids.org/young-adult-grief-support/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://newhopeforkids.org/young-adult-grief-support/</a></p>','2019-09-11','2019-11-20','https://newhopeforkids.org/young-adult-grief-support/','Dana Duffie','(407) 331-3059','information@newhopeforkids.org','New Hope For Kids','Publish',219),(2978,'Join Us for Empty Bowls — and Get a Bowl a Soup and Give a Bowl of Soup to Someone in Need','empty-bowls-central-florida','<p><span style=\"font-weight: inherit !important;\">We\'re bringing Empty Bowls to Central Florida! Over 600 handcrafted ceramic bowls have been fired and custom glazed by UCF art students from the<span> </span></span><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FUCFSVAD%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399436919&amp;sdata=eqaiKNC4NVbZbvs5Wfb5GFwJANCsEeqYvR%2BndANONLc%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF School of Visual Arts and Design</a><span style=\"font-weight: inherit !important;\"><span> </span>in support of our Empty Bowls event. Join us on Wednesday, Oct. 9 from 11:30-1:30 in the Live Oak Event Center on main campus</span><span style=\"font-weight: inherit !important;\">. If you would like the opportunity to pick out your bowl earlier, just be sure to donate ahead of time<span> </span></span><strong><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2FEmptyBowlsCF&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399446912&amp;sdata=9WdVs1OCHeuVdJluI6uPydDUryrY38vYXcFerGl1FaM%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></strong><span style=\"font-weight: inherit !important;\"><span> </span>for the chance to stop by during our<span> </span></span>early bird selection time(from 11-11:30 a.m.). Once you\'ve selected your bowl, enjoy a soup luncheon which will include your choice of soup, oyster crackers, and a beverage.<span> </span><span style=\"font-weight: inherit !important;\">The types of soups will be announced at a later date. All proceeds will be split 50/50 among<span> </span></span><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fstudentunion.ucf.edu%2Fknights-pantry%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399446912&amp;sdata=o0qT7z1RNifW%2Fss%2B60WvzJ4xsqVxHu3gzfxn4tht0Ps%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Knights Helping Knights Pantry at UCF</a><span> </span>and<span> </span><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ugo2.org%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399446912&amp;sdata=t4jWLgksgSCa%2B2w5nXbVrRJi3xBfo4jp6ViqnxCscVE%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">United Global Outreach</a>; two organizations that support our students and local community in need.</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-weight: inherit !important;\">Date:</span></stro