uncheon (soup, oyster crackers and a beverage)</li>\n<li>meal for a student or community member in need</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Hosted by:</strong><br><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fsvad.cah.ucf.edu%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399466905&amp;sdata=1ctesbGVdJ8rEGWDDi0A%2F8tGI%2FHGf7semSM87ysgB24%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF School of Visual Arts and Design</a><span> </span>+ UCF Potters Guild<br><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fstudentunion.ucf.edu%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399466905&amp;sdata=gQUdG%2FMvPnAEd4aUh%2B44t1sHn%2BcjoEN8dTuZP9WnqXs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Student Union</a><span> </span>+<span> </span><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fosi.ucf.edu%2Fagencies%2Fvucf%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399476899&amp;sdata=HF5p2lTZSbX%2F9v30t0aR8g1aCfU8oIJKWt1ClJ05R5o%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Volunteer UCF</a><br><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fstudentunion.ucf.edu%2Fknights-pantry%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399476899&amp;sdata=jIiN6RPOS4n0UqzWHdLKurJRjUs%2FZAv1Bt7kNqEvOWs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Knights Helping Knights Pantry</a><br><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ugo2.org%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399476899&amp;sdata=J5B9sPWD95UuY3rsUGR81yF%2FJwZHWJtlg7KTcUMLhA8%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">United Global Outreach</a><br><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdoubletree3.hilton.com%2Fen%2Fhotels%2Fflorida%2Fdoubletree-by-hilton-hotel-orlando-east-ucf-area-ORLOEDT%2Findex.html&amp;data=02%7C01%7CHannah.Estes%40ucf.edu%7C57e439280cfd4963017008d72c91f255%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637026878399486889&amp;sdata=CXJa2sp4nsdcXSK6Izt%2B2U7Dgu5yYhnuDPWm6LMbrgI%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">DoubleTree by Hilton</a></p>\n<p><strong><em>About Empty Bowls:</em></strong><em><br><span style=\"font-weight: inherit !important;\">Empty Bowls is an international grass-roots project to fight hunger, personalized by artists and art organizations on a community level. Founded by Lisa Blackburn and art teacher John Hartom in 1990-91 when<span> </span>they joined a drive to raise charitable funds in Hatrom\'s Michigan community.<span> </span>The<span> </span>idea was to organize a charitable event to give artists and art students a way to make a personal difference. Hartom\'s students made ceramic bowls in<span> </span>their high school art classes.<span> </span>The<span> </span>finished products were<span> </span>then used as serving pieces for a fund-raising meal of soup and bread. Contributing guests kept<span> </span>the<span> </span>empty bowl. During<span> </span>the<span> </span>next year, Hartom and other participants developed this concept into<span> </span>the<span> </span>Empty Bowls project.<span> </span>The<span> </span>Imagine/RENDER Group, a 501(c)3 organization, was created to promote<span> </span>the<span> </span>project.</span></em></p>','2019-09-12','2019-10-09','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1314191/empty-bowls-central-florida/','School of Visual Arts and Design','(407) 823-2676','svad@ucf.edu','School of Visual Arts and Design','Publish',200),(2979,'Join us for the Hispanic Serving Institutions Week Kickoff Event','join-us-for-the-hispanic-serving-institutions-week-kickoff-event','<p><span>UCF Celebrates National Hispanic Serving Institutions Week hosted by the Hispanic Association of Colleges and Universities. All students, staff and faculty are invited to join us in the Live Oak Event Center for the campus celebration. Refreshments will be provided at the conclusion of the program.</span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p></p>','2019-09-12','2019-09-16','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1369246/hispanic-serving-institutions-week-kickoff/','Cyndia Muniz','(407) 823-0524','cyndia.muniz@ucf.edu','Cyndia Muniz','Publish',35),(2980,'Get Your Ticket for the Drone Racing League: Artificial Intelligence Robotic Racing Event','drone-racing-league-artificial-intelligence-robotic-racing-airr-event','<p>The Artificial Intelligence Robotic Racing (AIRR) Circuit is the premier, autonomous drone racing series created by The Drone Racing League (DRL). Lockheed Martin and DRL recently launched the 2019 AlphaPilot Innovation Challenge, an open competition to develop artificial intelligence (AI) for high-speed racing drones. The top AlphaPilot teams earned a coveted spot in DRL\'s inaugural AIRR Circuit. On Tuesday, Oct 8, fans will watch AI go head-to-head through brightly colored aerial courses without any GPS, data relay or human intervention for a chance to win a $1 million cash prize. Doors open at 2pm ET for an exclusive networking opportunity featuring thought leaders and decision makers in the engineering and AI space. Key influencers within the category will also lead engaging panels around the future of autonomous flight throughout the event. The main race event begins at 5pm ET, featuring the 9 most elite AlphaPilot Teams in their fiercestcompetition yet. </p>','2019-09-13','2019-10-09','https://www1.ticketmaster.com/event/2200570779DF93DB','Drone Racing League',NULL,'hello@drl.io','Anthony M. Moore, University Communications','Publish',220),(2981,'Unity Star Workshops & Trainings','unity-star-workshops-trainings','<p> </p>\n<p>Diversity and Inclusion\'s Unity Star Workshop &amp; Training<br> <br> Unexplored Diversity - Belief Systems and Non-Belief Systems in Student Development -- DIV395.0002 on Wednesday, September 25 at 2:30-4:00 PM, which will be located at the Barbara Ying Center, Room 140 with Jeannie Kirwas as the facilitator.<br> <br> Register onlne at: <br> Faculty, A&amp;P, USPS: myucf. &gt;Employee Self Service &gt; Learning &amp; Development &gt; Request Training Enrollment<br> <br> Students, OPS: Email your name, course title and date, and UCFID/employee I.D. number to <a href=\"mailto:diverse@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">diverse@ucf.edu</a></p>','2019-09-25','2019-09-25',NULL,'Susan Laden','(407) 823-6479','sladen@ucf.edu','Susan Laden','Publish',221),(2982,'Register for the Urban and Regional Planning Distinguished Lecture Series today!','distinguished-lecture-series','<p><span>The</span><strong><span> </span>Urban and Regional Planning Distinguished Lecture Series </strong><span>fall lecture will take place on </span><strong>Wednesday, November 13th</strong><span> at UCF Downtown. The lecture will begin at 6:30 p.m. and will be preceded by a networking happy hour at 5:30 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>This lecture\'s topic on <em>Smart Citities, Global Lessons Learned</em> is presented by David Gilford. <br>Gilford advises public and private sector clients on the use of technology to make cities more livable, sustainable, and responsive. As a Principal with HR&amp;A Advisors, David is developing strategies in support of economic development and inclusive innovation for clients including New York City, the City of Pittsburgh, and the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey. David previously co-founded and led the Connected Communities practice at Intersection, an urban technology and media company backed by Alphabet’s Sidewalk Labs, where he focused on real estate, airports, and neighborhood development. David has led the creation of digital master plans for over 40mm square feet of mixed-use developments, including Orlando’s Lake Nona Town Center, using technology to unlock new sources of revenue, reduce costs, and improve quality of life. He has been recognized nationally among the 40 Under 40 Rising Stars in Economic Development, as well as one of New York State\'s Top Ten Energy Government Leaders.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Registration information is available at <a href=\"bit.ly/urpfa19\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/urpfa19</a>.</strong></p>\n<p>-----</p>\n<p><span>Each year, two of the nation’s leading planning experts are invited to Orlando to participate in UCF’s Urban and Regional Planning Distinguished Lecture Series. The lectures are open to the public and supported by generous contributions from members of the Central Florida planning community, as well as local organizations.</span></p>','2019-09-17','2019-11-13','http://bit.ly/urpfa19','Roberta Fennessy','(407) 823-1712','Roberta.Fennessy@ucf.edu','UCF School of Public Administration','Publish',155),(2983,'Creating an Ethical Culture: A Conversation with Lisa M. Lee','creating-an-ethical-culture-a-conversation-with-lisa-m-lee','<p><em><strong>Celebrate the newly-formed UCF Center for Ethics at its inaugural event.</strong></em></p>\n<p><em></em>Wednesday, September 25 at 10 am in the Live Oak Center Event</p>\n<p>Register at <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/creating-an-ethical-culture-a-conversation-with-lisa-m-lee-tickets-72147457989\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/creating-an-ethical-culture-a-conversation-with-lisa-m-lee-tickets-72147457989</a> </p>\n<p>How do we think about values and teach skills that help students, teachers, staff and all stakeholders make good decisions? Nationally recognized ethics educator and former director of the Presidential Bioethics Commission Dr. Lisa M. Lee talks about how UCF can cultivate an institution-wide culture of ethics.</p>\n<p>The conversation will be moderated by center founder Dr. Jonathan Beever, assistant professor of ethics and digital culture, and co-director Dr. Stephen Kuebler, professor of chemistry. Light refreshments will follow the conversation.</p>\n<p>Lee (Ph.D. Johns Hopkins, M.S. Bioethics, M.A. Educational Psychology) is an epidemiologist, bioethicist and ethics educator currently serving as associate vice president for research and innovation and director of the division of Scholarly Integrity and Research Compliance at Virginia Tech. Most recently, she served as the inaugural Chief of Bioethics at Walter Reed Army Institute of Research. During the Obama administration, she served as executive director of the Presidential Bioethics Commission. For over 25 years, Lee has worked in public health and ethics at the local, state, and federal levels, including 14 years at the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://philosophy.cah.ucf.edu/ethicscenter/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://philosophy.cah.ucf.edu/ethicscenter/</a></p>','2091-09-16','2019-09-25','https://philosophy.cah.ucf.edu/ethicscenter/','Jonathan Beever','(407) 823-4340','jonathan.beever@ucf.edu','Heather Gibson','Publish',56),(2984,'UCF Cares Movie Night: Christopher Robin','ucf-cares-movie-night-christopher-robin','<p><span>Join UCF Cares, Wellness and Health Promotion Services, Green Dot, the Recreation and Wellness Center, Outdoor Adventure, and Let\'s Be Clear for our </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/ucfsquadcare\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">#UCFSquadCare</a><span> Movie Night! We will have specialty prizes, games, and activities starting at 6pm with the movie screening around 7:15! Bring your squad and relax in the pool and on deck for a fun night under the stars.</span></p>','2019-09-18','2019-10-03','https://www.facebook.com/events/363489771195627/','Morgan Quinn','(407) 823-5607','morgan.quinn@ucf.edu','Morgan Quinn, UCF Cares','Publish',183),(2985,'The Impact of Hazing on our Campus Community: Changes to Anti-Hazing Laws in Florida','the-impact-of-hazing-on-our-campus-community-changes-to-anti-hazing-laws-in-florida','<p><strong>National Hazing Prevention Week Keynote Speakers</strong></p>\n<p>More than 55% of college students involved in clubs, teams and organizations have experienced or witnessed hazing.  These incidents not only impact the campus community but also the friends and families of both victims and perpetrators. </p>\n<p>What happens to a campus community when there is a death or loss?  </p>\n<p>In November 2017, Tom and Sandy Coffey lost their son Andrew to hazing.  On June 25, 2019, Governor Ron DeSantis signed “Andrew’s Law,” which made important changes to Florida’s existing anti-hazing law.  Come find out what you need to know about hazing in Florida.</p>\n<p>This presentation will feature the attorneys who drafted Andrew’s Law, <strong>David W. Bianchi</strong> and <strong>Michael E. Levine</strong> of Stewart Tilghman Fox Bianchi &amp; Cain, P.A. The goal is to educate Florida students, faculty and staff about the dangers and legal consequences of hazing and to raise awareness about “Andrew’s Law.”  </p>\n<p> There will be 2 sessions:</p>\n<p><strong> </strong><strong>Wednesday September 25, 2018</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>1:00pm </strong><strong>Student Union Key West Ballroom  </strong></li>\n<li><strong>6:30pm</strong><strong> Classroom Building 1 104</strong><strong> </strong></li>\n</ul>','2019-09-20','2019-09-26','https://antihazing.sdes.ucf.edu/','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Germayne Graham','Publish',41),(2987,'Join your UCF colleagues at the 47th Annual Knight Star Awards, Honoring our Employees','join-your-ucf-colleagues-at-the-47th-annual-knight-star-awards-honoring-our-employees-1','<p>It takes over 13,000 employees to create University of Central Florida’s diverse, welcoming environment and so many opportunities for students to grow, learn and succeed. On Wednesday, September 25 at 2:30 p.m., you are invited to celebrate with our outstanding employees at Human Resource’s 47th annual Knight Star Awards.</p>\n<p>The free event will be held in the Student Union Pegasus Ballroom.  Recipients of the USPS Employee of the Year, the Gabor A&amp;P Excellence Award, Employees of the Month, and employees celebrating years of service milestones will be among those recognized. Invited guest speaker is Interim President Thad Seymour, Jr. Complimentary event parking will be available in <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/Knight-Star-Awards-Parking.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Parking Garages D and H</a>.</p>\n<p>The event will be live-streamed on UCF\'s Youtube channel <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MDIOOETJlwk\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MDIOOETJlwk</a></p>','2019-09-23','2019-09-26','https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/','Human Resources','(407) 823-0558','askhr@ucf.edu','Lorie Parker MAtejowsky','Publish',122),(2988,'Apply to join the Omicron Delta Kappa Society today!','omicron-delta-kappa-applications','<p><strong>ODK applications are now open!</strong></p>\n<p>The Omicron Delta Kappa Society is the national leadership honor society for college students, faculty, staff, administrators, and alumni that recognizes and encourages superior scholarship, leadership, and exemplary character.</p>\n<p>The student and faculty members of Omicron Delta Kappa work closely together to foster leadership abilities within its members. The organization is also dedicated to a variety of projects that benefit the university and the surrounding community.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements for induction into the </strong><strong>Central Florida Circle of ODK:</strong></p>\n<p>Class standing: Junior (at least 60 credits), Senior, or Graduate Level</p>\n<p>Minimum GPA: 3.2 for undergraduates, 3.5 for graduate students</p>\n<p>Initiation fee of $95-includes lifetime membership and pin (graduation cords may be purchased for an additional $25) . If accepted your dues will be due by 11/4/19 at 12:00 PM. Induction will be held on Monday, 11/18/19 at 3:30pm in Ferrell Commons 165-LEAD Scholars Academy</p>\n<p>Demonstrated leadership in at least two of the five areas:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Scholarship</li>\n<li>Athletics</li>\n<li>Campus/Community Service, Social/Religious Activities, and Campus Government</li>\n<li>Journalism, Speech and the Mass Media</li>\n<li>Creative and Performing Arts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply:</strong></p>\n<p>Visit our website at <u><a href=\"https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form</a></u> to complete the online application</p>\n<p>Questions may be directed to Dr. Stacey Malaret, Faculty Secretary for ODK, in the LEAD Scholars Academy Office, Ferrell Commons 165</p>\n<p><strong>Online application deadline is </strong><strong>10/14/19</strong></p>','2019-09-23','2019-10-14','https://membership.odk.org/audience/prospective_members/membership_application_form','Stacey','(407) 823-6492','stacey.malaret@ucf.edu','Stacey Malaret','Publish',8),(2990,'Explore and Accelerate Sustainable Solutions at Climate Correction 2019','explore-and-accelerate-sustainable-solutions-at-climate-correction-2019-1','<p>Students, faculty and staff are invited to join UCF Sustainability Initiatives and VoLo Foundation at <a href=\"http://sustainable.ucf.edu/climatecorrection\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Climate Correction 2019</a><span>, a conference and expo dedicated to sharing and collaborating on climate change solutions. On October 3 in the UCF Student Union, attendees will network with over 40 speakers and panelists who are moving climate crises conversations forward through data-driven research and solution building. Attendees will dive into discussions about agriculture, health, extreme weather events, and more.</span></p>\n<p><span>If you have an interest in renewable energy, sea-level rise, clean eating, and sustainable living this conference is for you. Student tickets are just $15, and faculty and staff tickets are $45. Use promo code CC2019 for $5 off. Buffet breakfast and lunch will be served. </span></p>\n<p><span><strong></strong></span>Learn more and get your tickets at <a href=\"http://sustainable.ucf.edu/climatecorrection%20\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://sustainable.ucf.edu/climatecorrection<span> </span></a></p>\n<p><span>We also invite you to join us at the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">CC Engagement &amp; Art Expo</span>, where you can engage in current conversations and resolutions with leading organizers, researchers, and businesses. Discover where your skills are needed and sign up to participate and accelerate real-world climate solutions. The works of local artists inspired by creating solutions for a sustainable future will be on display.</span></p>\n<p>The CC Expo is FREE and held from 1 p.m. to 6 p.m.. Refreshments will be served.</p>','2019-09-27','2019-10-03','http://sustainable.ucf.edu/climatecorrection','Yara Watson Colon','(407) 823-3353','yara.watson@ucf.edu','Sustainability Initiatives','Publish',203),(2997,'Dive-in for the UCF Football Viewing Party','the-dive-in-ucf-football-viewing-party-1-2-3-4-5-6','<p><span>The best way to watch UCF Football is to relax in the Recreation and Wellness Center Leisure Pool! Join us on Oct. 4 at 7:30 p.m. and support your Knights as we give you a chance to sit in and by the pool to watch the Knights take on the Cincinnati Bearcats. Gates open at 7:30 p.m. and the game is set for 8 p.m. kick-off.</span></p>\n<p><span>There will be prizes, give-aways, and food! Not to mention plenty of inner tubes for everyone. It\'s all free to enrolled UCF students who bring their valid ID. </span></p>\n<p><span>Go Knights! Charge On!</span></p>','2019-09-27','2019-10-05','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1420769/ucf-dive-in-football-viewing-party/','Scott Mauro','(407) 823-2408','scott.mauro@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(2998,'Register for Open Water SCUBA Certifications','open-water-scuba-certifications','<p>A two weekend course to recieve your NAUI Open Water SCUBA Certification! MUST BE AVAILABLE DURING BOTH WEEKENDS! </p>\n<p><span>To register for the course, please visit the Outdoor Adventure Center (OAC) in the Recreation and Wellness Center. Our open hours are:</span></p>\n<p><span>Monday - noon to 6 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday - 2 p.m. to 6 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>Friday - noon to 6 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span> The OAC is room 154, located on the first floor of the Recreation and Wellness Center, just past the racquetball courts, down the long hallway, across from the RWC Wet Classroom and Men\'s locker room entrance to the lap pool.</span></p>\n<p><span>Call or stop in the Outdoor Adventure Center for more information regarding the certification. 407.823.2408 </span></p>\n<p><span>Total cost for the course is $320. Must pay a downpayment of $40 to reserve your spot. The rest of the money must be payed the day of the course.</span></p>','2019-09-27','2019-10-03','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1419650/open-water-scuba-certification/','Katherine Rocco','(407) 823-2408','katherine.rocco@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(2999,'UCF Intramural Sports Foot Tennis Tournament','ucf-intramural-sports-foot-tennis-tournament','<p><strong><span>Registration Deadline</span></strong></p>\n<