y enrolled UCF Students are eligible to participate in Intramural Sports. All Students listed on your team roster will be verified. A/P and USPS Full-Time Faculty and Staff at UCF may participate in Intramural Sports by purchasing an RWC Membership BEFORE playing in their first game.</p>\n<p>Captain\'s Guide</p>\n<p>For all Intramural Sports Policies &amp; Guidelines please look at our Team Captain\'s Guide <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/file.imleagues/Images/Schools/Uploaded/201702/2017291184.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a>.</p>\n<p>Event Description</p>\n<p>IM Sports Trivia will consist of teams of 3 participants. Teams will answer questions on a wide variety of sports topics to become the IM Sports Trivia Champion!</p>','2019-09-27','2019-10-09','https://www.imleagues.com/spa/sport/6e860fe3287f4e2aac127dd771b62948/home#sportname','Heather Marshall','(407) 823-2408','heather.marshall@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(3001,'Join us for RWC@Downtown Nature and Mindfulness Walk at Leu Gardens','rwcdowntown-nature-adn-mindfulness-walk-at-leu-gardens','<p><span>This trip is especially catered to UCF Downtown students.</span><br><span>Join us for a relaxing walk through Leu Gardens, a 50 acre botanical oasis. Harry P. Leu Gardens features a rose garden, several varieties of bromeliads, and stunning camellias. This trip incorporates mindfulness exercises where we take the opportunity to recenter ourselves before diving into the rest of the school week.</span></p>','2019-09-27','2019-10-07','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1356628/downtown-nature-and-mindfulness-walk-at-leu-gardens/','Katherine Rocco','(407) 823-2408','katherine.rocco@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(3002,'Join Us UCF Outdoor Adventure for a Backpacking Trip through Cumberland Island','ucf-outdoor-adventure-cumberland-island-backpacking-trip','<p><span>Come with OA and explore Cumberland Island, Georgia\'s largest and southernmost barrier island and home to over 9,800 acres of congressionally designated Wilderness. Here we will backpack through pristine maritime forests and wide marshes, while exploring the history of the island. Natives, missionaries, enslaved African Americans and Wealthy Industrialists all walked here. There are also wild ponies on the island!</span></p>\n<p><span>To register for the trip, please visit the Outdoor Adventure Center (OAC) in the Recreation and Wellness Center. Our open hours are:</span></p>\n<p><span>Monday - noon to 6 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday - 2 p.m. to 6 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>Friday - noon to 6 p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>The OAC is room 154, located on the first floor of the Recreation and Wellness Center, just past the racquetball courts, down the long hallway, across from the RWC Wet Classroom and Men\'s locker room entrance to the lap pool.</span></p>\n<p><span>*AFTER REGISTERING FOR THE COURSE, PARTICIPANTS MUST ATTEND THE PRE TRIP MEETING* </span></p>\n<p><span>Call or stop in the Outdoor Adventure Center for more information regarding the trip. 407.823.2408 </span></p>','2019-09-27','2019-10-08','http://rwc.sdes.ucf.edu/programs/outdoor-adventure/trips','Heather Marshall','(407) 823-2408','heather.marshall@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(3003,'UCF Intramural Shuffleboard at the Beardall Center near RWC@Downtown','ucf-intramural-shuffleboard-at-the-beardall-center-near-rwcdowntown','<p><strong><span>Registration Deadline</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span>Monday, September 30th 6:00 PM</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span>Event Date</span></strong></p>\n<p><span><strong>Thursday, October 3rd 7:00 PM</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong><span>Location</span></strong></p>\n<p><span><strong>Beardall Center</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong><span>Eligibility</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span>Currently enrolled UCF Students are eligible to participate in Intramural Sports. All Students listed on your team roster will be verified. A/P and USPS Full-Time Faculty and Staff at UCF may participate in Intramural Sports by purchasing an RWC Membership BEFORE playing in their first game.</span></strong></p>\n<p><span><strong>Captain\'s Guide</strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>For all Intramural Sports Policies &amp; Guidelines please look at our Team Captain\'s Guide <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/file.imleagues/Images/Schools/Uploaded/201608/201683154414.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a>.</strong></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>League Information</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong><span>Shuffleboard isn\'t just for old people! Sign up for our Intramural Shuffleboard tournament today! This will take place at the Beardall Center near our brand new Downtown Campus.</span></strong></p>','2019-09-27','2019-10-01','https://www.imleagues.com/spa/sport/6b2a7a57672b48dcab33ba832ee16374/home#sportname','Heather Marshall','(407) 823-2408','heather.marshall@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Pending',34),(3004,'Compete in the UCF Intramural Sports Global World-Cup Soccer Tournament','ucf-intramural-sports-global-world-cup-soccer-tournament','<p>Registration Deadline: Monday, October 21 at 6 p.m.</p>\n<p>Season Duration: Oct. 28 to Nov. 4</p>\n<p>Location: RWC – Turf Fields 1 – 5. Games will be from 3 p.m. to 6 p.m.</p>\n<p>Mandatory Captain’s Meeting: Tuesday, Oct. 22 at 1 p.m. in the RWC room 206. </p>\n<p>Eligibility: Currently enrolled UCF Students are eligible to participate in Intramural Sports. All Students listed on your team roster will be verified. A/P and USPS Full-Time Faculty and Staff at UCF may participate in Intramural Sports by purchasing an RWC Membership BEFORE playing in their first game.</p>\n<p>Captain\'s Guide: To learn more about the Intramural Sports Policies &amp; Guidelines, <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/file.imleagues/Images/Schools/Uploaded/201608/201683154414.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">check out the Team Captain\'s Guide</a>.</p>','2019-10-01','2019-10-21','https://www.imleagues.com/spa/sport/6cebb55d08bb47f1aceffdd95370fb41/home#sportname','Heather Marshall','(407) 823-2408','heather.marshall@ucf.edu','Scott Mauro','Publish',34),(3006,'Attend the 2019 Employee Benefits Fair','2019-employee-benefits-fair-1','<p>The 2019 Benefits Fair will be held on Friday, October 25, from 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. in the Pegasus Ballroom at the Student Union.</p>\n<p>Additional details: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/open-enrollment\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/open-enrollment</a></p>\n<p>The Benefits Fair is an opportunity to learn about benefit options and changes to help employees make the best choices during Open Enrollment, October 14 to November 1 (6 p.m.). During Open Enrollment, eligible employees can make changes to their insurance plans for the upcoming plan year. Changes will be effective January 1, 2020 and must be made through <a href=\"https://peoplefirst.myflorida.com\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://peoplefirst.myflorida.com</a>. You can also call toll-free at 866-663-4735.</p>\n<p>Employees who have not logged into People First within the past 90 days will need to update their password online.</p>\n<p>For questions regarding this information contact 407-823-2771 or <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">benefits@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2019-10-02','2019-10-26','https://hr.ucf.edu/current-employees/benefits/open-enrollment','Keven Ayala','(407) 823-1937','keven@ucf.edu','UCF HR Benefits','Publish',65),(3007,'Workshop: Envisioning an Active Future for Downtowns','workshop-envisioning-an-active-future-for-downtowns','<p>UCF Urban Knights Planning Students Association hosts technical skills workshops for UCF students studying or interested in studying urban planning and related topics, such as public administration.</p>\n<p>Eliza Harris Juliano (Canin Associates) and Gus Castro (City of Orlando) will speak on Envisioning an Active Future for Downtowns, Small and Large.</p>\n<p>This technical skills workshop will take place in DPAC 346, UCF Downtown, Monday, October 7th, 2019, 6 - 8 PM.</p>','2019-10-05','2019-10-07','https://www.facebook.com/events/951621895172013/','Heather','(321) 946-9752','heather.croney@knights.ucf.edu','Heather Croney','Pending',224),(3008,'Urban Knights General Organizational Meeting','urban-knights-general-organizational-meeting','<p>Friday, October 11, 2019 at 6 PM – 9 PM</p>\n<p><span>This meeting will begin at 6 PM. The meeting will take place at GAI Consultants at 618 E South St Ste 700, Orlando, Florida 32801. Suggested parking is on the 4th floor. Signs are posted on entry doors regarding access to the meeting. We will have a guest speaker 6-7 PM then 7-8 PM discuss organization business. Following the meeting, we will go out nearby for fun.</span></p>\n<p><span>Meeting agenda will be posted on our website: <a href=\"https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/</a></span></p>\n<p><span>More information about the organization is also available on our website as well as social media.</span></p>','2019-10-05','2019-10-11','https://www.facebook.com/events/393343268018497/','Heather','(321) 946-9752','heather.croney@knights.ucf.edu','Heather Croney','Pending',224),(3011,'Join us for the 18th Annual Community Partners Nonprofit Conference!','join-us-for-the-18th-annual-community-partners-nonprofit-conference-1','<p><span>Join the School of Public Administration\'s nonprofit management program on Tuesday, October 29, 2019, from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. at the new UCF Downtown campus for an inspiring day of networking, discussion and collaboration.</span><br><br><span>The conference theme this year is \"Dream Big: Nonprofits and UCF building community partnerships.\"</span><br><br><span>As the newest neighbors in the downtown Orlando community, we can’t wait to learn more about our new neighborhood. Together, we will consider opportunities, share ideas, discuss existing resources, and break bread as a “creative village.” This conference focuses on building relationships and forming partnerships that will impact the community, local nonprofits, public leaders and UCF for years to come.</span></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/18th-annual-ucf-nonprofit-partners-conference-tickets-74288457777\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register</a> today!</span></p>','2019-10-08','2019-10-29','https://ccie.ucf.edu/public-administration/nonprofit-management/info/#conference','Justin Miller','(407) 823-3794','justin.miller@ucf.edu','UCF School of Public Administration','Publish',155),(3012,'RSVP for the 9th Annual Orlando Health Nursing Lecture // First Do No Harm: Accelerating the Journey to High Reliability','rsvp-for-the-9th-annual-orlando-health-nursing-lecture','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">FEATURED SPEAKER:</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Mary Jo Assi, DNP, RN, NEA-BC, FAAN</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">SVP Clinical Excellence Solutions </span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Associate Chief Nursing Officer, Press Ganey</span><br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Is it really possible to achieve zero harm? Findings in many industries, including healthcare, support that a commitment to zero harm is a critical first step to implementing a culture of safety. Join Mary Jo Assi to learn more about key principles of high reliability, how it is connected to the Magnet journey, why nurses are key stakeholders and leaders in that work, and the importance of the academic-clinical nursing partnership to achieve goals.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">After the lecture, attendees will be able to:</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">1. Recognize the connection between Magnet and high-reliability frameworks that can accelerate the journey to nursing excellence.</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">2. List the three types of human errors common in the health care setting.</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">3. Describe the primary purpose of a just culture framework.</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">4. Discuss three best nursing practices that promote a culture of safety and high reliability.</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">5. Discuss the importance of a strong academic and clinical nursing partnership to achieve goals.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Attendees will earn 2.0 nursing contact hours. </span><br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">DEADLINE to RSVP: Wednesday, October 23</span><br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">Questions? Contact us:</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">UCF College of Nursing Events</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">nursingevents@ucf.edu</span><br><span style=\"font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;\">407.823.2744</span></p>','2019-10-07','2019-10-30','https://www.ucffoundation.org/OrlandoHealthLecture?srctid=1&erid=d7208fc3-7935-4eb0-bbce-41fc54e060fb&trid=d7208fc3-7935-4eb0-bbce-41fc54e060fb&fbclid=IwAR17jKDkXtVvphSuhNJnAaNkJjeiYO20waSEQ_hCLPKDiyn','UCF College of Nursing Events','(407) 823-2744','nursingevents@ucf.edu','UCF College of Nursing','Publish',218),(3014,'Attend CGI U 2020 at the University of Edinburgh in Scotland!','attend-cgi-u-2020-at-the-university-of-edinburgh-in-scotland','<p><span>Are you interested in social change? Do you see a need in your community that needs to be addressed? Maybe you could be the one to solve it! </span></p>\n<p><span>Each year, the <a href=\"cgiu.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Clinton Global Initiative University (or CGI U)</a> hosts a meeting where students, university representatives, topic experts, and celebrities come together to discuss and develop innovative solutions to pressing global challenges. Students create their own Commitments to Action that address issues on campus, in local communities, or around the world. </span></p>\n<p><span>We are looking for motivated and passionate student leaders to join our CGI U Class of 2020. Accepted students will be invited to join President Bill Clinton and Chelsea Clinton in Scotland at the <strong>University of Edinburgh</strong> from <strong>April 17-19, 2020</strong>! The deadline for students to apply is November 4. Application information and resources can be found at <a href=\"http://cgiu.org/apply\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">cgiu.org/apply</a></span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://events.ucf.edu/event/1403628/clinton-global-initiative-university-information-session/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">For more information about CGI U Info Sessions, click here!</a></p>','2019-10-07','2019-11-04','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1403628/clinton-global-initiative-university-information-session/','Mike McFadden','(407) 823-2223','michael.mcfadden@ucf.edu','Mike McFadden','Publish',52),(3015,'Apply for UCF\'s Three Minute Thesis (3MT) Competition by Oct. 16 — and Win Money','apply-for-ucfs-three-minute-thesis-3mt-competition-by-oct-16-and-win-money','<p>Doctoral students, time is running out to enter UCF’s Three Minute Thesis (3MT) competition, which has scholarships up for grabs.</p>\n<p>The 3MT competition is an international contest that has doctoral candidates present their dissertation findings in three minutes before a panel of non-experts. The goal is to help graduate students learn to explain their research in an engaging and concise way, which non-academics can understand.</p>\n<p>At least $2,000 worth of scholarships will be awarded and participants may have a chance to compete at the regional and statewide 3MT competition.  For more information click here. <a href=\"https://graduate.ucf.edu/3mt/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://graduate.ucf.edu/3mt/</a></p>\n<p>Last year’s winner <a href=\"https://graduate.ucf.edu/news/article/students-wow-in-ucfs-first-ever-3-minute-thesis-competition\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">presented about the future of medicine and the possibility of diagnosing diseases from human breath.</a></p>\n<p>To apply, students need to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Record a 90-second audition video describing your dissertation research and its importance.  </li>\n<li>Post the video on YouTube and include “#UCF3MT” in the title. </li>\n<li>Fill out <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_85JOgPeo0VLAGah\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>the application</strong></a> by <strong>Oct. 16, 2019.</strong> </li>\n</ul>\n<p> Participants must be currently enrolled UCF doctoral students who have entered candidacy and are actively engaged in dissertation research. The top applicants will compete at the UCF 3MT competition on Wednesday, Nov. 20, from 3 to 4:30 p.m.</p>\n<p>The College of Graduate Studies, Blackstone LaunchPad and the Office of Research host the competition at UCF.</p>\n<p>For more information, please see <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgraduate.ucf.edu%2F3mt%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CNathalia.Bauer%40ucf.edu%7C3805c6627db04e671ac208d74c188800%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637061540549847384&amp;sdata=Z8%2Bhtq7vUQLJ4kNWVaYUO%2FG%2Fofpl%2F19RZdUVeOszjeY%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">graduate.ucf.edu/3mt</a> or email <a href=\"mailto:gradworkshops@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">gradworkshops@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2019-10-09','2019-10-16','https://graduate.ucf.edu/3mt/','College of Graduate Studies','(407) 823-2766','gradworkshops@ucf.edu','Zenaida Kotala','Publish',35),(3016,'USPS Employee of the Month August - Victoria Lall-Bhagirath','usps-employee-of-the-month-august-victoria-lall-bhagirath','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for August 2019: Victoria Beatrice Lall-Bhagirath. Victoria was hired at UCF in August 2015. She is currently a Certified Medical Assistant in UCF Health Services Gateway Office. Her nominators, Melanie Brodeur and Katie Safreed, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>“<em>Victoria has the “unofficial” title of Dr. Weinstein’s ‘right hand’. If anyone has a question, needs help, etc., she is the one to have the answers and lend the hand. She is hard working and dedicated to giving patients the best care they can receive. She puts the needs of the UCF patients first. They are her top priority and she always shows compassion and care. </em></p>\n<p><em>” Her work ethic is one to be admired and will always be 110% no matter what. She goes above and beyond her regular duties daily, is an exceptional employee and one of the most reliable workers. She is an asset to UCF Dermatology and UCF!”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Victoria receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf</a></p>','2019-10-11','2019-10-18','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','407-823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Pending',23),(3017,'Technical Skills Workshop: Community and Economic Development','technical-skills-workshop-community-and-economic-development','<p><span>Students are invited to come learn from guest speakers. This technical skill workshop/presentation will begin at 6 pm at the UCF Downtown Campus. The classroom is DPAC 102.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/368691897357306/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/events/368691897357306/</a> <br><br><span>Dominique Greco, the City of Orlando Nighttime Economy Manager, will present on managing the downtown Orlando nightlife and entertainment district as well as the nighttime economy and community development and management. She will share about the Rideshare Hub Pilot Program that is recently operating and launched in downtown Orlando. More information on this is here: </span><a data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orlando.gov%2FParking-Transportation%2FRideshare-Hub-Pilot-Program%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR1vxy_tfNk-xsf8F9oBYjLFtRSt54jTmv6z8pZzhU40KFGbSK2lTyO6xiA&amp;h=AT2eFXaqqWTU9DI3Il7N0zG67SRpPce7pEVp_nUDDgfs885UimwTAQ59lKo-sCPXLPJxtZJUBBDTe6v66fofoiYW0Vg_hyC4KeI-po0r-t3dpCB-wzXDHKy7DqroWro\" href=\"https://www.orlando.gov/Parking-Transportation/Rideshare-Hub-Pilot-Program?fbclid=IwAR1vxy_tfNk-xsf8F9oBYjLFtRSt54jTmv6z8pZzhU40KFGbSK2lTyO6xiA\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.orlando.gov/Parking-Transportation/Rideshare-Hub-Pilot-Program</a><br><br><span>Martin Hudson from the City of Orlando will also be speaking, and focusing on Place and Finance. Martin is the South Downtown Improvement District Project Manager.</span><br><br><span>Pauline Eaton from the City of Orlando will present on Place Making and Economic Development as well as the Orlando Main Streets Program.</span></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/</a></span></p>','2019-10-10','2019-10-15','https://www.facebook.com/events/368691897357306/','Heather Croney','(321) 946-9752','heather.croney@knights.ucf.edu','Heather Croney, President of Urban Knights','Pending',224),(3018,'Urban Knights General Organizational Meeting','urban-knights-general-organizational-meeting-1','<p>Friday, November 8th, 2019 at 6 PM – 8 PM</p>\n<p><span>This meeting will begin at 6 PM. The meeting will take place at GAI Consultants at 618 E South St Ste 700, Orlando, Florida 32801. Suggested parking is on the 4th floor. Signs are posted on entry doors regarding access to the meeting. We will have a guest speaker 6-7 PM then 7-8 PM discuss organization business. Following the meeting, we will go out nearby for fun.</span></p>\n<p><span>Meeting agenda will be posted on our website: <a href=\"https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/</a></span></p>\n<p><span>More information about the organization is also available on our website as well as social media.</span></p>','2019-10-10','2019-11-08','https://www.facebook.com/events/752109005242201/','Heather Croney','(321) 946-9752','urbanknights3@gmail.com','Heather Croney, President of Urban Knights','Publish',224),(3019,'Urban Knights General Organizational Meeting','urban-knights-general-organizational-meeting-1-2','<p>Friday, November 8th, 2019 at 6 PM – 8 PM</p>\n<p>