1,'Urban Knights General Organizational Meeting','urban-knights-general-organizational-meeting-1-2-3-4','<p>Friday, November 8th, 2019, at 6 p.m. to 8 p.m.</p>\n<p><span>This meeting will begin at 6 p.m. The meeting will take place at GAI Consultants at 618 E South St Ste 700, Orlando, Florida 32801. Suggested parking is on the 4th floor. Signs are posted on entry doors regarding access to the meeting. We will have a guest speaker from 6-7 p.m. then 7-8 p.m. to discuss organization business. Following the meeting, we will go out nearby for fun.</span></p>\n<p><span>Meeting agenda will be posted on our website: <a href=\"https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://urbanknightsucf.wordpress.com/</a></span></p>\n<p><span>More information about the organization is also available on our website as well as social media.</span></p>','2019-10-20','2019-11-08','https://www.facebook.com/events/752109005242201/','Heather Croney','(321) 946-9752','urbanknights3@gmail.com','Heather Croney, President of Urban Knights','Publish',224),(3022,'Enroll in Spring 2020: SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP Preparation Courses','spring-2020-shrm-cpshrm-scp-preparation-courses','<p>We partner with the Society for Human Resources Management to offer preparation using the SHRM Learning System materials for the SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP certification exams. The new SHRM certification recognizes that HR professionals are at the core of leading organizational success. It is built upon one singular body of knowledge designed to elevate the HR profession around the world. It ensures that the HR professional possesses the relevant HR knowledge required for today’s workplace, but it goes one step further. The SHRM certification tests the HR professional’s competencies – the ability to put knowledge to work through critical thinking and application.</p>\n<p>This course is offered in both <strong>live-online</strong> and <strong>in-person</strong> formats. Below are the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spring 2020</span> course dates:</p>\n<p><strong>East Orlando</strong> (<a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/zFYq6\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">map/directions</a>)<br> Start date: February 19<br> Wednesdays; 6:00-9:00pm</p>\n<p><strong>Live-Online<br> </strong>Start date: February 25<br> Tuesdays; 6:00-9:00pm<strong><br> </strong><em><br> </em>We have detailed information on this program and registration available on our web page at: <a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ce.ucf.edu/phrm</a>.  The 2020 SHRM Learning System books and online access, along with additional online and printed materials, will be included within the cost of the course registration fee. We offer the early bird registration fee of <strong>$1249.00</strong> until January 17. After January 17, the cost of the course is <strong>$1349.00</strong>. A discounted rate of <strong>$1299.00</strong> is available for UCF faculty/student/staff/alumni, SHRM, CFEC, and GOOD members.</p>\n<p>Additionally, UCF Continuing Education offers payment plans in which course fees can be paid in installments prior to the start of the course. You are able to also view these on our website, and we have options that allow participants to complete the payment in either two or three installments.</p>\n<p>If you would like to learn more about the SHRM-CP/SHRM-SCP credentials, the eligibility, application or exam process, please visit <a href=\"http://certification.shrm.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://certification.shrm.org/</a></p>\n<p>Although this course is preparatory for the SHRM-CP and SHRM-SCP Certification exams, not all participants intend to sit for SHRM’s exams after the course. We welcome HR practitioners into this course for the valuable knowledge and professional development and participants will also receive a certificate of completion at the end of the course.</p>','2019-10-14','2020-02-12','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Professional-Human-Resources-Management-SHRM-CP-and-SHRM-SCP','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','lisa.ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno','Publish',30),(3023,'Applied Project Management Certificate Program - Project Management Professional (PMP) - Classes starts in January!','applied-project-management-certificate-program-project-management-professional-pmp-classes-starts-in-january','<p><strong>UCF’s Applied Project Management Certificate Program: </strong></p>\n<p>This Project Management course provides an applied approach to Project Management preparing participants to work in a project management capacity.  This course also prepares participants for the PMP or CAPM exams administered through the Project Management Institute (PMI). </p>\n<p><strong>APPLIED PROJECT MANAGEMENT CERTIFICATE PROGRAM </strong><a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>www.ce.ucf.edu/PM</strong></a></p>\n<p><strong>January 2020 Course:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>IMPORANT NOTE</strong> This session is designed to prepare CAPM/PMP students who seek to test prior to the <a href=\"https://www.pmi.org/certifications/types/project-management-pmp/exam-prep/changes\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">expiration</a> of the current version of the PMP/CAPM exam (June 30, 2020).<br> <br> <strong>Face-to-face Instruction</strong></p>\n<p>Tuesday evenings, January 7, 2020 – March 24, 2020</p>\n<p>5:30 - 9:30 p.m.</p>\n<p><strong>Registration Fee: </strong>$2,495 ($2,395.00 discounted UCF Alumni Registration fee available)</p>\n<p>Fee includes all program textbooks and materials. Materials include pre and post test questions, flashcards, final practice exam, exercises for practical application, online learning system, Textbook with PowerPoint Slides, 3 books that parallel the PMBOK and more resources.</p>\n<p>The course will cover the following topics: Project Management Concepts, Project Management Framework, Project Management Skills, Integration, Scope, Time, Cost, Quality, Human Resources, Communications, Risk, Procurement, Stakeholder and CAPM/PMP Exam review</p>\n<p><em>Full Payment plan options in either two installments or three installments are offered. </em>You are able to visit our website to access the course payment plan under the payment plan tab and view course details for the CAPM or PMP:</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ce.ucf.edu/PM\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>www.ce.ucf.edu/PM</strong></a></p>\n<p><strong>Why Choose our Program? </strong></p>\n<p>Our 12 session IN-PERSON program includes</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>The most up-to-date curriculum that aligns with the PMBOK® Guide –Sixth Edition.</strong></li>\n<li>One year access to an <strong>online learning system</strong> with a repository of study resources including a pre-test to help identify topics you already know and areas that require more time and attention</li>\n<li>A <strong>computer-based practice exam</strong> is included that mimics the actual certification exam in style, function, timing and weighted topics.</li>\n<li><strong>Learn and apply project management tools</strong> and techniques that are applicable to initiating, planning, executing, monitoring, controlling and closing a project.</li>\n<li>Our program <strong>meets PMI’s PM education requirement</strong> to become eligible to sit for the CAPM® or PMP® exam.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Our program <strong>qualifies</strong> for most company tuition reimbursements and we offer payment plans.</p>','2019-10-14','2020-01-06','https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Program/Applied-Project-Management-Certificate-Project-Management-Professional-PMP','Lisa Ruscigno','(407) 882-0337','lisa.ruscigno@ucf.edu','Lisa Ruscigno, UCF Continuing Education','Publish',30),(3024,'Technical Skills Workshop: Community and Economic Development','technical-skills-workshop-community-and-economic-development-1','<p>Technical Skills Workshop: Community and Economic Development</p>\n<p>Tuesday, October 15th, 2019</p>\n<p>6-9 PM</p>\n<p>DPAC 102</p>\n<p>The UCF Urban Knights Planning Students Organization organizes workshops to bring professionals and current happenings to the classroom for students to meet and learn from.</p>\n<p>During the Community &amp; Economic Development course, students in the class, as well as other interested students, are invited to come learn from guest speakers. This technical skill workshop/presentation will begin at 6 pm at the UCF Downtown Campus. The classroom is DPAC 102.<br><br>Dominique Greco, the City of Orlando Nighttime Economy Manager, will present on managing the downtown Orlando nightlife and entertainment district as well as the nighttime economy and community development and management. She will share about the Rideshare Hub Pilot Program that is recently operating and launched in downtown Orlando. More information on this is here: <a data-lynx-mode=\"hover\" data-lynx-uri=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orlando.gov%2FParking-Transportation%2FRideshare-Hub-Pilot-Program%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR2MZJ5YlWJUo13HtFpIgG4gh-QDhg0jFcUwt5gjft7Y-7xlbtGb9ngnEP4&amp;h=AT2c196PACNBoaGL3Todd5nLdcDJzVZXiR2_4ZNaTBbXTY5WkB_1TfRhMq4YLfM4TWRwCyDeQF8sZm8HUAkiZ_HNxp00RjvcBcOFSAAnNpCVRYbwby2VY-AThSJJl6IJ7Q\" href=\"https://www.orlando.gov/Parking-Transportation/Rideshare-Hub-Pilot-Program?fbclid=IwAR2MZJ5YlWJUo13HtFpIgG4gh-QDhg0jFcUwt5gjft7Y-7xlbtGb9ngnEP4\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.orlando.gov/Parking-Transportation/Rideshare-Hub-Pilot-Program</a><br><br>Martin Hudson from the City of Orlando will also be speaking, and focusing on Place and Finance. Martin is the South Downtown Improvement District Project Manager.<br><br>Pauline Eaton from the City of Orlando will present on Place Making and Economic Development as well as the Orlando Main Streets Program.</p>','2019-10-13','2019-10-16','https://www.facebook.com/events/368691897357306/','UCF Urban Knights','(321) 946-9752','urbank','UCF Urban Knights','Pending',224),(3025,'Affordable Housing Town Hall at UCF','affordable-housing-town-hall-at-ucf','<p>The <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Floufreyinstitute.org%2F&amp;data=02%7C01%7CShena.Parks%40ucf.edu%7C24db921157a3469b342f08d7518753a4%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637067513970080254&amp;sdata=5Rn4Wm%2F3EKzgq%2BrMbodpkalMp7Qlz3dmvUT%2FR%2FPRmLE%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Lou Frey Institute</strong></a> is hosting an Affordable Housing Town Hall at UCF in partnership with Florida State House Representatives <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.myfloridahouse.gov%2FSections%2FRepresentatives%2Fdetails.aspx%3FMemberId%3D4642%26LegislativeTermId%3D88&amp;data=02%7C01%7CShena.Parks%40ucf.edu%7C24db921157a3469b342f08d7518753a4%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637067513970090246&amp;sdata=VTMGjTYP%2B2dmIAjBNpz1A6fgsgCK3Ji0Cr0Ygj9RU1Y%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Carlos Guillermo Smith \'03</strong></a>, <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.myfloridahouse.gov%2FSections%2FRepresentatives%2Fdetails.aspx%3FMemberId%3D4746%26LegislativeTermId%3D88&amp;data=02%7C01%7CShena.Parks%40ucf.edu%7C24db921157a3469b342f08d7518753a4%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637067513970090246&amp;sdata=3ZfX7eyEP6EJoHtrCsyV8TRwTQ%2FlGtFeG%2FBct4hWtj4%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Anna Eskamani \'12 \'15MA</strong></a> and District 5 Commissioner <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orangecountyfl.net%2FBoardofCommissioners%2FDistrict5Commissioner.aspx%23.XaSiQkZKi70&amp;data=02%7C01%7CShena.Parks%40ucf.edu%7C24db921157a3469b342f08d7518753a4%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637067513970100239&amp;sdata=nQa0dKqfS6ZLQB8emDxuXXGLalDkzxULffdApFsM0Ic%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Emily Bonilla \'03</strong></a>. The event will be held to discuss affordable housing in Central Florida, with a special focus on its impact on college students.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>This event is<em> <strong>FREE</strong> </em>and open to the public!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Parking is available in Parking Garage A </em></p>\n<p><em>and Lot B5 for $5 per vehicle.</em></p>','2019-10-15','2019-10-30','https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2Fy3y2fmk6&data=02%7C01%7CShena.Parks%40ucf.edu%7C24db921157a3469b342f08d7518753a4%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%','Shena Parks','(407) 823-0644','shena.parks@ucf.edu','Shena Parks','Pending',9),(3026,'Congratulations to Torie Lall-Bhagirath — USPS Employee of the Month for August','usps-employee-of-the-month-august-torie-lall-bhagirath','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for August 2019: Victoria Beatrice Lall-Bhagirath. Victoria was hired at UCF in August 2015. She is currently a Certified Medical Assistant in UCF Health Services Gateway Office. Her nominators, Melanie Brodeur and Katie Safreed, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p>“<em>Victoria has the “unofficial” title of Dr. Weinstein’s ‘right hand’.  If anyone has a question, needs help, etc., she is the one to have the answers and lend the hand.  She is hard working and dedicated to giving patients the best care they can receive.  She puts the needs of the UCF patients first.  They are her top priority and she always shows compassion and care. </em></p>\n<p><em>” Her work ethic is one to be admired and will always be 110% no matter what.  She goes above and beyond her regular duties daily, is an exceptional employee and one of the most reliable workers.  She is an asset to UCF Dermatology and UCF!”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Victoria receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Annual Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff.  We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf</a></p>','2019-10-31','2019-11-07','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(3027,'Participate in Leadership Week 2020','leadership-week-2020','<p>The LEAD Scholars Academy invites individuals to share their leadership knowledge and experience with the UCF campus during Leadership Week 2020. The committee is looking for workshops/sessions that will challenge and inspire the campus community and showcase current leadership topics.  Please complete the <strong>program proposal form at</strong><strong>  </strong><a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0qbJviGCi0CNhOt\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Leadership Week 2020</a> or <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0qbJviGCi0CNhOt\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0qbJviGCi0CNhOt</a></p>\n<p>The deadline to submit a program proposal is <strong>Friday, November 7, 2019</strong>. Program proposals will be evaluated and presenters will be notified by November 15, 2019.</p>\n<p><em>For more information please contact  Dr. Germayne Graham at </em><a href=\"mailto:Germayne.Graham@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Germayne.Graham@ucf.edu</a> <em>or</em> <em>Leah Freeman at  </em><a href=\"mailto:leahfreeman@Knights.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">leahfreeman@Knights.ucf.edu</a></p>','2019-10-21','2019-11-10','http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0qbJviGCi0CNhOt','Germayne Graham','(407) 823-2223','germayne.graham@ucf.edu','Germayne Graham','Publish',41),(3028,'Congratulations to Pamela McGlinchey — USPS Employee of the Month for September','usps-employee-of-the-month-september-pamela-mcglinchey','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for September 2019: Pamela McGlinchey. Ms. McGlinchey was hired at UCF in May 2015. She is currently the Administrative Assistant in Modern Languages and Literature in the College of Arts and Humanities. Her nominators, Dr. Chiara Mazzucchelli and Dr. Geri Smith, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>          “Pam’s excellent work record in our department clearly meets and supersedes the criteria for this award in every respect. Her professionalism is invaluable and can be easily seen in her dependability and timeliness in completing assignments, even the dreaded paperwork; in her ability to prioritize work and manager her time. </em></p>\n<p><em>          Pam takes the initiative to make our department function better and ensure we comply with UCF and college policies. She lives the values of diversity and inclusion, has the well-being of students and colleagues at the top of her priorities, and consistently lives up to UCF’s highest ideals, making Pam an outstanding member of the UCF Community “.</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Pamela receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, her name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Knight Star Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf</a></p>','2019-10-31','2019-11-08','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',23),(3033,'Drop off Your Donations for the Bahamas Disaster Relief Drive','bahamas-disaster-relief-drive-drop-donation-center-1-2-3-4','<p>Please join the Nonprofit Leadership students at UCF for a drive and drop donation center to aid the Bahamas with disaster relief! We will be at Faith Assembly of God on November 9, 2019 from 12pm-5pm.</p>\n<p><span>9307 Curry Ford Rd. Orlando, FL, 32825</span></p>\n<p>Items in need: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Building supplies (Plywood/lumber, roofing material, nails, drip caps, etc.)</li>\n<li>Cleaning supplies (Mops, buckets, towels, gloves, wet wiped, trash bags, bleach, etc.)</li>\n<li>Groceries (Water, Canned goods, non-perishable dry goods, baby food, baby formula, etc.)</li>\n<li>Home &amp; Outdoor (Generators, portable stoves, blankets, air mattresses, pillows, sheets, etc.)</li>\n<li>Safety &amp; Hygiene (First Aid kits, water filtration devices, mosquito repellant, diapers, flashlights, etc.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For a full list of donation ideas please visit our eventbrite page:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bahamas-disaster-relief-drive-drop-donation-center-tickets-77880351227?aff=ebdssbeac\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bahamas-disaster-relief-drive-drop-donation-center-tickets-77880351227?aff=ebdssbeac</a></p>','2019-10-24','2019-11-09','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/bahamas-disaster-relief-drive-drop-donation-center-tickets-77880351227?aff=ebdssbeac','Raejah Burgess','(239) 634-3299','rburgess3@knights.ucf.edu','Raejah Burgess','Publish',223),(3035,'Attend the NEW Master of Public Policy Online Info Session','new-master-of-public-policy-online-info-session','<p>Do you have an interest in policy as it relates to local, state or federal government; health; transportation; and more? Want to learn more about UCF\'s<span> </span><strong>new</strong><span> </span>Master of Public Policy based in downtown Orlando? Then you don\'t want to miss this! </p>\n<p>Join Dr. Abdul-Akeem Sadiq on the first virtual information session for the program. Learn about the program curriculum, application requirements and employment opportunities related to public policy. Did we forget to mention that you can tune in from the comfort of your own home or in between your meetings? </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://applynow.graduate.ucf.edu/register/MPP1119\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register</a><span> </span>now to secure your spot! </p>','2019-10-31','2019-11-19','https://ccie.ucf.edu/public-administration/public-policy/','Edlira Dursun','(407) 823-2604','edlira.dursun@ucf.edu','UCF School of Public Administration','Publish',155),(3037,'Submit Your Proposal for the Public Administration Research Conference','submit-your-proposal-for-the-public-administration-research-conference-1','<p><strong>Call for proposals - due soon!</strong></p>\n<p>The Public Administration Research Conference invites submissions for proposals incorporating community engagement and social justice approaches to address public interests in complex urban environments in an effort to maintain community resilience and sustainability.<br><br>Global crises require us to focus our attention on the development of evidence-based policies and to expect those policies to address public interests that include everything from utilizing renewable energy sources to minimizing opportunities for government corruption. Sustainability and resilience are critical for every community, but they are especially important for governance in complex urban environments. <br><br>Proposals may be research papers, case studies, best practices, etc. that address this conference theme in a wide range of public management and policy domains, including, but not limited to: human and social services, nonprofit management, budgeting and financial management, emergency management, and planning and economic development. Proposals should be submitted by<span> </span><strong>November 25, 2019</strong>. For more information, visit the<span> <a href=\"https://ucfparc.wordpress.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">website</a>. </span></p>','2019-10-31','2019-11-26','https://ucfparc.wordpress.com/','Justin Miller','(407) 823-3794','justin.miller@ucf.edu','Center for Public and Nonprofit Management','Publish',155),(3038,'Want to teach English conversation overseas?  Get your TEFL Certificate at UCF in 2020 :-)','want-to-teach-english-conversation-overseas-get-your-tefl-certificate-at-ucf-in-2020-','<p>Want to teach English conversation overseas?  A professor who has taught English in Japan, Saudi Arabia, Malaysia, and Kuwait will explain UCF\'s <strong>TEFL Certificate</strong> program (<a href=\"../../degree/teaching-english-as-a-foreign-language-tefl-certificate/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ucf.edu/degree/teaching-english-as-a-foreign-language-tefl-certificate/</a>) and answer your questions (<a href=\"https://mll.cah.ucf.edu/programs/tesol-faq/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://mll.cah.ucf.edu/programs/tesol-faq/</a>). </p>\n<p>This certificate is open to ALL students of ALL majors.  You do not need extensive teaching experience or an education degree.  </p>\n<p>Hundreds of students have already graduated with this certificate and gotten great jobs all over the world after graduation (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Undergraduate-TEFL-Certificate-at-UCF-263007397052557/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/Undergraduate-TEFL-Certificate-at-UCF-263007397052557/</a>).  </p>\n<p><strong>This talk will take place six times in Trevor Colbourn Hall, Room 358 B, on:  </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Nov. 12 (4-5pm), </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Nov. 13 (2-3pm), </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Nov. 14 (4-5pm), </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Dec. 4 (2-3pm), </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Dec. 9 (2-3pm), </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Dec. 9 (4-5pm).</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Thanks! </p>','2019-11-06','2019-12-09','https://docs.google.com/document/d/106sUnoYAi1yMpIVy8_nK6X2yVmjWIFxyOMTk0Syc4kw/edit?usp=sharing','Keith Folse','(407) 823-2472','keith.folse@ucf.edu','Keith Folse, Professor TESOL','Publish',231),(3044,'UCF I-Corps program hiring student intern!','ucf-i-corps-program-hiring-student-intern-1-2-3-4-5','<p><span>UCF I-Corps program is looking to hire a student intern to help deliver our program.  The student will be responsible for coordinating program logistics, performing recruitment activities, and working with UCF researchers and entrepreneurs.  Ideal candidates are self starters with a passion for innovation and tech entrepreneurship.  Interested applications should send a resume and LinkedIn profile link to robin.phelps@ucf.edu.  </span></p>','2019-11-11','2019-11-29','https://icorps.cie.ucf.edu/','Daniel Elbrecht','(407) 882-0663','daniel.elbrecht@ucf.edu','UCF I-Corps','Publish',191),(3047,'Electronic Literature Organization Conference and Media Arts Festival Call for Submissions','electronic-literature-organization-conference-and-media-arts-festival-call-for-submissions','<p><span>We invite submissions for presentations, performances, and exhibition pieces at the annual Electronic Literature Organization Conference and Media Arts Festival (ELO), to be held July 16-19, 2020, at the University of Central Florida in downtown Orlando. </span><span>ELO seeks proposals related to electronic literature, or e-lit–literary works in which computation forms some essential part of the aesthetic. #ELOrlando offers an opportunity to share research and creative contributions within an engaging, collegial atmosphere comprising e-lit scholars and practitioners from across the globe.</span></p>','2019-11-06','2019-12-01','https://elo.cah.ucf.edu/','Anastasia Salter',NULL,'anastasia@ucf.edu','Anastasia Salter','Publish',233),(3048,'USPS Employee of the Month - October 2019 Cpl Frank Imparato','usps-employee-of-the-month-october-2019-cpl-frank-imparato','<p> </p>\n<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for October 2019: Cpl. Frank Imparato. Cpl. Imparato is a Law Enforcement Corporal in the UCF Police Department. He has been employed at UCF since January 2011. His nominators, Commander Scott Freeman and Commander James Mangan, had this to say about him:</p>\n<p><em>“On the first day UCF Police Department was providing law enforcement coverage at the new Downtown Campus, Cpl. Imparato responded to the scene of a construction incident where he found a gravely injured worker. Cpl. Imparato began performing life-saving care, including CPR on the worker, which allowed the worker to be saved and transported to the hospital. Without Cpl. Imparato’ s immediate care, the worker most likely would have died on the scene. In additional, Cpl. Imparato’s passion for helping others is demonstrated by being the UCF Police Department’s CPR Instructor and instructed many officers in how to provide lifesaving care.</em></p>\n<p><em>Cpl. Imparato’s actions to save the life of a stranger exemplifies the UCF Mission, Values and Goals</em><em> “.</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Cpl. Imparato receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, his name in lights on the UCF campus marquee, and an introduction to the Board of Trustees. He is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Knight Star Awards Program.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf</a></p>','2019-11-13','2019-11-22','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process-2019-20.pdf','Deborah Frankenbach','(407) 823-2777','deborah.frankenbach@ucf.edu','Deborah Frankenbach','Publish',23),(3049,'Attend Free Physical Therapy Screenings','free-physical-therapy-screenings','<p>Do you have muscle or joint pain?</p>\n<p>The team from Advent Health Sports Med and Rehab UCF Clinic (located in the Health Center) invite<span> </span><strong>YOU</strong><span> </span>to visit them outside of the Student Union on Friday, November 15th, any time between 8:00 am-10:00 am to receive a free screening and a giveaway item from a licensed physical therapist. You will be provided with expert advice on how to alleviate your pain and get quickly back to the things you love!</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Open to Students, Faculty, and Staff!</p>','2019-11-12','2019-11-15','https://events.ucf.edu/event/1451854/free-physical-therapy-screenings/','Crystal Zavallo','(407) 823-0776','crystal.zavallo@ucf.edu','UCF Student Health Services','Publish',235),(3050,'Don\'t Miss the Eminent Scholars Lecture Series!','dont-miss-the-eminent-scholars-lecture-series','<p>The Center for Public and Noprofit Management invites you to the Fall 2019 Eminent Scholars Lecture Series. </p>','2019-11-20','2019-12-06','https://ccie.ucf.edu/cpnm/about/lecture-series/','Justin Miller','(407) 823-3794','cpnm@ucf.edu','Center for Public and Nonprofit Management','Publish',155),(3052,'Enhancing Relationships & Empowering Careers (For Couples)','enhancing-relationships-empowering-careers-for-couples','<p><strong><span>Holidays putting stress on your relationship?</span></strong><span>  Want to enjoy a <em><strong>date night</strong></em> with your partner? Parents, what about a <strong><em>FUN</em></strong> <strong>place for your child </strong>to enjoy and engage in arts and crafts? How about enjoy delicious, fresh, <em><strong>catered</strong></em><strong> </strong><em><strong>meals </strong></em>and<em> </em>earn up to <strong>$100 in <em>gift cards</em></strong>?  If you answered <strong><u>YES</u></strong> to any of the questions above, please <u>call</u> us at <strong>407-823-1748. </strong>Project Harmony offers couples the opportunity at <strong><em>NO COST </em></strong>to spend quality time together, while enhancing their ability to resolve conflicts, improve communication skills, and manage stress. The program also includes a workshop that can assist with financial goals, as well as help explore one’s strengths and experiences to create a more fulfilling career path. </span></p>\n<p><span>Funding for this project was provided by the United States Department of Health and Human Services, Administration for Children and Families, Grant: # 90FM0078. These services are available to all eligible persons, regardless of race, gender, age, disability, or religion. Project Harmony is classified as a research study