Ashlinn Morris, Krizia Negron, David A. Organista, Amy Pauli, Shakarr Presley, Chantal Rios, Margeaux Rogers, Sarah Taylor, Lucy West, Savannah Wheaton, and Simona Wiig<strong><em></em></strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>Exhibition Dates: March 15 - 25, 2021<br><br></strong></em>Our physical gallery space has reopened! Hours of operation are as follows:<em><strong><br></strong></em><strong>Monday - Thursday:<span> </span></strong>10 a.m. - 5 p.m.<strong><br>Friday:<span> </span></strong>10 a.m. - 4 p.m. <br><em>Virtual exhibition link: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/amalgamBFA\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/amalgamBFA</a></em></p>\n<p><em><span>Free parking is available in Garage F next to CFE Arena. $5 parking lot H-4 or Garage I requires purchasing a visitor permit from a kiosk. Please note that visitors should park in green student spaces ONLY, as the $5 daily permit does not cover red and blue spaces.</span></em></p>','2021-03-14','2021-03-25','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/experimental-animation-bfa-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',200),(3267,'Apply for Women’s Executive Council Scholarships through June 30','apply-for-womens-executive-council-scholarships-through-june-30','<p>The Women’s Executive Council (WEC), an external professional women’s group, is accepting scholarship applications for its 2021 cycle. The amount of each scholarship, $1,972, commemorates the year WEC was founded. In 2020, WEC awarded 46 academic scholarships.</p>\n<p>Requirements,</p>\n<ul>\n<li>3.0 GPA</li>\n<li>Be registered for at least 12 credit hours at one of the following schools: Daytona State College; Florida A&amp;M University; Florida Institute of Technology; Herzing University (Orlando); Rollins College (College of Liberal Arts); Rollins College; Seminole State College; <strong>University of Central Florida</strong>; or Valencia College. </li>\n<li><em>High School</em> students must be a senior and registered to attend one of the above stated colleges/universities for Summer or Fall 2021.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>DEADLINE</strong>: June 30, 2021 (Applications and all materials must be submitted via email by 5:00 p.m.)</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>APPLICATION</strong> and full criteria information are available on the <a href=\"https://www.wecorlando.com/Scholarship-Application-Information/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">WEC website</a>.</p>','2021-03-02','2021-06-30','https://www.wecorlando.com/Scholarship-Application-Information/','Maritza Martinez-Guerrero','(407) 235-3935','Maritza.Martinez@ucf.edu','Maritza Martinez-Guerrero','Publish',165),(3268,'USPS Employee of the Month (February): Shirley Jeffrey','usps-employee-of-the-month-february-shirley-jeffrey','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for February 2021: Shirley Jeffrey.</p>\n<p><br>Shirley Jeffrey is an Administrative Assistant III in Undergraduate Affairs in the College of Community Innovation and Education. Her nominators, Katy Weilant and Megan Mitchell had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><br><em>“Shirley has shown commitment to UCF\'s values. She possesses integrity and is always humble and honest with everything she does. She is a life-learner and is always striving to learn more and do more. She promotes a sense of community by treating our team like family and helps make us a cohesive unit. She consistently comes up with creative ways to help business practices move more efficiently. She takes a lot of pride in her work and holds herself to very high standards, showing her excellence. She strives to be the best she can be and continues to keep growing, personally and professionally at UCF.</em></p>\n<p><br><em>Since our office has begun gradually re-opening after the COVID-19 campus closure, Shirley eagerly volunteered to work daily at both of our advising office locations on the main campus and downtown to prepare the office to meet with students, faculty, and staff in an environment that complies with CDC guidelines. Shirley is always the first to volunteer to do work behind the scenes that will make the jobs of her staff easier and better. She does these things with humility in that she truly wants to assist and serve the greater good, which is to serve our students, faculty, and staff. For anyone who knows Shirley, she takes a lot of pride in her work and is a vocal, passionate supporter of UCF and its mission to serve the Knights Community. All in all, the Undergraduate Affairs team is better because Shirley is a part of it“.</em></p>\n<p><br>As USPS Employee of the Month, Shirley receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Knight Star Awards.</p>\n<p><br>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2021-03-04','2021-03-19','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Theresa Scipione','(407) 823-6711','theresa.scipione@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',265),(3269,'2021 Financial Wellness Series','2021-financial-wellness-series','<p>The Financial Wellness Series is a monthlong event, held between April 1st-30th, where the UCF HR Benefits section hosts a series of workshops, presentations, and webinars designed to provide UCF employees with practical tools and resources to build their financial knowledge and future. Throughout the series, various vendors, companies, financial planners, and even UCF professors will provide extremely helpful information and material on how you can save money in different ways and plan for more a financially secure future.</p>\n<p>Schedules and descriptions of workshops and other series details: <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series</a><span>.</span></p>\n<p> For questions please contact <a href=\"mailto:benefits@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">benefits@ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2021-03-15','2021-04-29','https://hr.ucf.edu/financial-wellness-series','HR Benefits','(407) 823-2771','Benefits@ucf.edu','Venessa Williams','Publish',189),(3270,'Hispanic Heritage Scholarship Fund of Metro Orlando Now Open','hispanic-heritage-scholarship-fund-of-metro-orlando-now-open','<p>The Hispanic Heritage Scholarship Fund of Metro Orlando (HHSFMO) application period is now open.  Every year, the HHSFMO awards an average of 20 scholarships. Awards range between <strong>$2,500 and $5,000 each</strong>.</p>\n<p> To qualify, students must:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be of Hispanic heritage</li>\n<li>Have a minimum overall average GPA of 3.0 on a scale of 4.0 (or equivalent)</li>\n<li>Have plans to enroll full-time in an undergraduate program at an accredited university in Orange, Seminole, Osceola, or Lake counties for the 2021-2022 academic year,</li>\n<li>Be a United States citizen, a legal permanent resident, have the designation of Deferred Action For Childhood Arrivals (DACA) or be an eligible citizen as defined by the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA). </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Application is available <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hhsfmo.org%2Fapply&amp;data=04%7C01%7CNicole.Dudenhoefer%40ucf.edu%7C6a2f73be57d442c674ef08d8e31271d6%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637509015641176472%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=Ib09l9aM5dVhRrjkrhMpKqNmaIDya6tM%2Fxwy4VHuSzk%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">here. </a> </p>\n<p><strong>DEADLINE</strong> for application and FAFSA: March 15</p>\n<p><strong>DEADLINE</strong> for letters of recommendation and sealed transcripts: March 22</p>\n<p>For complete details, please visit, visit <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hhsfmo.org%2F&amp;data=04%7C01%7CNicole.Dudenhoefer%40ucf.edu%7C6a2f73be57d442c674ef08d8e31271d6%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637509015641186473%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=iLM4cq76fHFHDZSfcakQ7gtO22S2avFVVGxHtSvE8t0%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.hhsfmo.org</a></p>','2021-03-09','2021-03-22','http://www.hhsfmo.org','Maritza Martinez',NULL,'Maritza.Martinez@ucf.edu','UCF Communications','Publish',166),(3271,'Deadline Approaches to Apply for Hispanic Heritage Scholarship Fund','deadline-approaches-to-apply-for-hispanic-heritage-scholarship-fund','<p>The <strong>Hispanic Heritage Scholarship Fund</strong> of Metro Orlando (HHSFMO) application period is <strong>now open</strong>.  Every year, the HHSFMO awards an average of 20 scholarships, and awards range between <strong>$2500 and $5000 each</strong>.</p>\n<p> To qualify, students must:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be of Hispanic heritage,</li>\n<li>Have a minimum overall average of 3.0 on a scale of 4.0 (or equivalent),</li>\n<li>Have plans to enroll full-time in an undergraduate program at an accredited university in Orange, Seminole, Osceola, or Lake counties for the 2021-2022 academic year,</li>\n<li>Be a United States citizen, a legal permanent resident, have the designation of Deferred Action For Childhood Arrivals (DACA) or be an eligible citizen as defined by the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA). </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.hhsfmo.org/apply\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Apply Now</a></strong></p>\n<p><strong>DEADLINE</strong> for application and FAFSA: March 15</p>\n<p><strong>DEADLINE</strong> for letters of recommendation and sealed transcripts: March 22</p>\n<p>For complete details, please visit, visit <a href=\"http://www.hhsfmo.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.hhsfmo.org</a>.</p>','2021-03-10','2021-03-15','http://www.hhsfmo.org/apply','Maritza Martinez-Guerrero','(407) 235-3935','Maritza.Martinez@ucf.edu','Maritza Martinez-Guerrero','Publish',165),(3272,'Tune Into the 2021 Knight Star Awards','2021-knight-star-awards','<p><span>Please join us for an afternoon of celebration as UCF Human Resources recognizes our dedicated employees at the virtual 2021 Knight Star Awards. The event will be streamed on UCF’s YouTube and Facebook channels on Wednesday, May 26 at 3 p.m. Honorees include employees celebrating years of service milestones, retirees, and the recipients of the USPS Employee of the Year Award and Gabor A&amp;P Excellence Award.</span></p>\n<p><span>For more details, please visit the <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Knight Star Awards webpage</a></span><span>. We look forward to seeing you there!</span></p>','2021-03-15','2021-05-26','https://hr.ucf.edu/contentblock/annual-awards-program/','Lee Williams','(407) 823-0858','lee.williams@ucf,edu','Lee Williams','Publish',24),(3273,'USPS Employee of the Month Nominations','usps-employee-of-the-month-nominations-1','<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees.</p>\n<p>All USPS Employee of the Month recipients receive a $200 cash award, two $25 gift cards, and additional recognition.  The 12 USPS Employees of the Month are also eligible for the prestigious USPS Employee of the Year award with an additional $2,500 award presented at the Knight Star Awards.</p>\n<p>To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p>If you have questions, please contact Theresa.Scipione@ucf.edu or 407-823-6711.</p>','2021-03-17','2021-03-24','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Theresa Scipione','(407) 823-6711','theresa.scipione@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',265),(3274,'Safe Knight Weeks Starts March 29','safe-knight-weeks-starts-march-29','<p>UCF will host a series of interactive events at the end of March to raise awareness about safety and well-being.</p>\n<p>The goal of Safe Knight Week, which runs March 29-April 1, is to provide health and safety-related learning opportunities.</p>\n<p>Monday kicks off with a “Safety Search,” where students will scour the campus in search of clues throughout the week. Those who complete the scavenger hunt will receive a limited-edition prize.</p>\n<p>Tuesday’s highlights include an <em>Among Us </em>drop-in — a multi-player, social deduction game where Knights are either crewmates or imposters — on Discord. Additionally, a special virtual training session will be hosted by Green Dot, a nationally recognized bystander intervention course that educates the community about reactive and proactive ways to safely intervene when faced with violence.</p>\n<p>Wednesday’s events include a FreshU virtual cooking demonstration, where participants will learn how to make a healthy, delicious, galaxy-themed meal. Wellness Health and Promotion Services will provide all the ingredients included in the dish while supplies last. There will also be a virtual Arboretum safety course from UCF’s Landscape and Natural Resources team and a self-defense class hosted by the UCF Police Department.</p>\n<p>Thursday will feature a SkyWarn training, where participants will learn how to identify weather hazards from the National Weather Service. Counseling and Psychological Services will host a virtual Paws-itively Stress Free event with therapy animals. A session of Yoga Under the Stars at Lake Claire will provide a relaxing end to an informative and fun-filled week.</p>\n<p>Many of these events require pre-registration to attend. View the <a href=\"https://events.ucf.edu/tag/268237096/safe-knight-week/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Events Calendar</a> for a full listing of the week’s activities and registration information.</p>\n<p>Safe Knight Week 2020 is a collaboration among Wellness and Health Promotion Services; Recreation and Wellness Center; Student Care Services; Environmental Health &amp; Safety; Green Dot; Student Health Services; UCF Police Department; Department of Emergency Management; Counseling &amp; Psychological Services; Office of Institutional Equity; and Student Government.</p>\n<p> </p>','2021-03-17','2021-04-01','https://events.ucf.edu/tag/268237096/safe-knight-week/','Amanda Sellers',NULL,'amanda.sellers@ucf.edu','Amanda Sellers','Publish',165),(3275,'S. Kent Butler Honored for Career Excellence','s-kent-butler-honored-for-career-excellence','<p>S. Kent Butler Jr. has been named the 2021 Outstanding Higher Education Professional by the University of Connecticut’s Neag School of Education Alumni Board. This award annually honors a graduate of UConn’s Neag School of Education who demonstrates excellence and has made significant contributions to their profession. </p>\n<p>UCF’s interim chief Equity, Inclusion and Diversity earned his Bachelor of Science in communication sciences in 1985 from UConn, as well as his Master of Science in counseling psychology and his Ph.D. in educational psychology from UConn’s Neag School, in 1994 and in 1999, respectively. A professor of counselor education and school psychology at UCF, Butler has been serving in higher education for more than two decades, including currently being part of the UCF president’s cabinet, overseeing the Office of Diversity and Inclusion. His research — spanning such areas as African American student achievement and success as well as multicultural and social justice issues in counseling — has been widely presented and published at the national and international levels.</p>\n<p>“Kent’s knowledge and practice in the helping profession and higher education have enabled him to gain perspectives and experiences to develop him into a resourceful professional regarding so many issues that many seek his advice,” says nominator Leo M. Lachut, director of academic support at UConn. “He has an amazing ability to connect and engage with students of all ages and demonstrated his commitment and passion for supporting first-generation students.”  </p>\n<p>Among his many accolades, Butler has been recognized by UCF as a Faculty Fellow for Inclusive Excellence, a Tennessee Association for Multicultural Counseling and Development Appreciation Award winner, and an American Counseling Association Fellow.</p>\n<p>He is also a fellow with the National Association of Diversity Officers in Higher Education. Known as an accessible, engaged faculty member, he has also demonstrated his leadership in two large counseling professional organizations, including having been elected the 70th president, and second-ever African American male to serve, of the American Counseling Association.</p>\n<p>You can catch up with Dr. Butler weekly on his podcast, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKZwSu_zPMXx7NdKFW4683A\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Matters of Diversity with Dr. B</a>, hosted on YouTube.</p>','2021-03-17','2021-03-24','https://diversity.ucf.edu/about/the-diversity-team/','UCF Communications',NULL,'today@ucf.edu','UCF Communications','Publish',165),(3276,'Discount for UCF Celebrates the Arts with UCF ID','discount-for-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-with-ucf-id','<p><a href=\"https://arts.cah.ucf.edu/celebrates/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Celebrates the Arts</a><span> </span>will return to showcase creativity and collaboration at Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts April 2–10. The annual event brings UCF musicians, theatre practitioners, and visual artists from the UCF campus to the downtown Orlando community in an array of offerings including jazz, dance, musical theatre, opera, symphony, bands, visual arts, talks, choirs, family events, and more.</p>\n<p>This year, events will be held in-person and virtually. Although the festival will look a little different this year, the heart of the event remains the same: the arts are built on community. And that means we need the UCF community to show up and support our students. All UCF students, faculty and staff are eligible for a discount on tickets by using code <span><strong>UCFCTA2021</strong> when purchasing through the Dr. Phillips Center box office.</span></p>\n<p><span>Read more about UCF Celebrates the Arts 2021 in this <a href=\"../../news/lineup-announced-for-ucf-celebrates-the-arts-2021/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Today story</a> or at <a href=\"https://arts.cah.ucf.edu/celebrates/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">arts.ucf.edu/celebrates</a>.</span></p>','2021-03-19','2021-04-09','https://arts.cah.ucf.edu/celebrates/','Bridget Parry','(407) 823-1500','boxoffice@ucf.edu','Heather Gibson','Publish',56),(3277,'Peace Corps/ AmeriCorps Informational Session and Application Workshop','peace-corps-americorps-informational-session','<p>Want to learn more about Peace Corps or AmeriCorps? Join PC recruiter McKayla Raines and AC recruiter Meca Smith for an informational session about each of these long-term volunteer opportunities and their benefits. This Zoom event takes place March 26 at 1 p.m. </p>','2021-03-22','2021-03-26','https://ucf.zoom.us/meeting/register/tJEkduGqqjooHNzuQkpnlZ46LBVYS7EmsYX-','McKayla Raines','(407) 823-4397','peacecorps@ucf.edu','McKayla Raines','Publish',298),(3278,'UCF Alumni Sponsored Scholarships for Students Deadline Extended to March 28','ucf-alumni-sponsored-scholarships-for-students-deadline-extended-to-march-28','<p>Each year UCF Alumni Engagement and Annual Giving awards scholarships to UCF students demonstrating strong academic ability and significant extracurricular and community involvement. UCF Alumni Engagement and Annual Giving is pleased to again offer more than a dozen scholarship opportunities for the 2021-2022 academic year. <strong>Applications,</strong> <strong>which are due midnight Sunday, March 28, are available on <a href=\"https://ucf.academicworks.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">A2O: Access to Opportunities</a></strong>. Students are encouraged to apply for as many scholarships for which they are eligible. <span>Late, incomplete or paper applications will not be considered.</span></p>\n<p><strong>How to apply through A2O:   </strong>     <br>1. Log in to <a href=\"https://ucf.academicworks.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">A2O: Access to Opportunities</a><br>2. Complete the general application if this is your first time logging in. <br>3. Browse available scholarships &gt; click \"Opportunities\" and select \"Ours\" then search for the specific scholarship you are looking for.<br>4. Complete and submit application(s) and all required supporting documents.<br><br>*No paper applications will be accepted. Scholarship applications are only available online through the A2O portal. You will only see scholarships for which you meet the basic eligibility requirements.<br><br><strong>Scholarships Available:<br></strong>- Charles N. &amp; Frances Millican Scholarship        <br>- Jack &amp; Monica Thorsen Veteran Scholarship        <br>- Phoenix Scholarship        <br>- St. Onge Family Leadership Endowed Scholarship        <br>- UCF Alumni Fellows Leadership Scholarship        <br>- UCF Alumni Legacy Scholarship        <br>- <strong>Amy G. Buchman, \'95</strong>, Memorial Endowed Scholarship        <br>- College of Business Administration Alumni Chapter Scholarship        <br>- Debbie K. Phillis Space Coast UCF Alumni Chapter Endowed Scholarship        <br>- Lee A. Dumas Memorial Endowed Scholarship        <br>- UCF Regional Alumni Chapter/Club Scholarships       <br>- Jacksonville UCF Alumni Club Scholarship (permanent resident of Duval, Clay, St. Johns or Nassau counties in Florida)        <br>- Southeast Florida Knights Scholarship (permanent resident of Dade or Broward counties in Florida)        <br>- Tampa Bay Knights Legacy Scholarship (permanent resident of the Tampa Bay Area, preference to those whose parent/grandparent/legal guardian are UCF graduates)        <br>- Chicago UCF Alumni Chapter Scholarship (preference given to a UCF student from the state of Illinois)</p>','2021-03-22','2021-03-28','https://ucf.academicworks.com/','UCF Alumni','(407) 823-2274','scholarships@ucfalumni.com','UCF Communications','Publish',166),(3279,'UCF Seeks Accreditation for the Investigations Section of University Audit','university-of-central-florida-seeks-accreditation-for-the-investigations-section-of-university-audit','<p><strong></strong></p>\n<p> <strong>NEWS RELEASE | UNIVERSITY OF CENTRAL FLORIDA</strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong><strong>University of Central Florida Seeks Accreditation for the Investigations Section of University Audit</strong></p>\n<p> <strong>ORLANDO, March 26</strong> – The Investigations Section of the University of Central Florida’s University Audit will undergo an assessment by the Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation (CFA) in an effort to attain accredited status.</p>\n<p>Accreditation is the certification by an independent reviewing authority that an entity has met specific requirements and prescribed standards. An accreditation program has long been recognized as a means for maintaining the highest standards of professionalism. A copy of the CFA’s accreditation standards are available through the commission’s website at <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.flaccreditation.org&amp;data=04%7C01%7CTina.Maier%40ucf.edu%7C5b22e6d273604eee113708d8d3d90bb2%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637492276458643078%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=S5fDZwr%2FPvkzo0Kq4RvO820uAC8GNC%2FafyHCpoMYXwI%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.flaccreditation.org</a>.</p>\n<p>On April 28, 2021, University Audit’s Investigations Section will be assessed for compliance on policies and procedures, management, operations, and practices. As part of the assessment, UCF must notify the public at least 30 days prior to the accreditation assessment.</p>\n<p>After the assessment team completes their review of the Investigations Section, it will report back to the full commission for a final decision on accreditation. Participation in the accreditation process is voluntary and, if granted, will be for a three-year period.</p>\n<p>UCF employees as well as members of the general public are invited to direct comments on University Audit towards the assessment team by writing to the following address:</p>\n<p>Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation<br> P.O. Box 1489, Tallahassee, FL 32302<br> Email: <a href=\"mailto:info@flaccreditation.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">info@flaccreditation.org</a></p>\n<p><strong><u>About the University of Central Florida’s University Audit: </u></strong></p>\n<p>The mission of UCF’s Investigations Section is to investigate allegations of fraud, waste, abuse, and other related wrongdoing. This work is performed independently, objectively and in accordance with investigation standards to determine if these allegations are substantiated. The Investigations Section is responsible for determining whether allegations fall under the Whistle-blower’s Act (Sections 112.3187 – 112.31895, Florida Statutes) and conducting whistle-blower investigations.   </p>\n<p>In addition, efforts are made to identify and recommend internal control and process improvements to reduce the risk of future fraudulent and improper activities through a combination of preventative, detective, and corrective risk mitigation activities. The Investigations Section also serves as the university’s point of contact for the design and oversight of the university’s antifraud framework, strategies, and training.</p>\n<p>University Audit serves as the university\'s internal auditor, providing internal audits and reviews, management consulting and advisory services, investigations of fraud, abuse, employee misconduct, and other wrongdoing, as well as, follow-up of audit and investigation recommendations, evaluation of the processes of risk management and governance, and coordination with external auditors and other investigative bodies.</p>\n<p><strong><u>About the Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation: </u></strong></p>\n<p>The Commission establishes standards, oversees an accreditation program, and awards accreditation to compliant Florida law enforcement agencies. The Commission strives to improve the ability of law enforcement agencies to deliver professional public safety services.</p>\n<p>The Commission is comprised of 15 volunteer members, one of which is a representative appointed by the Office of the Chief Inspector General. The Commission meets three times per year to oversee the accreditation program and to officially accredit, or reaccredit, agencies that have passed the rigorous review process.</p>\n<p></p>','2021-03-26','2021-04-28','https://www.ucf.edu/news/university-of-central-florida-seeks-accreditation-for-the-investigations-section-of-university-audit/','Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation',NULL,'info@flaccreditation.org','Anthony M. Moore','Publish',220),(3280,'Free Online Personal Finance Course from UCF Continuing Education','free-online-personal-finance-course-from-ucf-continuing-education','<p>UCF Continuing Education’s self-paced, online <em><a href=\"https://www.ed2go.com/ucf/online-courses/personal-finance-self-paced-free/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Personal Finance</a></em> course is available at no cost for those who register by April 30. The special offer is designed to help develop and strengthen financial literacy in our community, which has been challenged by unprecedented employment and economic hardship during the COVID-19 pandemic. The course, which requires access to a computer and email account, covers setting financial goals, making smart investments, improving financial security and other beneficial topics. Students who <a href=\"https://www.ed2go.com/ucf/online-courses/personal-finance-self-paced-free/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">register by the April 30 deadline</a> will have 90 days to complete the course at their own pace.</p>\n<p>Personal Finance is <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/Category/List\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">among more than 400</a> personal and professional development courses offered through <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Continuing Education</a>. For more information, visit <a href=\"https://www.ce.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">ce.ucf.edu</a>.</p>','2021-04-01','2021-04-30','https://www.ed2go.com/ucf/online-courses/personal-finance-self-paced-free/','Eric Michael','(321) 279-4899','eric.michael@ucf.edu','Eric Michael','Publish',299),(3281,'USPS Employee of the Month - March 2021 Annie Brown','usps-employee-of-the-month-march-2021-annie-brown','<p>Please help us congratulate our newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for March 2021 – Annie Brown</p>\n<p> Annie is a Human Resources Assistant II for Facilities &amp; Safety.  This is how her nominators describe her:</p>\n<p><em>“As a diversity champion, Annie’s commitment to diversity and inclusion is evident in her interactions; she does a magnificent job building and fostering professional relationships internally and campus-wide. She exercises a level of self-awareness that is apparent when she communicates with our very diverse staff. Customer service is where Annie shines the most. I have observed Annie “meet the employee where they are”; this is an excellent quality to have because it allows Annie to express her thoughts, feelings, and concerns for others well, all the while making employees feel appreciated and valued.\"</em></p>\n<p><em>\"Brown started her employment with Facilities &amp; Safety in January of 2016 as an office assistant. She quickly became acclimated into the culture and was eager to learn all of our processes. Over the years, Brown grow into a confident HR professional. She is always willing to jump in and support her team, provides excellent customer service to our staff members, offers up new ideas and creates processes to streamline our work, and she does it all with a smile on her face.  I am grateful to have Brown on our team and I\'m confident she will do amazing things with her future.”</em></p>\n<p><em></em><em>As USPS Employee of the Month, Annie receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore and a goody bag. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Knight Star Awards.</em></p>\n<p><em><br>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees. To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></em></p>','2021-04-05','2021-04-26','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Theresa Scipione','(407) 823-6711','theresa.scipione@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',265),(3282,'USPS Employee of the Month Nominations','usps-employee-of-the-month-nominations-1-2','<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Award recognizes exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff. We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees.</p>\n<p> All USPS Employee of the Month recipients receive a $200 cash award, two $25 gift cards, and additional recognition.  The 12 USPS Employees of the Month are also eligible for the prestigious USPS Employee of the Year award with an additional $2,500 award presented at the annual Knight Star Awards.</p>\n<p> To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>\n<p> If you have questions, please contact Theresa.Scipone@ucf.edu or 407-823-6711.</p>','2021-04-05','2021-05-27','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Theresa Scipione','(407) 823-6711','theresa.scipione@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',265),(3283,'Apply for Free Nonprofit Training','apply-for-free-nonprofit-training','<p><span>If your nonprofit agency has a health and human services mission and is located in, and serving residents of, Orange County, Florida, you may be eligible to participate in a valuable capacity building opportunity.</span></p>\n<p><span>The University of Central Florida Center for Public and Nonprofit Management has partnered with Orange County Citizens’ Commission for Children (OCCCC) to provide 15 hours of capacity building training. Fifteen agencies will be accepted for the online training program (May 21 – July 30, 2021) focused on grant writing, organization governance, financial management, and strategic planning and program evaluation. One-on-one technical assistance will be provided virtually by UCF graduate students for a total of 20 hours per participating agency. The training program, free of charge to participants, is funded entirely by OCCCC. Please note that agencies will receive training and technical assistance, but no financial assistance.</span></p>\n<p><span>Preference will be given to 501(C)(3) not-for-profit organizations with a health and human service mission that are both located and provide services in Orange County and have been in operation for a minimum of one (1) year. Additional eligibility criteria are listed on the application website.</span></p>\n<p><span>To apply for the program and to get more information visit </span><a href=\"https://ccie.ucf.edu/cpnm/capacity-building/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><span>ccie.ucf.edu/cpnm/capacity-building/</span></a><span>. Applications are due by April 30, 2021. Early application is encouraged. </span></p>','2021-04-07','2021-04-30','https://ccie.ucf.edu/cpnm/capacity-building/','Center for Public and Nonprofit Management','(407) 823-3794','cpnm@ucf.edu','UCF Center for Public and Nonprofit Management','Publish',155),(3284,'Sociology Research Showcase','sociology-research-showcase','<p><strong>Join us for our annual celebration of research excellence, The Sociology Research Showcase! </strong></p>\n<p><span>This virtual event will feature our senior-level majors and graduate students as they display the research projects they have been working on all year. Learn about social science research and discuss topics ranging from Mental Health to COVID experiences to racial inequality.</span></p>\n<p><span>The showcase will be held via Zoom on April 22nd, 2021, 4:30pm-5:30pm.</span></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"https://events.ucf.edu/event/2073980/sociology-research-showcase/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for more information and to register</a></span></p>\n<p></p>','2021-04-13','2021-04-22','https://events.ucf.edu/event/2073980/sociology-research-showcase/','Bridgett Burk','(407) 823-3744','sociology@ucf.edu','Bridgett Burk','Publish',294),(3285,'UCF Staff Advisory Council Applications Accepted April 19-30','ucf-staff-advisory-council-applications-accepted-april-19-30','<p>The University of Central Florida Staff Advisory Council, formerly known as the USPS Staff Council, is happy to announce that for the first time in Council history Administrative and Professional (A&amp;P) employees can apply to become members. <strong>The application period is open from April 19 through April 30</strong>. <a href=\"https://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2021/04/Application-3-year.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">English</a> and <a href=\"https://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2021/04/Application-Spanish-Version-Revised-3.26.21.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Spanish </a>applications are available. </p>\n<p>The Council serves to move the university forward in continuous improvement and innovative changes that positively affect all staff. Its mission is to promote a spirit of unity while building communication, trust and integrity within our diverse community.</p>\n<p>Please note that in order to be eligible to serve on the council, a prospective member must be a University of Central Florida employee occupying a full-time, benefit eligible, non-teaching position among the Administrative and Professional (A&amp;P) and University Support Personnel Services (USPS) job classifications regardless of exempt or non-exempt, grant or non-grant funded, union or non-union.</p>\n<p>Eligibility for council membership excludes temporary staff, i.e. Other Personnel Services staff (OPS); contracted staff; student workers; those eligible to be members of the faculty senate; and employees with the job title of assistant director or higher. Eligibility requires employment in good standing and for at least seven months of continuous employment at the time an election application period opens (April 19). </p>\n<p>Those interested can visit the Staff Advisory Council website to learn more about their purpose and goals and to familiarize themselves with the application process, different committees available to serve on, and various opportunities associated with the Council: <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fstaffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu%2F&amp;data=04%7C01%7CNicole.Dudenhoefer%40ucf.edu%7C75bc1ab9e45f450c704408d9003718bc%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637541058910189935%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=JqAHR6FjFB%2FTvB3hwqK3W4eHMqyVIdJWnuIIDMBV%2B%2Bs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/</a></p>','2021-04-15','2021-04-30','https://staffcouncil.admfin.ucf.edu/','N/A','(407) 823-2351','admfin@ucf.edu','UCF Communications','Publish',166),(3286,'The Ringed Planet: Cassini’s Voyage of Discovery at Saturn','the-ringed-planet-cassinis-voyage-of-discovery-at-saturn','<p><strong>Tuesday, April 27<br>Noon - 1 pm EDT</strong></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7UGxn5k8iPINC8C\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RSVP here</a></strong></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><span>Join us for lunch in space with our Launch Break! Faculty from the</span><span> </span><a href=\"https://sciences.ucf.edu/physics/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Physics Department</a><span> </span><span>and the</span><span> </span><a href=\"https://planets.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Planetary Sciences Group</a><span>, and educators from Orlando Science Center, will help us blast off into space and explore our universe. These talks are collaborative efforts with the Orlando Science Center’s Planet Pioneers traveling exhibit. This exhibit helps you learn through the planet pioneers how to survive on another planet and travel to Mars and beyond! This exhibit will be at the Orlando Science Center until May 9, 2021.</span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Zoom Virtual Talks</strong>: 30-45 minute talks followed by a moderated Q&amp;A<br><em>*Safe for all ages, but recommended for those 13 years of age and older.</em></span></p>\n<p><span><em></em></span></p>\n<p><strong>The Ringed Planet: Cassini’s Voyage of Discovery at Saturn<br></strong></p>\n<p><span><strong>Speaker: </strong>Joshua Colwell, Ph.D., Cassini Co-Investigator, Pegasus Professor and Associate Chair, <a href=\"https://sciences.ucf.edu/physics/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Physics Department</a></span></p>\n<p><strong>Talk abstract: </strong></p>\n<p>Saturn, with its spectacular system of rings, is the jewel of the solar system. The Cassini spacecraft explored the ringed planet and its moons and rings from 2004-2017 and has helped us solve many of its mysteries while generating a wealth of new questions. This presentation will follow Cassini’s journey of discovery through the Saturn system, from the bizarre mountains of Iapetus to the geysers of Enceladus, the lakes of Titan, and the dynamic and evolving rings.</p>\n<p>Cassini’s instruments have revealed Enceladus and Titan to have subsurface oceans of liquid water. Its cameras have returned stunning images of rings in turmoil, a tumbling moon, the only extraterrestrial lakes known in the solar system, a hexagon of clouds, some of the highest mountains in the solar system and much more. Its final orbits featured a daring plunge between the rings and the cloud tops where measurements revealed the planet’s interior to be more mysterious than imagined shed new light on the age and origin of the rings.</p>\n<p><strong>Speaker biography: </strong></p>\n<p>Dr. Joshua Colwell is a Pegasus Professor of Physics at the University of Central Florida. Since 2011 he has been Associate Chair of the Department of Physics, Assistant Director of the Florida Space Institute, and Director of the Center for Microgravity Research. He came to UCF in 2006 from the Laboratory for Atmospheric and Space Physics at the University of Colorado where he earned his Ph.D. in Astrophysical, Planetary, and Atmospheric Sciences.</p>\n<p>His research interests are in the origin and evolution of the solar system with a particular emphasis on planet formation, asteroids, planetary rings, comets, and interplanetary dust. He was a Co-Investigator on the international Cassini mission to Saturn that orbited the ringed planet from 2004-2017. He studies the structure and dynamics of Saturn’s rings with data from Cassini. He has led experiments that have flown on the Space Shuttle, the International Space Station, suborbital rockets, and parabolic airplane flights.</p>\n<p>For more information on this talk:<span> <a href=\"https://sciences.ucf.edu/launch-break/the-ringed-planet/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">sciences.ucf.edu/launch-break/the-ringed-planet</a></span></p>','2021-04-15','2021-04-28','https://sciences.ucf.edu/launch-break/the-ringed-planet/','UCF College of Sciences','(407) 823-0120','COSMarketing@ucf.edu','UCF College of Sciences','Publish',278),(3287,'Extreme Explorers: Challenges of Exploring our Planetary Neighbors','extreme-explorers-challenges-of-exploring-our-planetary-neighbors','<p><strong>Tuesday, May 4</strong><br><strong>Noon - 1 pm EDT</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_7UGxn5k8iPINC8C\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>RSVP Here</strong></a></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Join us for lunch in space with our Launch Break! Faculty from the<span> </span><a href=\"https://sciences.ucf.edu/physics/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Physics Department</a><span> </span>and the<span> </span><a href=\"https://planets.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Planetary Sciences Group</a>, and educators from Orlando Science Center, will help us blast off into space and explore our universe. These talks are collaborative efforts with the Orlando Science Center’s Planet Pioneers traveling exhibit. This exhibit helps you learn through the planet pioneers how to survive on another planet and travel to Mars and beyond! This exhibit will be at the Orlando Science Center until May 9, 2021.</p>\n<p><strong>Zoom Virtual Talks</strong>: 30-45 minute talks followed by a moderated Q&amp;A<br><em>*Safe for all ages, but recommended for those 13 years of age and older.</em></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Speaker:<span> </span></strong><span><strong>Adrienne Dove</strong>, Ph.D., </span><span>Assistant Professor, </span><a href=\"https://sciences.ucf.edu/physics/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><span>UCF Physics Department</span></a></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><strong>Talk Abstract: </strong></p>\n<p>No air? Low gravity. Dust everywhere!</p>\n<p>Human and robotic explorers to other planets are presented with unique challenges to landing, moving around and operating on those surfaces. This is because the Moon, Mars and asteroids are all much smaller than Earth, don’t have it’s protective atmosphere and they have very rocky, dusty surfaces.</p>\n<p>In this talk, we will discuss some of these challenges and how we can do tests and experiments to understand them. We will also discuss how we are preparing our next explorers for these extreme environments.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Speaker Biography: </strong></p>\n<p>Dr. Adrienne (Addie) Dove is a planetary scientist and Assistant Professor in the Department of Physics at the University of Central Florida (UCF). She received her B.S. in Physics from the University of Missouri in 2006, and her Ph.D. in Astrophysics and Planetary Science from the University of Colorado – Boulder in 2012.</p>\n<p>She is passionate about space and space exploration (both human and robotic) and educating people about science and exploration. Her work involves experiments in the lab, on airplanes, and in space, and she has received numerous awards from UCF and NASA for her research contributions to the science and exploration communities.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>For more information on this talk:<span> </span><a href=\"https://sciences.ucf.edu/launch-break/extreme-explorers/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">sciences.ucf.edu/launch-break/extreme-explorers/</a></p>','2021-04-15','2021-05-05','https://sciences.ucf.edu/launch-break/extreme-explorers/','UCF College of Sciences','(407) 823-0120','COSMarketing@ucf.edu','UCF College of Sciences','Publish',278),(3288,'UCF Athletics Yard Sale Set for May 8','ucf-athletics-yard-sale-set-for-may-8','<p><span>Spring is yard sale season and UCF Athletics will be holding one of its own on the Bounce House concourse. UCF Athletics will hold a yard sale in conjunction with the softball team\'s game against South Florida and the baseball team\'s game against Wichita State on Saturday, May 8.</span><br><br><span>The yard sale begins at 1 p.m. with Shareholders Society members (at $5,000 annual donations and above) having the first opportunity to peruse the offerings. Access for current season ticket holders and current UCF students will begin at 2 p.m. All others will be allowed to enter the yard sale from 3:30 – 4:30 p.m. Each of UCF\'s 16 sports programs will have items available for sale.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>Claiming a complimentary ticket is required for the event. Tickets and capacity are limited.</span><br><span> </span><br><strong><u>How to claim a complimentary Yard Sale ticket:</u></strong><br><em>Season Ticket Holders:</em><span> To claim your complimentary Yard Sale tickets, you will need to login to your UCF Athletics account and save the tickets to your phone. You can claim the same number of Yard Sale tickets as you have season tickets. </span><br><span> </span><br><em>UCF Students:<span> </span></em><span>Can enter with a valid UCF I.D. (Entry gate TBD)</span><br><span> </span><br><em>General Public:</em><span> Claim your complimentary Yard Sale ticket here and save the tickets to your phone</span><strong><span> </span><a href=\"https://am.ticketmaster.com/ucf/yardsale#/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a></strong><span>.</span><br><span> </span><br><strong><u>Need to Know:</u></strong><span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mask required</li>\n<li>No back packs or bags permitted</li>\n<li>Must have a ticket for entry</li>\n<li>Credit card purchases only</li>\n<li>Items sold as is</li>\n<li>All sales are final</li>\n<li>All prices include sales tax</li>\n<li>No haggling</li>\n<li>Tickets and capacity limited</li>\n</ul>','2021-04-26','2021-05-07','https://ucfknights.com/news/2021/4/22/general-ucf-athletics-yard-sale-set-for-may-8th.aspx','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-1000','jskiles@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Athletics','Publish',165),(3289,'Survey: Examining the Disproportionate Impact of the COVID-19 Pandemic on the Work and Productivity of University Faculty','examining-the-disproportionate-impact-of-the-covid-19-pandemic-on-the-work-and-productivity-of-university-faculty','<p>Dear Faculty Member,</p>\n<p>We are a collaborative team of research faculty from the University of South Carolina (UofSC) and the University of Central Florida (UCF) conducting a study supported by the UofSC Office of the Vice President for Research, “<em>Examining the Disproportionate Impact of the COVID-19 Pandemic on the Work and Productivity of University Faculty.</em>” In this study, we focus on understanding the scope and type of impact the pandemic has had on faculty members in terms of their research, teaching, service, practice, work-family balance, and personal mental/physical wellbeing.  We also explore faculty perceptions on potential strategies and policies that could be used to ameliorate the impact of the pandemic on their own productivity and wellbeing. <span> <br></span></p>\n<p>To participate in this research, we ask that you follow the link below and complete the anonymous survey. We anticipate the survey should take approximately 20 minutes to complete. Participating in this survey is entirely voluntary. The survey measures the ways that faculty members may have been affected by the pandemic and explores their perceptions of a variety of strategies that may be employed by universities in response to the pandemic.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions or concerns regarding this study, please contact Dr. Barbara Koons-Witt at<span> </span><a href=\"mailto:bakoons@mailbox.sc.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">bakoons@mailbox.sc.edu</a>, Dr. Tia Andersen at<span> </span><a href=\"mailto:tstevens@mailbox.sc.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">tstevens@mailbox.sc.edu</a><span>,</span><span> </span>or Dr. Catherine Kaukinen at<span> </span><a href=\"mailto:Catherine.Kaukinen@ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Catherine.Kaukinen@ucf.edu</a>.<span> </span>You may also contact the University of South Carolina’s Office of Research Compliance at (803) 777-6670 regarding your rights as a research subject.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fredcap.link%2Ffacwork&amp;data=04%7C01%7CCatherine.Kaukinen%40ucf.edu%7C34f027bfd6444916463508d908c4af6f%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637550463115537884%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=xahN9F8LdzGSGXsqoQxepy%2BMqy09kxRPOPzI4EVl310%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://redcap.link/facwork</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Thank you for your consideration to participate in this study.<span> </span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\n<p>Dr. Catherine Kaukinen</p>\n<p>Department of Criminal Justice, University of Central Florida <span> <br></span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p>Dr. Barbara Koons-Witt and Dr. Tia Andersen</p>\n<p>Department of Criminology and Criminal Justice, University of South Carolina</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>','2021-04-26','2021-07-30',NULL,'Catherine Kaukinen',NULL,'catherine.kaukinen@ucf.edu','Catherine Kaukinen','Publish',308),(3290,'SVAD 2021 Animation Premieres','svad-2021-animation-premieres','<p><strong>UCF SVAD 2021 Premiere : Character Animation BFA / Animation &amp; Visual Effects MFA<br><br>Saturday, May 8 | 7PM<br>YouTube:<span> </span><a href=\"https://youtu.be/tY464vzIY4o\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://youtu.be/tY464vzIY4o</a></strong><strong></strong></p>\n<p><strong>BFA CHARACTER ANIMATION Class of 2021 — Premieres:</strong></p>\n<p>Students in this limited-access track of the Emerging Media BFA program spent two years working in teams to create these unique animated films.</p>\n<p>Please join us for the world-wide premiere screening of two new films created by the Class of 2021 Character Animation undergraduate students at UCF.</p>\n<p><em>Faculty advisement by Jo Anne Adams, Cheryl Briggs, Darlene Hadrika, Phil Peters and Stella Sung.</em></p>\n<p><em><strong>Symfaunic</strong></em><span> </span>– A young faun challenges the harmony of her forest glade when her new taste in music clashes with her brother\'s teachings.</p>\n<p>Created by Erin Bergin, Bailee Blaylock, Shawn Felski, Wesley Gordon, Savanah Harris, Madeline Kopitnik, Alexandra Kyzer, Gabriel Lopez, Leven Parguian, Ismael Perez, Nicole Ramos, Darby Snyder, Andy Soderstrom</p>\n<p><em><strong>Forget Me Not</strong></em><span> </span>— In an attempt to preserve her legacy, a cartoon classic goes head to head with her rebooted counterpart.</p>\n<p>Created by Sydney Barta, Jayme Brown, Emily Caban, Margaret Doebling, Kellie Driscoll, Jesus Evangelista, Tania Florit, Saige Guevara, Charlene Jacomino, Hannah Jurgens, Courtney Leblanc, Greta Lundy, Camille Morales, Alison Munnis, Paula Navarro, Sabrina Vega<br><br></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>_____________________________________________________________________________________</p>\n<p><strong>MFA ANIMATION AND VISUAL EFFECTS Class of 2021 — Premieres:</strong></p>\n<p>The premieres of UCF’s Master of Fine Arts in Animation and Visual Effects thesis films from the students who have graduated in Summer 2020, Fall 2020, or Spring 2021.</p>\n<p><em><strong>2030</strong></em><span> </span>by Angela Hernandez-Carlson ’16 — A worsening problem continues to threaten the stability of our future.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Two’s Accompany</strong></em><span> </span>by Brian Phinn ‘15 — Two musical neighbors performing out of sync learn to give each other a chance to shine.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Slapper the Cat</strong></em><span> </span>by Danny McCabe ‘18 — A zany cat unleashes a hilarious wave of musical chaos when he auditions for an uptight conductor\'s orchestra!</p>','2021-04-29','2021-05-08','https://youtu.be/tY464vzIY4o','UCF School of Visual Arts and Design',NULL,'svad@ucf.edu','UCF School of Visual Arts and Design','Publish',200),(3292,'USPS Employee of the Month - April 2021- Gloria Palacio','usps-employee-of-the-month-april-2021-gloria-palacio','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for April 2021: Gloria Palacio.</p>\n<p>Gloria Palacio is an Administrative Assistant II in the Office of the President. Her nominators, Heather Simeon and Lindsey La Chiana, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>“Gloria\'s cheerful and helpful personality are an immense asset not only to our office but to the entire university. She is extremely dedicated to helping others. She is the epitome of what we want our guests to experience when they call or visit the Office of the President and/or the university for that matter. </em></p>\n<p><em>This past year has been especially challenging due to managing constant changes surrounding the pandemic and the social and political climate. We have had an inordinate number of calls and emails to our office with questions about remote learning, new COVID protocols, housing assistance, financial aid, social justice issues, and many other topics that our constituents need assistance with or someone to listen to their concerns. We have received several compliments about how Gloria has delicately handled these situations that are highly frustrating, emotional, and greatly impacting the lives of our internal and external community. When people call our office, they are always relieved to have Gloria assist them.”</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Gloria receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the 2022 UCF Knight Star Awards.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff.  We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2021-05-03','2021-05-21','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Theresa Scipione','(407) 823-6711','theresa.scipione@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',265),(3293,'Gus Malzahn, Terry Mohajir to Headline 2021 ChargeOn Tour','gus-malzahn-terry-mohajir-to-headline-2021-chargeon-tour','<p><span>UCF head football coach </span><a href=\"https://ucfknights.com/coaches.aspx?rc=4177\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Gus Malzahn</a><span>, Director of Athletics </span><a href=\"https://ucfknights.com/staff.aspx?staff=2133\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Terry Mohajir</a><span> and more Knights favorites will be hitting the road for the 2021 ChargeOn Tour.</span><br><br><span>Due to logistical challenges from COVID-19 restrictions, there will be less stops on the tour than in previous years, but we\'re excited to get back in front of Knight Nation any way that we can. We look forward to the potential of getting back on the road with more stops next summer.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>The 2021 ChargeOn Tour will begin in Ft. Lauderdale on May 12, before continuing up to the Space Coast on May 19 and then rounding out the month in Oviedo on May 27. The tour will conclude at Downtown Orlando in August at date to be determined.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>Activities at each ChargeOn Tour stop will be held from 6-8 p.m. with a social hour and autograph session from 6-7 p.m. The formal portion of the program at each event will be scheduled to begin around 7 p.m.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>The ChargeOn Tour will be celebrating the announcement of an anonymous donor who is matching all gifts made to the Keep Charging On Fund, up to $150,000. This matching gift now makes Knight Nation\'s support more crucial than ever. Help us reach our goal for our Keep Charging On Fund campaign.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>Gifts can be made during your event registration or by visiting </span><a href=\"https://www.givecampus.com/schools/UniversityofCentralFlorida/keep-charging-on/?a=3880361\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>KeepChargingOn.com</strong></a><span>.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>The ChargeOn Tour is open to Knights of all ages and is free for all to attend, but registration is required due to capacity limits.</span><br><span> </span><br><span>Dates, information, and registration links are below.</span><br><span> </span><br><strong>May 12 – Ft. Lauderdale (Oakland Park)</strong><br><span>Location: Funky Buddha Brewery (1201 NE 38th St, Oakland Park, FL 33334)</span><br><span>Notes: Capacity is limited. Food and drink specials available. </span><a href=\"https://www.ucffoundation.org/ChargeOnTour\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Register here</strong></a><span>. Parties must register entire party together in order to sit together.</span><br><span> </span><br><strong>May 19 – Space Coast (Port Canaveral)</strong><br><span>Location: Gator\'s Dockside Port Canaveral (683 Dave Nisbet Dr., Port Canaveral, FL 32920)</span><br><span>Notes: Food and Drink specials available. </span><a href=\"https://www.ucffoundation.org/ChargeOnTour\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Register here</strong></a><span>.</span><br><span> </span><br><strong>May 27 – Oviedo</strong><br><span>Location: Oviedo on the Park (299 Center Lake Ln, Oviedo, FL 32765)</span><br><span>Notes: Join us at Oviedo on the Park for Food Truck Thursday. Bring a blanket or lawn chairs. The program will take place at the outdoor Oviedo Amphitheater and Cultural Center. </span><a href=\"https://www.ucffoundation.org/ChargeOnTour\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Register here</strong></a><span>.</span><br><span> </span><br><strong>August TBD - Downtown Orlando</strong><br><span>More info to come later in the summer for the Downtown Kickoff event.</span></p>','2021-05-04','2021-05-27','https://ucfknights.com/news/2021/4/30/football-gus-malzahn-terry-mohajir-to-headline-2021-chargeon-tour.aspx','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-1000','jskiles@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Athletics','Publish',165),(3294,'Safe Zone Series: LGBTQ+ 101 & Safe Zone Advocate Training','safe-zone-series-lgbtq-101-safe-zone-advocate-training','<p>UCF Alumni, in partnership with <a data-name=\"LGBTQ+ Services\" data-type=\"url\" href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Ft.e2ma.net%2Fclick%2F3dh6bt%2F7sfu2ep%2F70pzvr&amp;data=04%7C01%7Cstephanie.st.john%40ucf.edu%7C6fd0fe215f5b43be0a4908d914984a6a%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C1%7C637563466583257865%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&amp;sdata=tdaSGD93CdIpnVBmeajqwiqfMDz8a%2F0dkWaKXGU8p8E%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">LGBTQ+ Services</a> invites you to join us for the UCF Safe Zone Series: LGBTQ+ 101 &amp; Advocates. This training will be two sessions facilitated by LGBTQ+ Services staff and students. </p>\n<p><strong>Session 1 | LGBTQ+ 101</strong><br>Thursday, June 3<br>Noon - 1:30 p.m. ET<br>Zoom<br><br>Participants will be presented with general information about individual and societal concerns related to LGBTQ+ identity. This training serves as an introduction to these issues.<br><em>Registration will close on Sunday, May 30 at midnight.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Session 2 | Advocates</strong><br>Tuesday, June 15<br>Noon - 1:30 p.m. ET<br>Zoom<br><br>This training is to further individual knowledge and understanding of LGBTQ+ issues. The training is geared toward helping attendees explore, identify, and expose cultural biases and acquire skills necessary for advocating for marginalized populations.<br><em>Registration will close on Thursday, June 10 at midnight.</em></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Register:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.ucffoundation.org/safezoneseries\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ucffoundation.org/safezoneseries</a></p>','2021-05-17','2021-06-10','https://www.ucffoundation.org/safezoneseries','UCF Alumni',NULL,'knights@ucfalumni.com','UCF Alumni','Publish',280),(3295,'Knightro\'s Summer Reading Bingo','knightros-summer-reading-bingo','<p><span>It’s summertime, and the reading is easy! The UCF Alumni Book Club encourages Knights of all ages to take part in our Summer Reading Challenges from June 1 to August 31. </span></p>\n<p><span>Block out your BINGO card by reading selections in categories such as bestsellers or beach reads and by participating in the <strong><a href=\"http://ucfalumni.com/alumnibookclub\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Alumni Book Club Facebook Group</a></strong>.<br><br>Once you complete a BINGO, submit the <strong><a href=\"http://ucfalumni.com/summerreading\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">completion form</a></strong> to be entered for a chance to win a UCF-themed prize!</span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><span>Sign up to download your bingo card: <a href=\"https://www.ucffoundation.org/summerreadingbingo\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ucffoundation.org/summerreadingbingo</a></span></p>','2021-05-17','2021-08-27','https://www.ucffoundation.org/summerreadingbingo','UCF Alumni',NULL,'knights@ucfalumni.com','UCF Alumni','Publish',280),(3296,'Little Knights Summer Reading Challenge','little-knights-summer-reading-challenge','<p><span>It’s summertime, and the reading is easy! The UCF Alumni Book Club encourages Knights of all ages to take part in our Summer Reading Challenges from June 1 to August 31. </span></p>\n<p><span>We’ve got the perfect summer activity for your young bookworms! Every time they read a story this summer, they’ll color in a Knightro on our reading tracker.<br><br>Once all the Knightros are filled out, a parent or guardian can<strong> <a href=\"http://ucfalumni.com/summerreading\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">submit their name</a> </strong>for a completion certificate!<br><br>Plus, a lucky few Little Knights will receive a prize.</span></p>\n<p><span></span></p>\n<p><span>Sign up to download a reading tracker: <a href=\"https://www.ucffoundation.org/littleknightschallenge\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ucffoundation.org/littleknightschallenge</a></span></p>','2021-05-17','2021-08-27','https://www.ucffoundation.org/littleknightschallenge','UCF Alumni',NULL,'knights@ucfalumni.com','UCF Alumni','Publish',280),(3297,'UCF Coastal \"Lunch on the Coast\" Speaker Series','ucf-coastal-lunch-on-the-coast-speaker-series','<p>One goal of <a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF Coastal</a> is to enhance public awareness about the amazing coastal resources we frequently take for granted.  We are proud to serve as a reference and resource for everyone from marine scientists to the general public, businesses and policymakers.</p>\n<p>We’re highlighting some recent research undertaken by the diverse, interdisciplinary faculty of <strong>UCF Coastal</strong> in this new <em>Lunch on the Coast</em><span> </span>speaker series. Join us to learn what it really means to live in a coastal state, with expert perspectives ranging from archaeology to coastal planning, from engineering to ecosystem and human health.  You’ll discover the full scope of issues currently facing our coasts and the resources that<span> </span><strong>UCF Coastal</strong> is bringing to bear on understanding and resolving those threats.</p>\n<p><br><em><strong><a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Learn More about the Series and RSVP Here</a></strong></em></p>\n<p>Join us online for our monthly Coastal talks.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>- <strong>Tuesday, July 13 at Noon</strong><br>  <em><strong><a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/coastal-waters-a-microbial-smorgasbord/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Coastal Waters: A Microbial Smorgasbord</a></strong><br><strong>   </strong></em><strong>Speaker: Melanie Beazley</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>- Tuesday, August 10 at Noon</strong><br>  <em><strong><a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/what-no-oysters-for-lunch/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">What! No Oysters for Lunch?</a></strong><br><strong> </strong></em><strong>  Speaker: Stacy Barber </strong></p>\n<p><em></em></p>\n<p><strong>- Tuesday, September 14</strong><br><strong>  <em><a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/disaster-du-jour-overlapping-crises-on-the-menu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Disaster Du Jour:  Overlapping Crises on the Menu</a></em></strong><br><strong>   Speaker: Claire Knox</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>- Tuesday, October 12</strong><br><strong>  <a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/whats-a-beach-picnic-without-sand/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">What’s a Beach Picnic Without Sand?</a></strong><em><br></em><strong>   Speaker: Kelly Kibler </strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\n<p><strong>- Tuesday, November 9<br>   <a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/coastal-soil-carbon-feast-or-famine/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">C</a><em><a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/coastal-soil-carbon-feast-or-famine/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">oastal Soil Carbon: Feast or Famine</a><br>   </em>Speaker: Lisa Chambers</strong></p>\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n<p><strong>- Tuesday, December 7<br>  <a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/coastal-fish-whats-on-the-menu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"> </a><em><a href=\"https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/coastal-fish-whats-on-the-menu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Coastal Fish: What’s on the Menu?</a><br></em>   Speaker: Michelle Gaither</strong></p>','2021-05-18','2021-12-07','https://coastal.ucf.edu/lunch-on-the-coast/','UCF College of Sciences','(407) 823-0120','COSMarketing@ucf.edu','UCF Coastal','Publish',278),(3298,'USPS Employee of the Month (May 2021): Nikitta Campbell','usps-employee-of-the-month-may-2021-nikitta-campbell','<p>Please join UCF Human Resources in congratulating the newest USPS Employee of the Month (EOM) for May 2021: Nikitta Campbell.</p>\n<p>Nikitta Campbell is an Administrative Assistant II in the Physics Department. Her nominators, Eduardo Mucciolo and Jessica Brooks, had this to say about her:</p>\n<p><em>“Since joining the department about three years ago, she completely changed (for the better) how we operate. Not only she engaged with and transformed several aspects of the department\'s administrative operation, but also did so with enough empathy and consideration to others that the overall environment has improved significantly. You may have noticed that the Department of Physics is constantly featured in the UCF News postings recently, and this is primarily driven by Ms. Campbell chasing and helping produce stories that recognize the success of our students and faculty.</em></p>\n<p><em>UCF and Physics is lucky to have Nikitta. She consistently goes above and beyond to help anyone in the Department, whether it be the Chair, faculty, staff, or student. Her enthusiasm does not wane, and she puts forth 110% on anything she undertakes. She manages the Department with respect and diplomacy and has the best interest of everyone in the Department at heart. She shows grit and determination, but also kindness and integrity when working through a problem. She is a ray of light each day and a true pleasure to work alongside with”.</em></p>\n<p>As USPS Employee of the Month, Nikitta receives a $200 cash award, $25 from UCF Business Services and UCF Bookstore, and a goody bag. She is now eligible for the USPS Employee of the Year $2,500 award, announced at the UCF Knight Star Awards.</p>\n<p>The University of Central Florida USPS Employee of the Month and Year Awards recognize exceptional performance of currently employed USPS staff.  We welcome your nomination and assistance in recognizing exceptional university employees.  To see eligibility criteria or to nominate someone, visit <a href=\"https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf</a></p>','2021-05-24','2021-06-11','https://hr.ucf.edu/files/USPS-Employee-of-the-Month-Nomination-Process.pdf','Theresa Scipione','(407) 823-6711','theresa.scipione@ucf.edu','Human Resources','Publish',265),(3299,'Call For Art: Hidden Artists Exhibit 2021','call-for-art-hidden-artists-exhibit-2021','<p>Call for artwork by UCF faculty and staff. Every year the Hidden Artists exhibit at the John C. Hitt Library highlights the creativity of UCF employees. While the faculty and staff serve the UCF community, the exhibit is a great opportunity to showcase the hidden talents of its employees.</p>\n<p>Artwork submitted for consideration must be original works. Painting, drawing, photography, fiber, print artworks are acceptable. 2D artworks must be hanging ready. Sculpture and 3D works are acceptable with limited dimensions of less than 20 inches in height and width; less than 10 inches depth.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The exhibit will be on display from August through September 2021.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Deadline is July 23, 2021.</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Please send name, job title and/or department, title of artwork, medium, .jpeg files of artwork for consideration to: christopher.saclolo@ucf.edu</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>For more information go to: <a href=\"https://hiddenartistsucf.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">hiddenartistsucf.com</a></p>\n<p></p>','2021-06-01','2021-07-23','https://hiddenartistsucf.com/','Christopher Saclolo','(407) 823-0703','christopher.saclolo@ucf.edu','Christopher Saclolo','Publish',198),(3300,'UCF Physical Therapy Clinic Now Open','ucf-physical-therapy-clinic-now-open','<p>The UCF Physical Therapy Clinic opened this year inside the UCF Health Center. The faculty practice provides progressive, evidence-informed physical therapy services to UCF and the local community. All care is provided by licensed physical therapists who are clinical experts and faculty members of the UCF Division of Physical Therapy with expertise in orthopedics and sports physical therapy.</p>\n<p>The clinic offers free screenings for those experiencing pain or healing from an injury. Most insurances are accepted. Call to schedule an appointment, <a href=\"tel:407823037\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">407-823-0377</a>.</p>\n<p>Learn more at <a href=\"https://healthprofessions.ucf.edu/physicaltherapy/clinic/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://healthprofessions.ucf.edu/physicaltherapy/clinic/</a>.</p>\n<p>Watch for an invitation to an Open House in the Fall.</p>','2021-06-11','2021-08-30','http://healthprofessions.ucf.edu/physicaltherapy/clinic/','UCF Physical Therapy Clinic','(407) 823-0377','ptinfo@ucf.edu','College of Health Professions and Sciences','Publish',165),(3301,'Fall 2021 VA Enrollment Certification Start','fall-2021-va-enrollment-certification-start','<p>The Veterans Academic Resource Center (VARC) will begin accepting Fall 2021 Enrollment Certifications starting Monday, June 21, 2021. </p>\n<p>New to UCF or new to using GI Benefits, click <a href=\"https://varc.sdes.ucf.edu/new-students-checklist/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> for checklist. </p>\n<p>Returning Students, click <a href=\"https://varc.sdes.ucf.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/31/2021/06/VARC-Returning-Student-Checklist.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> for checklist.</p>','2021-06-17','2021-08-31','https://varc.sdes.ucf.edu/','Joshua \"JJ\" Johnson','(407) 823-2707','Joshua.Johnson@ucf.edu','Joshua Johnson','Publish',312),(3302,'University of Central Florida Seeks Accreditation for University Audit','university-of-central-florida-seeks-accreditation-for-university-audit','<p><strong>University Announcement | UNIVERSITY OF CENTRAL FLORIDA</strong></p>\n<p><strong>University of Central Florida Seeks Accreditation for University Audit </strong></p>\n<p>The Investigations Section of the University of Central Florida’s University Audit will undergo an assessment by the Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation (CFA) in an effort to attain accredited status.</p>\n<p>Accreditation is the certification by an independent reviewing authority that an entity has met specific requirements and prescribed standards. An accreditation program has long been recognized as a means for maintaining the highest standards of professionalism. A copy of the CFA’s accreditation standards are available through the commission’s website at <a href=\"https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.flaccreditation.org&amp;data=04%7C01%7CTina.Maier%40ucf.edu%7C5b22e6d273604eee113708d8d3d90bb2%7Cbb932f15ef3842ba91fcf3c59d5dd1f1%7C0%7C0%7C637492276458643078%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=S5fDZwr%2FPvkzo0Kq4RvO820uAC8GNC%2FafyHCpoMYXwI%3D&amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">www.flaccreditation.org</a>.</p>\n<p>On July 21, 2021, University Audit’s Investigations Section will be assessed for compliance on policies and procedures, management, operations, and practices. As part of the assessment, UCF must notify the public at least 30 days prior to the accreditation assessment.</p>\n<p>After the assessment team completes their review of the Investigations Section, it will report back to the full commission for a final decision on accreditation. Participation in the accreditation process is voluntary and, if granted, will be for a three-year period.</p>\n<p>UCF employees as well as members of the general public are invited to direct comments on University Audit towards the assessment team by writing to the following address:</p>\n<p>Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation<br> P.O. Box 1489, Tallahassee, FL 32302<br> Email: <a href=\"mailto:info@flaccreditation.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">info@flaccreditation.org</a></p>\n<p><strong><u>About the University of Central Florida’s University Audit: </u></strong></p>\n<p>The mission of UCF’s Investigations Section is to investigate allegations of fraud, waste, abuse, and other related wrongdoing. This work is performed independently, objectively and in accordance with investigation standards to determine if these allegations are substantiated. The Investigations Section is responsible for determining whether allegations fall under the Whistle-blower’s Act (Sections 112.3187 – 112.31895, Florida Statutes) and conducting whistle-blower investigations.  </p>\n<p>In addition, efforts are made to identify and recommend internal control and process improvements to reduce the risk of future fraudulent and improper activities through a combination of preventative, detective, and corrective risk mitigation activities. The Investigations Section also serves as the university’s point of contact for the design and oversight of the university’s antifraud framework, strategies, and training.</p>\n<p>University Audit serves as the university\'s internal auditor, providing internal audits and reviews, management consulting and advisory services, investigations of fraud, abuse, employee misconduct, and other wrongdoing, as well as, follow-up of audit and investigation recommendations, evaluation of the processes of risk management and governance, and coordination with external auditors and other investigative bodies.</p>\n<p><strong>About the Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation: </strong></p>\n<p>The Commission establishes standards, oversees an accreditation program, and awards accreditation to compliant Florida law enforcement agencies. The Commission strives to improve the ability of law enforcement agencies to deliver professional public safety services.</p>\n<p>The Commission is comprised of 15 volunteer members, one of which is a representative appointed by the Office of the Chief Inspector General. The Commission meets three times per year to oversee the accreditation program and to officially accredit, or reaccredit, agencies that have passed the rigorous review process.</p>\n<p>###</p>\n<p><strong></strong></p>','2021-06-17','2021-07-22','http://www.flaccreditation.org','Commission for Florida Law Enforcement Accreditation',NULL,'info@flaccreditation.org','The Investigations Section of the University of Central Florida’s University Audit','Publish',220),(3303,'Collective Bargaining Session – AFSCME','collective-bargaining-session-afscme-1-2','<p>A virtual collective bargaining session is scheduled between the Board of Trustees and the <span>American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees (AFSCME) for June 28th at 4:00p.m.</span></p>\n<p><span>Zoom link:  <a href=\"https://ucf.zoom.us/j/95745121712\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.zoom.us/j/95745121712</a></span></p>','2021-06-25','2021-06-29','https://ucf.zoom.us/j/95745121712','Maureen Binder','(407) 823-0425','maureen.binder@ucf.edu','Brittny Bannister','Publish',205),(3304,'Out of the Vault 2021 Exhibition','out-of-the-vault-2021-exhibition','<p><strong><em></em></strong>The <strong><em>Out of the Vault Exhibition</em></strong> presents artworks revived from the UCF Art Gallery’s permanent collection featuring an array of artists, mediums, and styles. The exhibition is a rare opportunity to see artists such as Thomas Hart Benton, John Chamberlain, Dorothy Gillespie, Doris Leeper, and Robert Rauschenberg as well as 20th century African masks, sculptures and figurines which have been donated by several prominent arts advocates and collectors. Nearly ten years have passed since the collection has been exhibited in the UCF Art Gallery and we are excited to share this excellent collection of diverse art that has emerged from the vault for this special occasion.</p>','2021-08-26','2021-09-30','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/out-of-the-vault-2021/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3305,'2021 Faculty Exhibition','2021-faculty-exhibition','<p>The UCF Art Gallery is proud to present a dynamic exhibition of artworks by the faculty of the <a href=\"https://svad.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">UCF School of Visual Arts and Design</a>. These professional artists have received both national and international recognition for their engaging and thought-provoking works. The exhibition showcases a wide range of traditional and contemporary media and processes including ceramics, drawing, digital art, mixed media, painting, photography, printmaking, sculpture, and textiles.</p>','2021-10-21','2021-11-04','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/2021-faculty-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3306,'Fall 2021 BFA Exhibition','fall-2021-bfa-exhibition','<p>The <em><strong>Fall 2021 BFA Exhibition</strong></em>, <span>which is on display at the UCF Art Gallery located in the School of Visual Art and Design,</span> provides the opportunity for undergraduate students majoring in book arts, ceramics, drawing, experimental animation, illustration, painting, photography, printmaking, and sculpture to share their research and artistic practice.</p>','2021-11-18','2021-12-07','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/fall-2021-bfa-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3307,'Flying Horse Editions Exhibition','flying-horse-editions-exhibition','<p><em><strong>Flying Horse Editions</strong></em> is a collaborative research studio for visual artists at the University of Central Florida. A non-profit publisher of limited-edition prints, artist books, and art objects by internationally renowned artists, FHE offers unique opportunities for artists, students, and the Central Florida community. <em>Flying Horse Editions</em> offers visiting artists the opportunity to work with FHE technicians to push the boundaries of their work while providing a unique educational experience for UCF students. This exhibition will commemorate the 30th anniversary of <em>Flying Horse Editions</em> and honor its beginnings in the printmaking studio inside the UCF School of Visual Arts and Design.</p>','2022-01-13','2022-02-03','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/flying-horse-editions-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3308,'2022 MFA Exhibition','2022-mfa-exhibition','<p>The exhibition, on display at the UCF Art Gallery in the School of Visual Arts and Design, showcases the thesis work of Master of Fine Arts candidates in the Studio Art and Design MFA track at the UCF School of Visual Arts and Design.</p>','2022-02-17','2022-03-11','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/2022-mfa-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3309,'Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition I','spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-i','<p><strong><em>Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition I</em></strong><em></em>, which is on display at the UCF Art Gallery located in the School of Visual Art and Design, provides the opportunity for senior undergraduate students majoring in book arts, ceramics, drawing, illustration, painting, photography, printmaking, and sculpture to share their research and artistic practice.</p>','2022-03-24','2022-04-07','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-i/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3310,'Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition II','spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-ii','<p><strong><em>Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition II</em></strong><em></em>, which is held at at UCF Art Gallery in the School of Visual Arts and Design, provides the opportunity for senior undergraduate students majoring in experimental animation to share their research and artistic practice.</p>','2022-04-21','2022-04-28','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-ii/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3311,'Opening Reception: Out of the Vault 2021 Exhibition','opening-reception-out-of-the-vault-2021-exhibition','<p>Join us for the opening reception of the <em><strong>Out of the Vault Exhibition</strong></em> on Thursday, Aug. 26 from 5-7 p.m. The <strong><em>Out of the Vault Exhibition</em></strong> presents artworks revived from the UCF Art Gallery’s permanent collection featuring an array of artists, mediums, and styles. The exhibition is a rare opportunity to see artists such as Thomas Hart Benton, John Chamberlain, Dorothy Gillespie, Doris Leeper, and Robert Rauschenberg as well as 20th century African masks, sculptures and figurines which have been donated by several prominent arts advocates and collectors. Nearly ten years have passed since the collection has been exhibited in the UCF Art Gallery and we are excited to share this excellent collection of diverse art that has emerged from the vault for this special occasion.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Exhibition Dates:</strong> Aug. 26 - Sept. 30<br><strong>Opening Reception:</strong> Thursday, Aug. 26 from 5-7 p.m. <br><strong>Register here</strong>: <a href=\"https://bit.ly/OutOfTheVault21\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/OutOfTheVault21</a></p>\n<p>Need help registering? Contact the UCF Box Office: 407-823-1500</p>\n<p>For more information, visit <a href=\"https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">gallery.cah.ucf.edu</a></p>\n<p><strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Planning to attend all of the opening receptions this season? Register once for our new UCF Art Gallery Season Pass and you’ll have access to attend each reception without having to register each time. Also, you’ll receive a limited-edition UCF Art Gallery memento! Register here: <a href=\"https://bit.ly/GallerySeason21\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/GallerySeason21</a></p>','2021-08-26','2021-08-26','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/out-of-the-vault-2021/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3312,'Opening Reception: 2021 SVAD Faculty Exhibition','opening-reception-2021-faculty-exhibition','<p>Join us for the opening reception of the <em><strong>2021 Faculty Exhibition</strong></em> on Thursday, Oct. 21 from 5-7 p.m. The UCF Art Gallery is proud to present a dynamic exhibition of artworks by the faculty of the UCF School of Visual Arts and Design. These professional artists have received both national and international recognition for their engaging and thought-provoking works. The exhibition showcases a wide range of traditional and contemporary media and processes including ceramics, drawing, digital art, mixed media, painting, photography, printmaking, sculpture, and textiles.</p>\n<p><strong>Exhibition Dates:</strong> Oct. 21 – Nov. 4<br><strong>Opening Reception:</strong> Thursday, Oct. 21 from 5-7 p.m. <br><strong>Register here</strong>: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/Faculty2021\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/Faculty2021</a></p>\n<p>Need help registering? Contact the UCF Box Office: 407-823-1500</p>\n<p>For more information, visit <a href=\"http://gallery.cah.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">gallery.cah.ucf.edu</a></p>\n<p><strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Planning to attend all of the opening receptions this season? Register once for our new UCF Art Gallery Season Pass and you’ll have access to attend each reception without having to register each time. Also, you’ll receive a limited-edition UCF Art Gallery memento! Register here: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/GallerySeason21\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/GallerySeason21</a></p>','2021-10-21','2021-10-21','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/2021-faculty-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3313,'Opening Reception: Fall 2021 BFA Exhibition','opening-reception-fall-2021-bfa-exhibition','<p>Join the UCF Art Gallery for the opening reception of the <em><strong>Fall 2021 BFA Exhibition</strong></em> on Thursday, Nov. 18 from 5-7 p.m. The <strong><em>Fall 2021 BFA Exhibition</em></strong> provides the opportunity for undergraduate students majoring in book arts, ceramics, drawing, experimental animation, illustration, painting, photography, printmaking, and sculpture to share their research and artistic practice.</p>\n<p><strong>Exhibition Dates:</strong> Nov. 18 – Dec. 7</p>\n<p><strong>Opening Reception:</strong> Thursday, Nov. 18 from 5-7 p.m.</p>\n<p><strong>Register here</strong>: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/BFAfall2021\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/BFAfall2021<br><br></a>Need help registering? Contact the UCF Box Office: 407-823-1500<br>For more information, visit <a href=\"http://gallery.cah.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">gallery.cah.ucf.edu</a></p>\n<p><strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Planning to attend all of the opening receptions this season? Register once for our new UCF Art Gallery Season Pass and you\'ll have access to attend each reception without having to register each time. Also, you\'ll receive a limited-edition UCF Art Gallery memento! Register here: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/GallerySeason21\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/GallerySeason21</a></p>','2021-11-18','2021-11-18','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/fall-2021-bfa-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3314,'Opening Reception: Flying Horse Editions Exhibition','opening-reception-flying-horse-editions-exhibition','<p>Join the UCF Art Gallery for the opening reception of the <strong><em>Flying Horse Editions Exhibition</em></strong> on Thursday, Jan. 13 5-7 p.m. <strong><em>Flying Horse Editions</em></strong> is a collaborative research studio for visual artists at the University of Central Florida. A non-profit publisher of limited-edition prints, artist books, and art objects by internationally renowned artists, FHE offers unique opportunities for artists, students, and the Central Florida community. Flying Horse Editions offers visiting artists the opportunity to work with FHE technicians to push the boundaries of their work while providing a unique educational experience for UCF students. This exhibition will commemorate the 30th anniversary of Flying Horse Editions and honor its beginnings in the printmaking studio inside the UCF School of Visual Arts and Design. </p>\n<p><strong>Exhibition Dates:</strong> Jan. 13 – Feb. 3</p>\n<p><strong>Opening Reception:</strong> Thursday, Jan. 13 from 5-7 p.m.</p>\n<p><strong>Register here</strong>: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/FlyingHorse2021\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/FlyingHorse2021</a></p>\n<p>Need help registering? Contact the UCF Box Office: 407.823.1500</p>\n<p>For more information, visit <a href=\"http://gallery.cah.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">gallery.cah.ucf.edu</a></p>\n<p><strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Planning to attend all of the opening receptions this season? Register once for our new UCF Art Gallery Season Pass and you\'ll have access to attend each reception without having to register each time. Also, you\'ll receive a limited-edition UCF Art Gallery memento. Register here: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/GallerySeason21\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/GallerySeason21</a></p>','2022-01-13','2022-01-13','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/flying-horse-editions-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3315,'Opening Reception: 2022 MFA Exhibition','opening-reception-2022-mfa-exhibition','<p>Join the UC Art Gallery for the opening reception of the <em><strong>2022 MFA Exhibition</strong></em> on Thursday, Feb. 17 from 6-8 p.m.  The exhibition showcases the thesis work of Master of Fine Arts candidates in the Studio Art &amp; Design MFA track at the UCF School of Visual Arts and Design.</p>\n<p><strong>Exhibition Dates:</strong> Feb. 17 – March 11</p>\n<p><strong>Opening Reception:</strong> Thursday, Feb. 17 from 6-8 p.m.</p>\n<p><strong>Register here</strong>: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/MFA2022\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/MFA2022</a></p>\n<p>Need help registering? Contact the UCF Box Office: 407-823-1500</p>\n<p>For more information, visit <a href=\"http://gallery.cah.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">gallery.cah.ucf.edu</a></p>\n<p><strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Planning to attend all of the opening receptions this season? Register once for our new UCF Art Gallery Season Pass and you’ll have access to attend each reception without having to register each time. Also, you’ll receive a limited-edition UCF Art Gallery memento! Register here: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/GallerySeason21\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">bit.ly/GallerySeason21</a></p>','2022-02-17','2022-02-17','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/2022-mfa-exhibition/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3316,'UCF Libraries Awards 2021 June S. Stillman Memorial Endowed Scholarship','ucf-libraries-award-2021-june-s-stillman-memorial-endowed-scholarship','<p><span>The University of Central Florida Libraries on behalf of the Selection Committee and Director\'s Advisory Group is proud to announce that Sarah Rasmussen is the 2021– 2022 recipient of the June S. Stillman Memorial Endowed Scholarship.</span><span></span></p>\n<p><span>Rasmussen is a 3rd year Education student with a double minor in English literature and world language education. She began working as a student assistant in the Curriculum Materials Center in January 2019. Her duties include shelf reading, assisting patrons, and reading books for the online Diverse Database. She intends to graduate with her bachelor’s in Spring 2022 and wants to pursue a master’s Degree in secondary education with a language arts track.</span><span></span></p>\n<p><span>Her volunteer experience includes over 500 hours of volunteer work, including leading “Care for Kids,” which included collecting and distributing holiday ornaments and gifts and volunteering at summer camps at her local church. She is also a certified soccer referee and coach. She even received the FIAAA Sportsmanship Award which is only awarded to 10 athletes in the state of Florida annually. </span><span></span></p>\n<p><span>This is the 23rd awarding of the Stillman scholarship, which is given to a student or staff member of the UCF Libraries. June S. Stillman was one of the first two librarians hired when UCF (then Florida Technological University) opened in 1968. Her impact on students can be seen from a 25th anniversary survey of the first graduating class, a majority of whom listed her as a key figure from their student days. Stillman received her second master’s degree in English Literature from UCF while working as the Head of Reference Services at the Library. She retired in 1996 and tragically killed in 1998. Her friends and family established the June S. Stillman Memorial Endowed Scholarship in her honor. She is remembered as a consummate professional, the epitome of gentility and compassion, and a proponent of lifelong learning.              </span><span></span></p>','2021-07-01','2021-07-31',NULL,'UCF Libraries','(407) 823-2564','infolit@ucf.edu','UCF Communications','Publish',166),(3317,'Opening Reception: Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition I','opening-reception-spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-i','<p><strong><em>Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition I</em></strong> provides the opportunity for senior undergraduate students majoring in book arts, ceramics, drawing, illustration, painting, photography, printmaking, and sculpture to share their research and artistic practice.</p>\n<p><strong>Opening Reception:</strong> Thursday, March 24 from 5-7 p.m. <a href=\"https://ci.ovationtix.com/34486/production/1066899\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register Here</a><br> Need help registering? Contact the UCF Box Office: 407.823.1500</p>\n<p><em>Additional programming and virtual exhibition links will be coming soon!</em></p>\n<p><strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Planning to attend all of the opening receptions this season? Register once for our new <em><strong>UCF Art Gallery Season Pass</strong> </em>and you’ll have access to attend each reception without having to register each time. Also, you’ll receive a limited-edition UCF Art Gallery memento! <a href=\"https://ci.ovationtix.com/34486/store/packages\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register Here</a></p>','2022-03-24','2022-03-24','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-i/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3318,'Opening Reception: Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition II','opening-reception-spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-ii','<p><strong><em>Spring 2022 BFA Exhibition II</em> </strong>provides the opportunity for senior undergraduate students majoring in experimental animation to share their research and artistic practice.</p>\n<p><strong>Opening Reception:</strong> Thursday, April 21 from 5-7 p.m. <a href=\"https://ci.ovationtix.com/34486/production/1066961?performanceId=10788059\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register Here</a><br> Need help registering? Contact the UCF Box Office: 407.823.1500</p>\n<p><em>Additional programming and virtual exhibition links will be coming soon!</em></p>\n<p><strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Planning to attend all of the opening receptions this season? Register once for our new <em><strong>UCF Art Gallery Season Pass</strong> </em>and you’ll have access to attend each reception without having to register each time. Also, you’ll receive a limited-edition UCF Art Gallery memento! <a href=\"https://ci.ovationtix.com/34486/store/packages\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Register Here</a></p>','2022-04-21','2022-04-21','https://gallery.cah.ucf.edu/exhibit/spring-2022-bfa-exhibition-ii/','UCF Art Gallery',NULL,'gallery@ucf.edu','UCF Art Gallery','Publish',313),(3319,'UCF to Test Emergency Communication Tools Wednesday','ucf-to-test-emergency-communication-tools-wednesday-1','<p>UCF\'s preparations for potential emergency situations include regular tests of the communication tools that provide critical information to the UCF community.</p>\n<p><br>Several of those UCF Alert communication tools will be tested Wednesday, July 7.</p>\n<p>In preparation for Wednesday\'s testing, students and faculty and staff members are encouraged to log in to myUCF and review their UCF Alert settings to ensure that contact information (email and cell phone number and provider) is correct.</p>\n<p>The emergency communication functions that will be tested Wednesday include:<br>-Outdoor sirens, which emit a tone followed by voice instructions, will be tested at noon.<br>-The UCF website, <a href=\"http://www.ucf.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ucf.edu</a>, will be tested from noon to 1 p.m. For most of the testing time, the UCF home page will remain active and fully functional with an alert bar at the top of the page. All messages on the alert bar will be marked as tests. A portion of the web site test will involve replacing the regular home page with an entirely text-only home page that may be used during some emergencies. When that text-only page is active, users will not be able to access links typically found on the UCF home page. Although other UCF web pages will not be impacted by the test, users may want to bookmark those pages in advance.<br>-A test emergency text and email will be sent around 1 p.m. All members of the UCF community whose UCF Alert contact information is up to date and who have not opted out of receiving emergency messages should receive both. A push notification also will be sent via the UCF Mobile app to those who have opted in.<br>-Indoor sirens that emit tones followed by voice instructions will be briefly tested in more than 70 buildings starting at 3 p.m.</p>\n<p>The UCF Alert testing also will include social media. For consistent updates and information in an emergency, follow UCF and the UCF Police Department on Twitter and Facebook. These are helpful resources for the UCF community every day and become official resources for information during emergencies.</p>\n<p>For more information on the UCF Alert system, visit <a href=\"https://police.ucf.edu/ucfalert\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://police.ucf.edu/ucfalert</a>.</p>','2021-07-06','2021-07-07','https://police.ucf.edu/ucfalert','Joe Thalheimer','(407) 823-5555','policedept@ucf.edu','Department of Emergency Management','Publish',165),(3321,'UCF Libraries Launches New Library System','ucf-libraries-new-library-system-primo-benefits-and-impacts','<p>On July 13, UCF Libraries switched to <a href=\"https://ucf-flvc.primo.exlibrisgroup.com/discovery/search?vid=01FALSC_UCF:UCF\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Primo</a>, a new library system replacing the library catalog and QuickSearch.</p>\n<p>Primo is a next-generation integrated library system (ILS) that leverages cloud-based services and offers a responsive web and mobile design. Primo will improve access to materials and enhance the user experience for students, faculty, and staff. Specifically, Primo allows for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>searching across books, chapters, articles, videos, and many other document types,</li>\n<li>cross searching the library collections of all 40 Florida public universities and state colleges, and</li>\n<li>virtual browsing, to show book jackets and titles organized as they would appear on the shelf.  This feature is especially useful as more items are stored in the Automated Retrieval Center (ARC).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Migrating to Primo means that links to the old library catalog and to QuickSearch will stop working.  Links that need to be updated include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>all links to the current library catalog, including records for books, ebooks, videos, and other documents,</li>\n<li>all links to content on QuickSearch (EBSCO Discovery Service), including articles, book chapters, Research Starters, and other documents, and</li>\n<li>all links created using the QuickSearch Lite tool in Canvas.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please contact your <a href=\"https://library.ucf.edu/subject/All/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Subject Librarian</a> for assistance with updating course links, <a href=\"https://library.ucf.edu/Ask/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">chat</a> with library staff real time for an immediate response to questions, or use <a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_3aeAZRovfZLZBZ4\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Report a Problem</a> for issues with accessing electronic materials or other library resources.  </p>\n<p>Take a look at Primo! Contact <a href=\"https://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_aY5UhYLTQWy50PP\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Library Instruction</a> to schedule an introduction to Primo for your class.</p>','2021-07-12','2021-10-01','https://guides.ucf.edu/newsystem/','Penny Beile','(407) 823-5488','pbeile@ucf.edu','Penny Beile, UCF Libraries','Publish',315),(3322,'Sociology Summer Research Showcase','sociology-summer-research-showcase','<p>This virtual event will feature our senior-level majors as they display the research projects they have been working on in their Capstone Data Analysis course. Learn about social science research and discuss a variety of sociological research topics.</p>\n<p>The event will be held via Zoom on July 29, 10:30-11:30 a.m.</p>\n<p>Zoom Registration Link:<span> </span><a href=\"https://ucf.zoom.us/meeting/register/tJ0ofuqqqDkqHNNazj4xt-1f6WILdTHUIlDN\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://ucf.zoom.us/meeting/register/tJ0ofuqqqDkqHNNazj4xt-1f6WILdTHUIlDN</a></p>\n<p><strong><em>Note: You must register for the event in order to receive the email with the Zoom meeting link.</em></strong></p>','2021-07-13','2021-07-28','https://events.ucf.edu/event/2139419/sociology-summer-research-showcase/','Bridgett Burk','(407) 823-1198','bridgett.burk@ucf.edu','Bridgett Burk, Department of Sociology','Publish',294),(3323,'UCF Sustainability Virtual Town Hall','ucf-to-host-sustainability-virtual-town-hall','<p><span>UCF will host a virtual town hall on sustainability on July 30, 2021 from noon to 1:30 PM.</span></p>\n<p><span>Beginning in March 2021, UCF launched a year-long sustainability strategic planning process. The new plan will build upon the successes of the 2010 Climate Action Plan, and guide the university’s path of innovative leadership in sustainability. The town hall will address curriculum and research, energy and the built environment, landscape and natural resources, transportation, and waste.</span></p>\n<p><span>The event will feature a panel of leaders from across the university and a special presentation from Zhihua Qu, faculty lead for UCF\'s Resilient, Intelligent and Sustainable Energy Systems Cluster (RISES).</span></p>\n<p><strong>Participants can email questions in advance to sustainable@ucf.edu and share their vision of a sustainable future by completing the Sustainability at UCF survey</strong>: <a href=\"http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0HSbBvoPKHEHurY\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">http://ucf.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_0HSbBvoPKHEHurY</a></p>\n<p><span><strong></strong></span></p>','2021-07-13','2021-07-30','https://events.ucf.edu/event/2140713/sustainability-virtual-town-hall/','Yara Watson Colon',NULL,'yara.watson@ucf.edu','Sustainability Initiatives','Publish',203),(3324,'UCF Sports Medicine Looking for Student Volunteers for Football Season','ucf-sports-medicine-looking-for-student-volunteers-for-football-season-1','<p><span>The UCF Athletics Sports Medicine department is looking for volunteers for the upcoming football season. UCF students interested in pursuing a career in sports medicine can apply to gain valuable experience with an NCAA Division I football team. </span></p>\n<p><span>Send your resume and fall class schedule to Associate Athletic Trainer Ed Woodley at ewoodley@athletics.ucf.edu. Students who have direct experience will be to be considered first. Resumes will be accepted throughout the summer. </span></p>','2021-07-19','2021-11-07','https://ucfknights.com/sports/2019/7/18/sports-medicine.aspx','Edmeston Woodley','(407) 823-0585','ewoodley@athletics.ucf,edu','Ed Woodley','Publish',204),(3325,'UCF Performance Nutrition Looking for Student Volunteers for Football Season and Fall Semester','ucf-performance-nutrition-looking-for-student-volunteers-for-football-season-and-fall-semester','<p>The UCF Athletics Performance Nutrition department is looking for volunteers for the upcoming football season and fall semester. UCF students interested in pursuing a career in sports nutrition and/or sports performance can apply to gain valuable experience with an NCAA Division I student-athletes. </p>\n<p>Send your resume and fall class schedule to Director of Performance Nutrition Ryan Jackson at <a href=\"mailto:rjackson@athletics.ucf.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">rjackson@athletics.ucf.edu</a>. Students who have direct experience will be to be considered first. Resumes will be accepted throughout the summer. </p>','2021-07-19','2021-11-07',NULL,'Ryan Jackson','(816) 726-5716','rjackson@athletics.ucf.edu','Ed Woodley','Publish',204),(3326,'UCF Recreation and Wellness Center to Begin New Flooring Renovations','ucf-recreation-and-wellness-center-to-begin-new-flooring-renovations','<p><span>The UCF Recreation and Wellness Center will soon be undergoing some exciting changes at its main facility. <strong>Starting July 28, the RWC will begin working on brand new flooring renovations</strong> that will bring a new look, a new multi-purpose surface and significant health and cleanliness benefits to RWC patrons.<br> <br> <strong>As a result of the flooring renovations, please be aware that some areas of the RWC will be closed and access might be re-routed between July 29th and August 22nd. Furthermore, from Aug. 7 - Aug. 15, the main RWC facility will be closed for scheduled maintenance</strong>. <br> <br> “We are so excited to be upgrading and modernizing our spaces and offerings,” says Kyra Dickie, assistant director of Fitness at the RWC. “We now have the opportunity to give UCF students a state-of-the-art functional training space, a key component of contemporary recreation centers.”<br> <br> The state-of-the-art functional training space will feature a 1,000-square-foot turf area, as well as functional training equipment like what is seen at the RWC @ Downtown facility.</span></p>\n<p>There will be signage present throughout the RWC to assist with directing patrons around the facility while the renovations are being completed. The RWC website and social media channels will also be updated with information regarding access points around the facility.</p>\n<p>RWC facilities at Knight’s Plaza and UCF Downtown will be open throughout the entirety of the main facility’s renovation.</p>\n<p>The UCF Recreation and Wellness Center offers UCF students opportunities to foster healthy lifestyle choices and wellness through efficient services, comprehensive programs and high-quality facilities.</p>\n<p>Please check <a href=\"rwc.sdes.ucf.edu/facility-updates/ a\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">the RWC website </a>a<span>nd social media channels (@UCFRWC) throughout this time to stay updated on spaces available, access points to the RWC and more information regarding the main facility’s reopening.</span></p>','2021-07-22','2021-08-22','https://rwc.sdes.ucf.edu/facility-updates/','Mari Milenkovic','(407) 823-0617','mari.milenkovic@ucf.edu','Mari Milenkovic','Publish',317),(3327,'Purchase Your Tickets for UCF Football Kickoff Luncheon','purchase-your-tickets-for-ucf-football-kickoff-luncheon','<p><span>Tickets are now available for the 2021 UCF Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon, presented by KnightPass. The annual event is set for Aug. 19 on the floor of Addition Financial Arena on the UCF campus.</span><br><br><span>\"The future of college football is here at UCF, and we are looking forward to the Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon celebration,\" says UCF vice president and director of athletics Terry Mohajir.</span><span> \"This is an event you won\'t want to miss, with the start of our 2021 season now a few weeks away.\"</span><br><span> </span><br><span>University president Alexander Cartwright, new head football coach Gus Malzahn</span><span> and Mohajir are among the speakers you\'ll hear from at the luncheon—as the Knights continue planning their return to the Bounce House at full capacity beginning Sept. 2 against Boise State.</span><br><br><span>This year\'s Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon is presented by KnightPass, a UCF-branded toll sticker powered by E-PASS and provided by the Central Florida Expressway Authority.</span><br><br><span>Single tickets ($120 each) and corporate tables (10 seats/$900) are available in limited quantities. Sponsorship opportunities for the Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon also are available. All proceeds from the Countdown to Kickoff Luncheon help provide scholarships and resources for UCF student-athletes.</span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Ticket Information (purchase tickets at </strong><a href=\"https://www.ucffoundation.org/KickoffLunch\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ucffoundation.org/KickoffLunch</a>)</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Single tickets are $120</li>\n<li>Corporate tables (10 seats) are $900</li>\n<li>Sponsorship opportunities start at $1,700</li>\n<li>Fans are encouraged to purchase their seats early as this event routinely sells out</li>\n<li>Contact the UCF ChargeOn Fund office at (407) 823-2086 or <a href=\"mailto:ChargeOnFund@UCFAthletics.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">ChargeOnFund@UCFAthletics.org</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span><strong>Parking</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Complimentary parking on Aug. 19 will be available in Garage D near Addition Financial Arena</li>\n</ul>','2021-07-26','2021-08-18','https://ucfknights.com/news/2021/7/23/ucf-football-kickoff-luncheon-set-for-august-19.aspx','UCF Athletics','(407) 823-2086','mwright@athletics.ucf.edu','UCF Athletics','Publish',165),(3328,'CAPS Student Positions Application Open','caps-student-positions','<p>Counseling &amp; Psychological Services (CAPS) has opened applications for several student positions for the upcoming 2021-22 academic year. If you are interested in getting involved with CAPS and supporting the department\'s events, <span> reducing stigma around mental health, </span>gaining experience in presenting mental health information, developing your leadership skills, or expanding your social media and marketing branding abilities and have an interest, then one of these opportunities is for you. </p>\n<p><span>These student positions will help support mental health outreach this upcoming year: </span><span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Student Outreach Coordinator: One paid position, with an <strong>application deadline of Aug. 13</strong> </span></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Peer Educators: Multiple volunteer opportunities, with an <strong>application deadline of Aug. 18</strong></span></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Social Media Interns: 1-3 intern position available for Web and Commnications majors (this is for course credit), with an <strong>application deadline of Aug. 18</strong> </span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span>For more information about the positions and how to apply, visit <a href=\"https://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/student-involvement/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">caps.sdes.ucf.edu/student-involvement/</a></span></p>','2021-07-27','2021-08-13','https://caps.sdes.ucf.edu/student-involvement/','Melissa Comeau','(407) 823-2811','melissa.comeau@ucf.edu','Melissa Comeau at Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS)','Publish',162),(3329,'LEAD Scholars Academy Applications Still Open for Fall 2021','lead-scholars-academy-applications-still-open-for-fall-2021','<p>The applications for the LEAD Scholars Academy are still open for the Fall 2021 cohort.</p>\n<p>UCF’s LEAD Scholars Academy is currently seeking well-rounded and talented <strong>graduating high school seniors, who are starting the college experience this summer or fall.</strong> LEAD Scholars are engage in a selective two-year academic leadership development program for first-time-in-college students and includes academic course work, service-learning, social events, and leadership development activities.<strong> </strong>These students are committed to academic excellence and making a difference in the world around them especially at the UCF and in Central Florida with thousands of hours of community service each year. <span>For more information about each of the LEAD Scholars Academy, please visit </span><a data-ft=\'{\"tn\":\"-U\"}\' data-lynx-mode=\"async\" href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Flsa.sdes.ucf.edu%2Fprograms%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR22P5NbIHkxJw5W8gom1mKX4Z5gJRGIXZaeCenTX9DFXF8_1GN261zsA8g&amp;h=AT1cjB789WaxxGClrvViuv1_CXDAxKJOnB7JRyR-7BDKLCaj7ttpgJZXGWZH0j2BH5tS2LNJlTzHRGnSK741iJgdI1YXTW1Xg6-JgMCJIhibVrq-1odSvfNMmaoKES5JHcEhZbxQlF2INPLRr2cXTQEJ5fZNDmk9CBy560Dpte6nnFCk2c3fvQ0IdA-CxX_RO7PgQYe4DR1FAghiyghUWqg0CS812ZHL8J5DDi0Dr18arYjNu3OadIX5em6kW1vFYRcAi7QFMkK8AP2SxzCA6CwzTZuDYgUK703Kt1LaQ3lJligdqZTmgd_WBK57R9t3RO351uUBQrfaOl_dI-mCeFYdA2-X0-rBrBz6-fRtfKQStsrRnO9nWPbuiVCwzf4T5N9FUUXrCgC32TuzOlsutQq8aeOPUWT4m6yyyHNoF8on-4k0hX6rlpoEHLoY1wW_BI5j8FAq9qq1W_9yPkfGgOkmEcMmgEvfibQhDI9iYIgfltYCLSSndm9fUaL1uDMseqIylvDBp4BxhYllUmlMArkbokFUuJOBjnGHTf0b5M9PF4rKBqGaU6-iivMQpvWvjLyIEHRkhkogrkWm9ACkcc6vPlvKrhbdGjha281oKmthcsemHgGTsqA\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/programs</a><span> </span><span>or contact us at</span><span> leadscholarsacademy</span><span>@ucf.edu.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Applications are due before Aug.20 for Fall 2021 for priority consideration</strong>. Click here to apply: <a href=\"http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/lead/apply\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/lead/apply</a></p>','2021-07-29','2021-08-19','http://lsa.sdes.ucf.edu/lead','Stacey Malaret','(407) 823-2223','leadscholarsacademy@ucf/edu','Mark Allen Poisel','Publish',318),(3330,'U-LEAD Programs Applications Open','u-lead-programs-applications-open','<p>The applications for the Fall 2021 U-LEAD Programs, in the LEAD Scholars Academy, are now open.</p>\n<p>The U-LEAD Programs are single-semester programs designed for transfer and upper division students with 60+ credits, a minimum 3.0 GPA, and an interest in ser